obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (185)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=185&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `In this Act, unless the context otherwise requires,--`
  line
  line `(1) "abridged prospectus" means a memorandum containing such salient features of a prospectus as`
  line `may be specified by the Securities and Exchange Board by making regulations in this behalf;`
  line
  line `(2) "accounting standards" means the standards of accounting or any addendum thereto for`
  line `companies or class of companies referred to in section 133;`
  line
  line `(3) "alter" or "alteration" includes the making of additions, omissions and substitutions;`
  line
  line `(4) "Appellate Tribunal" means the National Company Law Appellate Tribunal constituted under`
  line `section 410;`
  line
  line `(5) "articles" means the articles of association of a company as originally framed or as altered from`
  line `time to time or applied in pursuance of any previous company law or of this Act;`
  line
  line `(6) "associate company", in relation to another company, means a company in which that other`
  line `company has a significant influence, but which is not a subsidiary company of the company having`
  line `such influence and includes a joint venture company.`
  line
  line `^1[Explanation.-- For the purpose of this clause,--`
  line
  line `(a) the expression "significant influence" means control of at least twenty per cent. of total`
  line `voting power, or control of or participation in business decisions under an agreement;`
  line
  line `(b) the expression "joint venture" means a joint arrangement whereby the parties that have joint`
  line `control of the arrangement have rights to the net assets of the arrangement;]`
  line
  line `(7) "auditing standards" means the standards of auditing or any addendum thereto for companies or`
  line `class of companies referred to in sub-section (10) of section 143;`
  line
  line `(8) "authorised capital" or "nominal capital" means such capital as is authorised by the`
  line `memorandum of a company to be the maximum amount of share capital of the company;`
  line
  line `(9) "banking company" means a banking company as defined in clause (c) of section 5 of the`
  line `Banking Regulation Act, 1949 (10 of 1949);`
  line
  line `(10) "Board of Directors" or "Board", in relation to a company, means the collective body of the`
  line `directors of the company;`
  line
  line `(11) "body corporate" or "corporation" includes a company incorporated outside India, but does`
  line `not include--`
  line
  line `(i) a co-operative society registered under any law relating to co-operative societies; and`
  line
  line `(ii) any other body corporate (not being a company as defined in this Act), which the Central`
  line `Government may, by notification, specify in this behalf;`
  line
  line `(12) "book and paper" and "book or paper" include books of account, deeds, vouchers, writings,`
  line `documents, minutes and registers maintained on paper or in electronic form;`
  line
  line `(13) "books of account" includes records maintained in respect of--`
  line
  line `(i) all sums of money received and expended by a company and matters in relation to which the`
  line `receipts and expenditure take place;`
  line
  line `(ii) all sales and purchases of goods and services by the company;`
  line
  line `(iii) the assets and liabilities of the company; and`
  line
  line `(iv) the items of cost as may be prescribed under section 148 in the case of a company which`
  line `belongs to any class of companies specified under that section;`
  line
  line `(14) "branch office", in relation to a company, means any establishment described as such by the`
  line company;
  line
  line `(15) "called-up capital" means such part of the capital, which has been called for payment;`
  line
  line `(16) "charge" means an interest or lien created on the property or assets of a company or any of its`
  line `undertakings or both as security and includes a mortgage;`
  line
  line `(17) "chartered accountant" means a chartered accountant as defined in clause (b) of sub-section`
  line `(1) of section 2 of the Chartered Accountants Act, 1949 (38 of 1949) who holds a valid certificate of`
  line `practice under sub-section (1) of section 6 of that Act;`
  line
  line `(18) "Chief Executive Officer" means an officer of a company, who has been designated as such by`
  line it;
  line
  line `(19) "Chief Financial Officer" means a person appointed as the Chief Financial Officer of a`
  line company;
  line
  line `(20) "company" means a company incorporated under this Act or under any previous company`
  line law;
  line
  line `(21) "company limited by guarantee" means a company having the liability of its members limited`
  line `by the memorandum to such amount as the members may respectively undertake to contribute to the`
  line `assets of the company in the event of its being wound up;`
  line
  line `(22) "company limited by shares" means a company having the liability of its members limited by`
  line `the memorandum to the amount, if any, unpaid on the shares respectively held by them;`
  line
  line `^2[(23) "Company Liquidator" means a person appointed by the Tribunal as the Company`
  line `Liquidator in accordance with the provisions of section 275 for the winding up of a company under`
  line `this Act;]`
  line
  line `(24) "company secretary" or "secretary" means a company secretary as defined in clause (c) of`
  line `sub-section (1) of section 2 of the Company Secretaries Act, 1980 (56 of 1980) who is appointed by a`
  line `company to perform the functions of a company secretary under this Act;`
  line
  line `(25) "company secretary in practice" means a company secretary who is deemed to be in practice`
  line `under sub-section (2) of section 2 of the Company Secretaries Act, 1980 (56 of 1980);`
  line
  line `(26) "contributory" means a person liable to contribute towards the assets of the company in the`
  line `event of its being wound up.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purposes of this clause, it is hereby clarified that a person holding fully`
  line `paid-up shares in a company shall be considered as a contributory but shall have no liabilities of a`
  line `contributory under the Act whilst retaining rights of such a contributory;`
  line
  line `(27) "control" shall include the right to appoint majority of the directors or to control the`
  line `management or policy decisions exercisable by a person or persons acting individually or in concert, directly or indirectly, including by virtue of their shareholding or management rights or shareholders`
  line `agreements or voting agreements or in any other manner;`
  line
  line `^3[(28) "Cost Accountant" means a cost accountant as defined in clause (b) of sub-section (1) of`
  line `section 2 of the Cost and Works Accountants Act, 1959 (23 of 1959) and who holds a valid certificate of`
  line `practice under sub-section (1) of section 6 of that Act;]`
  line
  line `(29) "court" means--`
  line
  line `(i) the High Court having jurisdiction in relation to the place at which the registered office of the`
  line `company concerned is situate, except to the extent to which jurisdiction has been conferred on any`
  line `district court or district courts subordinate to that High Court under sub-clause (ii);`
  line
  line `(ii) the district court, in cases where the Central Government has, by notification, empowered any`
  line `district court to exercise all or any of the jurisdictions conferred upon the High Court, within the`
  line `scope of its jurisdiction in respect of a company whose registered office is situate in the district;`
  line
  line `(iii) the Court of Session having jurisdiction to try any offence under this Act or under any`
  line `previous company law;`
  line
  line `(iv) the Special Court established under section 435;`
  line
  line `(v) any Metropolitan Magistrate or a Judicial Magistrate of the First Class having jurisdiction to`
  line `try any offence under this Act or under any previous company law;`
  line
  line `(30) "debenture" includes debenture stock, bonds or any other instrument of a company evidencing a`
  line `debt, whether constituting a charge on the assets of the company or not:`
  line
  line `^4[Provided that--`
  line
  line `(a) the instruments referred to in Chapter III-D of the Reserve Bank of India Act, 1934 (2 of 1934);`
  line and
  line
  line `(b) such other instrument, as may be prescribed by the Central Government in consultation with`
  line `the Reserve Bank of India, issued by a company,`
  line
  line `shall not be treated as debenture;]`
  line
  line `(31) "deposit" includes any receipt of money by way of deposit or loan or in any other form by a`
  line `company, but does not include such categories of amount as may be prescribed in consultation with`
  line `the Reserve Bank of India;`
  line
  line `(32) "depository" means a depository as defined in clause (e) of sub-section (1) of section 2 of the`
  line `Depositories Act, 1996 (22 of 1996);`
  line
  line `(33) "derivative" means the derivative as defined in clause (ac) of section 2 of the Securities`
  line `Contracts (Regulation) Act, 1956 (42 of 1956);`
  line
  line `(34) "director" means a director appointed to the Board of a company;`
  line
  line `(35) "dividend" includes any interim dividend;`
  line
  line `(36) "document" includes summons, notice, requisition, order, declaration, form and register,`
  line `whether issued, sent or kept in pursuance of this Act or under any other law for the time being in force`
  line `or otherwise, maintained on paper or in electronic form;`
  line
  line `(37) "employees stock option" means the option given to the directors, officers or employees of a`
  line `company or of its holding company or subsidiary company or companies, if any, which gives such`
  line `directors, officers or employees, the benefit or right to purchase, or to subscribe for, the shares of the`
  line `company at a future date at a pre-determined price;`
  line
  line `(38) "expert" includes an engineer, a valuer, a chartered accountant, a company secretary, a cost`
  line `accountant and any other person who has the power or authority to issue a certificate in pursuance of`
  line `any law for the time being in force;`
  line
  line `(39) "financial institution" includes a scheduled bank, and any other financial institution defined or`
  line `notified under the Reserve Bank of India Act, 1934 (2 of 1934);`
  line
  line `(40) "financial statement" in relation to a company, includes--`
  line
  line `(i) a balance sheet as at the end of the financial year;`
  line
  line `(ii) a profit and loss account, or in the case of a company carrying on any activity not for profit,`
  line `an income and expenditure account for the financial year;`
  line
  line `(iii) cash flow statement for the financial year;`
  line
  line `(iv) a statement of changes in equity, if applicable; and`
  line
  line `(v) any explanatory note annexed to, or forming part of, any document referred to in sub-clause`
  line `(i) to sub-clause (iv):`
  line
  line `Provided that the financial statement, with respect to One Person Company, small company and`
  line `dormant company, may not include the cash flow statement;`
  line
  line `(41) "financial year", in relation to any company or body corporate, means the period ending on the`
  line `31st day of March every year, and where it has been incorporated on or after the 1st day of January of`
  line `a year, the period ending on the 31st day of March of the following year, in respect whereof financial`
  line `statement of the company or body corporate is made up:`
  line
  line `^5[Provided that where a company or body corporate, which is a holding company or a subsidiary`
  line `or associate company of a company incorporated outside India and is required to follow a different`
  line `financial year for consolidation of its accounts outside India, the Central Government may, on an`
  line `application made by that company or body corporate in such form and manner as may be prescribed,`
  line `allow any period as its financial year, whether or not that period is a year:`
  line
  line `Provided further that any application pending before the Tribunal as on the date of`
  line `commencement of the Companies (Amendment) Act, 2019, shall be disposed of by the Tribunal in`
  line `accordance with the provisions applicable to it before such commencement;]`
  line
  line `^6[Provided also that] a company or body corporate, existing on the commencement of this Act,`
  line `shall, within a period of two years from such commencement, align its financial year as per the`
  line `provisions of this clause;`
  line
  line `(42) "foreign company" means any company or body corporate incorporated outside India which--`
  line
  line `(a) has a place of business in India whether by itself or through an agent, physically or through`
  line `electronic mode; and`
  line
  line `(b) conducts any business activity in India in any other manner;`
  line
  line `(43) "free reserves" means such reserves which, as per the latest audited balance sheet of a`
  line `company, are available for distribution as dividend:`
  line
  line `Provided that--`
  line
  line `(i) any amount representing unrealised gains, notional gains or revaluation of assets, whether`
  line `shown as a reserve or otherwise, or`
  line
  line `(ii) any change in carrying amount of an asset or of a liability recognised in equity, including`
  line `surplus in profit and loss account on measurement of the asset or the liability at fair value,`
  line
  line `shall not be treated as free reserves;`
  line
  line `(44) "Global Depository Receipt" means any instrument in the form of a depository receipt, by`
  line `whatever name called, created by a foreign depository outside India and authorised by a company`
  line `making an issue of such depository receipts;`
  line
  line `(45) "Government company" means any company in which not less than fifty-one per cent. of the`
  line `paid-up share capital is held by the Central Government, or by any State Government or Governments,`
  line `or partly by the Central Government and partly by one or more State Governments, and includes a`
  line `company which is a subsidiary company of such a Government company;`
  line
  line `(46) "holding company", in relation to one or more other companies, means a company of which`
  line `such companies are subsidiary companies;`
  line
  line `^7[Explanation.-- For the purposes of this clause, the expression "company" includes any body corporate;]`
  line
  line `(47) "independent director" means an independent director referred to in sub-section (6) of section`
  line 149;
  line
  line `(48) "Indian Depository Receipt" means any instrument in the form of a depository receipt created`
  line `by a domestic depository in India and authorised by a company incorporated outside India making an`
  line `issue of such depository receipts;`
  line
  line `^8* * * * *`
  line
  line `(50) "issued capital" means such capital as the company issues from time to time for subscription;`
  line
  line `(51) "key managerial personnel", in relation to a company, means--`
  line
  line `(i) the Chief Executive Officer or the managing director or the manager;`
  line
  line `(ii) the company secretary;`
  line
  line `(iii) the whole-time director;`
  line
  line `(iv) the Chief Financial Officer; ^9***`
  line
  line `^10[(v) such other officer, not more than one level below the directors who is in whole-time employment,`
  line `designated as key managerial personnel by the Board; and`
  line
  line `(vi) such other officer as may be prescribed;]`
  line
  line `(52) "listed company" means a company which has any of its securities listed on any recognised`
  line `stock exchange;`
  line
  line ^11
  line `[Provided that such class of companies, which have listed or intend to list such class of securities,`
  line `as may be prescribed in consultation with the Securities and Exchange Board, shall not be considered as`
  line `listed companies.]`
  line
  line `(53) "manager" means an individual who, subject to the superintendence, control and direction of`
  line `the Board of Directors, has the management of the whole, or substantially the whole, of the affairs of a`
  line `company, and includes a director or any other person occupying the position of a manager, by`
  line `whatever name called, whether under a contract of service or not;`
  line
  line `(54) "managing director" means a director who, by virtue of the articles of a company or an`
  line `agreement with the company or a resolution passed in its general meeting, or by its Board of Directors,`
  line `is entrusted with substantial powers of management of the affairs of the company and includes a`
  line `director occupying the position of managing director, by whatever name called.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purposes of this clause, the power to do administrative acts of a routine`
  line `nature when so authorised by the Board such as the power to affix the common seal of the company to`
  line `any document or to draw and endorse any cheque on the account of the company in any bank or to`
  line `draw and endorse any negotiable instrument or to sign any certificate of share or to direct registration of transfer of any share, shall not be deemed to be included within the substantial powers of`
  line management;
  line
  line `(55) "member", in relation to a company, means--`
  line
  line `(i) the subscriber to the memorandum of the company who shall be deemed to have agreed to`
  line `become member of the company, and on its registration, shall be entered as member in its register`
  line `of members;`
  line
  line `(ii) every other person who agrees in writing to become a member of the company and whose`
  line `name is entered in the register of members of the company;`
  line
  line `(iii) every person holding shares of the company and whose name is entered as a beneficial`
  line `owner in the records of a depository;`
  line
  line `(56) "memorandum" means the memorandum of association of a company as originally framed or`
  line `as altered from time to time in pursuance of any previous company law or of this Act;`
  line
  line `(57) "net worth" means the aggregate value of the paid-up share capital and all reserves created out`
  line `of the profits ^12[, securities premium account and debit or credit balance of profit and loss account,]`
  line
  line `after deducting the aggregate value of the accumulated losses, deferred expenditure and miscellaneous`
  line `expenditure not written off, as per the audited balance sheet, but does not include reserves created out`
  line `of revaluation of assets, write-back of depreciation and amalgamation;`
  line
  line `(58) "notification" means a notification published in the Official Gazette and the expression`
  line `"notify" shall be construed accordingly;`
  line
  line `(59) "officer" includes any director, manager or key managerial personnel or any person in`
  line `accordance with whose directions or instructions the Board of Directors or any one or more of the`
  line `directors is or are accustomed to act;`
  line
  line `(60) "officer who is in default", for the purpose of any provision in this Act which enacts that an`
  line `officer of the company who is in default shall be liable to any penalty or punishment by way of`
  line `imprisonment, fine or otherwise, means any of the following officers of a company, namely:--`
  line
  line `(i) whole-time director;`
  line
  line `(ii) key managerial personnel;`
  line
  line `(iii) where there is no key managerial personnel, such director or directors as specified by the`
  line `Board in this behalf and who has or have given his or their consent in writing to the Board to such`
  line `specification, or all the directors, if no director is so specified;`
  line
  line `(iv) any person who, under the immediate authority of the Board or any key managerial`
  line `personnel, is charged with any responsibility including maintenance, filing or distribution of`
  line `accounts or records, authorises, actively participates in, knowingly permits, or knowingly fails to`
  line `take active steps to prevent, any default;`
  line
  line `(v) any person in accordance with whose advice, directions or instructions the Board of`
  line `Directors of the company is accustomed to act, other than a person who gives advice to the Board`
  line `in a professional capacity;`
  line
  line `(vi) every director, in respect of a contravention of any of the provisions of this Act, who is`
  line `aware of such contravention by virtue of the receipt by him of any proceedings of the Board or`
  line `participation in such proceedings without objecting to the same, or where such contravention had`
  line `taken place with his consent or connivance;`
  line
  line `(vii) in respect of the issue or transfer of any shares of a company, the share transfer agents,`
  line `registrars and merchant bankers to the issue or transfer;`
  line
  line `(61) "Official Liquidator" means an Official Liquidator appointed under sub-section (1) of`
  line `section 59;`
  line
  line `(62) "One Person Company" means a company which has only one person as a member;`
  line
  line `(63) "ordinary or special resolution" means an ordinary resolution, or as the case may be, special`
  line `resolution referred to in section 114;`
  line
  line `(64) "paid-up share capital" or "share capital paid-up" means such aggregate amount of money`
  line `credited as paid-up as is equivalent to the amount received as paid-up in respect of shares issued and`
  line `also includes any amount credited as paid-up in respect of shares of the company, but does not include`
  line `any other amount received in respect of such shares, by whatever name called;`
  line
  line `(65) "postal ballot" means voting by post or through any electronic mode;`
  line
  line `(66) "prescribed" means prescribed by rules made under this Act;`
  line
  line `(67)"previous company law" means any of the laws specified below:--`
  line
  line `(i) Acts relating to companies in force before the Indian Companies Act, 1866 (10 of 1866);`
  line
  line `(ii) the Indian Companies Act, 1866 (10 of 1866);`
  line
  line `(iii) the Indian Companies Act, 1882 (6 of 1882);`
  line
  line `(iv) the Indian Companies Act, 1913 (7 of 1913);`
  line
  line `(v) the Registration of Transferred Companies Ordinance, 1942 (Ord. 54 of 1942);`
  line
  line `(vi) the Companies Act, 1956 (1 of 1956); and`
  line
  line `(vii) any law corresponding to any of the aforesaid Acts or the Ordinances and in force--`
  line
  line `(A) in the merged territories or in a Part B State (other than the State of Jammu and`
  line `Kashmir*), or any part thereof, before the extension thereto of the Indian Companies Act,`
  line `1913 (7 of 1913); or`
  line
  line `(B) in the State of Jammu and Kashmir*, or any part thereof, before the commencement of`
  line `the Jammu and Kashmir (Extension of Laws) Act, 1956 (62 of 1956), in so far as banking,`
  line `insurance and financial corporations are concerned, and before the commencement of the`
  line `Central Laws (Extension to Jammu and Kashmir) Act, 1968 (25 of 1968), in so far as other`
  line `corporations are concerned;`
  line
  line `(viii) the Portuguese Commercial Code, in so far as it relates to sociedades anonimas; and`
  line
  line `(ix) the Registration of Companies (Sikkim) Act, 1961 (Sikkim Act 8 of 1961);`
  line
  line `(68) "private company" means a company having a minimum paid-up share capital ^13*** as may be`
  line `prescribed, and which by its articles,--`
  line
  line `(i) restricts the right to transfer its shares;`
  line
  line `(ii) except in case of One Person Company, limits the number of its members to two hundred:`
  line
  line `Provided that where two or more persons hold one or more shares in a company jointly, they shall,`
  line `for the purposes of this clause, be treated as a single member:`
  line
  line `Provided further that--`
  line
  line `(A) persons who are in the employment of the company; and`
  line
  line `(B) persons who, having been formerly in the employment of the company, were members of`
  line `the company while in that employment and have continued to be members after the employment`
  line ceased,
  line
  line `shall not be included in the number of members; and`
  line
  line `(iii) prohibits any invitation to the public to subscribe for any securities of the company;`
  line
  line `(69) "promoter" means a person--`
  line
  line `(a) who has been named as such in a prospectus or is identified by the company in the annual`
  line `return referred to in section 92; or`
  line
  line `(b) who has control over the affairs of the company, directly or in directly whether as a share`
  line `holder, director or otherwise; or`
  line
  line `(c) in accordance with whose advice, directions or instructions the Board of Directors of the`
  line `company is accustomed to act:`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing in sub-clause (c) shall apply to a person who is acting merely in a`
  line `professional capacity;`
  line
  line `(70) "prospectus" means any document described or issued as a prospectus and includes a red`
  line `herring prospectus referred to in section 32 or shelf prospectus referred to in section 31 or any notice,`
  line `circular, advertisement or other document inviting offers from the public for the subscription or`
  line `purchase of any securities of a body corporate;`
  line
  line `(71)"public company" means a company which--`
  line
  line `(a) is not a private company; ^14[and]`
  line
  line `(b) has a minimum paid-up share capital ^15*** as may be prescribed:`
  line
  line `Provided that a company which is a subsidiary of a company, not being a private company, shall be`
  line `deemed to be public company for the purposes of this Act even where such subsidiary company`
  line `continues to be a private company in its articles ;`
  line
  line `(72) "public financial institution" means--`
  line
  line `(i) the Life Insurance Corporation of India, established under section 3 of the Life Insurance`
  line `Corporation Act, 1956 (31 of 1956);`
  line
  line `(ii) the Infrastructure Development Finance Company Limited, referred to in clause (vi) of`
  line `sub-section (1) of section 4A of the Companies Act, 1956 (1 of 1956) so repealed under section`
  line `465 of this Act;`
  line
  line `(iii) specified company referred to in the Unit Trust of India (Transfer of Undertaking and`
  line `Repeal) Act, 2002 (58 of 2002);`
  line
  line `(iv) institutions notified by the Central Government under sub-section (2) of section 4A of the`
  line `Companies Act, 1956 (1 of 1956) so repealed under section 465 of this Act;`
  line
  line `(v) such other institution as may be notified by the Central Government in consultation with the`
  line `Reserve Bank of India:`
  line
  line `Provided that no institution shall be so notified unless--`
  line
  line `(A) it has been established or constituted by or under any Central or State Act ^16[other than this`
  line `Act or the previous company law]; or`
  line
  line `(B) not less than fifty-one per cent. of the paid-up share capital is held or controlled by the`
  line `Central Government or by any State Government or Governments or partly by the Central`
  line `Government and partly by one or more State Governments;`
  line
  line `(73) "recognised stock exchange" means a recognised stock exchange as defined in clause (f) of`
  line `section 2 of the Securities Contracts (Regulation) Act, 1956 (42 of 1956);`
  line
  line `(74) "register of companies" means the register of companies maintained by the Registrar on paper`
  line `or in any electronic mode under this Act;`
  line
  line `(75) "Registrar" means a Registrar, an Additional Registrar, a Joint Registrar, a Deputy Registrar or`
  line `an Assistant Registrar, having the duty of registering companies and discharging various functions`
  line `under this Act;`
  line
  line `(76) "related party", with reference to a company, means--`
  line
  line `(i) a director or his relative;`
  line
  line `(ii) a key managerial personnel or his relative;`
  line
  line `(iii) a firm, in which a director, manager or his relative is a partner;`
  line
  line `(iv) a private company in which a director or manager ^16[or his relative] is a member or director;`
  line
  line `(v) a public company in which a director or manager is a director ^17[and holds] along with his`
  line `relatives, more than two per cent. of its paid-up share capital;`
  line
  line `(vi) any body corporate whose Board of Directors, managing director or manager is accustomed`
  line `to act in accordance with the advice, directions or instructions of a director or manager;`
  line
  line `(vii) any person on whose advice, directions or instructions a director or manager is accustomed`
  line `to act:`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing in sub-clauses (vi) and (vii) shall apply to the advice, directions or`
  line `instructions given in a professional capacity;`
  line
  line `^18[(viii) any body corporate which is--`
  line
  line `(A) a holding, subsidiary or an associate company of such company;`
  line
  line `(B) a subsidiary of a holding company to which it is also a subsidiary; or`
  line
  line `(C) an investing company or the venturer of the company.`
  line
  line `Explanation.-- For the purpose of this clause, "the investing company or the venturer of a`
  line `company" means a body corporate whose investment in the company would result in the company`
  line `becoming an associate company of the body corporate];`
  line
  line `(ix) such other person as may be prescribed;`
  line
  line `(77) "relative", with reference to any person, means any one who is related to another, if--`
  line
  line `(i) they are members of a Hindu Undivided Family;`
  line
  line `(ii) they are husband and wife; or`
  line
  line `(iii) one person is related to the other in such manner as may be prescribed;`
  line
  line `(78) "remuneration" means any money or its equivalent given or passed to any person for services`
  line `rendered by him and includes perquisites as defined under the Income-tax Act, 1961 (43 of 1961);`
  line
  line `(79) "Schedule" means a Schedule annexed to this Act;`
  line
  line `(80) "scheduled bank" means the scheduled bank as defined in clause (e) of section 2 of the`
  line `Reserve Bank of India Act, 1934 (2 of 1934);`
  line
  line `(81) "securities" means the securities as defined in clause (h) of section 2 of the Securities`
  line `Contracts (Regulation) Act, 1956 (42 of 1956);`
  line
  line `(82) "Securities and Exchange Board" means the Securities and Exchange Board of India`
  line `established under section 3 of the Securities and Exchange Board of India Act, 1992 (15 of 1992);`
  line
  line `(83) "Serious Fraud Investigation Office" means the office referred to in section 211;`
  line
  line `(84) "share" means a share in the share capital of a company and includes stock;`
  line
  line `(85) "small company" means a company, other than a public company,--`
  line
  line `(i) paid-up share capital of which does not exceed fifty lakh rupees or such higher amount as`
  line `may be prescribed which shall not be more than ^19[ten crore rupees]; ^20[and]`
  line
  line `(ii) turnover of which ^21[as per profit and loss account for the immediately preceding financial`
  line `year] does not exceed two crore rupees or such higher amount as may be prescribed which shall not`
  line `be more than ^25[one hundred crore rupees]:`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing in this clause shall apply to--`
  line
  line `(A) a holding company or a subsidiary company;`
  line
  line `(B) a company registered under section 8; or`
  line
  line `(C) a company or body corporate governed by any special Act;`
  line
  line `(86) "subscribed capital" means such part of the capital which is for the time being subscribed by`
  line `the members of a company;`
  line
  line `(87) "subsidiary company" or "subsidiary", in relation to any other company (that is to say the`
  line `holding company), means a company in which the holding company--`
  line
  line `(i) controls the composition of the Board of Directors; or`
  line
  line `(ii) exercises or controls more than one-half of the ^23[total voting power] either at its own or`
  line `together with one or more of its subsidiary companies:`
  line
  line `Provided that such class or classes of holding companies as may be prescribed shall not have layers`
  line `of subsidiaries beyond such numbers as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purposes of this clause,--`
  line
  line `(a) a company shall be deemed to be a subsidiary company of the holding company even if the`
  line `control referred to in sub-clause (i) or sub-clause (ii) is of another subsidiary company of the`
  line `holding company;`
  line
  line `(b) the composition of a company's Board of Directors shall be deemed to be controlled by`
  line `another company if that other company by exercise of some power exercisable by it at its discretion`
  line `can appoint or remove all or a majority of the directors;`
  line
  line `(c) the expression company includes any body corporate;`
  line
  line `(d) "layer" in relation to a holding company means its subsidiary or subsidiaries;`
  line
  line `(88) "sweat equity shares" means such equity shares as are issued by a company to its directors or`
  line `employees at a discount or for consideration, other than cash, for providing their know-how or making`
  line `available rights in the nature of intellectual property rights or value additions, by whatever name called;`
  line
  line `(89) "total voting power", in relation to any matter, means the total number of votes which may be`
  line `cast in regard to that matter on a poll at a meeting of a company if all the members thereof or their`
  line `proxies having a right to vote on that matter are present at the meeting and cast their votes;`
  line
  line `(90) "Tribunal" means the National Company Law Tribunal constituted under section 408;`
  line `^24[(91) turnover means gross amount of revenue recognised in the profit and loss account from the sale,`
  line `supply, or distribution of goods or on account of services rendered, or both, by a company during a financial`
  line year;]
  line
  line `(92) "unlimited company" means a company not having any limit on the liability of its members;`
  line
  line `(93) "voting right" means the right of a member of a company to vote in any meeting of the`
  line `company or by means of postal ballot;`
  line
  line `(94) "whole-time director" includes a director in the whole-time employment of the company;`
  line
  line `^25[(94A) "winding up" means winding up under this Act or liquidation under the Insolvency and`
  line `Bankruptcy Code, 2016 (31 of 2016), as applicable;]`
  line
  line `(95) words and expressions used and not defined in this Act but defined in the Securities Contracts`
  line `(Regulation) Act, 1956 (42 of 1956) or the Securities and Exchange Board of India Act, 1992`
  line `(15 of 1992) or the Depositories Act, 1996 (22 of 1996) shall have the meanings respectively assigned`
  line `to them in those Acts.`
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. The Explanation subs. by Act 1 of 2018, s. 2 (w.e.f. 7-5-2018).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 31 of 2016, s. 255 and the Eleventh Schedule, for clause (23) (w.e.f. 15-11-2016).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 1 of 2018, s. 2, for clause (28) (w.e.f. 9-2-2018).`
  line
  line `4. The Proviso ins. by s. 2, ibid. (w.e.f. 9-2-2018).`
  line
  line `5. The proviso subs. by Act 22 of 2019, s. 2 (w.e.f. 2-11-2018).`
  line
  line `6. Subs. by s. 2, ibid., for Provided further that (w.e.f. 2-11-2018).`
  line
  line `7. The Explanation ins. by Act 1 of 2018, s. 2 (w.e.f. 9-2-2018).`
  line
  line `8. Clause (49) omitted by s. 2, ibid. (w.e.f. 9-2-2018).`
  line
  line `9. The word and omitted by s. 2, ibid. (w.e.f. 9-2-2018).`
  line
  line `10. Subs. by s. 2, ibid., for sub-clause (v) (w.e.f. 9-2-2018).`
  line
  line `11. The Proviso ins. by Act 29 of 2020, s. 2 (w.e.f. 22-1-2021).`
  line
  line `12. Subs. by Act 1 of 2018, s. 2, for and securities premium account (w.e.f. 9-2-2018).`
  line
  line `13. The words of one lakh rupees or such higher paid-up share capital omitted by Act 21 of 2015, s. 2 (w.e.f. 29-5-2015).`
  line
  line `14. Ins. by Act 1 of 2018, s. 2 (w.e.f. 9-2-2018).`
  line
  line `15. The words of five lakh rupees or such higher paid-up capital, omitted by Act 21 of 2015, s. 2 (w.e.f. 29-5-2015).`
  line
  line `16. Ins. by S.O. 1894 (E), dated 24th July, 2014.`
  line
  line `17. Subs. by S.O. 1820 (E), dated 9th July, 2014 for or holds .`
  line
  line `18. Subs. by Act 1 of 2018, s. 2, for sub-clause (viii) (w.e.f. 9-2-2018).`
  line
  line `19. Subs. by Act 1 of 2018, s. 2, for five crore rupees (w.e.f. 9-2-2018).`
  line
  line `20. Subs. by notification No. S.O. 504(E), dated 13th February, 2015, for word or (w.e.f. 13-2-2015).`
  line
  line `21. Subs. by Act 1 of 2018, s. 2, for as per its last profit and loss account (w.e.f. 9-2-2018).`
  line
  line `22. Subs. by s. 2, ibid., for twenty crore rupees (w.e.f. 9-2-2018).`
  line
  line `23. Subs. by s. 2, ibid., for total share capital (w.e.f. 7-5-2018).`
  line
  line `24. Subs. by Act 1 of 2018, s. 2, for clause (91) (w.e.f. 9-2-2018).`
  line
  line `25. Ins. by Act 31 of 2016, s. 255 and the Eleventh Schedule (w.e.f. 15-11-2016).`
  line
  line `*. Vide notification No. S.O. 3912(E), dated 30th October, 2019, this Act is made applicable to the Union territory of Jammu`
  line `and Kashmir and the Union territory of Ladakh.`
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (186)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title `Formation of company.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=186&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `(1) A company may be formed for any lawful purpose by--`
  line
  line `(a) seven or more persons, where the company to be formed is to be a public company;`
  line
  line `(b) two or more persons, where the company to be formed is to be a private company; or`
  line
  line `(c) one person, where the company to be formed is to be One Person Company that is to say, a private company,`
  line
  line `by subscribing their names or his name to a memorandum and complying with the requirements of this Act in respect of registration:`
  line
  line `Provided that the memorandum of One Person Company shall indicate the name of the other person,with his prior written consent in the prescribed form, who shall, in the event of the subscribers death or his incapacity to contract become the member of the company and the written consent of such person shall also be filed with the Registrar at the time of incorporation of the One Person Company along with its memorandum and articles:`
  line
  line `Provided further that such other person may withdraw his consent in such manner as may be prescribed:`
  line
  line `Provided also that the member of One Person Company may at any time change the name of such other person by giving notice in such manner as may be prescribed:`
  line `Provided also that it shall be the duty of the member of One Person Company to intimate the`
  line `company the change, if any, in the name of the other person nominated by him by indicating in the memorandum or otherwise within such time and in such manner as may be prescribed, and the company shall intimate the Registrar any such change within such time and in such manner as may be prescribed:`
  line `Provided also that any such change in the name of the person shall not be deemed to be an alteration of the memorandum.`
  line
  line `(2) A company formed under sub-section (1) may be either--`
  line
  line `(a) a company limited by shares; or`
  line
  line `(b) a company limited by guarantee; or`
  line
  line `(c) an unlimited company.`
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_3_a:
  sectionId (48973)
  sectionNo 3A
  orderNo 4
  title `Members severally liable in certain cases.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 1 of 2018, s. 3 (w.e.f. 9-2-2018).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=48973&sectionno=3A&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_3_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[3A. Members severally liable in certain cases.-- If at any time the number of members of a company`
  line `is reduced, in the case of a public company, below seven, in the case of a private company, below two,`
  line `and the company carries on business for more than six months while the number of members is so`
  line `reduced, every person who is a member of the company during the time that it so carries on business after`
  line `those six months and is cognisant of the fact that it is carrying on business with less than seven members`
  line `or two members, as the case may be, shall be severally liable for the payment of the whole debts of the`
  line `company contracted during that time, and may be severally sued therefor.]`
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (187)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 5
  title Memorandum.
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 1 of 2018, s. 4, for clause (i) (w.e.f. 26-1-2018).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=187&sectionno=4&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `(1) The memorandum of a company shall state--`
  line
  line `(a) the name of the company with the last word "Limited" in the case of a public limited`
  line `company, or the last words "Private Limited" in the case of a private limited company:`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing in this clause shall apply to a company registered under section 8;`
  line
  line `(b) the State in which the registered office of the company is to be situated;`
  line
  line `(c) the objects for which the company is proposed to be incorporated and any matter considered necessary in furtherance thereof;`
  line
  line `(d) the liability of members of the company, whether limited or unlimited, and also state,--`
  line
  line `(i) in the case of a company limited by shares, that liability of its members is limited to the`
  line `amount unpaid, if any, on the shares held by them; and`
  line
  line `(ii) in the case of a company limited by guarantee, the amount up to which each member`
  line `undertakes to contribute --`
  line
  line `(A) to the assets of the company in the event of its being wound-up while he is a member`
  line `or within one year after he ceases to be a member, for payment of the debts and liabilities of`
  line `the company or of such debts and liabilities as may have been contracted before he ceases to be a member, as the case may be; and`
  line
  line `(B) to the costs, charges and expenses of winding-up and for adjustment of the rights of`
  line `the contributories among themselves;`
  line
  line `(e) in the case of a company having a share capital,--`
  line
  line `(i) the amount of share capital with which the company is to be registered and the division`
  line `thereof into shares of a fixed amount and the number of shares which the subscribers to the`
  line `memorandum agree to subscribe which shall not be less than one share; and`
  line
  line `(ii) the number of shares each subscriber to the memorandum intends to take, indicated`
  line `opposite his name;`
  line
  line `(f) in the case of One Person Company, the name of the person who, in the event of death of the`
  line `subscriber, shall become the member of the company.`
  line
  line `(2) The name stated in the memorandum shall not--`
  line
  line `(a) be identical with or resemble too nearly to the name of an existing company registered under this Act or any previous company law; or`
  line
  line `(b) be such that its use by the company--`
  line
  line `(i) will constitute an offence under any law for the time being in force; or`
  line
  line `(ii) is undesirable in the opinion of the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(3) Without prejudice to the provisions of sub-section (2), a company shall not be registered with a name which contains--`
  line
  line `(a) any word or expression which is likely to give the impression that the company is in any way connected with, or having the patronage of, the Central Government, any State Government, or any local authority, corporation or body constituted by the Central Government or any State Government under any law for the time being in force; or`
  line
  line `(b) such word or expression, as may be prescribed, unless the previous approval of the Central Government has been obtained for the use of any such word or`
  line expression.
  line
  line `(4) A person may make an application, in such form and manner and accompanied by such fee, as may be prescribed, to the Registrar for the reservation of a name set out in the application as--`
  line
  line `(a) the name of the proposed company; or`
  line
  line `(b) the name to which the company proposes to change its name.`
  line
  line `(5) ^1[(i) Upon receipt of an application under sub-section (4), the Registrar may, on the basis of information and`
  line `documents furnished along with the application, reserve the name for a period of twenty days from the date of`
  line `approval or such other period as may be prescribed:`
  line
  line `Provided that in case of an application for reservation of name or for change of its name by an existing`
  line `company, the Registrar may reserve the name for a period of sixty days from the date of approval.]`
  line
  line `(ii) Where after reservation of name under clause (i), it is found that name was applied by furnishing wrong or incorrect information, then,--`
  line
  line `(a) if the company has not been incorporated, the reserved name shall be cancelled and the person making application under sub-section (4) shall be liable to a penalty which may extend to one lakh rupees;`
  line
  line `(b) if the company has been incorporated, the Registrar may, after giving the company an`
  line `opportunity of being heard--`
  line
  line `(i) either direct the company to change its name within a period of three months, after passing`
  line `an ordinary resolution;`
  line
  line `(ii) take action for striking off the name of the company from the register of companies; or`
  line
  line `(iii) make a petition for winding up of the company.`
  line
  line `(6) The memorandum of a company shall be in respective forms specified in Tables A, B, C, D and E in Schedule I as may be applicable to such company.`
  line
  line `(7) Any provision in the memorandum or articles, in the case of a company limited by guarantee and not having a share capital, purporting to give any person a right to participate in the divisible profits of thecompany otherwise than as a member, shall be void.`
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (188)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 6
  title Articles.
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=188&sectionno=5&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `(1) The articles of a company shall contain the regulations for management of the company.`
  line
  line `(2) The articles shall also contain such matters, as may be prescribed:`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing prescribed in this sub-section shall be deemed to prevent a company from including such additional matters in its articles as may be considered necessary for its management.`
  line
  line `(3) The articles may contain provisions for entrenchment to the effect that specified provisions of the articles may be altered only if conditions or procedures as that are more restrictive than those applicable in the case of a special resolution, are met or complied with.`
  line
  line `(4) The provisions for entrenchment referred to in sub-section (3) shall only be made either on formation of a company, or by an amendment in the articles agreed to by all the members of the company in the case of a private company and by a special resolution in the case of a public company.`
  line
  line `(5) Where the articles contain provisions for entrenchment, whether made on formation or by`
  line `amendment, the company shall give notice to the Registrar of such provisions in such form and manner as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(6) The articles of a company shall be in respective forms specified in Tables, F, G, H, I and J in Schedule I as may be applicable to such company.`
  line
  line `(7) A company may adopt all or any of the regulations contained in the model articles applicable to such company.`
  line
  line `(8) In case of any company, which is registered after the commencement of this Act, in so far as the registered articles of such company do not exclude or modify the regulations contained in the model articles applicable to such company, those regulations shall, so far as applicable, be the regulations of that company in the same manner and to the extent as if they were contained in the duly registered articles of the company.`
  line
  line `(9) Nothing in this section shall apply to the articles of a company registered under any previous company law unless amended under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (189)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 7
  title `Act to override memorandum, articles, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=189&sectionno=6&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `Save as otherwise expressly provided in this`
  line Act--
  line
  line `(a) the provisions of this Act shall have effect notwithstanding anything to the contrary contained in the memorandum or articles of a company, or in any agreement executed by it, or in any resolution passed by the company in general meeting or by its Board of Directors, whether the same be registered, executed or passed, as the case may be, before or after the commencement of this Act; and`
  line
  line `(b) any provision contained in the memorandum, articles, agreement or resolution shall, to the`
  line `extent to which it is repugnant to the provisions of this Act, become or be void, as the case may be.`
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (190)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 8
  title `Incorporation of company.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 1 of 2018, s. 5, for "an affidavit" (w.e.f. 27-7-2018).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=190&sectionno=7&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `(1) There shall be filed with the Registrar within whose jurisdiction the registered office of a company is proposed to be situated, the following documents and information for registration, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the memorandum and articles of the company duly signed by all the subscribers to the`
  line `memorandum in such manner as may be prescribed;`
  line
  line `(b) a declaration in the prescribed form by an advocate, a chartered accountant, cost accountant or company secretary in practice, who is engaged in the formation of the company, and by a person named in the articles as a director, manager or secretary of the company, that all the requirements of this Act and the rules made thereunder in respect of registration and matters precedent or incidental thereto have been complied with;`
  line
  line `(c) ^1[a declaration] from each of the subscribers to the memorandum and from persons named as the first directors, if any, in the articles that he is not convicted of any offence in connection with the promotion, formation or management of any company, or that he has not been found guilty of any fraud or misfeasance or of any breach of duty to any company under this Act or any previous company law during the preceding five years and that all the documents filed with the Registrar for registration of the company contain information that is correct and complete and true to the best of his knowledge and belief;`
  line
  line `(d) the address for correspondence till its registered office is established;`
  line
  line `(e) the particulars of name, including surname or family name, residential address, nationality and such other particulars of every subscriber to the memorandum along with proof of identity, as may be prescribed, and in the case of a subscriber being a body corporate, such particulars as may be prescribed;`
  line
  line `(f) the particulars of the persons mentioned in the articles as the first directors of the company, their names, including surnames or family names, the Director Identification Number, residential address, nationality and such other particulars including proof of identity as may be prescribed; and`
  line
  line `(g) the particulars of the interests of the persons mentioned in the articles as the first directors of the company in other firms or bodies corporate along with their consent to act as directors of the company in such form and manner as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(2) The Registrar on the basis of documents and information filed under sub-section (1) shall register all the documents and information referred to in that subsection in the register and issue a certificate of incorporation in the prescribed form to the effect that the proposed company is incorporated under this Act.`
  line
  line `(3) On and from the date mentioned in the certificate of incorporation issued under sub-section (2), the Registrar shall allot to the company a corporate identity number, which shall be a distinct identity for the company and which shall also be included in the certificate.`
  line
  line `(4) The company shall maintain and preserve at its registered office copies of all documents and information as originally filed under sub-section (1) till its dissolution under this Act.`
  line
  line `(5) If any person furnishes any false or incorrect particulars of any information or suppresses any material information, of which he is aware in any of the documents filed with the Registrar in relation to the registration of a company, he shall be liable for action under section 447.`
  line
  line `(6) Without prejudice to the provisions of sub-section (5) where, at any time after the incorporation of a company, it is proved that the company has been got incorporated by furnishing any false or incorrect information or representation or by suppressing any material fact or information in any of the documents or declaration filed or made for incorporating such company, or by any fraudulent action, the promoters, the persons named as the first directors of the company and the persons making declaration under clause (b) of subsection (1) shall each be liable for action under section 447.`
  line
  line `(7) Without prejudice to the provisions of sub-section (6), where a company has been got`
  line `incorporated by furnishing any false or incorrect information or representation or by suppressing any material fact or information in any of the documents or declaration filed or made for incorporating such--`
  line
  line `company or by any fraudulent action, the Tribunal may, on an application made to it, on being satisfied that the situation so warrants,`
  line
  line `(a) pass such orders, as it may think fit, for regulation of the management of the company`
  line `including changes, if any, in its memorandum and articles, in public interest or in the interest of the company and its members and creditors; or`
  line
  line `(b) direct that liability of the members shall be unlimited; or`
  line
  line `(c) direct removal of the name of the company from the register of companies; or`
  line
  line `(d) pass an order for the winding up of the company; or`
  line
  line `(e) pass such other orders as it may deem fit:`
  line
  line `Provided that before making any order under this sub-section,--`
  line
  line `(i) the company shall be given a reasonable opportunity of being heard in the matter; and`
  line
  line `(ii) the Tribunal shall take into consideration the transactions entered into by the company,`
  line
  line `including the obligations, if any, contracted or payment of any liability.`
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (191)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 9
  title `Formation of companies with charitable objects, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=191&sectionno=8&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where it is proved to the satisfaction`
  line `of the Central Government that a person or an association of persons proposed to be registered under this`
  line `Act as a limited company--`
  line
  line `(a) has in its objects the promotion of commerce, art, science, sports, education, research, social`
  line `welfare, religion, charity, protection of environment or any such other object;`
  line
  line `(b) intends to apply its profits, if any, or other income in promoting its objects; and`
  line
  line `(c) intends to prohibit the payment of any dividend to its members,`
  line
  line `the Central Government may, by licence issued in such manner as may be prescribed, and on such`
  line `conditions as it deems fit, allow that person or association of persons to be registered as a limited`
  line `company under this section without the addition to its name of the word "Limited", or as the case may be,`
  line `the words "Private Limited", and thereupon the Registrar shall, on application, in the prescribed form,`
  line `register such person or association of persons as a company under this section.`
  line
  line `(2) The company registered under this section shall enjoy all the privileges and be subject to all the`
  line `obligations of limited companies.`
  line
  line `(3) A firm may be a member of the company registered under this section.`
  line
  line `(4) (i) A company registered under this section shall not alter the provisions of its memorandum or`
  line `articles except with the previous approval of the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(ii) A company registered under this section may convert itself into company of any other kind only`
  line `after complying with such conditions as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(5) Where it is proved to the satisfaction of the Central Government that a limited company registered`
  line `under this Act or under any previous company law has been formed with any of the objects specified in`
  line `clause (a) of sub-section (1) and with the restrictions and prohibitions as mentioned respectively in`
  line `clauses (b) and (c) of that sub-section, it may, by licence, allow the company to be registered under this`
  line `section subject to such conditions as the Central Government deems fit and to change its name by`
  line `omitting the word "Limited", or as the case may be, the words "Private Limited" from its name and`
  line `thereupon the Registrar shall, on application, in the prescribed form, register such company under this`
  line `section and all the provisions of this section shall apply to that company.`
  line
  line `(6) The Central Government may, by order, revoke the licence granted to a company registered under`
  line `this section if the company contravenes any of the requirements of this section or any of the conditions`
  line `subject to which a licence is issued or the affairs of the company are conducted fraudulently or in a`
  line `manner violative of the objects of the company or prejudicial to public interest, and without prejudice to`
  line `any other action against the company under this Act, direct the company to convert its status and change`
  line `its name to add the word" Limited" or the words "Private Limited", as the case may be, to its name and`
  line `thereupon the Registrar shall, without prejudice to any action that may be taken under sub-section (7), on`
  line `application, in the prescribed form, register the company accordingly:`
  line
  line `Provided that no such order shall be made unless the company is given a reasonable opportunity of`
  line `being heard:`
  line
  line `Provided further that a copy of every such order shall be given to the Registrar.`
  line
  line `(7) Where a licence is revoked under sub-section (6), the Central Government may, by order, if it is`
  line `satisfied that it is essential in the public interest, direct that the company be wound up under this Act or`
  line `amalgamated with another company registered under this section:`
  line
  line `Provided that no such order shall be made unless the company is given a reasonable opportunity of`
  line `being heard.`
  line
  line `(8) Where a licence is revoked under sub-section (6) and where the Central Government is satisfied`
  line `that it is essential in the public interest that the company registered under this section should be`
  line `amalgamated with another company registered under this section and having similar objects, then,`
  line `notwithstanding anything to the contrary contained in this Act, the Central Government may, by order,`
  line `provide for such amalgamation to form a single company with such constitution, properties, powers,`
  line `rights, interest, authorities and privileges and with such liabilities, duties and obligations as may be`
  line `specified in the order.`
  line
  line `(9) If on the winding up or dissolution of a company registered under this section, there remains, after`
  line `the satisfaction of its debts and liabilities, any asset, they may be transferred to another company`
  line `registered under this section and having similar objects, subject to such conditions as the Tribunal may`
  line `impose, or may be sold and proceeds thereof credited to ^1`
  line `[Insolvency and Bankruptcy Fund formed under`
  line `section 224 of the Insolvency and Bankruptcy Code, 2016 (31 of 2016)].`
  line
  line `(10) A company registered under this section shall amalgamate only with another company registered`
  line `under this section and having similar objects.`
  line
  line `(11) If a company makes any default in complying with any of the requirements laid down in this`
  line `section, the company shall, without prejudice to any other action under the provisions of this section, be`
  line `punishable with fine which shall not be less than ten lakh rupees but which may extend to one crore`
  line `rupees and the directors and every officer of the company who is in default shall be punishable ^2*** with`
  line `fine which shall not be less than twenty-five thousand rupees but which may extend to ^3`
  line `[twenty-five lakh`
  line `rupees]:`
  line
  line `Provided that when it is proved that the affairs of the company were conducted fraudulently, every`
  line `officer in default shall be liable for action under section 447.`
obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 31 of 2016, s. 255 and the Eleventh Schedule, for "the Rehabilitation and Insolvency Fund formed under section`
  line `269" (w.e.f. 15-11-2016).`
  line
  line `2. The words "with imprisonment for a term which may extend to three years or" omitted by Act 29 of 2020, s. 3 (w.e.f. 21-12-`
  line `2020).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 29 of 2020, s. 3, for "twenty-five lakh rupees, or with both" (w.e.f. 21-12-2020).`
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (192)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 10
  title `Effect of registration.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes `1. The words and a common seal omitted by Act 21 of 2015, s.3 (w.e.f. 29-5-2015).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=192&sectionno=9&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `From the date of incorporation mentioned in the certificate of`
  line `incorporation, such subscribers to the memorandum and all other persons, as may, from time to time,`
  line `become members of the company, shall be a body corporate by the name contained in the memorandum,`
  line `capable of exercising all the functions of an incorporated company under this Act and having perpetual`
  line `succession ^1*** with power to acquire, hold and dispose of property, both movable and immovable,`
  line `tangible and intangible, to contract and to sue and be sued, by the said name.`
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (193)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 11
  title `Effect of memorandum and articles.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=193&sectionno=10&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line `(1) Subject to the provisions of this Act, the`
  line `memorandum and articles shall, when registered, bind the company and the members thereof to the same extent as if they respectively had been signed by the company and by each member, and contained covenants on its and his part to observe all the provisions of the memorandum and of the articles.`
  line
  line `(2) All monies payable by any member to the company under the memorandum or articles shall be adebt due from him to the company.`
obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_10_a:
  sectionId (49492)
  sectionNo 10A
  orderNo 12
  title `Commencement of business, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 22 of 2019, s. 3 (w.e.f. 2-11-2018).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=49492&sectionno=10A&orderno=12&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_10_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[10A. Commencement of business, etc.-- (1) A company incorporated after the commencement of`
  line `the Companies (Amendment) Act, 2019 and having a share capital shall not commence any business or`
  line `exercise any borrowing powers unless--`
  line
  line `(a) a declaration is filed by a director within a period of one hundred and eighty days of the date`
  line `of incorporation of the company in such form and verified in such manner as may be prescribed, with`
  line `the Registrar that every subscriber to the memorandum has paid the value of the shares agreed to be`
  line `taken by him on the date of making of such declaration; and`
  line
  line `(b) the company has filed with the Registrar a verification of its registered office as provided in`
  line `sub-section (2) of section 12.`
  line
  line `(2) If any default is made in complying with the requirements of this section, the company shall be`
  line `liable to a penalty of fifty thousand rupees and every officer who is in default shall be liable to a penalty`
  line `of one thousand rupees for each day during which such default continues but not exceeding an amount of`
  line `one lakh rupees.`
  line
  line `(3) Where no declaration has been filed with the Registrar under clause (a) of sub-section (1) within a`
  line `period of one hundred and eighty days of the date of incorporation of the company and the Registrar has`
  line `reasonable cause to believe that the company is not carrying on any business or operations, he may,`
  line `without prejudice to the provisions of sub-section (2), initiate action for the removal of the name of the`
  line `company from the register of companies under Chapter XVIII.]`
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  sectionId (194)
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 13
  title [Omitted].
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=194&sectionno=11&orderno=13&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line `[Commencement of business, etc.] Omitted by the Companies (Amendment) Act, 2015 (21 of`
  line `2015), s. 4 (w.e.f. 29-5-2015).`
obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_12:
  sectionId (195)
  sectionNo (12)
  orderNo 14
  title `Registered office of company.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=195&sectionno=12&orderno=14&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_12_content:
  string
  line `(1) A company shall, ^1[within thirty days of its incorporation]`
  line `and at all times thereafter, have a registered office capable of receiving and acknowledging all`
  line `communications and notices as may be addressed to it.`
  line
  line `(2) The company shall furnish to the Registrar verification of its registered office within a period of`
  line `thirty days of its incorporation in such manner as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(3) Every company shall--`
  line
  line `(a) paint or affix its name, and the address of its registered office, and keep the same painted or`
  line `affixed, on the outside of every office or place in which its business is carried on, in a conspicuous`
  line `position, in legible letters, and if the characters employed therefor are not those of the language or of`
  line `one of the languages in general use in that locality, also in the characters of that language or of one of`
  line `those languages;`
  line
  line `^2[(b) have its name engraved in legible characters on its seal, if any;]`
  line
  line `(c) get its name, address of its registered office and the Corporate Identity Number along with`
  line `telephone number, fax number, if any, e-mail and website addresses, if any, printed in all its business`
  line `letters, billheads, letter papers and in all its notices and other official publications; and`
  line
  line `(d) have its name printed on hundies, promissory notes, bills of exchange and such other`
  line `documents as may be prescribed:`
  line
  line `Provided that where a company has changed its name or names during the last two years, it shall paint`
  line `or affix or print, as the case may be, along with its name, the former name or names so changed during the`
  line `last two years as required under clauses (a) and (c):`
  line
  line `Provided further that the words One Person Company shall be mentioned in brackets below the`
  line `name of such company, wherever its name is printed, affixed or engraved.`
  line
  line `(4) Notice of every change of the situation of the registered office, verified in the manner prescribed,`
  line `after the date of incorporation of the company, shall be given to the Registrar ^3[within thirty days] of the`
  line `change, who shall record the same.`
  line
  line `(5) Except on the authority of a special resolution passed by a company, the registered office of the`
  line `company shall not be changed,--`
  line
  line `(a) in the case of an existing company, outside the local limits of any city, town or village where`
  line `such office is situated at the commencement of this Act or where it may be situated later by virtue of`
  line `a special resolution passed by the company; and`
  line
  line `(b) in the case of any other company, outside the local limits of any city, town or village where`
  line `such office is first situated or where it may be situated later by virtue of a special resolution passed by`
  line `the company:`
  line
  line `Provided that no company shall change the place of its registered office from the jurisdiction of one`
  line `Registrar to the jurisdiction of another Registrar within the same State unless such change is confirmed by`
  line `the Regional Director on an application made in this behalf by the company in the prescribed manner.`
  line
  line `(6) The confirmation referred to in sub-section (5) shall be communicated within a period of thirty`
  line `days from the date of receipt of application by the Regional Director to the company and the company`
  line `shall file the confirmation with the Registrar within a period of sixty days of the date of confirmation who`
  line `shall register the same and certify the registration within a period of thirty days from the date of filing of`
  line `such confirmation.`
  line
  line `(7) The certificate referred to in sub-section (6) shall be conclusive evidence that all the requirements`
  line `of this Act with respect to change of registered office in pursuance of sub-section (5) have been complied`
  line `with and the change shall take effect from the date of the certificate.`
  line
  line `(8) If any default is made in complying with the requirements of this section, the company and every`
  line `officer who is in default shall be liable to a penalty of one thousand rupees for every day during which the`
  line `default continues but not exceeding one lakh rupees.`
  line
  line `^4[(9) If the Registrar has reasonable cause to believe that the company is not carrying on any business`
  line `or operations, he may cause a physical verification of the registered office of the company in such`
  line `manner as may be prescribed and if any default is found to be made in complying with the requirements`
  line `of sub-section (1), he may without prejudice to the provisions of sub-section (8), initiate action for the`
  line `removal of the name of the company from the register of companies under Chapter XVIII.]`
obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 1 of 2018, s. 6, for on and from the fifteenth day of its incorporation (w.e.f. 27-7-2018).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 21 of 2015, s. 5, for clause (b) (w.e.f. 29-5-2015).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 1 of 2018, s. 6, for within fifteen days (w.e.f. 27-7-2018).`
  line
  line `4. Ins. by Act 22 of 2019, s. 4 (w.e.f. 2-11-2018).`
obj_root_law_sections_13:
  sectionId (196)
  sectionNo (13)
  orderNo 15
  title `Alteration of memorandum.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=196&sectionno=13&orderno=15&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_13_content:
  string
  line `(1)Save as provided in section 61, a company may, by a special resolution and after complying with the procedure specified in this section, alter the provisions of its memorandum.`
  line
  line `(2) Any change in the name of a company shall be subject to the provisions of subsections (2) and (3) of section 4 and shall not have effect except with the approval of the Central Government in writing:`
  line
  line `Provided that no such approval shall be necessary where the only change in the name of the company is the deletion therefrom, or addition thereto, of the word "Private", consequent on the conversion of any one class of companies to another class in accordance with the provisions of this Act.`
  line
  line `(3) When any change in the name of a company is made under sub-section (2), the Registrar shall enter the new name in the register of companies in place of the old name and issue a fresh certificate of incorporation with the new name and the change in the name shall be complete and effective only on the issue of such a certificate.`
  line
  line `(4) The alteration of the memorandum relating to the place of the registered office from one State to another shall not have any effect unless it is approved by the Central Government on an application in such form and manner as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(5) The Central Government shall dispose of the application under sub-section (4) within a period of sixty days and before passing its order may satisfy itself that the alteration has the consent of the creditors, debenture-holders and other persons concerned with the company or that the sufficient provision has been made by the company either for the due discharge of all its debts and obligations or that adequate security has been provided for such discharge.`
  line
  line `(6) Save as provided in section 64, a company shall, in relation to any alteration of its memorandum, file with the Registrar--`
  line
  line `(a) the special resolution passed by the company under sub-section (1);`
  line
  line `(b) the approval of the Central Government under sub-section (2), if the alteration involves any change in the name of the company.`
  line
  line `(7) Where an alteration of the memorandum results in the transfer of the registered office of a company from one State to another, a certified copy of the order of the Central Government approving the alteration shall be filed by the company with the Registrar of each of the States within such time and in such manner as may be prescribed, who shall register the same, and the Registrar of the State where the registered office is being shifted to, shall issue a fresh certificate of incorporation indicating the alteration.`
  line
  line `(8) A company, which has raised money from public through prospectus and still has any unutilised amount out of the money so raised, shall not change its objects for which it raised the money through prospectus unless a special resolution is passed by the company and--`
  line
  line `(i) the details, as may be prescribed, in respect of such resolution shall also be published in the newspapers (one in English and one in vernacular language) which is in circulation at the place where the registered office of the company is situated and shall also be placed on the website of the company, if any, indicating therein the justification for such change;`
  line
  line `(ii) the dissenting shareholders shall be given an opportunity to exit by the promoters and`
  line `shareholders having control in accordance with regulations to be specified by the Securities and Exchange Board.`
  line
  line `(9) The Registrar shall register any alteration of the memorandum with respect to the objects of the company and certify the registration within a period of thirty days from the date of filing of the special resolution in accordance with clause (a) of sub-section (6) of this section.`
  line
  line `(10) No alteration made under this section shall have any effect until it has been registered inaccordance with the provisions of this section.`
  line
  line `(11) Any alteration of the memorandum, in the case of a company limited by guarantee and not`
  line `having a share capital, purporting to give any person a right to participate in the divisible profits of thecompany otherwise than as a member, shall be void.`
obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_14:
  sectionId (197)
  sectionNo (14)
  orderNo 16
  title `Alteration of articles.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=197&sectionno=14&orderno=16&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_14_content:
  string
  line `(1) Subject to the provisions of this Act and the conditions contained in`
  line `its memorandum, if any, a company may, by a special resolution, alter its articles including alterations`
  line `having the effect of conversion of--`
  line
  line `(a) a private company into a public company; or`
  line
  line `(b) a public company into a private company:`
  line
  line `Provided that where a company being a private company alters its articles in such a manner that they`
  line `no longer include the restrictions and limitations which are required to be included in the articles of a`
  line `private company under this Act, the company shall, as from the date of such alteration, cease to be a`
  line `private company:`
  line
  line `^1[Provided further that any alteration having the effect of conversion of a public company into a`
  line `private company shall not valid unless it its approved by an order of the Central Government on an`
  line `application made in such form and manner as may be prescribed:`
  line
  line `Provided also that any application pending before the Tribunal, as on the date of commencement of`
  line `the Companies (amendment) Act, 2019, shall be disposed of by the Tribunal in accordance with the`
  line `provisions applicable to it before such commencement.]`
  line
  line `(2) Every alteration of the articles under this section and a copy of the order of the ^2[Central`
  line `Government] approving the alteration as per sub-section (1) shall be filed with the Registrar, together`
  line `with a printed copy of the altered articles, within a period of fifteen days in such manner as may be`
  line `prescribed, who shall register the same.`
  line
  line `(3) Any alteration of the articles registered under sub-section (2) shall, subject to the provisions of`
  line `this Act, be valid as if it were originally in the articles.`
obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 22 of 2019, s. 5, for the Proviso (w.e.f. 2-11-2018).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by s. 5, ibid., for "Tribunal" (w.e.f. 2-11-2018).`
obj_root_law_sections_15:
  sectionId (198)
  sectionNo (15)
  orderNo 17
  title `Alteration of memorandum or articles to be noted in every copy.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=198&sectionno=15&orderno=17&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_15_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every alteration made in the memorandum or articles of a company shall be noted in every copy of the memorandum or articles, as the case may be.`
  line
  line `(2) If a company makes any default in complying with the provisions of sub-section (1), the company and every officer who is in default shall be liable to a penalty of one thousand rupees for every copy of the memorandum or articles issued without such alteration.`
obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_16:
  sectionId (199)
  sectionNo (16)
  orderNo 18
  title `Rectification of name of company.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_16_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=199&sectionno=16&orderno=18&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_16_content:
  string
  line `(1) If, through inadvertence or otherwise, a company on its first registration or on its registration by a new name, is registered by a name which,--`
  line
  line `(a) in the opinion of the Central Government, is identical with or too nearly resembles the name by which a company in existence had been previously registered, whether under this Act or any previous company law, it may direct the company to change its name and the company shall change its name or new name, as the case may be, within a period of three months from the issue of such direction, after adopting an ordinary resolution for the purpose;`
  line
  line `(b) on an application by a registered proprietor of a trade mark that the name is identical with or too nearly resembles to a registered trade mark of such proprietor under the Trade Marks Act, 1999, made to the Central Government within three years of incorporation or registration or change of name of the company, whether under this Act or any previous company law, in the opinion of the Central Government, is identical with or too nearly resembles to an existing trade mark, it may direct the company to change its name and the company shall change its name or new name, as the case may be, within a period of six months from the issue of such direction, after adopting an ordinary resolution`
  line `for the purpose.`
  line
  line `(2) Where a company changes its name or obtains a new name under sub-section (1), it shall within a period of fifteen days from the date of such change, give notice of the change to the Registrar along with the order of the Central Government, who shall carry out necessary changes in the certificate of incorporation and the memorandum.`
  line
  line `(3) If a company makes default in complying with any direction given under sub-section (1), the company shall be punishable with fine of one thousand rupees for every day during which the default continues and every officer who is in default shall be punishable with fine which shall not be less than five thousand rupees but which may extend to one lakh rupees.`
obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_17:
  sectionId (200)
  sectionNo (17)
  orderNo 19
  title `Copies of memorandum, articles, etc., to be given to members.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_17_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=200&sectionno=17&orderno=19&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_17_content:
  string
  line `(1) A company shall, on`
  line `being so requested by a member, send to him within seven days of the request and subject to the payment of such fees as may be prescribed, a copy of each of the following documents, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the memorandum;`
  line
  line `(b) the articles; and`
  line
  line `(c) every agreement and every resolution referred to in sub-section (1) of section 117, if and in so far as they have not been embodied in the memorandum or articles.`
  line
  line `(2) If a company makes any default in complying with the provisions of this section, the company and every officer of the company who is in default shall be liable for each default, to a penalty of one thousand rupees for each day during which such default continues or one lakh rupees, whichever is less.`
obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_18:
  sectionId (201)
  sectionNo (18)
  orderNo 20
  title `Conversion of companies already registered.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_18_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=201&sectionno=18&orderno=20&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_18_content:
  string
  line `(1) A company of any class registered under this Act may convert itself as a company of other class under this Act by alteration of memorandum and articles of the company in accordance with the provisions of this Chapter.`
  line
  line `(2) Where the conversion is required to be done under this section, the Registrar shall on an`
  line `application made by the company, after satisfying himself that the provisions of this Chapter applicable for registration of companies have been complied with, close the former registration of the company and after registering the documents referred to in sub-section (1), issue a certificate of incorporation in the same manner as its first registration.`
  line
  line `(3) The registration of a company under this section shall not affect any debts, liabilities, obligations or contracts incurred or entered into, by or on behalf of the company before conversion and such debts, liabilities, obligations and contracts may be enforced in the manner as if such registration had not been done.`
obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_19:
  sectionId (202)
  sectionNo (19)
  orderNo 21
  title `Subsidiary company not to hold shares in its holding company.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_19_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=202&sectionno=19&orderno=21&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_19_content:
  string
  line `(1) No company shall,`
  line `either by itself or through its nominees, hold any shares in its holding company and no holding company`
  line `shall allot or transfer its shares to any of its subsidiary companies and any such allotment or transfer of`
  line `shares of a company to its subsidiary company shall be void:`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing in this sub-section shall apply to a case--`
  line
  line `(a) where the subsidiary company holds such shares as the legal representative of a deceased`
  line `member of the holding company; or`
  line
  line `(b) where the subsidiary company holds such shares as a trustee; or`
  line
  line `(c) where the subsidiary company is a shareholder even before it became a subsidiary company of`
  line `the holding company:`
  line
  line `Provided further that the subsidiary company referred to in the preceding proviso shall have a right to`
  line `vote at a meeting of the holding company only in respect of the shares held by it as a legal representative`
  line `or as a trustee, as referred to in clause (a) or clause (b) of the said proviso.`
  line
  line `(2) The reference in this section to the shares of a holding company which is a company limited by`
  line `guarantee or an unlimited company, not having a share capital, shall be construed as a reference to the`
  line `interest of its members, whatever be the form of interest.`
obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_20:
  sectionId (203)
  sectionNo (20)
  orderNo 22
  title `Service of documents.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_20_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=203&sectionno=20&orderno=22&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_20_content:
  string
  line `(1) A document may be served on a company or an officer thereof by sending it to the company or the officer at the registered office of the company by registered post or by speed post or by courier service or by leaving it at its registered office or by means of such electronic or other mode as may be prescribed:`
  line
  line `Provided that where securities are held with a depository, the records of the beneficial ownership may be served by such depository on the company by means of electronic or other mode.`
  line
  line `(2) Save as provided in this Act or the rules made thereunder for filing of documents with the`
  line `Registrar in electronic mode, a document may be served on Registrar or any member by sending it to him by post or by registered post or by speed post or by courier or by delivering at his office or address, or by such electronic or other mode as may be prescribed:`
  line
  line `Provided that a member may request for delivery of any document through a particular mode, for which he shall pay such fees as may be determined by the company in its annual general meeting.`
  line
  line `Explanation.-- For the purposes of this section, the term courier means a person or agency which delivers the document and provides proof of its delivery.`
obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_21:
  sectionId (204)
  sectionNo (21)
  orderNo 23
  title `Authentication of documents, proceedings and contracts.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_21_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 1 of 2018, s. 7, for “an officer of the company” (w.e.f. 9-2-2018).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=204&sectionno=21&orderno=23&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_21_content:
  string
  line `Save as otherwise provided in this Act,`
  line
  line `(a) a document or proceeding requiring authentication by a company; or`
  line
  line `(b) contracts made by or on behalf of a company,`
  line
  line `may be signed by any key managerial personnel or ^1[an officer or employee of the company] duly`
  line `authorised by the Board in this behalf.`
obj_root_law_sections_22:
  sectionId (205)
  sectionNo (22)
  orderNo 24
  title `Execution of bills of exchange, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_22_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=205&sectionno=22&orderno=24&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_22_content:
  string
  line `(1) A bill of exchange, hundi or promissory note shall be deemed to have been made, accepted, drawn or endorsed on behalf of a company if made, accepted, drawn, or endorsed in the name of, or on behalf of or on account of, the company by any person acting under its authority, express or implied.`
  line
  line `(2) A company may, by writing ^1[under its common seal, if any,] authorise any person, either`
  line `generally or in respect of any specified matters, as its attorney to execute other deeds on its behalf in any place either in or outside India:`
  line
  line `^2[Provided that in case a company does not have a common seal, the authorisation under this subsection shall be made by two directors or by a director and the Company Secretary, wherever the company has appointed a Company Secretary.]`
  line
  line `(3) A deed signed by such an attorney on behalf of the company and under his seal shall bind the`
  line `company ^3***.`
obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 21 of 2015, s. 6, for "under its common seal" (w.e.f. 29-5-2015).`
  line
  line `2. The proviso inserted by s. 6, ibid. (w.e.f. 29-5-2015).`
  line
  line `3. The words "and have the effect as if it were made under its common seal" omitted by s. 6, ibid. (w.e.f. 29-5-2015).`
obj_root_law_sections_23:
  sectionId (206)
  sectionNo (23)
  orderNo 25
  title `Public offer and private placement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_23_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 29 of 2020, s. 5, (w.e.f. 30-10-2023).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=206&sectionno=23&orderno=25&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_23_content:
  string
  line `(1) A public company may issue securities--`
  line
  line `(a) to public through prospectus (herein referred to as “public offer”) by complying with the`
  line `provisions of this Part; or`
  line
  line `(b) through private placement by complying with the provisions of Part II of this Chapter; or`
  line
  line `(c) through a rights issue or a bonus issue in accordance with the provisions of this Act and in case`
  line `of a listed company or a company which intends to get its securities listed also with the provisions of`
  line `the Securities and Exchange Board of India Act, 1992 (15 of 1992) and the rules and regulations made`
  line thereunder.
  line
  line `(2) A private company may issue securities--`
  line
  line `(a) by way of rights issue or bonus issue in accordance with the provisions of this Act; or`
  line
  line `(b) through private placement by complying with the provisions of Part II of this Chapter.`
  line
  line `^1[(3) Such class of public companies may issue such class of securities for the purposes of listing on`
  line `permitted stock exchanges in permissible foreign jurisdictions or such other jurisdictions, as may be`
  line prescribed.
  line
  line `(4) The Central Government may, by notification, exempt any class or classes of public companies`
  line `referred to in sub-section (3) from any of the provisions of this Chapter, Chapter IV, section 89, section 90`
  line `or section 127 and a copy of every such notification shall, as soon as may be after it is issued, be laid before`
  line `both Houses of Parliament.]`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purposes of this Chapter, “public offer” includes initial public offer or further`
  line `public offer of securities to the public by a company, or an offer for sale of securities to the public by an`
  line `existing shareholder, through issue of a prospectus.`
obj_root_law_sections_24:
  sectionId (207)
  sectionNo (24)
  orderNo 26
  title `Power of Securities and Exchange Board to regulate issue and transfer of securities, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_24_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=207&sectionno=24&orderno=26&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_24_content:
  string
  line `(1) The provisions contained in this Chapter, Chapter IV and in section 127 shall,--`
  line
  line `(a) in so far as they relate to--`
  line
  line `(i) issue and transfer of securities; and`
  line
  line `(ii) non-payment of dividend,`
  line
  line `by listed companies or those companies which intend to get their securities listed on any recognised stock exchange in India, except as provided under this Act, be administered by the Securities and Exchange Board by making regulations in this behalf;`
  line
  line `(b) in any other case, be administered by the Central Government.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the removal of doubts, it is hereby declared that all powers relating to all other matters relating to prospectus, return of allotment, redemption of preference shares and any other matter specifically provided in this Act, shall be exercised by the Central Government, the Tribunal or the Registrar, as the case may be.`
  line
  line `(2) The Securities and Exchange Board shall, in respect of matters specified in subsection (1) and the matters delegated to it under proviso to sub-section (1) of section 458, exercise the powers conferred upon it under sub-sections (1), (2A), (3) and (4) of section 11, sections 11A, 11B and 11D of the Securities and Exchange Board of India Act, 1992 (15 of 1992).`
obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_25:
  sectionId (208)
  sectionNo (25)
  orderNo 27
  title `Document containing offer of securities for sale to be deemed prospectus.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_25_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=208&sectionno=25&orderno=27&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_25_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where a`
  line `company allots or agrees to allot any securities of the company with a view to all or any of those securities being offered for sale to the public, any document by which the offer for sale to the public is made shall, for all purposes, be deemed to be a prospectus issued by the company; and all enactments and rules of law as to the contents of prospectus and as to liability in respect of mis-statements, in and omissions from, prospectus, or otherwise relating to prospectus, shall apply with the modifications`
  line `specified in subsections (3) and (4) and shall have effect accordingly, as if the securities had been offered to the public for subscription and as if persons accepting the offer in respect of any securities were subscribers for those securities, but without prejudice to the liability, if any, of the persons by whom the offer is made in respect of mis-statements contained in the document or otherwise in respect thereof.`
  line
  line `(2) For the purposes of this Act, it shall, unless the contrary is proved, be evidence that an allotment of, or an agreement to allot, securities was made with a view to the securities being offered for sale to the public if it is shown--`
  line
  line `(a) that an offer of the securities or of any of them for sale to the public was made within six`
  line `months after the allotment or agreement to allot; or`
  line
  line `(b) that at the date when the offer was made, the whole consideration to be received by the`
  line `company in respect of the securities had not been received by it.`
  line
  line `(3) Section 26 as applied by this section shall have effect as if--`
  line
  line `(i) it required a prospectus to state in addition to the matters required by that section to be stated in a prospectus`
  line
  line `(a) the net amount of the consideration received or to be received by the company in respect`
  line `of the securities to which the offer relates; and`
  line
  line `(b) the time and place at which the contract where under the said securities have been or are to be allotted may be inspected;`
  line
  line `(ii) the persons making the offer were persons named in a prospectus as directors of a company.`
  line
  line `(4) Where a person making an offer to which this section relates is a company or a firm, it shall be sufficient if the document referred to in sub-section (1) is signed on behalf of the company or firm by two directors of the company or by not less than one-half of the partners in the firm, as the case may be.`
obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_26:
  sectionId (209)
  sectionNo (26)
  orderNo 28
  title `Matters to be stated in prospectus.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_26_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=209&sectionno=26&orderno=28&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_26_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every prospectus issued by or on behalf of a public`
  line `company either with reference to its formation or subsequently, or by or on behalf of any person who is or`
  line `has been engaged or interested in the formation of a public company, shall be dated and signed and shall,`
  line ^1
  line `[state such information and set out such reports on financial information as may be specified by the`
  line `Securities and Exchange Board in consultation with the Central Government:`
  line
  line `Provided that until the Securities and Exchange Board specifies the information and reports on`
  line `financial information under this sub-section, the regulations made by the Securities and Exchange Board`
  line `under the Securities and Exchange Board of India Act, 1992 (15 of 1992), in respect of such financial`
  line `information or reports on financial information shall apply]; --`
  line
  line `^2* * * * *`
  line
  line `(c) make a declaration about the compliance of the provisions of this Act and a statement to the`
  line `effect that nothing in the prospectus is contrary to the provisions of this Act, the Securities Contracts`
  line `(Regulation) Act, 1956 (42 of 1956) and the Securities and Exchange Board of India Act, 1992`
  line `(15 of 1992) and the rules and regulations made thereunder; and`
  line
  line `^3* * * * *`
  line
  line `(2) Nothing in sub-section (1) shall apply--`
  line
  line `(a) to the issue to existing members or debenture-holders of a company, of a prospectus or form`
  line `of application relating to shares in or debentures of the company, whether an applicant has a right to`
  line `renounce the shares or not under sub-clause (ii) of clause (a) of sub-section (1) of section 62 in favour`
  line `of any other person; or`
  line
  line `(b) to the issue of a prospectus or form of application relating to shares or debentures which are,`
  line `or are to be, in all respects uniform with shares or debentures previously issued and for the time being`
  line `dealt in or quoted on a recognised stock exchange.`
  line
  line `(3) Subject to sub-section (2), the provisions of sub-section (1) shall apply to a prospectus or a form`
  line `of application, whether issued on or with reference to the formation of a company or subsequently.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--The date indicated in the prospectus shall be deemed to be the date of its publication.`
  line
  line `(4) No prospectus shall be issued by or on behalf of a company or in relation to an intended company`
  line `unless on or before the date of its publication, there has been delivered to the Registrar for ^3`
  line `[filing], a`
  line `copy thereof signed by every person who is named there in as a director or proposed director of the`
  line `company or by his duly authorised attorney.`
  line
  line `(5) A prospectus issued under sub-section (1) shall not include a statement purporting to be made by`
  line `an expert unless the expert is a person who is not, and has not been, engaged or interested in the formation`
  line `or promotion or management, of the company and has given his written consent to the issue of the`
  line `prospectus and has not withdrawn such consent before the delivery of a copy of the prospectus to the`
  line `Registrar for ^2`
  line `[filing] and a statement to that effect shall be included in the prospectus.`
  line
  line `(6) Every prospectus issued under sub-section (1) shall, on the face of it,--`
  line
  line `(a) state that a copy has been delivered for ^2`
  line `[filing] to the Registrar as required under`
  line `sub-section (4); and`
  line
  line `(b) specify any documents required by this section to be attached to the copy so delivered or refer`
  line `to statements included in the prospectus which specify these documents.`
  line
  line `^4* * * * *`
  line
  line `(8) No prospectus shall be valid if it is issued more than ninety days after the date on which a copy`
  line `thereof is delivered to the Registrar under sub-section (4).`
  line
  line `(9) If a prospectus is issued in contravention of the provisions of this section, the company shall be`
  line `punishable with fine which shall not be less than fifty thousand rupees but which may extend to three lakh rupees and every person who is knowingly a party to the issue of such prospectus shall be punishable ^5***`
  line `with fine which shall not be less than fifty thousand rupees but which may extend to ^6`
  line `[three lakh rupees].`
obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 1 of 2018, s. 8 (w.e.f. 7-5-2018).`
  line
  line `2. Clauses (a), (b) and (d) omitted by Act 1 of 2018, s. 8 (w.e.f. 7-5-2018).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 22 of 2019, s. 6, for "registration" (w.e.f. 15-8-2019).`
  line
  line `4. Sub-section (7) omitted by s. 6, ibid. (w.e.f. 15-8-2019).`
  line
  line `5. The words "with imprisonment for a term which may extend to three years or" omitted by Act 29 of 2020, s. 6 (w.e.f. 21-12-`
  line `2020).`
  line
  line `6. Subs. by s. 6, ibid., for "three lakh rupees, or with both" (w.e.f. 21-12-2020).`
obj_root_law_sections_27:
  sectionId (210)
  sectionNo (27)
  orderNo 29
  title `Variation in terms of contract or objects in prospectus.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_27_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=210&sectionno=27&orderno=29&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_27_content:
  string
  line `(1) A company shall not, at any time, vary the terms of a contract referred to in the prospectus or objects for which the prospectus was issued, except subject to the approval of, or except subject to an authority given by the company in general meeting by way of special resolution:`
  line
  line `Provided that the details, as may be prescribed, of the notice in respect of such resolution to`
  line `shareholders, shall also be published in the newspapers (one in English and one in vernacular language) in the city where the registered office of the company is situated indicating clearly the justification for such variation:`
  line
  line `Provided further that such company shall not use any amount raised by it through prospectus for buying, trading or otherwise dealing in equity shares of any other listed company.`
  line
  line `(2) The dissenting shareholders being those shareholders who have not agreed to the proposal to vary the terms of contracts or objects referred to in the prospectus, shall be given an exit offer by promoters or controlling shareholders at such exit price, and in such manner and conditions as may be specified by the Securities and Exchange Board by making regulations in this behalf.`
obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_28:
  sectionId (211)
  sectionNo (28)
  orderNo 30
  title `Offer of sale of shares by certain members of company.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_28_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=211&sectionno=28&orderno=30&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_28_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where certain members of a`
  line `company propose, in consultation with the Board of Directors to offer, in accordance with the provisions of any law for the time being in force, whole or part of their holding of shares to the public, they may do so in accordance with such procedure as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(2) Any document by which the offer of sale to the public is made shall, for all purposes, be deemed to be a prospectus issued by the company and all laws and rules made thereunder as to the contents of the prospectus and as to liability in respect of mis-statements in and omission from prospectus or otherwise relating to prospectus shall apply as if this is a prospectus issued by the company.`
  line
  line `(3) The members, whether individuals or bodies corporate or both, whose shares are proposed to be offered to the public, shall collectively authorise the company, whose shares are offered for sale to the public, to take all actions in respect of offer of sale for and on their behalf and they shall reimburse the company all expenses incurred by it on this matter.`
obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_29:
  sectionId (212)
  sectionNo (29)
  orderNo 31
  title `Public offer of securities to be in dematerialised form.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_29_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=212&sectionno=29&orderno=31&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_29_content:
  string
  line `(1) Notwithstanding anything`
  line `contained in any other provisions of this Act,--`
  line
  line `(a) every company making public offer; and`
  line
  line `(b) such other class or classes of ^1*** companies as may be prescribed,`
  line
  line `shall issue the securities only in dematerialised form by complying with the provisions of the Depositories`
  line `Act, 1996 (22 of 1996) and the regulations made thereunder.`
  line
  line `^2[(1A) In case of such class or classes of unlisted companies as may be prescribed, the securities shall`
  line `be held or transferred only in dematerialised form in the manner laid down in the Depositories Act, 1996`
  line `and the regulations made thereunder.]`
  line
  line `(2) Any company, other than a company mentioned in sub-section (1), may convert its securities into`
  line `dematerialised form or issue its securities in physical form in accordance with the provisions of this Act`
  line `or in dematerialised form in accordance with the provisions of the Depositories Act, 1996 (22 of 1996)`
  line `and the regulations made thereunder.`
obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. The word "public" omitted by Act 22 of 2019, s. 7 (w.e.f. 15-8-2019).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by s. 7, ibid. (w.e.f. 15-8-2019).`
obj_root_law_sections_30:
  sectionId (1220)
  sectionNo (30)
  orderNo 32
  title `Advertisement of prospectus.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_30_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=1220&sectionno=30&orderno=32&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_30_content:
  string
  line `Where an advertisement of any prospectus of a company is published in any manner, it shall be necessary to specify therein the contents of its memorandum as`
  line
  line `regards the objects, the liability of members and the amount of share capital of the company, and the names of the signatories to the memorandum and the number of shares subscribed for by them, and its capital structure.`
obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_31:
  sectionId (1221)
  sectionNo (31)
  orderNo 33
  title `Shelf prospectus.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_31_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=1221&sectionno=31&orderno=33&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_31_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any class or classes of companies, as the Securities and Exchange Board may provide by regulations in this behalf, may file a shelf prospectus with the Registrar at the stage of the first offer of securities included therein which shall indicate a period not exceeding one year as the period of validity of such prospectus which shall commence from the date of opening of the first offer of securities under that prospectus, and in respect of a second or subsequent offer of such securities issued during the period of validity of that prospectus, no further prospectus is required.`
  line
  line `(2) A company filing a shelf prospectus shall be required to file an information memorandum`
  line `containing all material facts relating to new charges created, changes in the financial position of the company as have occurred between the first offer of securities or the previous offer of securities and the succeeding offer of securities and such other changes as may be prescribed, with the Registrar within the prescribed time, prior to the issue of a second or subsequent offer of securities under the shelf prospectus:`
  line
  line `Provided that where a company or any other person has received applications for the allotment of securities along with advance payments of subscription before the making of any such change, the company or other person shall intimate the changes to such applicants and if they express a desire to withdraw their application, the company or other person shall refund all the monies received as subscription within fifteen days thereof.`
  line
  line `(3) Where an information memorandum is filed, every time an offer of securities is made under subsection`
  line `(2), such memorandum together with the shelf prospectus shall be deemed to be a prospectus.`
  line
  line `Explanation.-- For the purposes of this section, the expression "shelf prospectus" means a prospectus in respect of which the securities or class of securities included therein are issued for subscription in one or more issues over a certain period without the issue of a further prospectus.`
obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_32:
  sectionId (1222)
  sectionNo (32)
  orderNo 34
  title `Red herring prospectus.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_32_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=1222&sectionno=32&orderno=34&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_32_content:
  string
  line `(1) A company proposing to make an offer of securities may issue a red herring prospectus prior to the issue of a prospectus.`
  line
  line `(2) A company proposing to issue a red herring prospectus under sub-section (1) shall file it with the Registrar at least three days prior to the opening of the subscription list and the offer.`
  line
  line `(3) A red herring prospectus shall carry the same obligations as are applicable to a prospectus and any variation between the red herring prospectus and a prospectus shall be highlighted as variations in the prospectus.`
  line
  line `(4) Upon the closing of the offer of securities under this section, the prospectus stating therein the total capital raised, whether by way of debt or share capital, and the closing price of the securities and any other details as are not included in the red herring prospectus shall be filed with the Registrar and the Securities and Exchange Board.`
  line
  line `Explanation.-- For the purposes of this section, the expression "red herring prospectus" means a prospectus which does not include complete particulars of the quantum or price of the securities included therein`
obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_33:
  sectionId (1223)
  sectionNo (33)
  orderNo 35
  title `Issue of application forms for securities`
  content obj_root_law_sections_33_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=1223&sectionno=33&orderno=35&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_33_content:
  string
  line `(1) No form of application for the purchase of any of the securities of a company shall be issued unless such form is accompanied by an abridged prospectus:`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing in this sub-section shall apply if it is shown that the form of application was issued--`
  line
  line `(a) in connection with a bona fide invitation to a person to enter into an underwriting agreement`
  line `with respect to such securities; or`
  line
  line `(b) in relation to securities which were not offered to the public.`
  line
  line `(2) A copy of the prospectus shall, on a request being made by any person before the closing of the subscription list and the offer, be furnished to him.`
  line
  line `(3) If a company makes any default in complying with the provisions of this section, it shall be liable to a penalty of fifty thousand rupees for each default.`
obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_34:
  sectionId (1224)
  sectionNo (34)
  orderNo 36
  title `Criminal liability for mis-statements in prospectus.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_34_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_34_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=1224&sectionno=34&orderno=36&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_34_content:
  string
  line `Where a prospectus, issued, circulated or distributed under this Chapter, includes any statement which is untrue or misleading in form or context in which it is included or where any inclusion or omission of any matter is likely to mislead, every person who authorises the issue of such prospectus shall be liable under section 447:`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing in this section shall apply to a person if he proves that such statement or`
  line `omission was immaterial or that he had reasonable grounds to believe, and did up to the time of issue of the prospectus believe, that the statement was true or the inclusion or omission was necessary.`
obj_root_law_sections_34_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_35:
  sectionId (1225)
  sectionNo (35)
  orderNo 37
  title `Civil liability for mis-statements in prospectus.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_35_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_35_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=1225&sectionno=35&orderno=37&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_35_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where a person has subscribed for`
  line `securities of a company acting on any statement included, or the inclusion or omission of any matter, in`
  line `the prospectus which is misleading and has sustained any loss or damage as a consequence thereof, the`
  line `company and every person who--`
  line
  line `(a) is a director of the company at the time of the issue of the prospectus;`
  line
  line `(b) has authorised himself to be named and is named in the prospectus as a director of the`
  line `company, or has agreed to become such director, either immediately or after an interval of time;`
  line
  line `(c) is a promoter of the company;`
  line
  line `(d) has authorised the issue of the prospectus; and`
  line
  line `(e) is an expert referred to in sub-section (5) of section 26,`
  line
  line `shall, without prejudice to any punishment to which any person may be liable under section 36, be liable`
  line `to pay compensation to every person who has sustained such loss or damage.`
  line
  line `(2) No person shall be liable under sub-section (1), if he proves--`
  line
  line `(a) that, having consented to become a director of the company, he withdrew his consent before`
  line `the issue of the prospectus, and that it was issued without his authority or consent; or`
  line
  line `(b) that the prospectus was issued without his knowledge or consent, and that on becoming aware`
  line `of its issue, he forthwith gave a reasonable public notice that it was issued without his knowledge or`
  line consent.
  line
  line `^1[(c) that, as regards every misleading statement purported to be made by an expert or contained`
  line `in what purports to be a copy of or an extract from a report or valuation of an expert, it was a correct`
  line `and fair representation of the statement, or a correct copy of, or a correct and fair extract from, the`
  line `report or valuation; and he had reasonable ground to believe and did up to the time of the issue of the`
  line `prospectus believe, that the person making the statement was competent to make it and that the said`
  line `person had given the consent required by sub-section (5) of section 26 to the issue of the prospectus`
  line `and had not withdrawn that consent before ^2[filing of a copy of the prospectus with the Registrar] or,`
  line `to the defendant's knowledge, before allotment thereunder.]`
  line
  line `(3) Notwithstanding anything contained in this section, where it is proved that a prospectus has been`
  line `issued with intent to defraud the applicants for the securities of a company or any other person or for any`
  line `fraudulent purpose, every person referred to in sub-section (1) shall be personally responsible, without`
  line `any limitation of liability, for all or any of the losses or damages that may have been incurred by any`
  line `person who subscribed to the securities on the basis of such prospectus.`
obj_root_law_sections_35_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 1 of 2018, s. 9 (w.e.f. 9-2-2018).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 22 of 2019, s. 8, for "delivery of a copy of the prospectus for registration" (w.e.f. 15-8-2019).`
obj_root_law_sections_36:
  sectionId (1226)
  sectionNo (36)
  orderNo 38
  title `Punishment for fraudulently inducing persons to invest money.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_36_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_36_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=1226&sectionno=36&orderno=38&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_36_content:
  string
  line `Any person who, either`
  line `knowingly or recklessly makes any statement, promise or forecast which is false, deceptive or misleading, or deliberately conceals any material facts, to induce another person to enter into, or to offer to enter`
  line into,-
  line
  line `(a) any agreement for, or with a view to, acquiring, disposing of, subscribing for, or underwriting`
  line `securities; or`
  line
  line `(b) any agreement, the purpose or the pretended purpose of which is to secure a profit to any ofthe parties from the yield of securities or by reference to fluctuations in the value of securities; or`
  line
  line `(c) any agreement for, or with a view to obtaining credit facilities from any bank or financial institution,`
  line
  line `shall be liable for action under section 447.`
obj_root_law_sections_36_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_37:
  sectionId (1227)
  sectionNo (37)
  orderNo 39
  title `Action by affected persons.`
  content `A suit may be filed or any other action may be taken under section 34 or section 35 or section 36 by any person, group of persons or any association of persons affected byany misleading statement or the inclusion or omission of any matter in the prospectus.`
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_37_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=1227&sectionno=37&orderno=39&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_37_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_38:
  sectionId (1228)
  sectionNo (38)
  orderNo 40
  title `Punishment for personation for acquisition, etc., of securities`
  content obj_root_law_sections_38_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_38_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=1228&sectionno=38&orderno=40&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_38_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any person who--`
  line
  line `(a) makes or abets making of an application in a fictitious name to a company for acquiring, or`
  line `subscribing for, its securities; or`
  line
  line `(b) makes or abets making of multiple applications to a company in different names or in`
  line `different combinations of his name or surname for acquiring or subscribing for its securities; or`
  line
  line `(c) otherwise induces directly or indirectly a company to allot, or register any transfer of,`
  line `securities to him, or to any other person in a fictitious name,`
  line
  line `shall be liable for action under section 447.`
  line
  line `(2) The provisions of sub-section (1) shall be prominently reproduced in every prospectus issued by acompany and in every form of application for securities.`
  line
  line `(3) Where a person has been convicted under this section, the Court may also order disgorgement of gain, if any, made by, and seizure and disposal of the securities in possession of, such person.`
  line
  line `(4) The amount received through disgorgement or disposal of securities under subsection (3) shall becredited to the Investor Education and Protection Fund.`
obj_root_law_sections_38_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_39:
  sectionId (1229)
  sectionNo (39)
  orderNo 41
  title `Allotment of securities by company.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_39_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_39_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=1229&sectionno=39&orderno=41&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_39_content:
  string
  line `(1) No allotment of any securities of a company offered to the public for subscription shall be made unless the amount stated in the prospectus as the minimum amount has been subscribed and the sums payable on application for the amount so stated have been paid to and received by the company by cheque or other instrument.`
  line
  line `(2) The amount payable on application on every security shall not be less than five per cent. of the nominal amount of the security or such other percentage or amount, as may be specified by the Securities and Exchange Board by making regulations in this behalf.`
  line
  line `(3) If the stated minimum amount has not been subscribed and the sum payable on application is not received within a period of thirty days from the date of issue of the prospectus, or such other period as may be specified by the Securities and Exchange Board, the amount received under sub-section (1) shall be returned within such time and manner as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(4) Whenever a company having a share capital makes any allotment of securities, it shall file with the Registrar a return of allotment in such manner as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(5) In case of any default under sub-section (3) or sub-section (4), the company and its officer who is in default shall be liable to a penalty, for each default, of one thousand rupees for each day during whichsuch default continues or one lakh rupees, whichever is less.`
obj_root_law_sections_39_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_40:
  sectionId (1230)
  sectionNo (40)
  orderNo 42
  title `Securities to be dealt with in stock exchanges.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_40_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_40_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=1230&sectionno=40&orderno=42&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_40_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every company making public offer shall,`
  line `before making such offer, make an application to one or more recognised stock exchange or exchanges`
  line `and obtain permission for the securities to be dealt with in such stock exchange or exchanges.`
  line
  line `(2) Where a prospectus states that an application under sub-section (1) has been made, such`
  line `prospectus shall also state the name or names of the stock exchange in which the securities shall be dealt`
  line with.
  line
  line `(3) All monies received on application from the public for subscription to the securities shall be kept`
  line `in a separate bank account in a scheduled bank and shall not be utilised for any purpose other than--`
  line
  line `(a) for adjustment against allotment of securities where the securities have been permitted to be`
  line `dealt with in the stock exchange or stock exchanges specified in the prospectus; or`
  line
  line `(b) for the repayment of monies within the time specified by the Securities and Exchange Board,`
  line `received from applicants in pursuance of the prospectus, where the company is for any other reason`
  line `unable to allot securities.`
  line
  line `(4) Any condition purporting to require or bind any applicant for securities to waive compliance with`
  line `any of the requirements of this section shall be void.`
  line
  line `(5) If a default is made in complying with the provisions of this section, the company shall be`
  line `punishable with a fine which shall not be less than five lakh rupees but which may extend to fifty lakh`
  line `rupees and every officer of the company who is in default shall be punishable ^1*** or with fine which`
  line `shall not be less than fifty thousand rupees but which may extend to ^2`
  line `[three lakh rupees].`
  line
  line `(6) A company may pay commission to any person in connection with the subscription to its`
  line `securities subject to such conditions as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_40_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. The words "with imprisonment for a term which may extend to one year or" omitted by Act 29 of 2020, s. 7 (w.e.f. 21-12-`
  line `2020).`
  line `2. Subs. by s. 7, ibid., for "three lakh rupees, or with both" (w.e.f. 21-12-2020).`
obj_root_law_sections_41:
  sectionId (1231)
  sectionNo (41)
  orderNo 43
  title `Global depository receipt.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_41_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_41_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=1231&sectionno=41&orderno=43&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_41_content:
  string
  line `A company may, after passing a special resolution in its general`
  line `meeting, issue depository receipts in any foreign country in such manner, and subject to such conditions,`
  line `as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_41_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_42:
  sectionId (1232)
  sectionNo (42)
  orderNo 44
  title `Issue of shares on private placement basis.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_42_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 1 of 2018, s. 10 (w.e.f. 7-8-2018).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=1232&sectionno=42&orderno=44&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_42_content:
  string
  line `^1[42. Issue of shares on private placement basis.-- (1) A company may, subject to the provisions of`
  line `this section, make a private placement of securities.`
  line
  line `(2) A private placement shall be made only to a select group of persons who have been identified by`
  line `the Board (herein referred to as identified persons), whose number shall not exceed fifty or such higher`
  line `number as may be prescribed excluding the qualified institutional buyers and employees of the company`
  line `being offered securities under a scheme of employees stock option in terms of provisions of clause (b) of`
  line `sub-section (1) of section 62, in a financial year subject to such conditions as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(3) A company making private placement shall issue private placement offer and application in such`
  line `form and manner as may be prescribed to identified persons, whose names and addresses are recorded by`
  line `the company in such manner as may be prescribed:`
  line
  line `Provided that the private placement offer and application shall not carry any right of renunciation.`
  line
  line `Explanation I.-- "private placement" means any offer or invitation to subscribe or issue of securities`
  line `to a select group of persons by a company (other than by way of public offer) through private placement`
  line `offer-cum-application, which satisfies the conditions specified in this section.`
  line
  line `Explanation II.-- "qualified institutional buyer" means the qualified institutional buyer as defined in`
  line `the Securities and Exchange Board of India (Issue of Capital and Disclosure Requirements) Regulations,`
  line `2009, as amended from time to time, made under the Securities and Exchange Board of India Act, 1992,`
  line `(15 of 1992).`
  line
  line `Explanation III.-- If a company, listed or unlisted, makes an offer to allot or invites subscription, or`
  line `allots, or enters into an agreement to allot, securities to more than the prescribed number of persons,`
  line `whether the payment for the securities has been received or not or whether the company intends to list its`
  line `securities or not on any recognised stock exchange in or outside India, the same shall be deemed to be an`
  line `offer to the public and shall accordingly be governed by the provisions of Part I of this Chapter.`
  line
  line `(4) Every identified person willing to subscribe to the private placement issue shall apply in the`
  line `private placement and application issued to such person alongwith subscription money paid either by`
  line `cheque or demand draft or other banking channel and not by cash:`
  line
  line `Provided that a company shall not utilise monies raised through private placement unless allotment is`
  line `made and the return of allotment is filed with the Registrar in accordance with sub-section (8).`
  line
  line `(5) No fresh offer or invitation under this section shall be made unless the allotments with respect to`
  line `any offer or invitation made earlier have been completed or that offer or invitation has been withdrawn or`
  line `abandoned by the company:`
  line
  line `Provided that, subject to the maximum number of identified persons under sub-section (2), a company`
  line `may, at any time, make more than one issue of securities to such class of identified persons as may be`
  line prescribed.
  line
  line `(6) A company making an offer or invitation under this section shall allot its securities within sixty`
  line `days from the date of receipt of the application money for such securities and if the company is not able to`
  line `allot the securities within that period, it shall repay the application money to the subscribers within fifteen`
  line `days from the expiry of sixty days and if the company fails to repay the application money within the`
  line `aforesaid period, it shall be liable to repay that money with interest at the rate of twelve per cent. per`
  line `annum from the expiry of the sixtieth day:`
  line
  line `Provided that monies received on application under this section shall be kept in a separate bank`
  line `account in a scheduled bank and shall not be utilised for any purpose other than--`
  line
  line `(a) for adjustment against allotment of securities; or`
  line
  line `(b) for the repayment of monies where the company is unable to allot securities.`
  line
  line `(7) No company issuing securities under this section shall release any public advertisements or utilise`
  line `any media, marketing or distribution channels or agents to inform the public at large about such an issue.`
  line
  line `(8) A company making any allotment of securities under this section, shall file with the Registrar a`
  line `return of allotment within fifteen days from the date of the allotment in such manner as may be`
  line `prescribed, including a complete list of all allottees, with their full names, addresses, number of securities`
  line `allotted and such other relevant information as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(9) If a company defaults in filing the return of allotment within the period prescribed under subsection (8), the company, its promoters and directors shall be liable to a penalty for each default of one`
  line `thousand rupees for each day during which such default continues but not exceeding twenty-five lakh`
  line rupees.
  line
  line `(10) Subject to sub-section (11), if a company makes an offer or accepts monies in contravention of`
  line `this section, the company, its promoters and directors shall be liable for a penalty which may extend to the`
  line `amount raised through the private placement or two crore rupees, whichever is lower, and the company`
  line `shall also refund all monies with interest as specified in sub-section (6) to subscribers within a period of`
  line `thirty days of the order imposing the penalty.`
  line
  line `(11) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (9) and sub-section (10), any private`
  line `placement issue not made in compliance of the provisions of sub-section (2) shall be deemed to be a`
  line `public offer and all the provisions of this Act and the Securities Contracts (Regulation) Act, 1956`
  line `(42 of 1956) and the Securities and Exchange Board of India Act, 1992 (15 of 1992) shall be applicable.]`
obj_root_law_sections_43:
  sectionId (1233)
  sectionNo (43)
  orderNo 45
  title `Kinds of share capital.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_43_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_43_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=1233&sectionno=43&orderno=45&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_43_content:
  string
  line `The share capital of a company limited by shares shall be of two kinds,`
  line `namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) equity share capital--`
  line
  line `(i) with voting rights; or`
  line
  line `(ii) with differential rights as to dividend, voting or otherwise in accordance with such rules`
  line `as may be prescribed; and`
  line
  line `(b) preference share capital:`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing contained in this Act shall affect the rights of the preference shareholders who`
  line `are entitled to participate in the proceeds of winding up before the commencement of this Act.`
  line
  line `Explanation.-- For the purposes of this section,--`
  line
  line `(i) equity share capital, with reference to any company limited by shares, means all share`
  line `capital which is not preference share capital;`
  line
  line `(ii) preference share capital, with reference to any company limited by shares, means that part`
  line `of the issued share capital of the company which carries or would carry a preferential right with`
  line `respect to`
  line
  line `(a) payment of dividend, either as a fixed amount or an amount calculated at a fixed rate,`
  line `which may either be free of or subject to income-tax; and`
  line
  line `(b) repayment, in the case of a winding up or repayment of capital, of the amount of the share`
  line `capital paid-up or deemed to have been paid-up, whether or not, there is a preferential right to the`
  line `payment of any fixed premium or premium on any fixed scale, specified in the memorandum or`
  line `articles of the company;`
  line
  line `(iii) capital shall be deemed to be preference capital, notwithstanding that it is entitled to either or`
  line `both of the following rights, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) that in respect of dividends, in addition to the preferential rights to the amounts specified`
  line `in sub-clause (a) of clause (ii), it has a right to participate, whether fully or to a limited extent,`
  line `with capital not entitled to the preferential right aforesaid;`
  line
  line `(b) that in respect of capital, in addition to the preferential right to the repayment, on a`
  line `winding up, of the amounts specified in sub-clause (b) of clause (ii), it has a right to participate,`
  line `whether fully or to a limited extent, with capital not entitled to that preferential right in any`
  line `surplus which may remain after the entire capital has been repaid.`
obj_root_law_sections_43_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_44:
  sectionId (1234)
  sectionNo (44)
  orderNo 46
  title `Nature of shares or debentures.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_44_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_44_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=1234&sectionno=44&orderno=46&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_44_content:
  string
  line `The shares or debentures or other interest of any member in a`
  line `company shall be movable property transferable in the manner provided by the articles of the company.`
obj_root_law_sections_44_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_45:
  sectionId (1235)
  sectionNo (45)
  orderNo 47
  title `Numbering of shares`
  content obj_root_law_sections_45_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_45_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=1235&sectionno=45&orderno=47&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_45_content:
  string
  line `Every share in a company having a share capital shall be distinguished`
  line `by its distinctive number:`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing in this section shall apply to a share held by a person whose name is entered as`
  line `holder of beneficial interest in such share in the records of a depository.`
obj_root_law_sections_45_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_46:
  sectionId (1236)
  sectionNo (46)
  orderNo 48
  title `Certificate of shares.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_46_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 21 of 2015, s. 7, for "issued under the common seal of the company" (w.e.f. 29-5-2015).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=1236&sectionno=46&orderno=48&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_46_content:
  string
  line `(1) A certificate, ^1[issued under the common seal, if any, of the company`
  line `or signed by two directors or by a director and the Company Secretary, wherever the company has`
  line `appointed a Company Secretary], specifying the shares held by any person, shall be prima facie evidence`
  line `of the title of the person to such shares.`
  line
  line `(2) A duplicate certificate of shares may be issued, if such certificate--`
  line
  line `(a) is proved to have been lost or destroyed; or`
  line
  line `(b) has been defaced, mutilated or torn and is surrendered to the company.`
  line
  line `(3) Notwithstanding anything contained in the articles of a company, the manner of issue of a`
  line `certificate of shares or the duplicate thereof, the form of such certificate, the particulars to be entered in`
  line `the register of members and other matters shall be such as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(4) Where a share is held in depository form, the record of the depository is the prima facie evidence`
  line `of the interest of the beneficial owner.`
  line
  line `(5) If a company with intent to defraud issues a duplicate certificate of shares, the company shall be`
  line `punishable with fine which shall not be less than five times the face value of the shares involved in the`
  line `issue of the duplicate certificate but which may extend to ten times the face value of such shares or rupees`
  line `ten crores whichever is higher and every officer of the company who is in default shall be liable for action`
  line `under section 447.`
obj_root_law_sections_47:
  sectionId (1237)
  sectionNo (47)
  orderNo 49
  title `Voting rights`
  content obj_root_law_sections_47_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 1 of 2018, s. 11, for "provisions of section 43 and sub-section (2) of section 50" (w.e.f. 9-2-2018).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=1237&sectionno=47&orderno=49&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_47_content:
  string
  line `(1) Subject to the ^1[provisions of section 43, sub-section (2) of section 50 and`
  line `sub-section (1) of section 188],--`
  line
  line `(a) every member of a company limited by shares and holding equity share capital therein, shall`
  line `have a right to vote on every resolution placed before the company; and`
  line
  line `(b) his voting right on a poll shall be in proportion to his share in the paid-up equity share capital`
  line `of the company.`
  line
  line `(2) Every member of a company limited by shares and holding any preference share capital therein`
  line `shall, in respect of such capital, have a right to vote only on resolutions placed before the company which`
  line `directly affect the rights attached to his preference shares and, any resolution for the winding up of the`
  line `company or for the repayment or reduction of its equity or preference share capital and his voting right on`
  line `a poll shall be in proportion to his share in the paid-up preference share capital of the company:`
  line
  line `Provided that the proportion of the voting rights of equity shareholders to the voting rights of the`
  line `preference shareholders shall be in the same proportion as the paid-up capital in respect of the equity`
  line `shares bears to the paid-up capital in respect of the preference shares:`
  line
  line `Provided further that where the dividend in respect of a class of preference shares has not been paid`
  line `for a period of two years or more, such class of preference shareholders shall have a right to vote on all`
  line `the resolutions placed before the company.`
obj_root_law_sections_48:
  sectionId (1238)
  sectionNo (48)
  orderNo 50
  title `Variation of shareholders‘ rights`
  content obj_root_law_sections_48_content
  footnotes `1. Sub-section (5) omitted by Act 29 of 2020, s. 8 (w.e.f. 21-12-2020).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=1238&sectionno=48&orderno=50&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_48_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where a share capital of the company is divided into`
  line `different classes of shares, the rights attached to the shares of any class may be varied with the consent in`
  line `writing of the holders of not less than three-fourths of the issued shares of that class or by means of a`
  line `special resolution passed at a separate meeting of the holders of the issued shares of that class,--`
  line
  line `(a) if provision with respect to such variation is contained in the memorandum or articles of the`
  line `company; or`
  line
  line `(b) in the absence of any such provision in the memorandum or articles, if such variation is not`
  line `prohibited by the terms of issue of the shares of that class:`
  line
  line `Provided that if variation by one class of shareholders affects the rights of any other class of`
  line `shareholders, the consent of three-fourths of such other class of shareholders shall also be obtained and`
  line `the provisions of this section shall apply to such variation.`
  line
  line `(2) Where the holders of not less than ten per cent. of the issued shares of a class did not consent to`
  line `such variation or vote in favour of the special resolution for the variation, they may apply to the Tribunal`
  line `to have the variation cancelled, and where any such application is made, the variation shall not have effect`
  line `unless and until it is confirmed by the Tribunal:`
  line
  line `Provided that an application under this section shall be made within twenty-one days after the date on`
  line `which the consent was given or the resolution was passed, as the case may be, and may be made on behalf`
  line `of the shareholders entitled to make the application by such one or more of their number as they may`
  line `appoint in writing for the purpose.`
  line
  line `(3) The decision of the Tribunal on any application under sub-section (2) shall be binding on the`
  line shareholders.
  line
  line `(4) The company shall, within thirty days of the date of the order of the Tribunal, file a copy thereof`
  line `with the Registrar.`
  line
  line `^1* * * * *`
obj_root_law_sections_49:
  sectionId (1239)
  sectionNo (49)
  orderNo 51
  title `Calls on shares of same class to be made on uniform basis.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_49_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_49_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=1239&sectionno=49&orderno=51&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_49_content:
  string
  line `Where any calls for further share`
  line `capital are made on the shares of a class, such calls shall be made on a uniform basis on all shares falling`
  line `under that class.`
  line
  line `Explanation.-- For the purposes of this section, shares of the same nominal value on which different`
  line `amounts have been paid-up shall not be deemed to fall under the same class.`
obj_root_law_sections_49_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_50:
  sectionId (1240)
  sectionNo (50)
  orderNo 52
  title `Company to accept unpaid share capital, although not called up.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_50_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_50_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=1240&sectionno=50&orderno=52&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_50_content:
  string
  line `(1) A company may, if so`
  line `authorised by its articles, accept from any member, the whole or a part of the amount remaining unpaid on`
  line `any shares held by him, even if no part of that amount has been called up.`
  line
  line `(2) A member of the company limited by shares shall not be entitled to any voting rights in respect of`
  line `the amount paid by him under sub-section (1) until that amount has been called up.`
obj_root_law_sections_50_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_51:
  sectionId (1241)
  sectionNo (51)
  orderNo 53
  title `Payment of dividend in proportion to amount paid-up`
  content obj_root_law_sections_51_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_51_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=1241&sectionno=51&orderno=53&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_51_content:
  string
  line `A company may, if so authorised by`
  line `its articles, pay dividends in proportion to the amount paid-up on each share.`
obj_root_law_sections_51_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_52:
  sectionId (1242)
  sectionNo (52)
  orderNo 54
  title `Application of premiums received on issue of shares.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_52_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_52_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=1242&sectionno=52&orderno=54&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_52_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where a company issues shares at a`
  line `premium, whether for cash or otherwise, a sum equal to the aggregate amount of the premium received on`
  line `those shares shall be transferred to a securities premium account and the provisions of this Act relating`
  line `to reduction of share capital of a company shall, except as provided in this section, apply as if the`
  line `securities premium account were the paid-up share capital of the company.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (1), the securities premium account may be`
  line `applied by the company--`
  line
  line `(a) towards the issue of unissued shares of the company to the members of the company as fully`
  line `paid bonus shares;`
  line
  line `(b) in writing off the preliminary expenses of the company;`
  line
  line `(c) in writing off the expenses of, or the commission paid or discount allowed on, any issue of`
  line `shares or debentures of the company;`
  line
  line `(d) in providing for the premium payable on the redemption of any redeemable preference shares`
  line `or of any debentures of the company; or`
  line
  line `(e) for the purchase of its own shares or other securities under section 68.`
  line
  line `(3) The securities premium account may, notwithstanding anything contained in sub-sections (1) and`
  line `(2), be applied by such class of companies, as may be prescribed and whose financial statement comply`
  line `with the accounting standards prescribed for such class of companies under section 133,`
  line
  line `(a) in paying up unissued equity shares of the company to be issued to members of the company`
  line `as fully paid bonus shares; or`
  line
  line `(b) in writing off the expenses of or the commission paid or discount allowed on any issue of`
  line `equity shares of the company; or`
  line
  line `(c) for the purchase of its own shares or other securities under section 68.`
obj_root_law_sections_52_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_53:
  sectionId (1243)
  sectionNo (53)
  orderNo 55
  title `Prohibition on issue of shares at discount.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_53_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_53_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=1243&sectionno=53&orderno=55&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_53_content:
  string
  line `(1) Except as provided in section 54, a company`
  line `shall not issue shares at a discount.`
  line
  line `(2) Any share issued by a company at a ^1[discount] shall be void.`
  line
  line `^2[(2A) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-sections (1) and (2), a company may issue shares at`
  line `a discount to its creditors when its debt is converted into shares in pursuance of any statutory resolution`
  line `plan or debt restructuring scheme in accordance with any guidelines or directions or regulations specified`
  line `by the Reserve Bank of India under the Reserve Bank of India Act, 1934 (2 of 1934) or the Banking`
  line `(Regulation) Act, 1949 (10 of 1949).]`
  line
  line `^3[(3) Where any company fails to comply with the provisions of this section, such company and every`
  line `officer who is in default shall be liable to a penalty which may extend to an amount equal to the amount`
  line `raised through the issue of shares at a discount of five lakh rupees, whichever is less, and the company`
  line `shall also be liable to refund all monies received with interest at the rate of twelve per cent. per annum`
  line `from the date of issue of such shares to the persons to whom such shares have been issued.]`
obj_root_law_sections_53_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 1 of 2018, s. 12, for "discounted price" (w.e.f. 9-2-2018).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by s. 12, ibid. (w.e.f. 9-2-2018).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 22 of 2019, s. 9, for sub-section (3) (w.e.f. 2-11-2018).`
obj_root_law_sections_54:
  sectionId (1244)
  sectionNo (54)
  orderNo 56
  title `Issues of sweat equity shares`
  content obj_root_law_sections_54_content
  footnotes `1. Clause (c) omitted by s. 13, ibid. (w.e.f. 7-5-2018).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=1244&sectionno=54&orderno=56&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_54_content:
  string
  line `(1) Notwithstanding anything contained in section 53, a company`
  line `may issue sweat equity shares of a class of shares already issued, if the following conditions are fulfilled,`
  line `namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the issue is authorised by a special resolution passed by the company;`
  line
  line `(b) the resolution specifies the number of shares, the current market price, consideration, if any,`
  line `and the class or classes of directors or employees to whom such equity shares are to be issued;`
  line
  line `^1* * * * *`
  line
  line `(d) where the equity shares of the company are listed on a recognised stock exchange, the sweat`
  line `equity shares are issued in accordance with the regulations made by the Securities and Exchange`
  line `Board in this behalf and if they are not so listed, the sweat equity shares are issued in accordance with`
  line `such rules as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(2) The rights, limitations, restrictions and provisions as are for the time being applicable to equity`
  line `shares shall be applicable to the sweat equity shares issued under this section and the holders of such`
  line `shares shall rank pari passu with other equity shareholders.`
obj_root_law_sections_55:
  sectionId (1245)
  sectionNo (55)
  orderNo 57
  title `Issue and redemption of preference shares.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_55_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_55_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=1245&sectionno=55&orderno=57&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_55_content:
  string
  line `(1) No company limited by shares shall, after the`
  line `commencement of this Act, issue any preference shares which are irredeemable.`
  line
  line `(2) A company limited by shares may, if so authorised by its articles, issue preference shares which`
  line `are liable to be redeemed within a period not exceeding twenty years from the date of their issue subject`
  line `to such conditions as may be prescribed:`
  line
  line `Provided that a company may issue preference shares for a period exceeding twenty years for`
  line `infrastructure projects, subject to the redemption of such percentage of shares as may be prescribed on an`
  line `annual basis at the option of such preferential shareholders:`
  line
  line `Provided further that--`
  line
  line `(a) no such shares shall be redeemed except out of the profits of the company which would`
  line `otherwise be available for dividend or out of the proceeds of a fresh issue of shares made for the`
  line `purposes of such redemption;`
  line
  line `(b) no such shares shall be redeemed unless they are fully paid;`
  line
  line `(c) where such shares are proposed to be redeemed out of the profits of the company, there shall,`
  line `out of such profits, be transferred, a sum equal to the nominal amount of the shares to be redeemed, to`
  line `a reserve, to be called the Capital Redemption Reserve Account, and the provisions of this Act`
  line `relating to reduction of share capital of a company shall, except as provided in this section, apply as if`
  line `the Capital Redemption Reserve Account were paid-up share capital of the company; and`
  line
  line `(d) (i) in case of such class of companies, as may be prescribed and whose financial statement`
  line `comply with the accounting standards prescribed for such class of companies under section 133, the`
  line `premium, if any, payable on redemption shall be provided for out of the profits of the company,`
  line `before the shares are redeemed:`
  line
  line `Provided also that premium, if any, payable on redemption of any preference shares issued on or`
  line `before the commencement of this Act by any such company shall be provided for out of the profits of`
  line `the company or out of the companys securities premium account, before such shares are redeemed.`
  line
  line `(ii) in a case not falling under sub-clause (i) above, the premium, if any, payable on redemption`
  line `shall be provided for out of the profits of the company or out of the company's securities premium`
  line `account, before such shares are redeemed.`
  line
  line `(3) Where a company is not in a position to redeem any preference shares or to pay dividend, if any,`
  line `on such shares in accordance with the terms of issue (such shares hereinafter referred to as unredeemed`
  line `preference shares), it may, with the consent of the holders of three-fourths in value of such preference`
  line `shares and with the approval of the Tribunal on a petition made by it in this behalf, issue further`
  line `redeemable preference shares equal to the amount due, including the dividend thereon, in respect of the`
  line `unredeemed preference shares, and on the issue of such further redeemable preference shares, the`
  line `unredeemed preference shares shall be deemed to have been redeemed:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Tribunal shall, while giving approval under this sub-section, order the redemption`
  line `forthwith of preference shares held by such persons who have not consented to the issue of further`
  line `redeemable preference shares.`
  line
  line `Explanation.-- For the removal of doubts, it is hereby declared that the issue of further redeemable`
  line `preference shares or the redemption of preference shares under this section shall not be deemed to be an`
  line `increase or, as the case may be, a reduction, in the share capital of the company.`
  line
  line `(4) The capital redemption reserve account may, notwithstanding anything in this section, be applied`
  line `by the company, in paying up unissued shares of the company to be issued to members of the company as`
  line `fully paid bonus shares.`
  line
  line `Explanation.-- For the purposes of sub-section (2), the term infrastructure projects means the`
  line `infrastructure projects specified in Schedule VI.`
obj_root_law_sections_55_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_56:
  sectionId (1246)
  sectionNo (56)
  orderNo 58
  title `Transfer and transmission of securities.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_56_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 29 of 2020, s. 9, for sub-section (6) (w.e.f. 21-12-2020).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=1246&sectionno=56&orderno=58&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_56_content:
  string
  line `(1) A company shall not register a transfer of`
  line `securities of the company, or the interest of a member in the company in the case of a company having no`
  line `share capital, other than the transfer between persons both of whose names are entered as holders of`
  line `beneficial interest in the records of a depository, unless a proper instrument of transfer, in such form as`
  line `may be prescribed, duly stamped, dated and executed by or on behalf of the transferor and the transferee`
  line `and specifying the name, address and occupation, if any, of the transferee has been delivered to the`
  line `company by the transferor or the transferee within a period of sixty days from the date of execution, along`
  line `with the certificate relating to the securities, or if no such certificate is in existence, along with the letter`
  line `of allotment of securities:`
  line
  line `Provided that where the instrument of transfer has been lost or the instrument of transfer has not been`
  line `delivered within the prescribed period, the company may register the transfer on such terms as to`
  line `indemnity as the Board may think fit.`
  line
  line `(2) Nothing in sub-section (1) shall prejudice the power of the company to register, on receipt of an`
  line `intimation of transmission of any right to securities by operation of law from any person to whom such`
  line `right has been transmitted.`
  line
  line `(3) Where an application is made by the transferor alone and relates to partly paid shares, the transfer`
  line `shall not be registered, unless the company gives the notice of the application, in such manner as may be`
  line `prescribed, to the transferee and the transferee gives no objection to the transfer within two weeks from`
  line `the receipt of notice.`
  line
  line `(4) Every company shall, unless prohibited by any provision of law or any order of Court, Tribunal or`
  line `other authority, deliver the certificates of all securities allotted, transferred or transmitted--`
  line
  line `(a) within a period of two months from the date of incorporation, in the case of subscribers to the`
  line memorandum;
  line
  line `(b) within a period of two months from the date of allotment, in the case of any allotment of any`
  line `of its shares;`
  line
  line `(c) within a period of one month from the date of receipt by the company of the instrument of`
  line `transfer under sub-section (1) or, as the case may be, of the intimation of transmission under`
  line `sub-section (2), in the case of a transfer or transmission of securities;`
  line
  line `(d) within a period of six months from the date of allotment in the case of any allotment of`
  line `debenture:`
  line
  line `Provided that where the securities are dealt with in a depository, the company shall intimate the`
  line `details of allotment of securities to depository immediately on allotment of such securities.`
  line
  line `(5) The transfer of any security or other interest of a deceased person in a company made by his legal`
  line `representative shall, even if the legal representative is not a holder thereof, be valid as if he had been the`
  line `holder at the time of the execution of the instrument of transfer.`
  line
  line ^1
  line `[(6) Where any default is made in complying with the provisions of sub-sections (1) to (5), the`
  line `company and every officer of the company who is in default shall be liable to a penalty of fifty thousand`
  line rupees.]
  line
  line `(7) Without prejudice to any liability under the Depositories Act, 1996 (22 of 1996), where any`
  line `depository or depository participant, with an intention to defraud a person, has transferred shares, it shall`
  line `be liable under section 447.`
obj_root_law_sections_57:
  sectionId (1247)
  sectionNo (57)
  orderNo 59
  title `Punishment for personation of shareholder.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_57_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_57_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=1247&sectionno=57&orderno=59&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_57_content:
  string
  line `If any person deceitfully personates as an owner`
  line `of any security or interest in a company, or of any share warrant or coupon issued in pursuance of this`
  line `Act, and thereby obtains or attempts to obtain any such security or interest or any such share warrant or`
  line `coupon, or receives or attempts to receive any money due to any such owner, he shall be punishable with`
  line `imprisonment for a term which shall not be less than one year but which may extend to three years and`
  line `with fine which shall not be less than one lakh rupees but which may extend to five lakh rupees.`
obj_root_law_sections_57_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_58:
  sectionId (1248)
  sectionNo (58)
  orderNo 60
  title `Refusal of registration and appeal against refusal.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_58_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_58_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=1248&sectionno=58&orderno=60&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_58_content:
  string
  line `(1) If a private company limited by shares`
  line `refuses, whether in pursuance of any power of the company under its articles or otherwise, to register the`
  line `transfer of, or the transmission by operation of law of the right to, any securities or interest of a member`
  line `in the company, it shall within a period of thirty days from the date on which the instrument of transfer, or`
  line `the intimation of such transmission, as the case may be, was delivered to the company, send notice of the`
  line `refusal to the transferor and the transferee or to the person giving intimation of such transmission, as the`
  line `case may be, giving reasons for such refusal.`
  line
  line `(2) Without prejudice to sub-section (1), the securities or other interest of any member in a public`
  line `company shall be freely transferable:`
  line
  line `Provided that any contract or arrangement between two or more persons in respect of transfer of`
  line `securities shall be enforceable as a contract.`
  line
  line `(3) The transferee may appeal to the Tribunal against the refusal within a period of thirty days from`
  line `the date of receipt of the notice or in case no notice has been sent by the company, within a period of sixty`
  line `days from the date on which the instrument of transfer or the intimation of transmission, as the case may`
  line `be, was delivered to the company.`
  line
  line `(4) If a public company without sufficient cause refuses to register the transfer of securities within a`
  line `period of thirty days from the date on which the instrument of transfer or the intimation of transmission,`
  line `as the case may be, is delivered to the company, the transferee may, within a period of sixty days of such`
  line `refusal or where no intimation has been received from the company, within ninety days of the delivery of`
  line `the instrument of transfer or intimation of transmission, appeal to the Tribunal.`
  line
  line `(5) The Tribunal, while dealing with an appeal made under sub-section (3) or sub-section (4), may,`
  line `after hearing the parties, either dismiss the appeal, or by order--`
  line
  line `(a) direct that the transfer or transmission shall be registered by the company and the company`
  line `shall comply with such order within a period of ten days of the receipt of the order; or`
  line
  line `(b) direct rectification of the register and also direct the company to pay damages, if any,`
  line `sustained by any party aggrieved.`
  line
  line `(6) If a person contravenes the order of the Tribunal under this section, he shall be punishable with`
  line `imprisonment for a term which shall not be less than one year but which may extend to three years and`
  line `with fine which shall not be less than one lakh rupees but which may extend to five lakh rupees.`
obj_root_law_sections_58_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_59:
  sectionId (1249)
  sectionNo (59)
  orderNo 61
  title `Rectification of register of members.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_59_content
  footnotes `1. Sub-section (5) omitted by Act 29 of 2020, s. 10 (w.e.f. 21-12-2020).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=1249&sectionno=59&orderno=61&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_59_content:
  string
  line `(1) If the name of any person is, without sufficient`
  line `cause, entered in the register of members of a company, or after having been entered in the register, is,`
  line `without sufficient cause, omitted there from, or if a default is made, or unnecessary delay takes place in`
  line `entering in the register, the fact of any person having become or ceased to be a member, the person`
  line `aggrieved, or any member of the company, or the company may appeal in such form as may be`
  line `prescribed, to the Tribunal, or to a competent court outside India, specified by the Central Government by notification, in respect of foreign members or debenture holders residing outside India, for rectification of`
  line `the register.`
  line
  line `(2) The Tribunal may, after hearing the parties to the appeal under sub-section (1) by order, either`
  line `dismiss the appeal or direct that the transfer or transmission shall be registered by the company within a`
  line `period of ten days of the receipt of the order or direct rectification of the records of the depository or the`
  line `register and in the latter case, direct the company to pay damages, if any, sustained by the party`
  line aggrieved.
  line
  line `(3) The provisions of this section shall not restrict the right of a holder of securities, to transfer such`
  line `securities and any person acquiring such securities shall be entitled to voting rights unless the voting`
  line `rights have been suspended by an order of the Tribunal.`
  line
  line `(4) Where the transfer of securities is in contravention of any of the provisions of the Securities`
  line `Contracts (Regulation) Act, 1956 (42 of 1956), the Securities and Exchange Board of India Act, 1992`
  line `(15 of 1992) or this Act or any other law for the time being in force, the Tribunal may, on an application`
  line `made by the depository, company, depository participant, the holder of the securities or the Securities and`
  line `Exchange Board, direct any company or a depository to set right the contravention and rectify its register`
  line `or records concerned.`
  line
  line `^1* * * * *.`
obj_root_law_sections_60:
  sectionId (1250)
  sectionNo (60)
  orderNo 62
  title `Publication of authorised, subscribed and paid-up capital.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_60_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_60_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=1250&sectionno=60&orderno=62&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_60_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where any notice,`
  line `advertisement or other official publication, or any business letter, billhead or letter paper of a company`
  line `contains a statement of the amount of the authorised capital of the company, such notice, advertisement or`
  line `other official publication, or such letter, billhead or letter paper shall also contain a statement, in an`
  line `equally prominent position and in equally conspicuous characters, of the amount of the capital which has`
  line `been subscribed and the amount paid-up.`
  line
  line `(2) If any default is made in complying with the requirements of sub-section (1), the company shall`
  line `be liable to pay a penalty of ten thousand rupees and every officer of the company who is in default shall`
  line `be liable to pay a penalty of five thousand rupees, for each default.`
obj_root_law_sections_60_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_61:
  sectionId (1251)
  sectionNo (61)
  orderNo 63
  title `Power of limited company to alter its share capital.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_61_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_61_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=1251&sectionno=61&orderno=63&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_61_content:
  string
  line `(1) A limited company having a share`
  line `capital may, if so authorised by its articles, alter its memorandum in its general meeting to--`
  line
  line `(a) increase its authorised share capital by such amount as it thinks expedient;`
  line
  line `(b) consolidate and divide all or any of its share capital into shares of a larger amount than its`
  line `existing shares:`
  line
  line `Provided that no consolidation and division which results in changes in the voting percentage of`
  line `shareholders shall take effect unless it is approved by the Tribunal on an application made in the`
  line `prescribed manner;`
  line
  line `(c) convert all or any of its fully paid-up shares into stock, and reconvert that stock into fully`
  line `paid-up shares of any denomination;`
  line
  line `(d) sub-divide its shares, or any of them, into shares of smaller amount than is fixed by the`
  line `memorandum, so, however, that in the sub-division the proportion between the amount paid and the`
  line `amount, if any, unpaid on each reduced share shall be the same as it was in the case of the share from`
  line `which the reduced share is derived;`
  line
  line `(e) cancel shares which, at the date of the passing of the resolution in that behalf, have not been`
  line `taken or agreed to be taken by any person, and diminish the amount of its share capital by the amount`
  line `of the shares so cancelled.`
  line
  line `(2) The cancellation of shares under sub-section (1) shall not be deemed to be a reduction of share`
  line capital.
obj_root_law_sections_61_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_62:
  sectionId (1252)
  sectionNo (62)
  orderNo 64
  title `Further issue of share capital.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_62_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_62_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=1252&sectionno=62&orderno=64&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_62_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where at any time, a company having a share capital proposes`
  line `to increase its subscribed capital by the issue of further shares, such shares shall be offered--`
  line
  line `(a) to persons who, at the date of the offer, are holders of equity shares of the company in`
  line `proportion, as nearly as circumstances admit, to the paid-up share capital on those shares by sending a`
  line `letter of offer subject to the following conditions, namely:--`
  line
  line `(i) the offer shall be made by notice specifying the number of shares offered and limiting a time`
  line `not being less than fifteen days ^1[or such lesser number of days as may be prescribed] and not`
  line `exceeding thirty days from the date of the offer within which the offer, if not accepted, shall be`
  line `deemed to have been declined;`
  line
  line `(ii) unless the articles of the company otherwise provide, the offer aforesaid shall be deemed`
  line `to include a right exercisable by the person concerned to renounce the shares offered to him or any`
  line `of them in favour of any other person; and the notice referred to in clause (i) shall contain a`
  line `statement of this right;`
  line
  line `(iii) after the expiry of the time specified in the notice aforesaid, or on receipt of earlier`
  line `intimation from the person to whom such notice is given that he declines to accept the shares`
  line `offered, the Board of Directors may dispose of them in such manner which is not disadvantageous to the share holders and the company;`
  line
  line `(b) to employees under a scheme of employees’ stock option, subject to special resolution passed`
  line `by company and subject to such conditions as may be prescribed; or`
  line
  line `(c) to any persons, if it is authorised by a special resolution, whether or not those persons include`
  line `the persons referred to in clause (a) or clause (b), either for cash or for a consideration other than cash,`
  line `if the price of such shares is determined by the valuation report ^2[of a registered valuer, subject to the`
  line `compliance with the applicable provisions of Chapter III and any other conditions as may be`
  line prescribed].
  line
  line `^3[(2) The notice referred to in sub-clause (i) of clause (a) of sub-section (1) shall be dispatched through`
  line `registered post or speed post or through electronic mode or courier or any other mode having proof of`
  line `delivery to all the existing shareholders at least three days before the opening of the issue.]`
  line
  line `(3) Nothing in this section shall apply to the increase of the subscribed capital of a company caused by`
  line `the exercise of an option as a term attached to the debentures issued or loan raised by the company to`
  line `convert such debentures or loans into shares in the company:`
  line
  line `Provided that the terms of issue of such debentures or loan containing such an option have been`
  line `approved before the issue of such debentures or the raising of loan by a special resolution passed by the`
  line `company in general meeting.`
  line
  line `(4) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (3), where any debentures have been issued, or`
  line `loan has been obtained from any Government by a company, and if that Government considers it necessary`
  line `in the public interest so to do, it may, by order, direct that such debentures or loans or any part thereof shall`
  line `be converted into shares in the company on such terms and conditions as appear to the Government to be`
  line `reasonable in the circumstances of the case even if terms of the issue of such debentures or the raising of`
  line `such loans do not include a term for providing for an option for such conversion:`
  line
  line `Provided that where the terms and conditions of such conversion are not acceptable to the company, it`
  line `may, within sixty days from the date of communication of such order, appeal to the Tribunal which shall`
  line `after hearing the company and the Government pass such order as it deems fit.`
  line
  line `(5) In determining the terms and conditions of conversion under sub-section (4), the Government shall`
  line `have due regard to the financial position of the company, the terms of issue of debentures or loans, as the`
  line `case may be, the rate of interest payable on such debentures or loans and such other matters as it may`
  line `consider necessary.`
  line
  line `(6) Where the Government has, by an order made under sub-section (4), directed that any debenture or`
  line `loan or any part thereof shall be converted into shares in a company and where no appeal has been preferred`
  line `to the Tribunal under sub-section (4) or where such appeal has been dismissed, the memorandum of such`
  line `company shall, where such order has the effect of increasing the authorised share capital of the company,`
  line `stand altered and the authorised share capital of such company shall stand increased by an amount equal to`
  line `the amount of the value of shares which such debentures or loans or part thereof has been converted into.`
obj_root_law_sections_62_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 29 of 2020, s. 11 (w.e.f. 22-1-2021).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 1 of 2018, s. 14, for "of a registered valuer subject to such conditions as may be prescribed" (w.e.f. 9-2-2018).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by s. 14, ibid., for sub-section (2) (w.e.f. 9-2-2018).`
obj_root_law_sections_63:
  sectionId (1253)
  sectionNo (63)
  orderNo 65
  title `Issue of bonus shares`
  content obj_root_law_sections_63_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_63_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=1253&sectionno=63&orderno=65&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_63_content:
  string
  line `(1) A company may issue fully paid-up bonus shares to its members, in`
  line `any manner whatsoever, out of--`
  line
  line `(i) its free reserves;`
  line
  line `(ii) the securities premium account; or`
  line
  line `(iii) the capital redemption reserve account:`
  line
  line `Provided that no issue of bonus shares shall be made by capitalising reserves created by the`
  line `revaluation of assets.`
  line
  line `(2) No company shall capitalise its profits or reserves for the purpose of issuing fully paid-up bonus`
  line `shares under sub-section (1), unless--`
  line
  line `(a) it is authorised by its articles;`
  line
  line `(b) it has, on the recommendation of the Board, been authorised in the general meeting of the`
  line company;
  line
  line `(c) it has not defaulted in payment of interest or principal in respect of fixed deposits or debt`
  line `securities issued by it;`
  line
  line `(d) it has not defaulted in respect of the payment of statutory dues of the employees, such as,`
  line `contribution to provident fund, gratuity and bonus;`
  line
  line `(e) the partly paid-up shares, if any outstanding on the date of allotment, are made fully paid-up;`
  line
  line `(f) it complies with such conditions as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(3) The bonus shares shall not be issued in lieu of dividend.`
obj_root_law_sections_63_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_64:
  sectionId (1254)
  sectionNo (64)
  orderNo 66
  title `Notice to be given to Registrar for alteration of share capital.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_64_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_64_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=1254&sectionno=64&orderno=66&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_64_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where--`
  line
  line `(a) a company alters its share capital in any manner specified in sub-section (1) of section 61;`
  line
  line `(b) an order made by the Government under sub-section (4) read with sub-section (6) of`
  line `section 62 has the effect of increasing authorised capital of a company; or`
  line
  line `(c) a company redeems any redeemable preference shares,`
  line
  line `the company shall file a notice in the prescribed form with the Registrar within a period of thirty days of`
  line `such alteration or increase or redemption, as the case may be, along with an altered memorandum.`
  line
  line `^1[(2) where any company fails to comply with the provisions of sub-section (1), such company rupees`
  line `and every officer who is in default shall be liable to a penalty of ^2[five hundred rupees] for each day`
  line `during which such default continues, ^3[subject to a maximum of five lakh rupees in case of a company`
  line `and one lakh rupees in case of an officer who is in default].]`
obj_root_law_sections_64_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 22 of 2019, s. 10, for sub-section (2) (w.e.f. 2-11-2018).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by s. 12, ibid., for "one thousand rupees" (w.e.f. 21-12-2020).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by s. 12, ibid., for "or five lakh rupees whichever is less" (w.e.f. 21-12-2020).`
obj_root_law_sections_65:
  sectionId (1255)
  sectionNo (65)
  orderNo 67
  title `Unlimited company to provide for reserve share capital on conversion into limited company.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_65_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_65_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=1255&sectionno=65&orderno=67&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_65_content:
  string
  line `An unlimited company having a share capital may, by a resolution for registration as a`
  line `limited company under this Act, do either or both of the following things, namely--`
  line
  line `(a) increase the nominal amount of its share capital by increasing the nominal amount of each of`
  line `its shares, subject to the condition that no part of the increased capital shall be capable of being called`
  line `up except in the event and for the purposes of the company being wound up;`
  line
  line `(b) provide that a specified portion of its uncalled share capital shall not be capable of being`
  line `called up except in the event and for the purposes of the company being wound up.`
obj_root_law_sections_65_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_66:
  sectionId (1256)
  sectionNo (66)
  orderNo 68
  title `Reduction of share capital.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_66_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_66_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=1256&sectionno=66&orderno=68&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_66_content:
  string
  line `(1) Subject to confirmation by the Tribunal on an application by`
  line `the company, a company limited by shares or limited by guarantee and having a share capital may, by a`
  line `special resolution, reduce the share capital in any manner and in particular, may--`
  line
  line `(a) extinguish or reduce the liability on any of its shares in respect of the share capital not`
  line `paid-up; or`
  line
  line `(b) either with or without extinguishing or reducing liability on any of its shares,--`
  line
  line `(i) cancel any paid-up share capital which is lost or is unrepresented by available assets; or`
  line
  line `(ii) pay off any paid-up share capital which is in excess of the wants of the company,`
  line
  line `alter its memorandum by reducing the amount of its share capital and of its shares accordingly:`
  line
  line `Provided that no such reduction shall be made if the company is in arrears in the repayment of any`
  line `deposits accepted by it, either before or after the commencement of this Act, or the interest payable`
  line thereon.
  line
  line `(2) The Tribunal shall give notice of every application made to it under sub-section (1) to the Central`
  line `Government, Registrar and to the Securities and Exchange Board, in the case of listed companies, and the`
  line `creditors of the company and shall take into consideration the representations, if any, made to it by that`
  line `Government, Registrar, the Securities and Exchange Board and the creditors within a period of three`
  line `months from the date of receipt of the notice:`
  line
  line `Provided that where no representation has been received from the Central Government, Registrar, the`
  line `Securities and Exchange Board or the creditors within the said period, it shall be presumed that they have`
  line `no objection to the reduction.`
  line
  line `(3) The Tribunal may, if it is satisfied that the debt or claim of every creditor of the company has been`
  line `discharged or determined or has been secured or his consent is obtained, make an order confirming the`
  line `reduction of share capital on such terms and conditions as it deems fit:`
  line
  line `Provided that no application for reduction of share capital shall be sanctioned by the Tribunal unless`
  line `the accounting treatment, proposed by the company for such reduction is in conformity with the`
  line `accounting standards specified in section 133 or any other provision of this Act and a certificate to that`
  line `effect by the company's auditor has been filed with the Tribunal.`
  line
  line `(4) The order of confirmation of the reduction of share capital by the Tribunal under sub-section (3)`
  line `shall be published by the company in such manner as the Tribunal may direct.`
  line
  line `(5) The company shall deliver a certified copy of the order of the Tribunal under sub-section (3) and`
  line `of a minute approved by the Tribunal showing--`
  line
  line `(a) the amount of share capital;`
  line
  line `(b) the number of shares into which it is to be divided;`
  line
  line `(c) the amount of each share; and`
  line
  line `(d) the amount, if any, at the date of registration deemed to be paid-up on each share,`
  line
  line `to the Registrar within thirty days of the receipt of the copy of the order, who shall register the same and`
  line `issue a certificate to that effect.`
  line
  line `(6) Nothing in this section shall apply to buy-back of its own securities by a company under`
  line `section 68.`
  line
  line `(7) A member of the company, past or present, shall not be liable to any call or contribution in respect`
  line `of any share held by him exceeding the amount of difference, if any, between the amount paid on the`
  line `share, or reduced amount, if any, which is to be deemed to have been paid thereon, as the case may be,`
  line `and the amount of the share as fixed by the order of reduction.`
  line
  line `(8) Where the name of any creditor entitled to object to the reduction of share capital under this`
  line `section is, by reason of his ignorance of the proceedings for reduction or of their nature and effect with respect to his debt or claim, not entered on the list of creditors, and after such reduction, the company`
  line `^1[commits a default, within the meaning of section 6 of the Insolvency and Bankruptcy Code, 2016`
  line `(31 of 2016), in respect of the amount of his debt or claim],--`
  line
  line `(a) every person, who was a member of the company on the date of the registration of the order`
  line `for reduction by the Registrar, shall be liable to contribute to the payment of that debt or claim, an`
  line `amount not exceeding the amount which he would have been liable to contribute if the company had`
  line `commenced winding up on the day immediately before the said date; and`
  line
  line `(b) if the company is wound up, the Tribunal may, on the application of any such creditor and`
  line `proof of his ignorance as aforesaid, if it thinks fit, settle a list of persons so liable to contribute, and`
  line `make and enforce calls and orders on the contributories settled on the list, as if they were ordinary`
  line `contributories in a winding up.`
  line
  line `(9) Nothing in sub-section (8) shall affect the rights of the contributories among themselves.`
  line
  line `(10) If any officer of the company--`
  line
  line `(a) knowingly conceals the name of any creditor entitled to object to the reduction;`
  line
  line `(b) knowingly misrepresents the nature or amount of the debt or claim of any creditor; or`
  line
  line `(c) abets or is privy to any such concealment or misrepresentation as aforesaid,`
  line
  line `he shall be liable under section 447.`
  line
  line `^2* * * * *.`
obj_root_law_sections_66_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 31 of 2016, s. 255 and the Eleventh Schedule, for "is unable, within the meaning of sub-section (2) of section`
  line `271, to pay the amount of his debt or claim," (w.e.f. 15-11-2016).`
  line
  line `2. Sub-section (11) omitted by Act 29 of 2020, s. 13 (w.e.f. 21-12-2020).`
obj_root_law_sections_67:
  sectionId (1257)
  sectionNo (67)
  orderNo 69
  title `Restrictions on purchase by company or giving of loans by it for purchase of its shares.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_67_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_67_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=1257&sectionno=67&orderno=69&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_67_content:
  string
  line `(1) No company limited by shares or by guarantee and having a share capital shall have power to buy its own`
  line `shares unless the consequent reduction of share capital is effected under the provisions of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) No public company shall give, whether directly or indirectly and whether by means of a loan,`
  line `guarantee, the provision of security or otherwise, any financial assistance for the purpose of, or in`
  line `connection with, a purchase or subscription made or to be made, by any person of or for any shares in the`
  line `company or in its holding company.`
  line
  line `(3) Nothing in sub-section (2) shall apply to--`
  line
  line `(a) the lending of money by a banking company in the ordinary course of its business;`
  line
  line `(b) the provision by a company of money in accordance with any scheme approved by company`
  line `through special resolution and in accordance with such requirements as may be prescribed, for the`
  line `purchase of, or subscription for, fully paid-up shares in the company or its holding company, if the`
  line `purchase of, or the subscription for, the shares held by trustees for the benefit of the employees or`
  line `such shares held by the employee of the company;`
  line
  line `(c) the giving of loans by a company to persons in the employment of the company other than its`
  line `directors or key managerial personnel, for an amount not exceeding their salary or wages for a period`
  line `of six months with a view to enabling them to purchase or subscribe for fully paid-up shares in the`
  line `company or its holding company to be held by them by way of beneficial ownership:`
  line
  line `Provided that disclosures in respect of voting rights not exercised directly by the employees in respect`
  line `of shares to which the scheme relates shall be made in the Board's report in such manner as may be`
  line prescribed.
  line
  line `(4) Nothing in this section shall affect the right of a company to redeem any preference shares issued`
  line `by it under this Act or under any previous company law.`
  line
  line `(5) If a company contravenes the provisions of this section, it shall be punishable with fine which`
  line `shall not be less than one lakh rupees but which may extend to twenty-five lakh rupees and every officer`
  line `of the company who is in default shall be punishable with imprisonment for a term which may extend to`
  line `three years and with fine which shall not be less than one lakh rupees but which may extend to twentyfive`
  line `lakh rupees.`
obj_root_law_sections_67_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_68:
  sectionId (1258)
  sectionNo (68)
  orderNo 70
  title `Power of company to purchase its own securities.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_68_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_68_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=1258&sectionno=68&orderno=70&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_68_content:
  string
  line `(1) Notwithstanding anything contained in`
  line `this Act, but subject to the provisions of sub-section (2), a company may purchase its own shares or other`
  line `specified securities (hereinafter referred to as buy-back) out of--`
  line
  line `(a) its free reserves;`
  line
  line `(b) the securities premium account; or`
  line
  line `(c) the proceeds of the issue of any shares or other specified securities:`
  line
  line `Provided that no buy-back of any kind of shares or other specified securities shall be made out of the`
  line `proceeds of an earlier issue of the same kind of shares or same kind of other specified securities.`
  line
  line `(2) No company shall purchase its own shares or other specified securities under sub-section (1),`
  line unless--
  line
  line `(a) the buy-back is authorised by its articles;`
  line
  line `(b) a special resolution has been passed at a general meeting of the company authorising the`
  line `buy-back:`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing contained in this clause shall apply to a case where--`
  line
  line `(i) the buy-back is, ten per cent. or less of the total paid-up equity capital and free reserves of the`
  line `company; and`
  line
  line `(ii) such buy-back has been authorised by the Board by means of a resolution passed at its`
  line meeting;
  line
  line `(c) the buy-back is twenty-five per cent. or less of the aggregate of paid-up capital and free`
  line `reserves of the company:`
  line
  line `Provided that in respect of the buy-back of equity shares in any financial year, the reference to`
  line `twenty-five per cent. in this clause shall be construed with respect to its total paid-up equity capital in that`
  line `financial year;`
  line
  line `(d) the ratio of the aggregate of secured and unsecured debts owed by the company after buy-back`
  line `is not more than twice the paid-up capital and its free reserves:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Central Government may, by order, notify a higher ratio of the debt to capital`
  line `and free reserves for a class or classes of companies;`
  line
  line `(e) all the shares or other specified securities for buy-back are fully paid-up;`
  line
  line `(f) the buy-back of the shares or other specified securities listed on any recognized stock`
  line `exchange is in accordance with the regulations made by the Securities and Exchange Board in this`
  line `behalf; and`
  line
  line `(g) the buy-back in respect of shares or other specified securities other than those specified in`
  line `clause (f) is in accordance with such rules as may be prescribed:`
  line
  line `Provided that no offer of buy-back under this sub-section shall be made within a period of one year`
  line `reckoned from the date of the closure of the preceding offer of buy-back, if any.`
  line
  line `(3) The notice of the meeting at which the special resolution is proposed to be passed under clause (b)`
  line `of sub-section (2) shall be accompanied by an explanatory statement stating--`
  line
  line `(a) a full and complete disclosure of all material facts;`
  line
  line `(b) the necessity for the buy-back;`
  line
  line `(c) the class of shares or securities intended to be purchased under the buy-back;`
  line
  line `(d) the amount to be invested under the buy-back; and`
  line
  line `(e) the time-limit for completion of buy-back.`
  line
  line `(4) Every buy-back shall be completed within a period of one year from the date of passing of the`
  line `special resolution, or as the case may be, the resolution passed by the Board under clause (b) of`
  line `sub-section (2).`
  line
  line `(5) The buy-back under sub-section (1) may be--`
  line
  line `(a) from the existing shareholders or security holders on a proportionate basis;`
  line
  line `(b) from the open market;`
  line
  line `(c) by purchasing the securities issued to employees of the company pursuant to a scheme of`
  line `stock option or sweat equity.`
  line
  line `(6) Where a company proposes to buy-back its own shares or other specified securities under this`
  line `section in pursuance of a special resolution under clause (b) of sub-section (2) or a resolution under item`
  line `(ii) of the proviso thereto, it shall, before making such buy-back, file with the Registrar and the Securities`
  line `and Exchange Board, a declaration of solvency signed by atleast two directors of the company, one of`
  line `whom shall be the managing director, if any, in such form as may be prescribed and verified by an`
  line `affidavit to the effect that the Board of Directors of the company has made a full inquiry into the affairs of`
  line `the company as a result of which they have formed an opinion that it is capable of meeting its liabilities`
  line `and will not be rendered insolvent within a period of one year from the date of declaration adopted by the`
  line `Board:`
  line
  line `Provided that no declaration of solvency shall be filed with the Securities and Exchange Board by a`
  line `company whose shares are not listed on any recognised stock exchange.`
  line
  line `(7) Where a company buys back its own shares or other specified securities, it shall extinguish and`
  line `physically destroy the shares or securities so bought back within seven days of the last date of completion`
  line `of buy-back.`
  line
  line `(8) Where a company completes a buy-back of its shares or other specified securities under this`
  line `section, it shall not make a further issue of the same kind of shares or other securities including allotment`
  line `of new shares under clause (a) of sub-section (1) of section 62 or other specified securities within a period`
  line `of six months except by way of a bonus issue or in the discharge of subsisting obligations such as`
  line `conversion of warrants, stock option schemes, sweat equity or conversion of preference shares or`
  line `debentures into equity shares.`
  line
  line `(9) Where a company buys back its shares or other specified securities under this section, it shall`
  line `maintain a register of the shares or securities so bought, the consideration paid for the shares or securities`
  line `bought back, the date of cancellation of shares or securities, the date of extinguishing and physically`
  line `destroying the shares or securities and such other particulars as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(10) A company shall, after the completion of the buy-back under this section, file with the Registrar`
  line `and the Securities and Exchange Board a return containing such particulars relating to the buy-back`
  line `within thirty days of such completion, as may be prescribed:`
  line
  line `Provided that no return shall be filed with the Securities and Exchange Board by a company whose`
  line `shares are not listed on any recognised stock exchange.`
  line
  line `(11) If a company makes any default in complying with the provisions of this section or any`
  line `regulation made by the Securities and Exchange Board, for the purposes of clause (f) of sub-section (2),`
  line `the company shall be punishable with fine which shall not be less than one lakh rupees but which may`
  line `extend to three lakh rupees and every officer of the company who is in default shall be punishable ^1***`
  line `with fine which shall not be less than one lakh rupees but which may extend to ^2`
  line `[three lakh rupees].`
  line
  line `Explanation I.--For the purposes of this section and section 70, "specified securities" includes`
  line `employees' stock option or other securities as may be notified by the Central Government from time to`
  line time.
  line
  line `Explanation II.--For the purposes of this section, "free reserves" includes securities premium`
  line account.
obj_root_law_sections_68_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. The words "with imprisonment for a term which may extend to three years or" omitted by Act 29 of 2020, s. 14 (w.e.f. 21-12-`
  line `2020).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by s. 14, ibid., for "three lakh rupees, or with both" (w.e.f. 21-12-2020).`
obj_root_law_sections_69:
  sectionId (1259)
  sectionNo (69)
  orderNo 71
  title `Transfer of certain sums to capital redemption reserve account.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_69_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_69_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=1259&sectionno=69&orderno=71&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_69_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where a company`
  line `purchases its own shares out of free reserves or securities premium account, a sum equal to the nominal`
  line `value of the shares so purchased shall be transferred to the capital redemption reserve account and details`
  line `of such transfer shall be disclosed in the balance sheet.`
  line
  line `(2) The capital redemption reserve account may be applied by the company, in paying up unissued`
  line `shares of the company to be issued to members of the company as fully paid bonus shares.`
obj_root_law_sections_69_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_70:
  sectionId (1260)
  sectionNo (70)
  orderNo 72
  title `Prohibition for buy-back in certain circumstances.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_70_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_70_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=1260&sectionno=70&orderno=72&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_70_content:
  string
  line `(1) No company shall directly or`
  line `indirectly purchase its own shares or other specified securities--`
  line
  line `(a) through any subsidiary company including its own subsidiary companies;`
  line
  line `(b) through any investment company or group of investment companies; or`
  line
  line `(c) if a default, is made by the company, in the repayment of deposits accepted either before or`
  line `after the commencement of this Act, interest payment thereon, redemption of debentures or`
  line `preference shares or payment of dividend to any shareholder, or repayment of any term loan or`
  line `interest payable thereon to any financial institution or banking company:`
  line
  line `Provided that the buy-back is not prohibited, if the default is remedied and a period of three years`
  line `has lapsed after such default ceased to subsist.`
  line
  line `(2) No company shall, directly or indirectly, purchase its own shares or other specified securities in`
  line `case such company has not complied with the provisions of sections 92, 123, 127 and section 129.`
obj_root_law_sections_70_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_71:
  sectionId (1261)
  sectionNo (71)
  orderNo 73
  title Debentures
  content obj_root_law_sections_71_content
  footnotes `1. Sub-section (11) omitted by Act 29 of 2020, s. 15 (w.e.f. 21-12-2020).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=1261&sectionno=71&orderno=73&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_71_content:
  string
  line `(1) A company may issue debentures with an option to convert such debentures`
  line `into shares, either wholly or partly at the time of redemption:`
  line
  line `Provided that the issue of debentures with an option to convert such debentures into shares, wholly or`
  line `partly, shall be approved by a special resolution passed at a general meeting.`
  line
  line `(2) No company shall issue any debentures carrying any voting rights.`
  line
  line `(3) Secured debentures may be issued by a company subject to such terms and conditions as may be`
  line prescribed.
  line
  line `(4) Where debentures are issued by a company under this section, the company shall create a`
  line `debenture redemption reserve account out of the profits of the company available for payment of dividend`
  line `and the amount credited to such account shall not be utilised by the company except for the redemption of`
  line debentures.
  line
  line `(5) No company shall issue a prospectus or make an offer or invitation to the public or to its`
  line `members exceeding five hundred for the subscription of its debentures, unless the company has, before`
  line `such issue or offer, appointed one or more debenture trustees and the conditions governing the`
  line `appointment of such trustees shall be such as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(6) A debenture trustee shall take steps to protect the interests of the debenture-holders and redress`
  line `their grievances in accordance with such rules as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(7) Any provision contained in a trust deed for securing the issue of debentures, or in any contract`
  line `with the debenture-holders secured by a trust deed, shall be void in so far as it would have the effect of`
  line `exempting a trustee thereof from, or indemnifying him against, any liability for breach of trust, where he`
  line `fails to show the degree of care and due diligence required of him as a trustee, having regard to the`
  line `provisions of the trust deed conferring on him any power, authority or discretion:`
  line
  line `Provided that the liability of the debenture trustee shall be subject to such exemptions as may be`
  line `agreed upon by a majority of debenture-holders holding not less than three-fourths in value of the total`
  line `debentures at a meeting held for the purpose.`
  line
  line `(8) A company shall pay interest and redeem the debentures in accordance with the terms and`
  line `conditions of their issue.`
  line
  line `(9) Where at any time the debenture trustee comes to a conclusion that the assets of the company are`
  line `insufficient or are likely to become in sufficient to discharge the principal amount as and when it becomes`
  line `due, the debenture trustee may file a petition before the Tribunal and the Tribunal may, after hearing the`
  line `company and any other person interested in the matter, by order, impose such restrictions on the incurring`
  line `of any further liabilities by the company as the Tribunal may consider necessary in the interests of the`
  line debenture-holders.
  line
  line `(10) Where a company fails to redeem the debentures on the date of their maturity or fails to pay`
  line `interest on the debentures when it is due, the Tribunal may, on the application of any or all of the`
  line `debenture-holders, or debenture trustee and, after hearing the parties concerned, direct, by order, the`
  line `company to redeem the debentures forth with on payment of principal and interest due thereon.`
  line
  line `^1* * * * *`
  line
  line `(12) A contract with the company to take up and pay for any debentures of the company may be`
  line `enforced by a decree for specific performance.`
  line
  line `(13) The Central Government may prescribe the procedure, for securing the issue of debentures, the`
  line `form of debenture trust deed, the procedure for the debenture-holders to inspect the trust deed and to`
  line `obtain copies thereof, quantum of debenture redemption reserve required to be created and such other`
  line matters.
obj_root_law_sections_72:
  sectionId (1262)
  sectionNo (72)
  orderNo 74
  title `Power to nominate.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_72_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_72_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=1262&sectionno=72&orderno=74&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_72_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every holder of securities of a company may, at any time, nominate, in`
  line `the prescribed manner, any person to whom his securities shall vest in the event of his death.`
  line
  line `(2) Where the securities of a company are held by more than one person jointly, the joint holders may`
  line `together nominate, in the prescribed manner, any person to whom all the rights in the securities shall vest`
  line `in the event of death of all the joint holders.`
  line
  line `(3) Notwithstanding anything contained in any other law for the time being in force or in any`
  line `disposition, whether testamentary or otherwise, in respect of the securities of a company, where a`
  line `nomination made in the prescribed manner purports to confer on any person the right to vest the securities`
  line `of the company, the nominee shall, on the death of the holder of securities or, as the case may be, on the`
  line `death of the joint holders, become entitled to all the rights in the securities, of the holder or, as the case`
  line `may be, of all the joint holders, in relation to such securities, to the exclusion of all other persons, unless`
  line `the nomination is varied or cancelled in the prescribed manner.`
  line
  line `(4) Where the nominee is a minor, it shall be lawful for the holder of the securities, making the`
  line `nomination to appoint, in the prescribed manner, any person to become entitled to the securities of the`
  line `company, in the event of the death of the nominee during his minority.`
obj_root_law_sections_72_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_73:
  sectionId (1263)
  sectionNo (73)
  orderNo 75
  title `Prohibition on acceptance of deposits from public.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_73_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_73_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=1263&sectionno=73&orderno=75&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_73_content:
  string
  line `(1) On and after the commencement of`
  line `this Act, no company shall invite, accept or renew deposits under this Act from the public except in a`
  line `manner provided under this Chapter:`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing in this sub-section shall apply to a banking company and non-banking financial`
  line `company as defined in the Reserve Bank of India Act, 1934 (2 of 1934) and to such other company as the`
  line `Central Government may, after consultation with the Reserve Bank of India, specify in this behalf.`
  line
  line `(2) A company may, subject to the passing of a resolution in general meeting and subject to such rules`
  line `as may be prescribed in consultation with the Reserve Bank of India, accept deposits from its members on`
  line `such terms and conditions, including the provision of security, if any, or for the repayment of such`
  line `deposits with interest, as may be agreed upon between the company and its members, subject to the`
  line `fulfilment of the following conditions, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) issuance of a circular to its members including therein a statement showing the financial`
  line `position of the company, the credit rating obtained, the total number of depositors and the amount due`
  line `towards deposits in respect of any previous deposits accepted by the company and such other`
  line `particulars in such form and in such manner as may be prescribed;`
  line
  line `(b) filing a copy of the circular along with such statement with the Registrar within thirty days`
  line `before the date of issue of the circular;`
  line
  line `^1[(c) depositing, on or before the thirtieth day of April each year, such sum which shall not be less`
  line `than twenty per cent. of the amount of its deposits maturing during the following financial year and`
  line `kept in a scheduled bank in a separate bank account to be called deposit repayment reserve account;]`
  line
  line `^2* * * * *`
  line
  line `(e) certifying that the company has not committed any default in the repayment of deposits`
  line `accepted either before or after the commencement of this Act or payment of interest on,`
  line `^3[such deposits and where a default had occurred, the company made good the default and a period of five`
  line `years had lapsed since the date of making good the default;] and`
  line
  line `(f) providing security, if any for the due repayment of the amount of deposit or the interest`
  line `thereon including the creation of such charge on the property or assets of the company:`
  line
  line `Provided that in case where a company does not secure the deposits or secures such deposits`
  line `partially, then, the deposits shall be termed as unsecured deposits and shall be so quoted in every`
  line `circular, form, advertisement or in any document related to invitation or acceptance of deposits.`
  line
  line `(3) Every deposit accepted by a company under sub-section (2) shall be repaid with interest in`
  line `accordance with the terms and conditions of the agreement referred to in that sub-section.`
  line
  line `(4) Where a company fails to repay the deposit or part thereof or any interest thereon under`
  line `sub-section (3), the depositor concerned may apply to the Tribunal for an order directing the company to`
  line `pay the sum due or for any loss or damage incurred by him as a result of such non-payment and for such`
  line `other orders as the Tribunal may deem fit.`
  line
  line `(5) The deposit repayment reserve account referred to in clause (c) of sub-section (2) shall not be used`
  line `by the company for any purpose other than repayment of deposits.`
obj_root_law_sections_73_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 1 of 2018, s. 15, for clause (c) (w.e.f. 15-8-2018).`
  line
  line `2. Clause (d) omitted by s. 15, ibid. (w.e.f. 15-8-2018).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by s. 15,ibid., for "such deposits;" (w.e.f. 15-8-2018)`
obj_root_law_sections_74:
  sectionId (1264)
  sectionNo (74)
  orderNo 76
  title `Repayment of deposits, etc., accepted before commencement of this Act.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_74_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 1 of 2018, s. 16, for clause (b) (w.e.f. 15-8-2018).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=1264&sectionno=74&orderno=76&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_74_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where in`
  line `respect of any deposit accepted by a company before the commencement of this Act, the amount of such`
  line `deposit or part thereof or any interest due thereon remains unpaid on such commencement or becomes`
  line `due at any time thereafter, the company shall`
  line
  line `(a) file, within a period of three months from such commencement or from the date on which`
  line `such payments, are due, with the Registrar a statement of all the deposits accepted by the company`
  line `and sums remaining unpaid on such amount with the interest payable thereon along with the`
  line `arrangements made for such repayment, notwithstanding anything contained in any other law for the`
  line `time being in force or under the terms and conditions subject to which the deposit was accepted or`
  line `any scheme framed under any law; and`
  line
  line `^1[(b) repay within one year from such commencement or from the date on which such payments are`
  line `due, whichever is earlier.`
  line
  line `Provided that renewal of any such deposits shall be done in accordance with the provisions of`
  line `Chapter V and the rules made thereunder.]`
  line
  line `(2) The Tribunal may on an application made by the company, after considering the financial`
  line `condition of the company, the amount of deposit or part thereof and the interest payable thereon and such`
  line `other matters, allow further time as considered reasonable to the company to repay the deposit.`
  line
  line `(3) If a company fails to repay the deposit or part thereof or any interest thereon within the time`
  line `specified in sub-section (1) or such further time as may be allowed by the Tribunal under sub-section (2),`
  line `the company shall, in addition to the payment of the amount of deposit or part thereof and the interest`
  line `due, be punishable with fine which shall not be less than one crore rupees but which may extend to ten`
  line `crore rupees and every officer of the company who is in default shall be punishable with imprisonment`
  line `which may extend to seven years or with fine which shall not be less than twenty-five lakh rupees but`
  line `which may extend to two crore rupees, or with both.`
obj_root_law_sections_75:
  sectionId (1265)
  sectionNo (75)
  orderNo 77
  title `Damages for fraud.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_75_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_75_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=1265&sectionno=75&orderno=77&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_75_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where a company fails to repay the deposit or part thereof or any`
  line `interest thereon referred to in section 74 within the time specified in sub-section (1) of that section or such`
  line `further time as may be allowed by the Tribunal under sub-section (2) of that section, and it is proved that`
  line `the deposits had been accepted with intent to defraud the depositors or for any fraudulent purpose, every`
  line `officer of the company who was responsible for the acceptance of such deposit shall, without prejudice to`
  line `the provisions contained in subsection (3) of that section and liability under section 447, be personally`
  line `responsible, without any limitation of liability, for all or any of the losses or damages that may have been`
  line `incurred by the depositors.`
  line
  line `(2) Any suit, proceedings or other action may be taken by any person, group of persons or any`
  line `association of persons who had incurred any loss as a result of the failure of the company to repay the`
  line `deposits or part thereof or any interest thereon.`
obj_root_law_sections_75_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_76:
  sectionId (1266)
  sectionNo (76)
  orderNo 78
  title `Acceptance of deposits from public by certain companies.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_76_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_76_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=1266&sectionno=76&orderno=78&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_76_content:
  string
  line `(1) Notwithstanding anything`
  line `contained in section 73, a public company, having such net worth or turnover as may be prescribed, may`
  line `accept deposits from persons other than its members subject to compliance with the requirements`
  line `provided in sub-section (2) of section 73 and subject to such rules as the Central Government may, in`
  line `consultation with the Reserve Bank of India, prescribe:`
  line
  line `Provided that such a company shall be required to obtain the rating (including its networth, liquidity`
  line `and ability to pay its deposits on due date) from a recognised credit rating agency for informing the public`
  line `the rating given to the company at the time of invitation of deposits from the public which ensures`
  line `adequate safety and the rating shall be obtained for every year during the tenure of deposits:`
  line
  line `Provided further that every company accepting secured deposits from the public shall within thirty`
  line `days of such acceptance, create a charge on its assets of an amount not less than the amount of deposits`
  line
  line `accepted in favour of the deposit holders in accordance with such rules as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(2) The provisions of this Chapter shall, mutatis mutandis, apply to the acceptance of deposits from`
  line `public under this section.`
obj_root_law_sections_76_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_76_a:
  sectionId (1267)
  sectionNo 76A
  orderNo 79
  title `Punishment for contravention of section 73 or section 76.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_76_a_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_76_a_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=1267&sectionno=76A&orderno=79&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_76_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[76A. Punishment for contravention of section 73 or section 76.-- Where a company accepts or`
  line `invites or allows or causes any other person to accept or invite on its behalf any deposit in contravention`
  line `of the manner or the conditions prescribed under section 73 or section 76 or rules made thereunder or if a`
  line `company fails to repay the deposit or part thereof or any interest due thereon within the time specified`
  line `under section 73 or section 76 or rules made thereunder or such further time as may be allowed by the`
  line `Tribunal under section 73,--`
  line
  line `(a) the company shall, in addition to the payment of the amount of deposit or part thereof and the`
  line `interest due, be punishable with fine which shall not be less than ^2[one crore rupees or twice the`
  line `amount of deposit accepted by the company, whichever is lower] but which may extend to ten crore`
  line `rupees; and`
  line
  line `(b) every officer of the company who is in default shall be punishable with imprisonment which`
  line `may extend to ^3[seven years and with fine] which shall not be less than twenty-five lakh rupees but`
  line `which may extend to two crore rupees, ^4***:`
  line
  line `Provided that if it is proved that the officer of the company who is in default, has contravened such`
  line `provisions knowingly or wilfully with the intention to deceive the company or its shareholders or`
  line `depositors or creditors or tax authorities, he shall be liable for action under section 447.]`
obj_root_law_sections_76_a_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 21 of 2015, s. 8 (w.e.f. 29-5-2015).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 1 of 2018, s. 17, for "one crore rupees" (w.e.f. 9-2-2018).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by s. 17, ibid., for "seven years or with fine" (w.e.f. 9-2-2018).`
  line
  line `4. The words "or with both" omitted by s. 17, ibid. (w.e.f. 9-2-2018).`
obj_root_law_sections_77:
  sectionId (1268)
  sectionNo (77)
  orderNo 80
  title `Duty to register charges, etc`
  content obj_root_law_sections_77_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_77_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=1268&sectionno=77&orderno=80&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_77_content:
  string
  line `(1) It shall be the duty of every company creating a charge`
  line `within or outside India, on its property or assets or any of its undertakings, whether tangible or otherwise,`
  line `and situated in or outside India, to register the particulars of the charge signed by the company and the`
  line `charge-holder together with the instruments, if any, creating such charge in such form, on payment of`
  line `such fees and in such manner as may be prescribed, with the Registrar within thirty days of its creation:`
  line
  line `^1[Provided that the Registrar may, on an application by the company, allow such registration to be`
  line made--
  line
  line `(a) in case of charges created before the commencement of the Companies (Amendment) Act,`
  line `2019, within a period of three hundred days of such creation; or`
  line
  line `(b) in case of charges created on or after the commencement of the Companies (Amendment) Act,`
  line `2019, within a period of sixty days of such creation,`
  line
  line `on payment of such additional fees as may be prescribed:`
  line
  line `Provided further that if the registration is not made within the period specified--`
  line
  line `(a) in clause (a) to the first proviso, the registration of the charges shall be made within six`
  line `months from the date of commencement of the Companies (Amendment) Act, 2019, on payment of`
  line `such additional fees as may be prescribed and different fees may be prescribed for different classes of`
  line companies;
  line
  line `(b) in clause (b) to the first proviso, the Registrar may, on an application, allow such registration`
  line `to be made within a further period of sixty days after payment of such ad valorem fees as may be`
  line prescribed.]
  line
  line `Provided also that any subsequent registration of a charge shall not prejudice any right acquired in`
  line `respect of any property before the charge is actually registered:`
  line
  line `^2[Provided also that this section shall not apply to such charges as may be prescribed in consultation`
  line `with the Reserve Bank of India.]`
  line
  line `(2) Where a charge is registered with the Registrar under sub-section (1), he shall issue a certificate of`
  line `registration of such charge in such form and in such manner as may be prescribed to the company and, as`
  line `the case may be, to the person in whose favour the charge is created.`
  line
  line `(3) Notwithstanding anything contained in any other law for the time being in force, no charge`
  line `created by a company shall be taken into account by the liquidator ^3[appointed under this Act or the`
  line `Insolvency and Bankruptcy Code, 2016 (31 of 2016), as the case may be,] or any other creditor unless it is`
  line `duly registered under sub-section (1) and a certificate of registration of such charge is given by the`
  line `Registrar under sub-section (2).`
  line
  line `(4) Nothing in sub-section (3) shall prejudice any contract or obligation for the repayment of the`
  line `money secured by a charge.`
obj_root_law_sections_77_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 22 of 2019, s. 11, for first and second provisos (w.e.f. 2-11-2018).`
  line `2. The proviso ins. by Act 1 of 2018, s. 18 (w.e.f. 7-5-2018).`
  line `3. Ins. by Act 31 of 2016, s. 255 and the Eleventh Schedule (w.e.f. 15-11-2016).`
obj_root_law_sections_78:
  sectionId (1269)
  sectionNo (78)
  orderNo 81
  title `Application for registration of charge`
  content obj_root_law_sections_78_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 1 of 2018, s. 19, for "register the charge within the period specified in section 77" (w.e.f. 7-5-2018).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=1269&sectionno=78&orderno=81&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_78_content:
  string
  line `Where a company fails to ^1[register the charge within`
  line `the period specified in section 77], without prejudice to its liability in respect of any offence under this`
  line `Chapter, the person in whose favour the charge is created may apply to the Registrar for registration of`
  line `the charge along with the instrument created for the charge, within such time and in such form and`
  line `manner as may be prescribed and the Registrar may, on such application, within a period of fourteen days`
  line `after giving notice to the company, unless the company itself registers the charge or shows sufficient`
  line `cause why such charge should not be registered, allow such registration on payment of such fees, as may`
  line `be prescribed:`
  line
  line `Provided that where registration is effected on application of the person in whose favour the charge is`
  line `created, that person shall be entitled to recover from the company the amount of any fees or additional`
  line `fees paid by him to the Registrar for the purpose of registration of charge`
obj_root_law_sections_79:
  sectionId (1270)
  sectionNo (79)
  orderNo 82
  title `Section 77 to apply in certain matters.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_79_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_79_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=1270&sectionno=79&orderno=82&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_79_content:
  string
  line `The provisions of section 77 relating to registration of`
  line `charges shall, so far as may be, apply to--`
  line
  line `(a) a company acquiring any property subject to a charge within the meaning of that section; or`
  line
  line `(b) any modification in the terms or conditions or the extent or operation of any charge registered`
  line `under that section`
obj_root_law_sections_79_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_80:
  sectionId (1271)
  sectionNo (80)
  orderNo 83
  title `Date of notice of charge.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_80_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_80_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=1271&sectionno=80&orderno=83&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_80_content:
  string
  line `Where any charge on any property or assets of a company or any of`
  line `its undertakings is registered under section 77, any person acquiring such property, assets, undertakings or`
  line `part thereof or any share or interest therein shall be deemed to have notice of the charge from the date of`
  line `such registration.`
obj_root_law_sections_80_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_81:
  sectionId (1272)
  sectionNo (81)
  orderNo 84
  title `Register of charges to be kept by Registrar.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_81_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_81_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=1272&sectionno=81&orderno=84&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_81_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Registrar shall, in respect of every`
  line `company, keep a register containing particulars of the charges registered under this Chapter in such form`
  line `and in such manner as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(2) A register kept in pursuance of this section shall be open to inspection by any person on payment`
  line `of such fees as may be prescribed for each inspection.`
obj_root_law_sections_81_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_82:
  sectionId (1273)
  sectionNo (82)
  orderNo 85
  title `Company to report satisfaction of charge`
  content obj_root_law_sections_82_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_82_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=1273&sectionno=82&orderno=85&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_82_content:
  string
  line `(1) A company shall give intimation to the`
  line `Registrar in the prescribed form, of the payment or satisfaction in full of any charge registered under this`
  line `Chapter within a period of thirty days from the date of such payment or satisfaction ^1***.`
  line
  line `^2[Provided that the Registrar may, on an application by the company or the charge holder, allow such`
  line `intimation of payment or satisfaction to be made within a period of three hundred days of such payment`
  line `or satisfaction on payment of such additional fees as may be prescribed.]`
  line
  line `(2) The Registrar shall, on receipt of intimation under sub-section (1), cause a notice to be sent to the`
  line `holder of the charge calling upon him to show cause within such time not exceeding fourteen days, as`
  line `may be specified in such notice, as to why payment or satisfaction in full should not be recorded as`
  line `intimated to the Registrar, and if no cause is shown, by such holder of the charge, the Registrar shall order`
  line `that a memorandum of satisfaction shall be entered in the register of charges kept by him under section 81`
  line `and shall inform the company that he has done so:`
  line
  line `Provided that the notice referred to in this sub-section shall not be required to be sent, in case the`
  line `intimation to the Registrar in this regard is in the specified form and signed by the holder of charge.`
  line
  line `(3) If any cause is shown, the Registrar shall record a note to that effect in the register of charges and`
  line `shall inform the company.`
  line
  line `(4) Nothing in this section shall be deemed to affect the powers of the Registrar to make an entry in`
  line `the register of charges under section 83 or otherwise than on receipt of an intimation from the company.`
obj_root_law_sections_82_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Omitted by Act 1 of 2018, s. 20, for certain words (w.e.f. 5-7-2018).`
  line
  line `2. The Proviso ins. by s. 20, ibid. (w.e.f. 5-7-2018).`
obj_root_law_sections_83:
  sectionId (1274)
  sectionNo (83)
  orderNo 86
  title `Power of Registrar to make entries of satisfaction and release in absence of intimation from company.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_83_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_83_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=1274&sectionno=83&orderno=86&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_83_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Registrar may, on evidence being given to his satisfaction with respect to any`
  line `registered charge,--`
  line
  line `(a) that the debt for which the charge was given has been paid or satisfied in whole or in part; or`
  line
  line `(b) that part of the property or undertaking charged has been released from the charge or has`
  line `ceased to form part of the company's property or undertaking,`
  line `enter in the register of charges a memorandum of satisfaction in whole or in part, or of the fact that part of`
  line `the property or undertaking has been released from the charge or has ceased to form part of the`
  line `company's property or undertaking, as the case may be, notwithstanding the fact that no intimation has`
  line `been received by him from the company.`
  line
  line `(2) The Registrar shall inform the affected parties within thirty days of making the entry in the`
  line `register of charges kept under sub-section (1) of section 81.`
obj_root_law_sections_83_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_84:
  sectionId (1275)
  sectionNo (84)
  orderNo 87
  title `Intimation of appointment of receiver or manager.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_84_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_84_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=1275&sectionno=84&orderno=87&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_84_content:
  string
  line `(1) If any person obtains an order for the`
  line `appointment of a receiver of, or of a person to manage, the property, subject to a charge, of a company or`
  line `if any person appoints such receiver or person under any power contained in any instrument, he shall,`
  line `within a period of thirty days from the date of the passing of the order or of the making of the`
  line `appointment, give notice of such appointment to the company and the Registrar along with a copy of the`
  line `order or instrument and the Registrar shall, on payment of the prescribed fees, register particulars of the`
  line `receiver, person or instrument in the register of charges.`
  line
  line `(2) Any person appointed under sub-section (1) shall, on ceasing to hold such appointment, give to`
  line `the company and the Registrar a notice to that effect and the Registrar shall register such notice.`
obj_root_law_sections_84_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_85:
  sectionId (1276)
  sectionNo (85)
  orderNo 88
  title `Company‘s register of charges.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_85_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_85_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=1276&sectionno=85&orderno=88&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_85_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every company shall keep at its registered office a register`
  line `of charges in such form and in such manner as may be prescribed, which shall include therein all charges`
  line `and floating charges affecting any property or assets of the company or any of its undertakings, indicating`
  line `in each case such particulars as may be prescribed:`
  line
  line `Provided that a copy of the instrument creating the charge shall also be kept at the registered office of`
  line `the company along with the register of charges.`
  line
  line `(2) The register of charges and instrument of charges, kept under sub-section (1) shall be open for`
  line `inspection during business hours--`
  line
  line `(a) by any member or creditor without any payment of fees; or`
  line
  line `(b) by any other person on payment of such fees as may be prescribed,`
  line
  line `subject to such reasonable restrictions as the company may, by its articles, impose.`
obj_root_law_sections_85_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_86:
  sectionId (1277)
  sectionNo (86)
  orderNo 89
  title `Punishment for contravention.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_86_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_86_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=1277&sectionno=86&orderno=89&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_86_content:
  string
  line `^1[ ^2[(1)] If any company is in default in complying with any of`
  line `the provisions of this Chapter, the company shall be liable to a penalty of five lakh rupees and every`
  line `officer of the company who is in default shall be liable to a penalty of fifty thousand rupees].`
  line
  line `^3[(2) If any person willfully furnishes any false or incorrect information or knowingly suppresses any`
  line `material information, required to be registered in accordance with the provisions of section 77, he shall be`
  line `liable for action under section 447.]`
obj_root_law_sections_86_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 29 of 2020, s. 16, for sub-section (1) (w.e.f. 21-12-2020).`
  line
  line `2. Section 86 numbered as sub-section (1) thereof by Act 22 of 2019, s.12 (w.e.f. 2-11-2018).`
  line
  line `3. Ins. by s. 12, ibid. (w.e.f. 2-11-2018).`
obj_root_law_sections_87:
  sectionId (1278)
  sectionNo (87)
  orderNo 90
  title `Rectification by Central Government in Register of charges.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_87_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by s. 13, ibid., for section 86 (w.e.f. 2-11-2018).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=1278&sectionno=87&orderno=90&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_87_content:
  string
  line `^1[87. Rectification by Central Government in Register of charges.-- The Central Government on`
  line `being satisfied that--`
  line
  line `(a) the omission to give intimate to the Registrar of the payment or satisfaction of a charge,`
  line `within the time required under this Chapter; or`
  line
  line `(b) the omission or misstatement of any particulars, in any filing previously made to the Registrar`
  line `with respect to any charge or modification thereof or with respect to any memorandum of satisfaction`
  line `or other entry made in pursuance of section 82 or section 83,`
  line
  line `was accidental or due to inadvertence or some other sufficient cause or it is not of a nature to prejudice`
  line `the position of creditors or shareholders of the company, it may, on the application of the company or any`
  line `person interested and on such terms and conditions as it deems just and expedient, direct that the time for`
  line `the giving of intimation of payment or satisfaction shall be extended or, as the case may require, that the`
  line `omission or misstatement shall be rectified.]`
obj_root_law_sections_88:
  sectionId (1279)
  sectionNo (88)
  orderNo 91
  title `Register of members, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_88_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 29 of 2020, s. 17, for sub-section (5) (w.e.f. 21-12-2020).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=1279&sectionno=88&orderno=91&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_88_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every company shall keep and maintain the following registers`
  line `in such form and in such manner as may be prescribed, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) register of members indicating separately for each class of equity and preference shares held`
  line `by each member residing in or outside India;`
  line
  line `(b) register of debenture-holders; and`
  line
  line `(c) register of any other security holders.`
  line
  line `(2) Every register maintained under sub-section (1) shall include an index of the names included`
  line therein.
  line
  line `(3) The register and index of beneficial owners maintained by a depository under section 11 of the`
  line `Depositories Act, 1996 (22 of 1996), shall be deemed to be the corresponding register and index for the`
  line `purposes of this Act.`
  line
  line `(4) A company may, if so authorised by its articles, keep in any country outside India, in such manner`
  line `as may be prescribed, a part of the register referred to in sub-section (1), called "foreign register"`
  line `containing the names and particulars of the members, debenture-holders, other security holders or`
  line `beneficial owners residing outside India.`
  line
  line `^1[(5) If a company does not maintain a register of members or debenture-holders or other security`
  line `holders or fails to maintain them in accordance with the provisions of sub-section (1) or sub-section (2),`
  line `the company shall be liable to a penalty of three lakh rupees and every officer of the company who is in`
  line `default shall be liable to a penalty of fifty thousand rupees.]`
obj_root_law_sections_89:
  sectionId (1280)
  sectionNo (89)
  orderNo 92
  title `Declaration in respect of beneficial interest in any share`
  content obj_root_law_sections_89_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_89_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=1280&sectionno=89&orderno=92&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_89_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where the name of a person is`
  line `entered in the register of members of a company as the holder of shares in that company but who does not`
  line `hold the beneficial interest in such shares, such person shall make a declaration within such time and in`
  line `such form as may be prescribed to the company specifying the name and other particulars of the person`
  line `who holds the beneficial interest in such shares.`
  line
  line `(2) Every person who holds or acquires a beneficial interest in share of a company shall make a`
  line `declaration to the company specifying the nature of his interest, particulars of the person in whose name`
  line `the shares stand registered in the books of the company and such other particulars as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(3) Where any change occurs in the beneficial interest in such shares, the person referred to in`
  line `sub-section (1) and the beneficial owner specified in sub-section (2) shall, within a period of thirty days`
  line `from the date of such change, make a declaration to the company in such form and containing such`
  line `particulars as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(4) The Central Government may make rules to provide for the manner of holding and disclosing`
  line `beneficial interest and beneficial ownership under this section.`
  line
  line `^1[(5) If any person fails to make a declaration as required under sub-section (1) or sub-section (2) or`
  line `sub-section (3), he shall be liable to a penalty of fifty thousand rupees and in case of continuing failure,`
  line `with a further penalty of two hundred rupees for each day after the first during which such failure`
  line `continues, subject to a maximum of five lakh rupees.]`
  line
  line `(6) Where any declaration under this section is made to a company, the company shall make a note of`
  line `such declaration in the register concerned and shall file, within thirty days from the date of receipt of`
  line `declaration by it, a return in the prescribed form with the Registrar in respect of such declaration with`
  line `such fees or additional fees as may be prescribed, ^2***.`
  line
  line `^3[(7) If a company, required to file a return under sub-section (6), fails to do so before the expiry of the time specified therein, the company and every officer of the company who is in default shall be liable to a penalty of one thousand rupees for each day during which such failure continues, subject to a maximum of five lakh rupees in the case of a company and two lakh rupees in case of an officer who is in default.]`
  line
  line `(8) No right in relation to any share in respect of which a declaration is required to be made under this`
  line `section but not made by the beneficial owner, shall be enforceable by him or by any person claiming`
  line `through him.`
  line
  line `(9) Nothing in this section shall be deemed to prejudice the obligation of a company to pay dividend`
  line `to its members under this Act and the said obligation shall, on such payment, stand discharged.`
  line
  line `^4[(10) For the purposes of this section and section 90, beneficial interest in a share includes, directly`
  line `or indirectly, through any contract, arrangement or otherwise, the right or entitlement of a person alone or`
  line `together with any other person to--`
  line
  line `(i) exercise or cause to be exercised any or all of the rights attached to such share; or`
  line
  line `(ii) receive or participate in any dividend or other distribution in respect of such share.]`
  line
  line `^5[(11) The Central Government may, by notification, exempt any class or classes of persons from complying with any of the requirements of this section, except sub-section (10), if it is considered necessary to grant such exemption in the public interest and any such exemption may be granted either unconditionally or subject to such conditions as may be specified in the notification.]`
obj_root_law_sections_89_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by s. 18, ibid., for sub-section (5) (w.e.f. 21-12-2020).`
  line
  line `2. The words and figures "within the time specified under section 403" omitted by Act 1 of 2018, s. 21 (w.e.f. 7-5-2018).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 29 of 2020, s. 18, for sub-section (7) (w.e.f. 21-12-2020).`
  line
  line `4. Ins. by Act 1 of 2018, s. 21, (w.e.f. 13-6-2018).`
  line
  line `5. Ins. by Act 29 of 2020, s. 18 (w.e.f. 22-1-2021).`
obj_root_law_sections_90:
  sectionId (1281)
  sectionNo (90)
  orderNo 93
  title `Register of significant beneficial owners in a Company.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_90_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_90_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=1281&sectionno=90&orderno=93&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_90_content:
  string
  line ^1
  line `[90. Register of significant beneficial owners in a company.--(1) Every individual, who acting`
  line `alone or together, or through one or more persons or trust, including a trust and persons resident outside`
  line `India, holds beneficial interests, of not less than twenty-five per cent. or such other percentage as may be`
  line `prescribed, in shares of a company or the right to exercise, or the actual exercising of significant influence`
  line `or control as defined in clause (27) of section 2, over the company (herein referred to as "significant`
  line `beneficial owner"), shall make a declaration to the company, specifying the nature of his interest and`
  line `other particulars, in such manner and within such period of acquisition of the beneficial interest or rights`
  line `and any change thereof, as may be prescribed:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Central Government may prescribe a class or classes of persons who shall not be`
  line `required to make declaration under this sub-section.`
  line
  line `(2) Every company shall maintain a register of the interest declared by individuals under`
  line `sub-section (1) and changes therein which shall include the name of individual, his date of birth, address,`
  line `details of ownership in the company and such other details as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(3) The register maintained under sub-section (2) shall be open to inspection by any member of the`
  line `company on payment of such fees as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(4) Every company shall file a return of significant beneficial owners of the company and changes`
  line `therein with the Registrar containing names, addresses and other details as may be prescribed within such`
  line `time, in such form and manner as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line ^2
  line `[(4A) Every company shall take necessary steps to identify an individual who is a significant`
  line `beneficial owner in relation to the company and require him to comply with the provisions of this`
  line section.]
  line
  line `(5) A company shall give notice, in the prescribed manner, to any person (whether or not a member of`
  line `the company) whom the company knows or has reasonable cause to believe--`
  line
  line `(a) to be a significant beneficial owner of the company;`
  line
  line `(b) to be having knowledge of the identity of a significant beneficial owner or another person likely`
  line `to have such knowledge; or`
  line
  line `(c) to have been a significant beneficial owner of the company at any time during the three years`
  line `immediately preceding the date on which the notice is issued,`
  line
  line `and who is not registered as a significant beneficial owner with the company as required under this`
  line section.
  line
  line `(6) The information required by the notice under sub-section (5) shall be given by the concerned`
  line `person within a period not exceeding thirty days of the date of the notice.`
  line
  line `(7) The company shall,--`
  line
  line `(a) where that person fails to give the company the information required by the notice within the`
  line `time specified therein; or`
  line
  line `(b) where the information given is not satisfactory,`
  line
  line `apply to the Tribunal within a period of fifteen days of the expiry of the period specified in the notice, for`
  line `an order directing that the shares in question be subject to restrictions with regard to transfer of interest,`
  line `suspension of all rights attached to the shares and such other matters as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(8) On any application made under sub-section (7), the Tribunal may, after giving an opportunity of`
  line `being heard to the parties concerned, make such order restricting the rights attached with the shares within`
  line `a period of sixty days of receipt of application or such other period as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line ^3
  line `[(9) The company or the person aggrieved by the order of the Tribunal may make an application to`
  line `the Tribunal for relaxation or lifting of the restrictions placed under sub-section (8), within a period of one`
  line `year from the date of such order:`
  line
  line `Provided that if no such application has been filed within a period of one year from the date of the`
  line `order under sub-section (8), such shares shall be transferred, without any restrictions, to the authority`
  line `constituted under sub-section (5) of section 125, in such manner as may be prescribed;]`
  line
  line ^4
  line `[(9A) The Central Government may make rules for the purposes of this section.]`
  line
  line ^5
  line `[(10) If any person fails to make a declaration as required under sub-section (1), he shall be liable to`
  line `a penalty of fifty thousand rupees and in case of continuing failure, with a further penalty of one thousand`
  line `rupees for each day after the first during which such failure continues, subject to a maximum of two lakh`
  line rupees.]
  line
  line ^6
  line `[(11) If a company, required to maintain register under sub-section (2) and file the information under`
  line `sub-section (4) or required to take necessary steps under sub-section (4A), fails to do so or denies`
  line `inspection as provided therein, the company shall be liable to a penalty of one lakh rupees and in case of`
  line `continuing failure, with a further penalty of five hundred rupees for each day, after the first during which`
  line `such failure continues, subject to a maximum of five lakh rupees and every officer of the company who is`
  line `in default shall be liable to a penalty of twenty-five thousand rupees and in case of continuing failure,`
  line `with a further penalty of two hundred rupees for each day, after the first during which such failure`
  line `continues, subject to a maximum of one lakh rupees.]`
  line
  line `(12) If any person wilfully furnishes any false or incorrect information or suppresses any material`
  line `information of which he is aware in the declaration made under this section, he shall be liable to action`
  line `under section 447.]`
obj_root_law_sections_90_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by s. 22, ibid., for section 90 (w.e.f. 13-6-2018).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by Act 22 of 2019, s. 14 (w.e.f. 15-8-2019).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 22 of 2019, s. 14, for sub-section (9) (w.e.f. 2-11-2018).`
  line
  line `4. Ins. by s. 14, ibid. (w.e.f. 15-8-2019).`
  line
  line `5. Subs.by Act 29 of 2020, s. 19, for sub-section (10) (w.e.f. 21-12-2020).`
  line
  line `6. Subs. by s. 19, ibid., for sub-section (11) (w.e.f. 21-12-2020).`
obj_root_law_sections_91:
  sectionId (1282)
  sectionNo (91)
  orderNo 94
  title `Power to close register of members or debenture holders or other security holders`
  content obj_root_law_sections_91_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_91_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=1282&sectionno=91&orderno=94&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_91_content:
  string
  line `(1) A company may close the register of members or the register of debenture-holders or the register of other`
  line `security holders for any period or periods not exceeding in the aggregate forty-five days in each year, but`
  line `not exceeding thirty days at any one time, subject to giving of previous notice of at least seven days or`
  line `such lesser period as may be specified by Securities and Exchange Board for listed companies or the`
  line `companies which intend to get their securities listed, in such manner as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(2) If the register of members or of debenture-holders or of other security holders is closed without`
  line `giving the notice as provided in sub-section (1), or after giving shorter notice than that so provided, or for`
  line `a continuous or an aggregate period in excess of the limits specified in that sub-section, the company and`
  line `every officer of the company who is in default shall be liable to a penalty of five thousand rupees for`
  line `every day subject to a maximum of one lakh rupees during which the register is kept closed.`
obj_root_law_sections_91_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_92:
  sectionId (1283)
  sectionNo (92)
  orderNo 95
  title `Annual return.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_92_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_92_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=1283&sectionno=92&orderno=95&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_92_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every company shall prepare a return (hereinafter referred to as the annual`
  line `return) in the prescribed form containing the particulars as they stood on the close of the financial year`
  line regarding--
  line
  line `(a) its registered office, principal business activities, particulars of its holding, subsidiary and`
  line `associate companies;`
  line
  line `(b) its shares, debentures and other securities and shareholding pattern;`
  line
  line `^1* * * * *`
  line
  line `(d) its members and debenture-holders along with changes therein since the close of the previous`
  line `financial year;`
  line
  line `(e) its promoters, directors, key managerial personnel along with changes there in since the close`
  line `of the previous financial year;`
  line
  line `(f) meetings of members or a class thereof, Board and its various committees along with`
  line `attendance details;`
  line
  line `(g) remuneration of directors and key managerial personnel;`
  line
  line `(h) penalty or punishment imposed on the company, its directors or officers and details of`
  line `compounding of offences and appeals made against such penalty or punishment;`
  line
  line `(i) matters relating to certification of compliances, disclosures as may be prescribed;`
  line
  line `(j) details, as may be prescribed, in respect of shares held by or on behalf of the Foreign Institutional`
  line `Investors ^2***; and`
  line
  line `(k) such other matters as may be prescribed,`
  line
  line `and signed by a director and the company secretary, or where there is no company secretary, by a`
  line `company secretary in practice:`
  line
  line `Provided that in relation to One Person Company and small company, the annual return shall be`
  line `signed by the company secretary, or where there is no company secretary, by the director of the company.`
  line
  line `^3[Provided further that the Central Government may prescribe abridged form of annual return for "One`
  line `Person Company, small company and such other class of classes of companies as may be prescribed".]`
  line
  line `(2) ^4[The annual return, filed by a listed company or, by a company having such paid-up capital or`
  line `turnover as may be prescribed shall be certified by a company secretary in practice in the prescribed`
  line `form, stating that the annual return discloses the facts correctly and adequately and that the company has`
  line `complied with all the provisions of this Act.`
  line
  line `(3) An extract of the annual return in such form as may be prescribed shall form part of the Board's`
  line report.
  line
  line `(4) Every company shall file with the Registrar a copy of the annual return, within sixty days from the`
  line `date on which the annual general meeting is held or where no annual general meeting is held in any year`
  line `within sixty days from the date on which the annual general meeting should have been held together with`
  line `the statement specifying the reasons for not holding the annual general meeting, with such fees or`
  line `additional fees as may be prescribed, ^5***.`
  line
  line `^6[(5) If any company fails to file its annual return under sub-section (4), before the expiry of the`
  line `period specified therein, such company and its every officer who is in default shall be liable to a penalty`
  line `of ^7[ten thousand rupees] and in case of continuing failure, with a further penalty of one hundred rupees`
  line `for each day after the first during which such failure continues, subject to a maximum of ^8[two lakh`
  line `rupees in case of a company and fifty thousand rupees in case of an officer who is an default].]`
  line
  line `(6) If a company secretary in practice certifies the annual return otherwise than in conformity with the`
  line `requirements of this section or the rules made thereunder, he shall be ^8`
  line `[liable to a penalty of two lakh`
  line rupees].
obj_root_law_sections_92_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Clause (c) omitted by Act 1 of 2018, s. 23 (w.e.f. 5-3-2021).`
  line
  line `2. The words "indicating their names, addresses, countries of incorporation, registration and percentage of shareholding held by`
  line `them" omitted by s. 23, ibid (w.e.f. 5-3-2021).`
  line
  line `3. Ins. by Act 1 of 2018, s. 23 (w.e.f. 5-3-2021).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by S.O. 1177 (E), dated 29th April, 2014 for certain words (w.e.f. 29-4-2014).`
  line
  line `5. The words "within the time as specified, under section 403" omitted by Act 1 of 2018, s. 23 (w.e.f. 7-5-2018).`
  line
  line `6. Subs. by Act 22 of 2019, s. 15, for sub-section (5) (w.e.f. 2-11-2018).`
  line
  line `7. Subs. by Act 29 of 2020, s. 20, for "fifty thousand rupees" (w.e.f. 21-12-2020).`
  line
  line `8. Subs. by s. 20, ibid., for "five lakh rupees" (w.e.f. 21-12-2020).`
  line
  line `9. Subs. by s. 20, ibid., for "punishable with fine which shall not be less than fifty thousand rupees but which may extend to five`
  line `lakh rupees" (w.e.f. 21-12-2020).`
obj_root_law_sections_93:
  sectionId (1284)
  sectionNo (93)
  orderNo 96
  title Omitted.
  content obj_root_law_sections_93_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_93_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=1284&sectionno=93&orderno=96&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_93_content:
  string
  line `[Return to be filed with Registrar in case promoter's stake changes.] Omitted by the Companies`
  line `Act, 2017 (1 of 2018), s. 24 (w.e.f. 13-6-2018).`
obj_root_law_sections_93_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_94:
  sectionId (1285)
  sectionNo (94)
  orderNo 97
  title `Place of keeping and inspection of registers, returns, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_94_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_94_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=1285&sectionno=94&orderno=97&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_94_content:
  string
  line `(1) The registers required to be kept`
  line `and maintained by a company under section 88 and copies of the annual return filed under section 92 shall`
  line `be kept at the registered office of the company:`
  line
  line `Provided that such registers or copies of return may also be kept at any other place in India in which`
  line `more than one-tenth of the total number of members entered in the register of members reside, if`
  line `approved by a special resolution passed at a general meeting of the company ^1***:`
  line
  line `Provided further that the period for which the registers, returns and records are required to be kept`
  line `shall be such as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(2) The registers and their indices, except when they are closed under the provisions of this Act, and`
  line `the copies of all the returns shall be open for inspection by any member, debenture-holder, other security`
  line `holder or beneficial owner, during business hours without payment of any fees and by any other person on`
  line `payment of such fees as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(3) Any such member, debenture-holder, other security holder or beneficial owner or any other person`
  line may
  line
  line `(a) take extracts from any register, or index or return without payment of any fee; or`
  line
  line `(b) require a copy of any such register or entries therein or return on payment of such fees as may`
  line `be prescribed.`
  line
  line `^2[Provided that such particulars of the register or index or return as may be prescribed shall not be`
  line `available for inspection under sub-section (2) or for taking extracts or copies under this sub-section.].`
  line
  line `(4) If any inspection or the making of any extract or copy required under this section is refused, the`
  line `company and every officer of the company who is in default shall be liable, for each such default, to a penalty of one thousand rupees for every day subject to a maximum of one lakh rupees during which the`
  line `refusal or default continues.`
  line
  line `(5) The Central Government may also, by order, direct an immediate inspection of the document, or`
  line `direct that the extract required shall forthwith be allowed to be taken by the person requiring it.`
obj_root_law_sections_94_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. The words "and the Registrar has been given a copy of the proposed special resolution in advance" omitted by s. 25, ibid.`
  line `(w.e.f. 13-6-2018).`
  line `2. The proviso ins. by s. 25, ibid. (w.e.f. 13-6-2018).`
obj_root_law_sections_95:
  sectionId (1286)
  sectionNo (95)
  orderNo 98
  title `Registers, etc., to be evidence.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_95_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_95_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=1286&sectionno=95&orderno=98&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_95_content:
  string
  line `The registers, their indices and copies of annual returns`
  line `maintained under sections 88 and 94 shall be prima facie evidence of any matter directed or authorised to`
  line `be inserted therein by or under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_95_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_96:
  sectionId (1287)
  sectionNo (96)
  orderNo 99
  title `Annual general meeting.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_96_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 1 of 2018, s. 26, for "Provided that" (w.e.f. 13-6-2018).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=1287&sectionno=96&orderno=99&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_96_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every company other than a One Person Company shall in each`
  line `year hold in addition to any other meetings, a general meeting as its annual general meeting and shall`
  line `specify the meeting as such in the notices calling it, and not more than fifteen months shall elapse`
  line `between the date of one annual general meeting of a company and that of the next:`
  line
  line `Provided that in case of the first annual general meeting, it shall be held within a period of nine`
  line `months from the date of closing of the first financial year of the company and in any other case, within a`
  line `period of six months, from the date of closing of the financial year:`
  line
  line `Provided further that if a company holds its first annual general meeting as aforesaid, it shall not be`
  line `necessary for the company to hold any annual general meeting in the year of its incorporation:`
  line
  line `Provided also that the Registrar may, for any special reason, extend the time within which any annual`
  line `general meeting, other than the first annual general meeting, shall be held, by a period not exceeding three`
  line months.
  line
  line `(2) Every annual general meeting shall be called during business hours, that is, between 9 a.m. and 6`
  line `p.m. on any day that is not a National Holiday and shall be held either at the registered office of the`
  line `company or at some other place within the city, town or village in which the registered office of the`
  line `company is situate:`
  line
  line `^1[Provided that annual general meeting of an unlisted company may be held at any place in India if`
  line `consent is given in writing or by electronic mode by all the members in advance:`
  line
  line `Provided further that the Central Government may exempt any company from the provisions of this`
  line `sub-section subject to such conditions as it may impose.`
  line
  line `Explanation.-- For the purposes of this sub-section, National Holiday means and includes a day`
  line `declared as National Holiday by the Central Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_97:
  sectionId (1288)
  sectionNo (97)
  orderNo 100
  title `Power of Tribunal to call annual general meeting`
  content obj_root_law_sections_97_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_97_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=1288&sectionno=97&orderno=100&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_97_content:
  string
  line `(1) If any default is made in holding the`
  line `annual general meeting of a company under section 96, the Tribunal may, notwithstanding anything`
  line `contained in this Act or the articles of the company, on the application of any member of the company,`
  line `call, or direct the calling of, an annual general meeting of the company and give such ancillary or`
  line `consequential directions as the Tribunal thinks expedient:`
  line
  line `Provided that such directions may include a direction that one member of the company present in`
  line `person or by proxy shall be deemed to constitute a meeting.`
  line
  line `(2) A general meeting held in pursuance of sub-section (1) shall, subject to any directions of the`
  line `Tribunal, be deemed to be an annual general meeting of the company under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_97_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_98:
  sectionId (1289)
  sectionNo (98)
  orderNo 101
  title `Power of Tribunal to call meetings of members, etc`
  content obj_root_law_sections_98_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_98_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=1289&sectionno=98&orderno=101&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_98_content:
  string
  line `(1) If for any reason it is impracticable`
  line `to call a meeting of a company, other than an annual general meeting, in any manner in which meetings of`
  line `the company may be called, or to hold or conduct the meeting of the company in the manner prescribed`
  line `by this Act or the articles of the company, the Tribunal may, either suo motu or on the application of any`
  line `director or member of the company who would be entitled to vote at the meeting,--`
  line
  line `(a) order a meeting of the company to be called, held and conducted in such manner as the`
  line `Tribunal thinks fit; and`
  line
  line `(b) give such ancillary or consequential directions as the Tribunal thinks expedient, including`
  line `directions modifying or supplementing in relation to the calling, holding and conducting of the`
  line `meeting, the operation of the provisions of this Act or articles of the company:`
  line
  line `Provided that such directions may include a direction that one member of the company present in`
  line `person or by proxy shall be deemed to constitute a meeting.`
  line
  line `(2) Any meeting called, held and conducted in accordance with any order made under sub-section (1)`
  line `shall, for all purposes, be deemed to be a meeting of the company duly called, held and conducted.`
obj_root_law_sections_98_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_99:
  sectionId (1290)
  sectionNo (99)
  orderNo 102
  title `Punishment for default in complying with provisions of sections 96 to 98.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_99_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_99_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=1290&sectionno=99&orderno=102&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_99_content:
  string
  line `If any default is`
  line `made in holding a meeting of the company in accordance with section 96 or section 97 or section 98 or in`
  line `complying with any directions of the Tribunal, the company and every officer of the company who is in`
  line `default shall be punishable with fine which may extend to one lakh rupees and in the case of a continuing`
  line `default, with a further fine which may extend to five thousand rupees for every day during which such`
  line `default continues.`
obj_root_law_sections_99_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_100:
  sectionId (1291)
  sectionNo (100)
  orderNo 103
  title `Calling of extraordinary general meeting.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_100_content
  footnotes `1. The proviso ins. by Act 1 of 2018, s. 27 (w.e.f. 9-2-2018).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=1291&sectionno=100&orderno=103&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_100_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Board may, whenever it deems fit, call an`
  line `extraordinary general meeting of the company.`
  line
  line `^1[Provided that an extraordinary general meeting of the company, other than of the wholly owned`
  line `subsidiary of a company incorporated outside India, shall be held at a place within India.]`
  line
  line `(2) The Board shall, at the requisition made by,--`
  line
  line `(a) in the case of a company having a share capital, such number of members who hold, on the`
  line `date of the receipt of the requisition, not less than one-tenth of such of the paid-up share capital of the`
  line `company as on that date carries the right of voting;`
  line
  line `(b) in the case of a company not having a share capital, such number of members who have, on`
  line `the date of receipt of the requisition, not less than one-tenth of the total voting power of all the`
  line `members having on the said date a right to vote,`
  line `call an extraordinary general meeting of the company within the period specified in sub-section (4).`
  line
  line `(3) The requisition made under sub-section (2) shall set out the matters for the consideration of which`
  line `the meeting is to be called and shall be signed by the requisitionists and sent to the registered office of the`
  line company.
  line
  line `(4) If the Board does not, within twenty-one days from the date of receipt of a valid requisition in`
  line `regard to any matter, proceed to call a meeting for the consideration of that matter on a day not later than`
  line `forty-five days from the date of receipt of such requisition, the meeting may be called and held by the`
  line `requisitionists themselves within a period of three months from the date of the requisition.`
  line
  line `(5) A meeting under sub-section (4) by the requisitionists shall be called and held in the same manner`
  line `in which the meeting is called and held by the Board.`
  line
  line `(6) Any reasonable expenses incurred by the requisitionists in calling a meeting under sub-section (4)`
  line `shall be reimbursed to the requisitionists by the company and the sums so paid shall be deducted from any`
  line `fee or other remuneration under section 197 payable to such of the directors who were in default in calling`
  line `the meeting.`
obj_root_law_sections_101:
  sectionId (1292)
  sectionNo (101)
  orderNo 104
  title `Notice of meeting.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_101_content
  footnotes `1. The proviso subs. by s. 28, ibid. (w.e.f. 9-2-2018).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=1292&sectionno=101&orderno=104&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_101_content:
  string
  line `(1) A general meeting of a company may be called by giving not less than`
  line `clear twenty-one days' notice either in writing or through electronic mode in such manner as maybe`
  line `prescribed:`
  line
  line `^2[Provided that a general meeting may be called after giving shorter notice than that specified in this`
  line `sub-section if consent, in writing or by electronic mode, is accorded thereto--`
  line
  line `(i) in the case of an annual general meeting, by not less than ninty-five per cent. of the members`
  line `entitled to vote thereat; and`
  line
  line `(ii) in the case of any other general meeting, by members of the company--`
  line
  line `(a) holding, if the company has a share capital, majority in number of members entitled to vote`
  line `and who represent not less than ninety-five per cent. of such part of the paid-up share capital of the`
  line `company as gives a right to vote at the meeting; or`
  line
  line `(b) having, if the company has no share capital, not less than ninty-five per cent. of the total`
  line `voting power exercisable at that meeting:`
  line
  line `Provided further that where any member of a company is entitled to vote only on some resolution or`
  line `resolutions to be moved at a meeting and not on the others, those members shall be taken into account for the`
  line `purposes of this sub-section in respect of the former resolution or resolutions and not in respect of the latter.]`
  line
  line `(2) Every notice of a meeting shall specify the place, date, day and the hour of the meeting and shall`
  line `contain a statement of the business to be transacted at such meeting.`
  line
  line `(3) The notice of every meeting of the company shall be given to--`
  line
  line `(a) every member of the company, legal representative of any deceased member or the assignee`
  line `of an insolvent member;`
  line
  line `(b) the auditor or auditors of the company; and`
  line
  line `(c) every director of the company.`
  line
  line `(4) Any accidental omission to give notice to, or the non-receipt of such notice by, any member or`
  line `other person who is entitled to such notice for any meeting shall not invalidate the proceedings of the`
  line meeting.
obj_root_law_sections_102:
  sectionId (1293)
  sectionNo (102)
  orderNo 105
  title `Statement to be annexed to notice`
  content obj_root_law_sections_102_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 22 of 2019, s. 16, for sub-section (5) (w.e.f. 2-11-2018).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=1293&sectionno=102&orderno=105&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_102_content:
  string
  line `(1) A statement setting out the following material facts`
  line `concerning each item of special business to be transacted at a general meeting, shall be annexed to the`
  line `notice calling such meeting, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the nature of concern or interest, financial or otherwise, if any, in respect of each items of--`
  line
  line `(i) every director and the manager, if any;`
  line
  line `(ii) every other key managerial personnel; and`
  line
  line `(iii) relatives of the persons mentioned in sub-clauses (i) and (ii);`
  line
  line `(b) any other information and facts that may enable members to understand the meaning, scope`
  line `and implications of the items of business and to take decision thereon.`
  line
  line `(2) For the purposes of sub-section (1),--`
  line
  line `(a) in the case of an annual general meeting, all business to be transacted thereat shall be deemed`
  line `special, other than--`
  line
  line `(i) the consideration of financial statements and the reports of the Board of Directors and`
  line auditors;
  line
  line `(ii) the declaration of any dividend;`
  line
  line `(iii) the appointment of directors in place of those retiring;`
  line
  line `(iv) the appointment of, and the fixing of the remuneration of, the auditors; and`
  line
  line `(b) in the case of any other meeting, all business shall be deemed to be special:`
  line
  line `Provided that where any item of special business to be transacted at a meeting of the company relates`
  line `to or affects any other company, the extent of shareholding interest in that other company of every`
  line `promoter, director, manager, if any, and of every other key managerial personnel of the first mentioned`
  line `company shall, if the extent of such shareholding is not less than two per cent. of the paid-up share capital`
  line `of that company, also be set out in the statement.`
  line
  line `(3) Where any item of business refers to any document, which is to be considered at the meeting, the`
  line `time and place where such document can be inspected shall be specified in the statement under`
  line `sub-section (1).`
  line
  line `(4) Where as a result of the non-disclosure or insufficient disclosure in any statement referred to in`
  line `sub-section (1), being made by a promoter, director, manager, if any, or other key managerial personnel,`
  line `any benefit which accrues to such promoter, director, manager or other key managerial personnel or their`
  line `relatives, either directly or indirectly, the promoter, director, manager or other key managerial personnel,`
  line `as the case may be, shall hold such benefit in trust for the company, and shall, without prejudice to any`
  line `other action being taken against him under this Act or under any other law for the time being in force, be`
  line `liable to compensate the company to the extent of the benefit received by him.`
  line
  line `^1[(5) Without prejudice to the provisions of sub-section (4), if any default is made in complying with`
  line `the provisions of this section, every promoter, director, manager or other key managerial personnel of the`
  line `company who is in default shall be liable to a penalty of fifty thousand rupees or five times the amount of`
  line `benefit accruing to the promoter, director, manager or other key managerial personnel or any of his`
  line `relatives, whichever is higher.]`
obj_root_law_sections_103:
  sectionId (1294)
  sectionNo (103)
  orderNo 106
  title `Quorum for meetings`
  content obj_root_law_sections_103_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_103_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=1294&sectionno=103&orderno=106&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_103_content:
  string
  line `(1) Unless the articles of the company provide for a larger number,--`
  line
  line `(a) in case of a public company,--`
  line
  line `(i) five members personally present if the number of members as on the date of meeting is not`
  line `more than one thousand;`
  line
  line `(ii) fifteen members personally present if the number of members as on the date of meeting is more than one thousand but up to five thousand;`
  line
  line `(iii) thirty members personally present if the number of members as on the date of the`
  line `meeting exceeds five thousand;`
  line
  line `(b) in the case of a private company, two members personally present, shall be the quorum for a`
  line `meeting of the company.`
  line
  line `(2) If the quorum is not present within half-an-hour from the time appointed for holding a meeting of`
  line `the company--`
  line
  line `(a) the meeting shall stand adjourned to the same day in the next week at the same time and place, or to such other date and such other time and place as the Board may determine; or`
  line
  line `(b) the meeting, if called by requisitionists under section 100, shall stand cancelled:`
  line
  line `Provided that in case of an adjourned meeting or of a change of day, time or place of meeting under`
  line `clause (a), the company shall give not less than three days notice to the members either individually or by`
  line `publishing an advertisement in the newspapers (one in English and one in vernacular language) which is`
  line `in circulation at the place where the registered office of the company is situated.`
  line
  line `(3) If at the adjourned meeting also, a quorum is not present within half-an-hour from the time`
  line `appointed for holding meeting, the members present shall be the quorum.`
obj_root_law_sections_103_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_104:
  sectionId (1295)
  sectionNo (104)
  orderNo 107
  title `Chairman of meetings.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_104_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_104_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=1295&sectionno=104&orderno=107&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_104_content:
  string
  line `(1) Unless the articles of the company otherwise provide, the`
  line `members personally present at the meeting shall elect one of themselves to be the Chairman thereof on a`
  line `show of hands.`
  line
  line `(2) If a poll is demanded on the election of the Chairman, it shall be taken forthwith in accordance`
  line `with the provisions of this Act and the Chairman elected on a show of hands under sub-section (1) shall`
  line `continue to be the Chairman of the meeting until some other person is elected as Chairman as a result of`
  line `the poll, and such other person shall be the Chairman for the rest of the meeting.`
obj_root_law_sections_104_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_105:
  sectionId (1296)
  sectionNo (105)
  orderNo 108
  title Proxies
  content obj_root_law_sections_105_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_105_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=1296&sectionno=105&orderno=108&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_105_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any member of a company entitled to attend and vote at a meeting of the`
  line `company shall be entitled to appoint another person as a proxy to attend and vote at the meeting on his`
  line `behalf:`
  line
  line `Provided that a proxy shall not have the right to speak at such meeting and shall not been titled to`
  line `vote except on a poll:`
  line
  line `Provided further that, unless the articles of a company otherwise provide, this sub-section shall not`
  line `apply in the case of a company not having a share capital:`
  line
  line `Provided also that the Central Government may prescribe a class or classes of companies whose`
  line `members shall not be entitled to appoint another person as a proxy:`
  line
  line `Provided also that a person appointed as proxy shall act on behalf of such member or number of`
  line `members not exceeding fifty and such number of shares as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(2) In every notice calling a meeting of a company which has a share capital, or the articles of which`
  line `provide for voting by proxy at the meeting, there shall appear with reasonable prominence a statement`
  line `that a member entitled to attend and vote is entitled to appoint a proxy, or, where that is allowed, one or`
  line `more proxies, to attend and vote instead of himself, and that a proxy need not be a member.`
  line
  line `(3) If default is made in complying with sub-section (2), every officer of the company who is in`
  line `default shall be ^1`
  line `[liable to a penalty of five thousands rupees].`
  line
  line `(4) Any provision contained in the articles of a company which specifies or requires a longer period`
  line `than forty-eight hours before a meeting of the company, for depositing with the company or any other`
  line `person any instrument appointing a proxy or any other document necessary to show the validity or`
  line `otherwise relating to the appointment of a proxy in order that the appointment may be effective at such`
  line `meeting, shall have effect as if a period of forty-eight hours had been specified in or required by such`
  line `provision for such deposit.`
  line
  line `(5) If for the purpose of any meeting of a company, invitations to appoint as proxy a person or one of`
  line `a number of persons specified in the invitations are issued at the company’s expense to any member`
  line `entitled to have a notice of the meeting sent to him and to vote thereat by proxy, every officer of the`
  line `company ^2`
  line `[who issues the invitation as aforesaid or authorises or permits their issue, shall be liable to a`
  line `penalty of fifty thousand rupees]:`
  line
  line `Provided that an officer shall not be ^3`
  line `[liable] under this sub-section by reason only of the issue to a`
  line `member at his request in writing of a form of appointment naming the proxy, or of a list of persons`
  line `willing to act as proxies, if the form or list is available on request in writing to every member entitled to`
  line `vote at the meeting by proxy.`
  line
  line `(6) The instrument appointing a proxy shall--`
  line
  line `(a) be in writing; and`
  line
  line `(b) be signed by the appointer or his attorney duly authorised in writing or, if the appointer is a`
  line `body corporate, be under its seal or be signed by an officer or an attorney duly authorised by it.`
  line
  line `(7) An instrument appointing a proxy, if in the form as may be prescribed, shall not be questioned on`
  line `the ground that it fails to comply with any special requirements specified for such instrument by the`
  line `articles of a company.`
  line
  line `(8) Every member entitled to vote at a meeting of the company, or on any resolution to be moved`
  line `thereat, shall be entitled during the period beginning twenty-four hours before the time fixed for the`
  line `commencement of the meeting and ending with the conclusion of the meeting, to inspect the proxies`
  line `lodged, at any time during the business hours of the company, provided not less than three days’ notice in`
  line `writing of the intention so to inspect is given to the company.`
obj_root_law_sections_105_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 22 of 2019, s. 17, for "punishable with fine which may extend to five thousand rupees" (w.e.f. 2-11-2018).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 29 of 2020, s. 21, for certain words (w.e.f. 21-12-2020).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by s. 21, ibid., for "punishable" (w.e.f. 21-12-2020).`
obj_root_law_sections_106:
  sectionId (1297)
  sectionNo (106)
  orderNo 109
  title `Restriction on voting rights.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_106_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_106_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=1297&sectionno=106&orderno=109&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_106_content:
  string
  line `(1) Notwithstanding anything contained in this Act, the articles`
  line `of a company may provide that no member shall exercise any voting right in respect of any shares`
  line `registered in his name on which any calls or other sums presently payable by him have not been paid, or`
  line `in regard to which the company has exercised any right of lien.`
  line
  line `(2) A company shall not, except on the grounds specified in sub-section (1), prohibit any member`
  line `from exercising his voting right on any other ground.`
  line
  line `(3) On a poll taken at a meeting of a company, a member entitled to more than one vote, or his proxy,`
  line `where allowed, or other person entitled to vote for him, as the case may be, need not, if he votes, use all`
  line `his votes or cast in the same way all the votes he uses.`
obj_root_law_sections_106_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_107:
  sectionId (1298)
  sectionNo (107)
  orderNo 110
  title `Voting by show of hands.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_107_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_107_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=1298&sectionno=107&orderno=110&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_107_content:
  string
  line `(1) At any general meeting, a resolution put to the vote of the`
  line `meeting shall, unless a poll is demanded under section 109 or the voting is carried out electronically, be`
  line `decided on a show of hands.`
  line
  line `(2) A declaration by the Chairman of the meeting of the passing of a resolution or otherwise by show`
  line `of hands under sub-section (1) and an entry to that effect in the books containing the minutes of the`
  line `meeting of the company shall be conclusive evidence of the fact of passing of such resolution or`
  line otherwise.
obj_root_law_sections_107_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_108:
  sectionId (1299)
  sectionNo (108)
  orderNo 111
  title `Voting through electronic means.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_108_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_108_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=1299&sectionno=108&orderno=111&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_108_content:
  string
  line `The Central Government may prescribe the class or classes`
  line `of companies and manner in which a member may exercise his right to vote by the electronic means.`
obj_root_law_sections_108_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_109:
  sectionId (1300)
  sectionNo (109)
  orderNo 112
  title `Demand for poll.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_109_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_109_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=1300&sectionno=109&orderno=112&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_109_content:
  string
  line `(1) Before or on the declaration of the result of the voting on any resolution`
  line `on show of hands, a poll may be ordered to be taken by the Chairman of the meeting on his own motion,`
  line `and shall be ordered to be taken by him on a demand made in that behalf,--`
  line
  line `(a) in the case a company having a share capital, by the members present in person or by proxy,`
  line `where allowed, and having not less than one-tenth of the total voting power or holding shares on`
  line `which an aggregate sum of not less than five lakh rupees or such higher amount as may be prescribed`
  line `has been paid-up; and`
  line
  line `(b) in the case of any other company, by any member or members present in person or by proxy,`
  line `where allowed, and having not less than one-tenth of the total voting power.`
  line
  line `(2) The demand for a poll may be withdrawn at any time by the persons who made the demand.`
  line
  line `(3) A poll demanded for adjournment of the meeting or appointment of Chairman of the meeting shall`
  line `be taken forthwith.`
  line
  line `(4) A poll demanded on any question other than adjournment of the meeting or appointment of`
  line `Chairman shall be taken at such time, not being later than forty-eight hours from the time when the`
  line `demand was made, as the Chairman of the meeting may direct.`
  line
  line `(5) Where a poll is to be taken, the Chairman of the meeting shall appoint such number of persons, as`
  line `he deems necessary, to scrutinise the poll process and votes given on the poll and to report thereon to him`
  line `in the manner as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(6) Subject to the provisions of this section, the Chairman of the meeting shall have power to regulate`
  line `the manner in which the poll shall be taken.`
  line
  line `(7) The result of the poll shall be deemed to be the decision of the meeting on the resolution on which`
  line `the poll was taken.`
obj_root_law_sections_109_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_110:
  sectionId (1301)
  sectionNo (110)
  orderNo 113
  title `Postal ballot.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_110_content
  footnotes `1. The Proviso ins. by Act 1 of 2018, s. 29 (w.e.f. 9-2-2018).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=1301&sectionno=110&orderno=113&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_110_content:
  string
  line `(1) Notwithstanding anything contained in this Act, a company`
  line
  line `(a) shall, in respect of such items of business as the Central Government may, by notification,`
  line `declare to be transacted only by means of postal ballot; and`
  line
  line `(b) may, in respect of any item of business, other than ordinary business and any business in`
  line `respect of which directors or auditors have a right to be heard at any meeting, transact by means of`
  line `postal ballot,`
  line `in such manner as may be prescribed, instead of transacting such business at a general meeting:`
  line
  line `^1[Provided that any item of business required to be transacted by means of postal ballot under`
  line `clause (a), may be transacted at a general meeting by a company which is required to provide the facility`
  line `to members to vote by electronic means under section 108, in the manner provided in that section.]`
  line
  line `(2) If a resolution is assented to by the requisite majority of the shareholders by means of postal`
  line `ballot, it shall be deemed to have been duly passed at a general meeting convened in that behalf.`
obj_root_law_sections_111:
  sectionId (1302)
  sectionNo (111)
  orderNo 114
  title `Circulation of members‘ resolution.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_111_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_111_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=1302&sectionno=111&orderno=114&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_111_content:
  string
  line `(1) A company shall, on requisition in writing of such`
  line `number of members, as required in section 100--,`
  line
  line `(a) give notice to members of any resolution which may properly be moved and is intended to be`
  line `moved at a meeting; and`
  line
  line `(b) circulate to members any statement with respect to the matters referred to in proposed`
  line `resolution or business to be dealt with at that meeting.`
  line
  line `(2) A company shall not be bound under this section to give notice of any resolution or to circulate`
  line `any statement unless--`
  line
  line `(a) a copy of the requisition signed by the requisitionists (or two or more copies which, between`
  line `them, contain the signatures of all the requisitionists) is deposited at the registered office of the`
  line company,
  line
  line `(i) in the case of a requisition requiring notice of a resolution, not less than six weeks before`
  line `the meeting;`
  line
  line `(ii) in the case of any other requisition, not less than two weeks before the meeting; and`
  line
  line `(b) there is deposited or tendered with the requisition, a sum reasonably sufficient to meet the`
  line `companys expenses in giving effect thereto:`
  line
  line `Provided that if, after a copy of a requisition requiring notice of a resolution has been deposited at the`
  line `registered office of the company, an annual general meeting is called on a date within six weeks after the`
  line `copy has been deposited, the copy, although not deposited within the time required by this sub-section,`
  line `shall be deemed to have been properly deposited for the purposes thereof.`
  line
  line `(3) The company shall not be bound to circulate any statement as required by clause (b) of subsection (1), if on the application either of the company or of any other person who claims to be aggrieved,`
  line `the Central Government, by order, declares that the rights conferred by this section are being abused to`
  line `secure needless publicity for defamatory matter.`
  line
  line `(4) An order made under sub-section (3) may also direct that the cost incurred by the company by`
  line `virtue of this section shall be paid to the company by the requisitionists, notwithstanding that they are not`
  line `parties to the application.`
  line
  line `(5) If any default is made in complying with the provisions of this section, the company and every`
  line `officer of the company who is in default shall be liable to a penalty of twenty-five thousand rupees.`
obj_root_law_sections_111_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_112:
  sectionId (1303)
  sectionNo (112)
  orderNo 115
  title `Representation of President and Governors in meetings.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_112_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_112_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=1303&sectionno=112&orderno=115&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_112_content:
  string
  line `(1) The President of India or the`
  line `Governor of a State, if he is a member of a company, may appoint such person as he thinks fit to act as his`
  line `representative at any meeting of the company or at any meeting of any class of members of the company.`
  line
  line `(2) A person appointed to act under sub-section (1) shall, for the purposes of this Act, be deemed to`
  line `be a member of such a company and shall be entitled to exercise the same rights and powers, including`
  line `the right to vote by proxy and postal ballot, as the President or, as the case may be, the Governor could`
  line `exercise as a member of the company.`
obj_root_law_sections_112_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_113:
  sectionId (1304)
  sectionNo (113)
  orderNo 116
  title `Representation of corporations at meeting of companies and of creditors.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_113_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_113_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=1304&sectionno=113&orderno=116&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_113_content:
  string
  line `(1) A body`
  line `corporate, whether a company within the meaning of this Act or not, may,--`
  line
  line `(a) if it is a member of a company within the meaning of this Act, by resolution of its Board of`
  line `Directors or other governing body, authorise such person as it thinks fit to act as its representative at`
  line `any meeting of the company, or at any meeting of any class of members of the company;`
  line
  line `(b) if it is a creditor, including a holder of debentures, of a company within the meaning of this`
  line `Act, by resolution of its directors or other governing body, authorise such person as it thinks fit to act`
  line `as its representative at any meeting of any creditors of the company held in pursuance of this Act or`
  line `of any rules made thereunder, or in pursuance of the provisions contained in any debenture or trust`
  line `deed, as the case may be.`
  line
  line `(2) A person authorised by resolution under sub-section (1) shall be entitled to exercise the same`
  line `rights and powers, including the right to vote by proxy and by postal ballot, on behalf of the body`
  line `corporate which he represents as that body could exercise if it were an individual member, creditor or`
  line `holder of debentures of the company.`
obj_root_law_sections_113_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_114:
  sectionId (1305)
  sectionNo (114)
  orderNo 117
  title `Ordinary and special resolutions.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_114_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_114_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=1305&sectionno=114&orderno=117&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_114_content:
  string
  line `(1) A resolution shall be an ordinary resolution if the`
  line `notice required under this Act has been duly given and it is required to be passed by the votes cast,`
  line `whether on a show of hands, or electronically or on a poll, as the case may be, in favour of the resolution,`
  line `including the casting vote, if any, of the Chairman, by members who, being entitled so to do, vote in`
  line `person, or where proxies are allowed, by proxy or by postal ballot, exceed the votes, if any, cast against`
  line `the resolution by members, so entitled and voting.`
  line
  line `(2) A resolution shall be a special resolution when--`
  line
  line `(a) the intention to propose the resolution as a special resolution has been duly specified in the`
  line `notice calling the general meeting or other intimation given to the members of the resolution;`
  line
  line `(b) the notice required under this Act has been duly given; and`
  line
  line `(c) the votes cast in favour of the resolution, whether on a show of hands, or electronically or on a`
  line `poll, as the case may be, by members who, being entitled so to do, vote in person or by proxy or by`
  line `postal ballot, are required to be not less than three times the number of the votes, if any, cast against`
  line `the resolution by members so entitled and voting.`
obj_root_law_sections_114_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_115:
  sectionId (1306)
  sectionNo (115)
  orderNo 118
  title `Resolutions requiring special notice`
  content obj_root_law_sections_115_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_115_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=1306&sectionno=115&orderno=118&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_115_content:
  string
  line `Where, by any provision contained in this Act or in the`
  line `articles of a company, special notice is required of any resolution, notice of the intention to move such`
  line `resolution shall be given to the company by such number of members holding not less than one per cent.`
  line `of total voting power or holding shares on which such aggregate sum not exceeding five lakh rupees, as`
  line `may be prescribed, has been paid-up and the company shall give its members notice of the resolution in`
  line `such manner as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_115_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_116:
  sectionId (1307)
  sectionNo (116)
  orderNo 119
  title `Resolutions passed at adjourned meeting`
  content obj_root_law_sections_116_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_116_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=1307&sectionno=116&orderno=119&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_116_content:
  string
  line `Where a resolution is passed at an adjourned`
  line `meeting of--`
  line
  line `(a) a company; or`
  line
  line `(b) the holders of any class of shares in a company; or`
  line
  line `(c) the Board of Directors of a company,`
  line
  line `the resolution shall, for all purposes, be treated as having been passed on the date on which it was in fact`
  line `passed, and shall not be deemed to have been passed on any earlier date.`
obj_root_law_sections_116_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_117:
  sectionId (1308)
  sectionNo (117)
  orderNo 120
  title `Resolutions and agreements to be filed.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_117_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_117_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=1308&sectionno=117&orderno=120&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_117_content:
  string
  line `(1) A copy of every resolution or any agreement, in`
  line `respect of matters specified in sub-section (3) together with the explanatory statement under section 102,`
  line `if any, annexed to the notice calling the meeting in which the resolution is proposed, shall be filed with the Registrar within thirty days of the passing or making thereof in such manner and with such fees as`
  line `may be prescribed ^1***:`
  line
  line `Provided that the copy of every resolution which has the effect of altering the articles and the copy of`
  line `every agreement referred to in sub-section (3) shall be embodied in or annexed to every copy of the`
  line `articles issued after passing of the resolution or making of the agreement.`
  line
  line `^2(2) If any company fails to file the resolution or the agreement under sub-section (1) before the expiry of the period specified therein, such company shall be liable to a penalty of ten thousand rupees and in case of continuing failure, with a further penalty of one hundred rupees for each day after the first during which such failure continues, subject to a maximum of two lakh rupees and every officer of the company who is in default including liquidator of the company, if any, shall be liable to a penalty of ten thousand rupees and in case of continuing failure, with a further penalty of one hundred rupees for each day after the first during which such failure continues, subject to a maximum of fifty thousand rupees.]`
  line
  line `(3) The provisions of this section shall apply to--`
  line
  line `(a) special resolutions;`
  line
  line `(b) resolutions which have been agreed to by all the members of a company, but which, if not so`
  line `agreed to, would not have been effective for their purpose unless they had been passed as special`
  line resolutions;
  line
  line `(c) any resolution of the Board of Directors of a company or agreement executed by a company,`
  line `relating to the appointment, re-appointment or renewal of the appointment, or variation of the terms`
  line `of appointment, of a managing director;`
  line
  line `(d) resolutions or agreements which have been agreed to by any class of members but which, if`
  line `not so agreed to, would not have been effective for their purpose unless they had been passed by a`
  line `specified majority or otherwise in some particular manner; and all resolutions or agreements which`
  line `effectively bind such class of members though not agreed to by all those members;`
  line
  line `^3* * * * *`
  line
  line `(f) resolutions requiring a company to be wound up voluntarily passed in pursuance of ^4`
  line [section
  line `59 of the Insolvency and Bankruptcy Code, 2016 (31 of 2016)];`
  line
  line `(g) resolutions passed in pursuance of sub-section (3) of section 179:^5***`
  line
  line `^6[Provided that no person shall be entitled under section 399 to inspect or obtain copies of`
  line `such resolutions; ^7***]`
  line
  line `^8[Provided further that nothing contained in this clause shall apply in respect of a resolution passed to grant loans, or give guarantee or provide security in respect of loans under clause (f) of sub-section (3) of section 179 in the ordinary course of its business by--`
  line
  line `(a) a banking company;`
  line
  line `(b) any class of non-banking financial company registered under Chapter IIIB of the Reserve Bank of India Act, 1934, as may be prescribed in consultation with the Reserve Bank of India;`
  line
  line `(c) any class of housing finance company registered under the National Housing Bank Act, 1987 (53 of 1987), as may be prescribed in consultation with the National Housing Bank; and]`
  line
  line `(h) any other resolution or agreement as may be prescribed and placed in the public domain.`
obj_root_law_sections_117_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. The words and figures "within the time specified under section 403" omitted by Act 1 of 2018, s. 30 (w.e.f. 7-5-2018).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 29 of 2020, s. 22, for sub-section (2) (w.e.f. 21-12-2020).`
  line
  line `3.Clause (e) omitted by Act 1 of 2018, s. 30 (w.e.f. 7-5-2018).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by Act 31 of 2016, s. 255 and the Eleventh Schedule, for "section 304" (w.e.f. 15-11-2016).`
  line
  line `5. The word "and" omitted by Act 21 of 2015, s. 9 (w.e.f. 29-5-2015).`
  line
  line `6. Ins. by s. 9, ibid. (w.e.f. 29-5-2015).`
  line
  line `7. The "and" omitted by Act 1 of 2018, s. 30 (w.e.f. 7-5-2018).`
  line
  line `8.The proviso subs. by Act 29 of 2020, s. 22 (w.e.f. 22-1-2021).`
obj_root_law_sections_118:
  sectionId (1309)
  sectionNo (118)
  orderNo 121
  title `. Minutes of proceedings of general meeting, meeting of Board of Directors and other meeting and resolutions passed by postal ballot.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_118_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_118_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=1309&sectionno=118&orderno=121&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_118_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every company shall cause minutes of the`
  line `proceedings of every general meeting of any class of shareholders or creditors, and every resolution`
  line `passed by postal ballot and every meeting of its Board of Directors or of every committee of the Board, to`
  line `be prepared and signed in such manner as may be prescribed and kept within thirty days of the conclusion`
  line `of every such meeting concerned, or passing of resolution by postal ballot in books kept for that purpose`
  line `with their pages consecutively numbered.`
  line
  line `(2) The minutes of each meeting shall contain a fair and correct summary of the proceedings thereat.`
  line
  line `(3) All appointments made at any of the meetings aforesaid shall be included in the minutes of the`
  line meeting.
  line
  line `(4) In the case of a meeting of the Board of Directors or of a committee of the Board, the minutes`
  line `shall also contain--`
  line
  line `(a) the names of the directors present at the meeting; and`
  line
  line `(b) in the case of each resolution passed at the meeting, the names of the directors, if any, dissenting from, or not concurring with the resolution.`
  line
  line `(5) There shall not be included in the minutes, any matter which, in the opinion of the Chairman of`
  line `the meeting,--`
  line
  line `(a) is or could reasonably be regarded as defamatory of any person; or`
  line
  line `(b) is irrelevant or immaterial to the proceedings; or`
  line
  line `(c) is detrimental to the interests of the company.`
  line
  line `(6) The Chairman shall exercise absolute discretion in regard to the inclusion or non-inclusion of any`
  line `matter in the minutes on the grounds specified in sub-section (5).`
  line
  line `(7) The minutes kept in accordance with the provisions of this section shall be evidence of the`
  line `proceedings recorded therein.`
  line
  line `(8) Where the minutes have been kept in accordance with sub-section (1) then, until the contrary is`
  line `proved, the meeting shall be deemed to have been duly called and held, and all proceedings thereat to`
  line `have duly taken place, and the resolutions passed by postal ballot to have been duly passed and in`
  line `particular, all appointments of directors, key managerial personnel, auditors or company secretary in`
  line `practice, shall be deemed to be valid.`
  line
  line `(9) No document purporting to be a report of the proceedings of any general meeting of a company`
  line `shall be circulated or advertised at the expense of the company, unless it includes the matters required by`
  line `this section to be contained in the minutes of the proceedings of such meeting.`
  line
  line `(10) Every company shall observe secretarial standards with respect to general and Board meetings`
  line `specified by the Institute of Company Secretaries of India constituted under section 3 of the Company`
  line `Secretaries Act, 1980 (56 of 1980), and approved as such by the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(11) If any default is made in complying with the provisions of this section in respect of any meeting,`
  line `the company shall be liable to a penalty of twenty-five thousand rupees and every officer of the company`
  line `who is in default shall be liable to a penalty of five thousand rupees.`
  line
  line `(12) If a person is found guilty of tampering with the minutes of the proceedings of meeting, he shall`
  line `be punishable with imprisonment for a term which may extend to two years and with fine which shall not`
  line `be less than twenty-five thousand rupees but which may extend to one lakh rupees.`
obj_root_law_sections_118_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_119:
  sectionId (1310)
  sectionNo (119)
  orderNo 122
  title `Inspection of minute-books of general meeting`
  content obj_root_law_sections_119_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_119_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=1310&sectionno=119&orderno=122&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_119_content:
  string
  line `(1) The books containing the minutes of the`
  line `proceedings of any general meeting of a company or of a resolution passed by postal ballot, shall--`
  line
  line `(a) be kept at the registered office of the company; and`
  line
  line `(b) be open, during business hours, to the inspection by any member without charge, subject to`
  line `such reasonable restrictions as the company may, by its articles or in general meeting, impose, so,`
  line `however, that not less than two hours in each business day are allowed for inspection.`
  line
  line `(2) Any member shall be entitled to be furnished, within seven working days after he has made a`
  line `request in that behalf to the company, and on payment of such fees as may be prescribed, with a copy of`
  line `any minutes referred to in sub-section (1).`
  line
  line `(3) If any inspection under sub-section (1) is refused, or if any copy required under sub-section (2) is`
  line `not furnished within the time specified therein, the company shall be liable to a penalty of twenty-five`
  line `thousand rupees and every officer of the company who is in default shall be liable to a penalty of five`
  line `thousand rupees for each such refusal or default, as the case may be.`
  line
  line `(4) In the case of any such refusal or default, the Tribunal may, without prejudice to any action being`
  line `taken under sub-section (3), by order, direct an immediate inspection of the minute-books or direct that`
  line `the copy required shall forthwith be sent to the person requiring it.`
obj_root_law_sections_119_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_120:
  sectionId (1311)
  sectionNo (120)
  orderNo 123
  title `Maintenance and inspection of documents in electronic form.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_120_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_120_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=1311&sectionno=120&orderno=123&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_120_content:
  string
  line `Without prejudice to any`
  line `other provisions of this Act, any document, record, register, minutes, etc.,--`
  line
  line `(a) required to be kept by a company; or`
  line
  line `(b) allowed to be inspected or copies to be given to any person by a company under this Act, may`
  line `be kept or inspected or copies given, as the case may be, in electronic form in such form and manner`
  line `as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_120_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_121:
  sectionId (1312)
  sectionNo (121)
  orderNo 124
  title `Report on annual general meeting.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_121_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_121_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=1312&sectionno=121&orderno=124&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_121_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every listed public company shall prepare in the`
  line `prescribed manner a report on each annual general meeting including the confirmation to the effect that`
  line `the meeting was convened, held and conducted as per the provisions of this Act and the rules made`
  line thereunder.
  line
  line `(2) The company shall file with the Registrar a copy of the report referred to in sub-section (1) within`
  line `thirty days of the conclusion of the annual general meeting with such fees as may be prescribed, or with`
  line `such additional fees as may be prescribed, ^1***.`
  line
  line `^2[(3) If the company fails to file the report under sub-section (2) before the expiry of the period`
  line `specified therein, such company shall be liable to a penalty of one lakh rupees and in case of continuing`
  line `failure, with a further penalty of five hundred rupees for each day after the first during which such failure`
  line `continues, subject to a maximum of five lakh rupees and every officer of the company who is in default`
  line `shall be liable to a penalty which shall not be less than twenty-five thousand rupees and in case of`
  line `continuing failure, with a further penalty of five hundred rupees for each day after the first during which`
  line `such failure continues, subject to a maximum of one lakh rupees.]`
obj_root_law_sections_121_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. The words and figures "within the time as specified, under section 403" omitted by Act 1 of 2018, s. 31 (w.e.f. 7-5-2018).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 22 of 2019, s. 19, for sub-section (3) (w.e.f. 2-11-2018).`
obj_root_law_sections_122:
  sectionId (1313)
  sectionNo (122)
  orderNo 125
  title `Applicability of this Chapter to One Person Company`
  content obj_root_law_sections_122_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_122_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=1313&sectionno=122&orderno=125&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_122_content:
  string
  line `(1) The provisions of section 98 and`
  line `sections 100 to 111 (both inclusive) shall not apply to a One Person Company.`
  line
  line `(2) The ordinary businesses as mentioned under clause (a) of sub-section (2) of section 102 which a`
  line `company, other than a One Person Company, is required to transact at its annual general meeting, shall be`
  line `transacted, in case of One Person Company, as provided in sub-section (3).`
  line
  line `(3) For the purposes of section 114, any business which is required to be transacted at an annual`
  line `general meeting or other general meeting of a company by means of an ordinary or special resolution, it`
  line `shall be sufficient if, in case of One Person Company, the resolution is communicated by the member to`
  line `the company and entered in the minutes-book required to be maintained under section 118 and signed and`
  line `dated by the member and such date shall be deemed to be the date of the meeting for all the purposes`
  line `under this Act.`
  line
  line `(4) Notwithstanding anything in this Act, where there is only one director on the Board of Director of`
  line `a One Person Company, any business which is required to be transacted at the meeting of the Board of`
  line `Directors of a company, it shall be sufficient if, in case of such One Person Company, the resolution by`
  line `such director is entered in the minutes-book required to be maintained under section 118 and signed and`
  line `dated by such director and such date shall be deemed to be the date of the meeting of the Board of`
  line `Directors for all the purposes under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_122_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_123:
  sectionId (1314)
  sectionNo (123)
  orderNo 126
  title `Declaration of dividend`
  content obj_root_law_sections_123_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_123_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=1314&sectionno=123&orderno=126&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_123_content:
  string
  line `(1) No dividend shall be declared or paid by a company for any`
  line `financial year except--`
  line
  line `(a) out of the profits of the company for that year arrived at after providing for depreciation in`
  line `accordance with the provisions of sub-section (2), or out of the profits of the company for any`
  line `previous financial year or years arrived at after providing for depreciation in accordance with the`
  line `provisions of that sub-section and remaining undistributed, or out of ^1[both:]`
  line
  line `^2[Provided that in computing profits any amount representing unrealised gains, notional gains or`
  line `revaluation of assets and any change in carrying amount of an asset or of a liability on measurement of the`
  line `asset or the liability at fair value shall be excluded; or]`
  line
  line `(b) out of money provided by the Central Government or a State Government for the payment of`
  line `dividend by the company in pursuance of a guarantee given by that Government:`
  line
  line `Provided that a company may, before the declaration of any dividend in any financial year, transfer`
  line `such percentage of its profits for that financial year as it may consider appropriate to the reserves of the`
  line `company:`
  line
  line `Provided further that where, owing to inadequacy or absence of profits in any financial year, any`
  line `company proposes to declare dividend out of the accumulated profits earned by it in previous years and ^3[transferred by the company to the free reserves], such declaration of dividend shall not be made except`
  line `in accordance with such rules as may be prescribed in this behalf:`
  line
  line `Provided also that no dividend shall be declared or paid by a company from its reserves other than`
  line `free reserves:`
  line
  line `^4[Provided also that no company shall declare dividend unless carried over previous losses and`
  line `depreciation not provided in previous year or years are set off against profit of the company for the`
  line `current year.]`
  line
  line `(2) For the purposes of clause (a) of sub-section (1), depreciation shall be provided in accordance`
  line `with the provisions of Schedule II.`
  line
  line `^5[(3) The Board of Directors of a company may declare interim dividend during any financial year or`
  line `at any time during the period from closure of financial year till holding of the annual general meeting out`
  line `of the surplus in the profit and loss account or out of profits of the financial year for which such interim`
  line `dividend is sought to be declared or out of profits generated in the financial year till the quarter preceding`
  line `the date of declaration of the interim dividend:]`
  line
  line `Provided that in case the company has incurred loss during the current financial year up to the end of`
  line `the quarter immediately preceding the date of declaration of interim dividend, such interim dividend shall`
  line `not be declared at a rate higher than the average dividends declared by the company during immediately`
  line `preceding three financial years.]`
  line
  line `(4) The amount of the dividend, including interim dividend, shall be deposited in a scheduled bank in`
  line `a separate account within five days from the date of declaration of such dividend.`
  line
  line `(5) No dividend shall be paid by a company in respect of any share therein except to the registered`
  line `shareholder of such share or to his order or to his banker and shall not be payable except in cash:`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing in this sub-section shall be deemed to prohibit the capitalisation of profits or`
  line `reserves of a company for the purpose of issuing fully paid-up bonus shares or paying up any amount for`
  line `the time being unpaid on any shares held by the members of the company:`
  line
  line `Provided further that any dividend payable in cash may be paid by cheque or warrant or in any`
  line `electronic mode to the shareholder entitled to the payment of the dividend.`
  line
  line `(6) A company which fails to comply with the provisions of sections 73 and 74 shall not, so long as`
  line `such failure continues, declare any dividend on its equity shares.`
obj_root_law_sections_123_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by s. 32, ibid., for "both; or" (w.e.f. 9-2-2018).`
  line
  line `2. The proviso ins. by s. 32, ibid. (w.e.f. 9-2-2018).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by s. 32, ibid., for "transferred by the company to the reserves" (w.e.f. 9-2-2018).`
  line
  line `4. The Proviso ins. by Act 21 of 2015, s. 10 (w.e.f. 29-5-2015).`
  line
  line `5. Subs. by Act 1 of 2018, s. 32, for sub-section (3) (w.e.f. 9-2-2018).`
obj_root_law_sections_124:
  sectionId (1315)
  sectionNo (124)
  orderNo 127
  title `Unpaid Dividend Account`
  content obj_root_law_sections_124_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_124_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=1315&sectionno=124&orderno=127&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_124_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where a dividend has been declared by a company but has not`
  line `been paid or claimed within thirty days from the date of the declaration to any shareholder entitled to the`
  line `payment of the dividend, the company shall, within seven days from the date of expiry of the said period`
  line `of thirty days, transfer the total amount of dividend which remains unpaid or unclaimed to a special`
  line `account to be opened by the company in that behalf in any scheduled bank to be called the Unpaid`
  line `Dividend Account.`
  line
  line `(2) The company shall, within a period of ninety days of making any transfer of an amount under`
  line `sub-section (1) to the Unpaid Dividend Account, prepare a statement containing the names, their last`
  line `known addresses and the unpaid dividend to be paid to each person and place it on the website of the`
  line `company, if any, and also on any other website approved by the Central Government for this purpose, in`
  line `such form, manner and other particulars as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(3) If any default is made in transferring the total amount referred to in sub-section (1) or any part`
  line `thereof to the Unpaid Dividend Account of the company, it shall pay, from the date of such default,`
  line `interest on so much of the amount as has not been transferred to the said account, at the rate of twelve`
  line `per cent. per annum and the interest accruing on such amount shall ensure to the benefit of the members`
  line `of the company in proportion to the amount remaining unpaid to them.`
  line
  line `(4) Any person claiming to be entitled to any money transferred under sub-section (1) to the Unpaid`
  line `Dividend Account of the company may apply to the company for payment of the money claimed.`
  line
  line `(5) Any money transferred to the Unpaid Dividend Account of a company in pursuance of this section`
  line `which remains unpaid or unclaimed for a period of seven years from the date of such transfer shall be`
  line `transferred by the company along with interest accrued, if any, thereon to the Fund established under sub-section (1) of section 125 and the company shall send a statement in the prescribed form of the details`
  line `of such transfer to the authority which administers the said Fund and that authority shall issue a receipt to`
  line `the company as evidence of such transfer.`
  line
  line `(6) All shares in respect of which^1[dividend has not been paid or claimed for seven consecutive years`
  line `or more shall be] transferred by the company in the name of Investor Education and Protection Fund`
  line `along with a statement containing such details as may be prescribed:`
  line
  line `Provided that any claimant of shares transferred above shall be entitled to claim the transfer of shares`
  line `from Investor Education and Protection Fund in accordance with such procedure and on submission of`
  line `such documents as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `^2[Explanation.-- For the removal of doubts, it is hereby clarified that in case any dividend is paid or`
  line `claimed for any year during the said period of seven consecutive years, the share shall not be transferred`
  line `to Investor Education and Protection Fund.]`
  line
  line `(7) If a company fails to comply with any of the requirements of this section, the company shall be`
  line `punishable with fine which shall not be less than five lakh rupees but which may extend to twenty-five`
  line `lakh rupees and every officer of the company who is in default shall be punishable with fine which shall`
  line `not be less than one lakh rupees but which may extend to five lakh rupees.`
obj_root_law_sections_124_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 21 of 2015, s. 11, for "unpaid or unclaimed dividend has been transferred under sub-section (5) shall also be"`
  line `(w.e.f. 29-5-2015).`
  line
  line `2. The Explanation ins. by s. 11, ibid. (w.e.f. 29-5-2015).`
obj_root_law_sections_125:
  sectionId (1316)
  sectionNo (125)
  orderNo 128
  title `Investor Education and Protection Fund.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_125_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_125_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=1316&sectionno=125&orderno=128&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_125_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government shall establish a`
  line `Fund to be called the Investor Education and Protection Fund (herein referred to as the Fund).`
  line
  line `(2) There shall be credited to the Fund--`
  line
  line `(a) the amount given by the Central Government by way of grants after due appropriation made`
  line `by Parliament by law in this behalf for being utilised for the purposes of the Fund;`
  line
  line `(b) donations given to the Fund by the Central Government, State Governments, companies or`
  line `any other institution for the purposes of the Fund;`
  line
  line `(c) the amount in the Unpaid Dividend Account of companies transferred to the Fund under subsection`
  line `(5) of section 124;`
  line
  line `(d) the amount in the general revenue account of the Central Government which had been`
  line `transferred to that account under sub-section (5) of section 205A of the Companies Act, 1956 (1 of`
  line `1956), as it stood immediately before the commencement of the Companies (Amendment) Act, 1999`
  line `(21 of 1999), and remaining unpaid or unclaimed on the commencement of this Act;`
  line
  line `(e) the amount lying in the Investor Education and Protection Fund under section 205C of the`
  line `Companies Act, 1956 (1 of 1956);`
  line
  line `(f) the interest or other income received out of investments made from the Fund;`
  line
  line `(g) the amount received under sub-section (4) of section 38;`
  line
  line `(h) the application money received by companies for allotment of any securities and due for`
  line refund;
  line
  line `(i) matured deposits with companies other than banking companies;`
  line
  line `(j) matured debentures with companies;`
  line
  line `(k) interest accrued on the amounts referred to in clauses (h) to (j);`
  line
  line `(l) sale proceeds of fractional shares arising out of issuance of bonus shares, merger and`
  line `amalgamation for seven or more years;`
  line
  line `(m) redemption amount of preference shares remaining unpaid or unclaimed for seven or more`
  line `years; and`
  line
  line `(n) such other amount as may be prescribed:`
  line
  line `Provided that no such amount referred to in clauses (h) to (j) shall form part of the Fund unless such`
  line `amount has remained unclaimed and unpaid for a period of seven years from the date it became due for`
  line payment.
  line
  line `(3) The Fund shall be utilised for--`
  line
  line `(a) the refund in respect of unclaimed dividends, matured deposits, matured debentures, the`
  line `application money due for refund and interest thereon;`
  line
  line `(b) promotion of investors education, awareness and protection;`
  line
  line `(c) distribution of any disgorged amount among eligible and identifiable applicants for shares or`
  line `debentures, shareholders, debenture-holders or depositors who have suffered losses due to wrong`
  line `actions by any person, in accordance with the orders made by the Court which had ordered`
  line disgorgement;
  line
  line `(d) reimbursement of legal expenses incurred in pursuing class action suits under sections 37 and`
  line `245 by members, debenture-holders or depositors as may be sanctioned by the Tribunal; and`
  line
  line `(e) any other purpose incidental thereto,`
  line
  line `in accordance with such rules as may be prescribed:`
  line
  line `Provided that the person whose amounts referred to in clauses (a) to (d) of sub-section (2) of section`
  line `205C transferred to Investor Education and Protection Fund, after the expiry of the period of seven years`
  line `as per provisions of the Companies Act, 1956 (1 of 1956), shall be entitled to get refund out of the Fund`
  line `in respect of such claims in accordance with rules made under this section.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--The disgorged amount refers to the amount received through disgorgement or disposal`
  line `of securities.`
  line
  line `(4) Any person claiming to be entitled to the amount referred in sub-section (2) may apply to the`
  line `authority constituted under sub-section (5) for the payment of the money claimed.`
  line
  line `(5) The Central Government shall constitute, by notification, an authority for administration of the`
  line `Fund consisting of a chairperson and such other members, not exceeding seven and a chief executive`
  line `officer, as the Central Government may appoint.`
  line
  line `(6) The manner of administration of the Fund, appointment of chairperson, members and chief`
  line `executive officer, holding of meetings of the authority shall be in accordance with such rules as may be`
  line prescribed.
  line
  line `(7) The Central Government may provide to the authority such offices, officers, employees and other`
  line `resources in accordance with such rules as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(8) The authority shall administer the Fund and maintain separate accounts and other relevant records`
  line `in relation to the Fund in such form as may be prescribed after consultation with the Comptroller and`
  line `Auditor-General of India.`
  line
  line `(9) It shall be competent for the authority constituted under sub-section (5) to spend money out of the`
  line `Fund for carrying out the objects specified in sub-section (3).`
  line
  line `(10) The accounts of the Fund shall be audited by the Comptroller and Auditor-General of India at`
  line `such intervals as may be specified by him and such audited accounts together with the audit report`
  line `thereon shall be forwarded annually by the authority to the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(11) The authority shall prepare in such form and at such time for each financial year as may be`
  line `prescribed its annual report giving a full account of its activities during the financial year and forward a`
  line `copy thereof to the Central Government and the Central Government shall cause the annual report and the`
  line `audit report given by the Comptroller and Auditor-General of India to be laid before each House of`
  line Parliament.
obj_root_law_sections_125_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_126:
  sectionId (1317)
  sectionNo (126)
  orderNo 129
  title `Right to dividend, rights shares and bonus shares to be held in abeyance pending registration of transfer of shares.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_126_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_126_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=1317&sectionno=126&orderno=129&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_126_content:
  string
  line `Where any instrument of transfer of shares has been delivered to`
  line `any company for registration and the transfer of such shares has not been registered by the company, it`
  line `shall, notwithstanding anything contained in any other provision of this Act,--`
  line
  line `(a) transfer the dividend in relation to such shares to the Unpaid Dividend Account referred to in`
  line `section 124 unless the company is authorised by the registered holder of such shares in writing to pay`
  line `such dividend to the transferee specified in such instrument of transfer; and`
  line
  line `(b) keep in abeyance in relation to such shares, any offer of rights shares under clause (a) of subsection`
  line `(1) of section 62 and any issue of fully paid-up bonus shares in pursuance of first proviso to`
  line `sub-section (5) of section 123.`
obj_root_law_sections_126_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_127:
  sectionId (1318)
  sectionNo (127)
  orderNo 130
  title `Punishment for failure to distribute dividends.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_127_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_127_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=1318&sectionno=127&orderno=130&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_127_content:
  string
  line `Where a dividend has been declared by a`
  line `company but has not been paid or the warrant in respect thereof has not been posted within thirty days`
  line `from the date of declaration to any shareholder entitled to the payment of the dividend, every director of`
  line `the company shall, if he is knowingly a party to the default, be punishable with imprisonment which may`
  line `extend to two years and with fine which shall not be less than one thousand rupees for every day during`
  line `which such default continues and the company shall be liable to pay simple interest at the rate of eighteen`
  line `per cent. per annum during the period for which such default continues:`
  line
  line `Provided that no offence under this section shall be deemed to have been committed:--`
  line
  line `(a) where the dividend could not be paid by reason of the operation of any law;`
  line
  line `(b) where a shareholder has given directions to the company regarding the payment of the`
  line `dividend and those directions cannot be complied with and the same has been communicated to him;`
  line
  line `(c) where there is a dispute regarding the right to receive the dividend;`
  line
  line `(d) where the dividend has been lawfully adjusted by the company against any sum due to it from`
  line `the shareholder; or`
  line
  line `(e) where, for any other reason, the failure to pay the dividend or to post the warrant within the`
  line `period under this section was not due to any default on the part of the company.`
obj_root_law_sections_127_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_128:
  sectionId (1319)
  sectionNo (128)
  orderNo 131
  title `Books of account, etc., to be kept by company`
  content obj_root_law_sections_128_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_128_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=1319&sectionno=128&orderno=131&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_128_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every company shall prepare and keep at`
  line `its registered office books of account and other relevant books and papers and financial statement for`
  line `every financial year which give a true and fair view of the state of the affairs of the company, including`
  line `that of its branch office or offices, if any, and explain the transactions effected both at the registered office`
  line `and its branches and such books shall be kept on accrual basis and according to the double entry system`
  line `of accounting:`
  line
  line `Provided that all or any of the books of account aforesaid and other relevant papers may be kept at`
  line `such other place in India as the Board of Directors may decide and where such a decision is taken, the`
  line `company shall, within seven days thereof, file with the Registrar a notice in writing giving the full address`
  line `of that other place:`
  line
  line `Provided further that the company may keep such books of account or other relevant papers in`
  line `electronic mode in such manner as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(2) Where a company has a branch office in India or outside India, it shall be deemed to have`
  line `complied with the provisions of sub-section (1), if proper books of account relating to the transactions`
  line `effected at the branch office are kept at that office and proper summarized returns periodically are sent by`
  line `the branch office to the company at its registered office or the other place referred to in sub-section (1).`
  line
  line `(3) The books of account and other books and papers maintained by the company within India shall`
  line `be open for inspection at the registered office of the company or at such other place in India by any`
  line `director during business hours, and in the case of financial information, if any, maintained outside the`
  line `country, copies of such financial information shall be maintained and produced for inspection by any`
  line `director subject to such conditions as may be prescribed:`
  line
  line `Provided that the inspection in respect of any subsidiary of the company shall be done only by the`
  line `person authorised in this behalf by a resolution of the Board of Directors.`
  line
  line `(4) Where an inspection is made under sub-section (3), the officers and other employees of the`
  line `company shall give to the person making such inspection all assistance in connection with the inspection`
  line `which the company may reasonably be expected to give.`
  line
  line `(5) The books of account of every company relating to a period of not less than eight financial years`
  line `immediately preceding a financial year, or where the company had been in existence for a period less than`
  line `eight years, in respect of all the preceding years together with the vouchers relevant to any entry in such`
  line `books of account shall be kept in good order:`
  line
  line `Provided that where an investigation has been ordered in respect of the company under Chapter XIV,`
  line `the Central Government may direct that the books of account may be kept for such longer period as it`
  line `may deem fit.`
  line
  line `(6) If the managing director, the whole-time director in charge of finance, the Chief Financial Officer`
  line `or any other person of a company charged by the Board with the duty of complying with the provisions of`
  line `this section, contravenes such provisions, such managing director, whole-time director in charge of`
  line `finance, Chief Financial Officer or such other person of the company shall be punishable ^1*** with fine`
  line `which shall not be less than fifty thousand rupees but which may extend to five lakh rupees ^2***.`
obj_root_law_sections_128_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. The words [with imprisonment for a term which may extend to one year or] omitted by Act 29 of 2020, s. 24 (w.e.f. 21-21-`
  line `2020).`
  line
  line `2. The words [or with both] omitted by s. 24, ibid. (w.e.f. 21-12-2020).`
obj_root_law_sections_129:
  sectionId (1320)
  sectionNo (129)
  orderNo 132
  title `Financial statement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_129_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 1 of 2018, s. 33, for sub-section (3) (w.e.f. 7-5-2018).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=1320&sectionno=129&orderno=132&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_129_content:
  string
  line `(1) The financial statements shall give a true and fair view of the state`
  line `of affairs of the company or companies, comply with the accounting standards notified under section 133`
  line `and shall be in the form or forms as may be provided for different class or classes of companies in`
  line `Schedule III:`
  line
  line `Provided that the items contained in such financial statements shall be in accordance with the`
  line `accounting standards:`
  line
  line `Provided further that nothing contained in this sub-section shall apply to any insurance or banking`
  line `company or any company engaged in the generation or supply of electricity, or to any other class of`
  line `company for which a form of financial statement has been specified in or under the Act governing such`
  line `class of company:`
  line
  line `Provided also that the financial statements shall not be treated as not disclosing a true and fair view`
  line `of the state of affairs of the company, merely by reason of the fact that they do not disclose--`
  line
  line `(a) in the case of an insurance company, any matters which are not required to be disclosed by the`
  line `Insurance Act, 1938 (4 of 1938), or the Insurance Regulatory and Development Authority Act, 1999`
  line `(41 of 1999);`
  line
  line `(b) in the case of a banking company, any matters which are not required to be disclosed by the`
  line `Banking Regulation Act, 1949 (10 of 1949);`
  line
  line `(c) in the case of a company engaged in the generation or supply of electricity, any matters which`
  line `are not required to be disclosed by the Electricity Act, 2003 (36 of 2003);`
  line
  line `(d) in the case of a company governed by any other law for the time being in force, any matters`
  line `which are not required to be disclosed by that law.`
  line
  line `(2) At every annual general meeting of a company, the Board of Directors of the company shall lay`
  line `before such meeting financial statements for the financial year.`
  line
  line `^1[(3) Where a company has one or more subsidiaries, it shall, in addition to financial statements`
  line `provided under sub-section (2), prepare a consolidated financial statement of the company and of all the`
  line `subsidiaries in the same form and manner as that of its own which shall also be laid before the annual`
  line `general meeting of the company along with the laying of its financial statement under sub-section (2):`
  line
  line `Provided that the company shall also attach along with its financial statement, a separate statement`
  line `containing the salient features of the financial statement of its subsidiary or subsidiaries in such form as`
  line `may be prescribed:`
  line
  line `Provided further that the Central Government may provide for the consolidation of accounts of`
  line `companies in such manner as may be prescribed.]`
  line
  line `(4) The provisions of this Act applicable to the preparation, adoption and audit of the financial`
  line `statements of a holding company shall, mutatis mutandis, apply to the consolidated financial statements`
  line `referred to in sub-section (3).`
  line
  line `(5) Without prejudice to sub-section (1), where the financial statements of a company do not comply`
  line `with the accounting standards referred to in sub-section (1), the company shall disclose in its financial`
  line `statements, the deviation from the accounting standards, the reasons for such deviation and the financial`
  line `effects, if any, arising out of such deviation`
  line
  line `(6) The Central Government may, on its own or on an application by a class or classes of companies,`
  line `by notification, exempt any class or classes of companies from complying with any of the requirements of`
  line `this section or the rules made thereunder, if it is considered necessary to grant such exemption in the`
  line `public interest and any such exemption may be granted either unconditionally or subject to such`
  line `conditions as may be specified in the notification.`
  line
  line `(7) If a company contravenes the provisions of this section, the managing director, the whole-time`
  line `director in charge of finance, the Chief Financial Officer or any other person charged by the Board with`
  line `the duty of complying with the requirements of this section and in the absence of any of the officers`
  line `mentioned above, all the directors shall be punishable with imprisonment for a term which may extend to`
  line `one year or with fine which shall not be less than fifty thousand rupees but which may extend to five lakh`
  line `rupees, or with both.`
  line
  line `Explanation.-- For the purposes of this section, except where the context otherwise requires, any`
  line `reference to the financial statement shall include any notes annexed to or forming part of such financial`
  line `statement, giving information required to be given and allowed to be given in the form of such notes`
  line `under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_129_a:
  sectionId (51984)
  sectionNo 129A
  orderNo 133
  title `Periodical financial results.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_129_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 29 of 2020, s. 25 (w.e.f. 22-1-2021).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=51984&sectionno=129A&orderno=133&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_129_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[129A. Periodical financial results.--The Central Government may, require such class or classes of unlisted companies, as may be prescribed,--`
  line
  line `(a) to prepare the financial results of the company on such periodical basis and in such form as may be prescribed;`
  line
  line `(b) to obtain approval of the Board of Directors and complete audit or limited review of such periodical financial results in such manner as may be prescribed; and`
  line
  line `(c) file a copy with the Registrar within a period of thirty days of completion of the relevant period with such fees as may be prescribed.]`
obj_root_law_sections_130:
  sectionId (1321)
  sectionNo (130)
  orderNo 134
  title `Re-opening of accounts on court‘s or Tribunal‘s orders`
  content obj_root_law_sections_130_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_130_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=1321&sectionno=130&orderno=134&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_130_content:
  string
  line `(1) A company shall not re-open`
  line `its books of account and not recast its financial statements, unless an application in this regard is made by`
  line `the Central Government, the Income-tax authorities, the Securities and Exchange Board, any other`
  line `statutory regulatory body or authority or any person concerned and an order is made by a court of`
  line `competent jurisdiction or the Tribunal to the effect that--`
  line
  line `(i) the relevant earlier accounts were prepared in a fraudulent manner; or`
  line
  line `(ii) the affairs of the company were mismanaged during the relevant period, casting a doubt on`
  line `the reliability of financial statements:`
  line
  line `Provided that the court or the Tribunal, as the case may be, shall give notice to the Central`
  line `Government, the Income-tax authorities, the Securities and Exchange Board or any other statutory`
  line `regulatory body or authority concerned ^1[or any other person concerned] and shall take into`
  line `consideration the representations, if any, made by that Government or the authorities, Securities and`
  line `Exchange Board or the body or authority concerned ^1[or the other person concerned] before passing any`
  line `order under this section.`
  line
  line `(2) Without prejudice to the provisions contained in this Act the accounts so revised or re-cast under`
  line `sub-section (1) shall be final.`
  line
  line `^2[(3) No order shall be made under sub-section (1) in respect of re-opening of books of account`
  line `relating to a period earlier than eight financial years immediately preceding the current financial year:`
  line
  line `Provided that where a direction has been issued by the Central Government under the proviso to`
  line `sub-section (5) of section 128 for keeping of books of account for a period longer than eight years, the`
  line `books of account may be ordered to be re-opened within such longer period.]`
obj_root_law_sections_130_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 1 of 2018, s. 34 (w.e.f. 9-2-2018).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by Act 1 of 2018, s. 34 (w.e.f. 9-2-2018)`
obj_root_law_sections_131:
  sectionId (1322)
  sectionNo (131)
  orderNo 135
  title `Voluntary revision of financial statements or Board‘s report`
  content obj_root_law_sections_131_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_131_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=1322&sectionno=131&orderno=135&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_131_content:
  string
  line `(1) If it appears to the`
  line `directors of a company that--`
  line
  line `(a) the financial statement of the company; or`
  line
  line `(b) the report of the Board,`
  line
  line `do not comply with the provisions of section 129 or section 134 they may prepare revised financial`
  line `statement or a revised report in respect of any of the three preceding financial years after obtaining`
  line `approval of the Tribunal on an application made by the company in such form and manner as may be`
  line `prescribed and a copy of the order passed by the Tribunal shall be filed with the Registrar:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Tribunal shall give notice to the Central Government and the Income-tax authorities`
  line `and shall take into consideration the representations, if any, made by that Government or the authorities`
  line `before passing any order under this section:`
  line
  line `Provided further that such revised financial statement or report shall not be prepared or filed more`
  line `than once in a financial year:`
  line
  line `Provided also that the detailed reasons for revision of such financial statement or report shall also be`
  line `disclosed in the Board's report in the relevant financial year in which such revision is being made.`
  line
  line `(2) Where copies of the previous financial statement or report have been sent out to members or`
  line `delivered to the Registrar or laid before the company in general meeting, the revisions must be confined`
  line to--
  line
  line `(a) the correction in respect of which the previous financial statement or report do not comply`
  line `with the provisions of section 129 or section 134; and`
  line
  line `(b) the making of any necessary consequential alternation.`
  line
  line `(3) The Central Government may make rules as to the application of the provisions of this Act in`
  line `relation to revised financial statement or a revised director's report and such rules may, in particular--`
  line
  line `(a) make different provisions according to which the previous financial statement or report are`
  line `replaced or are supplemented by a document indicating the corrections to be made;`
  line
  line `(b) make provisions with respect to the functions of the company's auditor in relation to the`
  line `revised financial statement or report;`
  line
  line `(c) require the directors to take such steps as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_131_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_132:
  sectionId (1323)
  sectionNo (132)
  orderNo 136
  title `Constitution of National Financial Reporting Authority`
  content obj_root_law_sections_132_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_132_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=1323&sectionno=132&orderno=136&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_132_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may,`
  line `by notification, constitute a National Financial Reporting Authority to provide for matters relating to`
  line `accounting and auditing standards under this Act.`
  line
  line `^1[(1A) The National Financial Reporting Authority shall perform its functions through such divisions`
  line `as may be prescribed.]`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in any other law for the time being in force, the National`
  line `Financial Reporting Authority shall--`
  line
  line `(a) make recommendations to the Central Government on the formulation and laying down of`
  line `accounting and auditing policies and standards for adoption by companies or class of companies or`
  line `their auditors, as the case may be;`
  line
  line `(b) monitor and enforce the compliance with accounting standards and auditing standards in such`
  line `manner as may be prescribed;`
  line
  line `(c) over see the quality of service of the professions associated with ensuring compliance with`
  line `such standards, and suggest measures required for improvement in quality of service and such other`
  line `related matters as may be prescribed; and`
  line
  line `(d) perform such other functions relating to clauses (a), (b) and (c) as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(3) The National Financial Reporting Authority shall consist of a chairperson, who shall be a person`
  line `of eminence and having expertise in accountancy, auditing, finance or law to be appointed by the Central`
  line `Government and such other members not exceeding fifteen consisting of part-time and full-time members`
  line `as may be prescribed:`
  line
  line `Provided that the terms and conditions and the manner of appointment of the chairperson and`
  line `members shall be such as may be prescribed:`
  line
  line `Provided further that the chairperson and members shall make a declaration to the Central`
  line `Government in the prescribed form regarding no conflict of interest or lack of independence in respect of`
  line `his or their appointment:`
  line
  line `Provided also that the chairperson and members, who are in full-time employment with National`
  line `Financial Reporting Authority shall not be associated with any audit firm (including related consultancy`
  line `firms) during the course of their appointment and two years after ceasing to hold such appointment.`
  line
  line `^2[(3A) Each division of the National Financial Reporting Authority shall be presided over by the`
  line `Chairperson or a full-time Member authorized by the Chairperson.`
  line
  line `(3B) There shall be an executive body of the National Financial Reporting Authority consisting of the`
  line `Chairperson and full-time Members of such Authority for efficient discharge of its functions under`
  line `sub-section (2) [other than clause (a) and sub-section (4).]`
  line
  line `(4) Notwithstanding anything contained in any other law for the time being in force, the National`
  line `Financial Reporting Authority shall--`
  line
  line `(a) have the power to investigate, either suo motu or on a reference made to it by the Central`
  line `Government, for such class of bodies corporate or persons, in such manners may be prescribed into`
  line `the matters of professional or other misconduct committed by any member or firm of chartered`
  line `accountants, registered under the Chartered Accountants Act, 1949 (38 of 1949):`
  line
  line `Provided that no other institute or body shall initiate or continue any proceedings in such matters`
  line `of misconduct where the National Financial Reporting Authority has initiated an investigation under`
  line `this section;`
  line
  line `(b) have the same powers as are vested in a civil court under the Code of Civil Procedure, 1908`
  line `(5 of 1908), while trying a suit, in respect of the following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(i) discovery and production of books of account and other documents, at such place and at`
  line `such time as may be specified by the National Financial Reporting Authority;`
  line
  line `(ii) summoning and enforcing the attendance of persons and examining them on oath;`
  line
  line `(iii) inspection of any books, registers and other documents of any person referred to in`
  line `clause (b) at any place;`
  line
  line `(iv) issuing commissions for examination of witnesses or documents;`
  line
  line `(c) where professional or other misconduct is proved, have the power to make order for--`
  line
  line `(A) imposing penalty of--`
  line
  line `(I) not less than one lakh rupees, but which may extend to five times of the fees received,`
  line `in case of individuals; and`
  line `(II) not less than ^2[five lakh rupees], but which may extend to ten times of the fees`
  line `received, in case of firms;`
  line
  line `^3[(B) debarring the member or the firm from--`
  line
  line `I. being appointed as an auditor or internal auditor or undertaking any audit in respect t of`
  line `financial statements or internal audit of the functions and activities of any company or body`
  line `corporate; or`
  line
  line `II. performing any valuation as provided under section 247,`
  line
  line `for a minimum period of six months or such higher period not exceeding ten years as may be`
  line `determined by the National Financial Reporting Authority.]`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purposes of this sub-section, the expression "professional or other misconduct"`
  line `shall have the same meaning assigned to it under section 22 of the Chartered Accountants Act, 1949`
  line `(38 of 1949).`
  line
  line `(5) Any person aggrieved by any order of the National Financial Reporting Authority issued under`
  line `clause (c) of sub-section (4), may prefer an appeal before ^4[the Appellate Tribunal in such manner and on`
  line `payment of such fee as may be prescribed].`
  line
  line `^5* * * * *`
  line
  line `(10) The National Financial Reporting Authority shall meet at such times and places and shall`
  line `observe such rules of procedure in regard to the transaction of business at its meetings in such manner as`
  line `may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(11) The Central Government may appoint a secretary and such other employees as it may consider`
  line `necessary for the efficient performance of functions by the National Financial Reporting Authority under`
  line `this Act and the terms and conditions of service of the secretary and employees shall be such as may be`
  line prescribed.
  line
  line `(12) The head office of the National Financial Reporting Authority shall be at New Delhi and the`
  line `National Financial Reporting Authority may, meet at such other places in India as it deems fit.`
  line
  line `(13) The National Financial Reporting Authority shall cause to be maintained such books of account`
  line `and other books in relation to its accounts in such form and in such manner as the Central Government`
  line `may, in consultation with the Comptroller and Auditor-General of India prescribe.`
  line
  line `(14) The accounts of the National Financial Reporting Authority shall be audited by the Comptroller`
  line `and Auditor-General of India at such intervals as may be specified by him and such accounts as certified`
  line `by the Comptroller and Auditor-General of India together with the audit report thereon shall be forwarded`
  line `annually to the Central Government by the National Financial Reporting Authority.`
  line
  line `(15) The National Financial Reporting Authority shall prepare in such form and at such time for each`
  line `financial year as may be prescribed its annual report giving a full account of its activities during the financial year and forward a copy thereof to the Central Government and the Central Government shall`
  line `cause the annual report and the audit report given by the Comptroller and Auditor-General of India to be`
  line `laid before each House of Parliament.`
obj_root_law_sections_132_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 22 of 2019, s. 20 (w.e.f. 15-8-2019).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 1 of 2018, s. 35, for "ten lakh rupees" (w.e.f. 9-2-2018).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 22 of 2019, s. 20, for sub-clause (b) (w.e.f. 15-8-2019).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by s. 35, ibid., for "the Appellate Authority constituted under sub-section (6) in such manner as may be prescribed"`
  line `(w.e.f. 9-2-2018).`
  line
  line `5. Sub-sections (6), (7), (8) and (9) omitted by s. 35, ibid. (w.e.f. 9-2-2018).`
obj_root_law_sections_133:
  sectionId (1324)
  sectionNo (133)
  orderNo 137
  title `Central Government to prescribe accounting standards`
  content obj_root_law_sections_133_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by notification No. S.O. 1227(E), dated 29th March, 2016 (w.e.f 1-4-2015).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=1324&sectionno=133&orderno=137&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_133_content:
  string
  line `The Central Government may`
  line `prescribe the standards of accounting or any addendum thereto, as recommended by the Institute of`
  line `Chartered Accountants of India, constituted under section 3 of the Chartered Accountants Act, 1949`
  line `(38 of 1949), in consultation with and after examination of the recommendations made by the National`
  line `Financial Reporting Authority:`
  line
  line `^1[Provided that until the National Financial Reporting Authority is constituted under section 132 of`
  line `the Companies Act, 2013 (18 of 2013), the Central Government may prescribe the standards of`
  line `accounting or any addendum thereto, as recommended by the Institute of Chartered Accountants of India,`
  line `constituted under section 3 of the Chartered Accountants Act, 1949 (38 of 1949), in consultation with and`
  line `after examination of the recommendations made by National Advisory Committee on Accounting`
  line `Standards constituted under section 210A of the Companies Act, 1956 (1 of 1956).]`
obj_root_law_sections_134:
  sectionId (1325)
  sectionNo (134)
  orderNo 138
  title `Financial statement, Board‘s report, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_134_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_134_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=1325&sectionno=134&orderno=138&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_134_content:
  string
  line `^1[(1) The financial statement, including`
  line `consolidated financial statement, if any, shall be approved by the Board of Directors before they are`
  line `signed on behalf of the Board by the chairperson of the company where he is authorised by the Board or`
  line `by two directors out of which one shall be managing director, if any, and the Chief Executive Officer, the Chief Financial Officer and the company secretary of the company, wherever they are appointed, or in the`
  line `case of One Person Company, only by one director, for submission to the auditor for his report thereon.]`
  line
  line `(2) The auditors report shall be attached to every financial statement.`
  line
  line `(3) There shall be attached to statements laid before a company in general meeting, a report by its Board of`
  line `Directors, which shall include--`
  line
  line `^2[(a) the web address, if any, where annual return referred to in sub-section (3) of section 92 has been`
  line placed;]
  line
  line `(b) number of meetings of the Board;`
  line
  line `(c) Directors Responsibility Statement;`
  line
  line `^3[(ca) details in respect of frauds reported by auditors under sub-section (12) of section 143 other than`
  line `those which are reportable to the Central Government;]`
  line
  line `(d) a statement on declaration given by independent directors under sub-section (6) of section 149;`
  line
  line `(e) in case of a company covered under sub-section (1) of section 178, companys policy on directors`
  line `appointment and remuneration including criteria for determining qualifications, positive attributes,`
  line `independence of a director and other matters provided under sub-section (3) of section 178;`
  line
  line `(f) explanations or comments by the Board on every qualification, reservation or adverse remark or`
  line `disclaimer made--`
  line
  line `(i) by the auditor in his report; and`
  line
  line `(ii) by the company secretary in practice in his secretarial audit report;`
  line
  line `(g) particulars of loans, guarantees or investments under section 186;`
  line
  line `(h) particulars of contracts or arrangements with related parties referred to in sub-section (1) of section`
  line `188 in the prescribed form;`
  line
  line `(i) the state of the companys affairs;`
  line
  line `(j) the amounts, if any, which it proposes to carry to any reserves;`
  line
  line `(k) the amount, if any, which it recommends should be paid by way of dividend;`
  line
  line `(l) material changes and commitments, if any, affecting the financial position of the company which`
  line `have occurred between the end of the financial year of the company to which the financial statements`
  line `relate and the date of the report;`
  line
  line `(m) the conservation of energy, technology absorption, foreign exchange earnings and outgo, in such`
  line `manner as may be prescribed;`
  line
  line `(n) a statement indicating development and implementation of a risk management policy for the`
  line `company including identification therein of elements of risk, if any, which in the opinion of the Board may`
  line `threaten the existence of the company;`
  line
  line `(o) the details about the policy developed and implemented by the company incorporate social`
  line `responsibility initiatives taken during the year;`
  line
  line `(p) in case of a listed company and every other public company having such paid-up share capital as`
  line `may be prescribed, a statement indicating the manner in which formal ^4`
  line `annual evaluation of the`
  line `performance of the Board, its Committees and of individual directors has been made;`
  line
  line `(q) such other matters as may be prescribed:`
  line
  line `^5[Provided that where disclosures referred to in this sub-section have been included in the financial`
  line `statements, such disclosures shall be referred to instead of being repeated in the Board's report:`
  line
  line `Provided further that where the policy referred to in clause (e) or clause (o) is made available on`
  line `company's website, if any, it shall be sufficient compliance of the requirements under such clauses if the`
  line `salient features of the policy and any change therein are specified in brief in the Board's report and the`
  line `web-address is indicated therein at which the complete policy is available.]`
  line
  line `^6[(3A) The Central Government may prescribe an abridged Board's report, for the purpose of compliance`
  line `with this section by One Person Company or small company.]`
  line
  line `(4) The report of the Board of Directors to be attached to the financial statement under this section shall, in`
  line `case of a One Person Company, mean a report containing explanations or comments by the Board on every`
  line `qualification, reservation or adverse remark or disclaimer made by the auditor in his report.`
  line
  line `(5) The Directors Responsibility Statement referred to in clause (c) of sub-section (3) shall state`
  line that--
  line
  line `(a) in the preparation of the annual accounts, the applicable accounting standards had been`
  line `followed along with proper explanation relating to material departures;`
  line
  line `(b) the directors had selected such accounting policies and applied them consistently and made`
  line `judgments and estimates that are reasonable and prudent so as to give a true and fair view of the state`
  line `of affairs of the company at the end of the financial year and of the profit and loss of the company for`
  line `that period;`
  line
  line `(c) the directors had taken proper and sufficient care for the maintenance of adequate accounting`
  line `records in accordance with the provisions of this Act for safeguarding the assets of the company and`
  line `for preventing and detecting fraud another irregularities;`
  line
  line `(d) the directors had prepared the annual accounts on a going concern basis; and`
  line
  line `(e) the directors, in the case of a listed company, had laid down internal financial controls to be`
  line `followed by the company and that such internal financial controls are adequate and were operating`
  line effectively.
  line
  line `Explanation.-- For the purposes of this clause, the term internal financial controls means the`
  line `policies and procedures adopted by the company for ensuring the orderly and efficient conduct of its`
  line `business, including adherence to companys policies, the safeguarding of its assets, the prevention`
  line `and detection of frauds and errors, the accuracy and completeness of the accounting records, and the`
  line `timely preparation of reliable financial information;`
  line
  line `(f) the directors had devised proper systems to ensure compliance with the provisions of all`
  line `applicable laws and that such systems were adequate and operating effectively.`
  line
  line `(6) The Boards report and any annexures thereto under sub-section (3) shall be signed by its`
  line `chairperson of the company if he is authorised by the Board and where he is not so authorised, shall be`
  line `signed by at least two directors, one of whom shall be a managing director, or by the director where there`
  line `is one director.`
  line
  line `(7) A signed copy of every financial statement, including consolidated financial statement, if any,`
  line `shall be issued, circulated or published along with a copy each of--`
  line
  line `(a) any notes annexed to or forming part of such financial statement;`
  line
  line `(b) the auditors report; and`
  line
  line `(c) the Boards report referred to in sub-section (3).`
  line
  line ^7
  line `[(8) If a company is in default in complying with the provisions of this section, the company shall`
  line `be liable to a penalty of three lakh rupees and every officer of the company who is in default shall be`
  line `liable to a penalty of fifty thousand rupees.]`
obj_root_law_sections_134_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 1 of 2018, s. 36 (w.e.f. 31-7-2018).`
  line
  line `2. Subs by Act 1 of 2018, s. 36, for clause (a) (w.e.f. 31-7-2018).`
  line
  line `3. Ins. by Act 21 of 2015, s. 12 (w.e.f. 29-5-2015).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by Act 1 of 2018, s. 36 for "annual evaluation has been made by the Board of its own performance and that of its`
  line `committees and individual directors" (w.e.f. 31-7-2018).`
  line
  line `5. The provisos ins. by s. 36, ibid., (w.e.f. 31-7-2018).`
  line
  line `6. Sub-section (3A) ins. by s. 36, ibid., (w.e.f. 31-7-2018).`
  line
  line `7. Subs. by Act 29 of 2020, s. 26, for sub-section (8) (w.e.f. 21-12-2020).`
obj_root_law_sections_135:
  sectionId (1326)
  sectionNo (135)
  orderNo 139
  title `Corporate Social Responsibility`
  content obj_root_law_sections_135_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_135_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=1326&sectionno=135&orderno=139&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_135_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every company having net worth of rupees five hundred crore or more, or turnover of rupees one thousand crore or more or a net profit of rupees five crore or more during ^1[the immediately preceding financial year] shall constitute a Corporate Social Responsibility Committee of the Board consisting of three or more directors, out of which at least one director shall be an independent director:`
  line
  line `^2[Provided that where a company is not required to appoint an independent director under sub-section (4) of section 149, it shall have in its Corporate Social Responsibility Committee two or more directors.]`
  line
  line `(2) The Board's report under sub-section (3) of section 134 shall disclose the composition of the Corporate Social Responsibility Committee.`
  line
  line `(3) The Corporate Social Responsibility Committee shall,--`
  line
  line `(a) formulate and recommend to the Board, a Corporate Social Responsibility Policy which shall indicate the activities to be undertaken by the company ^3[in areas or subject, specified in Schedule VII];`
  line
  line `(b) recommend the amount of expenditure to be incurred on the activities referred to in clause (a); and`
  line
  line `(c) monitor the Corporate Social Responsibility Policy of the company from time to time.`
  line
  line `(4) The Board of every company referred to in sub-section (1) shall,--`
  line
  line `(a) after taking into account the recommendations made by the Corporate Social Responsibility Committee, approve the Corporate Social Responsibility Policy for the company and disclose contents of such Policy in its report and also place it on the company's website, if any, in such manner as may be prescribed; and`
  line
  line `(b) ensure that the activities as are included in Corporate Social Responsibility Policy of the company are undertaken by the company.`
  line
  line `(5) The Board of every company referred to in sub-section (1), shall ensure that the company spends, in every financial year, at least two per cent. of the average net profits of the company made during the three immediately preceding financial years, ^4[or where the company has not completed the period of three financial years since its incorporation, during such immediately preceding financial years] in pursuance of its Corporate Social Responsibility Policy:`
  line
  line `Provided that the company shall give preference to the local area and areas around it where it operates, for spending the amount earmarked for Corporate Social Responsibility activities:`
  line
  line `Provided further that if the company fails to spend such amount, the Board shall, in its report made under clause (o) of sub-section (3) of section 134, specify the reasons for not spending the amount ^5[and, unless the unspent amount relates to any ongoing project referred to in sub-section (6), transfer such unspent amount to a Fund specified in Schedule VII, within a period of six months of the expiry of the financial years].`
  line
  line `^6[Provided also that if the company spends an amount in excess of the requirements provided under this sub-section, such company may set off such excess amount against the requirement to spend under this sub-section for such number of succeeding financial years and in such manner, as may be prescribed.]`
  line
  line `^7[Explanation.--For the purposes of this section "net profit" shall not include such sums as may be prescribed, and shall be calculated in accordance with the provisions of section 198.]`
  line
  line `^8[(6) Any amount remaining unspent under sub-section (5), pursuant to any ongoing project, fulfilling such conditions as may be prescribed, undertaken by a company in pursuance of its Corporate Social Responsibility Policy, shall be transferred by the company within a period of thirty days from the end of the financial year to a special account to be opened by the company in that behalf for that financial year in any scheduled bank to be called the Unspent Corporate Social Responsibility Account, and such amount shall be spent by the company in pursuance of its obligation towards the Corporate Social Responsibility Policy within a period of three financial years from the date of such transfer, failing which, the company shall transfer the same to a Fund specified in Schedule VII, within a period of thirty days from the date of completion of the third financial year.`
  line
  line `^9[(7) If a company is in default in complying with the provisions of sub-section (5) or sub-section (6), the company shall be liable to a penalty of twice the amount required to be transferred by the company to the Fund specified in Schedule VII or the Unspent Corporate Social Responsibility Account, as the case may be, or one crore rupees, whichever is less, and every officer of the company who is in default shall be liable to a penalty of one-tenth of the amount required to be transferred by the company to such Fund specified in Schedule VII, or the Unspent Corporate Social Responsibility Account, as the case may be, or two lakh rupees, whichever is less.]`
  line
  line `(8) The Central Government may give such general or special directions to a company or class of companies as it considers necessary to ensure compliance of provisions of this section and such company or class of companies shall comply with such directions.]`
  line
  line `^10[(9) Where the amount to be spent by a company under sub-section (5) does not exceed fifty lakh rupees, the requirement under sub-section (1) for constitution of the Corporate Social Responsibility Committee shall not be applicable and the functions of such Committee provided under this section shall, in such cases, be discharged by the Board of Directors of such company.]`
obj_root_law_sections_135_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 1 of 2018, s. 37, for "any financial year" (w.e.f. 19-9-2018).`
  line
  line `2. The proviso ins. by s. 37, ibid., (w.e.f. 19-9-2018).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by s. 37, ibid., for "as specified in Schedule VII" (w.e.f. 19-9-2018).`
  line
  line `4. Ins. by Act 22 of 2019, s. 21 (w.e.f. 22-1-2021).`
  line
  line `5. Ins. by s. 21, ibid. (w.e.f. 22-1-2021).`
  line
  line `6. The Proviso ins. by Act 29 of 2020, s. 27 (w.e.f. 22-1-2021).`
  line
  line `7. Subs. by Act 1 of 2018, s. 37, for the Explanation (w.e.f. 19-9-2018).`
  line
  line `8 Ins. by Act 22 of 2019, s. 21 (w.e.f. 22-1-2021).`
  line
  line `9. Subs. by Act 29 of 2020, s. 27, for sub-section (7) (w.e.f. 22-1-2021).`
  line
  line `10. Ins. by s. 27, ibid. (w.e.f. 22-1-2021).`
obj_root_law_sections_136:
  sectionId (1327)
  sectionNo (136)
  orderNo 140
  title `Right of member to copies of audited financial statement`
  content obj_root_law_sections_136_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_136_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=1327&sectionno=136&orderno=140&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_136_content:
  string
  line `(1) ^1*** a copy of the financial`
  line `statements, including consolidated financial statements, if any, auditors report and every other document`
  line `required by law to be annexed or attached to the financial statements, which are to be laid before a`
  line `company in its general meeting, shall be sent to every member of the company, to every trustee for the`
  line `debenture-holder of any debentures issued by the company, and to all persons other than such member or`
  line `trustee, being the person so entitled, not less than twenty-one days before the date of the meeting:`
  line
  line `^2[Provided that if the copies of the documents are sent less than twenty-one days before the date of the`
  line `meeting, they shall, notwithstanding that fact, be deemed to have been duly sent if it is so agreed by`
  line members--
  line
  line `(a) holding, if the company has a share capital, majority in number entitled to vote and who`
  line `represent not less than ninety-five per cent. of such part of the paid-up share capital of the company as`
  line `gives a right to vote at the meeting; or`
  line
  line `(b) having, if the company has no share capital, not less than ninety-five per cent. of the total voting`
  line `power exercisable at the meeting:`
  line
  line `Provided further that] in the case of a listed company, the provisions of this sub-section shall be`
  line `deemed to be complied with, if the copies of the documents are made available for inspection at its`
  line `registered office during working hours for a period of twenty-one days before the date of the meeting and`
  line `a statement containing the salient features of such documents in the prescribed form or copies of the`
  line `documents, as the company may deem fit, is sent to every member of the company and to every trustee`
  line `for the holders of any debentures issued by the company not less than twenty-one days before the date of`
  line `the meeting unless the shareholders ask for full financial statements:`
  line
  line `^3[Provided also] that the Central Government may prescribe the manner of circulation of financial`
  line `statements of companies having such net worth and turnover as may be prescribed:`
  line
  line `Provided also that a listed company shall also place its financial statements including consolidated`
  line `financial statements, if any, and all other documents required to be attached`
  line `thereto, on its website, which is maintained by or on behalf of the company:`
  line
  line `^4[Provided also that every listed company having a subsidiary or subsidiaries shall place separate`
  line `audited accounts in respect of each of subsidiary on its website, if any:`
  line
  line `Provided also that a listed company which has a subsidiary incorporated outside India (herein referred`
  line `to as foreign subsidiary)--`
  line
  line `(a) where such foreign subsidiary is statutorily required to prepare consolidated financial statement`
  line `under any law of the country of its incorporation, the requirement of this proviso shall be met if`
  line `consolidated financial statement of such foreign subsidiary is placed on the website of the listed`
  line company;
  line
  line `(b) where such foreign subsidiary is not required to get its financial statement audited under any law`
  line `of the country of its incorporation and which does not get such financial statement audited, the holding`
  line `Indian listed company may place such unaudited financial statement on its website and where such`
  line `financial statement is in a language other than English, a translated copy of the financial statement in`
  line `English shall also be placed on the website.]`
  line
  line `(2) A company shall allow every member or trustee of the holder of any debentures issued by the`
  line `company to inspect the documents stated under sub-section (1) at its registered office during business`
  line hours.
  line
  line `^5[Provided that every company having a subsidiary or subsidiaries shall provide a copy of separate`
  line `audited or unaudited financial statements, as the case may be, as prepared in respect of each of its`
  line `subsidiary to any member of the company who asks for it.]`
  line
  line `(3) If any default is made in complying with the provisions of this section, the company shall be liable`
  line `to a penalty of twenty-five thousand rupees and every officer of the company who is in default shall be`
  line `liable to a penalty of five thousand rupees.`
obj_root_law_sections_136_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. The words and figures "Without prejudice to the provisions of section 101" omitted by s. 38, ibid., (w.e.f. 9-2-2018).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by s. 38, ibid., for "Provided that" (w.e.f. 9-2-2018).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by s. 38, ibid., for "Provided further" (w.e.f. 9-2-2018).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by Act 1 of 2018, s. 38, for the Fourth proviso (w.e.f. 9-2-2018).`
  line
  line `5. The proviso ins. by s. 38, ibid. (w.e.f. 9-2-2018).`
obj_root_law_sections_137:
  sectionId (1328)
  sectionNo (137)
  orderNo 141
  title `Copy of financial statement to be filed with Registrar`
  content obj_root_law_sections_137_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_137_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=1328&sectionno=137&orderno=141&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_137_content:
  string
  line `(1) A copy of the financial`
  line `statements, including consolidated financial statement, if any, along with all the documents which are`
  line `required to be or attached to such financial statements under this Act, duly adopted at the annual general`
  line `meeting of the company, shall be filed with the Registrar within thirty days of the date of annual general`
  line `meeting in such manner, with such fees or additional fees as may be prescribed ^1***:`
  line
  line `Provided that where the financial statements under sub-section (1) are not adopted at annual general`
  line `meeting or adjourned annual general meeting, such unadopted financial statements along with the`
  line `required documents under sub-section (1) shall be filed with the Registrar within thirty days of the date of`
  line `annual general meeting and the Registrar shall take them in his records as provisional till the financial`
  line `statements are filed with him after their adoption in the adjourned annual general meeting for that`
  line `purpose:`
  line
  line `Provided further that financial statements adopted in the adjourned annual general meeting shall be`
  line `filed with the Registrar within thirty days of the date of such adjourned annual general meeting with such`
  line `fees or such additional fees as may be prescribed ^1***:`
  line
  line `Provided also that a One Person Company shall file a copy of the financial statements duly adopted`
  line `by its member, along with all the documents which are required to be attached to such financial`
  line `statements, within one hundred eighty days from the closure of the financial year:`
  line
  line `Provided also that a company shall, along with its financial statements to be filed with the Registrar,`
  line `attach the accounts of its subsidiary or subsidiaries which have been incorporated outside India and which`
  line `have not established their place of business in India.`
  line
  line `^2[Provided also that in the case of a subsidiary which has been incorporated outside India (herein`
  line `referred to as foreign subsidiary), which is not required to get its financial statement audited under any`
  line `law of the country of its incorporation and which does not get such financial statement audited, the`
  line `requirements of the fourth proviso shall be met if the holding Indian company files such unaudited`
  line `financial statement along with a declaration to this effect and where such financial statement is in a`
  line `language other than English, along with a translated copy of the financial statement in English.]`
  line
  line `(2) Where the annual general meeting of a company for any year has not been held, the financial`
  line `statements along with the documents required to be attached under sub-section (1), duly signed along with`
  line `the statement of facts and reasons for not holding the annual general meeting shall be filed with the`
  line `Registrar within thirty days of the last date before which the annual general meeting should have been`
  line `held and in such manner, with such fees or additional fees as may be prescribed ^3***.`
  line
  line `(3) If a company fails to file the copy of the financial statements under sub-section (1) or`
  line `sub-section (2), as the case may be, before the expiry of the period specified ^4`
  line `[therein] the company shall`
  line `be ^5`
  line `[liable to a penalty] of ^6`
  line `[ten thousand rupees and in case of continuing failure, with a further penalty`
  line `of one hundred rupees for each day during which such failure continues, subject to a maximum of two`
  line `lakh rupees,] and the managing director and the Chief Financial Officer of the company, if any, and, in`
  line `the absence of the managing director and the Chief Financial Officer, any other director who is charged`
  line `by the Board with the responsibility of complying with the provisions of this section, and, in the absence`
  line `of any such director, all the directors of the company, shall be ^7`
  line `[shall be liable to a penalty of ^8`
  line [ten
  line `thousand rupees] and in case of continuing failure, with a further penalty of one hundred rupees for each`
  line `day after the first during which such failure continues, subject to a maximum of ^9`
  line `[fifty thousand rupees.]`
obj_root_law_sections_137_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. The words and figures "within the time specified under section 403" omitted by s. 39, ibid. (w.e.f. 7-5-2018).`
  line
  line `2. The proviso ins. by s. 39, ibid. (w.e.f. 7-5-2018).`
  line
  line `3. The words and figures "within the time specified, under section 403" omitted by Act 1 of 2018, s. 39 (w.e.f. 7-5-2018).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by s. 39, ibid., for "in section 403" (w.e.f. 7-5-2018).`
  line
  line `5. Subs. by Act 22 of 2019, s. 22, for "punishable with fine" (w.e.f. 2-11-2018).`
  line
  line `6. Subs. by Act 29 of 2020, s. 28, for "one thousand rupees for every day during which the failure continues but which`
  line `shall not be more than ten lakh rupees" (w.e.f. 21-12-2020).`
  line
  line `7. Subs. by s. 22, ibid., for "punishable with imprisonment for a term which may extend to six months or with fine which shall`
  line `not be less than one lakh rupees but which may extend to five lakh rupees, or with both" (w.e.f. 2-11-2018).`
  line
  line `8. Subs. by Act 29 of 2020, s. 28, for "one lakh rupees" (w.e.f. 21-12-2020).`
  line
  line `9. Subs. by s. 28, ibid., for "five lakh rupees" (w.e.f. 21-12-2020).`
obj_root_law_sections_138:
  sectionId (1329)
  sectionNo (138)
  orderNo 142
  title `Internal Audit.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_138_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_138_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=1329&sectionno=138&orderno=142&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_138_content:
  string
  line `(1) Such class or classes of companies as may be prescribed shall be required`
  line `to appoint an internal auditor, who shall either be a chartered accountant or a cost accountant, or such`
  line `other professional as may be decided by the Board to conduct internal audit of the functions and activities`
  line `of the company.`
  line
  line `(2) The Central Government may, by rules, prescribe the manner and the intervals in which the`
  line `internal audit shall be conducted and reported to the Board.`
obj_root_law_sections_138_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_139:
  sectionId (1330)
  sectionNo (139)
  orderNo 143
  title `Appointment of auditors`
  content obj_root_law_sections_139_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_139_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=1330&sectionno=139&orderno=143&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_139_content:
  string
  line `(1) Subject to the provisions of this Chapter, every company shall,`
  line `at the first annual general meeting, appoint an individual or a firm as an auditor who shall hold office`
  line `from the conclusion of that meeting till the conclusion of its sixth annual general meeting and thereafter`
  line `till the conclusion of every sixth meeting and the manner and procedure of selection of auditors by the`
  line `members of the company at such meeting shall be such as may be prescribed:`
  line
  line `^1* * * * *`
  line
  line `Provided further that before such appointment is made, the written consent of the auditor to such`
  line `appointment, and a certificate from him or it that the appointment, if made, shall be in accordance with`
  line `the conditions as may be prescribed, shall be obtained from the auditor:`
  line
  line `Provided also that the certificate shall also indicate whether the auditor satisfies the criteria provided`
  line `in section 141:`
  line
  line `Provided also that the company shall inform the auditor concerned of his or its appointment, and also`
  line `file a notice of such appointment with the Registrar within fifteen days of the meeting in which the`
  line `auditor is appointed.`
  line
  line `Explanation.-- For the purposes of this Chapter, "appointment" includes re-appointment.`
  line
  line `(2) No listed company or a company belonging to such class or classes of companies as may be`
  line `prescribed, shall appoint or re-appoint--`
  line
  line `(a) an individual as auditor for more than one term of five consecutive years; and`
  line
  line `(b) an audit firm as auditor for more than two terms of five consecutive years:`
  line
  line `Provided that--`
  line
  line `(i) an individual auditor who has completed his term under clause (a) shall not be eligible for`
  line `re-appointment as auditor in the same company for five years from the completion of his term;`
  line
  line `(ii) an audit firm which has completed its term under clause (b), shall not be eligible for reappointment`
  line `as auditor in the same company for five years from the completion of such term:`
  line
  line `Provided further that as on the date of appointment no audit firm having a common partner or partners`
  line `to the other audit firm, whose tenure has expired in a company immediately preceding the financial year,`
  line `shall be appointed as auditor of the same company for a period of five years:`
  line
  line `^2[Provided also that every company, existing on or before the commencement of this Act which is`
  line `required to comply with provisions of this sub-section, shall comply with the requirements of this subsection`
  line `within three years from the date of commencement of this Act:]`
  line
  line `Provided also that, nothing contained in this sub-section shall prejudice the right of the company to`
  line `remove an auditor or the right of the auditor to resign from such office of the company.`
  line
  line `(3) Subject to the provisions of this Act, members of a company may resolve to provide that--`
  line
  line `(a) in the audit firm appointed by it, the auditing partner and his team shall be rotated at such`
  line `intervals as may be resolved by members; or`
  line
  line `(b) the audit shall be conducted by more than one auditor.`
  line
  line `(4) The Central Government may, by rules, prescribe the manner in which the companies shall rotate`
  line `their auditors in pursuance of sub-section (2).`
  line
  line `Explanation.-- For the purposes of this Chapter, the word "firm" shall include a limited liability`
  line `partnership incorporated under the Limited Liability Partnership Act, 2008 (6 of 2009).`
  line
  line `(5) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (1), in the case of a Government company or`
  line `any other company owned or controlled, directly or indirectly, by the Central Government, or by any`
  line `State Government or Governments, or partly by the Central Government and partly by one or more State`
  line `Governments, the Comptroller and Auditor-General of India shall, in respect of a financial year, appoint`
  line `an auditor duly qualified to be appointed as an auditor of companies under this Act, within a period of one`
  line `hundred and eighty days from the commencement of the financial year, who shall hold office till the`
  line `conclusion of the annual general meeting.`
  line
  line `(6) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (1), the first auditor of a company, other than a`
  line `Government company, shall be appointed by the Board of Directors within thirty days from the date of`
  line `registration of the company and in the case of failure of the Board to appoint such auditor, it shall inform`
  line `the members of the company, who shall within ninety days at an extraordinary general meeting appoint`
  line `such auditor and such auditor shall hold office till the conclusion of the first annual general meeting.`
  line
  line `(7) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (1) or sub-section (5), in the case of a`
  line `Government company or any other company owned or controlled, directly or indirectly, by the Central`
  line `Government, or by any State Government, or Governments, or partly by the Central Government and`
  line `partly by one or more State Governments, the first auditor shall be appointed by the Comptroller and`
  line `Auditor-General of India within sixty days from the date of registration of the company and in case the`
  line `Comptroller and Auditor-General of India does not appoint such auditor within the said period, the Board`
  line `of Directors of the company shall appoint such auditor within the next thirty days; and in the case of`
  line `failure of the Board to appoint such auditor within the next thirty days, it shall inform the members of the`
  line `company who shall appoint such auditor within the sixty days at an extraordinary general meeting, who`
  line `shall hold office till the conclusion of the first annual general meeting.`
  line
  line `(8) Any casual vacancy in the office of an auditor shall--`
  line
  line `(i) in the case of a company other than a company whose accounts are subject to audit by an`
  line `auditor appointed by the Comptroller and Auditor-General of India, be filled by the Board of`
  line `Directors within thirty days, but if such casual vacancy is as a result of the resignation of an auditor,`
  line `such appointment shall also be approved by the company at a general meeting convened within three`
  line `months of the recommendation of the Board and he shall hold the office till the conclusion of the next`
  line `annual general meeting;`
  line
  line `(ii) in the case of a company whose accounts are subject to audit by an auditor appointed by the`
  line `Comptroller and Auditor-General of India, be filled by the Comptroller and Auditor-General of India`
  line `within thirty days:`
  line
  line `Provided that in case the Comptroller and Auditor-General of India does not fill the vacancy`
  line `within the said period, the Board of Directors shall fill the vacancy within next thirty days.`
  line
  line `(9) Subject to the provisions of sub-section (1) and the rules made thereunder, a retiring auditor may`
  line `be re-appointed at an annual general meeting, if--`
  line
  line `(a) he is not disqualified for re-appointment;`
  line
  line `(b) he has not given the company a notice in writing of his unwillingness to be re-appointed; and`
  line
  line `(c) a special resolution has not been passed at that meeting appointing some other auditor or`
  line `providing expressly that he shall not be re-appointed.`
  line
  line `(10) Where at any annual general meeting, no auditor is appointed or re-appointed, the existing`
  line `auditor shall continue to be the auditor of the company.`
  line
  line `(11) Where a company is required to constitute an Audit Committee under section 177, all`
  line `appointments, including the filling of a casual vacancy of an auditor under this section shall be made after`
  line `taking into account the recommendations of such committee.`
obj_root_law_sections_139_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. The first proviso omitted by s. 40, ibid. (w.e.f. 7-5-2018).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by notification No. S.O. 2264(E), dated 30th June, 2016, for the proviso (w.e.f.1-4-2014`
obj_root_law_sections_140:
  sectionId (1331)
  sectionNo (140)
  orderNo 144
  title `Removal, resignation of auditor and giving of special notice.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_140_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_140_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=1331&sectionno=140&orderno=144&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_140_content:
  string
  line `(1) The auditor appointed`
  line `under section 139 may be removed from his office before the expiry of his term only by a special`
  line `resolution of the company, after obtaining the previous approval of the Central Government in that behalf`
  line `in the prescribed manner:`
  line
  line `Provided that before taking any action under this sub-section, the auditor concerned shall be given a`
  line `reasonable opportunity of being heard.`
  line
  line `(2) The auditor who has resigned from the company shall file within a period of thirty days from the`
  line `date of resignation, a statement in the prescribed form with the company and the Registrar, and in case of`
  line `companies referred to in sub-section (5) of section 139, the auditor shall also file such statement with the`
  line `Comptroller and Auditor-General of India, indicating the reasons and other facts as may be relevant with`
  line `regard to his resignation.`
  line
  line `^1[(3) If the auditor does not comply with the provisions of sub-section (2), he or it shall be liable to a`
  line `penalty of fifty thousand rupees or an amount equal to the remuneration of the auditor, whichever is less,`
  line `and in case of continuing failure, with a further penalty of five hundred rupees for each day after the first`
  line `during which such failure continues, subject to a maximum of ^2`
  line `[two lakh rupees].]`
  line
  line `(4) (i) Special notice shall be required for a resolution at an annual general meeting appointing as`
  line `auditor a person other than a retiring auditor, or providing expressly that a retiring auditor shall not be reappointed,`
  line `except where the retiring auditor has completed a consecutive tenure of five years or, as the`
  line `case may be, ten years, as provided under sub-section (2) of section 139.`
  line
  line `(ii) On receipt of notice of such a resolution, the company shall forthwith send a copy thereof to the`
  line `retiring auditor.`
  line
  line `(iii) Where notice is given of such a resolution and the retiring auditor makes with respect thereto`
  line `representation in writing to the company (not exceeding a reasonable length) and requests its notification`
  line `to members of the company, the company shall, unless the representation is received by it too late for it to`
  line `do so,--`
  line
  line `(a) in any notice of the resolution given to members of the company, state the fact of the`
  line `representation having been made; and`
  line
  line `(b) send a copy of the representation to every member of the company to whom notice of the`
  line `meeting is sent, whether before or after the receipt of the representation by the company,`
  line
  line `and if a copy of the representation is not sent as aforesaid because it was received too late or because of`
  line `the companys default, the auditor may (without prejudice to his right to be heard orally) require that the`
  line `representation shall be read out at the meeting:`
  line
  line `Provided that if a copy of representation is not sent as aforesaid, a copy thereof shall be filed with the`
  line `Registrar:`
  line
  line `Provided further that if the Tribunal is satisfied on an application either of the company or of any`
  line `other aggrieved person that the rights conferred by this sub-section are being abused by the auditor, then,`
  line `the copy of the representation may not be sent and the representation need not be read out at the meeting.`
  line
  line `(5) Without prejudice to any action under the provisions of this Act or any other law for the time`
  line `being in force, the Tribunal either suo motu or on an application made to it by the Central Government or`
  line `by any person concerned, if it is satisfied that the auditor of a company has, whether directly or indirectly,`
  line `acted in a fraudulent manner or abetted or colluded in any fraud by, or in relation to, the company or its`
  line `directors or officers, it may, by order, direct the company to change its auditors:`
  line
  line `Provided that if the application is made by the Central Government and the Tribunal is satisfied that`
  line `any change of the auditor is required, it shall within fifteen days of receipt of such application, make an`
  line `order that he shall not function as an auditor and the Central Government may appoint another auditor in`
  line `his place:`
  line
  line `Provided further that an auditor, whether individual or firm, against whom final order has been passed`
  line `by the Tribunal under this section shall not be eligible to be appointed as an auditor of any company for a`
  line `period of five years from the date of passing of the order and the auditor shall also be liable for action`
  line `under section 447.`
  line
  line `Explanation I.-- It is hereby clarified that the case of a firm, the liability shall be of the firm and that`
  line `of every partner or partners who acted in a fraudulent manner or abetted or colluded in any fraud by, or in`
  line `relation to, the company or its director or officers.`
  line
  line `Explanation II.-- For the purposes of this Chapter the word "auditor" includes a firm of auditors.`
obj_root_law_sections_140_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 22 of 2019, s. 23, for sub-section (3) (w.e.f. 2-11-2018).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 29 of 2020, s. 29, for "five lakh rupees" (w.e.f. 21-12-2020).`
obj_root_law_sections_141:
  sectionId (49070)
  sectionNo (141)
  orderNo 145
  title `Eligibility, qualifications and disqualifications of auditors.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_141_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 1 of 2018, s. 42, for clause (i) (w.e.f. 9-2-2018).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=49070&sectionno=141&orderno=145&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_141_content:
  string
  line `(1) A person shall be eligible`
  line `for appointment as an auditor of a company only if he is a chartered accountant:`
  line
  line `Provided that a firm whereof majority of partners practising in India are qualified for appointment as`
  line `aforesaid may be appointed by its firm name to be auditor of a company.`
  line
  line `(2) Where a firm including a limited liability partnership is appointed as an auditor of a company,`
  line `only the partners who are chartered accountants shall be authorised to act and sign on behalf of the firm.`
  line
  line `(3) The following persons shall not be eligible for appointment as an auditor of a company,`
  line `namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) a body corporate other than a limited liability partnership registered under the Limited`
  line `Liability Partnership Act, 2008 (6 of 2009);`
  line
  line `(b) an officer or employee of the company;`
  line
  line `(c) a person who is a partner, or who is in the employment, of an officer or employee of the`
  line company;
  line
  line `(d) a person who, or his relative or partner--`
  line
  line `(i) is holding any security of or interest in the company or its subsidiary, or of its holding or`
  line `associate company or a subsidiary of such holding company:`
  line
  line `Provided that the relative may hold security or interest in the company of face value not`
  line `exceeding one thousand rupees or such sum as may be prescribed;`
  line
  line `(ii) is indebted to the company, or its subsidiary, or its holding or associate company or a`
  line `subsidiary of such holding company, in excess of such amount as may be prescribed; or`
  line
  line `(iii) has given a guarantee or provided any security in connection with the indebtedness of`
  line `any third person to the company, or its subsidiary, or its holding or associate company or a`
  line `subsidiary of such holding company, for such amount as may be prescribed;`
  line
  line `(e) a person or a firm who, whether directly or indirectly, has business relationship with the`
  line `company, or its subsidiary, or its holding or associate company or subsidiary of such holding`
  line `company or associate company of such nature as may be prescribed;`
  line
  line `(f) a person whose relative is a director or is in the employment of the company as a director or`
  line `key managerial personnel;`
  line
  line `(g) a person who is in full time employment elsewhere or a person or a partner of a firm holding`
  line `appointment as its auditor, if such persons or partner is at the date of such appointment or`
  line `reappointment holding appointment as auditor of more than twenty companies;`
  line
  line `(h) a person who has been convicted by a court of an offence involving fraud and a period of ten`
  line `years has not elapsed from the date of such conviction;`
  line
  line `^1[(i) a person who, directly or indirectly, renders any service referred to in section 144 to the`
  line `company or its holding company or its subsidiary company.`
  line
  line `Explanation.-- For the purposes of this clause, the term "directly or indirectly" shall have the`
  line `meaning assigned to it in the Explanation to section 144.]`
  line
  line `(4) Where a person appointed as an auditor of a company incurs any of the disqualifications`
  line `mentioned in sub-section (3) after his appointment, he shall vacate his office as such auditor and such`
  line `vacation shall be deemed to be a casual vacancy in the office of the auditor.`
obj_root_law_sections_142:
  sectionId (49071)
  sectionNo (142)
  orderNo 146
  title `Remuneration of auditors.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_142_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_142_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=49071&sectionno=142&orderno=146&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_142_content:
  string
  line `(1) The remuneration of the auditor of a company shall be fixed`
  line `in its general meeting or in such manner as may be determined therein:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Board may fix remuneration of the first auditor appointed by it.`
  line
  line `(2) The remuneration under sub-section (1) shall, in addition to the fee payable to an auditor, include`
  line `the expenses, if any, incurred by the auditor in connection with the audit of the company and any facility`
  line `extended to him but does not include any remuneration paid to him for any other service rendered by him`
  line `at the request of the company.`
obj_root_law_sections_142_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_143:
  sectionId (49072)
  sectionNo (143)
  orderNo 147
  title `Powers and duties of auditors and auditing standards.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_143_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_143_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=49072&sectionno=143&orderno=147&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_143_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every auditor of a company`
  line `shall have a right of access at all times to the books of account and vouchers of the company, whether`
  line `kept at the registered office of the company or at any other place and shall be entitled to require from the`
  line `officers of the company such information and explanation as he may consider necessary for the`
  line `performance of his duties as auditor and amongst other matters inquire into the following matters,`
  line `namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) whether loans and advances made by the company on the basis of security have been properly`
  line `secured and whether the terms on which they have been made are prejudicial to the interests of the`
  line `company or its members;`
  line
  line `(b) whether transactions of the company which are represented merely by book entries are`
  line `prejudicial to the interests of the company;`
  line
  line `(c) where the company not being an investment company or a banking company, whether so`
  line `much of the assets of the company as consist of shares, debentures and other securities have been sold`
  line `at a price less than that at which they were purchased by the company;`
  line
  line `(d) whether loans and advances made by the company have been shown as deposits;`
  line
  line `(e) whether personal expenses have been charged to revenue account;`
  line
  line `(f) where it is stated in the books and documents of the company that any shares have been`
  line `allotted for cash, whether cash has actually been received in respect of such allotment, and if no cash`
  line `has actually been so received, whether the position as stated in the account books and the balance`
  line `sheet is correct, regular and not misleading:`
  line
  line `Provided that the auditor of a company which is a holding company shall also have the right of access`
  line `to the records of all ^2[its subsidiaries and associate companies] in so far as it relates to the consolidation of`
  line `its financial statements with that of ^1[its subsidiaries and associate companies.]`
  line
  line `(2) The auditor shall make a report to the members of the company on the accounts examined by him`
  line `and on every financial statements which are required by or under this Act to be laid before the company`
  line `in general meeting and the report shall after taking into account the provisions of this Act, the accounting`
  line `and auditing standards and matters which are required to be included in the audit report under the`
  line `provisions of this Act or any rules made thereunder or under any order made under sub-section (11) and`
  line `to the best of his information and knowledge, the said accounts, financial statements give a true and fair`
  line `view of the state of the company's affairs as at the end of its financial year and profit or loss and cash`
  line `flow for the year and such other matters as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(3) The auditor's report shall also state--`
  line
  line `(a) whether he has sought and obtained all the information and explanations which to the best of`
  line `his knowledge and belief were necessary for the purpose of his audit and if not, the details thereof and`
  line `the effect of such information on the financial statements;`
  line
  line `(b) whether, in his opinion, proper books of account as required by law have been kept by the`
  line `company so far as appears from his examination of those books and proper returns adequate for the`
  line `purposes of his audit have been received from branches not visited by him;`
  line
  line `(c) whether the report on the accounts of any branch office of the company audited under subsection`
  line
  line `(8) by a person other than the company's auditor has been sent to him under the proviso to`
  line `that sub-section and the manner in which he has dealt with it in preparing his report;`
  line
  line `(d) whether the company's balance sheet and profit and loss account dealt with in the report are in`
  line `agreement with the books of account and returns;`
  line
  line `(e) whether, in his opinion, the financial statements comply with the accounting standards;`
  line
  line `(f) the observations or comments of the auditors on financial transactions or matters which have`
  line `any adverse effect on the functioning of the company;`
  line
  line `(g) whether any director is disqualified from being appointed as a director under sub-section (2)`
  line `of section 164;`
  line
  line `(h) any qualification, reservation or adverse remark relating to the maintenance of accounts and`
  line `other matters connected therewith;`
  line
  line `(i) whether the company has adequate ^3[internal financial controls with reference to financial`
  line `statements] in place and the operating effectiveness of such controls;`
  line
  line `(j) such other matters as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(4) Where any of the matters required to be included in the audit report under this section is answered`
  line `in the negative or with a qualification, the report shall state the reasons therefor.`
  line
  line `(5) ^4[In the case of a Government company or any other company owned or controlled, directly or`
  line `indirectly, by the Central Government, or by any State Government or Governments, or partly by the`
  line `Central Government and partly by one or more State Governments, the Comptroller and Auditor General`
  line `of India shall appoint the auditor under sub-section (5) or sub-section (7) of Section 139 and direct such`
  line `auditor the manner in which the accounts of the company are required to be audited and] thereupon the`
  line `auditor so appointed shall submit a copy of the audit report to the Comptroller and Auditor-General of`
  line `India which, among other things, include the directions, if any, issued by the Comptroller and`
  line `Auditor-General of India, the action taken thereon and its impact on the accounts and financial statement`
  line `of the company.`
  line
  line `(6) The Comptroller and Auditor-General of India shall within sixty days from the date of receipt of`
  line `the audit report under sub-section (5) have a right to,--`
  line
  line `(a) conduct a supplementary audit of the financial statement of the company by such person or`
  line `persons as he may authorise in this behalf; and for the purposes of such audit, require information or`
  line `additional information to be furnished to any person or persons, so authorised, on such matters, by`
  line `such person or persons, and in such form, as the Comptroller and Auditor-General of India may`
  line `direct; and`
  line
  line `(b) comment upon or supplement such audit report:`
  line
  line `Provided that any comments given by the Comptroller and Auditor-General of India upon, or`
  line `supplement to, the audit report shall be sent by the company to every person entitled to copies of`
  line `audited financial statements under sub section (1) of section 136 and also be placed before the annual`
  line `general meeting of the company at the same time and in the same manner as the audit report.`
  line
  line `(7) Without prejudice to the provisions of this Chapter, the Comptroller and Auditor-General of India`
  line `may, in case of any company covered under sub-section (5) or sub-section (7) of section 139, if he`
  line `considers necessary, by an order, cause test audit to be conducted of the accounts of such company and`
  line `the provisions of section 19A of the Comptroller and Auditor-General's (Duties, Powers and Conditions`
  line `of Service) Act, 1971 (56 of 1971), shall apply to the report of such test audit.`
  line
  line `(8) Where a company has a branch office, the accounts of that office shall be audited either by the`
  line `auditor appointed for the company (herein referred to as the company's auditor) under this Act or by any`
  line `other person qualified for appointment as an auditor of the company under this Act and appointed as such`
  line `under section 139, or where the branch office is situated in a country outside India, the accounts of the`
  line `branch office shall be audited either by the company's auditor or by an accountant or by any other person`
  line `duly qualified to act as an auditor of the accounts of the branch office in accordance with the laws of that`
  line `country and the duties and powers of the company's auditor with reference to the audit of the branch and`
  line `the branch auditor, if any, shall be such as may be prescribed:`
  line
  line `Provided that the branch auditor shall prepare a report on the accounts of the branch examined by him`
  line `and send it to the auditor of the company who shall deal with it in his report in such manner as he`
  line `considers necessary.`
  line
  line `(9) Every auditor shall comply with the auditing standards.`
  line
  line `(10) The Central Government may prescribe the standards of auditing or any addendum thereto, as`
  line `recommended by the Institute of Chartered Accountants of India, constituted under section 3 of the`
  line `Chartered Accountants Act, 1949 (38 of 1949), in consultation with and after examination of the`
  line `recommendations made by the National Financial Reporting Authority:`
  line
  line `Provided that until any auditing standards are notified, any standard or standards of auditing specified`
  line `by the Institute of Chartered Accountants of India shall be deemed to be the auditing standards.`
  line
  line `(11) The Central Government may, in consultation with the National Financial Reporting Authority,`
  line `by general or special order, direct, in respect of such class or description of companies, as may be`
  line `specified in the order, that the auditor's report shall also include a statement on such matters as may be`
  line `specified therein.`
  line
  line `^5[Provided that until the National Financial Reporting Authority is constituted under section 132, the`
  line `Central Government may hold consultation required under this sub-section with the Committee chaired`
  line `by an officer of the rank of Joint Secretary or equivalent in the Ministry of Corporate Affairs and the`
  line `Committee shall have the representatives from the Institute of Chartered Accountants of India and`
  line `Industry Chambers and also special invitees from the National Advisory Committee on Accounting`
  line `Standards and the office of the Comptroller and Auditor-General.]`
  line
  line `^6[(12) Notwithstanding anything contained in this section, if an auditor of a company, in the course of`
  line `the performance of his duties as auditor, has reason to believe that an offence involving fraud is being or`
  line `has been committed against the company by officers or employees of the company, he shall immediately`
  line `report the matter to the Central Government within such time and in such manner as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `Provided that in case of a fraud involving lesser than the specified amount, the auditor shall report the`
  line `matter to the audit committee constituted under section 177 or to the Board in other cases within such`
  line `time and in such manner as may be prescribed:`
  line
  line `Provided further that the companies, whose auditors have reported frauds under this sub-section to the`
  line `audit committee or the Board but not reported to the Central Government, shall disclose the details about`
  line `such frauds in the Board's report in such manner as may be prescribed.]`
  line
  line `(13) No duty to which an auditor of a company may be subject to shall be regarded as having been`
  line `contravened by reason of his reporting the matter referred to in sub-section (12) if it is done in good faith.`
  line
  line `(14) The provisions of this section shall mutatis mutandis apply to--`
  line
  line `(a) the ^7[cost accountant] conducting cost audit under section 148; or`
  line
  line `(b) the company secretary in practice conducting secretarial audit under section 204.`
  line
  line ^8
  line `[(15) If any auditor, cost accountant, or company secretary in practice does not comply`
  line `with the provisions of sub-section (12), he shall, --`
  line
  line `(a) in case of a listed company, be liable to a penalty of five lakh rupees; and`
  line
  line `(b) in case of any other company, be liable to a penalty of one lakh rupees.]`
obj_root_law_sections_143_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 1 of 2018, s. 42, for clause (i) (w.e.f. 9-2-2018).`
  line `2. Subs. by s. 43, ibid., for "its subsidiaries" (w.e.f. 9-2-2018).`
  line `3. Subs. by Act 1 of 2018, s. 43, for "internal financial controls system" (w.e.f. 9-2-2018).`
  line `4. Subs. by notification No. S.O. 2226(E), dated 4th September, 2014 for certain words (w.e.f. 4-9-2014).`
  line `5. Ins. by notification No. S.O. 1226(E), dated 29th March, 2016 (w.e.f. 10-4-2015).`
  line `6. Subs. by Act 21 of 2015, s. 13, for sub-section (12) (w.e.f. 14-12-2015).`
  line `7. Subs. by Act 1 of 2018, s. 43, for "cost accountant in practice" (w.e.f. 9-2-2018).`
  line `8. Subs. by Act 29 of 2020, s. 30, for sub-section (15) (w.e.f. 21-12-2020).`
obj_root_law_sections_144:
  sectionId (49073)
  sectionNo (144)
  orderNo 148
  title `Auditor not to render certain services.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_144_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_144_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=49073&sectionno=144&orderno=148&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_144_content:
  string
  line `An auditor appointed under this Act shall provide to`
  line `the company only such other services as are approved by the Board of Directors or the audit committee,`
  line `as the case may be, but which shall not include any of the following services (whether such services are`
  line `rendered directly or indirectly to the company), or its holding company or subsidiary company, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) accounting and book keeping services;`
  line
  line `(b) internal audit;`
  line
  line `(c) design and implementation of any financial information system;`
  line
  line `(d) actuarial services;`
  line
  line `(e) investment advisory services;`
  line
  line `(f) investment banking services;`
  line
  line `(g) rendering of outsourced financial services;`
  line
  line `(h) management services; and`
  line
  line `(i) any other kind of services as may be prescribed:`
  line
  line `Provided that an auditor or audit firm who or which has been performing any non-audit services on or`
  line `before the commencement of this Act shall comply with the provisions of this section before the closure`
  line `of the first financial year after the date of such commencement.`
  line
  line `Explanation.-- For the purposes of this sub-section, the term "directly or indirectly" shall include`
  line `rendering of services by the auditor,--`
  line
  line `(i) in case of auditor being an individual, either himself or through his relative or any other person`
  line `connected or associated with such individual or through any other entity, whatsoever, in which such`
  line `individual has significant influence or control, or whose name or trade mark or brand is used by such`
  line individual;
  line
  line `(ii) in case of auditor being a firm, either itself or through any of its partners or through its parent,`
  line `subsidiary or associate entity or through any other entity, whatsoever, in which the firm or any partner`
  line `of the firm has significant influence or control, or whose name or trade mark or brand is used by the`
  line `firm or any of its partners.`
obj_root_law_sections_144_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_145:
  sectionId (49074)
  sectionNo (145)
  orderNo 149
  title `Auditor to sign audit reports, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_145_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_145_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=49074&sectionno=145&orderno=149&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_145_content:
  string
  line `The person appointed as an auditor of the company shall`
  line `sign the auditor's report or sign or certify any other document of the company in accordance with the`
  line `provisions of sub-section (2) of section 141, and the qualifications, observations or comments on financial`
  line `transactions or matters, which have any adverse effect on the functioning of the company mentioned in`
  line `the auditors report shall be read before the company in general meeting and shall be open to inspection`
  line `by any member of the company.`
obj_root_law_sections_145_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_146:
  sectionId (49075)
  sectionNo (146)
  orderNo 150
  title `Auditors to attend general meeting.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_146_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_146_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=49075&sectionno=146&orderno=150&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_146_content:
  string
  line `All notices of, and other communications relating to,`
  line `any general meeting shall be forwarded to the auditor of the company, and the auditor shall, unless`
  line `otherwise exempted by the company, attend either by himself or through his authorised representative,`
  line `who shall also be qualified to be an auditor, any general meeting and shall have right to be heard at such`
  line `meeting on any part of the business which concerns him as the auditor`
obj_root_law_sections_146_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_147:
  sectionId (49076)
  sectionNo (147)
  orderNo 151
  title `Punishment for contravention.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_147_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_147_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=49076&sectionno=147&orderno=151&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_147_content:
  string
  line `(1) If any of the provisions of sections 139 to 146 (both`
  line `inclusive) is contravened, the company shall be punishable with fine which shall not be less than`
  line `twenty-five thousand rupees but which may extend to five lakh rupees and every officer of the company who is in default shall be punishable ^1*** with fine which shall not be less than ten thousand rupees but`
  line `which may extend to ^2[one lakh rupees].`
  line
  line `(2) If an auditor of a company contravenes any of the provisions of section 139, section 143, section`
  line `144 or section 145, the auditor shall be punishable with fine which shall not be less than twenty-five`
  line `thousand rupees but which may extend to five lakh rupees ^3`
  line `[or four times the remuneration of the auditor,`
  line `whichever is less]:`
  line
  line `Provided that if an auditor has contravened such provisions knowingly or willfully with the intention`
  line `to deceive the company or its shareholders or creditors or tax authorities, he shall be punishable with`
  line `imprisonment for a term which may extend to one year ^4`
  line `[and with fine which shall not be less than fifty`
  line `thousand rupees but which may extend to twenty-five lakh rupees or eight times the remuneration of the`
  line `auditor, whichever is less].`
  line
  line `(3) Where an auditor has been convicted under sub-section (2), he shall be liable to--`
  line
  line `(i) refund the remuneration received by him to the company; and`
  line
  line `(ii) pay for damages to the company, statutory bodies or authorities ^5`
  line `[or to members or creditors`
  line `of the company] for loss arising out of incorrect or misleading statements of particulars made in his`
  line `audit report.`
  line
  line `(4) The Central Government shall, by notification, specify any statutory body or authority or an`
  line `officer for ensuring prompt payment of damages to the company or the persons under clause (ii) of`
  line `sub-section (3) and such body, authority or officer shall after payment of damages to such company or`
  line `persons file a report with the Central Government in respect of making such damages in such manner as`
  line `may be specified in the said notification.`
  line
  line `(5) Where, in case of audit of a company being conducted by an audit firm, it is proved that the`
  line `partner or partners of the audit firm has or have acted in a fraudulent manner or a betted or colluded in`
  line `any fraud by, or in relation to or by, the company or its directors or officers, the liability, whether civil or`
  line `criminal as provided in this Act or in any other law for the time being in force, for such act shall be of the`
  line `partner or partners concerned of the audit firm and of the firm jointly and severally.`
  line
  line ^6
  line `[Provided that in case of criminal liability of an audit firm, in respect of liability other than fine, the`
  line `concerned partner or partners, who acted in a fraudulent manner or abetted or, as the case may be,`
  line `colluded in any fraud shall only be liable.]`
obj_root_law_sections_147_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. The words "with imprisonment for a term which may extend to one year or" omitted by Act 29 of 2020, s. 31 (w.e.f. 21-12-`
  line `2020).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by s. 31, ibid., for "one lakh rupees, or with both" (w.e.f. 21-12-2020).`
  line
  line `3. Ins. by Act 1 of 2018, s. 44 (w.e.f. 9-2-2018).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by Act 1 of 2018, s. 44, for "and with fine which shall not be less than one lakh rupees but which may extend to twentyfive lakh rupees" (w.e.f. 9-2-2018).`
  line
  line `5. Subs. by s. 44, ibid., for "or to any other persons" (w.e.f. 9-2-2018).`
  line
  line `6. The proviso ins. by s. 44, ibid., (w.e.f. 9-2-2018).`
obj_root_law_sections_148:
  sectionId (49077)
  sectionNo (148)
  orderNo 152
  title `Central Government to specify audit of items of cost in respect of certain companies.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_148_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_148_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=49077&sectionno=148&orderno=152&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_148_content:
  string
  line `(1) Notwithstanding anything contained in this Chapter, the Central Government may, by order, in respect of`
  line `such class of companies engaged in the production of such goods or providing such services as may be`
  line `prescribed, direct that particulars relating to the utilisation of material or labour or to other items of cost`
  line `as may be prescribed shall also be included in the books of account kept by that class of companies:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Central Government shall, before issuing such order in respect of any class of`
  line `companies regulated under a special Act, consult the regulatory body constituted or established under`
  line `such special Act.`
  line
  line `(2) If the Central Government is of the opinion, that it is necessary to do so, it may, by order, direct`
  line `that the audit of cost records of class of companies, which are covered under sub-section (1) and which`
  line `have a net worth of such amount as may be prescribed or a turnover of such amount as may be prescribed,`
  line `shall be conducted in the manner specified in the order.`
  line
  line `(3) The audit under sub-section (2) shall be conducted by a ^1[cost accountant] who shall be appointed`
  line `by the Board on such remuneration as may be determined by the members in such manner as may be`
  line `prescribed:`
  line
  line `Provided that no person appointed under section 139 as an auditor of the company shall be appointed`
  line `for conducting the audit of cost records:`
  line
  line `Provided further that the auditor conducting the cost audit shall comply with the cost auditing`
  line standards.
  line
  line `Explanation.-- For the purposes of this sub-section, the expression cost auditing standards mean`
  line `such standards as are issued by the ^2[Institute of Cost Accountants of India], constituted under the Cost`
  line `and Works Accountants Act, 1959 (23 of 1959), with the approval of the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(4) An audit conducted under this section shall be in addition to the audit conducted under section`
  line 143.
  line
  line `(5) The qualifications, disqualifications, rights, duties and obligations applicable to auditors under this`
  line `Chapter shall, so far as may be applicable, apply to a cost auditor appointed under this section and it shall`
  line `be the duty of the company to give all assistance and facilities to the cost auditor appointed under this`
  line `section for auditing the cost records of the company:`
  line
  line `Provided that the report on the audit of cost records shall be submitted by the ^3[cost accountant] to the`
  line `Board of Directors of the company`
  line
  line `(6) A company shall within thirty days from the date of receipt of a copy of the cost audit report`
  line `prepared in pursuance of a direction under sub-section (2) furnish the Central Government with such`
  line `report along with full information and explanation on every reservation or qualification contained therein.`
  line
  line `(7) If, after considering the cost audit report referred to under this section and the information and`
  line `explanation furnished by the company under sub-section (6), the Central Government is of the opinion`
  line `that any further information or explanation is necessary, it may call for such further information and`
  line `explanation and the company shall furnish the same within such time as may be specified by that`
  line Government.
  line
  line `(8) If any default is made in complying with the provisions of this section,`
  line
  line `(a) the company and every officer of the company who is in default shall be punishable in the`
  line `manner as provided in sub-section (1) of section 147;`
  line
  line `(b) the cost auditor of the company who is in default shall be punishable in the manner as`
  line `provided in sub-sections (2) to (4) of section 147.`
obj_root_law_sections_148_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 1 of 2018, s. 45, for Cost Accountant in practice(w.e.f. 9-2-2018).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by s. 45, ibid., for Institute of Cost and Works Accountants of India (w.e.f. 9-2-2018).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by s. 45, ibid., for cost accountant in practice(w.e.f. 9-2-2018).`
obj_root_law_sections_149:
  sectionId (49078)
  sectionNo (149)
  orderNo 153
  title `Company to have Board of Directors`
  content obj_root_law_sections_149_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_149_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=49078&sectionno=149&orderno=153&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_149_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every company shall have a Board of Directors`
  line `consisting of individuals as directors and shall have--`
  line
  line `(a) a minimum number of three directors in the case of a public company, two directors in the`
  line `case of a private company, and one director in the case of a One Person Company; and`
  line
  line `(b) a maximum of fifteen directors:`
  line
  line `Provided that a company may appoint more than fifteen directors after passing a special resolution:`
  line
  line `Provided further that such class or classes of companies as may be prescribed, shall have at least one`
  line `woman director.`
  line
  line `(2) Every company existing on or before the date of commencement of this Act shall within one year`
  line `from such commencement comply with the requirements of the provisions of sub-section (1).`
  line
  line `^1[(3) Every company shall have at least one director who stays in India for a total period of not less`
  line `than one hundred and eighty-two days during the financial year:`
  line
  line `Provided that in case of a newly incorporated company the requirement under this sub-section shall`
  line `apply proportionately at the end of the financial year in which it is incorporated];`
  line
  line `(4) Every listed public company shall have at least one-third of the total number of directors as`
  line `independent directors and the Central Government may prescribe the minimum number of independent`
  line `directors in case of any class or classes of public companies.`
  line
  line `Explanation.-- For the purposes of this sub-section, any fraction contained in such one-third number`
  line `shall be rounded off as one.`
  line
  line `(5) Every company existing on or before the date of commencement of this Act shall, within one year`
  line `from such commencement or from the date of notification of the rules in this regard as may be applicable,`
  line `comply with the requirements of the provisions of sub-section (4).`
  line
  line `(6) An independent director in relation to a company, means a director other than a managing director--`
  line
  line `or a whole-time director or a nominee director,`
  line
  line `(a) who, in the opinion of the Board, is a person of integrity and possesses relevant expertise and`
  line experience;
  line
  line `(b) (i) who is or was not a promoter of the company or its holding, subsidiary or associate`
  line company;
  line
  line `(ii) who is not related to promoters or directors in the company, its holding, subsidiary or`
  line `associate company;`
  line
  line `(c) who has or had no ^2[pecuniary relationship, other than remuneration as such director or having`
  line `transaction not exceeding ten per cent. of his total income or such amount as may be prescribed,] with`
  line `the company, its holding, subsidiary or associate company, or their promoters, or directors, during the`
  line `two immediately preceding financial years or during the current financial year;`
  line
  line `^3[(d) none of whose relatives--`
  line
  line `(i) is holding any security of or interest in the company, its holding, subsidiary or associate`
  line `company during the two immediately preceding financial years or during the current financial year:`
  line
  line `Provided that the relative may hold security or interest in the company of face value not`
  line `exceeding fifty lakh rupees or two per cent. of the paid-up capital of the company, its holding,`
  line `subsidiary or associate company or such higher sum as may be prescribed;`
  line
  line `(ii) is indebted to the company, its holding, subsidiary or associate company or their promoters,`
  line `or directors, in excess of such amount as may be prescribed during the two immediately preceding`
  line `financial years or during the current financial year;`
  line
  line `(iii) has given a guarantee or provided any security in connection with the indebtedness of any`
  line `third person to the company, its holding, subsidiary or associate company or their promoters, or`
  line `directors of such holding company, for such amount as may be prescribed during the two`
  line `immediately preceding financial years or during the current financial year; or`
  line
  line `(iv) has any other pecuniary transaction or relationship with the company, or its subsidiary, or`
  line `its holding or associate company amounting to two per cent. or more of its gross turnover or total`
  line `income singly or in combination with the transactions referred to in sub-clause (i), (ii) or (iii);]`
  line
  line `(e) who, neither himself nor any of his relatives`
  line
  line `(i) holds or has held the position of a key managerial personnel or is or has been employee of`
  line `the company or its holding, subsidiary or associate company in any of the three financial years`
  line `immediately preceding the financial year in which he is proposed to be appointed;`
  line
  line `^4[Provided that in case of a relative who is an employee, the restriction under this clause shall`
  line `not apply for his employment during preceding three financial years.]`
  line
  line `(ii) is or has been an employee or proprietor or a partner, in any of the three financial years`
  line `immediately preceding the financial year in which he is proposed to be appointed, of`
  line
  line `(A) a firm of auditors or company secretaries in practice or cost auditors of the company`
  line `or its holding, subsidiary or associate company; or`
  line
  line `(B) any legal or a consulting firm that has or had any transaction with the company, its`
  line `holding, subsidiary or associate company amounting to ten per cent. or more of the gross`
  line `turnover of such firm;`
  line
  line `(iii) holds together with his relatives two per cent. or more of the total voting power of the`
  line `company; or`
  line
  line `(iv) is a Chief Executive or director, by whatever name called, of any nonprofit organisation`
  line `that receives twenty-five per cent. or more of its receipts from the company, any of its promoters,`
  line `directors or its holding, subsidiary or associate company or that holds two per cent. or more of the`
  line `total voting power of the company; or`
  line
  line `(f) who possesses such other qualifications as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(7) Every independent director shall at the first meeting of the Board in which he participates as a`
  line `director and thereafter at the first meeting of the Board in every financial year or whenever there is any`
  line `change in the circumstances which may affect his status as an independent director, give a declaration that`
  line `he meets the criteria of independence as provided in sub-section (6).`
  line
  line `Explanation.-- For the purposes of this section, nominee director means a director nominated by`
  line `any financial institution in pursuance of the provisions of any law for the time being in force, or of any`
  line `agreement, or appointed by any Government, or any other person to represent its interests.`
  line
  line `(8) The company and independent directors shall abide by the provisions specified in Schedule IV.`
  line
  line `(9) Notwithstanding anything contained in any other provision of this Act, but subject to the`
  line `provisions of sections 197 and 198, an independent director shall not be entitled to any stock option and`
  line `may receive remuneration by way of fee provided under sub-section (5) of section 197, reimbursement of`
  line `expenses for participation in the Board and other meetings and profit related commission as may be`
  line `approved by the members.`
  line
  line `^5[Provided that if a company has no profits or its profits are inadequate, an independent director may receive`
  line `remuneration, exclusive of any fees payable under sub-section (5) of section 197, in accordance with the`
  line `provisions of Schedule V.]`
  line
  line `(10) Subject to the provisions of section 152, an independent director shall hold office for a term up to`
  line `five consecutive years on the Board of a company, but shall be eligible for reappointment on passing of a`
  line `special resolution by the company and disclosure of such appointment in the Board's report.`
  line
  line `(11) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (10), no independent director shall hold`
  line `office for more than two consecutive terms, but such independent director shall be eligible for`
  line `appointment after the expiration of three years of ceasing to become an independent director:`
  line
  line `Provided that an independent director shall not, during the said period of three years, be appointed in`
  line `or be associated with the company in any other capacity, either directly or indirectly.`
  line
  line `Explanation.-- For the purposes of sub-sections (10) and (11), any tenure of an independent director`
  line `on the date of commencement of this Act shall not be counted as a term under those sub-sections.`
  line
  line `(12) Notwithstanding anything contained in this Act,--`
  line
  line `(i) an independent director;`
  line
  line `(ii) a non-executive director not being promoter or key managerial personnel,`
  line
  line `shall be held liable, only in respect of such acts of omission or commission by a company which had`
  line `occurred with his knowledge, attributable through Board processes, and with his consent or connivance or`
  line `where he had not acted diligently.`
  line
  line `(13) The provisions of sub-sections (6) and (7) of section 152 in respect of retirement of directors by`
  line `rotation shall not be applicable to appointment of independent directors.`
obj_root_law_sections_149_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 1 of 2018, s. 46, for sub-section (3) (w.e.f. 7-5-2018).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by 46, ibid., for "pecuniary relationship" (w.e.f. 7-5-2018).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by s. 46, ibid., for Clause (d) (w.e.f. 7-5-2018).`
  line
  line `4. The proviso ins. by Act 1 of 2018, s. 46 (w.e.f. 7-5-2018).`
  line
  line `5. Ins. by Act 29 of 2020, s. 32 (w.e.f. 18-3-2021).`
obj_root_law_sections_150:
  sectionId (49079)
  sectionNo (150)
  orderNo 154
  title `Manner of selection of independent directors and maintenance of data bank of independent directors.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_150_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_150_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=49079&sectionno=150&orderno=154&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_150_content:
  string
  line `(1) Subject to the provisions contained in sub-section (6) of section 149, an independent`
  line `director may be selected from a data bank containing names, addresses and qualifications of persons who`
  line `are eligible and willing to act as independent directors, maintained by any body, institute or association,`
  line `as may by notified by the Central Government, having expertise in creation and maintenance of such data`
  line `bank and put on their website for the use by the company making the appointment of such directors:`
  line
  line `Provided that responsibility of exercising due diligence before selecting a person from the data bank`
  line `referred to above, as an independent director shall lie with the company making such appointment.`
  line
  line `(2) The appointment of independent director shall be approved by the company in general meeting as`
  line `provided in sub-section (2) of section 152 and the explanatory statement annexed to the notice of the`
  line `general meeting called to consider the said appointment shall indicate the justification for choosing the`
  line `appointee for appointment as independent director.`
  line
  line `(3) The data bank referred to in sub-section (1), shall create and maintain data of persons willing to`
  line `act as independent director in accordance with such rules as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(4) The Central Government may prescribe the manner and procedure of selection of independent`
  line `directors who fulfil the qualifications and requirements specified under section 149.`
obj_root_law_sections_150_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_151:
  sectionId (49080)
  sectionNo (151)
  orderNo 155
  title `Appointment of director elected by small shareholders.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_151_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_151_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=49080&sectionno=151&orderno=155&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_151_content:
  string
  line `A listed company may have one`
  line `director elected by such small shareholders in such manner and with such terms and conditions as may be`
  line prescribed.
  line
  line `Explanation.-- For the purposes of this section "small shareholders" means a shareholder holding`
  line `shares of nominal value of not more than twenty thousand rupees or such other sum as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_151_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_152:
  sectionId (49081)
  sectionNo (152)
  orderNo 156
  title `Appointment of directors`
  content obj_root_law_sections_152_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 1 of 2018, s. 47 (w.e.f. 9-2-2018).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=49081&sectionno=152&orderno=156&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_152_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where no provision is made in the articles of a company for`
  line `the appointment of the first director, the subscribers to the memorandum who are individuals shall be`
  line `deemed to be the first directors of the company until the directors are duly appointed and in case of a One`
  line `Person Company an individual being member shall be deemed to be its first director until the director or`
  line `directors are duly appointed by the member in accordance with the provisions of this section.`
  line
  line `(2) Save as otherwise expressly provided in this Act, every director shall be appointed by the`
  line `company in general meeting.`
  line
  line `(3) No person shall be appointed as a director of a company unless he has been allotted the Director`
  line `Identification Number under section 154 ^1[or any other number as may be prescribed under section 153].`
  line
  line `(4) Every person proposed to be appointed as a director by the company in general meeting or`
  line `otherwise, shall furnish his Director Identification Number ^1[or such other number as may be prescribed`
  line `under section 153] and a declaration that he is not disqualified to become a director under this Act.`
  line
  line `(5) A person appointed as a director shall not act as a director unless he gives his consent to hold the`
  line `office as director and such consent has been filed with the Registrar within thirty days of his appointment`
  line `in such manner as may be prescribed:`
  line
  line `Provided that in the case of appointment of an independent director in the general meeting, an`
  line `explanatory statement for such appointment, annexed to the notice for the general meeting, shall include a`
  line `statement that in the opinion of the Board, he fulfils the conditions specified in this Act for such an`
  line appointment.
  line
  line `(6) (a) Unless the articles provide for the retirement of all directors at every annual general meeting,`
  line `not less than two-thirds of the total number of directors of a public company shall--`
  line
  line `(i) be persons whose period of office is liable to determination by retirement of directors by`
  line `rotation; and`
  line
  line `(ii) save as otherwise expressly provided in this Act, be appointed by the company in general`
  line meeting.
  line
  line `(b) The remaining directors in the case of any such company shall, in default of, and subject to`
  line `any regulations in the articles of the company, also be appointed by the company in general meeting.`
  line
  line `(c) At the first annual general meeting of a public company held next after the date of the general`
  line `meeting at which the first directors are appointed in accordance with clauses (a) and (b) and at every`
  line `subsequent annual general meeting, one-third of such of the directors for the time being as are liable`
  line `to retire by rotation, or if their number is neither three nor a multiple of three, then, the number`
  line `nearest to one-third, shall retire from office.`
  line
  line `(d) The directors to retire by rotation at every annual general meeting shall be those who have`
  line `been longest in office since their last appointment, but as between persons who became directors on`
  line `the same day, those who are to retire shall, in default of and subject to any agreement among`
  line `themselves, be determined by lot.`
  line
  line `(e) At the annual general meeting at which a director retires as aforesaid, the company may fill up`
  line `the vacancy by appointing the retiring director or some other person thereto.`
  line
  line `Explanation.-- For the purposes of this sub-section, "total number of directors" shall not include`
  line `independent directors, whether appointed under this Act or any other law for the time being in force,`
  line `on the Board of a company.`
  line
  line `(7) (a) If the vacancy of the retiring director is not so filled-up and the meeting has not expressly`
  line `resolved not to fill the vacancy, the meeting shall stand adjourned till the same day in the next week, at`
  line `the same time and place, or if that day is a national holiday, till the next succeeding day which is not a`
  line `holiday, at the same time and place.`
  line
  line `(b) If at the adjourned meeting also, the vacancy of the retiring director is not filled up and that`
  line `meeting also has not expressly resolved not to fill the vacancy, the retiring director shall be deemed to`
  line `have been re-appointed at the adjourned meeting, unless--`
  line
  line `(i) at that meeting or at the previous meeting a resolution for the re-appointment of such director`
  line `has been put to the meeting and lost;`
  line
  line `(ii) the retiring director has, by a notice in writing addressed to the company or its Board of`
  line `directors, expressed his unwillingness to be so re-appointed;`
  line
  line `(iii) he is not qualified or is disqualified for appointment;`
  line
  line `(iv) a resolution, whether special or ordinary, is required for his appointment or re-appointment`
  line `by virtue of any provisions of this Act; or`
  line
  line `(v) section 162 is applicable to the case.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purposes of this section and section 160, the expression "retiring director"`
  line `means a director retiring by rotation.`
obj_root_law_sections_153:
  sectionId (49082)
  sectionNo (153)
  orderNo 157
  title `Application for allotment of Director Identification Number.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_153_content
  footnotes `1. The proviso ins. by Act 1 of 2018, s. 48 (w.e.f. 9-2-2018).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=49082&sectionno=153&orderno=157&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_153_content:
  string
  line `Every individual intending to`
  line `be appointed as director of a company shall make an application for allotment of Director Identification`
  line `Number to the Central Government in such form and manner and along with such fees as may be`
  line `prescribed:`
  line
  line `^1[Provided that the Central Government may prescribe any identification number which shall be treated as Director`
  line `Identification Number for the purposes of this Act and in case any individual holds or acquires such identification number,`
  line `the requirement of this section shall not apply or apply in such manner as may be prescribed.]`
obj_root_law_sections_154:
  sectionId (49083)
  sectionNo (154)
  orderNo 158
  title `Allotment of Director Identification Number.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_154_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_154_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=49083&sectionno=154&orderno=158&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_154_content:
  string
  line `The Central Government shall, within one`
  line `month from the receipt of the application under section 153, allot a Director Identification Number to an`
  line `applicant in such manner as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_154_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_155:
  sectionId (49084)
  sectionNo (155)
  orderNo 159
  title `Prohibition to obtain more than one Director Identification Number.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_155_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_155_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=49084&sectionno=155&orderno=159&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_155_content:
  string
  line `No individual, who`
  line `has already been allotted a Director Identification Number under section 154, shall apply for, obtain or`
  line `possess another Director Identification Number.`
obj_root_law_sections_155_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_156:
  sectionId (49085)
  sectionNo (156)
  orderNo 160
  title `Director to intimate Director Identification Number`
  content obj_root_law_sections_156_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_156_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=49085&sectionno=156&orderno=160&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_156_content:
  string
  line `Every existing director shall, within`
  line `one month of the receipt of Director Identification Number from the Central Government, intimate his`
  line `Director Identification Number to the company or all companies wherein he is a director.`
obj_root_law_sections_156_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_157:
  sectionId (49086)
  sectionNo (157)
  orderNo 161
  title `Company to inform Director Identification Number to Registrar.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_157_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_157_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=49086&sectionno=157&orderno=161&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_157_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every company shall,`
  line `within fifteen days of the receipt of intimation under section 156, furnish the Director Identification`
  line `Number of all its directors to the Registrar or any other officer or authority as may be specified by the`
  line `Central Government with such fees as may be prescribed or with such additional fees as may be`
  line `prescribed ^1*** and every such intimation shall be furnished in such form and manner as may be`
  line prescribed.
  line
  line `^2[(2) If any company fails to furnish the Director Identification Number under sub-section (1), such`
  line `company shall be liable to a penalty of twenty-five thousand rupees and in case of continuing failure, with`
  line `a further penalty of one hundred rupees for each day after the first during which such failure continues,`
  line `subject to a maximum of one lakh rupees, and every officer of the company who is in default shall be`
  line `liable to a penalty of not less than twenty-five thousand rupees and in case of continuing failure, with a`
  line `further penalty of one hundred rupees for each day after the first during which such failure continues,`
  line `subject to a maximum of one lakh rupees.]`
obj_root_law_sections_157_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. The words and figures "within the time specified under section 403" omitted by s. 49, ibid. (w.e.f. 7-5-2018).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 22 of 2019, s. 24, for sub-section (2) (w.e.f. 2-11-2018).`
obj_root_law_sections_158:
  sectionId (49087)
  sectionNo (158)
  orderNo 162
  title `Obligation to indicate Director Identification Number.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_158_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_158_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=49087&sectionno=158&orderno=162&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_158_content:
  string
  line `Every person or company, while`
  line `furnishing any return, information or particulars as are required to be furnished under this Act, shall`
  line `mention the Director Identification Number in such return, information or particulars in case such return,`
  line `information or particulars relate to the director or contain any reference of any director.`
obj_root_law_sections_158_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_159:
  sectionId (49088)
  sectionNo (159)
  orderNo 163
  title `Penalty for default of certain provisions`
  content obj_root_law_sections_159_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by s. 25, ibid., for section 159 (w.e.f. 2-11-2018).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=49088&sectionno=159&orderno=163&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_159_content:
  string
  line `^1[159. Penalty for default of certain provisions.-- If any individual or director of a company makes`
  line `any default in complying with any of the provisions of section 152, section 155 and section 156, such`
  line `individual or director of the company shall be liable to a penalty which may extend to fifty thousand`
  line `rupees and where the default is a continuing one, with a further penalty which may extend to five hundred`
  line `rupees for each day after the first during which such default continues.]`
obj_root_law_sections_160:
  sectionId (49089)
  sectionNo (160)
  orderNo 164
  title `Right of persons other than retiring directors to stand for directorship.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_160_content
  footnotes `1. The proviso ins. by s. 50, ibid. (w.e.f. 9-2-2018).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=49089&sectionno=160&orderno=164&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_160_content:
  string
  line `(1) A person who`
  line `is not a retiring director in terms of section 152 shall, subject to the provisions of this Act, be eligible for`
  line `appointment to the office of a director at any general meeting, if he, or some member intending to propose`
  line `him as a director, has, not less than fourteen days before the meeting, left at the registered office of the`
  line `company, a notice in writing under his hand signifying his candidature as a director or, as the case may`
  line `be, the intention of such member to propose him as a candidate for that office, along with the deposit of`
  line `one lakh rupees or such higher amount as may be prescribed which shall be refunded to such person or, as`
  line `the case may be, to the member, if the person proposed gets elected as a director or gets more than`
  line `twenty-five per cent. of total valid votes cast either on show of hands or on poll on such resolution.`
  line
  line `^1[Provided that requirements of deposit of amount shall not apply in case of appointment of an`
  line `independent director or a director recommended by the Nomination and Remuneration Committee, if any,`
  line `constituted under sub-section (1) of section 178 or a director recommended by the Board of Directors of`
  line `the Company, in the case of a company not required to constitute Nomination and Remuneration`
  line Committee.]
  line
  line `(2) The company shall inform its members of the candidature of a person for the office of director`
  line `under sub-section (1) in such manner as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_161:
  sectionId (49090)
  sectionNo (161)
  orderNo 165
  title `Appointment of additional director, alternate director and nominee director.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_161_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_161_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=49090&sectionno=161&orderno=165&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_161_content:
  string
  line `(1) The`
  line `articles of a company may confer on its Board of Directors the power to appoint any person, other than a`
  line `person who fails to get appointed as a director in a general meeting, as an additional director at any time`
  line `who shall hold office up to the date of the next annual general meeting or the last date on which the`
  line `annual general meeting should have been held, whichever is earlier.`
  line
  line `(2) The Board of Directors of a company may, if so authorised by its articles or by a resolution passed`
  line `by the company in general meeting, appoint a person, not being a person holding any alternate`
  line `directorship for any other director in the company ^1[or holding directorship in the same company], to act`
  line `as an alternate director for a director during his absence for a period of not less than three months from`
  line `India:`
  line
  line `Provided that no person shall be appointed as an alternate director for an independent director unless`
  line `he is qualified to be appointed as an independent director under the provisions of this Act:`
  line
  line `Provided further that an alternate director shall not hold office for a period longer than that`
  line `permissible to the director in whose place he has been appointed and shall vacate the office if and when`
  line `the director in whose place he has been appointed returns to India:`
  line
  line `Provided also that if the term of office of the original director is determined before he so returns to`
  line `India, any provision for the automatic re-appointment of retiring directors in default of another`
  line `appointment shall apply to the original, and not to the alternate director.`
  line
  line `(3) Subject to the articles of a company, the Board may appoint any person as a director nominated by`
  line `any institution in pursuance of the provisions of any law for the time being in force or of any agreement`
  line `or by the Central Government or the State Government by virtue of its shareholding in a Government`
  line company.
  line
  line `((4) ^2*** If the office of any director appointed by the company in general meeting is vacated before`
  line `his term of office expires in the normal course, the resulting casual vacancy may, in default of and subject`
  line `to any regulations in the articles of the company, be filled by the Board of Directors at a meeting of the`
  line `Board ^1[which shall be subsequently approved by members in the immediate next general meeting]:`
  line
  line `Provided that any person so appointed shall hold office only up to the date up to which the director in`
  line `whose place he is appointed would have held office if it had not been vacated.`
obj_root_law_sections_161_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 1 of 2018, s. 51 (w.e.f. 9-2-2018).`
  line
  line `2. The words "In the case of a public company," omitted by s. 51, ibid. (w.e.f. 9-2-2018).`
obj_root_law_sections_162:
  sectionId (49091)
  sectionNo (162)
  orderNo 166
  title `Appointment of directors to be voted individually.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_162_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_162_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=49091&sectionno=162&orderno=166&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_162_content:
  string
  line `(1) At a general meeting of a company,`
  line `a motion for the appointment of two or more persons as directors of the company by a single resolution`
  line `shall not be moved unless a proposal to move such a motion has first been agreed to at the meeting`
  line `without any vote being cast against it.`
  line
  line `(2) A resolution moved in contravention of sub-section (1) shall be void, whether or not any objection`
  line `was taken when it was moved.`
  line
  line `(3) A motion for approving a person for appointment, or for nominating a person for appointment as a`
  line `director, shall be treated as a motion for his appointment.`
obj_root_law_sections_162_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_163:
  sectionId (49092)
  sectionNo (163)
  orderNo 167
  title `Option to adopt principle of proportional representation for appointment of directors.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_163_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_163_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=49092&sectionno=163&orderno=167&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_163_content:
  string
  line `Notwithstanding anything contained in this Act, the articles of a company may provide for the`
  line `appointment of not less than two-thirds of the total number of the directors of a company in accordance`
  line `with the principle of proportional representation, whether by the single transferable vote or by a system of`
  line `cumulative voting or otherwise and such appointments may be made once in every three years and casual`
  line `vacancies of such directors shall be filled as provided in sub-section (4) of section 161.`
obj_root_law_sections_163_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_164:
  sectionId (49093)
  sectionNo (164)
  orderNo 168
  title `Disqualifications for appointment of director.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_164_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_164_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=49093&sectionno=164&orderno=168&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_164_content:
  string
  line `(1) A person shall not be eligible for`
  line `appointment as a director of a company, if --`
  line
  line `(a) he is of unsound mind and stands so declared by a competent court;`
  line
  line `(b) he is an undischarged insolvent;`
  line
  line `(c) he has applied to be adjudicated as an insolvent and his application is pending;`
  line
  line `(d) he has been convicted by a court of any offence, whether involving moral turpitude or`
  line `otherwise, and sentenced in respect thereof to imprisonment for not less than six months and a period`
  line `of five years has not elapsed from the date of expiry of the sentence:`
  line
  line `Provided that if a person has been convicted of any offence and sentenced in respect thereof to`
  line `imprisonment for a period of seven years or more, he shall not be eligible to be appointed as a`
  line `director in any company;`
  line
  line `(e) an order disqualifying him for appointment as a director has been passed by a court or`
  line `Tribunal and the order is in force;`
  line
  line `(f) he has not paid any calls in respect of any shares of the company held by him, whether alone`
  line `or jointly with others, and six months have elapsed from the last day fixed for the payment of the call;`
  line
  line `(g) he has been convicted of the offence dealing with related party transactions under section 188`
  line `at any time during the last preceding five years; or`
  line
  line `(h) he has not complied with sub-section (3) of section 152.`
  line
  line `^1[(i) he has not complied with the provisions of sub-section (1) of section 165.]`
  line
  line `(2) No person who is or has been a director of a company which--`
  line
  line `(a) has not filed financial statements or annual returns for any continuous period of three financial`
  line `years; or`
  line
  line `(b) has failed to repay the deposits accepted by it or pay interest thereon or to redeem any`
  line `debentures on the due date or pay interest due thereon or pay any dividend declared and such failure`
  line `to pay or redeem continues for one year or more,`
  line
  line `shall be eligible to be re-appointed as a director of that company or appointed in other company for a`
  line `period of five years from the date on which the said company fails to do so:`
  line
  line `^2[Provided that where a person is appointed as a director of a company which is in default of clause (a) or`
  line `clause (b), he shall not incur the disqualification for a period of six months from the date of his appointment.]`
  line
  line `(3) A private company may by its articles provide for any disqualifications for appointment as a`
  line `director in addition to those specified in sub-sections (1) and (2).`
  line
  line `^3[Provided that the disqualifications referred to in clauses (d), (e) and (g) of sub-section (1) shall`
  line `continue to apply even if the appeal or petition has been filed against the order of conviction or`
  line disqualification.]
obj_root_law_sections_164_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 22 of 2019, s. 26 (w.e.f. 2-11-2018).`
  line
  line `2. The proviso ins. by Act 1 of 2018, s. 52 (w.e.f. 7-5-2018).`
  line
  line `3. The proviso subs. by s. 52, ibid. (w.e.f. 7-5-2018).`
obj_root_law_sections_165:
  sectionId (49094)
  sectionNo (165)
  orderNo 169
  title `Number of directorships.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_165_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_165_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=49094&sectionno=165&orderno=169&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_165_content:
  string
  line `(1) No person, after the commencement of this Act, shall hold`
  line `office as a director, including any alternate directorship, in more than twenty companies at the same time:`
  line
  line `Provided that the maximum number of public companies in which a person can be appointed as a`
  line `director shall not exceed ten.`
  line
  line `^1[Explanation I ].-- For reckoning the limit of public companies in which a person can be appointed`
  line `as director, directorship in private companies that are either holding or subsidiary company of a public`
  line `company shall be included.`
  line
  line `^2[Explanation II.-- For reckoning the limit of directorships of twenty companies, the directorship in a`
  line `dormant company shall not be included.]`
  line
  line `(2) Subject to the provisions of sub-section (1), the members of a company may, by special`
  line `resolution, specify any lesser number of companies in which a director of the company may act as`
  line directors.
  line
  line `(3) Any person holding office as director in companies more than the limits as specified in`
  line `sub-section (1), immediately before the commencement of this Act shall, within a period of one year from`
  line `such commencement,--`
  line
  line `(a) choose not more than the specified limit of those companies, as companies in which he wishes`
  line `to continue to hold the office of director;`
  line
  line `(b) resign his office as director in the other remaining companies; and`
  line
  line `(c) intimate the choice made by him under clause (a), to each of the companies in which he was`
  line `holding the office of director before such commencement and to the Registrar having jurisdiction in`
  line `respect of each such company.`
  line
  line `(4) Any resignation made in pursuance of clause (b) of sub-section (3) shall become effective`
  line `immediately on the despatch thereof to the company concerned.`
  line
  line `(5) No such person shall act as director in more than the specified number of companies,--`
  line
  line `(a) after despatching the resignation of his office as director or non-executive director thereof, in`
  line `pursuance of clause (b) of sub-section (3); or`
  line
  line `(b) after the expiry of one year from the commencement of this Act,`
  line `whichever is earlier.`
  line
  line ^3
  line `[(6) If a person accepts an appointment as a director in violation of this section, he shall be liable to a`
  line `penalty of two thousand rupees for each day after the first during which such violation continues, subject`
  line `to a maximum of two lakh rupees.].`
obj_root_law_sections_165_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. The Explanation renumbered as Explanation I thereof by s. 53, ibid. (w.e.f. 9-2-2018).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by s. 53, ibid. (w.e.f. 9-2-2018`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 29 of 2020, s. 33, for sub-section (6) (w.e.f. 21-12-2020).`
obj_root_law_sections_166:
  sectionId (49095)
  sectionNo (166)
  orderNo 170
  title `Duties of directors.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_166_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_166_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=49095&sectionno=166&orderno=170&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_166_content:
  string
  line `(1) Subject to the provisions of this Act, a director of a company shall act`
  line `in accordance with the articles of the company.`
  line
  line `(2) A director of a company shall act in good faith in order to promote the objects of the company for`
  line `the benefit of its members as a whole, and in the best interests of the company, its employees, the`
  line `shareholders, the community and for the protection of environment.`
  line
  line `(3) A director of a company shall exercise his duties with due and reasonable care, skill and diligence`
  line `and shall exercise independent judgment.`
  line
  line `(4) A director of a company shall not involve in a situation in which he may have a direct or indirect`
  line `interest that conflicts, or possibly may conflict, with the interest of the company.`
  line
  line `(5) A director of a company shall not achieve or attempt to achieve any undue gain or advantage`
  line `either to himself or to his relatives, partners, or associates and if such director is found guilty of making`
  line `any undue gain, he shall be liable to pay an amount equal to that gain to the company.`
  line
  line `(6) A director of a company shall not assign his office and any assignment so made shall be void.`
  line
  line `(7) If a director of the company contravenes the provisions of this section such director shall be`
  line `punishable with fine which shall not be less than one lakh rupees but which may extend to five lakh`
  line rupees.
obj_root_law_sections_166_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_167:
  sectionId (49096)
  sectionNo (167)
  orderNo 171
  title `Vacation of office of director.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_167_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_167_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=49096&sectionno=167&orderno=171&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_167_content:
  string
  line `(1) The office of a director shall become vacant in case--`
  line
  line `(a) he incurs any of the disqualifications specified in section 164:`
  line
  line `^1[Provided that where he incurs disqualification under sub-section (2) of section 164, the office of`
  line `the director shall become vacant in all the companies, other than the company which is in default`
  line `under that sub-section];`
  line
  line `(b) he absents himself from all the meetings of the Board of Directors held during a period of`
  line `twelve months with or without seeking leave of absence of the Board;`
  line
  line `(c) he acts in contravention of the provisions of section 184 relating to entering into contracts or`
  line `arrangements in which he is directly or indirectly interested;`
  line
  line `(d) he fails to disclose his interest in any contract or arrangement in which he is directly or`
  line `indirectly interested, in contravention of the provisions of section 184;`
  line
  line `(e) he becomes disqualified by an order of a court or the Tribunal;`
  line
  line `(f) he is convicted by a court of any offence, whether involving moral turpitude or otherwise and`
  line `sentenced in respect thereof to imprisonment for not less than six months:`
  line
  line `^2[Provided that the office shall not be vacated by the director in case of orders referred to in`
  line `clauses (e) and (f)--`
  line
  line `(i) for thirty days from the date of conviction or order of disqualification;`
  line
  line `(ii) where an appeal or petition is preferred within thirty days as aforesaid against the conviction`
  line `resulting in sentence or order, until expiry of seven days from the date on which such appeal or`
  line `petition is disposed of; or`
  line
  line `(iii) where any further appeal or petition is preferred against order or sentence within seven`
  line `days, until such further appeal or petition is disposed of.]`
  line
  line `(g) he is removed in pursuance of the provisions of this Act;`
  line
  line `(h) he, having been appointed a director by virtue of his holding any office or other employment in`
  line `the holding, subsidiary or associate company, ceases to hold such office or other employment in that`
  line company.
  line
  line `(2) If a person, functions as a director even when he knows that the office of director held by him has`
  line `become vacant on account of any of the disqualifications specified in sub-section (1), he shall be`
  line `punishable ^3*** with fine which shall not be less than one lakh rupees but which may extend to ^4`
  line [five
  line `lakh rupees].`
  line
  line `(3) Where all the directors of a company vacate their offices under any of the disqualifications`
  line `specified in sub-section (1), the promoter or, in his absence, the Central Government shall appoint the`
  line `required number of directors who shall hold office till the directors are appointed by the company in the`
  line `general meeting.`
  line
  line `(4) A private company may, by its articles, provide any other ground for the vacation of the office of`
  line `a director in addition to those specified in sub-section (1).`
obj_root_law_sections_167_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. The proviso ins. by Act 1 of 2018, s. 54 (w.e.f. 7-5-2018).`
  line
  line `2. The proviso subs. by Act 1 of 2018, s. 54 (w.e.f. 7-5-2018).`
  line
  line `3. The words "with imprisonment for a term which may extend to one year or" omitted by Act 29 of 2020, s. 34 (w.e.f. 21-12-`
  line `2020).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by s. 34, ibid., for "five lakh rupees, or with both" (w.e.f. 21-12-2020).`
obj_root_law_sections_168:
  sectionId (49097)
  sectionNo (168)
  orderNo 172
  title `Resignation of director.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_168_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by s. 55, ibid., for "director shall also forward" (w.e.f. 7-5-2018).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=49097&sectionno=168&orderno=172&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_168_content:
  string
  line `(1) A director may resign from his office by giving a notice in`
  line `writing to the company and the Board shall on receipt of such notice take note of the same and the`
  line `company shall intimate the Registrar in such manner, within such time and in such form as may be`
  line `prescribed and shall also place the fact of such resignation in the report of directors laid in the`
  line `immediately following general meeting by the company:`
  line
  line `Provided that a ^1[director may also forward] a copy of his resignation along with detailed reasons for`
  line `the resignation to the Registrar within thirty days of resignation in such manner as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(2) The resignation of a director shall take effect from the date on which the notice is received by the`
  line `company or the date, if any, specified by the director in the notice, whichever is later:`
  line
  line `Provided that the director who has resigned shall be liable even after his resignation for the offences`
  line `which occurred during his tenure.`
  line
  line `(3) Where all the directors of a company resign from their offices, or vacate their offices under`
  line `section 167, the promoter or, in his absence, the Central Government shall appoint the required number of`
  line `directors who shall hold office till the directors are appointed by the company in general meeting.`
obj_root_law_sections_169:
  sectionId (1360)
  sectionNo (169)
  orderNo 173
  title `Removal of directors`
  content obj_root_law_sections_169_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_169_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=1360&sectionno=169&orderno=173&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_169_content:
  string
  line `(1) A company may, by ordinary resolution, remove a director, not`
  line `being a director appointed by the Tribunal under section 242, before the expiry of the period of his office`
  line `after giving him a reasonable opportunity of being heard:`
  line
  line `^1[Provided that an independent director re-appointed for second term under sub-section (10) of`
  line `section 149 shall be removed by the company only by passing a special resolution and after giving him a`
  line `reasonable opportunity of being heard:]`
  line
  line `^2[Provided further that] nothing contained in this sub-section shall apply where the company has`
  line `availed itself of the option given to it under section 163 to appoint not less than two-thirds of the total`
  line `number of directors according to the principle of proportional representation.`
  line
  line `(2) A special notice shall be required of any resolution, to remove a director under this section, or to`
  line `appoint somebody in place of a director so removed, at the meeting at which he is removed.`
  line
  line `(3) On receipt of notice of a resolution to remove a director under this section, the company shall`
  line `forthwith send a copy thereof to the director concerned, and the director, whether or not he is a member of`
  line `the company, shall be entitled to be heard on the resolution at the meeting.`
  line
  line `(4) Where notice has been given of a resolution to remove a director under this section and the`
  line `director concerned makes with respect thereto representation in writing to the company and requests its`
  line `notification to members of the company, the company shall, if the time permits it to do so,--`
  line
  line `(a) in any notice of the resolution given to members of the company, state the fact of the`
  line `representation having been made; and`
  line
  line `(b) send a copy of the representation to every member of the company to whom notice of the`
  line `meeting is sent (whether before or after receipt of the representation by the company),`
  line `and if a copy of the representation is not sent as aforesaid due to insufficient time or for the company's`
  line `default, the director may without prejudice to his right to be heard orally require that the representation`
  line `shall be read out at the meeting:`
  line
  line `Provided that copy of the representation need not be sent out and the representation need not be read`
  line `out at the meeting if, on the application either of the company or of any other person who claims to be`
  line `aggrieved, the Tribunal is satisfied that the rights conferred by this sub-section are being abused to secure`
  line `needless publicity for defamatory matter; and the Tribunal may order the company's costs on the`
  line `application to be paid in whole or in part by the director notwithstanding that he is not a party to it.`
  line
  line `(5) A vacancy created by the removal of a director under this section may, if he had been appointed`
  line `by the company in general meeting or by the Board, be filled by the appointment of another director in his`
  line `place at the meeting at which he is removed, provided special notice of the intended appointment has been`
  line `given under sub-section (2).`
  line
  line `(6) A director so appointed shall hold office till the date up to which his predecessor would have held`
  line `office if he had not been removed.`
  line
  line `(7) If the vacancy is not filled under sub-section (5), it may be filled as a casual vacancy in`
  line `accordance with the provisions of this Act:`
  line
  line `Provided that the director who was removed from office shall not be re-appointed as a director by the`
  line `Board of Directors.`
  line
  line `(8) Nothing in this section shall be taken--`
  line
  line `(a) as depriving a person removed under this section of any compensation or damages payable to`
  line `him in respect of the termination of his appointment as director as per the terms of contract or terms`
  line `of his appointment as director, or of any other appointment terminating with that as director; or`
  line
  line `(b) as derogating from any power to remove a director under other provisions of this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_169_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. The proviso ins. by Notification No. S.O. 768(E), dated 21st February, 2018 (w.e.f. 21-2-2018).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by ibid., for "Provided that" (w.e.f. 21-2-2018)`
obj_root_law_sections_170:
  sectionId (1361)
  sectionNo (170)
  orderNo 174
  title `Register of directors and key managerial personnel and their shareholding.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_170_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_170_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=1361&sectionno=170&orderno=174&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_170_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every`
  line `company shall keep at its registered office a register containing such particulars of its directors and key`
  line `managerial personnel as may be prescribed, which shall include the details of securities held by each of`
  line `them in the company or its holding, subsidiary, subsidiary of company's holding company or associate`
  line companies.
  line
  line `(2) A return containing such particulars and documents as may be prescribed, of the directors and the`
  line `key managerial personnel shall be filed with the Registrar within thirty days from the appointment of`
  line `every director and key managerial personnel, as the case may be, and within thirty days of any change`
  line `taking place.`
obj_root_law_sections_170_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_171:
  sectionId (1362)
  sectionNo (171)
  orderNo 175
  title `Members‘ right to inspect.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_171_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_171_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=1362&sectionno=171&orderno=175&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_171_content:
  string
  line `(1) The register kept under sub-section (1) of section 170,--`
  line
  line `(a) shall be open for inspection during business hours and the members shall have a right to take`
  line `extracts therefrom and copies thereof, on a request by the members, be provided to them free of cost`
  line `within thirty days; and`
  line
  line `(b) shall also be kept open for inspection at every annual general meeting of the company and`
  line `shall be made accessible to any person attending the meeting.`
  line
  line `(2) If any inspection as provided in clause (a) of sub-section (1) is refused, or if any copy required`
  line `under that clause is not sent within thirty days from the date of receipt of such request, the Registrar shall`
  line `on an application made to him order immediate inspection and supply of copies required thereunder.`
obj_root_law_sections_171_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_172:
  sectionId (49098)
  sectionNo (172)
  orderNo 176
  title Penalty.
  content obj_root_law_sections_172_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 29 of 2020, s. 35, for section 35 (w.e.f. 21-12-2020).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=49098&sectionno=172&orderno=176&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_172_content:
  string
  line `^1[172. Penalty.-- If a company is in default in complying with any of the provisions of this Chapter`
  line `and for which no specific penalty or punishment is provided therein, the company and every officer of the`
  line `company who is in default shall be liable to a penalty of fifty thousand rupees, and in case of continuing`
  line `failure, with a further penalty of five hundred rupees for each day during which such failure continues,`
  line `subject to a maximum of three lakh rupees in case of a company and one lakh rupees in case of an officer`
  line `who is in default.]`
obj_root_law_sections_173:
  sectionId (49099)
  sectionNo (173)
  orderNo 177
  title `Meetings of Board.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_173_content
  footnotes `1. The proviso ins. by Act 1 of 2018, s. 56 (w.e.f. 7-5-2018).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=49099&sectionno=173&orderno=177&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_173_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every company shall hold the first meeting of the Board of Directors`
  line `within thirty days of the date of its incorporation and thereafter hold a minimum number of four meetings`
  line `of its Board of Directors every year in such a manner that not more than one hundred and twenty days`
  line `shall intervene between two consecutive meetings of the Board:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Central Government may, by notification, direct that the provisions of this subsection`
  line `shall not apply in relation to any class or description of companies or shall apply subject to such`
  line `exceptions, modifications or conditions as may be specified in the notification.`
  line
  line `(2) The participation of directors in a meeting of the Board may be either in person or through video`
  line `conferencing or other audio visual means, as may be prescribed, which are capable of recording and`
  line `recognising the participation of the directors and of recording and storing the proceedings of such`
  line `meetings along with date and time:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Central Government may, by notification, specify such matters which shall not be`
  line `dealt with in a meeting through video conferencing or other audio visual means.`
  line
  line `^1[Provided further that where there is quorum in a meeting through physical presence of directors, any`
  line `other director may participate through video conferencing or other audio visual means in such meeting on`
  line `any matter specified under the first proviso.]`
  line
  line `(3) A meeting of the Board shall be called by giving not less than seven days notice in writing to`
  line `every director at his address registered with the company and such notice shall be sent by hand delivery or`
  line `by post or by electronic means:`
  line
  line `Provided that a meeting of the Board may be called at shorter notice to transact urgent business`
  line `subject to the condition that at least one independent director, if any, shall be present at the meeting:`
  line
  line `Provided further that in case of absence of independent directors from such a meeting of the Board,`
  line `decisions taken at such a meeting shall be circulated to all the directors and shall be final only on`
  line `ratification thereof by at least one independent director, if any.`
  line
  line `(4) Every officer of the company whose duty is to give notice under this section and who fails to do`
  line `so shall be liable to a penalty of twenty-five thousand rupees.`
  line
  line `(5) A One Person Company, small company and dormant company shall be deemed to have complied`
  line `with the provisions of this section if at least one meeting of the Board of Directors has been conducted in`
  line `each half of a calendar year and the gap between the two meetings is not less than ninety days:`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing contained in this sub-section and in section 174 shall apply to One Person`
  line `Company in which there is only one director on its Board of Directors.`
obj_root_law_sections_174:
  sectionId (49100)
  sectionNo (174)
  orderNo 178
  title `Quorum for meetings of Board`
  content obj_root_law_sections_174_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_174_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=49100&sectionno=174&orderno=178&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_174_content:
  string
  line `(1) The quorum for a meeting of the Board of Directors of a`
  line `company hall be one-third of its total strength or two directors, whichever is higher, and the participation`
  line `of the directors by video conferencing or by other audio visual means shall also be counted for the`
  line `purposes of quorum under this sub-section.`
  line
  line `(2) The continuing directors may act notwithstanding any vacancy in the Board; but, if and so long as`
  line `their number is reduced below the quorum fixed by the Act for a meeting of the Board, the continuing`
  line `directors or director may act for the purpose of increasing the number of directors to that fixed for the`
  line `quorum, or of summoning a general meeting of the company and for no other purpose.`
  line
  line `(3) Where at any time the number of interested directors exceeds or is equal to two-thirds of the total`
  line `strength of the Board of Directors, the number of directors who are not interested directors and present at`
  line `the meeting, being not less than two, shall be the quorum during such time.`
  line
  line `Explanation.-- For the purposes of this sub-section, "interested director" means a director within the`
  line `meaning of sub-section (2) of section 184.`
  line
  line `(4) Where a meeting of the Board could not be held for want of quorum, then, unless the articles of`
  line `the company otherwise provide, the meeting shall automatically stand adjourned to the same day at the`
  line `same time and place in the next week or if that day is a national holiday, till the next succeeding day,`
  line `which is not a national holiday, at the same time and place.`
  line
  line `Explanation.-- For the purposes of this section,--`
  line
  line `(i) any fraction of a number shall be rounded off as one;`
  line
  line `(ii) "total strength" shall not include directors whose places are vacant.`
obj_root_law_sections_174_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_175:
  sectionId (49101)
  sectionNo (175)
  orderNo 179
  title `Passing of resolution by circulation`
  content obj_root_law_sections_175_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_175_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=49101&sectionno=175&orderno=179&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_175_content:
  string
  line `(1) No resolution shall be deemed to have been duly`
  line `passed by the Board or by a committee thereof by circulation, unless the resolution has been circulated in`
  line `draft, together with the necessary papers, if any, to all the directors, or members of the committee, as the`
  line `case may be, at their addresses registered with the company in India by hand delivery or by post or by`
  line `courier, or through such electronic means as may be prescribed and has been approved by a majority of`
  line `the directors or members, who are entitled to vote on the resolution:`
  line
  line `Provided that, where not less than one-third of the total number of directors of the company for the`
  line `time being require that any resolution under circulation must be decided at a meeting, the chairperson`
  line `shall put the resolution to be decided at a meeting of the Board.`
  line
  line `(2) A resolution under sub-section (1) shall be noted at a subsequent meeting of the Board or the`
  line `committee thereof, as the case may be, and made part of the minutes of such meeting.`
obj_root_law_sections_175_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_176:
  sectionId (49102)
  sectionNo (176)
  orderNo 180
  title `Defects in appointment of directors not to invalidate actions taken`
  content obj_root_law_sections_176_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_176_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=49102&sectionno=176&orderno=180&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_176_content:
  string
  line `No act done by a`
  line `person as a director shall be deemed to be invalid, notwithstanding that it was subsequently noticed that`
  line `his appointment was invalid by reason of any defect or disqualification or had terminated by virtue of any`
  line `provision contained in this Act or in the articles of the company:`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing in this section shall be deemed to give validity to any act done by the director`
  line `after his appointment has been noticed by the company to be invalid or to have terminated.`
obj_root_law_sections_176_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_177:
  sectionId (49103)
  sectionNo (177)
  orderNo 181
  title `Audit committee.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_177_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_177_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=49103&sectionno=177&orderno=181&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_177_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Board of Directors of ^1[every listed public company] and such`
  line `other class or classes of companies, as may be prescribed, shall constitute an Audit Committee.`
  line
  line `(2) The Audit Committee shall consist of a minimum of three directors with independent directors`
  line `forming a majority:`
  line
  line `Provided that majority of members of Audit Committee including its Chairperson shall be persons`
  line `with ability to read and understand, the financial statement.`
  line
  line `(3) Every Audit Committee of a company existing immediately before the commencement of this Act`
  line `shall, within one year of such commencement, be reconstituted in accordance with sub-section (2).`
  line
  line `(4) Every Audit Committee shall act in accordance with the terms of reference specified in writing by`
  line `the Board which shall, inter alia, include,--`
  line
  line `(i) the recommendation for appointment, remuneration and terms of appointment of auditors of`
  line `the company;`
  line
  line `(ii) review and monitor the auditor's independence and performance, and effectiveness of audit`
  line process;
  line
  line `(iii) examination of the financial statement and the auditors report thereon;`
  line
  line `(iv) approval or any subsequent modification of transactions of the company with related parties:`
  line
  line `^2[Provided that the Audit Committee may make omnibus approval for related party transactions`
  line `proposed to be entered into by the company subject to such conditions as may be prescribed;]`
  line
  line `^3[Provided further that in case of transaction, other than transactions referred to in section 188,`
  line `and where Audit Committee does not approve the transaction, it shall make its recommendations to`
  line `the Board:`
  line
  line `Provided also that in case any transaction involving any amount not exceeding one crore rupees is`
  line `entered into by a director or officer of the company without obtaining the approval of the Audit`
  line `Committee and it is not ratified by the Audit Committee within three months from the date of the`
  line `transaction, such transaction shall be voidable at the option of the Audit Committee and if the`
  line `transaction is with the related party to any director or is authorised by any other director, the director`
  line `concerned shall indemnify the company against any loss incurred by it:`
  line
  line `Provided also that the provisions of this clause shall not apply to a transaction, other than a`
  line `transaction referred to in section 188, between a holding company and its wholly owned subsidiary`
  line company.]
  line
  line `(v) scrutiny of inter-corporate loans and investments;`
  line
  line `(vi) valuation of undertakings or assets of the company, wherever it is necessary;`
  line
  line `(vii) evaluation of internal financial controls and risk management systems;`
  line
  line `(viii) monitoring the end use of funds raised through public offers and related matters.`
  line
  line `(5) The Audit Committee may call for the comments of the auditors about internal control systems,`
  line `the scope of audit, including the observations of the auditors and review of financial statement before`
  line `their submission to the Board and may also discuss any related issues with the internal and statutory`
  line `auditors and the management of the company.`
  line
  line `(6) The Audit Committee shall have authority to investigate into any matter in relation to the items`
  line `specified in sub-section (4) or referred to it by the Board and for this purpose shall have power to obtain`
  line `professional advice from external sources and have full access to information contained in the records of`
  line `the company.`
  line
  line `(7) The auditors of a company and the key managerial personnel shall have a right to be heard in the`
  line `meetings of the Audit Committee when it considers the auditors report but shall not have the right to`
  line vote.
  line
  line `(8) The Board's report under sub-section (3) of section 134 shall disclose the composition of an Audit`
  line `Committee and where the Board had not accepted any recommendation of the Audit Committee, the same`
  line `shall be disclosed in such report along with the reasons therefor.`
  line
  line `(9) Every listed company or such class or classes of companies, as may be prescribed, shall establish`
  line `a vigil mechanism for directors and employees to report genuine concerns in such manner as may be`
  line prescribed.
  line
  line `(10) The vigil mechanism under sub-section (9) shall provide for adequate safeguards against`
  line `victimisation of persons who use such mechanism and make provision for direct access to the chairperson`
  line `of the Audit Committee in appropriate or exceptional cases:`
  line
  line `Provided that the details of establishment of such mechanism shall be disclosed by the company on its`
  line `website, if any, and in the Boards report.`
obj_root_law_sections_177_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 1 of 2018, s. 57, for "every listed company" (w.e.f. 7-5-2018).`
  line
  line `2. The proviso ins. by Act 21 of 2015, s. 14 (w.e.f. 14-12-2015).`
  line
  line `3. Ins. by Act 1 of 2018, s. 57 (w.e.f. 7-5-2018).`
obj_root_law_sections_178:
  sectionId (49104)
  sectionNo (178)
  orderNo 182
  title `Nomination and Remuneration Committee and Stakeholders Relationship Committee.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_178_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_178_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=49104&sectionno=178&orderno=182&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_178_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Board of Directors of ^1[every listed public company] and such other class or`
  line `classes of companies, as may be prescribed shall constitute the Nomination and Remuneration Committee`
  line `consisting of three or more non-executive directors out of which not less than one-half shall be`
  line `independent directors:`
  line
  line `Provided that the chairperson of the company (whether executive or non-executive) may be appointed`
  line `as a member of the Nomination and Remuneration Committee but shall not chair such Committee.`
  line
  line `(2) The Nomination and Remuneration Committee shall identify persons who are qualified to become`
  line `directors and who may be appointed in senior management in accordance with the criteria laid down,`
  line `recommend to the Board their appointment and removal and ^2[shall specify the manner for effective`
  line `evaluation of performance of Board, its committees and individual directors to be carried out either by the`
  line `Board, by the Nomination and Remuneration Committee or by an independent external agency and`
  line `review its implementation and compliance].`
  line
  line `(3) The Nomination and Remuneration Committee shall formulate the criteria for determining`
  line `qualifications, positive attributes and independence of a director and recommend to the Board a policy,`
  line `relating to the remuneration for the directors, key managerial personnel and other employees.`
  line
  line `(4) The Nomination and Remuneration Committee shall, while formulating the policy under subsection (3) ensure that--`
  line
  line `(a) the level and composition of remuneration is reasonable and sufficient to attract, retain and`
  line `motivate directors of the quality required to run the company successfully;`
  line
  line `(b) relationship of remuneration to performance is clear and meets appropriate performance`
  line `benchmarks; and`
  line
  line `(c) remuneration to directors, key managerial personnel and senior management involves a`
  line `balance between fixed and incentive pay reflecting short and long-term performance objectives`
  line `appropriate to the working of the company and its goals:`
  line
  line `^3[Provided that such policy shall be placed on the website of the company, if any, and the salient`
  line `features of the policy and changes therein, if any, along with the web address of the policy, if any,`
  line `shall be disclosed in the Board's report.]`
  line
  line `(5) The Board of Directors of a company which consists of more than one thousand shareholders,`
  line `debenture-holders, deposit-holders and any other security holders at any time during a financial year shall`
  line `constitute a Stakeholders Relationship Committee consisting of a chairperson who shall be a nonexecutive`
  line `director and such other members as may be decided by the Board.`
  line
  line `(6) The Stakeholders Relationship Committee shall consider and resolve the grievances of security`
  line `holders of the company.`
  line
  line `(7) The chairperson of each of the committees constituted under this section or, in his absence, any`
  line `other member of the committee authorised by him in this behalf shall attend the general meetings of the`
  line company.
  line
  line `(8) In case of any contravention of the provisions of section 177 and this section, the company shall`
  line `be punishable with fine which shall not be less than one lakh rupees but which may extend to five lakh`
  line `rupees and every officer of the company who is in default shall be ^4`
  line `[liable to a penalty of five lakh rupees`
  line `and every officer of the company who is in default shall be liable to a penalty of one lakh rupees]:`
  line
  line `Provided that ^5[inability to resolve or consider any grievance] by the Stakeholders Relationship`
  line `Committee in good faith shall not constitute a contravention of this section.`
  line
  line `Explanation.-- The expression "senior management" means personnel of the company who are`
  line `members of its core management team excluding Board of Directors comprising all members of`
  line `management one level below the executive directors, including the functional heads.`
obj_root_law_sections_178_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 1 of 2018, s. 58, for "every listed company" (w.e.f. 7-5-2018).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by s. 58, ibid., for "shall carry out evaluation of every director's performance" (w.e.f. 7-5-2018).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by s. 58, ibid., for the proviso (w.e.f. 7-5-2018).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by Act 29 of 2020, s. 36, for certain words (w.e.f. 21-12-2020).`
  line
  line `5. Subs. by Act 1 of 2018, s. 58, for "non-consideration of resolution of any grievance" (w.e.f. 7-5-2018).`
obj_root_law_sections_179:
  sectionId (49105)
  sectionNo (179)
  orderNo 183
  title `Powers of Board.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_179_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_179_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=49105&sectionno=179&orderno=183&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_179_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Board of Directors of a company shall be entitled to exercise all`
  line `such powers, and to do all such acts and things, as the company is authorised to exercise and do:`
  line
  line `Provided that in exercising such power or doing such act or thing, the Board shall be subject to the`
  line `provisions contained in that behalf in this Act, or in the memorandum or articles, or in any regulations not`
  line `inconsistent therewith and duly made thereunder, including regulations made by the company in general`
  line `meeting:`
  line
  line `Provided further that the Board shall not exercise any power or do any act or thing which is directed`
  line `or required, whether under this Act or by the memorandum or articles of the company or otherwise, to be`
  line `exercised or done by the company in general meeting.`
  line
  line `(2) No regulation made by the company in general meeting shall invalidate any prior act of the Board`
  line `which would have been valid if that regulation had not been made.`
  line
  line `(3) The Board of Directors of a company shall exercise the following powers on behalf of the`
  line `company by means of resolutions passed at meetings of the Board, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) to make calls on shareholders in respect of money unpaid on their shares;`
  line
  line `(b) to authorise buy-back of securities under section 68;`
  line
  line `(c) to issue securities, including debentures, whether in or outside India;`
  line
  line `(d) to borrow monies;`
  line
  line `(e) to invest the funds of the company;`
  line
  line `(f) to grant loans or give guarantee or provide security in respect of loans;`
  line
  line `(g) to approve financial statement and the Boards report;`
  line
  line `(h) to diversify the business of the company;`
  line
  line `(i) to approve amalgamation, merger or reconstruction;`
  line
  line `(j) to take over a company or acquire a controlling or substantial stake in another company;`
  line
  line `(k) any other matter which may be prescribed:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Board may, by a resolution passed at a meeting, delegate to any committee of`
  line `directors, the managing director, the manager or any other principal officer of the company or in the case`
  line `of a branch office of the company, the principal officer of the branch office, the powers specified in`
  line `clauses (d) to (f) on such conditions as it may specify:`
  line
  line `Provided further that the acceptance by a banking company in the ordinary course of its business of`
  line `deposits of money from the public repayable on demand or otherwise and withdrawable by cheque, draft,`
  line `order or otherwise, or the placing of monies on deposit by a banking company with another banking`
  line `company on such conditions as the Board may prescribe, shall not be deemed to be a borrowing of`
  line `monies or, as the case may be, a making of loans by a banking company within the meaning of this`
  line section.
  line
  line `Explanation I.--Nothing in clause (d) shall apply to borrowings by a banking company from other`
  line `banking companies or from the Reserve Bank of India, the State Bank of India or any other banks`
  line `established by or under any Act.`
  line
  line `Explanation II.--In respect of dealings between a company and its bankers, the exercise by the`
  line `company of the power specified in clause (d) shall mean the arrangement made by the company with its`
  line `bankers for the borrowing of money by way of overdraft or cash credit or otherwise and not the actual`
  line `day-to-day operation on overdraft, cash credit or other accounts by means of which the arrangement so`
  line `made is actually availed of.`
  line
  line `(4) Nothing in this section shall be deemed to affect the right of the company in general meeting to`
  line `impose restrictions and conditions on the exercise by the Board of any of the powers specified in this`
  line section.
obj_root_law_sections_179_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_180:
  sectionId (49106)
  sectionNo (180)
  orderNo 184
  title `Restrictions on powers of Board.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_180_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 1 of 2018, s. 59, for “paid-up share capital and free reserves” (w.e.f. 9-2-2018)`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=49106&sectionno=180&orderno=184&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_180_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Board of Directors of a company shall exercise the`
  line `following powers only with the consent of the company by a special resolution, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) to sell, lease or otherwise dispose of the whole or substantially the whole of the undertaking of`
  line `the company or where the company owns more than one undertaking, of the whole or substantially`
  line `the whole of any of such undertakings.`
  line
  line `Explanation.-- For the purposes of this clause,--`
  line
  line `(i) "undertaking" shall mean an undertaking in which the investment of the company exceeds`
  line `twenty per cent. of its net worth as per the audited balance sheet of the preceding financial year or`
  line `an undertaking which generates twenty per cent. of the total income of the company during the`
  line `previous financial year;`
  line
  line `(ii) the expression "substantially the whole of the undertaking" in any financial year shall`
  line `mean twenty per cent. or more of the value of the undertaking as per the audited balance sheet of`
  line `the preceding financial year;`
  line
  line `(b) to invest otherwise in trust securities the amount of compensation received by it as a result of`
  line `any merger or amalgamation;`
  line
  line `(c) to borrow money, where the money to be borrowed, together with the money already`
  line `borrowed by the company will exceed aggregate of its ^1[paid-up share capital, free reserves and`
  line `securities premium], apart from temporary loans obtained from the company’s bankers in the ordinary`
  line `course of business:`
  line
  line `Provided that the acceptance by a banking company, in the ordinary course of its business, of`
  line `deposits of money from the public, repayable on demand or otherwise, and withdrawable by cheque,`
  line `draft, order or otherwise, shall not be deemed to be a borrowing of monies by the banking company`
  line `within the meaning of this clause.`
  line
  line `Explanation.-- For the purposes of this clause, the expression "temporary loans" means loans`
  line `repayable on demand or within six months from the date of the loan such as short-term, cash credit`
  line `arrangements, the discounting of bills and the issue of other short-term loans of a seasonal character,`
  line `but does not include loans raised for the purpose of financial expenditure of a capital nature;`
  line
  line `(d) to remit, or give time for the repayment of, any debt due from a director.`
  line
  line `(2) Every special resolution passed by the company in general meeting in relation to the exercise of`
  line `the powers referred to in clause (c) of sub-section (1) shall specify the total amount up to which monies`
  line `may be borrowed by the Board of Directors.`
  line
  line `(3) Nothing contained in clause (a) of sub-section (1) shall affect--`
  line
  line `(a) the title of a buyer or other person who buys or takes on lease any property, investment or`
  line `undertaking as is referred to in that clause, in good faith; or`
  line
  line `(b) the sale or lease of any property of the company where the ordinary business of the company`
  line `consists of, or comprises, such selling or leasing.`
  line
  line `(4) Any special resolution passed by the company consenting to the transaction as is referred to in`
  line `clause (a) of sub-section (1) may stipulate such conditions as may be specified in such resolution,`
  line `including conditions regarding the use, disposal or investment of the sale proceeds which may result from`
  line `the transactions:`
  line
  line `Provided that this sub-section shall not be deemed to authorise the company to effect any reduction in`
  line `its capital except in accordance with the provisions contained in this Act.`
  line
  line `(5) No debt incurred by the company in excess of the limit imposed by clause (c) of sub-section (1)`
  line `shall be valid or effectual, unless the lender proves that he advanced the loan in good faith and without`
  line `knowledge that the limit imposed by that clause had been exceeded.`
obj_root_law_sections_181:
  sectionId (49107)
  sectionNo (181)
  orderNo 185
  title `Company to contribute to bona fide and charitable funds, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_181_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_181_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=49107&sectionno=181&orderno=185&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_181_content:
  string
  line `The Board of Directors of a`
  line `company may contribute to bona fide charitable and other funds:`
  line
  line `Provided that prior permission of the company in general meeting shall be required for such`
  line `contribution in case any amount the aggregate of which, in any financial year, exceed five per cent. of its`
  line `average net profits for the three immediately preceding financial years.`
obj_root_law_sections_181_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_182:
  sectionId (49108)
  sectionNo (182)
  orderNo 186
  title `Prohibitions and restrictions regarding political contributions`
  content obj_root_law_sections_182_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_182_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=49108&sectionno=182&orderno=186&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_182_content:
  string
  line `(1) Notwithstanding`
  line `anything contained in any other provision of this Act, a company, other than a Government company and`
  line `a company which has been in existence for less than three financial years, may contribute any amount`
  line `directly or indirectly to any political party:`
  line
  line `^1* * * * *`
  line
  line `Provided ^2*** that no such contribution shall be made by a company unless a resolution authorising`
  line `the making of such contribution is passed at a meeting of the Board of Directors and such resolution shall,`
  line `subject to the other provisions of this section, be deemed to be justification in law for the making ^3*** of`
  line `the contribution authorised by it.`
  line
  line `(2) Without prejudice to the generality of the provisions of sub-section (1),--`
  line
  line `(a) a donation or subscription or payment caused to be given by a company on its behalf or on its`
  line `account to a person who, to its knowledge, is carrying on any activity which, at the time at which`
  line `such donation or subscription or payment was given or made, can reasonably be regarded as likely to`
  line `affect public support for a political party shall also be deemed to be contribution of the amount of`
  line `such donation, subscription or payment to such person for a political purpose;`
  line
  line `(b) the amount of expenditure incurred, directly or indirectly, by a company on an advertisement`
  line `in any publication, being a publication in the nature of a souvenir, brochure, tract, pamphlet or the`
  line `like, shall also be deemed,--`
  line
  line `(i) where such publication is by or on behalf of a political party, to be a contribution of such`
  line `amount to such political party, and`
  line
  line `(ii) where such publication is not by or on behalf of, but for the advantage of a political party,`
  line `to be a contribution for a political purpose.`
  line
  line `^4[(3) Every company shall disclose in its profit and loss account the total amount contributed by it under`
  line `this section during the financial year to which the account relates.`
  line
  line `(3A) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (1), the contribution under this section shall`
  line `not be made except by an account payee cheque drawn on a bank or an account payee bank draft or use of`
  line `electronic clearing system through a bank account:`
  line
  line `Provided that a company may make contribution through any instrument, issued pursuant to any`
  line `scheme notified under any law for the time being in force, for contribution to the political parties.]`
  line
  line `(4) If a company makes any contribution in contravention of the provisions of this section, the`
  line `company shall be punishable with fine which may extend to five times the amount so contributed and`
  line `every officer of the company who is in default shall be punishable with imprisonment for a term which`
  line `may extend to six months and with fine which may extend to five times the amount so contributed.`
  line
  line `Explanation.-- For the purposes of this section, "political party" means a political party registered`
  line `under section 29A of the Representation of the People Act, 1951 (43 of 1951).`
obj_root_law_sections_182_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. The proviso omitted by Act 7 of 2017, s. 154 (w.e.f. 31-3-2017).`
  line `2. The word “further” omitted by s. 154, ibid. (w.e.f. 31-3-2017).`
  line `3. The words “and the acceptance” omitted by s. 154, ibid. (w.e.f. 31-3-2017).`
  line `4. Subs. by s. 154, ibid., for sub-section (3) (w.e.f. 31-3-2017).`
obj_root_law_sections_183:
  sectionId (49109)
  sectionNo (183)
  orderNo 187
  title `Power of Board and other persons to make contributions to national defence fund, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_183_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_183_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=49109&sectionno=183&orderno=187&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_183_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Board of Directors of any company or any person or authority exercising the powers of the Board`
  line `of Directors of a company, or of the company in general meeting, may, notwithstanding anything`
  line `contained in sections 180, 181 and section 182 or any other provision of this Act or in the memorandum,`
  line `articles or any other instrument relating to the company, contribute such amount as it thinks fit to the`
  line `National Defence Fund or any other Fund approved by the Central Government for the purpose of`
  line `national defence.`
  line
  line `(2) Every company shall disclose in its profits and loss account the total amount or amounts`
  line `contributed by it to the Fund referred to in sub-section (1) during the financial year to which the amount`
  line relates.
obj_root_law_sections_183_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_184:
  sectionId (49110)
  sectionNo (184)
  orderNo 188
  title `Disclosure of interest by director.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_184_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_184_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=49110&sectionno=184&orderno=188&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_184_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every director shall at the first meeting of the Board in`
  line `which he participates as a director and thereafter at the first meeting of the Board in every financial year`
  line `or whenever there is any change in the disclosures already made, then at the first Board meeting held after`
  line `such change, disclose his concern or interest in any company or companies or bodies corporate, firms, or`
  line `other association of individuals which shall include the shareholding, in such manner as may be`
  line prescribed.
  line
  line `(2) Every director of a company who is in any way, whether directly or indirectly, concerned or`
  line `interested in a contract or arrangement or proposed contract or arrangement entered into or to be entered`
  line into--
  line
  line `(a) with a body corporate in which such director or such director in association with any other`
  line `director, holds more than two per cent. shareholding of that body corporate, or is a promoter, manager, Chief Executive Officer of that body corporate; or`
  line
  line `(b) with a firm or other entity in which, such director is a partner, owner or member, as the case`
  line `may be,`
  line
  line `shall disclose the nature of his concern or interest at the meeting of the Board in which the contract or`
  line `arrangement is discussed and shall not participate in such meeting:`
  line
  line `Provided that where any director who is not so concerned or interested at the time of entering into`
  line `such contract or arrangement, he shall, if he becomes concerned or interested after the contract or`
  line `arrangement is entered into, disclose his concern or interest forthwith when he becomes concerned or`
  line `interested or at the first meeting of the Board held after he becomes so concerned or interested.`
  line
  line `(3) A contract or arrangement entered into by the company without disclosure under sub-section (2)`
  line `or with participation by a director who is concerned or interested in any way, directly or indirectly, in the`
  line `contract or arrangement, shall be voidable at the option of the company.`
  line
  line `(4) If a director of the company contravenes the provisions of sub-section (1) or sub-section (2), such`
  line `director shall be ^1`
  line `[liable to a penalty of one lakh rupees].br`
  line
  line `(5) Nothing in this section--`
  line
  line `(a) shall be taken to prejudice the operation of any rule of law restricting a director of a company`
  line `from having any concern or interest in any contract or arrangement with the company;`
  line
  line `^2[(b) shall apply to any contract or arrangement entered into or to be entered into between two`
  line `companies or between one or more companies and one or more bodies corporate where any of the`
  line `directors of the one company or body corporate or two or more of them together holds or hold not more`
  line `than two per cent. of the paid-up share capital in the other company or the body corporate.]`
obj_root_law_sections_184_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 29 of 2020, s. 37, for certain words (w.e.f. 21-12-2020).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 1 of 2018, s. 60, for clause (b) (w.e.f. 9-2-2018).`
obj_root_law_sections_185:
  sectionId (49111)
  sectionNo (185)
  orderNo 189
  title `Loan to directors, etc`
  content obj_root_law_sections_185_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by s. 61, ibid., for section 185 (w.e.f. 7-5-2018).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=49111&sectionno=185&orderno=189&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_185_content:
  string
  line `^1[185. Loans to directors, etc.-- (1) No company shall, directly or indirectly, advance any loan,`
  line `including any loan represented by a book debt to, or give any guarantee or provide any security in`
  line `connection with any loan taken by,--`
  line
  line `(a) any director of company, or of a company which is its holding company or any partner or`
  line `relative of any such director; or`
  line
  line `(b) any firm in which any such director or relative is a partner.`
  line
  line `(2) A company may advance any loan including any loan represented by a book debt, or give any`
  line `guarantee or provide any security in connection with any loan taken by any person in whom any of the`
  line `director of the company is interested, subject to the condition that--`
  line
  line `(a) a special resolution is passed by the company in general meeting:`
  line
  line `Provided that the explanatory statement to the notice for the relevant general meeting shall disclose`
  line `the full particulars of the loans given, or guarantee given or security provided and the purpose for`
  line `which the loan or guarantee or security is proposed to be utilised by the recipient of the loan or`
  line `guarantee or security and any other relevant fact; and`
  line
  line `(b) the loans are utilised by the borrowing company for its principal business activities.`
  line
  line `Explanation.-- For the purposes of this sub-section, the expression "any person in whom any of the`
  line `director of the company is interested" means--`
  line
  line `(a) any private company of which any such director is a director or member;`
  line
  line `(b) any body corporate at a general meeting of which not less than twenty-five per cent. of the total`
  line `voting power may be exercised or controlled by any such director, or by two or more such directors,`
  line `together; or`
  line
  line `(c) any body corporate, the Board of directors, managing director or manager, whereof is`
  line `accustomed to act in accordance with the directions or instructions of the Board, or of any director or`
  line `directors, of the lending company.`
  line
  line `(3) Nothing contained in sub-sections (1) and (2) shall apply to--`
  line
  line `(a) the giving of any loan to a managing or whole-time director--`
  line
  line `(i) as a part of the conditions of service extended by the company to all its employees; or`
  line
  line `(ii) pursuant to any scheme approved by the members by a special resolution; or`
  line
  line `(b) a company which in the ordinary course of its business provides loans or gives guarantees or securities for the due repayment of any loan and in respect of such loans an interest is charged at a rate`
  line `not less than the rate of prevailing yield of one year, three years, five years or ten years Government`
  line `security closest to the tenor of the loan; or`
  line
  line `(c) any loan made by a holding company to its wholly owned subsidiary company or any guarantee`
  line `given or security provided by a holding company in respect of any loan made to its wholly owned`
  line `subsidiary company; or`
  line
  line `(d) any guarantee given or security provided by a holding company in respect of loan made by any`
  line `bank or financial institution to its subsidiary company:`
  line
  line `Provided that the loans made under clauses (c) and (d) are utilised by the subsidiary company for`
  line `its principal business activities.`
  line
  line `(4) If any loan is advanced or a guarantee or security is given or provided or utilised in contravention`
  line `of the provisions of this section,--`
  line
  line `(i) the company shall be punishable with fine which shall not be less than five lakh rupees but`
  line `which may extend to twenty-five lakh rupees;`
  line
  line `(ii) every officer of the company who is in default shall be punishable with imprisonment for a term`
  line `which may extend to six months or with fine which shall not be less than five lakh rupees but which`
  line `may extend to twenty-five lakh rupees; and`
  line
  line `(iii) the director or the other person to whom any loan is advanced or guarantee or security is given`
  line `or provided in connection with any loan taken by him or the other person, shall be punishable with`
  line `imprisonment which may extend to six months or with fine which shall not be less than five lakh`
  line `rupees but which may extend to twenty-five lakh rupees, or with both.]`
obj_root_law_sections_186:
  sectionId (49112)
  sectionNo (186)
  orderNo 190
  title `Loan and investment by company`
  content obj_root_law_sections_186_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_186_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=49112&sectionno=186&orderno=190&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_186_content:
  string
  line `(1) Without prejudice to the provisions contained in this`
  line `Act, a company shall unless otherwise prescribed, make investment through not more than two layers of`
  line `investment companies:`
  line
  line `Provided that the provisions of this sub-section shall not affect,--`
  line
  line `(i) a company from acquiring any other company incorporated in a country outside India if such`
  line `other company has investment subsidiaries beyond two layers as per the laws of such country;`
  line
  line `(ii) a subsidiary company from having any investment subsidiary for the purposes of meeting the`
  line `requirements under any law or under any rule or regulation framed under any law for the time being`
  line `in force.`
  line
  line `(2) No company shall directly or indirectly.--`
  line
  line `(a) give any loan to any person or other body corporate;`
  line
  line `(b) give any guarantee or provide security in connection with a loan to any other body corporate`
  line `or person; and`
  line
  line `(c) acquire by way of subscription, purchase or otherwise, the securities of any other body`
  line corporate,
  line
  line `exceeding sixty per cent. of its paid-up share capital, free reserves and securities premium account or one`
  line `hundred per cent. of its free reserves and securities premium account, whichever is more.`
  line
  line `^1[Explanation.-- For the purposes of this sub-section, the word person does not include any`
  line `individual who is in the employment of the company.]`
  line
  line `^2[(3) Where the aggregate of the loans and investment so far made, the amount for which guarantee or`
  line `security so far provided to or in all other bodies corporate along with the investment, loan, guarantee or`
  line `security proposed to be made or given by the Board, exceed the limits specified under sub-section (2), no`
  line `investment or loan shall be made or guarantee shall be given or security shall be provided unless`
  line `previously authorised by a special resolution passed in a general meeting:`
  line
  line `(Provided that where a loan or guarantee is given or where a security has been provided by a company`
  line `to its wholly owned subsidiary company or a joint venture company, or acquisition is made by a holding`
  line `company, by way of subscription, purchase or otherwise of, the securities of its wholly owned subsidiary`
  line `company, the requirement of this sub-section shall not apply:`
  line
  line `Provided further that the company shall disclose the details of such loans or guarantee or security or`
  line `acquisition in the financial statement as provided under sub-section (4).]`
  line
  line `(4) The company shall disclose to the members in the financial statement the full particulars of the`
  line `loans given, investment made or guarantee given or security provided and the purpose for which the loan`
  line `or guarantee or security is proposed to be utilised by the recipient of the loan or guarantee or security.`
  line
  line `(5) No investment shall be made or loan or guarantee or security given by the company unless the`
  line `resolution sanctioning it is passed at a meeting of the Board with the consent of all the directors present at`
  line `the meeting and the prior approval of the public financial institution concerned where any term loan is`
  line `subsisting, is obtained:`
  line
  line `Provided that prior approval of a public financial institution shall not be required where the aggregate`
  line `of the loans and investments so far made, the amount for which guarantee or security so far provided to or`
  line `in all other bodies corporate, along with the investments, loans, guarantee or security proposed to be made`
  line `or given does not exceed the limit as specified in sub-section (2), and there is no default in repayment of`
  line `loan instalments or payment of interest thereon as per the terms and conditions of such loan to the public`
  line `financial institution.`
  line
  line `(6) No company, which is registered under section 12 of the Securities and Exchange Board of India`
  line `Act, 1992 (15 of 1992) and covered under such class or classes of companies as may be prescribed, shall`
  line `take inter-corporate loan or deposits exceeding the prescribed limit and such company shall furnish in its`
  line `financial statement the details of the loan or deposits.`
  line
  line `(7) No loan shall be given under this section at a rate of interest lower than the prevailing yield of one`
  line `year, three year, five year or ten year Government Security closest to the tenor of the loan.`
  line
  line `(8) No company which is in default in the repayment of any deposits accepted before or after the`
  line `commencement of this Act or in payment of interest thereon, shall give any loan or give any guarantee or`
  line `provide any security or make an acquisition till such default is subsisting.`
  line
  line `(9) Every company giving loan or giving a guarantee or providing security or making an acquisition`
  line `under this section shall keep a register which shall contain such particulars and shall be maintained in`
  line `such manner as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(10) The register referred to in sub-section (9) shall be kept at the registered office of the company`
  line and--
  line
  line `(a) shall be open to inspection at such office; and`
  line
  line `(b) extracts may be taken therefrom by any member, and copies thereof may be furnished to any`
  line `member of the company on payment of such fees as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `^3[(11) Nothing contained in this section, except sub-section (1), shall apply--`
  line
  line `(a) to any loan made, any guarantee given or any security provided or any investment made by a`
  line `banking company, or an insurance company, or a housing finance company in the ordinary course of`
  line `its business, or a company established with the object of and engaged in the business of financing`
  line `industrial enterprises, or of providing infrastructural facilities;`
  line
  line `(b) to any investment--`
  line
  line `(i) made by an investment company;`
  line
  line `(ii) made in shares allotted in pursuance of clause (a) of sub-section (1) of section 62 or in`
  line `shares allotted in pursuance of rights issues made by a body corporate;`
  line
  line `(iii) made, in respect of investment or lending activities, by a non-banking financial company`
  line `registered under Chapter III-B of the Reserve Bank of India Act, 1934 (2 of 1934) and whose`
  line `principal business is acquisition of securities.]`
  line
  line `(12) The Central Government may make rules for the purposes of this section.`
  line
  line `(13) If a company contravenes the provisions of this section, the company shall be punishable with`
  line `fine which shall not be less than twenty-five thousand rupees but which may extend to five lakh rupees`
  line `and every officer of the company who is in default shall be punishable with imprisonment for a term`
  line `which may extend to two years and with fine which shall not be less than twenty-five thousand rupees but`
  line `which may extend to one lakh rupees.--`
  line
  line `Explanation.-- For the purposes of this section,`
  line
  line `(a) the expression "investment company" means a company whose principal business is the`
  line `acquisition of shares, debentures or other securities];`
  line
  line `(b) the expression "infrastructure facilities" means the facilities specified in Schedule VI.`
obj_root_law_sections_186_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 1 of 2018, s. 62 (w.e.f. 7-5-2018).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by s. 62, ibid., for "sub-section(3)" (w.e.f. 7-5-2018).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 1 of 2018, s. 62 for sub-section (11) (w.e.f. 7-5-2018).`
obj_root_law_sections_187:
  sectionId (49113)
  sectionNo (187)
  orderNo 191
  title `Investments of company to be held in its own name.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_187_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 29 of 2020, s. 38, for sub-section (4) (w.e.f. 21-12-2020).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=49113&sectionno=187&orderno=191&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_187_content:
  string
  line `(1) All investments made or held by a`
  line `company in any property, security or other asset shall be made and held by it in its own name:`
  line
  line `Provided that the company may hold any shares in its subsidiary company in the name of any`
  line `nominee or nominees of the company, if it is necessary to do so, to ensure that the number of members of`
  line `the subsidiary company is not reduced below the statutory limit.`
  line
  line `(2) Nothing in this section shall be deemed to prevent a company--`
  line
  line `(a) from depositing with a bank, being the bankers of the company, any shares or securities for`
  line `the collection of any dividend or interest payable thereon; or`
  line
  line `(b) from depositing with, or transferring to, or holding in the name of, the State Bank of India or a`
  line `scheduled bank, being the bankers of the company, shares or securities, in order to facilitate the`
  line `transfer thereof:`
  line
  line `Provided that if within a period of six months from the date on which the shares or securities are`
  line `transferred by the company to, or are first held by the company in the name of, the State Bank of`
  line `India or a scheduled bank as aforesaid, no transfer of such shares or securities takes place, the`
  line `company shall, as soon as practicable after the expiry of that period, have the shares or securities retransferred`
  line `to it from the State Bank of India or the scheduled bank or, as the case may be, again hold`
  line `the shares or securities in its own name; or`
  line
  line `(c) from depositing with, or transferring to, any person any shares or securities, by way of`
  line `security for the repayment of any loan advanced to the company or the performance of any obligation`
  line `undertaken by it;`
  line
  line `(d) from holding investments in the name of a depository when such investments are in the form`
  line `of securities held by the company as a beneficial owner.`
  line
  line `(3) Where in pursuance of clause (d) of sub-section (2), any shares or securities in which investments`
  line `have been made by a company are not held by it in its own name, the company shall maintain a register`
  line `which shall contain such particulars as may be prescribed and such register shall be open to inspection by`
  line `any member or debenture-holder of the company without any charge during business hours subject to`
  line `such reasonable restrictions as the company may by its articles or in general meeting impose.`
  line
  line `^1[(4) If a company is in default in complying with the provisions of this section, the company shall`
  line `be liable to a penalty of five lakh rupees and every officer of the company who is in default shall be liable`
  line `to a penalty of fifty thousand rupees.]`
obj_root_law_sections_188:
  sectionId (49114)
  sectionNo (188)
  orderNo 192
  title `Related party transactions.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_188_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_188_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=49114&sectionno=188&orderno=192&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_188_content:
  string
  line `(1) Except with the consent of the Board of Directors given by a`
  line `resolution at a meeting of the Board and subject to such conditions as may be prescribed, no company`
  line `shall enter into any contract or arrangement with a related party with respect to--`
  line
  line `(a) sale, purchase or supply of any goods or materials;`
  line
  line `(b) selling or otherwise disposing of, or buying, property of any kind;`
  line
  line `(c) leasing of property of any kind;`
  line
  line `(d) availing or rendering of any services;`
  line
  line `(e) appointment of any agent for purchase or sale of goods, materials, services or property;`
  line
  line `(f) such related party's appointment to any office or place of profit in the company, its subsidiary`
  line `company or associate company; and`
  line
  line `(g) underwriting the subscription of any securities or derivatives thereof, of the company:`
  line
  line `Provided that no contract or arrangement, in the case of a company having a paid-up share capital of`
  line `not less than such amount, or transactions exceeding such sums, as may be prescribed, shall be entered`
  line `into except with the prior approval of the company by a ^1[resolution]:`
  line
  line `Provided further that no member of the company shall vote on such ^1[resolution], to approve any`
  line `contract or arrangement which may be entered into by the company, if such member is a related party:`
  line
  line `^2[Provided also that nothing contained in the second proviso shall apply to a company in which ninety`
  line `per cent. or more members, in number, are relatives of promoters or are related parties:]`
  line
  line `Provided also that nothing in this sub-section shall apply to any transactions entered into by the`
  line `company in its ordinary course of business other than transactions which are not on an arms length basis:`
  line
  line `^3[Provided also that the requirement of passing the resolution under first proviso shall not be`
  line `applicable for transactions entered into between a holding company and its wholly owned subsidiary`
  line `whose accounts are consolidated with such holding company and placed before the shareholders at the`
  line `general meeting for approval.]`
  line
  line `Explanation.-- In this sub-section,--`
  line
  line `(a) the expression "office or place of profit" means any office or place--`
  line
  line `(i) where such office or place is held by a director, if the director holding it receives from the`
  line `company anything by way of remuneration over and above the remuneration to which he is`
  line `entitled as director, by way of salary, fee, commission, perquisites, any rent-free accommodation,`
  line `or otherwise;`
  line
  line `(ii) where such office or place is held by an individual other than a director or by any firm,`
  line `private company or other body corporate, if the individual, firm, private company or body`
  line `corporate holding it receives from the company anything by way of remuneration, salary, fee,`
  line `commission, perquisites, any rent-free accommodation, or otherwise;`
  line
  line `(b) the expression "arm's length transaction" means a transaction between two related parties that`
  line `is conducted as if they were unrelated, so that there is no conflict of interest.`
  line
  line `(2) Every contract or arrangement entered into under sub-section (1) shall be referred to in the`
  line `Boards report to the shareholders along with the justification for entering into such contract or`
  line arrangement.
  line
  line `(3) Where any contract or arrangement is entered into by a director or any other employee, without`
  line `obtaining the consent of the Board or approval by a ^1[resolution] in the general meeting under`
  line `sub-section (1) and if it is not ratified by the Board or, as the case may be, by the shareholders at a`
  line `meeting within three months from the date on which such contract or arrangement was entered into, such`
  line `contract or arrangement ^4[shall be voidable at the option of the Board or, as the case may be, of the`
  line `shareholders] and if the contract or arrangement is with a related party to any director, or is authorised by`
  line `any other director, the directors concerned shall indemnify the company against any loss incurred by it.`
  line
  line `(4) Without prejudice to anything contained in sub-section (3), it shall be open to the company to`
  line `proceed against a director or any other employee who had entered into such contract or arrangement in`
  line `contravention of the provisions of this section for recovery of any loss sustained by it as a result of such`
  line `contract or arrangement.`
  line
  line `(5) Any director or any other employee of a company, who had entered into or authorized the contract`
  line `or arrangement in violation of the provisions of this section shall,--`
  line
  line `(i) in case of listed company, be ^5[liable to a penalty of twenty-five lakh rupees]; and`
  line
  line `(ii) in case of any other company, be ^6[liable to a penalty of five lakh rupees]].`
obj_root_law_sections_188_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 21 of 2015, s. 16, for "special resolution" (w.e.f. 29-5-2015).`
  line
  line `2. The proviso ins. by Act 1 of 2018, s. 63 (w.e.f. 9-2-2018).`
  line
  line `3. The proviso ins. by Act 21 of 2015, s. 16 (w.e.f. 29-5-2015).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by Act 1 of 2018, s. 63, for "shall be voidable at the option of the Board" (w.e.f. 9-2-2018).`
  line
  line `5. Subs. by Act 29 of 2020, s. 39, for certain words (w.e.f. 21-12-2020).`
  line
  line `6. Subs. by s. 39, ibid., for certain words (w.e.f. 21-12-2020).`
obj_root_law_sections_189:
  sectionId (49115)
  sectionNo (189)
  orderNo 193
  title `Register of contracts or arrangements in which directors are interested`
  content obj_root_law_sections_189_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_189_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=49115&sectionno=189&orderno=193&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_189_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every`
  line `company shall keep one or more registers giving separately the particulars of all contracts or`
  line `arrangements to which sub-section (2) of section 184 or section 188 applies, in such manner and`
  line `containing such particulars as may be prescribed and after entering the particulars, such register or`
  line `registers shall be placed before the next meeting of the Board and signed by all the directors present at the`
  line meeting.
  line
  line `(2) Every director or key managerial personnel shall, within a period of thirty days of his`
  line `appointment, or relinquishment of his office, as the case may be, disclose to the company the particulars`
  line `specified in sub-section (1) of section 184 relating to his concern or interest in the other associations`
  line `which are required to be included in the register under that sub-section or such other information relating`
  line `to himself as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(3) The register referred to in sub-section (1) shall be kept at the registered office of the company and`
  line `it shall be open for inspection at such office during business hours and extracts may be taken therefrom,`
  line `and copies thereof as may be required by any member of the company shall be furnished by the company`
  line `to such extent, in such manner, and on payment of such fees as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(4) The register to be kept under this section shall also be produced at the commencement of every`
  line `annual general meeting of the company and shall remain open and accessible during the continuance of`
  line `the meeting to any person having the right to attend the meeting.--`
  line
  line `(5) Nothing contained in sub-section (1) shall apply to any contract or arrangement`
  line
  line `(a) for the sale, purchase or supply of any goods, materials or services if the value of such goods`
  line `and materials or the cost of such services does not exceed five lakh rupees in the aggregate in any`
  line `year; or`
  line
  line `(b) by a banking company for the collection of bills in the ordinary course of its business.`
  line
  line `(6) Every director who fails to comply with the provisions of this section and the rules made`
  line `thereunder shall be liable to a penalty of twenty-five thousand rupees.`
obj_root_law_sections_189_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_190:
  sectionId (49116)
  sectionNo (190)
  orderNo 194
  title `Contract of employment with managing or whole-time directors`
  content obj_root_law_sections_190_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_190_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=49116&sectionno=190&orderno=194&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_190_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every company`
  line `shall keep at its registered office,--`
  line
  line `(a) where a contract of service with a managing or whole-time director is in writing, a copy of the`
  line `contract; or`
  line
  line `(b) where such a contract is not in writing, a written memorandum setting out its terms.`
  line
  line `(2) The copies of the contract or the memorandum kept under sub-section (1) shall be open to`
  line `inspection by any member of the company without payment of fee.`
  line
  line `(3) If any default is made in complying with the provisions of sub-section (1) or sub-section`
  line
  line `(2), the`
  line `company shall be liable to a penalty of twenty-five thousand rupees and every officer of the company`
  line `who is in default shall be liable to a penalty of five thousand rupees for each default.`
  line
  line `(4) The provisions of this section shall not apply to a private company.`
obj_root_law_sections_190_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_191:
  sectionId (49117)
  sectionNo (191)
  orderNo 195
  title `Payment to director for loss of office, etc., in connection with transfer of undertaking, property or shares.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_191_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 22 of 2019, s. 28, for sub-section (5) (w.e.f. 2-11-2018).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=49117&sectionno=191&orderno=195&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_191_content:
  string
  line `(1) No director of a company shall, in connection with--`
  line
  line `(a) the transfer of the whole or any part of any undertaking or property of the company; or`
  line
  line `(b) the transfer to any person of all or any of the shares in a company being a transfer resulting`
  line from--
  line
  line `(i) an offer made to the general body of shareholders;`
  line
  line `(ii) an offer made by or on behalf of some other body corporate with a view to a company`
  line `becoming a subsidiary company of such body corporate or a subsidiary company of its holding`
  line company;
  line
  line `(iii) an offer made by or on behalf of an individual with a view to his obtaining the right to`
  line `exercise, or control the exercise of, not less than one-third of the total voting power at any general`
  line `meeting of the company; or`
  line
  line `(iv) any other offer which is conditional on acceptance to a given extent, receive any payment`
  line `by way of compensation for loss of office or as consideration for retirement from office, or in`
  line `connection with such loss or retirement from such company or from the transferee of such`
  line `undertaking or property, or from the transferees of shares or from any other person, not being`
  line `such company, unless particulars as may be prescribed with respect to the payment proposed to`
  line `be made by such transferee or person, including the amount thereof, have been disclosed to the`
  line `members of the company and the proposal has been approved by the company in general meeting.`
  line
  line `(2) Nothing in sub-section (1) shall affect any payment made by a company to a managing director or`
  line `whole-time director or manager of the company by way of compensation for loss of office or as`
  line `consideration for retirement from office or in connection with such loss or retirement subject to limits or`
  line `priorities, as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(3) If the payment under sub-section (1) or sub-section (2) is not approved for want of quorum either`
  line `in a meeting or an adjourned meeting, the proposal shall not be deemed to have been approved.`
  line
  line `(4) Where a director of a company receives payment of any amount in contravention of sub-section`
  line `(1) or the proposed payment is made before it is approved in the meeting, the amount so received by the`
  line `director shall be deemed to have been received by him in trust for the company.`
  line
  line `^1[(5) If a director of the company makes any default in complying with the provisions of this section,`
  line `such director shall be liable to a penalty of one lakh rupees.]`
  line
  line `(6) Nothing in this section shall be taken to prejudice the operation of any law requiring disclosure to`
  line `be made with respect to any payment received under this section or such other like payments made to a`
  line director.
obj_root_law_sections_192:
  sectionId (49118)
  sectionNo (192)
  orderNo 196
  title `Restriction on non-cash transactions involving directors.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_192_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_192_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=49118&sectionno=192&orderno=196&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_192_content:
  string
  line `(1) No company shall enter into`
  line `an arrangement by which--`
  line
  line `(a) a director of the company or its holding, subsidiary or associate company or a person`
  line `connected with him acquires or is to acquire assets for consideration other than cash, from the`
  line `company; or`
  line
  line `(b) the company acquires or is to acquire assets for consideration other than cash, from such`
  line `director or person so connected,`
  line
  line `unless prior approval for such arrangement is accorded by a resolution of the company in general meeting`
  line `and if the director or connected person is a director of its holding company, approval under this subsection`
  line `shall also be required to be obtained by passing a resolution in general meeting of the holding`
  line company.
  line
  line `(2) The notice for approval of the resolution by the company or holding company in general meeting`
  line `under sub-section (1) shall include the particulars of the arrangement along with the value of the assets`
  line `involved in such arrangement duly calculated by a registered valuer.`
  line
  line `(3) Any arrangement entered into by a company or its holding company in contravention of the`
  line `provisions of this section shall be voidable at the instance of the company unless--`
  line
  line `(a) the restitution of any money or other consideration which is the subject matter of the`
  line `arrangement is no longer possible and the company has been indemnified by any other person for any`
  line `loss or damage caused to it; or`
  line
  line `(b) any rights are acquired bona fide for value and without notice of the contravention of the`
  line `provisions of this section by any other person.`
obj_root_law_sections_192_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_193:
  sectionId (49119)
  sectionNo (193)
  orderNo 197
  title `Contract by One Person Company.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_193_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_193_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=49119&sectionno=193&orderno=197&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_193_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where One Person Company limited by shares or by`
  line `guarantee enters into a contract with the sole member of the company who is also the director of the`
  line `company, the company shall, unless the contract is in writing, ensure that the terms of the contract or`
  line `offer are contained in a memorandum or are recorded in the minutes of the first meeting of the Board of`
  line `Directors of the company held next after entering into contract:`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing in this sub-section shall apply to contracts entered into by the company in the`
  line `ordinary course of its business.`
  line
  line `(2) The company shall inform the Registrar about every contract entered into by the company and`
  line `recorded in the minutes of the meeting of its Board of Directors under sub-section (1) within a period of`
  line `fifteen days of the date of approval by the Board of Directors.`
obj_root_law_sections_193_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_194:
  sectionId (49120)
  sectionNo (194)
  orderNo 198
  title `Prohibition on forward dealings in securities of company by director or key managerial personnel`
  content obj_root_law_sections_194_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_194_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=49120&sectionno=194&orderno=198&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_194_content:
  string
  line `[Prohibition on forward dealings in securities of company by director or key managerial`
  line `personnel.] Omitted by the Companies (Amendment) Act, 2017 (1 of 2018), s. 64 (w.e.f. 9-2-2018).`
obj_root_law_sections_194_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_195:
  sectionId (49121)
  sectionNo (195)
  orderNo 199
  title `Prohibition on insider trading of securities.`
  content `[Prohibition on insider trading of securities.] Omitted by s. 65, ibid. (w.e.f. 9-2-2018).`
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_195_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=49121&sectionno=195&orderno=199&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_195_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_196:
  sectionId (49122)
  sectionNo (196)
  orderNo 200
  title `Appointment of managing director, whole-time director or manager.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_196_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_196_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=49122&sectionno=196&orderno=200&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_196_content:
  string
  line `(1) No company`
  line `shall appoint or employ at the same time a managing director and a manager.`
  line
  line `(2) No company shall appoint or re-appoint any person as its managing director, whole-time director`
  line `or manager for a term exceeding five years at a time:`
  line
  line `Provided that no re-appointment shall be made earlier than one year before the expiry of his term.`
  line
  line `(3) No company shall appoint or continue the employment of any person as managing director,`
  line `whole-time director or manager who --`
  line
  line `(a) is below the age of twenty-one years or has attained the age of seventy years:`
  line
  line `Provided that appointment of a person who has attained the age of seventy years may be made by`
  line `passing a special resolution in which case the explanatory statement annexed to the notice for such`
  line `motion shall indicate the justification for appointing such person;`
  line
  line `^1Provided further that where no such special resolution is passed but votes cast in favour of the`
  line `motion exceed the votes, if any, cast against the motion and the Central Government is satisfied, on`
  line `an application made by the Board, that such appointment is most beneficial to the company, the`
  line `appointment of the person who has attained the age of seventy years may be made.]";`
  line
  line `(b) is an undischarged insolvent or has at any time been adjudged as an insolvent;`
  line
  line `(c) has at any time suspended payment to his creditors or makes, or has at any time made, a`
  line `composition with them; or`
  line
  line `(d) has at any time been convicted by a court of an offence and sentenced for a period of more`
  line `than six months.`
  line
  line `(4) Subject to the provisions of section 197 and Schedule V, a managing director, whole-time director`
  line `or manager shall be appointed and the terms and conditions of such appointment and remuneration`
  line `payable be approved by the Board of Directors at a meeting which shall be subject to approval by a`
  line `resolution at the next general meeting of the company and by the Central Government in case such`
  line `appointment is at variance to the conditions ^2[specified in Part I of that Schedule]:`
  line
  line `Provided that a notice convening Board or general meeting for considering such appointment shall`
  line `include the terms and conditions of such appointment, remuneration payable and such other matters`
  line `including interest, of a director or directors in such appointments, if any:`
  line
  line `Provided further that a return in the prescribed form shall be filed within sixty days of such`
  line `appointment with the Registrar.`
  line
  line `(5) Subject to the provisions of this Act, where an appointment of a managing director, whole-time`
  line `director or manager is not approved by the company at a general meeting, any act done by him before`
  line `such approval shall not be deemed to be invalid.`
obj_root_law_sections_196_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. The proviso ins. by Act 1 of 2018, s. 66 (w.e.f. 12-9-2018).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by s. 66, ibid., for the words "specified in that Schedule" (w.e.f. 12-9-2018).`
obj_root_law_sections_197:
  sectionId (49123)
  sectionNo (197)
  orderNo 201
  title `Overall maximum managerial remuneration and managerial remuneration in case of absence or inadequacy of profits.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_197_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_197_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=49123&sectionno=197&orderno=201&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_197_content:
  string
  line `(1) The total managerial remuneration payable by a public`
  line `company, to its directors, including managing director and whole-time director, and its manager in respect`
  line `of any financial year shall not exceed eleven per cent. of the net profits of that company for that financial`
  line `year computed in the manner laid down in section 198 except that the remuneration of the directors shall`
  line `not be deducted from the gross profits:`
  line
  line `Provided that the company in general meeting may, ^1*** authorise the payment of remuneration`
  line `exceeding eleven per cent. of the net profits of the company, subject to the provisions of Schedule V:`
  line
  line `Provided further that, except with the approval of the company in general meeting, ^2[by a special`
  line resolution,]--
  line
  line `(i) the remuneration payable to any one managing director; or whole-time director or manager`
  line `shall not exceed five per cent. of the net profits of the company and if there is more than one such`
  line `director remuneration shall not exceed ten per cent. of the net profits to all such directors and`
  line `manager taken together;`
  line
  line `(ii) the remuneration payable to directors who are neither managing directors nor whole-time`
  line `directors shall not exceed,--`
  line
  line `(A) one per cent. of the net profits of the company, if there is a managing or whole-time`
  line `director or manager;`
  line
  line `(B) three per cent. of the net profits in any other case.`
  line
  line `^3[Provided also that, where the company has defaulted in payment of dues to any bank or public`
  line `financial institution or non-convertible debenture holders or any other secured creditor, the prior approval`
  line `of the bank or public financial institution concerned or the non-convertible debenture holders or other`
  line `secured creditor, as the case may be, shall be obtained by the company before obtaining the approval in`
  line `the general meeting.]`
  line
  line `(2) The percentages aforesaid shall be exclusive of any fees payable to directors under sub-section`
  line `(5).`
  line
  line `(3) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-sections (1) and (2), but subject to the provisions of`
  line `Schedule V, if, in any financial year, a company has no profits or its profits are inadequate, the company`
  line `shall not pay to its directors, including any managing or whole-time director or manager, ^4[or any other`
  line `non-executive director, including an independent director] by way of`
  line `remuneration any sum exclusive of any fees payable to directors under sub-section (5) hereunder except`
  line `in accordance with the provisions of Schedule V ^5***.`
  line
  line `(4) The remuneration payable to the directors of a company, including any managing or whole-time`
  line `director or manager, shall be determined, in accordance with and subject to the provisions of this section,`
  line `either by the articles of the company, or by a resolution or, if the articles so require, by a special`
  line `resolution, passed by the company in general meeting and the remuneration payable to a director`
  line `determined aforesaid shall be inclusive of the remuneration payable to him for the services rendered by`
  line `him in any other capacity:`
  line
  line `Provided that any remuneration for services rendered by any such director in other capacity shall not`
  line `be so included if--`
  line
  line `(a) the services rendered are of a professional nature; and`
  line
  line `(b) in the opinion of the Nomination and Remuneration Committee, if the company is covered`
  line `under sub-section (1) of section 178, or the Board of Directors in other cases, the director possesses`
  line `the requisite qualification for the practice of the profession.`
  line
  line `(5) A director may receive remuneration by way of fee for attending meetings of the Board or`
  line `Committee thereof or for any other purpose whatsoever as may be decided by the Board:`
  line
  line `Provided that the amount of such fees shall not exceed the amount as may be prescribed:`
  line
  line `Provided further that different fees for different classes of companies and fees in respect of`
  line `independent director may be such as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(6) A director or manager may be paid remuneration either by way of a monthly payment or at a`
  line `specified percentage of the net profits of the company or partly by one way and partly by the other.`
  line
  line `^6* * * * * *`
  line
  line `(8) The net profits for the purposes of this section shall be computed in the manner referred to in`
  line `section 198.`
  line
  line `^7[(9) If any director draws or receives, directly or indirectly, by way of remuneration any such sums`
  line `in excess of the limit prescribed by this section or without approval required under this section, he shall`
  line `refund such sums to the company, within two years or such lesser period as may be allowed by the`
  line `company, and until such sum is refunded, hold it in trust for the company.]`
  line
  line `(10) The company shall not waive the recovery of any sum refundable to it under sub-section (9)`
  line `unless ^8[approved by the company by special resolution within two years from the date the sum becomes`
  line refundable.]
  line
  line `^9[Provided that where the company has defaulted in payment of dues to any bank or public financial`
  line `institution or non-convertible debenture holders or any other secured creditor, the prior approval of the`
  line `bank or public financial institution concerned or the non-convertible debenture holders or other secured`
  line `creditor, as the case may be, shall be obtained by the company before obtaining approval of such waiver.]`
  line
  line `(11) In cases where Schedule V is applicable on grounds of no profits or inadequate profits, any`
  line `provision relating to the remuneration of any director which purports to increase or has the effect of`
  line `increasing the amount thereof, whether the provision be contained in the companys memorandum or`
  line `articles, or in an agreement entered into by it, or in any resolution passed by the company in general`
  line `meeting or its Board, shall not have any effect unless such increase is in accordance with the conditions`
  line `specified in that Schedule ^10***.`
  line
  line `(12) Every listed company shall disclose in the Boards report, the ratio of the remuneration of each`
  line `director to the median employees remuneration and such other details as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(13) Where any insurance is taken by a company on behalf of its managing director, whole-time`
  line `director, manager, Chief Executive Officer, Chief Financial Officer or Company Secretary for`
  line `indemnifying any of them against any liability in respect of any negligence, default, misfeasance, breach`
  line `of duty or breach of trust for which they may be guilty in relation to the company, the premium paid on`
  line `such insurance shall not be treated as part of the remuneration payable to any such personnel:`
  line
  line `Provided that if such person is proved to be guilty, the premium paid on such insurance shall be`
  line `treated as part of the remuneration.`
  line
  line `(14) Subject to the provisions of this section, any director who is in receipt of any commission from`
  line `the company and who is a managing or whole-time director of the company shall not be disqualified from`
  line `receiving any remuneration or commission from any holding company or subsidiary company of such`
  line `company subject to its disclosure by the company in the Board's report.`
  line
  line `^11[(15) If any person makes any default in complying with the provisions of this section, he shall be`
  line `liable to a penalty of one lakh rupees and where any default has been made by a company, the company`
  line `shall be liable to a penalty of five lakh rupees.]`
  line
  line `^12[(16) The auditor of the company shall, in his report under section 143, make a statement as to`
  line `whether the remuneration paid by the company to its directors is in accordance with the provisions of this`
  line `section, whether remuneration paid to any director is in excess of the limit laid down under this section`
  line `and give such other details as may be prescribed..`
  line
  line `(17) On and from the commencement of the Companies (Amendment) Act, 2017, any application`
  line `made to the Central Government under the provisions of this section [as it stood before such`
  line `commencement], which is pending with that Government shall abate, and the company shall, within one`
  line `year of such commencement, obtain the approval in accordance with the provisions of this section, as so`
  line amended.]
obj_root_law_sections_197_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. The words "with the approval of the Central Government", omitted by Act 1 of 2018, s. 67 (w.e.f. 12-9-2018).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by s. 67, ibid., (w.e.f. 12-9-2018).`
  line
  line `3. The proviso ins. by s. 67, ibid. (w.e.f. 12-9-2018).`
  line
  line `4. Ins. by Act 29 of 2020, s. 40 (w.e.f. 18-3-2021).`
  line
  line `5. The words "and if it is not able to comply with such provisions, with the previous approval of the Central Government"`
  line `omitted by s. 67, ibid., (w.e.f.12-9-2018).`
  line
  line `6. Sub-section (7) omitted by Act 22 of 2019, s. 29 (w.e.f. 2-11-2018).`
  line
  line `7. Subs. by Act 1 of 2018, s. 67 (w.e.f. 12-9-2018).`
  line
  line `8. Subs. by s. 67, ibid., for "permitted by the Central Government" (w.e.f. 12-9-2018).`
  line
  line `9. The proviso ins. by s. 67, ibid., (w.e.f. 12-9-2018).`
  line
  line `10. The words "and if such conditions are not being complied, the approval of the Central Government had been obtained" by`
  line `s. 67, ibid., (w.e.f. 12-9-2018).`
  line
  line `11. Subs. by Act 22 of 2019, s. 29, for sub-section (15) (w.e.f. 2-11-2018).`
  line
  line `12. Ins. by Act 1 of 2018, s. 67 (w.e.f. 12-9-2018).`
obj_root_law_sections_198:
  sectionId (49124)
  sectionNo (198)
  orderNo 202
  title `Calculation of profits`
  content obj_root_law_sections_198_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_198_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=49124&sectionno=198&orderno=202&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_198_content:
  string
  line `(1) In computing the net profits of a company in any financial year for`
  line `the purpose of section 197,--`
  line
  line `(a) credit shall be given for the sums specified in sub-section (2), and credit shall not be given for`
  line `those specified in sub-section (3); and`
  line
  line `(b) the sums specified in sub-section (4) shall be deducted, and those specified in sub-section (5)`
  line `shall not be deducted.`
  line
  line `(2) In making the computation aforesaid, credit shall be given for the bounties and subsidies received`
  line `from any Government, or any public authority constituted or authorised in this behalf, by any`
  line `Government, unless and except in so far as the Central Government otherwise directs.`
  line
  line `(3) In making the computation aforesaid, credit shall not be given for the following sums, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) profits, by way of premium on shares or debentures of the company, which are issued or sold`
  line `by the company ^1[unless the company is an investment company as referred to in clause (a) of the`
  line `Explanation to section 186];`
  line
  line `(b) profits on sales by the company of forfeited shares;`
  line
  line `(c) profits of a capital nature including profits from the sale of the undertaking or any of the`
  line `undertakings of the company or of any part thereof;`
  line
  line `(d) profits from the sale of any immovable property or fixed assets of a capital nature comprised`
  line `in the undertaking or any of the undertakings of the company, unless the business of the company`
  line `consists, whether wholly or partly, of buying and selling any such property or assets:`
  line
  line `Provided that where the amount for which any fixed asset is sold exceeds the written-down value`
  line `thereof, credit shall be given for so much of the excess as is not higher than the difference between`
  line `the original cost of that fixed asset and its written-down value;`
  line
  line `(e) any change in carrying amount of an asset or of a liability recognised in equity reserves`
  line `including surplus in profit and loss account on measurement of the asset or the liability at fair value.`
  line
  line `^2[(f) any amount representing unrealised gains, notional gains or revaluation of assets.]`
  line
  line `(4) In making the computation aforesaid, the following sums shall be deducted, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) all the usual working charges;`
  line
  line `(b) directors remuneration;`
  line
  line `(c) bonus or commission paid or payable to any member of the company's staff, or to any`
  line `engineer, technician or person employed or engaged by the company, whether on a whole-time or on`
  line `a part-time basis;`
  line
  line `(d) any tax notified by the Central Government as being in the nature of a tax on excess or`
  line `abnormal profits;`
  line
  line `(e) any tax on business profits imposed for special reasons or in special circumstances and`
  line `notified by the Central Government in this behalf;`
  line
  line `(f) interest on debentures issued by the company;`
  line
  line `(g) interest on mortgages executed by the company and on loans and advances secured by a`
  line `charge on its fixed or floating assets;`
  line
  line `(h) interest on unsecured loans and advances;`
  line
  line `(i) expenses on repairs, whether to immovable or to movable property, provided the repairs are`
  line `not of a capital nature;`
  line
  line `(j) outgoings inclusive of contributions made under section 181;`
  line
  line `(k) depreciation to the extent specified in section 123;`
  line
  line `(l) the excess of expenditure over income, which had arisen in computing the net profits in`
  line `accordance with this section in any year ^1***, in so far as such excess has not been deducted in any`
  line `subsequent year preceding the year in respect of which the net profits have to be ascertained;`
  line
  line `(m) any compensation or damages to be paid in virtue of any legal liability including a liability`
  line `arising from a breach of contract;`
  line
  line `(n) any sum paid by way of insurance against the risk of meeting any liability such as is referred`
  line `to in clause (m);`
  line
  line `(o) debts considered bad and written off or adjusted during the year of account.`
  line
  line `(5) In making the computation aforesaid, the following sums shall not be deducted, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) income-tax and super-tax payable by the company under the Income-tax Act, 1961 (43 of`
  line `1961), or any other tax on the income of the company not falling under clauses (d) and (e) of subsection`
  line `(4);`
  line
  line `(b) any compensation, damages or payments made voluntarily, that is to say, otherwise than in`
  line `virtue of a liability such as is referred to in clause (m) of sub-section (4);`
  line
  line `(c) loss of a capital nature including loss on sale of the undertaking or any of the undertakings of`
  line `the company or of any part thereof not including any excess of the written-down value of any asset`
  line `which is sold, discarded, demolished or destroyed over its sale proceeds or its scrap value;`
  line
  line `(d) any change in carrying amount of an asset or of a liability recognised in equity reserves`
  line `including surplus in profit and loss account on measurement of the asset or the liability at fair value.`
obj_root_law_sections_198_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by s. 68, iibid., (w.e.f. 12-9-2018).`
  line
  line `2. Clause (f) ins. by s. 68, ibid., (w.e.f. 12-9-2018).`
  line
  line `3. The words "which begins at or after the commencement of this Act" omitted by Act 1 of 2018, s. 68 (w.e.f. 12-9-2018)`
obj_root_law_sections_199:
  sectionId (49125)
  sectionNo (199)
  orderNo 203
  title `Recovery of remuneration in certain cases`
  content obj_root_law_sections_199_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_199_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=49125&sectionno=199&orderno=203&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_199_content:
  string
  line `Without prejudice to any liability incurred under`
  line `the provisions of this Act or any other law for the time being in force, where a company is required to restate`
  line `its financial statements due to fraud or non-compliance with any requirement under this Act and the`
  line `rules made thereunder, the company shall recover from any past or present managing director or wholetime`
  line `director or manager or Chief Executive Officer (by whatever name called) who, during the period for`
  line `which the financial statements are required to be re-stated, received the remuneration (including stock`
  line `option) in excess of what would have been payable to him as per restatement of financial statements.`
obj_root_law_sections_199_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_200:
  sectionId (49126)
  sectionNo (200)
  orderNo 204
  title `Central Government or company to fix limit with regard to remuneration`
  content obj_root_law_sections_200_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_200_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=49126&sectionno=200&orderno=204&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_200_content:
  string
  line `Notwithstanding anything contained in this Chapter, ^2*** a company may, while according its approval`
  line `under section 196, to any appointment or to any remuneration under section 197 in respect of cases where`
  line `the company has inadequate or no profits, fix the remuneration within the limits specified in this Act, at`
  line `such amount or percentage of profits of the company, as it may deem fit and while fixing the`
  line `remuneration, ^1*** the company shall have regard to--`
  line
  line `(a) the financial position of the company;`
  line
  line `(b) the remuneration or commission drawn by the individual concerned in any other capacity;`
  line
  line `(c) the remuneration or commission drawn by him from any other company;`
  line
  line `(d) professional qualifications and experience of the individual concerned;`
  line
  line `(e) such other matters as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_200_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. The words "which begins at or after the commencement of this Act" omitted by Act 1 of 2018, s. 68 (w.e.f. 12-9-2018).`
  line
  line `2. The words "the Central Government or" omitted s. 69, ibid., (w.e.f. 12-9-2018).`
obj_root_law_sections_201:
  sectionId (49127)
  sectionNo (201)
  orderNo 205
  title `Forms of, and procedure in relation to, certain applications.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_201_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_201_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=49127&sectionno=201&orderno=205&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_201_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every application made to`
  line `the Central Government under ^1[section 196] shall be in such form as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(2) (a) Before any application is made by a company to the Central Government under ^2[section 196], there shall be issued by or on behalf of the company a general notice to the members thereof, indicating`
  line `the nature of the application proposed to be made.`
  line
  line `(b) Such notice shall be published at least once in a newspaper in the principal language of the district`
  line `in which the registered office of the company is situate and circulating in that district, and at least once in`
  line `English in an English newspaper circulating in that district.`
  line
  line `(c) The copies of the notices, together with a certificate by the company as to the due publication`
  line `thereof, shall be attached to the application.`
obj_root_law_sections_201_footnotes:
  string
  line `1The words "this Chapter" omitted by s. 70, ibid., (w.e.f. 12-9-2018).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by s. 70, ibid., for "any of the sections aforesaid" (w.e.f. 12-9-2018)`
obj_root_law_sections_202:
  sectionId (49128)
  sectionNo (202)
  orderNo 206
  title `Compensation for loss of office of managing or whole-time director or manager.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_202_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_202_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=49128&sectionno=202&orderno=206&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_202_content:
  string
  line `(1) A`
  line `company may make payment to a managing or whole-time director or manager, but not to any other`
  line `director, by way of compensation for loss of office, or as consideration for retirement from office or in`
  line `connection with such loss or retirement.`
  line
  line `(2) No payment shall be made under sub-section (1) in the following cases, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) where the director resigns from his office as a result of the reconstruction of the company,or`
  line `of its amalgamation with any other body corporate or bodies corporate, and is appointed as the`
  line `managing or whole-time director, manager or other officer of the reconstructed company or of the`
  line `body corporate resulting from the amalgamation;`
  line
  line `(b) where the director resigns from his office otherwise than on the reconstruction of the company`
  line `or its amalgamation as aforesaid;`
  line
  line `(c) where the office of the director is vacated under sub-section (1) of section 167;`
  line
  line `(d) where the company is being wound up, whether by an order of the Tribunal or voluntarily,`
  line `provided the winding up was due to the negligence or default of the director;`
  line
  line `(e) where the director has been guilty of fraud or breach of trust in relation to, or of gross`
  line `negligence in or gross mismanagement of, the conduct of the affairs of the company or any subsidiary`
  line `company or holding company thereof; and`
  line
  line `(f) where the director has instigated, or has taken part directly or indirectly in bringing about, the`
  line `termination of his office.`
  line
  line `(3) Any payment made to a managing or whole-time director or manager in pursuance of sub-section (1) shall not exceed the remuneration which he would have earned if he had been in office for the`
  line `remainder of his term or for three years, whichever is shorter, calculated on the basis of the average`
  line `remuneration actually earned by him during a period of three years immediately preceding the date on`
  line `which he ceased to hold office, or where he held the office for a lesser period than three years, during`
  line `such period:`
  line
  line `Provided that no such payment shall be made to the director in the event of the commencement of the`
  line `winding up of the company, whether before or at any time within twelve months after, the date on which`
  line `he ceased to hold office, if the assets of the company on the winding up, after deducting the expenses`
  line `thereof, are not sufficient to repay to the shareholders the share capital, including the premiums, if any,`
  line `contributed by them.`
  line
  line `(4) Nothing in this section shall be deemed to prohibit the payment to a managing or whole-time`
  line `director, or manager, of any remuneration for services rendered by him to the company in any other`
  line capacity.
obj_root_law_sections_202_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_203:
  sectionId (49129)
  sectionNo (203)
  orderNo 207
  title `Appointment of key managerial personnel.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_203_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 22 of 2019, s. 30, for sub-section (5) (w.e.f. 2-11-2018).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=49129&sectionno=203&orderno=207&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_203_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every company belonging to such class or`
  line `classes of companies as may be prescribed shall have the following whole-time key managerial`
  line personnel,--
  line
  line `(i) managing director, or Chief Executive Officer or manager and in their absence, a whole-time`
  line director;
  line
  line `(ii) company secretary; and`
  line
  line `(iii) Chief Financial Officer :`
  line
  line `Provided that an individual shall not be appointed or reappointed as the chairperson of the`
  line `company, in pursuance of the articles of the company, as well as the managing director or Chief`
  line `Executive Officer of the company at the same time after the date of commencement of this Act`
  line unless,--
  line
  line `(a) the articles of such a company provide otherwise; or`
  line
  line `(b) the company does not carry multiple businesses:`
  line
  line `Provided further that nothing contained in the first proviso shall apply to such class of`
  line `companies engaged in multiple businesses and which has appointed one or more Chief Executive`
  line `Officers for each such business as may be notified by the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(2) Every whole-time key managerial personnel of a company shall be appointed by means of a`
  line `resolution of the Board containing the terms and conditions of the appointment including the`
  line remuneration.
  line
  line `(3) A whole-time key managerial personnel shall not hold office in more than one company except in`
  line `its subsidiary company at the same time:`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing contained in this sub-section shall disentitle a key managerial personnel from`
  line `being a director of any company with the permission of the Board:`
  line
  line `Provided further that whole-time key managerial personnel holding office in more than one company`
  line `at the same time on the date of commencement of this Act, shall, within a period of six months from such`
  line `commencement, choose one company, in which he wishes to continue to hold the office of key`
  line `managerial personnel:`
  line
  line `Provided also that a company may appoint or employ a person as its managing director, if he is the`
  line `managing director or manager of one, and of not more than one, other company and such appointment or`
  line `employment is made or approved by a resolution passed at a meeting of the Board with the consent of all`
  line `the directors present at the meeting and of which meeting, and of the resolution to be moved thereat,`
  line `specific notice has been given to all the directors then in India.`
  line
  line `(4) If the office of any whole-time key managerial personnel is vacated, the resulting vacancy shall be`
  line `filled-up by the Board at a meeting of the Board within a period of six months from the date of such`
  line vacancy.
  line
  line `^1[(5) If any company makes any default in complying with the provisions of this section, such`
  line `company shall be liable to a penalty of five lakh rupees and every director and key managerial personnel`
  line `of the company who is in default shall be liable to a penalty of fifty thousand rupees and where the default`
  line `is a continuing one, with a further penalty of one thousand rupees for each day after the first during which`
  line `such default continues but not exceeding five lakh rupees.]`
obj_root_law_sections_204:
  sectionId (49130)
  sectionNo (204)
  orderNo 208
  title `Secretarial audit for bigger companies`
  content obj_root_law_sections_204_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 29 of 2020, s. 41, for certain words (w.e.f. 21-12-2020).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=49130&sectionno=204&orderno=208&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_204_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every listed company and a company belonging`
  line `to other class of companies as may be prescribed shall annex with its Board's report made in terms of`
  line `sub-section (3) of section 134, a secretarial audit report, given by a company secretary in practice, in such`
  line `form as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(2) It shall be the duty of the company to give all assistance and facilities to the company secretary in`
  line `practice, for auditing the secretarial and related records of the company.`
  line
  line `(3) The Board of Directors, in their report made in terms of sub-section (3) of section 134, shall`
  line `explain in full any qualification or observation or other remarks made by the company secretary in`
  line `practice in his report under sub-section (1).`
  line
  line `(4) If a company or any officer of the company or the company secretary in practice, contravenes the`
  line `provisions of this section, the company, every officer of the company or the company secretary in`
  line `practice, who is in default, shall be ^1[liable to a penalty of two lakh rupees].`
obj_root_law_sections_205:
  sectionId (49131)
  sectionNo (205)
  orderNo 209
  title `Functions of company secretary.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_205_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_205_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=49131&sectionno=205&orderno=209&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_205_content:
  string
  line `(1) The functions of the company secretary shall`
  line include,--
  line
  line `(a) to report to the Board about compliance with the provisions of this Act, the rules made`
  line `thereunder and other laws applicable to the company;`
  line
  line `(b) to ensure that the company complies with the applicable secretarial standards;`
  line
  line `(c) to discharge such other duties as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purpose of this section, the expression secretarial standards means`
  line `secretarial standards issued by the Institute of Company Secretaries of India constituted under section 3 of`
  line `the Company Secretaries Act, 1980 (56 of 1980) and approved by the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(2) The provisions contained in section 204 and section 205 shall not affect the duties and functions`
  line `of the Board of Directors, chairperson of the company, managing director or whole-time director under`
  line `this Act, or any other law for the time being in force.`
obj_root_law_sections_205_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_206:
  sectionId (49132)
  sectionNo (206)
  orderNo 210
  title `Power to call for information, inspect books and conduct inquiries`
  content obj_root_law_sections_206_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_206_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=49132&sectionno=206&orderno=210&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_206_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where on a`
  line `scrutiny of any document filed by a company or on any information received by him, the Registrar is of`
  line `the opinion that any further information or explanation or any further documents relating to the company`
  line `is necessary, he may by a written notice require the company--`
  line
  line `(a) to furnish in writing such information or explanation; or`
  line
  line `(b) to produce such documents,`
  line
  line `within such reasonable time, as may be specified in the notice.`
  line
  line `(2) On the receipt of a notice under sub-section (1), it shall be the duty of the company and of its`
  line `officers concerned to furnish such information or explanation to the best of their knowledge and power`
  line `and to produce the documents to the Registrar within the time specified or extended by the Registrar:`
  line
  line `Provided that where such information or explanation relates to any past period, the officers who had`
  line `been in the employment of the company for such period, if so called upon by the Registrar through a`
  line `notice served on them in writing, shall also furnish such information or explanation to the best of their`
  line knowledge.
  line
  line `(3) If no information or explanation is furnished to the Registrar within the time specified under subsection`
  line `(1) or if the Registrar on an examination of the documents furnished is of the opinion that the`
  line `information or explanation furnished is inadequate or if the Registrar is satisfied on a scrutiny of the`
  line `documents furnished that an unsatisfactory state of affairs exists in the company and does not disclose a`
  line `full and fair statement of the information required, he may, by another written notice, call on the company`
  line `to produce for his inspection such further books of account, books, papers and explanations as he may`
  line `require at such place and at such time as he may specify in the notice:`
  line
  line `Provided that before any notice is served under this sub-section, the Registrar shall record his reasons`
  line `in writing for issuing such notice.`
  line
  line `(4) If the Registrar is satisfied on the basis of information available with or furnished to him or on a`
  line `representation made to him by any person that the business of a company is being carried on for a`
  line `fraudulent or unlawful purpose or not in compliance with the provisions of this Act or if the grievances of`
  line `investors are not being addressed, the Registrar may, after informing the company of the allegations made`
  line `against it by a written order, call on the company to furnish in writing any information or explanation on`
  line `matters specified in the order within such time as he may specify therein and carry out such inquiry as he`
  line `deems fit after providing the company a reasonable opportunity of being heard:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Central Government may, if it is satisfied that the circumstances so warrant, direct`
  line `the Registrar or an inspector appointed by it for the purpose to carry out the inquiry under this subsection:`
  line
  line `Provided further that where business of a company has been or is being carried on for a fraudulent or`
  line `unlawful purpose, every officer of the company who is in default shall be punishable for fraud in the`
  line `manner as provided in section 447.`
  line
  line `(5) Without prejudice to the foregoing provisions of this section, the Central Government may, if it is`
  line `satisfied that the circumstances so warrant, direct inspection of books and papers of a company by an`
  line `inspector appointed by it for the purpose.`
  line
  line `(6) The Central Government may, having regard to the circumstances by general or special order,`
  line `authorise any statutory authority to carry out the inspection of books of account of a company or class of`
  line companies.
  line
  line `(7) If a company fails to furnish any information or explanation or produce any document required`
  line `under this section, the company and every officer of the company, who is in default shall be punishable`
  line `with a fine which may extend to one lakh rupees and in the case of a continuing failure, with an additional`
  line `fine which may extend to five hundred rupees for every day after the first during which the failure`
  line continues.
obj_root_law_sections_206_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_207:
  sectionId (49133)
  sectionNo (207)
  orderNo 211
  title `Conduct of inspection and inquiry.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_207_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_207_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=49133&sectionno=207&orderno=211&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_207_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where a Registrar or inspector calls for the books of`
  line `account and other books and papers under section 206, it shall be the duty of every director, officer or`
  line `other employee of the company to produce all such documents to the Registrar or inspector and furnish`
  line `him with such statements, information or explanations in such form as the Registrar or inspector may`
  line `require and shall render all assistance to the Registrar or inspector in connection with such inspection.`
  line
  line `(2) The Registrar or inspector, making an inspection or inquiry under section 206 may, during the`
  line `course of such inspection or inquiry, as the case may be,--`
  line
  line `(a) make or cause to be made copies of books of account and other books and papers; or`
  line
  line `(b) place or cause to be placed any marks of identification in such books in token of the`
  line `inspection having been made.`
  line
  line `(3) Notwithstanding anything contained in any other law for the time being in force or in any contract`
  line `to the contrary, the Registrar or inspector making an inspection or inquiry shall have all the powers as are`
  line `vested in a civil court under the Code of Civil Procedure, 1908 (5 of 1908), while trying a suit in respect`
  line `of the following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the discovery and production of books of account and other documents, at such place and time`
  line `as may be specified by such Registrar or inspector making the inspection or inquiry;`
  line
  line `(b) summoning and enforcing the attendance of persons and examining them on oath; and`
  line
  line `(c) inspection of any books, registers and other documents of the company at any place.`
  line
  line `(4) (i) If any director or officer of the company disobeys the direction issued by the Registrar or the`
  line `inspector under this section, the director or the officer shall be punishable with imprisonment which may`
  line `extend to one year and with fine which shall not be less than twenty-five thousand rupees but which may`
  line `extend to one lakh rupees.`
  line
  line `(ii) If a director or an officer of the company has been convicted of an offence under this section, the`
  line `director or the officer shall, on and from the date on which he is so convicted, be deemed to have vacated`
  line `his office as such and on such vacation of office, shall be disqualified from holding an office in any`
  line company.
obj_root_law_sections_207_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_208:
  sectionId (49134)
  sectionNo (208)
  orderNo 212
  title `Report on inspection made.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_208_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_208_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=49134&sectionno=208&orderno=212&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_208_content:
  string
  line `The Registrar or inspector shall, after the inspection of the`
  line `books of account or an inquiry under section 206 and other books and papers of the company under`
  line `section 207, submit a report in writing to the Central Government along with such documents, if any, and`
  line `such report may, if necessary, include a recommendation that further investigation into the affairs of the`
  line `company is necessary giving his reasons in support.`
obj_root_law_sections_208_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_209:
  sectionId (49135)
  sectionNo (209)
  orderNo 213
  title `Search and seizure.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_209_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_209_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=49135&sectionno=209&orderno=213&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_209_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where, upon information in his possession or otherwise, the`
  line `Registrar or inspector has reasonable ground to believe that the books and papers of a company, or`
  line `relating to the key managerial personnel or any director or auditor or company secretary in practice if the`
  line `company has not appointed a company secretary, are likely to be destroyed, mutilated, altered, falsified or`
  line `secreted, he may, after obtaining an order from the Special Court for the seizure of such books and`
  line papers,--
  line
  line `(a) enter, with such assistance as may be required, and search, the place or places where such`
  line `books or papers are kept; and`
  line
  line `(b) seize such books and papers as he considers necessary after allowing the company to take`
  line `copies of, or extracts from, such books or papers at its cost.`
  line
  line `(2) The Registrar or inspector shall return the books and papers seized under subsection (1), as soon`
  line `as may be, and in any case not later than one hundred and eightieth day after such seizure, to the company`
  line `from whose custody or power such books or papers were seized:`
  line
  line `Provided that the books and papers may be called for by the Registrar or inspector for a further period`
  line `of one hundred and eighty days by an order in writing if they are needed again:`
  line
  line `Provided further that the Registrar or inspector may, before returning such books and papers as`
  line `aforesaid, take copies of, or extracts from them or place identification marks on them or any part thereof`
  line `or deal with the same in such other manner as he considers necessary.`
  line
  line `(3) The provisions of the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974) relating to searches or`
  line `seizures shall apply, mutatis mutandis, to every search and seizure made under this section.`
obj_root_law_sections_209_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_210:
  sectionId (49136)
  sectionNo (210)
  orderNo 214
  title `Investigation into affairs of company.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_210_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_210_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=49136&sectionno=210&orderno=214&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_210_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where the Central Government is of the opinion,`
  line `that it is necessary to investigate into the affairs of a company,--`
  line
  line `(a) on the receipt of a report of the Registrar or inspector under section 208;`
  line
  line `(b) on intimation of a special resolution passed by a company that the affairs of the company`
  line `ought to be investigated; or`
  line
  line `(c) in public interest,`
  line
  line `it may order an investigation into the affairs of the company.`
  line
  line `(2) Where an order is passed by a court or the Tribunal in any proceedings before it that the affairs of`
  line `a company ought to be investigated, the Central Government shall order an investigation into the affairs`
  line `of that company.`
  line
  line `(3) For the purposes of this section, the Central Government may appoint one or more persons as`
  line `inspectors to investigate into the affairs of the company and to report thereon in such manner as the`
  line `Central Government may direct.`
obj_root_law_sections_210_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_211:
  sectionId (49137)
  sectionNo (211)
  orderNo 215
  title `Establishment of Serious Fraud Investigation Office`
  content obj_root_law_sections_211_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_211_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=49137&sectionno=211&orderno=215&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_211_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government shall, by notification, establish an office to be called the Serious Fraud Investigation Office to investigate frauds`
  line `relating to a company:`
  line
  line `Provided that until the Serious Fraud Investigation Office is established under subsection (1), the`
  line `Serious Fraud Investigation Office set-up by the Central Government in terms of the Government of India`
  line `Resolution No. 45011/16/2003-Adm-I, dated the 2nd July, 2003 shall be deemed to be the Serious Fraud`
  line `Investigation Office for the purpose of this section.`
  line
  line `(2) The Serious Fraud Investigation Office shall be headed by a Director and consist of such number`
  line `of experts from the following fields to be appointed by the Central Government from amongst persons of`
  line `ability, integrity and experience in,--`
  line
  line `(i) banking;`
  line
  line `(ii) corporate affairs;`
  line
  line `(iii) taxation;`
  line
  line `(iv) forensic audit;`
  line
  line `(v) capital market;`
  line
  line `(vi) information technology;`
  line
  line `(vii) law; or`
  line
  line `(viii) such other fields as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(3) The Central Government shall, by notification, appoint a Director in the Serious Fraud`
  line `Investigation Office, who shall be an officer not below the rank of a Joint Secretary to the Government of`
  line `India having knowledge and experience in dealing with matters relating to corporate affairs.`
  line
  line `(4) The Central Government may appoint such experts and other officers and employees in the`
  line `Serious Fraud Investigation Office as it considers necessary for the efficient discharge of its functions`
  line `under this Act.`
  line
  line `(5) The terms and conditions of service of Director, experts, and other officers and employees of the`
  line `Serious Fraud Investigation Office shall be such as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_211_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_212:
  sectionId (49138)
  sectionNo (212)
  orderNo 216
  title `Investigation into affairs of company by Serious Fraud Investigation Office.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_212_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_212_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=49138&sectionno=212&orderno=216&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_212_content:
  string
  line `(1) Without`
  line `prejudice to the provisions of section 210, where the Central Government is of the opinion, that it is`
  line `necessary to investigate into the affairs of a company by the Serious Fraud Investigation Office--`
  line
  line `(a) on receipt of a report of the Registrar or inspector under section 208;`
  line
  line `(b) on intimation of a special resolution passed by a company that its affairs are required to be`
  line investigated;
  line
  line `(c) in the public interest; or`
  line
  line `(d) on request from any Department of the Central Government or a State Government,`
  line
  line `the Central Government may, by order, assign the investigation into the affairs of the said company to the`
  line `Serious Fraud Investigation Office and its Director, may designate such number of inspectors, as he may`
  line `consider necessary for the purpose of such investigation.`
  line
  line `(2) Where any case has been assigned by the Central Government to the Serious Fraud Investigation`
  line `Office for investigation under this Act, no other investigating agency of Central Government or any State`
  line `Government shall proceed with investigation in such case in respect of any offence under this Act and in`
  line `case any such investigation has already been initiated, it shall not be proceeded further with and the`
  line `concerned agency shall transfer the relevant documents and records in respect of such offences under this`
  line `Act to Serious Fraud Investigation Office.`
  line
  line `(3) Where the investigation into the affairs of a company has been assigned by the Central`
  line `Government to Serious Fraud Investigation Office, it shall conduct the investigation in the manner and`
  line `follow the procedure provided in this Chapter; and submit its report to the Central Government within`
  line `such period as may be specified in the order.`
  line
  line `(4) The Director, Serious Fraud Investigation Office shall cause the affairs of the company to be`
  line `investigated by an Investigating Officer who shall have the power of the inspector under section 217.`
  line
  line `(5) The company and its officers and employees, who are or have been in employment of the`
  line `company shall be responsible to provide all information, explanation, documents and assistance to the`
  line `Investigating Officer as he may require for conduct of the investigation.`
  line
  line `(6) Notwithstanding anything contained in the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974), ^1[offence covered under section 447] of this Act shall be cognizable and no person accused of any offence`
  line `under those sections shall be released on bail or on his own bond unless--`
  line
  line `(i) the Public Prosecutor has been given an opportunity to oppose the application for such release;`
  line and
  line
  line `(ii) where the Public Prosecutor opposes the application, the court is satisfied that there are`
  line `reasonable grounds for believing that he is not guilty of such offence and that he is not likely to`
  line `commit any offence while on bail:`
  line
  line `Provided that a person, who, is under the age of sixteen years or is a woman or is sick or infirm, may`
  line `be released on bail, if the Special Court so directs:`
  line
  line `Provided further that the Special Court shall not take cognizance of any offence referred to this subsection`
  line `except upon a complaint in writing made by--`
  line
  line `(i) the Director, Serious Fraud Investigation Office; or`
  line
  line `(ii) any officer of the Central Government authorised, by a general or special order in writing in`
  line `this behalf by that Government.`
  line
  line `(7) The limitation on granting of bail specified in sub-section (6) is in addition to the limitations under`
  line `the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974) or any other law for the time being in force on granting`
  line `of bail.`
  line
  line `(8) ^2[If any officer not below the rank of Assistant Director] of Serious Fraud Investigation Office`
  line `authorised in this behalf by the Central Government by general or special order, has on the basis of`
  line `material in his possession reason to believe (the reason for such belief to be recorded in writing) that any`
  line `person has been guilty of any offence punishable under sections referred to in sub-section (6), he may`
  line `arrest such person and shall, as soon as may be, inform him of the grounds for such arrest.`
  line
  line `(9) ^3[The officer authorized under sub-section (8) shall, immediately after arrest of such person under`
  line `such sub-section], forward a copy of the order, along with the material in his possession, referred to in`
  line `that sub-section, to the Serious Fraud Investigation Office in a sealed envelope, in such manner as may be`
  line `prescribed and the Serious Fraud Investigation Office shall keep such order and material for such period`
  line `as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(10) Every person arrested under sub-section (8) shall within twenty-four hours, be taken to a`
  line `^4[Special Court or Judicial Magistrate] or a Metropolitan Magistrate, as the case may be, having`
  line `jurisdiction:`
  line
  line `Provided that the period of twenty-four hours shall exclude the time necessary for the journey from`
  line `the place of arrest to the ^5[Special Court or Magistrate's court].`
  line
  line `(11) The Central Government if so directs, the Serious Fraud Investigation Office shall submit an`
  line `interim report to the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(12) On completion of the investigation, the Serious Fraud Investigation Office shall submit the`
  line `investigation report to the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(13) Notwithstanding anything contained in this Act or in any other law for the time being in force, a`
  line `copy of the investigation report may be obtained by any person concerned by making an application in`
  line `this regard to the court.`
  line
  line `(14) On receipt of the investigation report, the Central Government may, after examination of the`
  line `report (and after taking such legal advice, as it may think fit), direct the Serious Fraud Investigation`
  line `Office to initiate prosecution against the company and its officers or employees, who are or have been in`
  line `employment of the company or any other person directly or indirectly connected with the affairs of the`
  line company.
  line
  line `^6[(14A) Where the report under sub-section (11) or sub-section (12) states that fraud has taken place`
  line `in a company and due to such fraud any director, key managerial personnel, other officer of the company`
  line `or any other person or entity, has taken undue advantage or benefit, whether in the form of any asset,`
  line `property or cash or in any other manner, the Central Government may file an application before the`
  line `Tribunal for appropriate orders with regard to disgorgement of such asset, property or cash and also for`
  line `holding such director, key managerial personnel, other officer or any other person liable personally`
  line `without any limitation of liability.]`
  line
  line `(15) Notwithstanding anything contained in this Act or in any other law for the time being in force,`
  line `the investigation report filed with the Special Court for framing of charges shall be deemed to be a report`
  line `filed by a police officer under section 173 of the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974).`
  line
  line `(16) Notwithstanding anything contained in this Act, any investigation or other action taken or`
  line `initiated by Serious Fraud Investigation Office under the provisions of the Companies Act, 1956 (1 of`
  line `1956) shall continue to be proceeded with under that Act as if this Act had not been passed.`
  line
  line `(17) (a) In case Serious Fraud Investigation Office has been investigating any offence under this Act,`
  line `any other investigating agency, State Government, police authority, income-tax authorities having any`
  line `information or documents in respect of such offence shall provide all such information or documents`
  line `available with it to the Serious Fraud Investigation Office;`
  line
  line `(b) The Serious Fraud Investigation Office shall share any information or documents available with it,`
  line `with any investigating agency, State Government, police authority or income-tax authorities, which may`
  line `be relevant or useful for such investigating agency, State Government, police authority or income-tax`
  line `authorities in respect of any offence or matter being investigated or examined by it under any other law.`
obj_root_law_sections_212_footnotes:
  string
