obj_root_law_sections_213:
  sectionId (49139)
  sectionNo (213)
  orderNo 217
  title `Investigation into company‘s affairs in other cases.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_213_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_213_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=49139&sectionno=213&orderno=217&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_213_content:
  string
  line `The Tribunal may,--`
  line
  line `(a) on an application made by--`
  line
  line `(i) not less than one hundred members or members holding not less than one-tenth of the total`
  line `voting power, in the case of a company having a share capital; or`
  line
  line `(ii) not less than one-fifth of the persons on the companys register of members, in the case of`
  line `a company having no share capital,`
  line
  line `and supported by such evidence as may be necessary for the purpose of showing that the applicants have`
  line `good reasons for seeking an order for conducting an investigation into the affairs of the company; or`
  line
  line `(b) on an application made to it by any other person or otherwise, if it is satisfied that there are`
  line `circumstances suggesting that--`
  line
  line `(i) the business of the company is being conducted with intent to defraud its creditors, members`
  line `or any other person or otherwise for a fraudulent or unlawful purpose, or in a manner oppressive to`
  line `any of its members or that the company was formed for any fraudulent or unlawful purpose;`
  line
  line `(ii) persons concerned in the formation of the company or the management of its affairs have in`
  line `connection therewith been guilty of fraud, misfeasance or other misconduct towards the company or`
  line `towards any of its members; or`
  line
  line `(iii) the members of the company have not been given all the information with respect to its`
  line `affairs which they might reasonably expect, including information relating to the calculation of the`
  line `commission payable to a managing or other director, or the manager, of the company,`
  line
  line `order, after giving a reasonable opportunity of being heard to the parties concerned, that the affairs of the`
  line `company ought to be investigated by an inspector or inspectors appointed by the Central Government and`
  line `where such an order is passed, the Central Government shall appoint one or more competent persons as`
  line `inspectors to investigate into the affairs of the company in respect of such matters and to report thereupon`
  line `to it in such manner as the Central Government may direct:`
  line
  line `Provided that if after investigation it is proved that--`
  line
  line `(i) the business of the company is being conducted with intent to defraud its creditors, members`
  line `or any other persons or otherwise for a fraudulent or unlawful purpose, or that the company was`
  line `formed for any fraudulent or unlawful purpose; or`
  line
  line `(ii) any person concerned in the formation of the company or the management of its affairs have`
  line `in connection therewith been guilty of fraud,`
  line
  line `then, every officer of the company who is in default and the person or persons concerned in the formation`
  line `of the company or the management of its affairs shall be punishable for fraud in the manner as provided`
  line `in section 447.`
obj_root_law_sections_213_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_214:
  sectionId (49140)
  sectionNo (214)
  orderNo 218
  title `Security for payment of costs and expenses of investigation`
  content obj_root_law_sections_214_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_214_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=49140&sectionno=214&orderno=218&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_214_content:
  string
  line `Where an investigation is`
  line `ordered by the Central Government in pursuance of clause (b) of sub-section (1) of section 210, or in`
  line `pursuance of an order made by the Tribunal under section 213, the Central Government may before`
  line `appointing an inspector under subsection (3) of section 210 or clause (b) of section 213, require the`
  line `applicant to give such security not exceeding twenty-five thousand rupees as may be prescribed, as it may`
  line `think fit, for payment of the costs and expenses of the investigation and such security shall be refunded to`
  line `the applicant if the investigation results in prosecution.`
obj_root_law_sections_214_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_215:
  sectionId (49141)
  sectionNo (215)
  orderNo 219
  title `Firm, body corporate or association not to be appointed as inspector`
  content obj_root_law_sections_215_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_215_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=49141&sectionno=215&orderno=219&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_215_content:
  string
  line `No firm, body`
  line `corporate or other association shall be appointed as an inspector.`
obj_root_law_sections_215_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_216:
  sectionId (49142)
  sectionNo (216)
  orderNo 220
  title `Investigation of ownership of company.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_216_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_216_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=49142&sectionno=216&orderno=220&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_216_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where it appears to the Central Government`
  line `that there is a reason so to do, it may appoint one or more inspectors to investigate and report on matters`
  line `relating to the company, and its membership for the purpose of determining the true persons--`
  line
  line `(a) who are or have been financially interested in the success or failure, whether real or apparent,`
  line `of the company; or`
  line
  line `(b) who are or have been able to control or to materially influence the policy of the ^1[company; or].`
  line
  line `^2[(c) who have or had beneficial interest in shares of a company or who are or have been`
  line `beneficial owners or significant beneficial owner of a company].`
  line
  line `(2) Without prejudice to its powers under sub-section (1), the Central Government shall appoint one`
  line `or more inspectors under that sub-section, if the Tribunal, in the course of any proceeding before it,`
  line `directs by an order that the affairs of the company ought to be investigated as regards the membership of`
  line `the company and other matters relating to the company, for the purposes specified in sub-section (1).`
  line
  line `(3) While appointing an inspector under sub-section (1), the Central Government may define the`
  line `scope of the investigation, whether as respects the matters or the period to which it is to extend or`
  line `otherwise, and in particular, may limit the investigation to matters connected with particular shares or`
  line debentures.
  line
  line `(4) Subject to the terms of appointment of an inspector, his powers shall extend to the investigation of`
  line `any circumstances suggesting the existence of any arrangement or understanding which, though not`
  line `legally binding, is or was observed or is likely to be observed in practice and which is relevant for the`
  line `purposes of his investigation.`
obj_root_law_sections_216_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 1 of 2018, s. 71 for "company" (w.e.f. 13-6-2018).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by s. 71, ibid., (w.e.f. 13-6-2018).`
obj_root_law_sections_217:
  sectionId (49143)
  sectionNo (217)
  orderNo 221
  title `Procedure, powers, etc., of inspectors.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_217_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_217_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=49143&sectionno=217&orderno=221&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_217_content:
  string
  line `(1) It shall be the duty of all officers and other`
  line `employees and agents including the former officers, employees and agents of a company which is under`
  line `investigation in accordance with the provisions contained in this Chapter, and where the affairs of any`
  line `other body corporate or a person are investigated under section 219, of all officers and other employees`
  line `and agents including former officers, employees and agents of such body corporate or a person--`
  line
  line `(a) to preserve and to produce to an inspector or any person authorised by him in this behalf all`
  line `books and papers of, or relating to, the company or, as the case may be, relating to the other body`
  line `corporate or the person, which are in their custody or power; and`
  line
  line `(b) otherwise to give to the inspector all assistance in connection with the investigation which`
  line `they are reasonably able to give.`
  line
  line `(2) The inspector may require any body corporate, other than a body corporate referred to in subsection`
  line `(1), to furnish such information to, or produce such books and papers before him or any person`
  line `authorised by him in this behalf as he may consider necessary, if the furnishing of such information or the`
  line `production of such books and papers is relevant or necessary for the purposes of his investigation.`
  line
  line `(3) The inspector shall not keep in his custody any books and papers produced under sub-section (1)`
  line `or sub-section (2) for more than one hundred and eighty days and return the same to the company, body`
  line `corporate, firm or individual by whom or on whose behalf the books and papers were produced:`
  line
  line `Provided that the books and papers may be called for by the inspector if they are needed again for a`
  line `further period of one hundred and eighty days by an order in writing.`
  line
  line `(4) An inspector may examine on oath--`
  line
  line `(a) any of the persons referred to in sub-section (1); and`
  line
  line `(b) with the prior approval of the Central Government, any other person,`
  line
  line `in relation to the affairs`
  line `of the company, or other body corporate or person, as the case may be, and for that purpose may`
  line `require any of those persons to appear before him personally:`
  line
  line `Provided that in case of an investigation under section 212, the prior approval of Director, Serious`
  line `Fraud Investigation Office shall be sufficient under clause (b).`
  line
  line `(5) Notwithstanding anything contained in any other law for the time being in force or in any contract`
  line `to the contrary, the inspector, being an officer of the Central Government, making an investigation under`
  line `this Chapter shall have all the powers as are vested in a civil court under the Code of Civil Procedure,`
  line `1908 (5 of 1908), while trying a suit in respect of the following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the discovery and production of books of account and other documents, at such place and time`
  line `as may be specified by such person;`
  line
  line `(b) summoning and enforcing the attendance of persons and examining them on oath; and`
  line
  line `(c) inspection of any books, registers and other documents of the company at any place.`
  line
  line `(6) (i) If any director or officer of the company disobeys the direction issued by the Registrar or the`
  line `inspector under this section, the director or the officer shall be punishable with imprisonment which may`
  line `extend to one year and with fine which shall not be less than twenty-five thousand rupees but which may`
  line `extend to one lakh rupees.`
  line
  line `(ii) If a director or an officer of the company has been convicted of an offence under this section, the`
  line `director or the officer shall, on and from the date on which he is so convicted, be deemed to have vacated`
  line `his office as such and on such vacation of office, shall be disqualified from holding an office in any`
  line company.
  line
  line `(7) The notes of any examination under sub-section (4) shall be taken down in writing and shall be`
  line `read over to, or by, and signed by, the person examined, and may thereafter be used in evidence against`
  line him.
  line
  line `(8) If any person fails without reasonable cause or refuses--`
  line
  line `(a) to produce to an inspector or any person authorised by him in this behalf any book or paper`
  line `which is his duty under sub-section (1) or sub-section (2) to produce;`
  line
  line `(b) to furnish any information which is his duty under sub-section (2) to furnish;`
  line
  line `(c) to appear before the inspector personally when required to do so under subsection (4) or to`
  line `answer any question which is put to him by the inspector in pursuance of that sub-section; or`
  line
  line `(d) to sign the notes of any examination referred to in sub-section (7),`
  line
  line `he shall be punishable with imprisonment for a term which may extend to six months and with fine which`
  line `shall not be less than twenty-five thousand rupees but which may extend to one lakh rupees, and also with`
  line `a further fine which may extend to two thousand rupees for every day after the first during which the`
  line `failure or refusal continues.`
  line
  line `(9) The officers of the Central Government, State Government, police or statutory authority shall`
  line `provide assistance to the inspector for the purpose of inspection, inquiry or investigation, which the`
  line
  line `inspector may, with the prior approval of the Central Government, require.`
  line
  line `(10) The Central Government may enter into an agreement with the Government of a foreign State for`
  line `reciprocal arrangements to assist in any inspection, inquiry or investigation under this Act or under the`
  line `corresponding law in force in that State and may, by notification, render the application of this Chapter in`
  line `relation to a foreign State with which reciprocal arrangements have been made subject to such`
  line `modifications, exceptions, conditions and qualifications as may be deemed expedient for implementing`
  line `the agreement with that State.`
  line
  line `(11) Notwithstanding anything contained in this Act or in the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of`
  line `1974) if, in the course of an investigation into the affairs of the company, an application is made to the`
  line `competent court in India by the inspector stating that evidence is, or may be, available in a country or`
  line `place outside India, such court may issue a letter of request to a court or an authority in such country or`
  line `place, competent to deal with such request, to examine orally, or otherwise, any person, supposed to be`
  line `acquainted with the facts and circumstances of the case, to record his statement made in the course of`
  line `such examination and also to require such person or any other person to produce any document or thing,`
  line `which may be in his possession pertaining to the case, and to forward all the evidence so taken or`
  line `collected or the authenticated copies thereof or the things so collected to the court in India which had`
  line `issued such letter of request:`
  line
  line `Provided that the letter of request shall be transmitted in such manner as the Central Government may`
  line `specify in this behalf:`
  line
  line `Provided further that every statement recorded or document or thing received under this sub-section`
  line `shall be deemed to be the evidence collected during the course of investigation.`
  line
  line `(12) Upon receipt of a letter of request from a court or an authority in a country or place outside India,`
  line `competent to issue such letter in that country or place for the examination of any person or production of`
  line `any document or thing in relation to affairs of a company under investigation in that country or place, the`
  line `Central Government may, if it thinks fit, forward such letter of request to the court concerned, which shall`
  line `thereupon summon the person before it and record his statement or cause any document or thing to be`
  line `produced, or send the letter to any inspector for investigation, who shall thereupon investigate into the`
  line `affairs of company in the same manner as the affairs of a company are investigated under this Act and the`
  line `inspector shall submit the report to such court within thirty days or such extended time as the court may`
  line `allow for further action:`
  line
  line `Provided that the evidence taken or collected under this sub-section or authenticated copies thereof or`
  line `the things so collected shall be forwarded by the court, to the Central Government for transmission, in`
  line `such manner as the Central Government may deem fit, to the court or the authority in country or place`
  line `outside India which had issued the letter of request.`
obj_root_law_sections_217_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_218:
  sectionId (49144)
  sectionNo (218)
  orderNo 222
  title `Protection of employees during investigation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_218_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_218_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=49144&sectionno=218&orderno=222&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_218_content:
  string
  line `(1) Notwithstanding anything contained in`
  line `any other law for the time being in force, if--`
  line
  line `(a) during the course of any investigation of the affairs and other matters of or relating to a`
  line `company, other body corporate or person under section 210, section 212, section 213 or section 219`
  line `or of the membership and other matters of or relating to a company, or the ownership of shares in or`
  line `debentures of a company or body corporate, or the affairs and other matters of or relating to a`
  line `company, other body corporate or person, under section 216; or`
  line
  line `(b) during the pendency of any proceeding against any person concerned in the conduct and`
  line `management of the affairs of a company under Chapter XVI,`
  line `such company, other body corporate or person proposes`
  line
  line `(i) to discharge or suspend any employee; or`
  line
  line `(ii) to punish him, whether by dismissal, removal, reduction in rank or otherwise; or`
  line
  line `(iii) to change the terms of employment to his disadvantage,`
  line
  line `the company, other body corporate or person, as the case may be, shall obtain approval of the Tribunal of`
  line `the action proposed against the employee and if the Tribunal has any objection to the action proposed, it`
  line `shall send by post notice thereof in writing to the company, other body corporate or person concerned.`
  line
  line `(2) If the company, other body corporate or person concerned does not receive within thirty days of`
  line `making of application under sub-section (1), the approval of the Tribunal, then and only then, the`
  line `company, other body corporate or person concerned may proceed to take against the employee, the action`
  line proposed.
  line
  line `(3) If the company, other body corporate or person concerned is dissatisfied with the objection raised`
  line `by the Tribunal, it may, within a period of thirty days of the receipt of the notice of the objection, prefer`
  line `an appeal to the Appellate Tribunal in such manner and on payment of such fees as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(4) The decision of the Appellate Tribunal on such appeal shall be final and binding on the Tribunal`
  line `and on the company, other body corporate or person concerned.`
  line
  line `(5) For the removal of doubts, it is hereby declared that the provisions of this section shall have effect`
  line `without prejudice to the provisions of any other law for the time being in force.`
obj_root_law_sections_218_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_219:
  sectionId (49145)
  sectionNo (219)
  orderNo 223
  title `Power of inspector to conduct investigation into affairs of related companies, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_219_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_219_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=49145&sectionno=219&orderno=223&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_219_content:
  string
  line `If an`
  line `inspector appointed under section 210 or section 212 or section 213 to investigate into the affairs of a`
  line `company considers it necessary for the purposes of the investigation, to investigate also the affairs of`
  line
  line `(a) any other body corporate which is, or has at any relevant time been the companys subsidiary`
  line `company or holding company, or a subsidiary company of its holding company;`
  line
  line `(b) any other body corporate which is, or has at any relevant time been managed by any person as`
  line `managing director or as manager, who is, or was, at the relevant time, the managing director or the`
  line `manager of the company;`
  line
  line `(c) any other body corporate whose Board of Directors comprises nominees of the company or is`
  line `accustomed to act in accordance with the directions or instructions of the company or any of its`
  line `directors; or`
  line
  line `(d) any person who is or has at any relevant time been the companys managing director or`
  line `manager or employee,`
  line
  line `he shall, subject to the prior approval of the Central Government, investigate into and report on the affairs`
  line `of the other body corporate or of the managing director or manager, in so far as he considers that the`
  line `results of his investigation are relevant to the investigation of the affairs of the company for which he is`
  line appointed.
obj_root_law_sections_219_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_220:
  sectionId (49146)
  sectionNo (220)
  orderNo 224
  title `Seizure of documents by inspector`
  content obj_root_law_sections_220_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_220_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=49146&sectionno=220&orderno=224&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_220_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where in the course of an investigation under this`
  line `Chapter, the inspector has reasonable grounds to believe that the books and papers of, or relating to, any`
  line `company or other body corporate or managing director or manager of such company are likely to be`
  line `destroyed, mutilated, altered, falsified or secreted, the inspector may--`
  line
  line `(a) enter, with such assistance as may be required, the place or places where such books and`
  line `papers are kept in such manner as may be required; and`
  line
  line `(b) seize books and papers as he considers necessary after allowing the company to take copies`
  line `of, or extracts from, such books and papers at its cost for the purposes of his investigation.`
  line
  line `(2) The inspector shall keep in his custody the books and papers seized under this section for such a`
  line `period not later than the conclusion of the investigation as he considers necessary and thereafter shall`
  line `return the same to the company or the other body corporate, or, as the case may be, to the managing`
  line `director or the manager or any other person from whose custody or power they were seized:`
  line
  line `Provided that the inspector may, before returning such books and papers as aforesaid, take copies of,`
  line `or extracts from them or place identification marks on them or any part thereof or deal with the same in`
  line `such manner as he considers necessary.`
  line
  line `(3) The provisions of the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974), relating to searches or`
  line `seizures shall apply mutatis mutandis to every search or seizure made under this section.`
obj_root_law_sections_220_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_221:
  sectionId (49147)
  sectionNo (221)
  orderNo 225
  title `Freezing of assets of company on inquiry and investigation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_221_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_221_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=49147&sectionno=221&orderno=225&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_221_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where it appears to the`
  line `Tribunal, on a reference made to it by the Central Government or in connection with any inquiry or`
  line `investigation into the affairs of a company under this Chapter or on any complaint made by such number`
  line `of members as specified under sub-section (1) of section 244 or a creditor having one lakh amount`
  line `outstanding against the company or any other person having a reasonable ground to believe that the`
  line `removal, transfer or disposal of funds, assets, properties of the company is likely to take place in a manner`
  line `that is prejudicial to the interests of the company or its shareholders or creditors or in public interest, it`
  line `may by order direct that such transfer, removal or disposal shall not take place during such period not`
  line `exceeding three years as may be specified in the order or may take place subject to such conditions and`
  line `restrictions as the Tribunal may deem fit.`
  line
  line `(2) In case of any removal, transfer or disposal of funds, assets, or properties of the company in`
  line `contravention of the order of the Tribunal under sub-section (1), the company shall be punishable with`
  line `fine which shall not be less than one lakh rupees but which may extend to twenty-five lakh rupees and`
  line `every officer of the company who is in default shall be punishable with imprisonment for a term which`
  line `may extend to three years or with fine which shall not be less than fifty thousand rupees but which may`
  line `extend to five lakh rupees, or with both.`
obj_root_law_sections_221_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_222:
  sectionId (49148)
  sectionNo (222)
  orderNo 226
  title `Imposition of restrictions upon securities.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_222_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_222_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=49148&sectionno=222&orderno=226&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_222_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where it appears to the Tribunal, in`
  line `connection with any investigation under section 216 or on a complaint made by any person in this behalf,`
  line `that there is good reason to find out the relevant facts about any securities issued or to be issued by a`
  line `company and the Tribunal is of the opinion that such facts cannot be found out unless certain restrictions,`
  line `as it may deem fit, are imposed, the Tribunal may, by order, direct that the securities shall be subject to`
  line `such restrictions as it may deem fit for such period not exceeding three years as may be specified in the`
  line order.
  line
  line `(2) Where securities in any company are issued or transferred or acted upon in contravention of an`
  line `order of the Tribunal under sub-section (1), the company shall be punishable with fine which shall not be`
  line `less than one lakh rupees but which may extend to twenty-five lakh rupees and every officer of the`
  line `company who is in default shall be punishable with imprisonment for a term which may extend to six`
  line `months or with fine which shall not be less than twenty-five thousand rupees but which may extend to`
  line `five lakh rupees, or with both.`
obj_root_law_sections_222_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_223:
  sectionId (49149)
  sectionNo (223)
  orderNo 227
  title `Inspector‘s report.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_223_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_223_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=49149&sectionno=223&orderno=227&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_223_content:
  string
  line `(1) An inspector appointed under this Chapter may, and if so directed by`
  line `the Central Government shall, submit interim reports to that Government, and on the conclusion of the`
  line `investigation, shall submit a final report to the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(2) Every report made under sub-section (1) shall be in writing or printed as the Central Government`
  line `may direct.`
  line
  line `(3) A copy of the report made under sub-section (1) may be obtained ^1[by members, creditors or any`
  line `other person whose interest is likely to be affected] by making an application in this regard to the Central`
  line Government.
  line
  line `(4) The report of any inspector appointed under this Chapter shall be authenticated either--`
  line
  line `(a) ^2[by the seal, if any] of the company whose affairs have been investigated; or`
  line
  line `(b) by a certificate of a public officer having the custody of the report, as provided under section`
  line `76 of the Indian Evidence Act, 1872 (1 of 1872),`
  line
  line `and such report shall be admissible in any legal proceeding as evidence in relation to any matter contained`
  line `in the report.`
  line
  line `(5) Nothing in this section shall apply to the report referred to in section 212.`
obj_root_law_sections_223_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 1 of 2018, s. 72 (w.e.f. 9-2-2018).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 21 of 2015, s. 18, for "by the seal" (w.e.f. 29-5-2015).`
obj_root_law_sections_224:
  sectionId (49150)
  sectionNo (224)
  orderNo 228
  title `Actions to be taken in pursuance of inspector‘s report.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_224_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 31 of 2016, s. 255 and the Eleventh Schedule (w.e.f. 15-11-2016).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=49150&sectionno=224&orderno=228&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_224_content:
  string
  line `(1) If, from an inspectors report,`
  line `made under section 223, it appears to the Central Government that any person has, in relation to the`
  line `company or in relation to any other body corporate or other person whose affairs have been investigated`
  line `under this Chapter been guilty of any offence for which he is criminally liable, the Central Government`
  line `may prosecute such person for the offence and it shall be the duty of all officers and other employees of`
  line `the company or body corporate to give the Central Government the necessary assistance in connection`
  line `with the prosecution.`
  line
  line `(2) If any company or other body corporate is liable to be wound up under this Act ^1[or under the`
  line `Insolvency and Bankruptcy Code, 2016 (31 of 2016)] and it appears to the Central Government from any`
  line `such report made under section 223 that it is expedient so to do by reason of any such circumstances as`
  line `are referred to in section 213, the Central Government may, unless the company or body corporate is`
  line `already being wound up by the Tribunal, cause to be presented to the Tribunal by any person authorised`
  line `by the Central Government in this behalf--`
  line
  line `(a) a petition for the winding up of the company or body corporate on the ground that it is just`
  line `and equitable that it should be wound up;`
  line
  line `(b) an application under section 241; or`
  line
  line `(c) both.`
  line
  line `(3) If from any such report as aforesaid, it appears to the Central Government that proceedings ought,`
  line `in the public interest, to be brought by the company or any body corporate whose affairs have been`
  line `investigated under this Chapter--`
  line
  line `(a) for the recovery of damages in respect of any fraud, misfeasance or other misconduct in`
  line `connection with the promotion or formation, or the management of the affairs, of such company or`
  line `body corporate; or`
  line
  line `(b) for the recovery of any property of such company or body corporate which has been`
  line `misapplied or wrongfully retained,`
  line
  line `the Central Government may itself bring proceedings for winding up in the name of such company or`
  line `body corporate.`
  line
  line `(4) The Central Government, shall be indemnified by such company or body corporate against any`
  line `costs or expenses incurred by it in, or in connection with, any proceedings brought by virtue of subsection`
  line `(3).`
  line
  line `(5) Where the report made by an inspector states that fraud has taken place in a company and due to`
  line `such fraud any director, key managerial personnel, other officer of the company or any other person or`
  line `entity, has taken undue advantage or benefit, whether in the form of any asset, property or cash or in any`
  line `other manner, the Central Government may file an application before the Tribunal for appropriate orders`
  line `with regard to disgorgement of such asset, property, or cash, as the case may be, and also for holding such`
  line `director, key managerial personnel, officer or other person liable personally without any limitation of`
  line liability.
obj_root_law_sections_225:
  sectionId (49151)
  sectionNo (225)
  orderNo 229
  title `Expenses of investigation`
  content obj_root_law_sections_225_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_225_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=49151&sectionno=225&orderno=229&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_225_content:
  string
  line `(1) The expenses of, and incidental to, an investigation by an`
  line `inspector appointed by the Central Government under this Chapter other than expenses of inspection`
  line `under section 214 shall be defrayed in the first instance by the Central Government, but shall be`
  line `reimbursed by the following persons to the extent mentioned below, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) any person who is convicted on a prosecution instituted, or who is ordered to pay damages or`
  line `restore any property in proceedings brought, under section 224, to the extent that he may in the same`
  line `proceedings be ordered to pay the said expenses as may be specified by the court convicting such`
  line `person, or ordering him to pay such damages or restore such property, as the case may be;`
  line
  line `(b) any company or body corporate in whose name proceedings are brought as aforesaid, to the`
  line `extent of the amount or value of any sums or property recovered by it as a result of such proceedings;`
  line
  line `(c) unless, as a result of the investigation, a prosecution is instituted under section 224,--`
  line
  line `(i) any company, body corporate, managing director or manager dealt with by the report of`
  line `the inspector; and`
  line
  line `(ii) the applicants for the investigation, where the inspector was appointed under section 213,`
  line
  line `to such extent as the Central Government may direct.`
  line
  line `(2) Any amount for which a company or body corporate is liable under clause (b) of sub-section (1)`
  line `shall be a first charge on the sums or property mentioned in that clause.`
obj_root_law_sections_225_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_226:
  sectionId (49152)
  sectionNo (226)
  orderNo 230
  title `Voluntary winding up of company, etc., not to stop investigation proceedings`
  content obj_root_law_sections_226_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_226_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=49152&sectionno=226&orderno=230&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_226_content:
  string
  line An
  line `investigation under this Chapter may be initiated notwithstanding, and no such investigation shall be`
  line `stopped or suspended by reason only of, the fact that--`
  line
  line `(a) an application has been made under section 241;`
  line
  line `(b) the company has passed a special resolution for voluntary winding up; or`
  line
  line `(c) any other proceeding for the winding up of the company is pending before the Tribunal:`
  line
  line `Provided that where a winding up order is passed by the Tribunal in a proceeding referred to in clause`
  line `(c), the inspector shall inform the Tribunal about the pendency of the investigation proceedings before`
  line `him and the Tribunal shall pass such order as it may deem fit:`
  line
  line `Provided further that nothing in the winding up order shall absolve any director or other employee of`
  line `the company from participating in the proceedings before the inspector or any liability as a result of the`
  line `finding by the inspector.`
obj_root_law_sections_226_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_227:
  sectionId (49153)
  sectionNo (227)
  orderNo 231
  title `Legal advisers and bankers not to disclose certain information.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_227_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_227_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=49153&sectionno=227&orderno=231&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_227_content:
  string
  line `Nothing in this Chapter`
  line `shall require the disclosure to the Tribunal or to the Central Government or to the Registrar or to an`
  line `inspector appointed by the Central Government--`
  line
  line `(a) by a legal adviser, of any privileged communication made to him in that capacity, except as`
  line `respects the name and address of his client; or`
  line
  line `(b) by the bankers of any company, body corporate, or other person, of any information as to the`
  line `affairs of any of their customers, other than such company, body corporate, or person.`
obj_root_law_sections_227_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_228:
  sectionId (49154)
  sectionNo (228)
  orderNo 232
  title `Investigation, etc., of foreign companies.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_228_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_228_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=49154&sectionno=228&orderno=232&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_228_content:
  string
  line `The provisions of this Chapter shall apply mutatis`
  line `mutandis to inspection, inquiry or investigation in relation to foreign companies.`
obj_root_law_sections_228_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_229:
  sectionId (49155)
  sectionNo (229)
  orderNo 233
  title `Penalty for furnishing false statement, mutilation, destruction of documents`
  content obj_root_law_sections_229_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_229_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=49155&sectionno=229&orderno=233&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_229_content:
  string
  line `Where a`
  line `person who is required to provide an explanation or make a statement during the course of inspection,`
  line `inquiry or investigation, or an officer or other employee of a company or other body corporate which is`
  line `also under investigation,--`
  line
  line `(a) destroys, mutilates or falsifies, or conceals or tampers or unauthorisedly removes, or is a party`
  line `to the destruction, mutilation or falsification or concealment or tampering or unauthorised removal of,`
  line `documents relating to the property, assets or affairs of the company or the body corporate;`
  line
  line `(b) makes, or is a party to the making of, a false entry in any document concerning the company`
  line `or body corporate; or`
  line
  line `(c) provides an explanation which is false or which he knows to be false, he shall be punishable`
  line `for fraud in the manner as provided in section 447.`
obj_root_law_sections_229_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_230:
  sectionId (49156)
  sectionNo (230)
  orderNo 234
  title `Power to compromise or make arrangements with creditors and members`
  content obj_root_law_sections_230_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_230_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=49156&sectionno=230&orderno=234&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_230_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where a`
  line `compromise or arrangement is proposed--`
  line
  line `(a) between a company and its creditors or any class of them; or`
  line
  line `(b) between a company and its members or any class of them,`
  line
  line `the Tribunal may, on the application of the company or of any creditor or member of the company, or in`
  line `the case of a company which is being wound up, of the liquidator, ^1[appointed under this Act or under the`
  line `Insolvency and Bankruptcy Code, 2016 (31 of 2016), as the case may be,] order a meeting of the creditors`
  line `or class of creditors, or of the members or class of members, as the case may be, to be called, held and`
  line `conducted in such manner as the Tribunal directs.`
  line
  line `Explanation.-- For the purposes of this sub-section, arrangement includes a reorganisation of the`
  line `company's share capital by the consolidation of shares of different classes or by the division of shares`
  line `into shares of different classes, or by both of those methods.`
  line
  line `(2) The company or any other person, by whom an application is made under subsection (1), shall`
  line `disclose to the Tribunal by affidavit--`
  line
  line `(a) all material facts relating to the company, such as the latest financial position of the company,`
  line `the latest auditors report on the accounts of the company and the pendency of any investigation or`
  line `proceedings against the company;`
  line
  line `(b) reduction of share capital of the company, if any, included in the compromise or arrangement;`
  line
  line `(c) any scheme of corporate debt restructuring consented to by not less than seventy-five per cent.`
  line `of the secured creditors in value, including--`
  line
  line `(i) a creditors responsibility statement in the prescribed form;`
  line
  line `(ii) safeguards for the protection of other secured and unsecured creditors;`
  line
  line `(iii) report by the auditor that the fund requirements of the company after the corporate debt`
  line `restructuring as approved shall conform to the liquidity test based upon the estimates provided to`
  line `them by the Board;`
  line
  line `(iv) where the company proposes to adopt the corporate debt restructuring guidelines`
  line `specified by the Reserve Bank of India, a statement to that effect; and`
  line
  line `(v) a valuation report in respect of the shares and the property and all assets, tangible and`
  line `intangible, movable and immovable, of the company by a registered valuer.`
  line
  line `(3) Where a meeting is proposed to be called in pursuance of an order of the Tribunal under subsection`
  line `(1), a notice of such meeting shall be sent to all the creditors or class of creditors and to all the`
  line `members or class of members and the debenture-holders of the company, individually at the address`
  line `registered with the company which shall be accompanied by a statement disclosing the details of the`
  line `compromise or arrangement, a copy of the valuation report, if any, and explaining their effect on`
  line `creditors, key managerial personnel, promoters and non-promoter members, and the debenture-holders`
  line `and the effect of the compromise or arrangement on any material interests of the directors of the company`
  line `or the debenture trustees, and such other matters as may be prescribed:`
  line
  line `Provided that such notice and other documents shall also be placed on the website of the company, if`
  line `any, and in case of a listed company, these documents shall be sent to the Securities and Exchange Board`
  line `and stock exchange where the securities of the companies are listed, for placing on their website and shall`
  line `also be published in newspapers in such manner as may be prescribed:`
  line
  line `Provided further that where the notice for the meeting is also issued by way of an advertisement, it`
  line `shall indicate the time within which copies of the compromise or arrangement shall be made available to`
  line `the concerned persons free of charge from the registered office of the company.`
  line
  line `(4) A notice under sub-section (3) shall provide that the persons to whom the notice is sent may vote`
  line `in the meeting either themselves or through proxies or by postal ballot to the adoption of the compromise`
  line `or arrangement within one month from the date of receipt of such notice:`
  line
  line `Provided that any objection to the compromise or arrangement shall be made only by persons holding`
  line `not less than ten per cent. of the shareholding or having outstanding debt amounting to not less than five`
  line `per cent. of the total outstanding debt as per the latest audited financial statement.`
  line
  line `(5) A notice under sub-section (3) along with all the documents in such form as may be prescribed`
  line `shall also be sent to the Central Government, the income-tax authorities, the Reserve Bank of India, the`
  line `Securities and Exchange Board, the Registrar, the respective stock exchanges, the Official Liquidator, the`
  line `Competition Commission of India established under sub-section (1) of section 7 of the Competition Act,`
  line `2002 (12 of 2003), if necessary, and such other sectoral regulators or authorities which are likely to be`
  line `affected by the compromise or arrangement and shall require that representations, if any, to be made by`
  line `them shall be made within a period of thirty days from the date of receipt of such notice, failing which, it`
  line `shall be presumed that they have no representations to make on the proposals.`
  line
  line `(6) Where, at a meeting held in pursuance of sub-section (1), majority of persons representing threefourths in value of the creditors, or class of creditors or members or class of members, as the case may be,`
  line `voting in person or by proxy or by postal ballot, agree to any compromise or arrangement and if such`
  line `compromise or arrangement is sanctioned by the Tribunal by an order, the same shall be binding on the`
  line `company, all the creditors, or class of creditors or members or class of members, as the case may be, or,`
  line `in case of a company being wound up, on the liquidator ^2[appointed under this act or under the Insolvency`
  line `and Bankruptcy Code, 2016 (31 of 2016), as the case may be,] and the contributories of the company`
  line
  line `(7) An order made by the Tribunal under sub-section (6) shall provide for all or any of the following`
  line `matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) where the compromise or arrangement provides for conversion of preference shares into`
  line `equity shares, such preference shareholders shall be given an option to either obtain arrears of`
  line `dividend in cash or accept equity shares equal to the value of the dividend payable;`
  line
  line `(b) the protection of any class of creditors;`
  line
  line `(c) if the compromise or arrangement results in the variation of the shareholders rights, it shall be`
  line `given effect to under the provisions of section 48;`
  line
  line `(d) if the compromise or arrangement is agreed to by the creditors under sub-section (6), any`
  line `proceedings pending before the Board for Industrial and Financial Reconstruction established under`
  line `section 4 of the Sick Industrial Companies (Special Provisions) Act, 1985 (1 of 1986) shall abate;`
  line
  line `(e) such other matters including exit offer to dissenting shareholders, if any, as are in the opinion`
  line `of the Tribunal necessary to effectively implement the terms of the compromise or arrangement:`
  line
  line `Provided that no compromise or arrangement shall be sanctioned by the Tribunal unless a certificate`
  line `by the company's auditor has been filed with the Tribunal to the effect that the accounting treatment, if`
  line `any, proposed in the scheme of compromise or arrangement is in conformity with the accounting`
  line `standards prescribed under section 133.`
  line
  line `(8) The order of the Tribunal shall be filed with the Registrar by the company within a period of thirty`
  line `days of the receipt of the order.`
  line
  line `(9) The Tribunal may dispense with calling of a meeting of creditor or class of creditors where such`
  line `creditors or class of creditors, having at least ninety per cent. value, agree and confirm, by way of`
  line `affidavit, to the scheme of compromise or arrangement.`
  line
  line `(10) No compromise or arrangement in respect of any buy-back of securities under this section shall`
  line `be sanctioned by the Tribunal unless such buy-back is in accordance with the provisions of section 68.`
  line
  line `(11) Any compromise or arrangement may include takeover offer made in such manner as may be`
  line `prescribed:`
  line
  line `Provided that in case of listed companies, takeover offer shall be as per the regulations framed by the`
  line `Securities and Exchange Board`
  line
  line `(12) An aggrieved party may make an application to the Tribunal in the event of any grievances with`
  line `respect to the takeover offer of companies other than listed companies in such manner as may be`
  line `prescribed and the Tribunal may, on application, pass such order as it may deem fit.`
  line
  line `Explanation.-- For the removal of doubts, it is hereby declared that the provisions of section 66 shall`
  line `not apply to the reduction of share capital effected in pursuance of the order of the Tribunal under this`
  line section.
obj_root_law_sections_230_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 31 of 2016, s. 255 and the Eleventh Schedule (w.e.f. 15-11-2016)`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by Act 31 of 2016, s. 255 and The Eleventh Schedule (w.e.f. 15-11-2016).`
obj_root_law_sections_231:
  sectionId (49157)
  sectionNo (231)
  orderNo 235
  title `Power to Tribunal to enforce compromise or arrangement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_231_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_231_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=49157&sectionno=231&orderno=235&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_231_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where the Tribunal makes`
  line `an order under section 230 sanctioning a compromise or an arrangement in respect of a company, it`
  line
  line `(a) shall have power to supervise the implementation of the compromise or arrangement; and--`
  line
  line `(b) may, at the time of making such order or at any time thereafter, give such directions in regard`
  line `to any matter or make such modifications in the compromise or arrangement as it may consider`
  line `necessary for the proper implementation of the compromise or arrangement.`
  line
  line `(2) If the Tribunal is satisfied that the compromise or arrangement sanctioned under section 230`
  line `cannot be implemented satisfactorily with or without modifications, and the company is unable to pay its`
  line `debts as per the scheme, it may make an order for winding up the company and such an order shall be`
  line `deemed to be an order made under section 273.`
  line
  line `(3) The provisions of this section shall, so far as may be, also apply to a company in respect of which`
  line `an order has been made before the commencement of this Act sanctioning a compromise or an`
  line arrangement.
obj_root_law_sections_231_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_232:
  sectionId (49158)
  sectionNo (232)
  orderNo 236
  title `Merger and amalgamation of companies.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_232_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 29 of 2020, s. 42, for sub-section (8) (w.e.f. 21-12-2020).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=49158&sectionno=232&orderno=236&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_232_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where an application is made to the Tribunal`
  line `under section 230 for the sanctioning of a compromise or an arrangement proposed between a company`
  line `and any such persons as are mentioned in that section, and it is shown to the Tribunal--`
  line
  line `(a) that the compromise or arrangement has been proposed for the purposes of, or in connection`
  line `with, a scheme for the reconstruction of the company or companies involving merger or the`
  line `amalgamation of any two or more companies; and`
  line
  line `(b) that under the scheme, the whole or any part of the undertaking, property or liabilities of any`
  line `company (hereinafter referred to as the transferor company) is required to be transferred to another`
  line `company (hereinafter referred to as the transferee company), or is proposed to be divided among and`
  line `transferred to two or more companies,`
  line
  line `the Tribunal may on such application, order a meeting of the creditors or class of creditors or the`
  line `members or class of members, as the case may be, to be called, held and conducted in such manner as the`
  line `Tribunal may direct and the provisions of sub-sections (3) to (6) of section 230 shall apply mutatis`
  line mutandis.
  line
  line `(2) Where an order has been made by the Tribunal under sub-section (1), merging companies or the`
  line `companies in respect of which a division is proposed, shall also be required to circulate the following for`
  line `the meeting so ordered by the Tribunal, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the draft of the proposed terms of the scheme drawn up and adopted by the directors of the`
  line `merging company;`
  line
  line `(b) confirmation that a copy of the draft scheme has been filed with the Registrar;`
  line
  line `(c) a report adopted by the directors of the merging companies explaining effect of compromise`
  line `on each class of shareholders, key managerial personnel, promoters and non-promoter shareholders`
  line `laying out in particular the share exchange ratio, specifying any special valuation difficulties;`
  line
  line `(d) the report of the expert with regard to valuation, if any;`
  line
  line `(e) a supplementary accounting statement if the last annual accounts of any of the merging`
  line `company relate to a financial year ending more than six months before the first meeting of the`
  line `company summoned for the purposes of approving the scheme.`
  line
  line `(3) The Tribunal, after satisfying itself that the procedure specified in sub-sections (1) and (2) has`
  line `been complied with, may, by order, sanction the compromise or arrangement or by a subsequent order,`
  line `make provision for the following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the transfer to the transferee company of the whole or any part of the undertaking, property or`
  line `liabilities of the transferor company from a date to be determined by the parties unless the Tribunal,`
  line `for reasons to be recorded by it in writing, decides otherwise;`
  line
  line `(b) the allotment or appropriation by the transferee company of any shares, debentures, policies or`
  line `other like instruments in the company which, under the compromise or arrangement, are to be allotted`
  line `or appropriated by that company to or for any person:`
  line
  line `Provided that a transferee company shall not, as a result of the compromise or arrangement, hold`
  line `any shares in its own name or in the name of any trust whether on its behalf or on behalf of any of its`
  line `subsidiary or associate companies and any such shares shall be cancelled or extinguished;`
  line
  line `(c) the continuation by or against the transferee company of any legal proceedings pending by or`
  line `against any transferor company on the date of transfer;`
  line
  line `(d) dissolution, without winding-up, of any transferor company;`
  line
  line `(e) the provision to be made for any persons who, within such time and in such manner as the`
  line `Tribunal directs, dissent from the compromise or arrangement;`
  line
  line `(f) where share capital is held by any non-resident shareholder under the foreign direct investment`
  line `norms or guidelines specified by the Central Government or in accordance with any law for the time`
  line `being in force, the allotment of shares of the transferee company to such shareholder shall be in the`
  line `manner specified in the order;`
  line
  line `(g) the transfer of the employees of the transferor company to the transferee company;`
  line
  line `(h) where the transferor company is a listed company and the transferee company is an unlisted`
  line company,--
  line
  line `(A) the transferee company shall remain an unlisted company until it becomes a listed`
  line company;
  line
  line `(B) if shareholders of the transferor company decide to opt out of the transferee company,`
  line `provision shall be made for payment of the value of shares held by them and other benefits in`
  line `accordance with a pre-determined price formula or after a valuation is made, and the`
  line `arrangements under this provision may be made by the Tribunal:`
  line
  line `Provided that the amount of payment or valuation under this clause for any share shall not be less`
  line `than what has been specified by the Securities and Exchange Board under any regulations framed by`
  line it;
  line
  line `(i) where the transferor company is dissolved, the fee, if any, paid by the transferor company on`
  line `its authorised capital shall be set-off against any fees payable by the transferee company on its`
  line `authorised capital subsequent to the amalgamation; and`
  line
  line `(j) such incidental, consequential and supplemental matters as are deemed necessary to secure`
  line `that the merger or amalgamation is fully and effectively carried out:`
  line
  line `Provided that no compromise or arrangement shall be sanctioned by the Tribunal unless a`
  line `certificate by the companys auditor has been filed with the Tribunal to the effect that the accounting`
  line `treatment, if any, proposed in the scheme of compromise or arrangement is in conformity with the`
  line `accounting standards prescribed under section 133.`
  line
  line `(4) Where an order under this section provides for the transfer of any property or liabilities, then, by`
  line `virtue of the order, that property shall be transferred to the transferee company and the liabilities shall be`
  line `transferred to and become the liabilities of the transferee company and any property may, if the order so`
  line `directs, be freed from any charge which shall by virtue of the compromise or arrangement, cease to have`
  line effect.
  line
  line `(5) Every company in relation to which the order is made shall cause a certified copy of the order to`
  line `be filed with the Registrar for registration within thirty days of the receipt of certified copy of the order.`
  line
  line `(6) The scheme under this section shall clearly indicate an appointed date from which it shall be`
  line `effective and the scheme shall be deemed to be effective from such date and not at a date subsequent to`
  line `the appointed date.`
  line
  line `(7) Every company in relation to which the order is made shall, until the completion of the scheme,`
  line `file a statement in such form and within such time as may be prescribed with the Registrar every year`
  line `duly certified by a chartered accountant or a cost accountant or a company secretary in practice indicating`
  line `whether the scheme is being complied with in accordance with the orders of the Tribunal or not.`
  line
  line `^1[(8) If a company fails to comply with sub-section (5), the company and every officer of the`
  line `company who is in default shall be liable to a penalty of twenty thousand rupees, and where the failure is`
  line `a continuing one, with a further penalty of one thousand rupees for each day after the first during which`
  line `such failure continues, subject to a maximum of three lakh rupees.]`
  line
  line `Explanation. -- For the purposes of this section,--`
  line
  line `(i) in a scheme involving a merger, where under the scheme the undertaking, property and`
  line `liabilities of one or more companies, including the company in respect of which the compromise or`
  line `arrangement is proposed, are to be transferred to another existing company, it is a merger by`
  line `absorption, or where the undertaking, property and liabilities of two or more companies, including the`
  line `company in respect of which the compromise or arrangement is proposed, are to be transferred to a`
  line `new company, whether or not a public company, it is a merger by formation of a new company;`
  line
  line `(ii) references to merging companies are in relation to a merger by absorption, to the transferor`
  line `and transferee companies, and, in relation to a merger by formation of a new company, to the`
  line `transferor companies;`
  line
  line `(iii) a scheme involves a division, where under the scheme the undertaking, property and`
  line `liabilities of the company in respect of which the compromise or arrangement is proposed are to be`
  line `divided among and transferred to two or more companies each of which is either an existing company`
  line `or a new company; and`
  line
  line `(iv) property includes assets, rights and interests of every description and liabilities include debts`
  line `and obligations of every description.`
obj_root_law_sections_233:
  sectionId (49159)
  sectionNo (233)
  orderNo 237
  title `Merger or amalgamation of certain companies.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_233_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_233_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=49159&sectionno=233&orderno=237&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_233_content:
  string
  line `(1) Notwithstanding the provisions of`
  line `section 230 and section 232, a scheme of merger or amalgamation may be entered into between two or`
  line `more small companies or between a holding company and its wholly-owned subsidiary company or such`
  line `other class or classes of companies as may be prescribed, subject to the following, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) a notice of the proposed scheme inviting objections or suggestions, if any, from the Registrar`
  line `and Official Liquidators where registered office of the respective companies are situated or persons`
  line `affected by the scheme within thirty days is issued by the transferor company or companies and the`
  line `transferee company;`
  line
  line `(b) the objections and suggestions received are considered by the companies in their respective`
  line `general meetings and the scheme is approved by the respective members or class of members at a`
  line `general meeting holding at least ninety per cent. of the total number of shares;`
  line
  line `(c) each of the companies involved in the merger files a declaration of solvency, in the prescribed`
  line `form, with the Registrar of the place where the registered office of the company is situated; and`
  line
  line `(d) the scheme is approved by majority representing nine-tenths in value of the creditors or class`
  line `of creditors of respective companies indicated in a meeting convened by the company by giving a`
  line `notice of twenty-one days along with the scheme to its creditors for the purpose or otherwise`
  line `approved in writing.`
  line
  line `(2) The transferee company shall file a copy of the scheme so approved in the manner as may be`
  line `prescribed, with the Central Government, Registrar and the Official Liquidator where the registered office`
  line `of the company is situated.`
  line
  line `(3) On the receipt of the scheme, if the Registrar or the Official Liquidator has no objections or`
  line `suggestions to the scheme, the Central Government shall register the same and issue a confirmation`
  line `thereof to the companies.`
  line
  line `(4) If the Registrar or Official Liquidator has any objections or suggestions, he may communicate the`
  line `same in writing to the Central Government within a period of thirty days:`
  line
  line `Provided that if no such communication is made, it shall be presumed that he has no objection to the`
  line scheme.
  line
  line `(5) If the Central Government after receiving the objections or suggestions or for any reason is of the`
  line `opinion that such a scheme is not in public interest or in the interest of the creditors, it may file an`
  line `application before the Tribunal within a period of sixty days of the receipt of the scheme under subsection`
  line `(2) stating its objections and requesting that the Tribunal may consider the scheme under section`
  line 232.
  line
  line `(6) On receipt of an application from the Central Government or from any person, if the Tribunal, for`
  line `reasons to be recorded in writing, is of the opinion that the scheme should be considered as per the`
  line `procedure laid down in section 232, the Tribunal may direct accordingly or it may confirm the scheme by`
  line `passing such order as it deems fit:`
  line
  line `Provided that if the Central Government does not have any objection to the scheme or it does not file`
  line `any application under this section before the Tribunal, it shall be deemed that it has no objection to the`
  line scheme.
  line
  line `(7) A copy of the order under sub-section (6) confirming the scheme shall be communicated to the`
  line `Registrar having jurisdiction over the transferee company and the persons concerned and the Registrar`
  line `shall register the scheme and issue a confirmation thereof to the companies and such confirmation shall be`
  line `communicated to the Registrars where transferor company or companies were situated.`
  line
  line `(8) The registration of the scheme under sub-section (3) or sub-section (7) shall be deemed to have`
  line `the effect of dissolution of the transferor company without process of winding-up.`
  line
  line `(9) The registration of the scheme shall have the following effects, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) transfer of property or liabilities of the transferor company to the transferee company so that`
  line `the property becomes the property of the transferee company and the liabilities become the liabilities`
  line `of the transferee company;`
  line
  line `(b) the charges, if any, on the property of the transferor company shall be applicable and`
  line `enforceable as if the charges were on the property of the transferee company;`
  line
  line `(c) legal proceedings by or against the transferor company pending before any court of law shall`
  line `be continued by or against the transferee company; and`
  line
  line `(d) where the scheme provides for purchase of shares held by the dissenting shareholders or`
  line `settlement of debt due to dissenting creditors, such amount, to the extent it is unpaid, shall become the`
  line `liability of the transferee company.`
  line
  line `(10) A transferee company shall not on merger or amalgamation, hold any shares in its own name or`
  line `in the name of any trust either on its behalf or on behalf of any of its subsidiary or associate company and`
  line `all such shares shall be cancelled or extinguished on the merger or amalgamation.`
  line
  line `(11) The transferee company shall file an application with the Registrar along with the scheme`
  line `registered, indicating the revised authorised capital and pay the prescribed fees due on revised capital:`
  line
  line `Provided that the fee, if any, paid by the transferor company on its authorised capital prior to its`
  line `merger or amalgamation with the transferee company shall be set-off against the fees payable by the`
  line `transferee company on its authorised capital enhanced by the merger or amalgamation.`
  line
  line `(12) The provisions of this section shall mutatis mutandis apply to a company or companies specified`
  line `in sub-section (1) in respect of a scheme of compromise or arrangement referred to in section 230 or`
  line `division or transfer of a company referred to clause (b) of subsection (1) of section 232.`
  line
  line `(13) The Central Government may provide for the merger or amalgamation of companies in such`
  line `manner as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(14) A company covered under this section may use the provisions of section 232 for the approval of`
  line `any scheme for merger or amalgamation.`
obj_root_law_sections_233_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_234:
  sectionId (49160)
  sectionNo (234)
  orderNo 238
  title `Merger or amalgamation of company with foreign company`
  content obj_root_law_sections_234_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_234_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=49160&sectionno=234&orderno=238&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_234_content:
  string
  line `(1) The provisions of this`
  line `Chapter unless otherwise provided under any other law for the time being in force, shall apply mutatis`
  line `mutandis to schemes of mergers and amalgamations between companies registered under this Act and`
  line `companies incorporated in the jurisdictions of such countries as may be notified from time to time by the`
  line `Central Government:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Central Government may make rules, in consultation with the Reserve Bank of`
  line `India, in connection with mergers and amalgamations provided under this section.`
  line
  line `(2) Subject to the provisions of any other law for the time being in force, a foreign company, may`
  line `with the prior approval of the Reserve Bank of India, merge into a company registered under this Act or`
  line `vice versa and the terms and conditions of the scheme of merger may provide, among other things, for the`
  line `payment of consideration to the shareholders of the merging company in cash, or in Depository Receipts,`
  line `or partly in cash and partly in Depository Receipts, as the case may be, as per the scheme to be drawn up`
  line `for the purpose.`
  line
  line `Explanation.-- For the purposes of sub-section (2), the expression foreign company means any`
  line `company or body corporate incorporated outside India whether having a place of business in India or not.`
obj_root_law_sections_234_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_235:
  sectionId (49161)
  sectionNo (235)
  orderNo 239
  title `Power to acquire shares of shareholders dissenting from scheme or contract approved by majority`
  content obj_root_law_sections_235_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_235_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=49161&sectionno=235&orderno=239&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_235_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where a scheme or contract involving the transfer of shares or any class of shares in a`
  line `company (the transferor company) to another company (the transferee company) has, within four months`
  line `after making of an offer in that behalf by the transferee company, been approved by the holders of not less`
  line `than nine-tenths in value of the shares whose transfer is involved, other than shares already held at the`
  line `date of the offer by, or by a nominee of the transferee company or its subsidiary companies, the transferee`
  line `company may, at any time within two months after the expiry of the said four months, give notice in the`
  line `prescribed manner to any dissenting shareholder that it desires to acquire his shares.`
  line
  line `(2) Where a notice under sub-section (1) is given, the transferee company shall, unless on an`
  line `application made by the dissenting shareholder to the Tribunal, within one month from the date on which`
  line `the notice was given and the Tribunal thinks fit to order otherwise, be entitled to and bound to acquire`
  line `those shares on the terms on which, under the scheme or contract, the shares of the approving`
  line `shareholders are to be transferred to the transferee company.`
  line
  line `(3) Where a notice has been given by the transferee company under sub-section (1) and the Tribunal`
  line `has not, on an application made by the dissenting shareholder, made an order to the contrary, the`
  line `transferee company shall, on the expiry of one month from the date on which the notice has been given,`
  line `or, if an application to the Tribunal by the dissenting shareholder is then pending, after that application`
  line `has been disposed of, send a copy of the notice to the transferor company together with an instrument of`
  line `transfer, to be executed on behalf of the shareholder by any person appointed by the transferor company`
  line `and on its own behalf by the transferee company, and pay or transfer to the transferor company the`
  line `amount or other consideration representing the price payable by the transferee company for the shares`
  line `which, by virtue of this section, that company is entitled to acquire, and the transferor company shall--`
  line
  line `(a) thereupon register the transferee company as the holder of those shares; and`
  line
  line `(b) within one month of the date of such registration, inform the dissenting shareholders of the`
  line `fact of such registration and of the receipt of the amount or other consideration representing the price`
  line `payable to them by the transferee company.`
  line
  line `(4) Any sum received by the transferor company under this section shall be paid into a separate bank`
  line `account, and any such sum and any other consideration so received shall be held by that company in trust`
  line `for the several persons entitled to the shares in respect of which the said sum or other consideration were`
  line `respectively received and shall be disbursed to the entitled shareholders within sixty days.`
  line
  line `(5) In relation to an offer made by a transferee company to shareholders of a transferor company`
  line `before the commencement of this Act, this section shall have effect with the following modifications,`
  line `namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) in sub-section (1), for the words "the shares whose transfer is involved other than shares`
  line `already held at the date of the offer by, or by a nominee of, the transferee company or its`
  line subsidiaries,
  line `", the words "the shares affected" shall be substituted; and`
  line
  line `(b) in sub-section (3), the words "together with an instrument of transfer, to be executed on behalf`
  line `of the shareholder by any person appointed by the transferee company and on its own behalf by the`
  line `transferor company" shall be omitted.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purposes of this section, "dissenting shareholder" includes a shareholder who`
  line `has not assented to the scheme or contract and any shareholder who has failed or refused to transfer his`
  line `shares to the transferee company in accordance with the scheme or contract.`
obj_root_law_sections_235_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_236:
  sectionId (49162)
  sectionNo (236)
  orderNo 240
  title `Purchase of minority shareholding.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_236_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_236_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=49162&sectionno=236&orderno=240&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_236_content:
  string
  line `(1) In the event of an acquirer, or a person acting in`
  line `concert with such acquirer, becoming registered holder of ninety per cent. or more of the issued equity`
  line `share capital of a company, or in the event of any person or group of persons becoming ninety per cent.`
  line `majority or holding ninety per cent. of the issued equity share capital of a company, by virtue of an`
  line `amalgamation, share exchange, conversion of securities or for any other reason, such acquirer, person or`
  line `group of persons, as the case may be, shall notify the company of their intention to buy the remaining`
  line `equity shares.`
  line
  line `(2) The acquirer, person or group of persons under sub-section (1) shall offer to the minority`
  line `shareholders of the company for buying the equity shares held by such shareholders at a price determined`
  line `on the basis of valuation by a registered valuer in accordance with such rules as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(3) Without prejudice to the provisions of sub-sections (1) and (2), the minority shareholders of the`
  line `company may offer to the majority shareholders to purchase the minority equity shareholding of the`
  line `company at the price determined in accordance with such rules as may be prescribed under sub-section`
  line `(2).`
  line
  line `(4) The majority shareholders shall deposit an amount equal to the value of shares to be acquired by`
  line `them under sub-section (2) or sub-section (3), as the case may be, in a separate bank account to be`
  line `operated by the ^1[company whose shares are being transferred] company for at least one year for payment to the minority shareholders and`
  line `such amount shall be disbursed to the entitled shareholders within sixty days:`
  line
  line `Provided that such disbursement shall continue to be made to the entitled shareholders for a period of`
  line `one year, who for any reason had not been made disbursement within the said period of sixty days or if`
  line `the disbursement have been made within the aforesaid period of sixty days, fail to receive or claim`
  line `payment arising out of such disbursement.`
  line
  line `(5) In the event of a purchase under this section, the transferor company shall act as a transfer agent`
  line `for receiving and paying the price to the minority shareholders and for taking delivery of the shares and`
  line `delivering such shares to the majority, as the case may be.`
  line
  line `(6) In the absence of a physical delivery of shares by the shareholders within the time specified by the`
  line `company, the share certificates shall be deemed to be cancelled, and the transferor company shall be`
  line `authorised to issue shares in lieu of the cancelled shares and complete the transfer in accordance with law`
  line `and make payment of the price out of deposit made under sub-section (4) by the majority in advance to`
  line `the minority by dispatch of such payment.`
  line
  line `(5) In the event of a purchase under this section, the ^2[company whose shares are being transferred] shall act as a transfer agent for receiving and paying the price to the minority shareholders and for taking`
  line `delivery of the shares and delivering such shares to the majority, as the case may be.`
  line
  line `(7) In the event of a majority shareholder or shareholders requiring a full purchase and making`
  line `payment of price by deposit with the company for any shareholder or shareholders who have died or`
  line `ceased to exist, or whose heirs, successors, administrators or assignees have not been brought on record`
  line `by transmission, the right of such shareholders to make an offer for sale of minority equity shareholding`
  line `shall continue and be available for a period of three years from the date of majority acquisition or`
  line `majority shareholding.`
  line
  line `(8) Where the shares of minority shareholders have been acquired in pursuance of this section and as`
  line `on or prior to the date of transfer following such acquisition, the shareholders holding seventy-five per`
  line `cent. or more minority equity shareholding negotiate or reach an understanding on a higher price for any`
  line `transfer, proposed or agreed upon, of the shares held by them without disclosing the fact or likelihood of`
  line `transfer taking place on the basis of such negotiation, understanding or agreement, the majority`
  line `shareholders shall share the additional compensation so received by them with such minority shareholders`
  line `on a pro rata basis.`
  line
  line `Explanation.-- For the purposes of this section, the expressions "acquirer" and "person acting in`
  line `concert" shall have the meanings respectively assigned to them in clause (b) and clause (e) of subregulation`
  line `(1) of regulation 2 of the Securities and Exchange Board of India (Substantial Acquisition of`
  line `Shares and Takeovers) Regulations, 1997.`
  line
  line `(9) When a shareholder or the majority equity shareholder fails to acquire full purchase of the shares`
  line `of the minority equity shareholders, then, the provisions of this section shall continue to apply to the`
  line `residual minority equity shareholders, even though,--`
  line
  line `(a) the shares of the company of the residual minority equity shareholder had been delisted; and`
  line
  line `(b) the period of one year or the period specified in the regulations made by the Securities and`
  line `Exchange Board under the Securities and Exchange Board of India Act, 1992 (15 of 1992), had`
  line elapsed.
obj_root_law_sections_236_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 1 of 2018, s. 73, for "transferor company" (w.e.f. 9-2-2018).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 1 of 2018, s. 73, for "transferor company" (w.e.f. 9-2-2018).`
obj_root_law_sections_237:
  sectionId (49163)
  sectionNo (237)
  orderNo 241
  title `Power of Central Government to provide for amalgamation of companies in public interest.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_237_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_237_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=49163&sectionno=237&orderno=241&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_237_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where the Central Government is satisfied that it is essential in the public interest that two`
  line `or more companies should amalgamate, the Central Government may, by order notified in the Official`
  line `Gazette, provide for the amalgamation of those companies into a single company with such constitution,`
  line `with such property, powers, rights, interests, authorities and privileges, and with such liabilities, duties`
  line `and obligations, as may be specified in the order.`
  line
  line `(2) The order under sub-section (1) may also provide for the continuation by or against the transferee`
  line `company of any legal proceedings pending by or against any transferor company and such consequential,`
  line `incidental and supplemental provisions as may, in the opinion of the Central Government, be necessary to`
  line `give effect to the amalgamation.`
  line
  line `(3) Every member or creditor, including a debenture holder, of each of the transferor companies`
  line `before the amalgamation shall have, as nearly as may be, the same interest in or rights against the`
  line `transferee company as he had in the company of which he was originally a member or creditor, and in`
  line `case the interest or rights of such member or creditor in or against the transferee company are less than his`
  line `interest in or rights against the original company, he shall be entitled to compensation to that extent,`
  line `which shall be assessed by such authority as may be prescribed and every such assessment shall be`
  line `published in the Official Gazette, and the compensation so assessed shall be paid to the member or`
  line `creditor concerned by the transferee company.`
  line
  line `(4) Any person aggrieved by any assessment of compensation made by the prescribed authority under`
  line `sub-section (3) may, within a period of thirty days from the date of publication of such assessment in the`
  line `Official Gazette, prefer an appeal to the Tribunal and thereupon the assessment of the compensation shall`
  line `be made by the Tribunal.`
  line
  line `(5) No order shall be made under this section unless--`
  line
  line `(a) a copy of the proposed order has been sent in draft to each of the companies concerned;`
  line
  line `(b) the time for preferring an appeal under sub-section (4) has expired, or where any such appeal`
  line `has been preferred, the appeal has been finally disposed off; and`
  line
  line `(c) the Central Government has considered, and made such modifications, if any, in the draft`
  line `order as it may deem fit in the light of suggestions and objections which may be received by it from`
  line `any such company within such period as the Central Government may fix in that behalf, not being`
  line `less than two months from the date on which the copy aforesaid is received by that company, or from`
  line `any class of shareholders therein, or from any creditors or any class of creditors thereof.`
  line
  line `(6) The copies of every order made under this section shall, as soon as may be after it has been made,`
  line `be laid before each House of Parliament.`
obj_root_law_sections_237_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_238:
  sectionId (49164)
  sectionNo (238)
  orderNo 242
  title `Registration of offer of schemes involving transfer of shares.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_238_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_238_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=49164&sectionno=238&orderno=242&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_238_content:
  string
  line `(1) In relation to every offer`
  line `of a scheme or contract involving the transfer of shares or any class of shares in the transferor company to`
  line `the transferee company under section 235,--`
  line
  line `(a) every circular containing such offer and recommendation to the members of the transferor`
  line `company by its directors to accept such offer shall be accompanied by such information and in such`
  line `manner as may be prescribed;`
  line
  line `(b) every such offer shall contain a statement by or on behalf of the transferee company,`
  line `disclosing the steps it has taken to ensure that necessary cash will be available; and`
  line
  line `(c) every such circular shall be presented to the Registrar for registration and no such circular`
  line `shall be issued until it is so registered:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Registrar may refuse, for reasons to be recorded in writing, to register any such`
  line `circular which does not contain the information required to be given under clause (a) or which sets out`
  line `such information in a manner likely to give a false impression, and communicate such refusal to the`
  line `parties within thirty days of the application.`
  line
  line `(2) An appeal shall lie to the Tribunal against an order of the Registrar refusing to register any`
  line `circular under sub-section (1).`
  line
  line `((3) The director who issues a circular which has not been presented for registration and registered`
  line `under clause (c) of sub-section (1), shall be ^1[liable to a penalty of one lakh rupees.]`
obj_root_law_sections_238_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 22 of 2019, s. 32, for "punishable with fine which shall not be less than twenty-five thousand rupees but which`
  line `may extend to five lakh rupees" (w.e.f. 2-11-2018).`
obj_root_law_sections_239:
  sectionId (49165)
  sectionNo (239)
  orderNo 243
  title `Preservation of books and papers of amalgamated companies`
  content obj_root_law_sections_239_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_239_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=49165&sectionno=239&orderno=243&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_239_content:
  string
  line `The books and papers of a`
  line `company which has been amalgamated with, or whose shares have been acquired by, another company`
  line `under this Chapter shall not be disposed of without the prior permission of the Central Government and`
  line `before granting such permission, that Government may appoint a person to examine the books and papers`
  line `or any of them for the purpose of ascertaining whether they contain any evidence of the commission of an`
  line `offence in connection with the promotion or formation, or the management of the affairs, of the transferor`
  line `company or its amalgamation or the acquisition of its shares.`
obj_root_law_sections_239_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_240:
  sectionId (49166)
  sectionNo (240)
  orderNo 244
  title `Liability of officers in respect of offences committed prior to merger, amalgamation, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_240_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_240_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=49166&sectionno=240&orderno=244&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_240_content:
  string
  line `Notwithstanding anything in any other law for the time being in force, the liability in respect of offences`
  line `committed under this Act by the officers in default, of the transferor company prior to its merger,`
  line `amalgamation or acquisition shall continue after such merger, amalgamation or acquisition.`
obj_root_law_sections_240_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_241:
  sectionId (49167)
  sectionNo (241)
  orderNo 245
  title `Application to Tribunal for relief in cases of oppression, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_241_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 22 of 2019, s. 33 (w.e.f. 15-8-2019).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=49167&sectionno=241&orderno=245&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_241_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any member of a`
  line `company who complains that--`
  line
  line `(a) the affairs of the company have been or are being conducted in a manner prejudicial to public`
  line `interest or in a manner prejudicial or oppressive to him or any other member or members or in a`
  line `manner prejudicial to the interests of the company; or`
  line
  line `(b) the material change, not being a change brought about by, or in the interests of, any creditors,`
  line `including debenture holders or any class of shareholders of the company, has taken place in the`
  line `management or control of the company, whether by an alteration in the Board of Directors, or`
  line `manager, or in the ownership of the companys shares, or if it has no share capital, in its membership,`
  line `or in any other manner whatsoever, and that by reason of such change, it is likely that the affairs of`
  line `the company will be conducted in a manner prejudicial to its interests or its members or any class of`
  line members,
  line
  line `may apply to the Tribunal, provided such member has a right to apply under section 244, for an order`
  line `under this Chapter.`
  line
  line `(2) The Central Government, if it is of the opinion that the affairs of the company are being conducted`
  line `in a manner prejudicial to public interest, it may itself apply to the Tribunal for an order under this`
  line Chapter.
  line
  line `^1[Provided that the applicants under this sub-section, in respect of such company or class of`
  line `companies, as may be prescribed, shall be made before the Principal Bench of the Tribunal which shall be`
  line `dealt with by such Bench.]`
  line
  line `^1[(3) Where in the opinion of the Central Government there exist circumstances suggesting that--`
  line
  line `(a) any person concerned in the conduct and management of the affairs of a company is or has`
  line `been in connection therewith guilty of fraud, misfeasance, persistent negligence or default in carrying`
  line `out his obligations and functions under the law or of breach of trust;`
  line
  line `(b) the business of a company is not or has not been conducted and managed by such person in`
  line `accordance with sound business principle or prudent commercial practices;`
  line
  line `(c) a company is or has been conducted and managed by such person in a manner which likely to`
  line `cause, or has caused, serious injury or damage to the interest of the trade, industry or business to`
  line `which such company pertains; or`
  line
  line `(d) the business of a company is or has been conducted and managed by such person with intent`
  line `to default its creditors, members or any other person or otherwise for a fraudulent or unlawful purpose`
  line `or in a manner prejudicial to public interest,`
  line
  line `the Central Government may intiate a case against such person and refer the same to the Tribunal with a`
  line `request that the Tribunal may inquire into the case and record a decision as to whether or not such person`
  line `is a fit and proper person to hold the officer of director or any other office connected with the conduct and`
  line `management of any company.`
  line
  line `(4) The person against whom a case is referred to the Tribunal under sub-section (3), shall be`
  line `jointed as a respondent to the applicantion.`
  line
  line `(5) Every application under sub-section (3)--`
  line
  line `(a) shall contain a concise statement of such circumstances and materials as the Central`
  line `Government may consider necessary for the purpose of the inquiry; and`
  line
  line `(b) shall be signed and verified in the manner laid down in the Code of Civil Procedure (5 of`
  line `1908), for the signature and verification of a plaint in a suit by the Central Government.]`
obj_root_law_sections_242:
  sectionId (49168)
  sectionNo (242)
  orderNo 246
  title `Powers of Tribunal.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_242_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_242_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=49168&sectionno=242&orderno=246&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_242_content:
  string
  line `(1) If, on any application made under section 241, the Tribunal is of the`
  line opinion--
  line
  line `(a) that the company's affairs have been or are being conducted in a manner prejudicial or`
  line `oppressive to any member or members or prejudicial to public interest or in a manner prejudicial to`
  line `the interests of the company; and`
  line
  line `(b) that to wind up the company would unfairly prejudice such member or members, but that`
  line `otherwise the facts would justify the making of a winding-up order on the ground that it was just and`
  line `equitable that the company should be wound up,`
  line
  line `the Tribunal may, with a view to bringing to an end the matters complained of, make such order as it`
  line `thinks fit.`
  line
  line `(2) Without prejudice to the generality of the powers under sub-section (1), an order under that subsection`
  line `may provide for--`
  line
  line `(a) the regulation of conduct of affairs of the company in future;`
  line
  line `(b) the purchase of shares or interests of any members of the company by other members thereof`
  line `or by the company;`
  line
  line `(c) in the case of a purchase of its shares by the company as aforesaid, the consequent reduction`
  line `of its share capital;`
  line
  line `(d) restrictions on the transfer or allotment of the shares of the company;`
  line
  line `(e) the termination, setting aside or modification, of any agreement, howsoever arrived at,`
  line `between the company and the managing director, any other director or manager, upon such terms and`
  line `conditions as may, in the opinion of the Tribunal, be just and equitable in the circumstances of the`
  line case;
  line
  line `(f) the termination, setting aside or modification of any agreement between the company and any`
  line `person other than those referred to in clause (e):`
  line
  line `Provided that no such agreement shall be terminated, set aside or modified except after due notice`
  line `and after obtaining the consent of the party concerned;`
  line
  line `(g) the setting aside of any transfer, delivery of goods, payment, execution or other act relating to`
  line `property made or done by or against the company within three months before the date of the`
  line `application under this section, which would, if made or done by or against an individual, be deemed`
  line `in his insolvency to be a fraudulent preference;`
  line
  line `(h) removal of the managing director, manager or any of the directors of the company;`
  line
  line `(i) recovery of undue gains made by any managing director, manager or director during the period`
  line `of his appointment as such and the manner of utilisation of the recovery including transfer to Investor`
  line `Education and Protection Fund or repayment to identifiable victims;`
  line
  line `(j) the manner in which the managing director or manager of the company may be appointed`
  line `subsequent to an order removing the existing managing director or manager of the company made`
  line `under clause (h);`
  line
  line `(k) appointment of such number of persons as directors, who may be required by the Tribunal to`
  line `report to the Tribunal on such matters as the Tribunal may direct;`
  line
  line `(l) imposition of costs as may be deemed fit by the Tribunal;`
  line
  line `(m) any other matter for which, in the opinion of the Tribunal, it is just and equitable that`
  line `provision should be made.`
  line
  line `(3) A certified copy of the order of the Tribunal under sub-section (1) shall be filed by the company`
  line `with the Registrar within thirty days of the order of the Tribunal.`
  line
  line `(4) The Tribunal may, on the application of any party to the proceeding, make any interim order`
  line `which it thinks fit for regulating the conduct of the company's affairs upon such terms and conditions as`
  line `appear to it to be just and equitable.`
  line
  line `^1[(4A) At the conclusion of the hearing of the case in respect of sub-section (3) of section 241, the`
  line `Tribunal shall record its decision stating therein specifically as to whether or not respondent is a fit and`
  line `proper person to hold the officer of director or any other officer connected with the conduct and`
  line `management of any company.]`
  line
  line `(5) Where an order of the Tribunal under sub-section (1) makes any alteration in the memorandum or`
  line `articles of a company, then, notwithstanding any other provision of this Act, the company shall not have`
  line `power, except to the extent, if any, permitted in the order, to make, without the leave of the Tribunal, any`
  line `alteration whatsoever which is inconsistent with the order, either in the memorandum or in the articles.`
  line
  line `(6) Subject to the provisions of sub-section (1), the alterations made by the order in the memorandum`
  line `or articles of a company shall, in all respects, have the same effect as if they had been duly made by the`
  line `company in accordance with the provisions of this Act and the said provisions shall apply accordingly to`
  line `the memorandum or articles so altered.`
  line
  line `(7) A certified copy of every order altering, or giving leave to alter, a company's memorandum or`
  line `articles, shall within thirty days after the making thereof, be filed by the company with the Registrar who`
  line `shall register the same.`
  line
  line `(8) If a company contravenes the provisions of sub-section (5), the company shall be punishable with`
  line `fine which shall not be less than one lakh rupees but which may extend to twenty-five lakh rupees and`
  line `every officer of the company who is in default shall be punishable ^2*** with fine which shall not be less`
  line `than twenty-five thousand rupees but which may extend to ^3[one lakh rupees].`
obj_root_law_sections_242_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 22 of 2019, s. 34 (w.e.f. 15-8-2019).`
  line
  line `2. The words "with imprisonment for a term which may extend to six months or" omitted by Act 29 of 2020, s. 43 (w.e.f. 21-12-`
  line `2020).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by s. 43, ibid., for "one lakh rupees, or with both" (w.e.f. 21-12-2020).`
obj_root_law_sections_243:
  sectionId (49169)
  sectionNo (243)
  orderNo 247
  title `Consequence of termination or modification of certain agreements.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_243_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_243_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=49169&sectionno=243&orderno=247&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_243_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where an order`
  line `made under section 242 terminates, sets aside or modifies an agreement such as is referred to in subsection (2) of that section,--`
  line
  line `(a) such order shall not give rise to any claims whatever against the company by any person for`
  line `damages or for compensation for loss of office or in any other respect either in pursuance of the`
  line `agreement or otherwise;`
  line
  line `(b) no managing director or other director or manager whose agreement is so terminated or set`
  line `aside shall, for a period of five years from the date of the order terminating or setting aside the`
  line `agreement, without the leave of the Tribunal, be appointed, or act, as the managing director or other`
  line `director or manager of the company:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Tribunal shall not grant leave under this clause unless notice of the intention to`
  line `apply for leave has been served on the Central Government and that Government has been given a`
  line `reasonable opportunity of being heard in the matter.`
  line
  line `^1[(1A) The person who is not a fit and proper person pursuant to sub-section (4A) of section 242 shall`
  line `not hold the officer of a director or any other officer connected with the conduct and management of the`
  line `affairs of any other officer connected with the conduct and management of the affairs of any company for`
  line `a period of five years from the date of the said decision:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Central Government may, with the leave of the Tribunal, permit such person to hold`
  line `any such office before the expiry of the said period of five years.`
  line
  line `(1B) Notwithstanding anything contained in any other provisions of this Act, or any other law for the`
  line `time being in force, or any contract, memorandum or articles, on the removal of a person from the officer`
  line `of a director or any other officer connected with the conduct and management of the affairs of the`
  line `company, that person shall not be entitled to, or be paid, any compensation for the loss or termination of`
  line officer.]
  line
  line `(2) Any person who knowingly acts as a managing director or other director or manager of a company`
  line `in contravention of clause (b) of sub-section (1)`
  line `^2[or sub-section (1A)], and every other director of the`
  line `company who is knowingly a party to such contravention, shall be punishable ^3*** with fine which may`
  line `extend to ^4[five lakh rupees].`
obj_root_law_sections_243_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 22 of 2019, s. 35 (w.e.f. 15-8-2019).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by s. 35, ibid. (w.e.f. 15-8-2019).`
  line
  line `3. The words "with imprisonment for a term which may extend to six months or" s. 44, ibid. (w.e.f. 21-12-2020).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by s. 44, ibid., for "five lakh rupees, or with both" (w.e.f. 21-12-2020).`
obj_root_law_sections_244:
  sectionId (49170)
  sectionNo (244)
  orderNo 248
  title `Right to apply under section 241.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_244_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_244_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=49170&sectionno=244&orderno=248&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_244_content:
  string
  line `(1) The following members of a company shall have the`
  line `right to apply under section 241, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) in the case of a company having a share capital, not less than one hundred members of the`
  line `company or not less than one-tenth of the total number of its members, whichever is less, or any`
  line `member or members holding not less than one-tenth of the issued share capital of the company,`
  line `subject to the condition that the applicant or applicants has or have paid all calls and other sums due`
  line `on his or their shares;`
  line
  line `(b) in the case of a company not having a share capital, not less than one-fifth of the total number`
  line `of its members:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Tribunal may, on an application made to it in this behalf, waive all or any of the`
  line `requirements specified in clause (a) or clause (b) so as to enable the members to apply under section 241.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purposes of this sub-section, where any share or shares are held by two or`
  line `more persons jointly, they shall be counted only as one member.`
  line
  line `(2) Where any members of a company are entitled to make an application under subsection (1), any`
  line `one or more of them having obtained the consent in writing of the rest, may make the application on`
  line `behalf and for the benefit of all of them.`
obj_root_law_sections_244_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_245:
  sectionId (49171)
  sectionNo (245)
  orderNo 249
  title `Class action`
  content obj_root_law_sections_245_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_245_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=49171&sectionno=245&orderno=249&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_245_content:
  string
  line `(1) Such number of member or members, depositor or depositors or any class of`
  line `them, as the case may be, as are indicated in sub-section (2) may, if they are of the opinion that the`
  line `management or conduct of the affairs of the company are being conducted in a manner prejudicial to the`
  line `interests of the company or its members or depositors, file an application before the Tribunal on behalf of`
  line `the members or depositors for seeking all or any of the following orders, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) to restrain the company from committing an act which is ultra vires the articles or`
  line `memorandum of the company;`
  line
  line `(b) to restrain the company from committing breach of any provision of the companys`
  line `memorandum or articles;`
  line
  line `(c) to declare a resolution altering the memorandum or articles of the company as void if the`
  line `resolution was passed by suppression of material facts or obtained by mis-statement to the members`
  line `or depositors;`
  line
  line `(d) to restrain the company and its directors from acting on such resolution;`
  line
  line `(e) to restrain the company from doing an act which is contrary to the provisions of this Act or`
  line `any other law for the time being in force;`
  line
  line `(f) to restrain the company from taking action contrary to any resolution passed by the members;`
  line
  line `(g) to claim damages or compensation or demand any other suitable action from or against`
  line
  line `(i) the company or its directors for any fraudulent, unlawful or wrongful act or omission or`
  line `conduct or any likely act or omission or conduct on its or their part;`
  line
  line `(ii) the auditor including audit firm of the company for any improper or misleading statement`
  line `of particulars made in his audit report or for any fraudulent, unlawful or wrongful act or conduct;`
  line or
  line
  line `(iii) any expert or advisor or consultant or any other person for any incorrect or misleading`
  line `statement made to the company or for any fraudulent, unlawful or wrongful act or conduct or any`
  line `likely act or conduct on his part;`
  line
  line `(h) to seek any other remedy as the Tribunal may deem fit.`
  line
  line `(2) Where the members or depositors seek any damages or compensation or demand any other`
  line `suitable action from or against an audit firm, the liability shall be of the firm as well as of each partner`
  line `who was involved in making any improper or misleading statement of particulars in the audit report or`
  line `who acted in a fraudulent, unlawful or wrongful manner.`
  line
  line `(3) (i) The requisite number of members provided in sub-section (1) shall be as under:`
  line
  line `(a) in the case of a company having a share capital, not less than one hundred members of the`
  line `company or not less than such percentage of the total number of its members as may be prescribed,`
  line `whichever is less, or any member or members holding not less than such percentage of the issued`
  line `share capital of the company as may be prescribed, subject to the condition that the applicant or`
  line `applicants has or have paid all calls and other sums due on his or their shares;`
  line
  line `(b) in the case of a company not having a share capital, not less than one-fifth of the total number`
  line `of its members.`
  line
  line `(ii) The requisite number of depositors provided in sub-section (1) shall not be less than one hundred`
  line `depositors or not less than such percentage of the total number of depositors as may be prescribed,`
  line `whichever is less, or any depositor or depositors to whom the company owes such percentage of total`
  line `deposits of the company as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(4) In considering an application under sub-section (1), the Tribunal shall take into account, in`
  line particular--
  line
  line `(a) whether the member or depositor is acting in good faith in making the application for seeking`
  line `an order;`
  line
  line `(b) any evidence before it as to the involvement of any person other than directors or officers of`
  line `the company on any of the matters provided in clauses (a) to (f) of subsection (1);`
  line
  line `(c) whether the cause of action is one which the member or depositor could pursue in his own`
  line `right rather than through an order under this section;`
  line
  line `(d) any evidence before it as to the views of the members or depositors of the company who have`
  line `no personal interest, direct or indirect, in the matter being proceeded under this section;`
  line
  line `(e) where the cause of action is an act or omission that is yet to occur, whether the act or omission`
  line `could be, and in the circumstances would be likely to be`
  line
  line `(i) authorised by the company before it occurs; or`
  line
  line `(ii) ratified by the company after it occurs;`
  line
  line `(f) where the cause of action is an act or omission that has already occurred, whether the act or`
  line `omission could be, and in the circumstances would be likely to be, ratified by the company.`
  line
  line `(5) If an application filed under sub-section (1) is admitted, then the Tribunal shall have regard to the`
  line `following, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) public notice shall be served on admission of the application to all the members or depositors`
  line `of the class in such manner as may be prescribed;`
  line
  line `(b) all similar applications prevalent in any jurisdiction should be consolidated into a single`
  line `application and the class members or depositors should be allowed to choose the lead applicant and in`
  line `the event the members or depositors of the class are unable to come to a consensus, the Tribunal shall`
  line `have the power to appoint a lead applicant, who shall be in charge of the proceedings from the`
  line `applicants side;`
  line
  line `(c) two class action applications for the same cause of action shall not be allowed;`
  line
  line `(d) the cost or expenses connected with the application for class action shall be defrayed by the`
  line `company or any other person responsible for any oppressive act.`
  line
  line `(6) Any order passed by the Tribunal shall be binding on the company and all its members, depositors`
  line `and auditor including audit firm or expert or consultant or advisor or any other person associated with the`
  line company.
  line
  line `(7) Any company which fails to comply with an order passed by the Tribunal under this section shall`
  line `be punishable with fine which shall not be less than five lakh rupees but which may extend to twenty-five`
  line `lakh rupees and every officer of the company who is in default shall be punishable with imprisonment for`
  line `a term which may extend to three years and with fine which shall not be less than twenty-five thousand`
  line `rupees but which may extend to one lakh rupees.`
  line
  line `(8) Where any application filed before the Tribunal is found to be frivolous or vexatious, it shall, for`
  line `reasons to be recorded in writing, reject the application and make an order that the applicant shall pay to`
  line `the opposite party such cost, not exceeding one lakh rupees, as may be specified in the order.`
  line
  line `(9) Nothing contained in this section shall apply to a banking company.`
  line
  line `(10) Subject to the compliance of this section, an application may be filed or any other action may be`
  line `taken under this section by any person, group of persons or any association of persons representing the`
  line `persons affected by any act or omission, specified in sub-section (1).`
obj_root_law_sections_245_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_246:
  sectionId (49172)
  sectionNo (246)
  orderNo 250
  title `Application of certain provisions to proceedings under section 241 or section 245.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_246_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_246_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=49172&sectionno=246&orderno=250&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_246_content:
  string
  line The
  line `provisions of sections 337 to 341 (both inclusive) shall apply mutatis mutandis, in relation to an`
  line `application made to the Tribunal under section 241 or section 245.`
obj_root_law_sections_246_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_247:
  sectionId (49173)
  sectionNo (247)
  orderNo 251
  title `Valuation by registered valuers.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_247_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_247_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=49173&sectionno=247&orderno=251&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_247_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where a valuation is required to be made in respect of`
  line `any property, stocks, shares, debentures, securities or goodwill or any other assets (herein referred to as`
  line `the assets) or net worth of a company or its liabilities under the provision of this Act, it shall be valued by`
  line `^1[a person having such qualifications and experience, registered as a valuer and being a member of an`
  line `organisation recognised, in such manner, on such terms and conditions as may be prescribed] and`
  line `appointed by the audit committee or in its absence by the Board of Directors of that company.`
  line
  line `(2) The valuer appointed under sub-section (1) shall,--`
  line
  line `(a) make an impartial, true and fair valuation of any assets which may be required to be valued;`
  line
  line `(b) exercise due diligence while performing the functions as valuer;`
  line
  line `(c) make the valuation in accordance with such rules as may be prescribed; and`
  line
  line `(d) not undertake valuation of any assets in which he has a direct or indirect interest or becomes`
  line `so interested at any time ^2[during a period of three years prior to his appointments as valuer or three`
  line `years after the valuation of assets was conducted by him].`
  line
  line `(3) If a valuer contravenes the provisions of this section or the rules made thereunder, the valuer shall`
  line `be punishable with fine which shall not be less than twenty-five thousand rupees but which may extend to`
  line `one lakh rupees:`
  line
  line `Provided that if the valuer has contravened such provisions with the intention to defraud the company`
  line `or its members, he shall be punishable with imprisonment for a term which may extend to one year and`
  line `with fine which shall not be less than one lakh rupees but which may extend to five lakh rupees.`
  line
  line `(4) Where a valuer has been convicted under sub-section (3), he shall be liable to--`
  line
  line `(i) refund the remuneration received by him to the company; and`
  line
  line `(ii) pay for damages to the company or to any other person for loss arising out of incorrect or`
  line `misleading statements of particulars made in his report.`
obj_root_law_sections_247_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. vide Notification No. S.O. 3400(E), s. 2 for certain words (w.e.f. 23-10-2017).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 1 of 2018, s. 74, for "during or after the valuation of assets" (w.e.f. 9-2-2018).`
obj_root_law_sections_248:
  sectionId (49174)
  sectionNo (248)
  orderNo 252
  title `Power of Registrar to remove name of company from register of companies.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_248_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_248_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=49174&sectionno=248&orderno=252&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_248_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where`
  line `the Registrar has reasonable cause to believe that--`
  line
  line `(a) a company has failed to commence its business within one year of its incorporation; ^1[or]`
  line
  line `^2* * * * *`
  line
  line `(c) a company is not carrying on any business or operation for a period of two immediately`
  line `preceding financial years and has not made any application within such period for obtaining the status`
  line `of a dormant company under ^3[section 455; or]`
  line
  line `^4[(d) the subscribers to the memorandum have not paid the subscription which they had`
  line `undertaken to pay at the time of incorporation of a company and a declaration to this effect has not`
  line `been filed within one hundred and eighty days of its incorporation under sub-section (1) of section`
  line `10A; or`
  line
  line `(e) the company is not carrying on any business or operations, as revealed after the physical`
  line `verification carried out under sub-section (9) of section 12.]`
  line
  line `he shall send a notice to the company and all the directors of the company, of his intention to remove`
  line `the name of the company from the register of companies and requesting them to send their`
  line `representations along with copies of the relevant documents, if any, within a period of thirty days`
  line `from the date of the notice.`
  line
  line `(2) Without prejudice to the provisions of sub-section (1), a company may, after extinguishing all its`
  line `liabilities, by a special resolution or consent of seventy-five per cent. members in terms of paid-up share`
  line `capital, file an application in the prescribed manner to the Registrar for removing the name of the`
  line `company from the register of companies on all or any of the grounds specified in sub-section (1) and the`
  line `Registrar shall, on receipt of such application, cause a public notice to be issued in the prescribed manner:`
  line
  line `Provided that in the case of a company regulated under a special Act, approval of the regulatory body`
  line `constituted or established under that Act shall also be obtained and enclosed with the application.`
  line
  line `(3) Nothing in sub-section (2) shall apply to a company registered under section 8.`
  line
  line `(4) A notice issued under sub-section (1) or sub-section (2) shall be published in the prescribed`
  line `manner and also in the Official Gazette for the information of the general public.`
  line
  line `(5) At the expiry of the time mentioned in the notice, the Registrar may, unless cause to the contrary`
  line `is shown by the company, strike off its name from the register of companies, and shall publish notice`
  line `thereof in the Official Gazette, and on the publication in the Official Gazette of this notice, the company`
  line `shall stand dissolved.`
  line
  line `(6) The Registrar, before passing an order under sub-section (5), shall satisfy himself that sufficient`
  line `provision has been made for the realisation of all amount due to the company and for the payment or`
  line `discharge of its liabilities and obligations by the company within a reasonable time and, if necessary,`
  line `obtain necessary undertakings from the managing director, director or other persons in charge of the`
  line `management of the company:`
  line
  line `Provided that notwithstanding the undertakings referred to in this sub-section, the assets of the`
  line `company shall be made available for the payment or discharge of all its liabilities and obligations even`
  line `after the date of the order removing the name of the company from the register of companies.`
  line
  line `(7) The liability, if any, of every director, manager or other officer who was exercising any power of`
  line `management, and of every member of the company dissolved under sub-section (5), shall continue and`
  line `may be enforced as if the company had not been dissolved.`
  line
  line `(8) Nothing in this section shall affect the power of the Tribunal to wind up a company the name of`
  line `which has been struck off from the register of companies.`
obj_root_law_sections_248_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 21 of 2015, s. 19 (w.e.f. 29-5-2015).`
  line
  line `2. Cl. (b) omitted by s.19, ibid. (w.e.f. 29-5-2015).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 22 of 2019, s. 36, for "section 455," (w.e.f. 2-11-2018).`
  line
  line `4. Ins. by s. 36, iibid. (w.e.f. 2-11-2018).`
obj_root_law_sections_249:
  sectionId (49175)
  sectionNo (249)
  orderNo 253
  title `Restrictions on making application under section 248 in certain situations.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_249_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 31 of 2016, s. 255 and the Eleventh Schedule, for clause (e) (w.e.f. 15-11-2016).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=49175&sectionno=249&orderno=253&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_249_content:
  string
  line `(1) An`
  line `application under sub-section (2) of section 248 on behalf of a company shall not be made if, at any time`
  line `in the previous three months, the company--`
  line
  line `(a) has changed its name or shifted its registered office from one State to another;`
  line
  line `(b) has made a disposal for value of property or rights held by it, immediately before cesser of`
  line `trade or otherwise carrying on of business, for the purpose of disposal for gain in the normal course of`
  line `trading or otherwise carrying on of business;`
  line
  line `(c) has engaged in any other activity except the one which is necessary or expedient for the`
  line `purpose of making an application under that section, or deciding whether to do so or concluding the`
  line `affairs of the company, or complying with any statutory requirement;`
  line
  line `(d) has made an application to the Tribunal for the sanctioning of a compromise or arrangement`
  line `and the matter has not been finally concluded; or`
  line
  line `^1[(e) is being wound up under Chapter XX of this Act or under the Insolvency and Bankruptcy`
  line `Code, 2016 (31 of 2016).]`
  line
  line `(2) If a company files an application under sub-section (2) of section 248 in violation of sub-section`
  line `(1), it shall be punishable with fine which may extend to one lakh rupees.`
  line
  line `(3) An application filed under sub-section (2) of section 248 shall be withdrawn by the company or`
  line `rejected by the Registrar as soon as conditions under sub-section (1) are brought to his notice.`
obj_root_law_sections_250:
  sectionId (49176)
  sectionNo (250)
  orderNo 254
  title `Effect of company notified as dissolved.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_250_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_250_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=49176&sectionno=250&orderno=254&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_250_content:
  string
  line `Where a company stands dissolved under section`
  line `248, it shall on and from the date mentioned in the notice under sub-section (5) of that section cease to`
  line `operate as a company and the Certificate of Incorporation issued to it shall be deemed to have been`
  line `cancelled from such date except for the purpose of realising the amount due to the company and for the`
  line `payment or discharge of the liabilities or obligations of the company.`
obj_root_law_sections_250_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_251:
  sectionId (49177)
  sectionNo (251)
  orderNo 255
  title `Fraudulent application for removal of name`
  content obj_root_law_sections_251_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_251_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=49177&sectionno=251&orderno=255&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_251_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where it is found that an application by a`
  line `company under sub-section (2) of section 248 has been made with the object of evading the liabilities of`
  line `the company or with the intention to deceive the creditors or to defraud any other persons, the persons in`
  line `charge of the management of the company shall, notwithstanding that the company has been notified as`
  line dissolved--
  line
  line `(a) be jointly and severally liable to any person or persons who had incurred loss or damage as a`
  line `result of the company being notified as dissolved; and`
  line
  line `(b) be punishable for fraud in the manner as provided in section 447.`
  line
  line `(2) Without prejudice to the provisions contained in sub-section (1), the Registrar may also`
  line `recommend prosecution of the persons responsible for the filing of an application under sub-section (2) of`
  line `section 248.`
obj_root_law_sections_251_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_252:
  sectionId (49178)
  sectionNo (252)
  orderNo 256
  title `Appeal to Tribunal.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_252_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_252_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=49178&sectionno=252&orderno=256&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_252_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any person aggrieved by an order of the Registrar, notifying a`
  line `company as dissolved under section 248, may file an appeal to the Tribunal within a period of three years`
  line `from the date of the order of the Registrar and if the Tribunal is of the opinion that the removal of the`
  line `name of the company from the register of companies is not justified in view of the absence of any of the`
  line `grounds on which the order was passed by the Registrar, it may order restoration of the name of the`
  line `company in the register of companies:`
  line
  line `Provided that before passing any order under this section, the Tribunal shall give a reasonable`
  line `opportunity of making representations and of being heard to the Registrar, the company and all the`
  line `persons concerned :`
  line
  line `Provided further that if the Registrar is satisfied, that the name of the company has been struck off`
  line `from the register of companies either inadvertently or on the basis of incorrect information furnished by`
  line `the company or its directors, which requires restoration in the register of companies, he may within a`
  line `period of three years from the date of passing of the order dissolving the company under section 248, file`
  line `an application before the Tribunal seeking restoration of name of such company.`
  line
  line `(2) A copy of the order passed by the Tribunal shall be filed by the company with the Registrar within`
  line `thirty days from the date of the order and on receipt of the order, the Registrar shall cause the name of the`
  line `company to be restored in the register of companies and shall issue a fresh certificate of incorporation.`
  line
  line `(3) If a company, or any member or creditor or workman thereof feels aggrieved by the company`
  line `having its name struck off from the register of companies, the Tribunal on an application made by the`
  line `company, member, creditor or workman before the expiry of twenty years from the publication in the`
  line `Official Gazette of the notice under sub-section (5) of section 248 may, if satisfied that the company was,`
  line `at the time of its name being struck off, carrying on business or in operation or otherwise it is just that the`
  line `name of the company be restored to the register of companies, order the name of the company to be`
  line `restored to the register of companies, and the Tribunal may, by the order, give such other directions and`
  line `make such provisions as deemed just for placing the company and all other persons in the same position`
  line `as nearly as may be as if the name of the company had not been struck off from the register of companies.`
obj_root_law_sections_252_footnotes:
  string
  line
