obj_root_law_sections_270:
  sectionId (49196)
  sectionNo (270)
  orderNo 274
  title `Modes of winding up.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_270_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 31 of 2016, s. 255 and the Eleventh Schedule, for section 270 (w.e.f. 15-11-2016).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=49196&sectionno=270&orderno=274&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_270_content:
  string
  line `^1[270.Winding up by Tribunal.-- The provisions of Part I shall apply to the winding up of a`
  line `company by the Tribunal under this Act.]`
obj_root_law_sections_271:
  sectionId (49197)
  sectionNo (271)
  orderNo 275
  title `Circumstances in which company may be wound up by Tribunal.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_271_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by s. 255 and the Eleventh Schedule, ibid., for section 271 (w.e.f. 15-11-2016).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=49197&sectionno=271&orderno=275&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_271_content:
  string
  line `^1[271. Circumstances in which company may be wound up by Tribunal-- A company may, on a`
  line `petition under section 272, be wound up by the Tribunal,--`
  line
  line `(a) if the company has, by special resolution, resolved that the company be wound up by the`
  line Tribunal;
  line
  line `(b) if the company has acted against the interests of the sovereignty and integrity of India, the`
  line `security of the State, friendly relations with foreign States, public order, decency or morality;`
  line
  line `(c) if on an application made by the Registrar or any other person authorised by the Central`
  line `Government by notification under this Act, the Tribunal is of the opinion that the affairs of the`
  line `company have been conducted in a fraudulent manner or the company was formed for fraudulent and`
  line `unlawful purpose or the persons concerned in the formation or management of its affairs have been`
  line `guilty of fraud, misfeasance or misconduct in connection therewith and that it is proper that the`
  line `company be wound up;`
  line
  line `(d) if the company has made a default in filing with the Registrar its financial statements or`
  line `annual returns for immediately preceding five consecutive financial years; or`
  line
  line `(e) if the Tribunal is of the opinion that it is just and equitable that the company should be wound up.]`
obj_root_law_sections_272:
  sectionId (49198)
  sectionNo (272)
  orderNo 276
  title `Petition for winding up.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_272_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_272_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=49198&sectionno=272&orderno=276&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_272_content:
  string
  line `^1[272. Petition for winding up.-- (1) Subject to the provisions of this section, a petition to the`
  line `Tribunal for the winding up of a company shall be presented by--`
  line
  line `(a) the company;`
  line
  line `(b) any contributory or contributories;`
  line
  line `(c) all or any of the persons specified in clauses (a) and (b);`
  line
  line `(d) the Registrar;`
  line
  line `(e) any person authorised by the Central Government in that behalf; or`
  line
  line `(f) in a case falling under clause (b) of section 271, by the Central Government or a State`
  line Government.
  line
  line `(2) A contributory shall be entitled to present a petition for the winding up of a company,`
  line `notwithstanding that he may be the holder of fully paid-up shares, or that the company may have no assets`
  line `at all or may have no surplus assets left for distribution among the shareholders after the satisfaction of its`
  line `liabilities, and shares in respect of which he is a contributory or some of them were either originally`
  line `allotted to him or have been held by him, and registered in his name, for at least six months during the`
  line `eighteen months immediately before the commencement of the winding up or have devolved on him`
  line `through the death of a former holder.`
  line
  line `(3) The Registrar shall be entitled to present a petition for winding up under section 271, except on`
  line `the grounds specified in clause (a)`
  line `^2[of that section]:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Registrar shall obtain the previous sanction of the Central Government to the`
  line `presentation of a petition:`
  line
  line `Provided further that the Central Government shall not accord its sanction unless the company has`
  line `been given a reasonable opportunity of making representations.`
  line
  line `(4) A petition presented by the company for winding up before the Tribunal shall be admitted only if`
  line `accompanied by a statement of affairs in such form and in such manner as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(5) A copy of the petition made under this section shall also be filed with the Registrar and the`
  line `Registrar shall, without prejudice to any other provisions, submit his views to the Tribunal within sixty`
  line `days of receipt of such petition.]`
obj_root_law_sections_272_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by s. 255 and the Eleventh Schedule, ibid., for section 272 (w.e.f. 15-11-2016).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 22 of 2019, s. 37, for "or clause (e) of that sub-section" (w.e.f. 15-8-2019).`
obj_root_law_sections_273:
  sectionId (49199)
  sectionNo (273)
  orderNo 277
  title `Powers of Tribunal.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_273_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_273_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=49199&sectionno=273&orderno=277&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_273_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Tribunal may, on receipt of a petition for winding up under`
  line `section 272 pass any of the following orders, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) dismiss it, with or without costs;`
  line
  line `(b) make any interim order as it thinks fit;`
  line
  line `(c) appoint a provisional liquidator of the company till the making of a winding up order;`
  line
  line `(d) make an order for the winding up of the company with or without costs; or`
  line
  line `(e) any other order as it thinks fit:`
  line
  line `Provided that an order under this sub-section shall be made within ninety days from the date of`
  line `presentation of the petition:`
  line
  line `Provided further that before appointing a provisional liquidator under clause (c), the Tribunal shall`
  line `give notice to the company and afford a reasonable opportunity to it to make its representations, if any,`
  line `unless for special reasons to be recorded in writing, the Tribunal thinks fit to dispense with such notice:`
  line
  line `Provided also that the Tribunal shall not refuse to make a winding up order on the ground only that`
  line `the assets of the company have been mortgaged for an amount equal to or in excess of those assets, or that`
  line `the company has no assets.`
  line
  line `(2) Where a petition is presented on the ground that it is just and equitable that the company should be`
  line `wound up, the Tribunal may refuse to make an order of winding up, if it is of the opinion that some other`
  line `remedy is available to the petitioners and that they are acting unreasonably in seeking to have the`
  line `company wound up instead of pursuing the other remedy.`
obj_root_law_sections_273_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_274:
  sectionId (49200)
  sectionNo (274)
  orderNo 278
  title `Directions for filing statement of affairs`
  content obj_root_law_sections_274_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_274_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=49200&sectionno=274&orderno=278&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_274_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where a petition for winding up is filed before`
  line `the Tribunal by any person other than the company, the Tribunal shall, if satisfied that a prima facie case`
  line `for winding up of the company is made out, by an order direct the company to file its objections along`
  line `with a statement of its affairs within thirty days of the order in such form and in such manner as may be`
  line `prescribed:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Tribunal may allow a further period of thirty days in a situation of contingency or`
  line `special circumstances:`
  line
  line `Provided further that the Tribunal may direct the petitioner to deposit such security for costs as it may`
  line `consider reasonable as a precondition to issue directions to the company.`
  line
  line `(2) A company, which fails to file the statement of affairs as referred to in sub-section (1), shall`
  line `forfeit the right to oppose the petition and such directors and officers of the company as found responsible`
  line `for such non-compliance, shall be liable for punishment under sub-section (4).`
  line
  line `(3) The directors and other officers of the company, in respect of which an order for winding up is`
  line `passed by the Tribunal under clause (d) of sub-section (1) of section 273, shall, within a period of thirty`
  line `days of such order, submit, at the cost of the company, the books of account of the company completed`
  line `and audited up to the date of the order, to such liquidator and in the manner specified by the Tribunal.`
  line
  line `(4) If any director or officer of the company contravenes the provisions of this section, the director or`
  line `the officer of the company who is in default shall be punishable with imprisonment for a term which may`
  line `extend to six months or with fine which shall not be less than twenty-five thousand rupees but which may`
  line `extend to five lakh rupees, or with both.`
  line
  line `(5) The complaint may be filed in this behalf before the Special Court by Registrar, provisional`
  line `liquidator, Company Liquidator or any person authorised by the Tribunal.`
obj_root_law_sections_274_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_275:
  sectionId (49201)
  sectionNo (275)
  orderNo 279
  title `Company Liquidators and their appointments`
  content obj_root_law_sections_275_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_275_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=49201&sectionno=275&orderno=279&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_275_content:
  string
  line `(1) For the purposes of winding up of a`
  line `company by the Tribunal, the Tribunal at the time of the passing of the order of winding up, shall appoint`
  line `an Official Liquidator or a liquidator from the panel maintained under sub-section (2) as the Company`
  line Liquidator.
  line
  line `^1[(2) The provisional liquidator or the Company Liquidator, as the case may, shall be appointed by`
  line `the Tribunal from amongst the insolvency professionals registered under the Insolvency and Bankruptcy`
  line `Code, 2016 (31 of 2016);]`
  line
  line `(3) Where a provisional liquidator is appointed by the Tribunal, the Tribunal may limit and restrict his`
  line `powers by the order appointing him or it or by a subsequent order, but otherwise he shall have the same`
  line `powers as a liquidator.`
  line
  line `^2* * * * *`
  line
  line `(5) The terms and conditions of appointment of a provisional liquidator or Company Liquidator and`
  line `the fee payable to him or it shall be specified by the Tribunal on the basis of task required to be`
  line `performed, experience, qualification of such liquidator and size of the company.`
  line
  line `(6) On appointment as provisional liquidator or Company Liquidator, as the case may be, such`
  line `liquidator shall file a declaration within seven days from the date of appointment in the prescribed form`
  line `disclosing conflict of interest or lack of independence in respect of his appointment, if any, with the`
  line `Tribunal and such obligation shall continue throughout the term of his appointment.`
  line
  line `(7) While passing a winding up order, the Tribunal may appoint a provisional liquidator, if any,`
  line `appointed under clause (c) of sub-section (1) of section 273, as the Company Liquidator for the conduct`
  line `of the proceedings for the winding up of the company.`
obj_root_law_sections_275_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 31 of 2016, s. 255 and the Eleventh Schedule, for sub-section (2) (w.e.f. 15-11-2016).`
  line
  line `2. Sub-section (4) omitted by s. 255 and the Eleventh Schedule, ibid. (w.e.f. 15-11-2016).`
obj_root_law_sections_276:
  sectionId (49202)
  sectionNo (276)
  orderNo 280
  title `Removal and replacement of liquidator`
  content obj_root_law_sections_276_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_276_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=49202&sectionno=276&orderno=280&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_276_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Tribunal may, on a reasonable cause being`
  line `shown and for reasons to be recorded in writing, remove the provisional liquidator or the Company`
  line `Liquidator, as the case may be, as liquidator of the company on any of the following grounds, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) misconduct;`
  line
  line `(b) fraud or misfeasance;`
  line
  line `(c) professional incompetence or failure to exercise due care and diligence in performance of the`
  line `powers and functions;`
  line
  line `(d) inability to act as provisional liquidator or as the case may be, Company Liquidator;`
  line
  line `(e) conflict of interest or lack of independence during the term of his appointment that would`
  line `justify removal.`
  line
  line `(2) In the event of death, resignation or removal of the provisional liquidator or as the case may be,`
  line `Company Liquidator, the Tribunal may transfer the work assigned to him or it to another Company`
  line `Liquidator for reasons to be recorded in writing.`
  line
  line `(3) Where the Tribunal is of the opinion that any liquidator is responsible for causing any loss or`
  line `damage to the company due to fraud or misfeasance or failure to exercise due care and diligence in the`
  line `performance of his or its powers and functions, the Tribunal may recover or cause to be recovered such`
  line `loss or damage from the liquidator and pass such other orders as it may think fit.`
  line
  line `(4) The Tribunal shall, before passing any order under this section, provide a reasonable opportunity`
  line `of being heard to the provisional liquidator or, as the case may be, Company Liquidator.`
obj_root_law_sections_276_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_277:
  sectionId (49203)
  sectionNo (277)
  orderNo 281
  title `Intimation to Company Liquidator, provisional liquidator and Registrar`
  content obj_root_law_sections_277_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_277_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=49203&sectionno=277&orderno=281&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_277_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where the`
  line `Tribunal makes an order for appointment of provisional liquidator or for the winding up of a company, it`
  line `shall, within a period not exceeding seven days from the date of passing of the order, cause intimation`
  line `thereof to be sent to the Company Liquidator or provisional liquidator, as the case may be, and the`
  line Registrar.
  line
  line `(2) On receipt of the copy of order of appointment of provisional liquidator or winding up order, the`
  line `Registrar shall make an endorsement to that effect in his records relating to the company and notify in the`
  line `Official Gazette that such an order has been made and in the case of a listed company, the Registrar shall`
  line `intimate about such appointment or order, as the case may be, to the stock exchange or exchanges where`
  line `the securities of the company are listed.`
  line
  line `(3) The winding up order shall be deemed to be a notice of discharge to the officers, employees and`
  line `workmen of the company, except when the business of the company is continued.`
  line
  line `(4) Within three weeks from the date of passing of winding up order, the Company Liquidator shall`
  line `make an application to the Tribunal for constitution of a winding up committee to assist and monitor the`
  line `progress of liquidation proceedings by the Company Liquidator in carrying out the function as provided`
  line `in sub-section (5) and such winding up committee shall comprise of the following persons, namely:--`
  line
  line `(i) Official Liquidator attached to the Tribunal;`
  line
  line `(ii) nominee of secured creditors; and`
  line
  line `(iii) a professional nominated by the Tribunal.`
  line
  line `(5) The Company Liquidator shall be the convener of the meetings of the winding up committee`
  line `which shall assist and monitor the liquidation proceedings in following areas of liquidation functions,`
  line `namely:--`
  line
  line `(i) taking over assets;`
  line
  line `(ii) examination of the statement of affairs;`
  line
  line `(iii) recovery of property, cash or any other assets of the company including benefits derived`
  line therefrom;
  line
  line `(iv) review of audit reports and accounts of the company;`
  line
  line `(v) sale of assets;`
  line
  line `(vi) finalisation of list of creditors and contributories;`
  line
  line `(vii) compromise, abandonment and settlement of claims;`
  line
  line `(viii) payment of dividends, if any; and`
  line
  line `(ix) any other function, as the Tribunal may direct from time to time.`
  line
  line `(6) The Company Liquidator shall place before the Tribunal a report along with minutes of the`
  line `meetings of the committee on monthly basis duly signed by the members present in the meeting for`
  line `consideration till the final report for dissolution of the company is submitted before the Tribunal.`
  line
  line `(7) The Company Liquidator shall prepare the draft final report for consideration and approval of the`
  line `winding up committee.`
  line
  line `(8) The final report so approved by the winding up committee shall be submitted by the Company`
  line `Liquidator before the Tribunal for passing of a dissolution order in respect of the company.`
obj_root_law_sections_277_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_278:
  sectionId (49204)
  sectionNo (278)
  orderNo 282
  title `Effect of winding up order.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_278_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_278_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=49204&sectionno=278&orderno=282&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_278_content:
  string
  line `The order for the winding up of a company shall operate in`
  line `favour of all the creditors and all contributories of the company as if it had been made out on the joint`
  line `petition of creditors and contributories.`
obj_root_law_sections_278_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_279:
  sectionId (49205)
  sectionNo (279)
  orderNo 283
  title `Stay of suits, etc., on winding up order.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_279_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_279_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=49205&sectionno=279&orderno=283&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_279_content:
  string
  line `(1) When a winding up order has been passed or a`
  line `provisional liquidator has been appointed, no suit or other legal proceeding shall be commenced, or if`
  line `pending at the date of the winding up order, shall be proceeded with, by or against the company, except`
  line `with the leave of the Tribunal and subject to such terms as the Tribunal may impose:`
  line
  line `Provided that any application to the Tribunal seeking leave under this section shall be disposed of by`
  line `the Tribunal within sixty days.`
  line
  line `(2) Nothing in sub-section (1) shall apply to any proceeding pending in appeal before the Supreme`
  line `Court or a High Court.`
obj_root_law_sections_279_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_280:
  sectionId (49206)
  sectionNo (280)
  orderNo 284
  title `Jurisdiction of Tribunal.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_280_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 31 of 2016, s. 255 and the Eleventh Schedule, for section 280 (w.e.f. 15-11-2016)`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=49206&sectionno=280&orderno=284&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_280_content:
  string
  line `^1[280. Jurisdiction of Tribunal.-- The Tribunal shall, notwithstanding anything contained in any`
  line `other law for the time being in force, have jurisdiction to entertain, or dispose of,--`
  line
  line `(a) any suit or proceeding by or against the company;`
  line
  line `(b) any claim made by or against the company, including claims by or against any of its branches`
  line `in India;`
  line
  line `(c) any application made under section 233;`
  line
  line `(d) any question of priorities or any other question whatsoever, whether of law or facts, including`
  line `those relating to assets, business, actions, rights, entitlements, privileges, benefits, duties,`
  line `responsibilities, obligations or in any matter arising out of, or in relation to winding up of the`
  line company,
  line
  line `whether such suit or proceeding has been instituted, or is instituted, or such claim or question has arisen`
  line `or arises or such application has been made or is made or such scheme has been submitted, or is`
  line `submitted, before or after the order for the winding up of the company is made.]`
obj_root_law_sections_281:
  sectionId (49207)
  sectionNo (281)
  orderNo 285
  title `Submission of report by Company Liquidator`
  content obj_root_law_sections_281_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_281_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=49207&sectionno=281&orderno=285&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_281_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where the Tribunal has made a winding`
  line `up order or appointed a Company Liquidator, such liquidator shall, within sixty days from the order,`
  line `submit to the Tribunal, a report containing the following particulars, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the nature and details of the assets of the company including their location and value, stating`
  line `separately the cash balance in hand and in the bank, if any, and the negotiable securities, if any, held`
  line `by the company:`
  line
  line `Provided that the valuation of the assets shall be obtained from registered valuers for this`
  line purpose;
  line
  line `(b) amount of capital issued, subscribed and paid-up;`
  line
  line `(c) the existing and contingent liabilities of the company including names, addresses and`
  line `occupations of its creditors, stating separately the amount of secured and unsecured debts, and in the`
  line `case of secured debts, particulars of the securities given, whether by the company or an officer`
  line `thereof, their value and the dates on which they were given;`
  line
  line `(d) the debts due to the company and the names, addresses and occupations of the persons from`
  line `whom they are due and the amount likely to be realised on account thereof;`
  line
  line `(e) guarantees, if any, extended by the company;`
  line
  line `(f) list of contributories and dues, if any, payable by them and details of any unpaid call;`
  line
  line `(g) details of trade marks and intellectual properties, if any, owned by the company;`
  line
  line `(h) details of subsisting contracts, joint ventures and collaborations, if any;`
  line
  line `(i) details of holding and subsidiary companies, if any;`
  line
  line `(j) details of legal cases filed by or against the company; and`
  line
  line `(k) any other information which the Tribunal may direct or the Company Liquidator may consider`
  line `necessary to include.`
  line
  line `(2) The Company Liquidator shall include in his report the manner in which the company was`
  line `promoted or formed and whether in his opinion any fraud has been committed by any person in its`
  line `promotion or formation or by any officer of the company in relation to the company since the formation`
  line `thereof and any other matters which, in his opinion, it is desirable to bring to the notice of the Tribunal.`
  line
  line `(3) The Company Liquidator shall also make a report on the viability of the business of the company`
  line `or the steps which, in his opinion, are necessary for maximising the value of the assets of the company.`
  line
  line `(4) The Company Liquidator may also, if he thinks fit, make any further report or reports.`
  line
  line `(5) Any person describing himself in writing to be a creditor or a contributory of the company shall`
  line `be entitled by himself or by his agent at all reasonable times to inspect the report submitted in accordance`
  line `with this section and take copies thereof or extracts therefrom on payment of the prescribed fees.`
obj_root_law_sections_281_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_282:
  sectionId (49208)
  sectionNo (282)
  orderNo 286
  title `Directions of Tribunal on report of Company Liquidator.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_282_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_282_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=49208&sectionno=282&orderno=286&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_282_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Tribunal shall, on`
  line `consideration of the report of the Company Liquidator, fix a time limit within which the entire`
  line `proceedings shall be completed and the company be dissolved:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Tribunal may, if it is of the opinion, at any stage of the proceedings, or on`
  line `examination of the reports submitted to it by the Company Liquidator and after hearing the Company`
  line `Liquidator, creditors or contributories or any other interested person, that it will not be advantageous or`
  line `economical to continue the proceedings, revise the time limit within which the entire proceedings shall be`
  line `completed and the company be dissolved.`
  line
  line `(2) The Tribunal may, on examination of the reports submitted to it by the Company Liquidator and`
  line `after hearing the Company Liquidator, creditors or contributories or any other interested person, order`
  line `sale of the company as a going concern or its assets or part thereof:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Tribunal may, where it considers fit, appoint a sale committee comprising such`
  line `creditors, promoters and officers of the company as the Tribunal may decide to assist the Company`
  line `Liquidator in sale under this sub-section.`
  line
  line `(3) Where a report is received from the Company Liquidator or the Central Government or any`
  line `person that a fraud has been committed in respect of the company, the Tribunal shall, without prejudice to`
  line `the process of winding up, order for investigation under section 210, and on consideration of the report of`
  line `such investigation it may pass order and give directions under sections 339 to 342 or direct the Company`
  line `Liquidator to file a criminal complaint against persons who were involved in the commission of fraud.`
  line
  line `(4) The Tribunal may order for taking such steps and measures, as may be necessary, to protect,`
  line `preserve or enhance the value of the assets of the company.`
  line
  line `(5) The Tribunal may pass such other order or give such other directions as it considers fit.`
obj_root_law_sections_282_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_283:
  sectionId (49209)
  sectionNo (283)
  orderNo 287
  title `Custody of company‘s properties`
  content obj_root_law_sections_283_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_283_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=49209&sectionno=283&orderno=287&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_283_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where a winding up order has been made or where a`
  line `provisional liquidator has been appointed, the Company Liquidator or the provisional liquidator, as the`
  line `case may be, shall, on the order of the Tribunal, forthwith take into his or its custody or control all the`
  line `property, effects and actionable claims to which the company is or appears to be entitled to and take such`
  line `steps and measures, as may be necessary, to protect and preserve the properties of the company.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (1), all the property and effects of the company`
  line `shall be deemed to be in the custody of the Tribunal from the date of the order for the winding up of the`
  line company.
  line
  line `(3) On an application by the Company Liquidator or otherwise, the Tribunal may, at any time after`
  line `the making of a winding up order, require any contributory for the time being on the list of contributories,`
  line `and any trustee, receiver, banker, agent, officer or other employee of the company, to pay, deliver,`
  line `surrender or transfer forthwith, or within such time as the Tribunal directs, to the Company Liquidator,`
  line `any money, property or books and papers in his custody or under his control to which the company is or`
  line `appears to be entitled.`
obj_root_law_sections_283_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_284:
  sectionId (49210)
  sectionNo (284)
  orderNo 288
  title `Promoters, directors, etc., to cooperate with Company Liquidator.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_284_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 29 of 2020, s. 46, for sub-section (2) (w.e.f. 21-12-2020).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=49210&sectionno=284&orderno=288&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_284_content:
  string
  line `(1) The promoters,`
  line `directors, officers and employees, who are or have been in employment of the company or acting or`
  line `associated with the company shall extend full cooperation to the Company Liquidator in discharge of his`
  line `functions and duties.`
  line
  line `^1[(2) If any person required to assist or cooperate with the Company Liquidator under sub-section (1)`
  line `does not assist or cooperate, the Company Liquidator may make an application to the Tribunal for`
  line `necessary directions.`
  line
  line `(3) On receiving an application under sub-section (2), the Tribunal shall, by an order, direct the`
  line `person required to assist or cooperate with the Company Liquidator to comply with the instructions of the`
  line `Company Liquidator and to cooperate with him in discharging his functions and duties.]`
obj_root_law_sections_285:
  sectionId (49211)
  sectionNo (285)
  orderNo 289
  title `Settlement of list of contributories and application of assets.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_285_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_285_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=49211&sectionno=285&orderno=289&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_285_content:
  string
  line `(1) As soon as may be after`
  line `the passing of a winding up order by the Tribunal, the Tribunal shall settle a list of contributories, cause`
  line `rectification of register of members in all cases where rectification is required in pursuance of this Act`
  line `and shall cause the assets of the company to be applied for the discharge of its liability:`
  line
  line `Provided that where it appears to the Tribunal that it would not be necessary to make calls on or`
  line `adjust the rights of contributories, the Tribunal may dispense with the settlement of a list of`
  line contributories.
  line
  line `(2) In settling the list of contributories, the Tribunal shall distinguish between those who are`
  line `contributories in their own right and those who are contributories as being representatives of, or liable for`
  line `the debts of, others.`
  line
  line `(3) While settling the list of contributories, the Tribunal shall include every person, who is or has`
  line `been a member, who shall be liable to contribute to the assets of the company an amount sufficient for`
  line `payment of the debts and liabilities and the costs, charges and expenses of winding up, and for the`
  line `adjustment of the rights of the contributories among themselves, subject to the following conditions,`
  line `namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) a person who has been a member shall not be liable to contribute if he has ceased to be a`
  line `member for the preceding one year or more before the commencement of the winding up;`
  line
  line `(b) a person who has been a member shall not be liable to contribute in respect of any debt or`
  line `liability of the company contracted after he ceased to be a member;`
  line
  line `(c) no person who has been a member shall be liable to contribute unless it appears to the`
  line `Tribunal that the present members are unable to satisfy the contributions required to be made by them`
  line `in pursuance of this Act;`
  line
  line `(d) in the case of a company limited by shares, no contribution shall be required from any person,`
  line `who is or has been a member exceeding the amount, if any, unpaid on the shares in respect of which`
  line `he is liable as such member;`
  line
  line `(e) in the case of a company limited by guarantee, no contribution shall be required from any`
  line `person, who is or has been a member exceeding the amount undertaken to be contributed by him to`
  line `the assets of the company in the event of its being wound up but if the company has a share capital,`
  line `such member shall be liable to contribute to the extent of any sum unpaid on any shares held by him`
  line `as if the company were a company limited by shares.`
obj_root_law_sections_285_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_286:
  sectionId (49212)
  sectionNo (286)
  orderNo 290
  title `Obligations of directors and managers.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_286_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_286_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=49212&sectionno=286&orderno=290&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_286_content:
  string
  line `In the case of a limited company, any person who is`
  line `or has been a director or manager, whose liability is unlimited under the provisions of this Act, shall, in`
  line `addition to his liability, if any, to contribute as an ordinary member, be liable to make a further`
  line `contribution as if he were at the commencement of winding up, a member of an unlimited company:`
  line
  line `Provided that--`
  line
  line `(a) a person who has been a director or manager shall not be liable to make such further`
  line `contribution, if he has ceased to hold office for a year or upwards before the commencement of the`
  line `winding up;`
  line
  line `(b) a person who has been a director or manager shall not be liable to make such further`
  line `contribution in respect of any debt or liability of the company contracted after he ceased to hold`
  line office;
  line
  line `(c) subject to the articles of the company, a director or manager shall not be liable to make such`
  line `further contribution unless the Tribunal deems it necessary to require the contribution in order to`
  line `satisfy the debts and liabilities of the company, and the costs, charges and expenses of the winding`
  line up.
obj_root_law_sections_286_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_287:
  sectionId (49213)
  sectionNo (287)
  orderNo 291
  title `Advisory Committee.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_287_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_287_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=49213&sectionno=287&orderno=291&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_287_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Tribunal may, while passing an order of winding up of a`
  line `company, direct that there shall be, an advisory committee to advise the Company Liquidator and to`
  line `report to the Tribunal on such matters as the Tribunal may direct.`
  line
  line `(2) The advisory committee appointed by the Tribunal shall consist of not more than twelve members,`
  line `being creditors and contributories of the company or such other persons in such proportion as the Tribunal`
  line `may, keeping in view the circumstances of the company under liquidation, direct.`
  line
  line `(3) The Company Liquidator shall convene a meeting of creditors and contributories, as ascertained`
  line `from the books and documents, of the company within thirty days from the date of order of winding up`
  line `for enabling the Tribunal to determine the persons who may be members of the advisory committee.`
  line
  line `(4) The advisory committee shall have the right to inspect the books of account and other documents,`
  line `assets and properties of the company under liquidation at a reasonable time.`
  line
  line `(5) The provisions relating to the convening of the meetings, the procedure to be followed thereat and`
  line `other matters relating to conduct of business by the advisory committee shall be such as may be`
  line prescribed.
  line
  line `(6) The meeting of advisory committee shall be chaired by the Company Liquidator.`
obj_root_law_sections_287_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_288:
  sectionId (49214)
  sectionNo (288)
  orderNo 292
  title `Submission of periodical reports to Tribunal.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_288_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_288_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=49214&sectionno=288&orderno=292&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_288_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Company Liquidator shall make`
  line `periodical reports to the Tribunal and in any case make a report at the end of each quarter with respect to`
  line `the progress of the winding up of the company in such form and manner as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(2) The Tribunal may, on an application by the Company Liquidator, review the orders made by it`
  line `and make such modifications as it thinks fit.`
obj_root_law_sections_288_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_289:
  sectionId (49215)
  sectionNo (289)
  orderNo 293
  title `Power of Tribunal on application for stay of winding up.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_289_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_289_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=49215&sectionno=289&orderno=293&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_289_content:
  string
  line `[Power of Tribunal on application for stay of winding up.] Omitted by the Insolvency and`
  line `Bankruptcy Code, 2016 (31 of 2016), s. 255 and the Eleventh Schedule (w.e.f. 15-11-2016).`
obj_root_law_sections_289_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_290:
  sectionId (49216)
  sectionNo (290)
  orderNo 294
  title `Powers and duties of Company Liquidator.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_290_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_290_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=49216&sectionno=290&orderno=294&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_290_content:
  string
  line `(1) Subject to directions by the Tribunal, if any,`
  line `in this regard, the Company Liquidator, in a winding up of a company by the Tribunal, shall have the`
  line power--
  line
  line `(a) to carry on the business of the company so far as may be necessary for the beneficial winding`
  line `up of the company;`
  line
  line `(b) to do all acts and to execute, in the name and on behalf of the company, all deeds, receipts and`
  line `other documents, and for that purpose, to use, when necessary, the companys seal;`
  line
  line `(c) to sell the immovable and movable property and actionable claims of the company by public`
  line `auction or private contract, with power to transfer such property to any person or body corporate, or`
  line `to sell the same in parcels;`
  line
  line `(d) to sell the whole of the undertaking of the company as a going concern;`
  line
  line `(e) to raise any money required on the security of the assets of the company;`
  line
  line `(f) to institute or defend any suit, prosecution or other legal proceeding, civil or criminal, in the`
  line `name and on behalf of the company;`
  line
  line `(g) to invite and settle claim of creditors, employees or any other claimant and distribute sale`
  line `proceeds in accordance with priorities established under this Act;`
  line
  line `(h) to inspect the records and returns of the company on the files of the Registrar or any other`
  line authority;
  line
  line `(i) to prove rank and claim in the insolvency of any contributory for any balance against his`
  line `estate, and to receive dividends in the insolvency, in respect of that balance, as a separate debt due`
  line `from the insolvent, and rateably with the other separate creditors;`
  line
  line `(j) to draw, accept, make and endorse any negotiable instruments including cheque, bill of`
  line `exchange, hundi or promissory note in the name and on behalf of the company, with the same effect`
  line `with respect to the liability of the company as if such instruments had been drawn, accepted, made or`
  line `endorsed by or on behalf of the company in the course of its business;`
  line
  line `(k) to take out, in his official name, letters of administration to any deceased contributory, and to`
  line `do in his official name any other act necessary for obtaining payment of any money due from a`
  line `contributory or his estate which cannot be conveniently done in the name of the company, and in all`
  line `such cases, the money due shall, for the purpose of enabling the Company Liquidator to take out the`
  line `letters of administration or recover the money, be deemed to be due to the Company Liquidator`
  line himself;
  line
  line `(l) to obtain any professional assistance from any person or appoint any professional, in discharge`
  line `of his duties, obligations and responsibilities and for protection of the assets of the company, appoint`
  line `an agent to do any business which the Company Liquidator is unable to do himself;`
  line
  line `(m) to take all such actions, steps, or to sign, execute and verify any paper, deed, document,`
  line `application, petition, affidavit, bond or instrument as may be necessary,--`
  line
  line `(i) for winding up of the company;`
  line
  line `(ii) for distribution of assets;`
  line
  line `(iii) in discharge of his duties and obligations and functions as Company Liquidator; and`
  line
  line `(n) to apply to the Tribunal for such orders or directions as may be necessary for the winding up`
  line `of the company.`
  line
  line `(2) The exercise of powers by the Company Liquidator under sub-section (1) shall be subject to the`
  line `overall control of the Tribunal.`
  line
  line `(3) Notwithstanding the provisions of sub-section (1), the Company Liquidator shall perform such`
  line `other duties as the Tribunal may specify in this behalf.`
obj_root_law_sections_290_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_291:
  sectionId (49217)
  sectionNo (291)
  orderNo 295
  title `Provision for professional assistance to Company Liquidator`
  content obj_root_law_sections_291_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_291_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=49217&sectionno=291&orderno=295&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_291_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Company`
  line `Liquidator may, with the sanction of the Tribunal, appoint one or more chartered accountants or company`
  line `secretaries or cost accountants or legal practitioners or such other professionals on such terms and`
  line `conditions, as may be necessary, to assist him in the performance of his duties and functions under this`
  line Act.
  line
  line `(2) Any person appointed under this section shall disclose forthwith to the Tribunal in the prescribed`
  line `form any conflict of interest or lack of independence in respect of his appointment.`
obj_root_law_sections_291_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_292:
  sectionId (49218)
  sectionNo (292)
  orderNo 296
  title `Exercise and control of Company Liquidator‘s powers.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_292_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_292_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=49218&sectionno=292&orderno=296&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_292_content:
  string
  line `(1) Subject to the provisions of this`
  line `Act, the Company Liquidator shall, in the administration of the assets of the company and the distribution`
  line `thereof among its creditors, have regard to any directions which may be given by the resolution of the`
  line `creditors or contributories at any general meeting or by the advisory committee.`
  line
  line `(2) Any directions given by the creditors or contributories at any general meeting shall, in case of`
  line `conflict, be deemed to override any directions given by the advisory committee.`
  line
  line `(3) The Company Liquidator--`
  line
  line `(a) may summon meetings of the creditors or contributories, whenever he thinks fit, for the`
  line `purpose of ascertaining their wishes; and`
  line
  line `(b) shall summon such meetings at such times, as the creditors or contributories, as the case may`
  line `be, may, by resolution, direct, or whenever requested in writing to do so by not less than one-tenth in`
  line `value of the creditors or contributories, as the case may be.`
  line
  line `(4) Any person aggrieved by any act or decision of the Company Liquidator may apply to the`
  line `Tribunal, and the Tribunal may confirm, reverse or modify the act or decision complained of and make`
  line `such further order as it thinks just and proper in the circumstances.`
obj_root_law_sections_292_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_293:
  sectionId (49219)
  sectionNo (293)
  orderNo 297
  title `Books to be kept by Company Liquidator`
  content obj_root_law_sections_293_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_293_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=49219&sectionno=293&orderno=297&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_293_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Company Liquidator shall keep proper`
  line `books in such manner, as may be prescribed, in which he shall cause entries or minutes to be made of`
  line `proceedings at meetings and of such other matters as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(2) Any creditor or contributory may, subject to the control of the Tribunal, inspect any such books,`
  line `personally or through his agent.`
obj_root_law_sections_293_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_294:
  sectionId (49220)
  sectionNo (294)
  orderNo 298
  title `Audit of Company Liquidator‘s accounts.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_294_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_294_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=49220&sectionno=294&orderno=298&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_294_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Company Liquidator shall maintain`
  line `proper and regular books of account including accounts of receipts and payments made by him in such`
  line `form and manner as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(2) The Company Liquidator shall, at such times as may be prescribed but not less than twice in each`
  line `year during his tenure of office, present to the Tribunal an account of the receipts and payments as such`
  line `liquidator in the prescribed form in duplicate, which shall be verified by a declaration in such form and`
  line `manner as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(3) The Tribunal shall cause the accounts to be audited in such manner as it thinks fit, and for the`
  line `purpose of the audit, the Company Liquidator shall furnish to the Tribunal with such vouchers and`
  line `information as the Tribunal may require, and the Tribunal may, at any time, require the production of, and`
  line `inspect, any books of account kept by the Company Liquidator.`
  line
  line `(4) When the accounts of the company have been audited, one copy thereof shall be filed by the`
  line `Company Liquidator with the Tribunal, and the other copy shall be delivered to the Registrar which shall`
  line `be open to inspection by any creditor, contributory or person interested.`
  line
  line `(5) Where an account referred to in sub-section (4) relates to a Government company, the Company`
  line `Liquidator shall forward a copy thereof--`
  line
  line `(a) to the Central Government, if that Government is a member of the Government company; or`
  line
  line `(b) to any State Government, if that Government is a member of the Government company; or`
  line
  line `(c) to the Central Government and any State Government, if both the Governments are members`
  line `of the Government company.`
  line
  line `(6) The Company Liquidator shall cause the accounts when audited, or a summary thereof, to be`
  line `printed, and shall send a printed copy of the accounts or summary thereof by post to every creditor and`
  line `every contributory:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Tribunal may dispense with the compliance of the provisions of this sub-section in`
  line `any case it deems fit.`
obj_root_law_sections_294_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_295:
  sectionId (49221)
  sectionNo (295)
  orderNo 299
  title `Payment of debts by contributory and extent of set-off.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_295_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_295_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=49221&sectionno=295&orderno=299&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_295_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Tribunal may, at any time`
  line `after passing of a winding up order, pass an order requiring any contributory for the time being on the list`
  line `of contributories to pay, in the manner directed by the order, any money due to the company, from him or`
  line `from the estate of the person whom he represents, exclusive of any money payable by him or the estate by`
  line `virtue of any call in pursuance of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) The Tribunal, in making an order, under sub-section (1), may,--`
  line
  line `(a) in the case of an unlimited company, allow to the contributory, by way of setoff, any money`
  line `due to him or to the estate which he represents, from the company, on any independent dealing or`
  line `contract with the company, but not any money due to him as a member of the company in respect of`
  line `any dividend or profit; and`
  line
  line `(b) in the case of a limited company, allow to any director or manager whose liability is`
  line `unlimited, or to his estate, such set-off.`
  line
  line `(3) In the case of any company, whether limited or unlimited, when all the creditors have been paid in`
  line `full, any money due on any account whatever to a contributory from the company may be allowed to him`
  line `by way of set-off against any subsequent call.`
obj_root_law_sections_295_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_296:
  sectionId (49222)
  sectionNo (296)
  orderNo 300
  title `Power of Tribunal to make calls.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_296_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_296_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=49222&sectionno=296&orderno=300&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_296_content:
  string
  line `The Tribunal may, at any time after the passing of a`
  line `winding up order, and either before or after it has ascertained the sufficiency of the assets of the`
  line company,--
  line
  line `(a) make calls on all or any of the contributories for the time being on the list of the`
  line `contributories, to the extent of their liability, for payment of any money which the Tribunal considers`
  line `necessary to satisfy the debts and liabilities of the company, and the costs, charges and expenses of`
  line `winding up, and for the adjustment of the rights of the contributories among themselves; and`
  line
  line `(b) make an order for payment of any calls so made.`
obj_root_law_sections_296_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_297:
  sectionId (49223)
  sectionNo (297)
  orderNo 301
  title `Adjustment of rights of contributories.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_297_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_297_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=49223&sectionno=297&orderno=301&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_297_content:
  string
  line `The Tribunal shall adjust the rights of the`
  line `contributories among themselves and distribute any surplus among the persons entitled thereto.`
obj_root_law_sections_297_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_298:
  sectionId (49224)
  sectionNo (298)
  orderNo 302
  title `Power to order costs.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_298_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_298_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=49224&sectionno=298&orderno=302&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_298_content:
  string
  line `The Tribunal may, in the event of the assets of a company being`
  line `insufficient to satisfy its liabilities, make an order for the payment out of the assets, of the costs, charges`
  line `and expenses incurred in the winding up, in such order of priority inter se as the Tribunal thinks just and`
  line proper.
obj_root_law_sections_298_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_299:
  sectionId (49225)
  sectionNo (299)
  orderNo 303
  title `Power to summon persons suspected of having property of company, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_299_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_299_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=49225&sectionno=299&orderno=303&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_299_content:
  string
  line `(1) The`
  line `Tribunal may, at any time after the appointment of a provisional liquidator or the passing of a winding up`
  line `order, summon before it any officer of the company or person known or suspected to have in his`
  line `possession any property or books or papers, of the company, or known or suspected to be indebted to the`
  line `company, or any person whom the Tribunal thinks to be capable of giving information concerning the`
  line `promotion, formation, trade, dealings, property, books or papers, or affairs of the company.`
  line
  line `(2) The Tribunal may examine any officer or person so summoned on oath concerning the matters`
  line `aforesaid, either by word of mouth or on written interrogatories or on affidavit and may, in the first case,`
  line `reduce his answers to writing and require him to sign them.`
  line
  line `(3) The Tribunal may require any officer or person so summoned to produce any books and papers`
  line `relating to the company in his custody or power, but, where he claims any lien on books or papers`
  line `produced by him, the production shall be without prejudice to such lien, and the Tribunal shall have`
  line `power to determine all questions relating to that lien.`
  line
  line `(4) The Tribunal may direct the liquidator to file before it a report in respect of debt or property of the`
  line `company in possession of other persons.`
  line
  line `(5) If the Tribunal finds that--`
  line
  line `(a) a person is indebted to the company, the Tribunal may order him to pay to the provisional`
  line `liquidator or, as the case may be, the liquidator at such time and in such manner as the Tribunal may`
  line `consider just, the amount in which he is indebted, or any part thereof, either in full discharge of the`
  line `whole amount or not, as the Tribunal thinks fit, with or without costs of the examination;`
  line
  line `(b) a person is in possession of any property belonging to the company, the Tribunal may order`
  line `him to deliver to the provisional liquidator or, as the case may be, the liquidator, that property or any`
  line `part thereof, at such time, in such manner and on such terms as the Tribunal may consider just.`
  line
  line `(6) If any officer or person so summoned fails to appear before the Tribunal at the time appointed`
  line `without a reasonable cause, the Tribunal may impose an appropriate cost.`
  line
  line `(7) Every order made under sub-section (5) shall be executed in the same manner as decrees for the`
  line `payment of money or for the delivery of property under the Code of Civil Procedure, 1908 (5 of 1908).`
  line
  line `(8) Any person making any payment or delivery in pursuance of an order made under sub-section (5)`
  line `shall by such payment or delivery be, unless otherwise directed by such order, discharged from all`
  line `liability whatsoever in respect of such debt or property.`
obj_root_law_sections_299_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_300:
  sectionId (49226)
  sectionNo (300)
  orderNo 304
  title `Power to order examination of promoters, directors, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_300_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_300_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=49226&sectionno=300&orderno=304&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_300_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where an order has been`
  line `made for the winding up of a company by the Tribunal, and the Company Liquidator has made a report to`
  line `the Tribunal under this Act, stating that in his opinion a fraud has been committed by any person in the`
  line `promotion, formation, business or conduct of affairs of the company since its formation, the Tribunal`
  line `may, after considering the report, direct that such person or officer shall attend before the Tribunal on a`
  line `day appointed by it for that purpose, and be examined as to the promotion or formation or the conduct of`
  line `the business of the company or as to his conduct and dealings as an officer thereof.`
  line
  line `(2) The Company Liquidator shall take part in the examination, and for that purpose he or it may, if`
  line `specially authorised by the Tribunal in that behalf, employ such legal assistance as may be sanctioned by`
  line `the Tribunal.`
  line
  line `(3) The person shall be examined on oath and shall answer all such questions as the Tribunal may put,`
  line `or allow to be put, to him.`
  line
  line `(4) A person ordered to be examined under this section--`
  line
  line `(a) shall, before his examination, be furnished at his own cost with a copy of the report of the`
  line `Company Liquidator; and`
  line
  line `(b) may at his own cost employ chartered accountants or company secretaries or cost accountants`
  line `or legal practitioners entitled to appear before the Tribunal under section 432, who shall be at liberty`
  line `to put to him such questions as the Tribunal may consider just for the purpose of enabling him to`
  line `explain or qualify any answers given by him.`
  line
  line `(5) If any such person applies to the Tribunal to be exculpated from any charges made or`
  line `suggested against him, it shall be the duty of the Company Liquidator to appear on the hearing of`
  line `such application and call the attention of the Tribunal to any matters which appear to the Company`
  line `Liquidator to be relevant.`
  line
  line `(6) If the Tribunal, after considering any evidence given or hearing witnesses called by the`
  line `Company Liquidator, allows the application made under sub-section (5), the Tribunal may order`
  line `payment to the applicant of such costs as it may think fit.`
  line
  line `(7) Notes of the examination shall be taken down in writing, and shall be read over to or by, and`
  line `signed by, the person examined, a copy be supplied to him and may thereafter be used in evidence`
  line `against him, and shall be open to inspection by any creditor or contributory at all reasonable times.`
  line
  line `(8) The Tribunal may, if it thinks fit, adjourn the examination from time to time.`
  line
  line `(9) An examination under this section may, if the Tribunal so directs, be held before any person`
  line `or authority authorised by the Tribunal.`
  line
  line `(10) The powers of the Tribunal under this section as to the conduct of the examination, but not`
  line `as to costs, may be exercised by the person or authority before whom the examination is held in`
  line `pursuance of sub-section (9).`
obj_root_law_sections_300_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_301:
  sectionId (49227)
  sectionNo (301)
  orderNo 305
  title `Arrest of person trying to leave India or abscond.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_301_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_301_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=49227&sectionno=301&orderno=305&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_301_content:
  string
  line `At any time either before or after`
  line `passing a winding up order, if the Tribunal is satisfied that a contributory or a person having property,`
  line `accounts or papers of the company in his possession is about to leave India or otherwise to abscond,`
  line `or is about to remove or conceal any of his property, for the purpose of evading payment of calls or of`
  line `avoiding examination respecting the affairs of the company, the Tribunal may cause--`
  line
  line `(a) the contributory to be detained until such time as the Tribunal may order; and`
  line
  line `(b) his books and papers and movable property to be seized and safely kept until such time as`
  line `the Tribunal may order.`
obj_root_law_sections_301_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_302:
  sectionId (49228)
  sectionNo (302)
  orderNo 306
  title `Dissolution of company by Tribunal.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_302_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_302_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=49228&sectionno=302&orderno=306&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_302_content:
  string
  line `(1) When the affairs of a company have been completely wound up, the Company Liquidator shall make an application to the Tribunal for dissolution of such company.`
  line
  line `(2) The Tribunal shall on an application filed by the Company Liquidator under sub-section (1) or when the Tribunal is of the opinion that it is just and reasonable in the circumstances of the case that an order for the dissolution of the company should be made, make an order that the company be dissolved from the date of the order, and the company shall be dissolved accordingly.`
  line
  line `^1 [(3) The Tribunal shall, within a period of thirty days form the date of the order, --`
  line
  line `(a) forward a copy of the order to the Registrar who shall record in the register relating to the company a minute of the dissolution of the company; and`
  line
  line `(b) direct the Company Liquidator to forward a copy of the order to the Registrar who shall record in the register relating to the company a minute of the dissolution of the company.]`
  line
  line `^2* * * * *`
obj_root_law_sections_302_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 29 of 2020, s. 47, for sub-section (3) (w.e.f. 21-212020).`
  line
  line `2. Sub-section (4) omitted by s. 47, ibid. (w.e.f. 21-12-2020).`
obj_root_law_sections_303:
  sectionId (49229)
  sectionNo (303)
  orderNo 307
  title `Appeals from orders made before commencement of Act.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_303_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_303_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=49229&sectionno=303&orderno=307&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_303_content:
  string
  line `Nothing in this Chapter shall`
  line `affect the operation or enforcement of any order made by any Court in any proceedings for the winding`
  line `up of a company immediately before the commencement of this Act and an appeal against such order`
  line `shall be filed before such authority competent to hear such appeals before such commencement.`
obj_root_law_sections_303_footnotes:
  string
  line
