obj_root_law_sections_325_content:
  string
  line `[Application of insolvency rules in winding up of insolvent companies.] Omitted by the Insolvency`
  line `and Bankruptcy Code, 2016 (31 of 2016) s. 255 and the Eleventh Schedule (w.e.f. 15-11-2016).`
obj_root_law_sections_325_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_326:
  sectionId (1517)
  sectionNo (326)
  orderNo 330
  title `Overriding preferential payments.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_326_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 31 of 2016, s. 255 and the Eleventh Schedule, for section 326 (w.e.f. 15-11-2016).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=1517&sectionno=326&orderno=330&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_326_content:
  string
  line `^1[326. Overriding preferential payments.-- (1) In the winding up of a company under this Act, the`
  line `following debts shall be paid in priority to all other debts:--`
  line
  line `(a) workmen's dues; and`
  line
  line `(b) where a secured creditor has realised a secured asset, so much of the debts due to such secured`
  line `creditor as could not be realised by him or the amount of the workmen's portion in his security (if`
  line `payable under the law), whichever is less, pari passu with the workmen's dues:`
  line
  line `Provided that in case of the winding up of a company, the sums referred to in sub-clauses (i) and`
  line `(ii) of clause (b) of the Explanation, which are payable for a period of two years preceding the`
  line `winding up order or such other period as may be prescribed, shall be paid in priority to all other debts`
  line `(including debts due to secured creditors), within a period of thirty days of sale of assets and shall be`
  line `subject to such charge over the security of secured creditors as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(2) The debts payable under the proviso to sub-section (1) shall be paid in full before any payment is`
  line `made to secured creditors and thereafter debts payable under that sub-section shall be paid in full, unless`
  line `the assets are insufficient to meet them, in which case they shall abate in equal proportions.`
  line
  line `Explanation.-- For the purposes of this section, and section 327--`
  line
  line `(a) "workmen", in relation to a company, means the employees of the company, being workmen`
  line `within the meaning of clause (s) of section 2 of the Industrial Disputes Act, 1947 (14 of 1947);`
  line
  line `(b) "workmen's dues", in relation to a company, means the aggregate of the following sums due`
  line `from the company to its workmen, namely:--`
  line
  line `(i) all wages or salary including wages payable for time or piece work and salary earned`
  line `wholly or in part by way of commission of any workman in respect of services rendered to the`
  line `company and any compensation payable to any workman under any of the provisions of the`
  line `Industrial Disputes Act, 1947 (14 of 1947);`
  line
  line `(ii) all accrued holiday remuneration becoming payable to any workman or, in the case of his`
  line `death, to any other person in his right on the termination of his employment before or by the`
  line `effect of the winding up order or resolution;`
  line
  line `(iii) unless the company is being wound up voluntarily merely for the purposes of`
  line `reconstruction or amalgamation with another company or unless the company has, at the`
  line `commencement of the winding up, under such a contract with insurers as is mentioned in section 14 of the Workmen's Compensation Act, 1923 (19 of 1923), rights capable of being transferred to`
  line `and vested in the workmen, all amount due in respect of any compensation or liability for`
  line `compensation under the said Act in respect of the death or disablement of any workman of the`
  line company;
  line
  line `(iv) all sums due to any workman from the provident fund, the pension fund, the gratuity fund`
  line `or any other fund for the welfare of the workmen, maintained by the company;`
  line
  line `(c) "workmen's portion", in relation to the security of any secured creditor of a company, means`
  line `the amount which bears to the value of the security the same proportion as the amount of the`
  line `workmen's dues bears to the aggregate of the amount of workmen's dues and the amount of the debts`
  line `due to the secured creditors.`
  line
  line Illustration
  line
  line `The value of the security of a secured creditor of a company is Rs. 1,00,000. The total amount of the workmen's`
  line `dues is Rs. 1,00,000. The amount of the debts due from the company to its secured creditors is Rs.3,00,000. The`
  line `aggregate of the amount of workmen's dues and the amount of debts due to secured creditors is Rs. 4,00,000. The`
  line `workmen's portion of the security is, therefore, one-fourth of the value of the security, that is Rs. 25,000.]`
obj_root_law_sections_327:
  sectionId (1518)
  sectionNo (327)
  orderNo 331
  title `Preferential payments.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_327_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_327_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=1518&sectionno=327&orderno=331&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_327_content:
  string
  line `(1) In a winding up, subject to the provisions of section 326, there`
  line `shall be paid in priority to all other debts,--`
  line
  line `(a) all revenues, taxes, cesses and rates due from the company to the Central Government or a`
  line `State Government or to a local authority at the relevant date, and having become due and payable`
  line `within the twelve months immediately before that date;`
  line
  line `(b) all wages or salary including wages payable for time or piece work and salary earned wholly`
  line `or in part by way of commission of any employee in respect of services rendered to the company and`
  line `due for a period not exceeding four months within the twelve months immediately before the relevant`
  line `date, subject to the condition that the amount payable under this clause to any workman shall not`
  line `exceed such amount as may be notified;`
  line
  line `(c) all accrued holiday remuneration becoming payable to any employee, or in the case of his`
  line `death, to any other person claiming under him, on the termination of his employment before, or by the`
  line `winding up order, or, as the case may be, the dissolution of the company;`
  line
  line `(d) unless the company is being wound up voluntarily merely for the purposes of reconstruction`
  line `or amalgamation with another company, all amount due in respect of contributions payable during the`
  line `period of twelve months immediately before the relevant date by the company as the employer of`
  line `persons under the Employees State Insurance Act, 1948 (34 of 1948) or any other law for the time`
  line `being in force;`
  line
  line `(e) unless the company has, at the commencement of winding up, under such a contract with any`
  line `insurer as is mentioned in section 14 of the Workmens Compensation Act, 1923 (8 of 1923), rights`
  line `capable of being transferred to and vested in the workmen, all amount due in respect of any`
  line `compensation or liability for compensation under the said Act in respect of the death or disablement`
  line `of any employee of the company:`
  line
  line `Provided that where any compensation under the said Act is a weekly payment, the amount`
  line `payable under this clause shall be taken to be the amount of the lump sum for which such weekly`
  line `payment could, if redeemable, be redeemed, if the employer has made an application under that Act;`
  line
  line `(f) all sums due to any employee from the provident fund, the pension fund, the gratuity fund or`
  line `any other fund for the welfare of the employees, maintained by the company; and`
  line
  line `(g) the expenses of any investigation held in pursuance of sections 213 and 216, in so far as they`
  line `are payable by the company.`
  line
  line `(2) Where any payment has been made to any employee of a company on account of wages or salary`
  line `or accrued holiday remuneration, himself or, in the case of his death, to any other person claiming through`
  line `him, out of money advanced by some person for that purpose, the person by whom the money was`
  line `advanced shall, in a winding up, have a right of priority in respect of the money so advanced and paid-up`
  line `to the amount by which the sum in respect of which the employee or other person in his right would have`
  line `been entitled to priority in the winding up has been reduced by reason of the payment having been made.`
  line
  line `(3) The debts enumerated in this section shall--`
  line
  line `(a) rank equally among themselves and be paid in full, unless the assets are insufficient to meet`
  line `them, in which case they shall abate in equal proportions; and`
  line
  line `(b) so far as the assets of the company available for payment to general creditors are insufficient`
  line `to meet them, have priority over the claims of holders of debentures under any floating charge created`
  line `by the company, and be paid accordingly out of any property comprised in or subject to that charge.`
  line
  line `(4) Subject to the retention of such sums as may be necessary for the costs and expenses of the`
  line `winding up, the debts under this section shall be discharged forthwith so far as the assets are sufficient to`
  line `meet them, and in the case of the debts to which priority is given under clause (d) of sub-section (1),`
  line `formal proof thereof shall not be required except in so far as may be otherwise prescribed.`
  line
  line `(5) In the event of a landlord or other person distraining or having distrained on any goods or effects`
  line `of the company within three months immediately before the date of a winding up order, the debts to`
  line `which priority is given under this section shall be a first charge on the goods or effects so distrained on or`
  line `the proceeds of the sale thereof:`
  line
  line `Provided that, in respect of any money paid under any such charge, the landlord or other person shall`
  line `have the same rights of priority as the person to whom the payment is made.`
  line
  line `(6) Any remuneration in respect of a period of holiday or of absence from work on medical grounds`
  line `through sickness or other good cause shall be deemed to be wages in respect of services rendered to the`
  line `company during that period.`
  line
  line `^1[(7) Sections 326 and 327 shall not be applicable in the event of liquidation under the Insolvency and`
  line `Bankruptcy Code, 2016 (31 of 2016).]`
  line
  line `Explanation.-- For the purposes of this section,--`
  line
  line `(a) the expression accrued holiday remuneration includes, in relation to any person, all sums`
  line `which, by virtue either of his contract of employment or of any enactment including any order made`
  line `or direction given thereunder, are payable on account of the remuneration which would, in the`
  line `ordinary course, have become payable to him in respect of a period of holiday, had his employment`
  line `with the company continued until he became entitled to be allowed the holiday;`
  line
  line `(b) the expression employee does not include a workman; and`
  line
  line `^2[(c) the expression relevant date means in the case of a company being wound up by the`
  line `Tribunal, the date of appointment or first appointment of a provisional liquidator, or if no such`
  line `appointment was made, the date of the winding up order, unless, in either case, the company had`
  line `commenced to be wound up voluntarily before that date under the Insolvency and Bankruptcy Code,`
  line `2016 (31 of 2016).]`
obj_root_law_sections_327_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 31 of 2016, s. 255 and the Eleventh Schedule (w.e.f. 15-11-2016).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by s. 255 and the Eleventh Schedule, ibid., for clause (c) (w.e.f. 15-11-2016).`
obj_root_law_sections_328:
  sectionId (1519)
  sectionNo (328)
  orderNo 332
  title `Fraudulent preference`
  content obj_root_law_sections_328_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_328_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=1519&sectionno=328&orderno=332&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_328_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where a company has given preference to a person who is one of`
  line `the creditors of the company or a surety or guarantor for any of the debts or other liabilities of the`
  line `company, and the company does anything or suffers anything done which has the effect of putting that`
  line `person into a position which, in the event of the company going into liquidation, will be better than the`
  line `position he would have been in if that thing had not been done prior to six months of making winding up`
  line `application, the Tribunal, if satisfied that, such transaction is a fraudulent preference may order as it may`
  line `think fit for restoring the position to what it would have been if the company had not given that`
  line preference.
  line
  line `(2) If the Tribunal is satisfied that there is a preference transfer of property, movable or immovable,`
  line `or any delivery of goods, payment, execution made, taken or done by or against a company within six`
  line `months before making winding up application, the Tribunal may order as it may think fit and may declare`
  line `such transaction invalid and restore the position.`
obj_root_law_sections_328_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_329:
  sectionId (1520)
  sectionNo (329)
  orderNo 333
  title `Transfers not in good faith to be void`
  content obj_root_law_sections_329_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 31 of 2016, s. 255 and the Eleventh Schedule, for section 329 (w.e.f. 15-11-2016).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=1520&sectionno=329&orderno=333&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_329_content:
  string
  line `^1[329. Transfers not in good faith to be void.-- Any transfer of property, movable or immovable, or`
  line `any delivery of goods, made by a company, not being a transfer or delivery made in the ordinary course`
  line `of its business or in favour of a purchaser or encumbrance in good faith and for valuable consideration, if`
  line `made within a period of one year before the presentation of a petition for winding up by the Tribunal or`
  line `the passing of a resolution for voluntary winding up of the company, shall be void against the Company`
  line Liquidator.]
obj_root_law_sections_330:
  sectionId (1521)
  sectionNo (330)
  orderNo 334
  title `Certain transfers to be void.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_330_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_330_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=1521&sectionno=330&orderno=334&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_330_content:
  string
  line `Any transfer or assignment by a company of all its properties or`
  line `assets to trustees for the benefit of all its creditors shall be void.`
obj_root_law_sections_330_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_331:
  sectionId (1522)
  sectionNo (331)
  orderNo 335
  title `Liabilities and rights of certain persons fraudulently preferred.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_331_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_331_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=1522&sectionno=331&orderno=335&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_331_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where a company is`
  line `being wound up and anything made, taken or done after the commencement of this Act is invalid under`
  line `section 328 as a fraudulent preference of a person interested in property mortgaged or charged to secure`
  line `the companys debt, then, without prejudice to any rights or liabilities arising, apart from this provision,`
  line `the person preferred shall be subject to the same liabilities, and shall have the same rights, as if he had`
  line `undertaken to be personally liable as a surety for the debt, to the extent of the mortgage or charge on the`
  line `property or the value of his interest, whichever is less.`
  line
  line `(2) The value of the interest of the person preferred under sub-section (1) shall be determined as at the`
  line `date of the transaction constituting the fraudulent preference, as if the interest were free of all`
  line `encumbrances other than those to which the mortgage or charge for the debt of the company was then`
  line subject.
  line
  line `(3) On an application made to the Tribunal with respect to any payment on the ground that the`
  line `payment was a fraudulent preference of a surety or guarantor, the Tribunal shall have jurisdiction to`
  line `determine any questions with respect to the payment arising between the person to whom the payment`
  line `was made and the surety or guarantor and to grant relief in respect thereof, notwithstanding that it is not`
  line `necessary so to do for the purposes of the winding up, and for that purpose, may give leave to bring in the`
  line `surety or guarantor as a third party as in the case of a suit for the recovery of the sum paid.`
  line
  line `(4) The provisions of sub-section (3) shall apply mutatis mutandis in relation to transactions other`
  line `than payment of money.`
obj_root_law_sections_331_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_332:
  sectionId (1523)
  sectionNo (332)
  orderNo 336
  title `Effect of floating charge.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_332_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_332_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=1523&sectionno=332&orderno=336&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_332_content:
  string
  line `Where a company is being wound up, a floating charge on the`
  line `undertaking or property of the company created within the twelve months immediately preceding the`
  line `commencement of the winding up, shall, unless it is proved that the company immediately after the`
  line `creation of the charge was solvent, be invalid, except for the amount of any cash paid to the company at`
  line `the time of, or subsequent to the creation of, and in consideration for, the charge, together with interest on`
  line `that amount at the rate of five per cent. per annum or such other rate as may be notified by the Central`
  line `Government in this behalf.`
obj_root_law_sections_332_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_333:
  sectionId (1524)
  sectionNo (333)
  orderNo 337
  title `Disclaimer of onerous property.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_333_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_333_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=1524&sectionno=333&orderno=337&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_333_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where any part of the property of a company which is`
  line `being wound up consists of--`
  line
  line `(a) land of any tenure, burdened with onerous covenants;`
  line
  line `(b) shares or stocks in companies;`
  line
  line `(c) any other property which is not saleable or is not readily saleable by reason of the possessor`
  line `thereof being bound either to the performance of any onerous act or to the payment of any sum of`
  line `money; or`
  line
  line `(d) unprofitable contracts,`
  line
  line `the Company Liquidator may, notwithstanding that he has endeavoured to sell or has taken possession of`
  line `the property or exercised any act of ownership in relation thereto or done anything in pursuance of the`
  line `contract, with the leave of the Tribunal and subject to the provisions of this section, by writing signed by`
  line `him, at any time within twelve months after the commencement of the winding up or such extended`
  line `period as may be allowed by the Tribunal, disclaim the property:`
  line
  line `Provided that where the Company Liquidator had not become aware of the existence of any such`
  line `property within one month from the commencement of the winding up, the power of disclaiming the`
  line `property may be exercised at any time within twelve months after he has become aware thereof or such`
  line `extended period as may be allowed by the Tribunal.`
  line
  line `(2) The disclaimer shall operate to determine, as from the date of disclaimer, the rights, interest and`
  line `liabilities of the company in or in respect of the property disclaimed, but shall not, except so far as is`
  line `necessary for the purpose of releasing the company and the property of the company from liability, affect`
  line `the rights, interest or liabilities of any other person.`
  line
  line `(3) The Tribunal, before or on granting leave to disclaim, may require such notices to be given to`
  line `persons interested, and impose such terms as a condition of granting leave, and make such other order in`
  line `the matter as the Tribunal considers just and proper.`
  line
  line `(4) The Company Liquidator shall not be entitled to disclaim any property in any case where an`
  line `application in writing has been made to him by any person interested in the property requiring him to`
  line `decide whether he will or will not disclaim and the Company Liquidator has not, within a period of`
  line `twenty-eight days after the receipt of the application or such extended period as may be allowed by the`
  line `Tribunal, give notice to the applicant that he intends to apply to the Tribunal for leave to disclaim, and in`
  line `case the property is under a contract, if the Company Liquidator after such an application as aforesaid`
  line `does not within the said period or extended period disclaim the contract, he shall be deemed to have`
  line `adopted it.`
  line
  line `(5) The Tribunal may, on the application of any person who is, as against the Company Liquidator,`
  line `entitled to the benefit or subject to the burden of a contract made with the company, make an order`
  line `rescinding the contract on such terms as to payment by or to either party of damages for the nonperformance`
  line `of the contract, or otherwise as the Tribunal considers just and proper, and any damages`
  line `payable under the order to any such person may be proved by him as a debt in the winding up.`
  line
  line `(6) The Tribunal may, on an application by any person who either claims any interest in any`
  line `disclaimed property or is under any liability not discharged under this Act in respect of any disclaimed`
  line `property, and after hearing any such persons as it thinks fit, make an order for the vesting of the property`
  line `in, or the delivery of the property to, any person entitled thereto or to whom it may seem just that the`
  line `property should be delivered by way of compensation for such liability as aforesaid, or a trustee for him,`
  line `and on such terms as the Tribunal considers just and proper, and on any such vesting order being made,`
  line `the property comprised therein shall vest accordingly in the person named therein in that behalf without`
  line `any conveyance or assignment for the purpose:`
  line
  line `Provided that where the property disclaimed is of a leasehold nature, the Tribunal shall not make a`
  line `vesting order in favour of any person claiming under the company, whether as under-lessee or as`
  line `mortgagee or holder of a charge by way of demise, except upon the terms of making that person`
  line
  line `(a) subject to the same liabilities and obligations as those to which the company was subject`
  line `under the lease in respect of the property at the commencement of the winding up; or`
  line
  line `(b) if the Tribunal thinks fit, subject only to the same liabilities and obligations as if the lease had`
  line `been assigned to that person at that date,`
  line
  line `and in either event as if the lease had comprised only the property comprised in the vesting order, and any`
  line `mortgagee or under-lessee declining to accept a vesting order upon such terms shall be excluded from all`
  line `interest in, and security upon the property, and, if there is no person claiming under the company who is`
  line `willing to accept an order upon such terms, the Tribunal shall have power to vest the estate and interest of`
  line `the company in the property in any person liable, either personally or in a representative character, and`
  line `either alone or jointly with the company, to perform the covenants of the lessee in the lease, free and`
  line `discharged from all estates, encumbrances and interests created therein by the company.`
  line
  line `(7) Any person affected by the operation of a disclaimer under this section shall be deemed to be a`
  line `creditor of the company to the amount of the compensation or damages payable in respect of such effect,`
  line `and may accordingly prove the amount as a debt in the winding up.`
obj_root_law_sections_333_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_334:
  sectionId (1525)
  sectionNo (334)
  orderNo 338
  title `Transfers, etc., after commencement of winding up to be void.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_334_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 31 of 2016, s. 255 and the Eleventh Schedule, for section 334 (w.e.f. 15-11-2016).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=1525&sectionno=334&orderno=338&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_334_content:
  string
  line `^1[334. Transfers, etc., after commencement of winding up to be void-- In the case of a winding up`
  line `by the Tribunal, any disposition of the property including actionable claims, of the company and any`
  line `transfer of shares in the company or alteration in the status of its members, made after the commencement`
  line `of the winding up shall, unless the Tribunal otherwise orders, be void.]`
obj_root_law_sections_335:
  sectionId (1526)
  sectionNo (335)
  orderNo 339
  title `Certain attachments, executions, etc., in winding up by Tribunal to be void`
  content obj_root_law_sections_335_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_335_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=1526&sectionno=335&orderno=339&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_335_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where`
  line `any company is being wound up by the Tribunal,--`
  line
  line `(a) any attachment, distress or execution put in force, without leave of the Tribunal against the`
  line `estate or effects of the company, after the commencement of the winding up; or`
  line
  line `(b) any sale held, without leave of the Tribunal of any of the properties or effects of the company,`
  line `after such commencement,`
  line
  line `shall be void.`
  line
  line `(2) Nothing in this section shall apply to any proceedings for the recovery of any tax or impost or any`
  line `dues payable to the Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_335_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_336:
  sectionId (1527)
  sectionNo (336)
  orderNo 340
  title `Offences by officers of companies in liquidation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_336_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_336_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=1527&sectionno=336&orderno=340&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_336_content:
  string
  line `(1) If any person, who is or has been an`
  line `officer of a company which, at the time of the commission of the alleged offence, is being wound up, ^1[by`
  line `the Tribunal under this Act or which is subsequently ordered to be wound up by the Tribunal under this`
  line Act],--
  line
  line `(a) does not, to the best of his knowledge and belief, fully and truly disclose to the Company`
  line `Liquidator all the property, movable and immovable, of the company, and how and to whom and for`
  line `what consideration and when the company disposed of any part thereof, except such part as has been`
  line `disposed of in the ordinary course of the business of the company;`
  line
  line `(b) does not deliver up to the Company Liquidator, or as he directs, all such part of the movable`
  line `and immovable property of the company as is in his custody or under his control and which he is`
  line `required by law to deliver up;`
  line
  line `(c) does not deliver up to the Company Liquidator, or as he directs, all such books and papers of`
  line `the company as are in his custody or under his control and which he is required by law to deliver up;`
  line
  line `(d) within the twelve months immediately before the commencement of the winding up or at any`
  line `time thereafter,--`
  line
  line `(i) conceals any part of the property of the company to the value of one thousand rupees or`
  line `more, or conceals any debt due to or from the company;`
  line
  line `(ii) fraudulently removes any part of the property of the company to the value of one`
  line `thousand rupees or more;`
  line
  line `(iii) conceals, destroys, mutilates or falsifies, or is privy to the concealment, destruction,`
  line `mutilation or falsification of, any book or paper affecting or relating to, the property or affairs of`
  line `the company;`
  line
  line `(iv) makes, or is privy to the making of, any false entry in any book or paper affecting or`
  line `relating to, the property or affairs of the company;`
  line
  line `(v) fraudulently parts with, alters or makes any omission in, or is privy to the fraudulent`
  line `parting with, altering or making of any omission in, any book or paper affecting or relating to the`
  line `property or affairs of the company;`
  line
  line `(vi) by any false representation or other fraud, obtains on credit, for or on behalf of the`
  line `company, any property which the company does not subsequently pay for;`
  line
  line `(vii) under the false pretence that the company is carrying on its business, obtains on credit,`
  line `for or on behalf of the company, any property which the company does not subsequently pay for;`
  line or
  line
  line `(viii) pawns, pledges or disposes of any property of the company which has been obtained on`
  line `credit and has not been paid for, unless such pawning, pledging or disposing of the property is in`
  line `the ordinary course of business of the company;`
  line
  line `(e) makes any material omission in any statement relating to the affairs of the company;`
  line
  line `(f) knowing or believing that a false debt has been proved by any person under the winding up,`
  line `fails for a period of one month to inform the Company Liquidator thereof;`
  line
  line `(g) after the commencement of the winding up, prevents the production of any book or paper`
  line `affecting or relating to the property or affairs of the company;`
  line
  line `(h) after the commencement of the winding up or at any meeting of the creditors of the company`
  line `within the twelve months next before the commencement of the winding up, attempts to account for`
  line `any part of the property of the company by fictitious losses or expenses; or`
  line
  line `(i) is guilty of any false representation or fraud for the purpose of obtaining the consent of the`
  line `creditors of the company or any of them, to an agreement with reference to the affairs of the company`
  line `or to the winding up,`
  line
  line `he shall be punishable with imprisonment for a term which shall not be less than three years but which`
  line `may extend to five years and with fine which shall not be less than one lakh rupees but which may extend`
  line `to three lakh rupees:`
  line
  line `Provided that it shall be a good defence if the accused proves that he had no intent to defraud or to`
  line `conceal the true state of affairs of the company or to defeat the law.`
  line
  line `(2) Where any person pawns, pledges or disposes of any property in circumstances which amount to`
  line `an offence under sub-clause (viii) of clause (d) of sub-section (1), every person who takes in pawn or`
  line `pledge or otherwise receives the property, knowing it to be pawned, pledged, or disposed of in such`
  line `circumstances as aforesaid, shall be punishable with imprisonment for a term which shall not be less than`
  line `three years but which may extend to five years and with fine which shall not be less than three lakh rupees`
  line `but which may extend to five lakh rupees.`
  line
  line `Explanation.-- For the purposes of this section, the expression "officer" includes any person in`
  line `accordance with whose directions or instructions the directors of the company have been accustomed to`
  line act.
obj_root_law_sections_336_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by s. 255 and the Eleventh Schedule, ibid., for "whether by the Tribunal or voluntarily, or which is subsequently ordered`
  line `to be wound up by the Tribunal or which subsequently passes a resolution for voluntary winding up" (w.e.f. 15-11-2016).`
obj_root_law_sections_337:
  sectionId (1528)
  sectionNo (337)
  orderNo 341
  title `Penalty for frauds by officers.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_337_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_337_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=1528&sectionno=337&orderno=341&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_337_content:
  string
  line `If any person, being at the time of the commission of the`
  line `alleged offence an officer of a company which is subsequently ordered to be wound up by the Tribunal ^1[under this Act]--`
  line
  line `(a) has, by false pretences or by means of any other fraud, induced any person to give credit to`
  line `the company;`
  line
  line `(b) with intent to defraud creditors of the company or any other person, has made or caused to be`
  line `made any gift or transfer of, or charge on, or has caused or connived at the levying of any execution`
  line `against, the property of the company; or`
  line
  line `(c) with intent to defraud creditors of the company, has concealed or removed any part of the`
  line `property of the company since the date of any unsatisfied judgment or order for payment of money`
  line `obtained against the company or within two months before that date,`
  line
  line `he shall be punishable with imprisonment for a term which shall not be less than one year but which may`
  line `extend to three years and with fine which shall not be less than one lakh rupees but which may extend to`
  line `three lakh rupees.`
obj_root_law_sections_337_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 31 of 2016, s. 255 and the Eleventh Schedule, for "or which subsequently passes a resolution for voluntary`
  line `winding up," (w.e.f. 15-11-2016).`
obj_root_law_sections_338:
  sectionId (1529)
  sectionNo (338)
  orderNo 342
  title `Liability where proper accounts not kept`
  content obj_root_law_sections_338_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_338_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=1529&sectionno=338&orderno=342&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_338_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where a company is being wound up, if it is`
  line `shown that proper books of account were not kept by the company throughout the period of two years`
  line `immediately preceding the commencement of the winding up, or the period between the incorporation of`
  line `the company and the commencement of the winding up, whichever is shorter, every officer of the`
  line `company who is in default shall, unless he shows that he acted honestly and that in the circumstances in`
  line `which the business of the company was carried on, the default was excusable, be punishable with`
  line `imprisonment for a term which shall not be less than one year but which may extend to three years and`
  line `with fine which shall not be less than one lakh rupees but which may extend to three lakh rupees.`
  line
  line `(2) For the purposes of sub-section (1), it shall be deemed that proper books of account have not been`
  line `kept in the case of any company,--`
  line
  line `(a) if such books of account as are necessary to exhibit and explain the transactions and financial`
  line `position of the business of the company, including books containing entries made from day-to-day in`
  line `sufficient detail of all cash received and all cash paid, have not been kept; and`
  line
  line `(b) where the business of the company has involved dealings in goods, statements of the annual`
  line `stock takings and, except in the case of goods sold by way of ordinary retail trade, of all goods sold`
  line `and purchased, showing the goods and the buyers and the sellers thereof in sufficient detail to enable`
  line `those goods and those buyers and sellers to be identified, have not been kept.`
obj_root_law_sections_338_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_339:
  sectionId (1530)
  sectionNo (339)
  orderNo 343
  title `Liability for fraudulent conduct of business`
  content obj_root_law_sections_339_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_339_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=1530&sectionno=339&orderno=343&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_339_content:
  string
  line `(1) If in the course of the winding up of a`
  line `company, it appears that any business of the company has been carried on with intent to defraud creditors`
  line `of the company or any other persons or for any fraudulent purpose, the Tribunal, on the application of the`
  line `Official Liquidator, or the Company Liquidator or any creditor or contributory of the company, may, if it`
  line `thinks it proper so to do, declare that any person, who is or has been a director, manager, or officer of the`
  line `company or any persons who were knowingly parties to the carrying on of the business in the manner`
  line `aforesaid shall be personally responsible, without any limitation of liability, for all or any of the debts or`
  line `other liabilities of the company as the Tribunal may direct:`
  line
  line `Provided that on the hearing of an application under this sub-section, the Official Liquidator or the`
  line `Company Liquidator, as the case may be, may himself give evidence or call witnesses.`
  line
  line `(2) Where the Tribunal makes any such declaration, it may give such further directions as it thinks`
  line `proper for the purpose of giving effect to that declaration and, in particular,--`
  line
  line `(a) make provision for making the liability of any such person under the declaration a charge on`
  line `any debt or obligation due from the company to him, or on any mortgage or charge or any interest in`
  line `any mortgage or charge on any assets of the company held by or vested in him, or any person on his`
  line `behalf, or any person claiming as assignee from or through the person liable or any person acting on`
  line `his behalf;`
  line
  line `(b) make such further order as may be necessary for the purpose of enforcing any charge imposed`
  line `under this sub-section.`
  line
  line `(3) Where any business of a company is carried on with such intent or for such purpose as is`
  line `mentioned in sub-section (1), every person who was knowingly a party to the carrying on of the business`
  line `in the manner aforesaid, shall be liable for action under section 447.`
  line
  line `(4) This section shall apply, notwithstanding that the person concerned may be punishable under any`
  line `other law for the time being in force in respect of the matters on the ground of which the declaration is to`
  line `be made.`
  line
  line `Explanation.-- For the purposes of this section,--`
  line
  line `(a) the expression "assignee" includes any person to whom or in whose favour, by the directions`
  line `of the person liable, the debt, obligation, mortgage or charge was created, issued or transferred or the`
  line `interest was created, but does not include an assignee for valuable consideration, not including`
  line `consideration by way of marriage, given in good faith and without notice of any of the matters on the`
  line `ground of which the declaration is made;`
  line
  line `(b) the expression "officer" includes any person in accordance with whose directions or`
  line `instructions the directors of the company have been accustomed to act.`
obj_root_law_sections_339_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_340:
  sectionId (1531)
  sectionNo (340)
  orderNo 344
  title `Power of Tribunal to assess damages against delinquent directors, etc`
  content obj_root_law_sections_340_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_340_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=1531&sectionno=340&orderno=344&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_340_content:
  string
  line `(1) If in the course`
  line `of winding up of a company, it appears that any person who has taken part in the promotion or formation`
  line `of the company, or any person, who is or has been a director, manager, Company Liquidator or officer of`
  line `the company--`
  line
  line `(a) has misapplied, or retained, or become liable or accountable for, any money or property of the`
  line `company; or`
  line
  line `(b) has been guilty of any misfeasance or breach of trust in relation to the company,`
  line
  line `the Tribunal may, on the application of the Official Liquidator, or the Company Liquidator, or of any`
  line `creditor or contributory, made within the period specified in that behalf in sub-section (2), inquire into the`
  line `conduct of the person, director, manager, Company Liquidator or officer aforesaid, and order him to`
  line `repay or restore the money or property or any part thereof respectively, with interest at such rate as the`
  line `Tribunal considers just and proper, or to contribute such sum to the assets of the company by way of`
  line `compensation in respect of the misapplication, retainer, misfeasance or breach of trust, as the Tribunal`
  line `considers just and proper.`
  line
  line `(2) An application under sub-section (1) shall be made within five years from the date of the winding`
  line `up order, or of the first appointment of the Company Liquidator in the winding up, or of the`
  line `misapplication, retainer, misfeasance or breach of trust, as the case may be, whichever is longer.`
  line
  line `(3) This section shall apply, notwithstanding that the matter is one for which the person concerned`
  line `may be criminally liable.`
obj_root_law_sections_340_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_341:
  sectionId (1532)
  sectionNo (341)
  orderNo 345
  title `Liability under sections 339 and 340 to extend to partners or directors in firms or companies`
  content obj_root_law_sections_341_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_341_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=1532&sectionno=341&orderno=345&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_341_content:
  string
  line `Where a declaration under section 339 or an order under section 340 is made in respect of a`
  line `firm or body corporate, the Tribunal shall also have power to make a declaration under section 339, or`
  line `pass an order under section 340, as the case may be, in respect of any person who was at the relevant time`
  line `a partner in that firm or a director of that body corporate.`
obj_root_law_sections_341_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_342:
  sectionId (1533)
  sectionNo (342)
  orderNo 346
  title `Prosecution of delinquent officers and members of company.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_342_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_342_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=1533&sectionno=342&orderno=346&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_342_content:
  string
  line `(1) If it appears to the Tribunal in the course of a winding up by the Tribunal, that any person, who is or has been an officer, or any member, of the company has been guilty of any offence in relation to the company, the Tribunal may, either on the application of any person interested in the winding up or suo motu, direct the liquidator to prosecute the offender or to refer the matter to the Registrar.`
  line
  line `^1* * * * *`
  line
  line `(5) When any prosecution is instituted under this section, it shall be the duty of the liquidator and of every person, who is or has been an officer and agent of the company to give all assistance in connection with the prosecution which he is reasonably able to give.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purposes of this sub-section, the expression "agent", in relation to a company, shall include any banker or legal adviser of the company and any person employed by the company as auditor.`
  line
  line `^2* * * * *`
obj_root_law_sections_342_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Sub-sections (2), (3) and (4) omitted by Act 31 of 2016, s. 255 and the Eleventh Schedule (w.e.f. 15-11-2016).`
  line
  line `2. Sub-section (6) omitted by Act 29 of 2020, s. 48 (w.e.f. 21-12-2020).`
obj_root_law_sections_343:
  sectionId (1534)
  sectionNo (343)
  orderNo 347
  title `Company Liquidator to exercise certain powers subject to sanction.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_343_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by s. 255 and the Eleventh Schedule, ibid., for sub-section (1) (w.e.f. 15-11-2016).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=1534&sectionno=343&orderno=347&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_343_content:
  string
  line `^1[(1) The Company`
  line `Liquidator may, with the sanction of the Tribunal, when the company is being wound up by the`
  line Tribunal,--
  line
  line `(i) pay any class of creditors in full;`
  line
  line `(ii) make any compromise or arrangement with creditors or persons claiming to be creditors, or`
  line `having or alleging themselves to have any claim, present or future, certain or contingent, against the`
  line `company, or whereby the company may be rendered liable; or`
  line
  line `(iii) compromise any call or liability to call, debt, and liability capable of resulting in a debt, and`
  line `any claim, present or future, certain or contingent, ascertained or sounding only in damages,`
  line `subsisting or alleged to subsist between the company and a contributory or alleged contributory or`
  line `other debtor or person apprehending liability to the company, and all questions in any way relating to`
  line `or affecting the assets or liabilities or the winding up of the company, on such terms as may be`
  line `agreed, and take any security for the discharge of any such call, debt, liability or claim, and give a`
  line `complete discharge in respect thereof.]`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (1), in the case of a winding up by the`
  line `Tribunal, the Central Government may make rules to provide that the Company Liquidator may, under`
  line `such circumstances, if any, and subject to such conditions, restrictions and limitations, if any, as may be`
  line `prescribed, exercise any of the powers referred to in sub-clause (ii) or sub-clause (iii) of clause (b) of`
  line `sub-section (1) without the sanction of the Tribunal.`
  line
  line `(3) Any creditor or contributory may apply in the manner prescribed to the Tribunal with respect to`
  line `any exercise or proposed exercise of powers by the Company Liquidator under this section, and the`
  line `Tribunal shall after giving a reasonable opportunity to such applicant and the Company Liquidator, pass`
  line `such orders as it may think fit.`
obj_root_law_sections_344:
  sectionId (1535)
  sectionNo (344)
  orderNo 348
  title `Statement that company is in liquidation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_344_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_344_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=1535&sectionno=344&orderno=348&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_344_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where a company is being wound up, whether`
  line `by the Tribunal or voluntarily, every invoice, order for goods or business letter issued by or on behalf of`
  line `the company or a Company Liquidator of the company, or a receiver or manager of the property of the`
  line `company, being a document on or in which the name of the company appears, shall contain a statement`
  line `that the company is being wound up.`
  line
  line `(2) If a company contravenes the provisions of sub-section (1), the company, and every officer of the`
  line `company, the Company Liquidator and any receiver or manager, who wilfully authorises or permits the`
  line `non-compliance, shall be punishable with fine which shall not be less than fifty thousand rupees but`
  line `which may extend to three lakh rupees.`
obj_root_law_sections_344_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_345:
  sectionId (1536)
  sectionNo (345)
  orderNo 349
  title `Books and papers of company to be evidence.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_345_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_345_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=1536&sectionno=345&orderno=349&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_345_content:
  string
  line `Where a company is being wound up, all`
  line `books and papers of the company and of the Company Liquidator shall, as between the contributories of`
  line `the company, be prima facie evidence of the truth of all matters purporting to be recorded therein.`
obj_root_law_sections_345_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_346:
  sectionId (1537)
  sectionNo (346)
  orderNo 350
  title `Inspection of books and papers by creditors and contributories.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_346_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_346_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=1537&sectionno=346&orderno=350&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_346_content:
  string
  line `(1) At any time after the`
  line `making of an order for the winding up of a company by the Tribunal, any creditor or contributory of the`
  line `company may inspect the books and papers of the company only in accordance with, and subject to such`
  line `rules as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(2) Nothing contained in sub-section (1) shall exclude or restrict any rights conferred by any law for`
  line `the time being in force--`
  line
  line `(a) on the Central Government or a State Government;`
  line
  line `(b) on any authority or officer thereof; or`
  line
  line `(c) on any person acting under the authority of any such Government or of any such authority or`
  line officer.
obj_root_law_sections_346_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_347:
  sectionId (49242)
  sectionNo (347)
  orderNo 351
  title `Disposal of books and papers of company`
  content obj_root_law_sections_347_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_347_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=49242&sectionno=347&orderno=351&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_347_content:
  string
  line `^1 (1) When the affairs of a company have been completely wound up and it is about to be dissolved, the books and papers of such company and those of the Company Liquidator may be disposed of in such manner as the Tribunal directs.]`
  line
  line `(2) After the expiry of five years from the dissolution of the company, no responsibility shall devolve on the company, the Company Liquidator, or any person to whom the custody of the books and papers has been entrusted, by reason of any book or paper not being forthcoming to any person claiming to be interested therein.`
  line
  line `(3) The Central Government may, by rules,--`
  line
  line `(a) prevent for such period as it thinks proper the destruction of the books and papers of a company which has been wound up and of its Company Liquidator; and`
  line
  line `(b) enable any creditor or contributory of the company to make representations to the Central Government in respect of the matters specified in clause (a) and to appeal to the Tribunal from any order which may be made by the Central Government in the matter.`
  line
  line `(4) If any person acts in contravention of any rule framed or an order made under sub-section (3), he shall be punishable ^2*** with fine which may extend to ^3[fifty thousand rupees].`
obj_root_law_sections_347_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 31 of 2016, s. 255 and the Eleventh Schedule, for sub-section (1) (w.e.f. 15-11-2016).`
  line
  line `2. The words "with imprisonment for a term which may extend to six months or" omitted by Act 29 of 2020, s. 49 (w.e.f. 21-12-`
  line `2020).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by s. 49, ibid., for "fifty thousand rupees, or with both" (w.e.f. 21-12-2020)`
obj_root_law_sections_348:
  sectionId (49243)
  sectionNo (348)
  orderNo 352
  title `Information as to pending liquidations.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_348_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_348_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=49243&sectionno=348&orderno=352&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_348_content:
  string
  line `^1[(1) If the winding up of a company is not`
  line `concluded within one year after its commencement, the Company Liquidator shall, unless he is exempted`
  line `from so doing, either wholly or in part by the Central Government, within two months of the expiry of`
  line `such year and thereafter until the winding up is concluded, at intervals of not more than one year or at`
  line `such shorter intervals, if any, as may be prescribed, file a statement in such form containing such`
  line `particulars as may be prescribed, duly audited, by a person qualified to act as auditor of the company,`
  line `with respect to the proceedings in, and position of, the liquidation, with the Tribunal:`
  line
  line `Provided that no such audit as is referred to in this sub-section shall be necessary where the`
  line `provisions of section 294 apply.]`
  line
  line `(2) When the statement is filed with the Tribunal under clause (a) of sub-section (1), a copy shall`
  line `simultaneously be filed with the Registrar and shall be kept by him along with the other records of the`
  line company.
  line
  line `(3) Where a statement referred to in sub-section (1) relates to a Government company in liquidation,`
  line `the Company Liquidator shall forward a copy thereof--`
  line
  line `(a) to the Central Government, if that Government is a member of the Government company;`
  line
  line `(b) to any State Government, if that Government is a member of the Government company; or`
  line
  line `(c) to the Central Government and any State Government, if both the Governments are members`
  line `of the Government company.`
  line
  line `(4) Any person stating himself in writing to be a creditor or contributory of the company shall be`
  line `entitled, by himself or by his agent, at all reasonable times, on payment of the prescribed fee, to inspect`
  line `the statement referred to in sub-section (1), and to receive a copy thereof or an extract there from.`
  line
  line `(5) Any person fraudulently stating himself to be a creditor or contributory under sub-section (4) shall`
  line `be deemed to be guilty of an offence under section 182 of the Indian Penal Code (45 of 1860), and shall,`
  line `on the application of the Company Liquidator, be punishable accordingly.`
  line
  line `^2[(6) Where a Company Liquidator, who is an insolvency professional registered under the`
  line `Insolvency and Bankrupt Code, 2016 (31 of 2016) is in default in complying with the provisions of this`
  line `section, then such default shall be deemed to be a contravention of the provisions of the said Code, and`
  line `the rules and regulations made thereunder for the purpose of proceedings under chapter VI of Part IV of`
  line `that Code.]`
  line
  line `^3* * * * *`
obj_root_law_sections_348_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by s. 255 and the Eleventh Schedule, ibid., for sub-section (1) (w.e.f. 15-11-2016).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 29 of 2020, s. 50, for sub-section (6) (w.e.f. 21-12-2020).`
  line
  line `3. Sub-section (7) omitted by s. 50, ibid. (w.e.f. 21-12-2020).`
obj_root_law_sections_349:
  sectionId (49244)
  sectionNo (349)
  orderNo 353
  title `Official Liquidator to make payments into public account of India.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_349_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_349_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=49244&sectionno=349&orderno=353&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_349_content:
  string
  line `Every Official`
  line `Liquidator shall, in such manner and at such times as may be prescribed, pay the monies received by him`
  line `as Official Liquidator of any company, into the public account of India in the Reserve Bank of India.`
obj_root_law_sections_349_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_350:
  sectionId (49245)
  sectionNo (350)
  orderNo 354
  title `Company Liquidator to deposit monies into scheduled bank`
  content obj_root_law_sections_350_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_350_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=49245&sectionno=350&orderno=354&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_350_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every Company`
  line `Liquidator of a company shall, in such manner and at such times as may be prescribed, deposit the monies`
  line `received by him in his capacity as such in a scheduled bank to the credit of a special bank account opened`
  line `by him in that behalf:`
  line
  line `Provided that if the Tribunal considers that it is advantageous for the creditors or contributories or the`
  line `company, it may permit the account to be opened in such other bank specified by it.`
  line
  line `(2) If any Company Liquidator at any time retains for more than ten days a sum exceeding five`
  line `thousand rupees or such other amount as the Tribunal may, on the application of the Company Liquidator,`
  line `authorise him to retain, then, unless he explains the retention to the satisfaction of the Tribunal, he shall`
  line
  line `(a) pay interest on the amount so retained in excess, at the rate of twelve per cent. per annum and`
  line `also pay such penalty as may be determined by the Tribunal;`
  line
  line `(b) be liable to pay any expenses occasioned by reason of his default; and`
  line
  line `(c) also be liable to have all or such part of his remuneration, as the Tribunal may consider just`
  line `and proper, disallowed, or may also be removed from his office.`
obj_root_law_sections_350_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_351:
  sectionId (49246)
  sectionNo (351)
  orderNo 355
  title `Liquidator not to deposit monies into private banking account.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_351_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_351_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=49246&sectionno=351&orderno=355&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_351_content:
  string
  line `Neither the Official`
  line `Liquidator nor the Company Liquidator of a company shall deposit any monies received by him in his`
  line `capacity as such into any private banking account.`
obj_root_law_sections_351_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_352:
  sectionId (49247)
  sectionNo (352)
  orderNo 356
  title `Company Liquidation Dividend and Undistributed Assets Account`
  content obj_root_law_sections_352_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_352_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=49247&sectionno=352&orderno=356&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_352_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where any`
  line `company is being wound up and the liquidator has in his hands or under his control any money`
  line representing--
  line
  line `(a) dividends payable to any creditor but which had remained unpaid for six months after the date`
  line `on which they were declared; or`
  line
  line `(b) assets refundable to any contributory which have remained undistributed for six months after`
  line `the date on which they become refundable,`
  line
  line `the liquidator shall forthwith deposit the said money into a separate special account to be known as the`
  line `Company Liquidation Dividend and Undistributed Assets Account maintained in a scheduled bank.`
  line
  line `(2) The liquidator shall, on the dissolution of the company, pay into the Company Liquidation`
  line `Dividend and Undistributed Assets Account any money representing unpaid dividends or undistributed`
  line `assets in his hands at the date of dissolution.`
  line
  line `(3) The liquidator shall, when making any payment referred to in sub-sections (1) and (2), furnish to`
  line `the Registrar, a statement in the prescribed form, setting forth, in respect of all sums included in such`
  line `payment, the nature of the sums, the names and last known addresses of the persons entitled to participate`
  line `therein, the amount to which each is entitled and the nature of his claim thereto, and such other particulars`
  line `as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(4) The liquidator shall be entitled to a receipt from the scheduled bank for any money paid to it under`
  line `sub-sections (1) and (2), and such receipt shall be an effectual discharge of the Company Liquidator in`
  line `respect thereof.`
  line
  line `(5) Where a company is being wound up voluntarily, the Company Liquidator shall, when filing a`
  line `statement in pursuance of sub-section (1) of section 348, indicate the sum of money which is payable`
  line `under sub-sections (1) and (2) of this section during the six months preceding the date on which the said`
  line `statement is prepared, and shall, within fourteen days of the date of filing the said statement, pay that sum`
  line `into the Company Liquidation Dividend and Undistributed Assets Account.`
  line
  line `(6) Any person claiming to be entitled to any money paid into the Company Liquidation Dividend`
  line `and Undistributed Assets Account, whether paid in pursuance of this section or under the provisions of`
  line `any previous company law may apply to the Registrar for payment thereof, and the Registrar, if satisfied`
  line `that the person claiming is entitled, may make the payment to that person of the sum due:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Registrar shall settle the claim of such person within a period of sixty days from the`
  line `date of receipt of such claim, failing which the Registrar shall make a report to the Regional Director`
  line `giving reasons of such failure.`
  line
  line `(7) Any money paid into the Company Liquidation Dividend and Undistributed Assets Account in`
  line `pursuance of this section, which remains unclaimed thereafter for a period of fifteen years, shall be`
  line `transferred to the general revenue account of the Central Government, but a claim to any money so`
  line `transferred may be preferred under sub-section (6) and shall be dealt with as if such transfer had not been`
  line `made and the order, if any, for payment on the claim will be treated as an order for refund of revenue.`
  line
  line `(8) Any liquidator retaining any money which should have been paid by him into the Company`
  line `Liquidation Dividend and Undistributed Assets Account under this section shall--`
  line
  line `(a) pay interest on the amount so retained at the rate of twelve per cent. per annum and also pay`
  line `such penalty as may be determined by the Registrar:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Central Government may in any proper case remit either in part or in whole the`
  line `amount of interest which the liquidator is required to pay under this clause;`
  line
  line `(b) be liable to pay any expenses occasioned by reason of his default; and`
  line
  line `(c) where the winding up is by the Tribunal, also be liable to have all or such part of his`
  line `remuneration, as the Tribunal may consider just and proper, to be disallowed, and to be removed from`
  line `his office by the Tribunal.`
obj_root_law_sections_352_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_353:
  sectionId (49248)
  sectionNo (353)
  orderNo 357
  title `Liquidator to make returns, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_353_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_353_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=49248&sectionno=353&orderno=357&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_353_content:
  string
  line `(1) If any Company Liquidator who has made any default`
  line `in filing, delivering or making any return, account or other document, or in giving any notice which he is`
  line `by law required to file, deliver, make or give, fails to make good the default within fourteen days after the`
  line `service on him of a notice requiring him to do so, the Tribunal may, on an application made to it by any`
  line `contributory or creditor of the company or by the Registrar, make an order directing the Company`
  line `Liquidator to make good the default within such time as may be specified in the order.`
  line
  line `(2) Any order under sub-section (1) may provide that all costs of, and incidental to, the application`
  line `shall be borne by the Company Liquidator.`
  line
  line `(3) Nothing in this section shall prejudice the operation of any enactment imposing penalties on a`
  line `Company Liquidator in respect of any such default as aforesaid.`
obj_root_law_sections_353_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_354:
  sectionId (49249)
  sectionNo (354)
  orderNo 358
  title `Meetings to ascertain wishes of creditors or contributories`
  content obj_root_law_sections_354_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_354_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=49249&sectionno=354&orderno=358&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_354_content:
  string
  line `(1) In all matters relating to the`
  line `winding up of a company, the Tribunal may--`
  line
  line `(a) have regard to the wishes of creditors or contributories of the company, as proved to it by any`
  line `sufficient evidence;`
  line
  line `(b) if it thinks fit for the purpose of ascertaining those wishes, direct meetings of the creditors or`
  line `contributories to be called, held and conducted in such manner as the Tribunal may direct; and`
  line
  line `(c) appoint a person to act as chairman of any such meeting and to report the result thereof to the`
  line Tribunal.
  line
  line `(2) While ascertaining the wishes of creditors under sub-section (1), regard shall be had to the value`
  line `of each debt of the creditor.`
  line
  line `(3) While ascertaining the wishes of contributories under sub-section (1), regard shall be had to the`
  line `number of votes which may be cast by each contributory.`
obj_root_law_sections_354_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_355:
  sectionId (49250)
  sectionNo (355)
  orderNo 359
  title `Court, tribunal or person, etc., before whom affidavit may be sworn.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_355_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_355_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=49250&sectionno=355&orderno=359&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_355_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any affidavit`
  line `required to be sworn under the provisions, or for the purposes, of this Chapter may be sworn--`
  line
  line `(a) in India before any court, tribunal, judge or person lawfully authorised to take and receive`
  line `affidavits; and`
  line
  line `(b) in any other country before any court, judge or person lawfully authorised to take and receive`
  line `affidavits in that country or before an Indian diplomatic or consular officer.`
  line
  line `(2) All tribunals, judges, Justices, commissioners and persons acting judicially in India shall take`
  line `judicial notice of the seal, stamp or signature, as the case may be, of any such court, tribunal, judge,`
  line `person, diplomatic or consular officer, attached, appended or subscribed to any such affidavit or to any`
  line `other document to be used for the purposes of this Chapter.`
obj_root_law_sections_355_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_356:
  sectionId (49251)
  sectionNo (356)
  orderNo 360
  title `Power of Tribunal to declare dissolution of company void.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_356_content
  footnotes `1. Subs.by Act 29 of 2020, s. 51, for sub-section (2) (w.e.f. 21-12-2020).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=49251&sectionno=356&orderno=360&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_356_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where a company has been dissolved, whether in pursuance of this Chapter or of section 232 or otherwise, the Tribunal may at any time within two years of the date of the dissolution, on application by the Company Liquidator of the company or by any other person who appears to the Tribunal to be interested, make an order, upon such terms as the Tribunal thinks fit, declaring the dissolution to be void, and thereupon such proceedings may be taken as if the company had not been dissolved.`
  line
  line `^1 [(2) The Tribunal shall--`
  line
  line `(a) forward a copy of the order, within thirty days from the date thereof, to the Registrar who shall record the same; and`
  line
  line `(b) direct the Company Liquidator or the person on whose application the order was made, to file a certified copy of the order, within thirty days from the date thereof such further period as allowed by the Tribunal, with the Registrar who shall record the same.]`
obj_root_law_sections_357:
  sectionId (49252)
  sectionNo (357)
  orderNo 361
  title `Commencement of winding up by Tribunal.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_357_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 31 of 2016, s. 255 and the Eleventh Schedule, for section 357 (w.e.f. 15-11-2016).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=49252&sectionno=357&orderno=361&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_357_content:
  string
  line `^1[357. Commencement of winding up by Tribunal.-- The winding up of a company by the Tribunal`
  line `under this Act shall be deemed to commence at the time of the presentation of the petition for the winding`
  line up.]
obj_root_law_sections_358:
  sectionId (49253)
  sectionNo (358)
  orderNo 362
  title `Exclusion of certain time in computing period of limitation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_358_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_358_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=49253&sectionno=358&orderno=362&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_358_content:
  string
  line `Notwithstanding anything in`
  line `the Limitation Act, 1963 (36 of 1963), or in any other law for the time being in force, in computing the`
  line `period of limitation specified for any suit or application in the name and on behalf of a company which is`
  line `being wound up by the Tribunal, the period from the date of commencement of the winding up of the`
  line `company to a period of one year immediately following the date of the winding up order shall be`
  line excluded.
obj_root_law_sections_358_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_359:
  sectionId (49254)
  sectionNo (359)
  orderNo 363
  title `Appointment of Official Liquidator`
  content obj_root_law_sections_359_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_359_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=49254&sectionno=359&orderno=363&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_359_content:
  string
  line `(1) For the purposes of this Act, so far as it relates to`
  line `the winding up of companies by the Tribunal, the Central Government may appoint as many Official`
  line `Liquidators, Joint, Deputy or Assistant Official Liquidators as it may consider necessary to discharge the`
  line `functions of the Official Liquidator.`
  line
  line `(2) The liquidators appointed under sub-section (1) shall be whole-time officers of the Central`
  line Government.
  line
  line `(3) The salary and other allowances of the Official Liquidator, Joint Official Liquidator, Deputy`
  line `Official Liquidator and Assistant Official Liquidator shall be paid by the Central Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_359_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_360:
  sectionId (49255)
  sectionNo (360)
  orderNo 364
  title `Powers and functions of Official Liquidator.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_360_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_360_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=49255&sectionno=360&orderno=364&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_360_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Official Liquidator shall exercise such`
  line `powers and perform such duties as the Central Government may prescribe.`
  line
  line `(2) Without prejudice to the provisions of sub-section (1), the Official Liquidator may--`
  line
  line `(a) exercise all or any of the powers as may be exercised by a Company Liquidator under the`
  line `provisions of this Act; and`
  line
  line `(b) conduct inquiries or investigations, if directed by the Tribunal or the Central Government, in`
  line `respect of matters arising out of winding up proceedings.`
obj_root_law_sections_360_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_361:
  sectionId (49256)
  sectionNo (361)
  orderNo 365
  title `Summary procedure for liquidation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_361_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_361_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=49256&sectionno=361&orderno=365&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_361_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where the company to be wound up under this`
  line Chapter,--
  line
  line `(i) has assets of book value not exceeding one crore rupees; and`
  line
  line `(ii) belongs to such class or classes of companies as may be prescribed,`
  line
  line `the Central Government may order it to be wound up by summary procedure provided under this Part.`
  line
  line `(2) Where an order under sub-section (1) is made, the Central Government shall appoint the Official`
  line `Liquidator as the liquidator of the company.`
  line
  line `(3) The Official Liquidator shall forthwith take into his custody or control all assets, effects and`
  line `actionable claims to which the company is or appears to be entitled.`
  line
  line `(4) The Official Liquidator shall, within thirty days of his appointment, submit a report to the Central`
  line `Government in such manner and form, as may be prescribed, including a report whether in his opinion,`
  line `any fraud has been committed in promotion, formation or management of the affairs of the company or`
  line not.
  line
  line `(5) On receipt of the report under sub-section (4), if the Central Government is satisfied that any fraud`
  line `has been committed by the promoters, directors or any other officer of the company, it may direct further`
  line `investigation into the affairs of the company and that a report shall be submitted within such time as may`
  line `be specified.`
  line
  line `(6) After considering the investigation report under sub-section (5), the Central Government may`
  line `order that winding up may be proceeded under Part I of this Chapter or under the provision of this Part.`
obj_root_law_sections_361_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_362:
  sectionId (49257)
  sectionNo (362)
  orderNo 366
  title `Sale of assets and recovery of debts due to company.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_362_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_362_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=49257&sectionno=362&orderno=366&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_362_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Official Liquidator shall`
  line `expeditiously dispose of all the assets whether movable or immovable within sixty days of his`
  line appointment.
  line
  line `(2) The Official Liquidator shall serve a notice within thirty days of his appointment calling upon the`
  line `debtors of the company or the contributories, as the case may be, to deposit within thirty days with him`
  line `the amount payable to the company.`
  line
  line `(3) Where any debtor does not deposit the amount under sub-section (2), the Central Government`
  line `may, on an application made to it by the Official Liquidator, pass such orders as it thinks fit.`
  line
  line `(4) The amount recovered under this section by the Official Liquidator shall be deposited in`
  line `accordance with the provisions of section 349.`
obj_root_law_sections_362_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_363:
  sectionId (49258)
  sectionNo (363)
  orderNo 367
  title `Settlement of claims of creditors by Official Liquidator.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_363_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_363_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=49258&sectionno=363&orderno=367&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_363_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Official Liquidator within`
  line `thirty days of his appointment shall call upon the creditors of the company to prove their claims in such`
  line `manner as may be prescribed, within thirty days of the receipt of such call.`
  line
  line `(2) The Official Liquidator shall prepare a list of claims of creditors in such manner as may be`
  line `prescribed and each creditor shall be communicated of the claims accepted or rejected along with reasons`
  line `to be recorded in writing.`
obj_root_law_sections_363_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_364:
  sectionId (49259)
  sectionNo (364)
  orderNo 368
  title `Appeal by creditor`
  content obj_root_law_sections_364_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_364_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=49259&sectionno=364&orderno=368&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_364_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any creditor aggrieved by the decision of the Official Liquidator`
  line `under section 363 may file an appeal before the Central Government within thirty days of such decision.`
  line
  line `(2) The Central Government may after calling the report from the Official Liquidator either dismiss`
  line `the appeal or modify the decision of the Official Liquidator.`
  line
  line `(3) The Official Liquidator shall make payment to the creditors whose claims have been accepted.`
  line
  line `(4) The Central Government may, at any stage during settlement of claims, if considers necessary,`
  line `refer the matter to the Tribunal for necessary orders.`
obj_root_law_sections_364_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_365:
  sectionId (49260)
  sectionNo (365)
  orderNo 369
  title `Order of dissolution of company`
  content obj_root_law_sections_365_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_365_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=49260&sectionno=365&orderno=369&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_365_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Official Liquidator shall, if he is satisfied that the`
  line `company is finally wound up, submit a final report to--`
  line
  line `(i) the Central Government, in case no reference was made to the Tribunal under sub-section (4)`
  line `of section 364; and`
  line
  line `(ii) in any other case, the Central Government and the Tribunal.`
  line
  line `(2) The Central Government, or as the case may be, the Tribunal on receipt of such report shall order`
  line `that the company be dissolved.`
  line
  line `(3) Where an order is made under sub-section (2), the Registrar shall strike off the name of the`
  line `company from the register of companies and publish a notification to this effect.`
obj_root_law_sections_365_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_366:
  sectionId (49261)
  sectionNo (366)
  orderNo 370
  title `Companies capable of being registered`
  content obj_root_law_sections_366_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_366_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=49261&sectionno=366&orderno=370&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_366_content:
  string
  line `.(1) For the purposes of this Part, the word`
  line `"company" includes any partnership firm, limited liability partnership, cooperative society, society or any`
  line `other business entity formed under any other law for the time being in force which applies for registration`
  line `under this Part.`
  line
  line `(2) With the exceptions and subject to the provisions contained in this section, any company formed,`
  line `whether before or after the commencement of this Act, in pursuance of any Act of Parliament other than`
  line `this Act or of any other law for the time being in force or being otherwise duly constituted according to`
  line `law, and consisting of ^1[two or more members], may at any time register under this Act as an unlimited`
  line `company, or as a company limited by shares, or as a company limited by guarantee, in such manner as`
  line `may be prescribed and the registration shall not be invalid by reason only that it has taken place with a`
  line `view to the company's being wound up:`
  line
  line `Provided that--`
  line
  line `(i) a company registered under the Indian Companies Act, 1882 (6 of 1882) or under the Indian`
  line `Companies Act, 1913 (7 of 1913) or the Companies Act, 1956 (1 of 1956), shall not register in`
  line `pursuance of this section;`
  line
  line `(ii) a company having the liability of its members limited by any Act of Parliament other than this`
  line `Act or by any other law for the time being in force, shall not register in pursuance of this section as an`
  line `unlimited company or as a company limited by guarantee;`
  line
  line `(iii) a company shall be registered in pursuance of this section as a company limited by shares`
  line `only if it has a permanent paid-up or nominal share capital of fixed amount divided into shares, also`
  line `of fixed amount, or held and transferable as stock, or divided and held partly in the one way and`
  line `partly in the other, and formed on the principle of having for its members the holders of those shares`
  line `or that stock, and no other persons;`
  line
  line `(iv) a company shall not register in pursuance of this section without the assent of a majority of`
  line `such of its members as are present in person, or where proxies are allowed, by proxy, at a general`
  line `meeting summoned for the purpose;`
  line
  line `(v) where a company not having the liability of its members limited by any Act of Parliament or`
  line `any other law for the time being in force is about to register as a limited company, the majority`
  line `required to assent as aforesaid shall consist of not less than three-fourths of the members present in`
  line `person, or where proxies are allowed, by proxy, at the meeting;`
  line
  line `(vi) where a company is about to register as a company limited by guarantee, the assent to its`
  line `being so registered shall be accompanied by a resolution declaring that each member undertakes to`
  line `contribute to the assets of the company, in the event of its being wound up while he is a member, or`
  line `within one year after he ceases to be a member, for payment of the debts and liabilities of the`
  line `company or of such debts and liabilities as may have been contracted before he ceases to be a`
  line `member, and of the costs, charges and expenses of winding up, and for the adjustment of the rights of`
  line `the contributories among themselves, such amount as may be required, not exceeding a specified`
  line amount.
  line
  line `^2[(vii) a company with less than seven members shall register as a private company.]`
  line
  line `(3) In computing any majority required for the purposes of sub-section (1), when a poll is demanded,`
  line `regard shall be had to the number of votes to which each member is entitled according to the regulations`
  line `of the company.`
obj_root_law_sections_366_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 1 of 2018, s. 75, for "seven or more members" (w.e.f. 15-8-2018).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by s. 75, ibid. (w.e.f. 15-8-2018).`
obj_root_law_sections_367:
  sectionId (49262)
  sectionNo (367)
  orderNo 371
  title `Certificate of registration of existing companies`
  content obj_root_law_sections_367_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_367_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=49262&sectionno=367&orderno=371&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_367_content:
  string
  line `On compliance with the requirements of`
  line `this Chapter with respect to registration, and on payment of such fees, if any, as are payable under section`
  line `403, the Registrar shall certify under his hand that the company applying for registration is incorporated`
  line `as a company under this Act, and in the case of a limited company that it is limited and thereupon the`
  line `company shall be so incorporated.`
obj_root_law_sections_367_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_368:
  sectionId (49263)
  sectionNo (368)
  orderNo 372
  title `Vesting of property on registration.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_368_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_368_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=49263&sectionno=368&orderno=372&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_368_content:
  string
  line `All property, movable and immovable (including`
  line `actionable claims), belonging to or vested in a company at the date of its registration in pursuance of this`
  line `Part, shall, on such registration, pass to and vest in the company as incorporated under this Act for all the`
  line `estate and interest of the company therein.`
obj_root_law_sections_368_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_369:
  sectionId (49264)
  sectionNo (369)
  orderNo 373
  title `Saving of existing liabilities`
  content obj_root_law_sections_369_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_369_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=49264&sectionno=369&orderno=373&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_369_content:
  string
  line `The registration of a company in pursuance of this Part shall not`
  line `affect its rights or liabilities in respect of any debt or obligation incurred, or any contract entered into, by,`
  line `to, with, or on behalf of, the company before registration.`
obj_root_law_sections_369_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_370:
  sectionId (49265)
  sectionNo (370)
  orderNo 374
  title `Continuation of pending legal proceedings.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_370_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 31 of 2016, s. 255 and the Eleventh Schedule (w.e.f. 15-11-2016).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=49265&sectionno=370&orderno=374&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_370_content:
  string
  line `All suits and other legal proceedings taken by or`
  line `against the company, or any public officer or member thereof, which are pending at the time of the`
  line `registration of a company in pursuance of this Part, may be continued in the same manner as if the`
  line `registration had not taken place:`
  line
  line `Provided that execution shall not issue against the property or persons of any individual member of`
  line `the company on any decree or order obtained in any such suit or proceeding; but, in the event of the`
  line `property of the company being insufficient to satisfy the decree or order, an order may be obtained for`
  line `winding up the company ^1[in accordance with the provisions of this Act or of the Insolvency and`
  line `Bankruptcy Code, 2016 (31 of 2016)].`
obj_root_law_sections_371:
  sectionId (49266)
  sectionNo (371)
  orderNo 375
  title `Effect of registration under this Part.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_371_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_371_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=49266&sectionno=371&orderno=375&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_371_content:
  string
  line `(1) When a company is registered in pursuance of this`
  line `Part, sub-sections (2) to (7) shall apply.`
  line
  line `(2) All provisions contained in any Act of Parliament or any other law for the time being in force, or`
  line `other instrument constituting or regulating the company, including, in the case of a company registered as`
  line `a company limited by guarantee, the resolution declaring the amount of the guarantee, shall be deemed to`
  line `be conditions and regulations of the company, in the same manner and with the same incidents as if so`
  line `much thereof as would, if the company had been formed under this Act, have been required to be inserted`
  line `in the memorandum, were contained in a registered memorandum, and the residue thereof were contained`
  line `in registered articles.`
  line
  line `(3) All the provisions of this Act shall apply to the company and the members, contributories and`
  line `creditors thereof, in the same manner in all respects as if it had been formed under this Act, subject as`
  line `follows:--`
  line
  line `(a) Table F in Schedule I shall not apply unless and except in so far as it is adopted by special`
  line resolution;
  line
  line `(b) the provisions of this Act relating to the numbering of shares shall not apply to any company`
  line `whose shares are not numbered;`
  line
  line `(c) in the event of the company being wound up, every person shall be a contributory, in respect`
  line `of the debts and liabilities of the company contracted before registration, who is liable to pay or`
  line `contribute to the payment of any debt or liability of the company contracted before registration, or to`
  line `pay or contribute to the payment of any sum for the adjustment of the rights of the members among`
  line `themselves in respect of any such debt or liability, or to pay or contribute to the payment of the costs,`
  line `charges and expenses of winding up the company, so far as relates to such debts or liabilities as`
  line aforesaid;
  line
  line `(d) in the event of the company being wound up, every contributory shall be liable to contribute`
  line `to the assets of the company, in the course of the winding up, all sums due from him in respect of any`
  line `such liability as aforesaid; and in the event of the death or insolvency of any contributory, the`
  line `provisions of this Act with respect to the legal representatives of deceased contributories, or with`
  line `respect to the assignees of insolvent contributories, as the case may be, shall apply.`
  line
  line `(4) The provisions of this Act with respect to--`
  line
  line `(a) the registration of an unlimited company as a limited company;`
  line
  line `(b) the powers of an unlimited company on registration as a limited company, to increase the`
  line `nominal amount of its share capital and to provide that a portion of its share capital shall not be`
  line `capable of being called-up except in the event of winding up;`
  line
  line `(c) the power of a limited company to determine that a portion of its share capital shall not be`
  line `capable of being called-up except in the event of winding up,`
  line
  line `shall apply, notwithstanding anything in any Act of Parliament or any other law for the time being in`
  line `force, or other instrument constituting or regulating the company.`
  line
  line `(5) Nothing in this section shall authorise the company to alter any such provisions contained in any`
  line `instrument constituting or regulating the company as would, if the company had originally been formed`
  line `under this Act, have been required to be contained in the memorandum and are not authorised to be`
  line `altered by this Act.`
  line
  line `(6) None of the provisions of this Act (apart from those of section 242) shall derogate from any power`
  line `of altering its constitution or regulations which may be vested in the company, by virtue of any Act of`
  line `Parliament or any other law for the time being in force, or other instrument constituting or regulating the`
  line company.
  line
  line `(7) In this section, the expression instrument includes deed of settlement, deed of partnership, or`
  line `limited liability partnership.`
obj_root_law_sections_371_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_372:
  sectionId (49267)
  sectionNo (372)
  orderNo 376
  title `Power of Court to stay or restrain proceedings`
  content obj_root_law_sections_372_content
  footnotes `1. The proviso ins. by Act 31 of 2016, s. 255 and the Eleventh Schedule (w.e.f. 15-11-2016).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=49267&sectionno=372&orderno=376&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_372_content:
  string
  line `The provisions of this Act ^1[or of the`
  line `Insolvency and Bankruptcy Code, 2016 (31 of 2016), as the case may be,] with respect to staying and`
  line `restraining suits and other legal proceedings against a company at any time after the presentation of a`
  line `petition for winding up and before the making of a winding up order, shall, in the case of a company`
  line `registered in pursuance of this Part, where the application to stay or restrain is by a creditor, extend to`
  line `suits and other legal proceedings against any contributory of the company.`
obj_root_law_sections_373:
  sectionId (49268)
  sectionNo (373)
  orderNo 377
  title `Suits stayed on winding up order`
  content obj_root_law_sections_373_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_373_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=49268&sectionno=373&orderno=377&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_373_content:
  string
  line `Where an order has been made for winding up, or a`
  line `provisional liquidator has been appointed for, a company registered in pursuance of this Part, no suit or`
  line `other legal proceeding shall be proceeded with or commenced against the company or any contributory of`
  line `the company in respect of any debt of the company, except by leave of the Tribunal and except on such`
  line `terms as the Tribunal may impose.`
obj_root_law_sections_373_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_374:
  sectionId (49269)
  sectionNo (374)
  orderNo 378
  title `Obligations of companies registering under this Part`
  content obj_root_law_sections_374_content
  footnotes `1. The proviso ins. by Act 1 of 2018, s. 76 (w.e.f. 15-8-2018).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=49269&sectionno=374&orderno=378&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_374_content:
  string
  line `Every company which is seeking`
  line `registration under this Part shall,--`
  line
  line `(a) ensure that secured creditors of the company, prior to its registration under this Part, have`
  line `either consented to or have given their no objection to company's registration under this Part;`
  line
  line `(b) publish in a newspaper, advertisement one in English and one in vernacular language in such`
  line `form as may be prescribed giving notice about registration under this Part, seeking objections and`
  line `address them suitably;`
  line
  line `(c) file an affidavit, duly not arised, from all the members or partners to provide that in the event`
  line `of registration under this Part, necessary documents or papers shall be submitted to the registering or`
  line `other authority with which the company was earlier registered, for its dissolution as partnership firm,`
  line `limited liability partnership, cooperative society, society or any other business entity, as the case may`
  line be.
  line
  line `(d) comply with such other conditions as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `^1[Provided that upon registration as a company under this Part a limited liability partnership incorporated`
  line `under the Limited Liability Partnership Act, 2008 (6 of 2009) shall be deemed to have been dissolved under that Act without any further act or deed.]`
obj_root_law_sections_375:
  sectionId (49270)
  sectionNo (375)
  orderNo 379
  title `Winding up of unregistered companies`
  content obj_root_law_sections_375_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_375_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=49270&sectionno=375&orderno=379&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_375_content:
  string
  line `(1) Subject to the provisions of this Part, any`
  line `unregistered company may be wound up under this Act, in such manner as may be prescribed, and all the`
  line `provisions of this Act, with respect to winding up shall apply to an unregistered company, with the`
  line `exceptions and additions mentioned in sub-sections (2) to (4).`
  line
  line `(2) No unregistered company shall be wound up under this Act voluntarily.`
  line
  line `(3) An unregistered company may be wound up under the following circumstances, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) if the company is dissolved, or has ceased to carry on business, or is carrying on business only`
  line `for the purpose of winding up its affairs;`
  line
  line `(b) if the company is unable to pay its debts;`
  line
  line `(c) if the Tribunal is of opinion that it is just and equitable that the company should be wound up.`
  line
  line `(4) An unregistered company shall, for the purposes of this Act, be deemed to be unable to pay its`
  line debts--
  line
  line `(a) if a creditor, by assignment or otherwise, to whom the company is indebted in a sum`
  line `exceeding one lakh rupees then due, has served on the company, by leaving at its principal place of`
  line `business, or by delivering to the secretary, or some director, manager or principal officer of the`
  line `company, or by otherwise serving in such manner as the Tribunal may approve or direct, a demand`
  line `under his hand requiring the company to pay the sum so due, and the company has, for three weeks`
  line `after the service of the demand, neglected to pay the sum or to secure or compound for it to the`
  line `satisfaction of the creditor;`
  line
  line `(b) if any suit or other legal proceeding has been instituted against any member for any debt or`
  line `demand due, or claimed to be due, from the company, or from him in his character as a member, and`
  line `notice in writing of the institution of the suit or other legal proceeding having been served on the`
  line `company by leaving the same at its principal place of business or by delivering it to the secretary, or`
  line `some director, manager or principal officer of the company or by otherwise serving the same in such`
  line `manner as the Tribunal may approve or direct, the company has not, within ten days after service of`
  line `the notice,--`
  line
  line `(i) paid, secured or compounded for the debt or demand;`
  line
  line `(ii) procured the suit or other legal proceeding to be stayed; or`
  line
  line `(iii) indemnified the defendant to his satisfaction against the suit or other legal proceeding,`
  line `and against all costs, damages and expenses to be incurred by him by reason of the same;`
  line
  line `(c) if execution or other process issued on a decree or order of any Court or Tribunal in favour of`
  line `a creditor against the company, or any member thereof as such, or any person authorised to be sued as`
  line `nominal defendant on behalf of the company, is returned unsatisfied in whole or in part;`
  line
  line `(d) if it is otherwise proved to the satisfaction of the Tribunal that the company is unable to pay`
  line `its debts.`
  line
  line `Explanation.-- For the purposes of this Part, the expression unregistered company--`
  line
  line `(a) shall not include`
  line
  line `(i) a railway company incorporated under any Act of Parliament or other Indian law or any`
  line `Act of Parliament of the United Kingdom;`
  line
  line `(ii) a company registered under this Act; or`
  line
  line `(iii) a company registered under any previous companies law and not being a company the`
  line `registered office whereof was in Burma, Aden, Pakistan immediately before the separation of that`
  line `country from India; and`
  line
  line `(b) save as aforesaid, shall include any partnership firm, limited liability partnership or society or`
  line `co-operative society, association or company consisting of more than seven members at the time`
  line `when the petition for winding up the partnership firm, limited liability partnership or society or cooperative`
  line `society, association or company, as the case may be, is presented before the Tribunal.`
obj_root_law_sections_375_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_376:
  sectionId (49271)
  sectionNo (376)
  orderNo 380
  title `Power to wind up foreign companies although dissolved.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_376_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_376_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=49271&sectionno=376&orderno=380&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_376_content:
  string
  line `Where a body corporate`
  line `incorporated outside India which has been carrying on business in India, ceases to carry on business in`
  line `India, it may be wound up as an unregistered company under this Part, notwithstanding that the body`
  line `corporate has been dissolved or otherwise ceased to exist as such under or by virtue of the laws of the`
  line `country under which it was incorporated.`
obj_root_law_sections_376_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_377:
  sectionId (49272)
  sectionNo (377)
  orderNo 381
  title `Provisions of Chapter cumulative`
  content obj_root_law_sections_377_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_377_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=49272&sectionno=377&orderno=381&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_377_content:
  string
  line `(1) The provisions of this Part, with respect to`
  line `unregistered companies shall be in addition to and not in derogation of, any provisions hereinbefore in`
  line `this Act contained with respect to the winding up of companies by the Tribunal.`
  line
  line `(2) The Tribunal or Official Liquidator may exercise any powers or do any act in the case of`
  line `unregistered companies which might be exercised or done by the Tribunal or Official Liquidator in`
  line `winding up of companies formed and registered under this Act:`
  line
  line `Provided that an unregistered company shall not, except in the event of its being wound up, be`
  line `deemed to be a company under this Act, and then only to the extent provided by this Part.`
obj_root_law_sections_377_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_378:
  sectionId (49273)
  sectionNo (378)
  orderNo 382
  title `Saving and construction of enactments conferring power to wind up partnership firm, association or company, etc., in certain cases.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_378_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_378_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=49273&sectionno=378&orderno=382&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_378_content:
  string
  line `Nothing in this Part, shall affect the operation of any`
  line `enactment which provides for any partnership firm, limited liability partnership or society or co-operative`
  line `society, association or company being wound up, or being wound up as a company or as an unregistered`
  line `company, under the Companies Act, 1956 (1 of 1956), or any Act repealed by that Act:`
  line
  line `Provided that references in any such enactment to any provision contained in the Companies Act,`
  line `1956 (1 of 1956) or in any Act repealed by that Act shall be read as references to the corresponding`
  line `provision, if any, contained in this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_378_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_378_a:
  sectionId (52424)
  sectionNo 378A
  orderNo 383
  title Definitions
  content obj_root_law_sections_378_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 29 of 2020, s. 52 (w.e.f. 11-2-2021).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=52424&sectionno=378A&orderno=383&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_378_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[378A. Definitions.-- In this Chapter, unless the context otherwise requires,--`
  line
  line `(a) "active Member" means a Member who fulfils the quantum and period of patronage of the`
  line `Producer Company as may be required by the articles;`
  line
  line `(b) "Chief Executive" means an individual appointed as such under sub-section (1) of section`
  line 378W;
  line
  line `(c) "inter-State co-operative society" means a multi-State co-operative society as defined in clause`
  line `(p) of section 3 of the Multi-State Co-operative Societies Act, 2002 (39 of 2002) and includes any co-operative society registered under any other law for the time being in force, which has, subsequent to`
  line `its formation, extended any of its objects to more than one State by enlisting the participation of persons`
  line `or by extending any of its activities outside the State, whether directly or indirectly or through an`
  line `institution of which it is a constituent;`
  line
  line `(d) "limited return" means the maximum dividend as may be specified by the articles;`
  line
  line `(e) "Member" means a person or Producer Institution (whether incorporated or not) admitted as a`
  line `Member of a Producer Company and who retains the qualifications necessary for continuance as such;`
  line
  line `(f) "mutual assistance principles" means the principles set out in sub-section (2) of section 378G;`
  line
  line `(g) "officer" includes any director or Chief Executive or Secretary or any person in accordance`
  line `with whose directions or instructions part or whole of the business of the Producer Company is carried`
  line on;
  line
  line `(h) "patronage" means the use of services offered by the Producer Company to its Members by`
  line `participation in its business activities;`
  line
  line `(i) "patronage bonus" means payments made by a Producer Company out of its surplus income to`
  line `the Members in proportion to their respective patronage;`
  line
  line `(j) "primary produce" means --`
  line
  line `(i) produce of farmers, arising from agriculture (including animal husbandry, horticulture,`
  line `floriculture, pisciculture, viticulture, forestry, forest products, re-vegetation, bee raising and farming`
  line `plantation products), or from any other primary activity or service which promotes the interest of the`
  line `farmers or consumers; or`
  line
  line `(ii) produce of persons engaged in handloom, handicraft and other cottage industries; or`
  line
  line `(iii) any product resulting from any of the above activities, including by-products of such products;`
  line or
  line
  line `(iv) any product resulting from an ancillary activity that may assist or promote any of the aforesaid`
  line `activities or anything ancillary thereto; or`
  line
  line `(v) any activity which is intended to increase the production of anything referred to in sub-clauses`
  line `(i) to (iv) or improve the quality thereof;`
  line
  line `(k) "producer" means any person engaged in any activity connected with or relatable to any primary`
  line produce;
  line
  line `(l) "Producer Company" means a body corporate having objects or activities specified in section`
  line `378B and registered as Producer Company under this Act or under the Companies Act, 1956`
  line `(1 of 1956);`
  line
  line `(m) "Producer Institution" means a Producer Company or any other institution having only`
  line `producer or producers or Producer Company or Producer Companies as its member whether`
  line `incorporated or not having any of the objects referred to in section 378B and which agrees to make use`
  line `of the services of the Producer Company or Producer Companies as provided in its articles;`
  line
  line `(n) "withheld price" means part of the price due and payable for goods supplied by any Member to`
  line `the Producer Company; and as withheld by the Producer Company for payment on a subsequent date.]`
obj_root_law_sections_378_b:
  sectionId (52425)
  sectionNo 378B
  orderNo 384
  title `Objects of producer company.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_378_b_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 29 of 2020, s. 52 (w.e.f. 11-2-2021).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=52425&sectionno=378B&orderno=384&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_378_b_content:
  string
  line `^1[378B. Objects of Producer Company.--(1) The objects of the Producer Company shall relate to all`
  line `or any of the following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) production, harvesting, procurement, grading, pooling, handling, marketing, selling, export of`
  line `primary produce of the Members or import of goods or services for their benefit:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Producer Company may carry on any of the activities specified in this clause`
  line `either by itself or through other institution;`
  line
  line `(b) processing including preserving, drying, distilling, brewing, vinting, canning and packaging of`
  line `produce of its Members;`
  line
  line `(c) manufacture, sale or supply of machinery, equipment or consumables mainly to its Members;`
  line
  line `(d) providing education on the mutual assistance principles to its Members and others;`
  line
  line `(e) rendering technical services, consultancy services, training, research and development and all`
  line `other activities for the promotion of the interests of its Members;`
  line
  line `(f) generation, transmission and distribution of power, revitalisation of land and water resources,`
  line `their use, conservation and communications relatable to primary produce;`
  line
  line `(g) insurance of producers or their primary produce;`
  line
  line `(h) promoting techniques of mutuality and mutual assistance;`
  line
  line `(i) welfare measures or facilities for the benefit of Members as may be decided by the Board;`
  line
  line `(j) any other activity, ancillary or incidental to any of the activities referred to in clauses (a) to (i)`
  line `or other activities which may promote the principles of mutuality and mutual assistance amongst the`
  line `Members in any other manner;`
  line
  line `(k) financing of procurement, processing, marketing or other activities specified in clauses (a) to`
  line `(j) which include extending of credit facilities or any other financial services to its Members.".`
  line
  line `(2) Every Producer Company shall deal primarily with the produce of its active Members for carrying`
  line `out any of its objects specified in this section.]`
obj_root_law_sections_378_c:
  sectionId (52426)
  sectionNo 378C
  orderNo 385
  title `Formation of Producer Company and its registration.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_378_c_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 29 of 2020, s. 52 (w.e.f. 11-2-2021).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=52426&sectionno=378C&orderno=385&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_378_c_content:
  string
  line `^1[378C. Formation of Producer Company and its registration.--(1) Any ten or more individuals,`
  line `each of them being a producer or any two or more Producer Institutions, or a combination of ten or more`
  line `individuals and Producer Institutions, desirous of forming a Producer Company having its objects specified`
  line `in section 378B and otherwise complying with the requirements of this Chapter and the provisions of this`
  line `Act in respect of registration, may form an incorporated company as a Producer Company under this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) If the Registrar is satisfied that all the requirements of this Act have been complied with in respect`
  line `of registration and matters precedent and incidental thereto, he shall, within thirty days of the receipt of the`
  line `documents required for registration, register the memorandum, the articles and other documents, if any, and`
  line `issue a certificate of incorporation under this Act.`
  line
  line `(3) A Producer Company so formed shall have the liability of its Members limited by the memorandum`
  line `to the amount, if any, unpaid on the shares respectively held by them and be termed a company limited by`
  line shares.
  line
  line `(4) The Producer Company may reimburse to its promoters all other direct costs associated with the`
  line `promotion and registration of the company including registration, legal fees, printing of a memorandum and articles and the payment thereof shall be subject to the approval at its first general meeting of the`
  line Members.
  line
  line `(5) On registration under sub-section (2), the Producer Company shall become a body corporate as if it`
  line `is a private limited company to which the provisions contained in this Chapter apply, without, however,`
  line `any limit to the number of Members thereof, and the Producer Company shall not, under any circumstance,`
  line `whatsoever, become or be deemed to become a public limited company under this Act.]`
obj_root_law_sections_378_d:
  sectionId (52427)
  sectionNo 378D
  orderNo 386
  title `Membership and voting rights of Members of Producer Company`
  content obj_root_law_sections_378_d_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 29 of 2020, s. 52 (w.e.f. 11-2-2021).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=52427&sectionno=378D&orderno=386&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_378_d_content:
  string
  line `^1[378D. Membership and voting rights of Members of Producer Company.-- (1)(a) In a case where`
  line `the membership consists solely of individual Members, the voting rights shall be based on a single vote for`
  line `every Member, irrespective of his shareholding or patronage of the Producer Company.`
  line
  line `(b) In a case where the membership consists of Producer Institutions only, the voting rights of such`
  line `Producer Institutions shall be determined on the basis of their participation in the business of the Producer`
  line `Company in the previous year, as may be specified by articles:`
  line
  line `Provided that during the first year of registration of a Producer Company, the voting rights shall be`
  line `determined on the basis of the shareholding by such Producer Institutions.`
  line
  line `(c) In a case where the membership consists of individuals and Producer Institutions, the voting rights`
  line `shall be computed on the basis of a single vote for every Member.`
  line
  line `(2) The articles of any Producer Company may provide for the conditions, subject to which a Member`
  line `may continue to retain his membership, and the manner in which voting rights shall be exercised by the`
  line Members.
  line
  line `(3) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (1) or sub-section (2), any Producer Company`
  line `may, if so authorised by its articles, restrict the voting rights to active Members, in any special or general`
  line meeting.
  line
  line `(4) No person, who has any business interest which is in conflict with business of the Producer`
  line `Company, shall become a Member of that Company.`
  line
  line `(5) A Member, who acquires any business interest which is in conflict with the business of the Producer`
  line `Company, shall cease to be a Member of that Company and be removed as a Member in accordance with`
  line `the articles.]`
obj_root_law_sections_378_e:
  sectionId (52428)
  sectionNo 378E
  orderNo 387
  title `Benefits to Members.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_378_e_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 29 of 2020, s. 52 (w.e.f. 11-2-2021).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=52428&sectionno=378E&orderno=387&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_378_e_content:
  string
  line `^1[378E. Benefits to Members.--(1) Subject to the provisions made in articles, every Member shall`
  line `initially receive only such value for the produce or products pooled and supplied as the Board of Producer`
  line `Company may determine, and the withheld price may be disbursed later in cash or in kind or by allotment`
  line `of equity shares, in proportion to the produce supplied to the Producer Company during the financial year`
  line `to such extent and in such manner and subject to such conditions as may be decided by the Board.`
  line
  line `(2) Every Member shall, on the share capital contributed, receive only a limited return:`
  line
  line `Provided that every such Member may be allotted bonus shares in accordance with the provisions`
  line `contained in section 378ZJ.`
  line
  line `(3) The surplus if any, remaining after making provision for payment of limited return and reserves`
  line `referred to in section 378ZI, may be disbursed as patronage bonus, amongst the Members, in proportion to`
  line `their participation in the business of the Producer Company, either in cash or by way of allotment of equity`
  line `shares, or both, as may be decided by the Members at the general meeting.]`
obj_root_law_sections_378_f:
  sectionId (52429)
  sectionNo 378F
  orderNo 388
  title `Memorandum of Producer Company.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_378_f_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 29 of 2020, s. 52 (w.e.f. 11-2-2021).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=52429&sectionno=378F&orderno=388&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_378_f_content:
  string
  line `^1[378F. Memorandum of Producer Company.--The memorandum of association of every Producer`
  line `Company shall state--`
  line
  line `(a) the name of the company with "Producer Company Limited" as the last words of the name of`
  line `such Company;`
  line
  line `(b) the State in which the registered office of the Producer Company is to situate;`
  line
  line `(c) the main objects of the Producer Company shall be one or more of the objects specified in`
  line `section 378B;`
  line
  line `(d) the names and addresses of the persons who have subscribed to the memorandum;`
  line
  line `(e) the amount of share capital with which the Producer Company is to be registered and division`
  line `thereof into shares of a fixed amount;`
  line
  line `(f) the names, addresses and occupations of the subscribers being producers, who shall act as the`
  line `first directors in accordance with sub-section (2) of section 378J;`
  line
  line `(g) that the liability of its members is limited;`
  line
  line `(h) against the subscriber's name, the number of shares each subscriber takes:`
  line
  line `Provided that no subscriber shall take less than one share;`
  line
  line `(i) that in case the objects of the Producer Company are not confined to one State, the States to`
  line `whose territories the objects extend.]`
obj_root_law_sections_378_g:
  sectionId (52430)
  sectionNo 378G
  orderNo 389
  title `Articles of association.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_378_g_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 29 of 2020, s. 52 (w.e.f. 11-2-2021).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=52430&sectionno=378G&orderno=389&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_378_g_content:
  string
  line `^1[378G. Articles of association.--(1) There shall be presented, for registration to the Registrar of the`
  line `State to which the registered office of the Producer Company is, stated by the memorandum of association,`
  line `to be situate--`
  line
  line `(a) memorandum of the Producer Company;`
  line
  line `(b) its articles duly signed by the subscribers to the memorandum.`
  line
  line `(2) The articles shall contain the following mutual assistance principles, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the membership shall be voluntary and available, to all eligible persons who, can participate or`
  line `avail of the facilities or services of the Producer Company, and are willing to accept the duties of`
  line membership;
  line
  line `(b) each Member shall, save as otherwise provided in this Chapter, have only a single vote`
  line `irrespective of the shareholding;`
  line
  line `(c) the Producer Company shall be administered by a Board consisting of persons elected or`
  line `appointed as directors in the manner consistent with the provisions of this Chapter and the Board shall`
  line `be accountable to the Members;`
  line
  line `(d) particulars on limited return on share capital;`
  line
  line `(e) the surplus arising out of the operations of the Producer Company shall be distributed in an`
  line `equitable manner by--`
  line
  line `(i) providing for the development of the business of the Producer Company;`
  line
  line `(ii) providing for common facilities; and`
  line
  line `(iii) distributing amongst the Members, as may be admissible in proportion to their respective`
  line `participation in the business;`
  line
  line `(f) provision for the education of Members, employees and others, on the principles of mutuality`
  line `and techniques of mutual assistance;`
  line
  line `(g) the Producer Company shall actively co-operate with other Producer Companies (and other`
  line `organisations following similar principles) at local, national or international level so as to best serve`
  line `the interest of their Members and the communities it purports to serve.`
  line
  line `(3) Without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing provisions of sub-sections (1) and (2), the`
  line `articles shall contain the following provisions, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the qualifications for membership, the conditions for continuance or cancellation of membership`
  line `and the terms, conditions and procedure for transfer of shares;`
  line
  line `(b) the manner of ascertaining the patronage and voting right based on patronage;`
  line
  line `(c) subject to the provisions contained in sub-section (1) of section 378N, the manner of constitution`
  line `of the Board, its powers and duties, the minimum and maximum number of directors, manner of election and appointment of directors and retirement by rotation, qualifications for being elected or continuance`
  line `as such and the terms of office of the said directors, their powers and duties, conditions for election or`
  line `co-option of directors, method of removal of directors and the filling up of vacancies on the Board, and`
  line `the manner and the terms of appointment of the Chief Executive;`
  line
  line `(d) the election of the Chairman, term of office of directors and the Chairman, manner of voting at`
  line `the general or special meetings of Members, procedure for voting, by directors at meetings of the Board,`
  line `powers of the Chairman and the circumstances under which the Chairman may exercise a casting vote;`
  line
  line `(e) the circumstances under which, and the manner in which, the withheld price is to be determined`
  line `and distributed;`
  line
  line `(f) the manner of disbursement of patronage bonus in cash or by issue of equity shares, or both;`
  line
  line `(g) the contribution to be shared and related matters referred to in sub-section (2) of section 378ZI;`
  line
  line `(h) the matters relating to issue of bonus shares out of general reserves as set out in section 378ZJ;`
  line
  line `(i) the basis and manner of allotment of equity shares of the Producer Company in lieu of the whole`
  line `or part of the sale proceeds of produce or products supplied by the Members;`
  line
  line `(j) the amount of reserves, sources from which funds may be raised, limitation on raising of funds,`
  line `restriction on the use of such funds and the extent of debt that may be contracted and the conditions`
  line thereof;
  line
  line `(k) the credit, loans or advances which may be granted to a Member and the conditions for the grant`
  line `of the same;`
  line
  line `(l) the right of any Member to obtain information relating to general business of the company;`
  line
  line `(m) the basis and manner of distribution and disposal of funds available after meeting liabilities in`
  line `the event of dissolution or liquidation of the Producer Company;`
  line
  line `(n) the authorisation for division, amalgamation, merger, creation of subsidiaries and the entering`
  line `into joint ventures and other matters connected therewith;`
  line
  line `(o) laying of the memorandum and articles of the Producer Company before a special general`
  line `meeting to be held within ninety days of its registration;`
  line
  line `(p) any other provision, which the Members may, by special resolution recommend to be included`
  line `in the articles.]`
obj_root_law_sections_378_h:
  sectionId (52431)
  sectionNo 378H
  orderNo 390
  title `Amendment of memorandum.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_378_h_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 29 of 2020, s. 52 (w.e.f. 11-2-2021).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=52431&sectionno=378H&orderno=390&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_378_h_content:
  string
  line `^1[378H. Amendment of memorandum.--(1) A Producer Company shall not alter the conditions`
  line `contained in its memorandum except in the cases, by the mode and to the extent for which express provision`
  line `is made in this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) A Producer Company may, by special resolution, not inconsistent with section 378B, alter its objects`
  line `specified in its memorandum.`
  line
  line `(3) A copy of the amended memorandum, together with a copy of the special resolution duly certified`
  line `by two directors, shall be filed with the Registrar within thirty days from the date of adoption of any`
  line `resolution referred to in sub-section (2):`
  line
  line `Provided that in the case of transfer of the registered office of a Producer Company from the jurisdiction`
  line `of one Registrar to another, certified copies of the special resolution certified by two directors shall be filed`
  line `with both the Registrars within thirty days, and each Registrar shall record the same, and thereupon the`
  line `Registrar from whose jurisdiction the office is transferred, shall forthwith forward to the other Registrar all`
  line `documents relating to the Producer Company.`
  line
  line `(4) The alteration of the provisions of memorandum relating to the change of the place of its registered`
  line `office from one State to another shall not take effect unless it is approved by the Central Government on an`
  line `application in such form and manner as may be prescribed.]`
obj_root_law_sections_378_i:
  sectionId (52432)
  sectionNo 378-I
  orderNo 391
  title `Amendment of articles.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_378_i_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 29 of 2020, s. 52 (w.e.f. 11-2-2021).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=52432&sectionno=378-I&orderno=391&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_378_i_content:
  string
  line `^1[378-I. Amendment of articles.-- (1) Any amendment of the articles shall be proposed by not less than`
  line `two-thirds of the elected directors or by not less than one-third of the Members of the Producer Company,`
  line `and adopted by the Members by a special resolution.`
  line
  line `(2) A copy of the amended articles together with the copy of the special resolution, both duly certified`
  line `by two directors, shall be filed with the Registrar within fifteen days from the date of its adoption.]`
obj_root_law_sections_378_j:
  sectionId (52433)
  sectionNo 378J
  orderNo 392
  title `Option to inter-State co-operative societies to become Producer Companies.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_378_j_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 29 of 2020, s. 52 (w.e.f. 11-2-2021).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=52433&sectionno=378J&orderno=392&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_378_j_content:
  string
  line `^1[378J. Option to inter-State co-operative societies to become Producer Companies.--(1)`
  line `Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (1) of section 378C, any inter-State co-operative society`
  line `with objects not confined to one State may make an application to the Registrar for registration as Producer`
  line `Company under this Chapter.`
  line
  line `(2) Every application under sub-section (1) shall be accompanied by--`
  line
  line `(a) a copy of the special resolution, of not less than two-thirds of total members of inter-State cooperative society, for its incorporation as a Producer Company under this Act;`
  line
  line `(b) a statement showing--`
  line
  line `(i) names and addresses or the occupation of the directors and the Chief Executive, if any, by`
  line `whatever name called, of such co-operative; and`
  line
  line `(ii) list of members of such inter-State co-operative society;`
  line
  line `(c) a statement indicating that the inter-State co-operative society is engaged in any one or more of`
  line `the objects specified in section 378B;`
  line
  line `(d) a declaration by two or more directors of the inter-State co-operative society certifying that`
  line `particulars given in clauses (a) to (c) are correct.`
  line
  line `(3) When an inter-State co-operative society is registered as a Producer Company, the words "Producer`
  line `Company Limited" shall form part of its name with any word or expression to show its identity preceding`
  line it.
  line
  line `(4) On compliance with the requirements of sub-sections (1) to (3), the Registrar shall, within a period`
  line `of thirty days of the receipt of application, certify under his hand that the inter-State co-operative society`
  line `applying for registration is registered and thereby incorporated as a Producer Company under this Chapter.`
  line
  line `(5) A co-operative society formed by producers, by federation or union of co-operative societies of`
  line `producers or co-operatives of producers, registered under any law for the time being in force which has`
  line `extended its objects outside the State, either directly or through a union or federation of co-operatives of`
  line `which it is a constituent, as the case may be, and any federation or unions of such co-operatives, which has`
  line `so extended any of its objects or activities outside the State, shall be eligible to make an application under`
  line `sub-section (1) and to obtain registration as a Producer Company under this Chapter.`
  line
  line `(6) The inter-State co-operative society shall, upon registration under sub-section (1), stand transformed`
  line `into a Producer Company, and thereafter shall be governed by the provisions of this Chapter to the exclusion`
  line `of the law by which it was earlier governed, save in so far as anything done or omitted to be done before`
  line `its registration as a Producer Company, and notwithstanding anything contained in any other law for the`
  line `time being in force, no person shall have any claim against the co-operative institution or the company by`
  line `reason of such conversion or transformation.`
  line
  line `(7) Upon registration as a Producer Company, the Registrar of Companies who registers the company`
  line `shall forthwith intimate the Registrar with whom the erstwhile inter-State co-operative society was earlier`
  line `registered for deletion of the society from its register.]`
obj_root_law_sections_378_k:
  sectionId (52434)
  sectionNo 378K
  orderNo 393
  title `Effect of incorporation of Producer Company.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_378_k_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 29 of 2020, s. 52 (w.e.f. 11-2-2021).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=52434&sectionno=378K&orderno=393&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_378_k_content:
  string
  line `^1[378K. Effect of incorporation of Producer Company.--Every shareholder of the inter-State cooperative society immediately before the date of registration of Producer Company (hereafter in this`
  line `Chapter referred to as the date of transformation) shall be deemed to be registered on and from that date as`
  line `a shareholder of the Producer Company to the extent of the face value of the shares held by such`
  line shareholder.]
obj_root_law_sections_378_l:
  sectionId (52435)
  sectionNo 378L
  orderNo 394
  title `Vesting of undertaking in Producer Company.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_378_l_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 29 of 2020, s. 52 (w.e.f. 11-2-2021).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=52435&sectionno=378L&orderno=394&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_378_l_content:
  string
  line `^1[378L. Vesting of undertaking in Producer Company.--(1) All properties and assets, movable and`
  line `immovable, of, or belonging to, the inter-State co-operative society as on the date of transformation, shall`
  line `vest in the Producer Company.`
  line
  line `(2) All the rights, debts, liabilities, interests, privileges and obligations of the inter-State co-operative`
  line `society as on the date of transformation shall stand transferred to, and be the rights, debts, liabilities,`
  line `interests, privileges and obligations of, the Producer Company.`
  line
  line `(3) Without prejudice to the provisions contained in sub-section (2), all debts, liabilities and obligations`
  line `incurred, all contracts entered into and all matters and things engaged to be done by, with or for, the society`
  line `as on the date of transformation for or in connection with their purposes, shall be deemed to have been`
  line `incurred, entered into, or engaged to be done by, with or for, the Producer Company.`
  line
  line `(4) All sums of money due to the inter-State co-operative society immediately before the date of`
  line `transformation, shall be deemed to be due to the Producer Company.`
  line
  line `(5) Every organisation, which was being managed immediately before the date of transformation by`
  line `the inter-State co-operative society shall be managed by the Producer Company for such period, to such`
  line `extent and in such manner as the circumstances may require.`
  line
  line `(6) Every organisation which was getting financial, managerial or technical assistance from the interState co-operative society, immediately before the date of transformation, may continue to be given`
  line `financial, managerial or technical assistance, as the case may be, by the Producer Company, for such period,`
  line `to such extent and in such manner as that company may deem fit.`
  line
  line `(7) The amount representing the capital of the erstwhile inter-State co-operative society shall form part`
  line `of the capital of the Producer Company.`
  line
  line `(8) Any reference to the inter-State co-operative society in any law other than this Act or in any contract`
  line `or other instrument, shall be deemed to be reference to the Producer Company.`
  line
  line `(9) If, on the date of transformation, there is pending any suit, arbitration, appeal or other legal`
  line `proceeding of whatever nature by or against the inter-State co-operative society, the same shall not abate,`
  line `be discontinued or be in any way prejudicially affected by reason of the incorporation of the Producer`
  line `Company under section 378C or transformation of the inter-State co-operative society as a Producer`
  line `Company under section 378J, as the case may be, but the suit, arbitration, appeal or other proceeding, may`
  line `be continued, prosecuted and enforced by or against the Producer Company in the same manner and to the`
  line `same extent as it would have, or may have been continued, prosecuted and enforced by or against the interState co-operative society as if the provisions contained in this Chapter had not come into force.]`
obj_root_law_sections_378_m:
  sectionId (52436)
  sectionNo 378M
  orderNo 395
  title `Concession, etc., to be deemed to have been granted to Producer Company`
  content obj_root_law_sections_378_m_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 29 of 2020, s. 52 (w.e.f. 11-2-2021).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=52436&sectionno=378M&orderno=395&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_378_m_content:
  string
  line `^1[378M. Concession etc., to be deemed to have been granted to Producer Company.--With effect`
  line `from the date of transformation, all fiscal and other concessions, licences, benefits, privileges and`
  line `exemptions granted to the inter-State co-operative society in connection with the affairs and business of the`
  line `inter-State co-operative society under any law for the time being in force shall be deemed to have been`
  line `granted to the Producer Company.]`
obj_root_law_sections_378_n:
  sectionId (52437)
  sectionNo 378N
  orderNo 396
  title `Provisions in respect of officers and other employees of inter-State co-operative society.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_378_n_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 29 of 2020, s. 52 (w.e.f. 11-2-2021).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=52437&sectionno=378N&orderno=396&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_378_n_content:
  string
  line `^1[378N. Provisions in respect of officers and other employees of inter-State co-operative society.--`
  line `(1) Notwithstanding anything contained in section 378-O, all the directors in the inter-State co-operative`
  line `society before the incorporation of the Producer Company shall continue in office for a period of one year`
  line `from the date of transformation and in accordance with the provisions of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) Every officer or other employee of the inter-State co-operative society (except a director of the`
  line `Board, Chairman or Managing Director) serving in its employment immediately before the date of`
  line `transformation shall, in so far as such officer or other employee is employed in connection with the interState co-operative society which has vested in the Producer Company by virtue of this Act, become, as`
  line `from the date of transformation, an officer or, as the case may be, other employee of the Producer Company`
  line `and shall hold his office or service therein by the same tenure, at the same remuneration, upon the same`
  line `terms and conditions, with the same obligations and with the same rights and privileges as to leave, leave`
  line `travel concession, welfare scheme, medical benefit scheme, insurance, provident fund, other funds,`
  line `retirement, voluntary retirement, gratuity and other benefits as he would have held under the erstwhile inter-State co-operative society if its undertaking had not vested in the Producer Company and shall continue to`
  line `do so as an officer or, as the case may be, other employee of the Producer Company.`
  line
  line `(3) Where an officer or other employee of the inter-State co-operative society opts under sub-section`
  line `(2) not to be in employment or service of the Producer Company, such officer or other employee shall be`
  line `deemed to have resigned.`
  line
  line `(4) Notwithstanding anything contained in the Industrial Disputes Act, 1947 (14 of 1947) or in any`
  line `other law for the time being in force, the transfer of the services of any officer or other employee of the`
  line `inter-State co-operative society to the Producer Company shall not entitle such officer or other employee`
  line `to any compensation under this Act or under any other law for the time being in force and no such claim`
  line `shall be entertained by any court, tribunal or other authority.`
  line
  line `(5) The officers and other employees who have retired before the date of transformation from the`
  line `service of the inter-State co-operative society and are entitled to any benefits, rights or privileges, shall be`
  line `entitled to receive the same benefits, rights or privileges from the Producer Company.`
  line
  line `(6) The trusts of the provident fund or the gratuity fund of the inter-State co-operative society and any`
  line `other bodies created for the welfare of officers or employees shall continue to discharge functions in the`
  line `Producer Company as was being done hitherto in the inter-State co-operative society and any tax exemption`
  line `granted to the provident fund or the gratuity fund would continue to be applied to the Producer Company.`
  line
  line `(7) Notwithstanding anything contained in this Act or in any other law for the time being in force or in`
  line `the regulations of the inter-State co-operative society, no director of the Board, Chairman, Managing`
  line `Director or any other person entitled to manage the whole or substantial part of the business and affairs of`
  line `the inter-State co-operative society shall be entitled to any compensation against the inter-State co-operative`
  line `society or the Producer Company for the loss of office or for the premature termination of any contract of`
  line `management entered into by him with the inter-State co-operative society.]`
obj_root_law_sections_378_o:
  sectionId (52438)
  sectionNo 378-O
  orderNo 397
  title `Number of directors.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_378_o_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 29 of 2020, s. 52 (w.e.f. 11-2-2021).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=52438&sectionno=378-O&orderno=397&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_378_o_content:
  string
  line `^1[378-O. Number of directors.--Every Producer Company shall have at least five and not more than`
  line `fifteen directors:`
  line
  line `Provided that in the case of an inter-State co-operative society incorporated as a Producer Company,`
  line `such company may have more than fifteen directors for a period of one year from the date of its`
  line `incorporation as a Producer Company.]`
obj_root_law_sections_378_p:
  sectionId (52439)
  sectionNo 378P
  orderNo 398
  title `Appointment of directors.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_378_p_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 29 of 2020, s. 52 (w.e.f. 11-2-2021).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=52439&sectionno=378P&orderno=398&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_378_p_content:
  string
  line `^1[378P. Appointment of directors.-- (1)Save as otherwise provided in section 378N, the Members who`
  line `sign the memorandum and the articles may designate therein the Board of Directors, not less than five, who`
  line `shall govern the affairs of the Producer Company until the directors are elected in accordance with the`
  line `provisions of this section.`
  line
  line `(2) The election of directors shall be conducted within a period of ninety days of the registration of the`
  line `Producer Company:`
  line
  line `Provided that in the case of an inter-State co-operative society which has been registered as a Producer`
  line `Company under sub-section (4) of section 378J in which at least five directors [including the directors`
  line `continuing in office under sub-section (1) of section 378N] hold office as such on the date of registration`
  line `of such company, the provisions of this sub-section shall have effect as if for the words "ninety days", the`
  line `words "three hundred and sixty-five days" had been substituted.`
  line
  line `(3) Every person shall hold office of a director for a period not less than one year but not exceeding`
  line `five years as may be specified in the articles.`
  line
  line `(4) Every director, who retires in accordance with the articles, shall be eligible for re-appointment as a`
  line director.
  line
  line `(5) Save as otherwise provided in sub-section (2), the directors of the Board shall be elected or`
  line `appointed by the Members in the annual general meeting.`
  line
  line `(6) The Board may co-opt one or more expert directors or an additional director not exceeding onefifth of the total number of directors or appoint any other person as additional director for such period as`
  line `the Board may deem fit:`
  line
  line `Provided that the expert directors shall not have the right to vote in the election of the Chairman but`
  line `shall be eligible to be elected as Chairman, if so provided by its articles:`
  line
  line `Provided further that the maximum period, for which the expert director or the additional director holds`
  line `office, shall not exceed such period as may be specified in the articles.]`
obj_root_law_sections_378_q:
  sectionId (52440)
  sectionNo 378Q
  orderNo 399
  title `Vacation of office by directors.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_378_q_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 29 of 2020, s. 52 (w.e.f. 11-2-2021).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=52440&sectionno=378Q&orderno=399&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_378_q_content:
  string
  line `^1[378Q. Vacation of office by directors.-- (1) The office of the director of a Producer Company shall`
  line `become vacant if,--`
  line
  line `(a) he is convicted by a court of any offence involving moral turpitude and sentenced in respect`
  line `thereof to imprisonment for not less than six months;`
  line
  line `(b) the Producer Company, in which he is a director, has made a default in repayment of any`
  line `advances or loans taken from any company or institution or any other person and such default continues`
  line `for ninety days;`
  line
  line `(c) he has made a default in repayment of any advances or loans taken from the Producer Company`
  line `in which he is a director;`
  line
  line `(d) the Producer Company, in which he is a director--`
  line
  line `(i) has not filed the annual accounts and annual return for any continuous three financial years;`
  line or
  line
  line `(ii) has failed to, repay its deposit or withheld price or patronage bonus or interest thereon on`
  line `due date, or pay dividend and such failure continues for one year or more;`
  line
  line `(e) default is made in holding election for the office of director, in the Producer Company in which`
  line `he is a director, in accordance with the provisions of this Act and articles;`
  line
  line `(f) the annual general meeting or extraordinary general meeting of the Producer Company, in which`
  line `he is a director, is not called in accordance with the provisions of this Act except due to natural calamity`
  line `or such other reason.`
  line
  line `(2) The provisions of sub-section (1) shall, as far as may be, apply to the director of a Producer`
  line `Institution which is a member of a Producer Company.]`
obj_root_law_sections_378_r:
  sectionId (52441)
  sectionNo 378R
  orderNo 400
  title `Powers and functions of Board.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_378_r_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 29 of 2020, s. 52 (w.e.f. 11-2-2021).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=52441&sectionno=378R&orderno=400&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_378_r_content:
  string
  line `^1[378R. Powers and functions of Board.--(1) Subject to the provisions of this Act and articles, the`
  line `Board of Directors of a Producer Company shall exercise all such powers and to do all such acts and things,`
  line `as that Company is authorised so to do.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing powers, such powers may`
  line `include all or any of the following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) determination of the dividend payable;`
  line
  line `(b) determination of the quantum of withheld price and recommend patronage to be approved at`
  line `general meeting;`
  line
  line `(c) admission of new Members;`
  line
  line `(d) pursue and formulate the organisational policy, objectives, establish specific long-term and`
  line `annual objectives, and approve corporate strategies and financial plans;`
  line
  line `(e) appointment of a Chief Executive and such other officers of the Producer Company, as may be`
  line `specified in the articles;`
  line
  line `(f) exercise superintendence, direction and control over Chief Executive and other officers`
  line `appointed by it;`
  line
  line `(g) cause proper books of account to be maintained; prepare annual accounts to be placed before`
  line `the annual general meeting with the report of the auditor and the replies on qualifications, if any, made`
  line `by the auditors;`
  line
  line `(h) acquisition or disposal of property of the Producer Company in its ordinary course of business;`
  line
  line `(i) investment of the funds of the Producer Company in the ordinary course of its business;`
  line
  line `(j) sanction any loan or advance, in connection with the business activities of the Producer`
  line `Company to any Member, not being a director or his relative;`
  line
  line `(k) take such other measures or do such other acts as may be required in the discharge of its`
  line `functions or exercise of its powers.`
  line
  line `(3) All the powers specified in sub-sections (1) and (2) shall be exercised by the Board, by means of`
  line `resolution passed at its meeting on behalf of the Producer Company.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the removal of doubts, it is hereby declared that a director or a group of directors,`
  line `who do not constitute the Board, shall not exercise any of the powers exercisable by it.]`
obj_root_law_sections_378_s:
  sectionId (52442)
  sectionNo 378S
  orderNo 401
  title `Matters to be transacted at general meeting.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_378_s_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 29 of 2020, s. 52 (w.e.f. 11-2-2021).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=52442&sectionno=378S&orderno=401&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_378_s_content:
  string
  line `^1[378S. Matters to be transacted at general meeting.-- The Board of Directors of a Producer Company`
  line `shall exercise the following powers on behalf of that Company, and it shall do so only by means of`
  line `resolutions passed at the annual general meeting of its Members, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) approval of budget and adoption of annual accounts of the Producer Company;`
  line
  line `(b) approval of patronage bonus;`
  line
  line `(c) issue of bonus shares;`
  line
  line `(d) declaration of limited return and decision on the distribution of patronage;`
  line
  line `(e) specify the conditions and limits of loans that may be given by the Board to any director; and`
  line
  line `(f) approval of any transaction of the nature as is to be reserved in the articles for approval by the`
  line Members.]
obj_root_law_sections_378_t:
  sectionId (52443)
  sectionNo 378T
  orderNo 402
  title `Liability of directors.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_378_t_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 29 of 2020, s. 52 (w.e.f. 11-2-2021).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=52443&sectionno=378T&orderno=402&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_378_t_content:
  string
  line `^1[378T. Liability of directors.-- (1) When the directors vote for a resolution, or approve by any other`
  line `means, anything done in contravention of the provisions of this Act or any other law for the time being in`
  line `force or articles, they shall be jointly and severally liable to make good any loss or damage suffered by the`
  line `Producer Company.`
  line
  line `(2) Without prejudice to the provisions contained in sub-section (1), the Producer Company shall have`
  line `the right to recover from its director--`
  line
  line `(a) where such director has made any profit as a result of the contravention specified in`
  line `sub-section (1), an amount equal to the profit so made;`
  line
  line `(b) where the Producer Company incurred a loss or damage as a result of the contravention specified`
  line `in sub-section (1), an amount equal to that loss or damage.`
  line
  line `(3) The liability imposed under this section shall be in addition to and not in derogation of a liability`
  line `imposed on a director under this Act or any other law for the time being in force.]`
obj_root_law_sections_378_u:
  sectionId (52444)
  sectionNo 378U
  orderNo 403
  title `Committee of directors.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_378_u_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 29 of 2020, s. 52 (w.e.f. 11-2-2021).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=52444&sectionno=378U&orderno=403&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_378_u_content:
  string
  line `^1[378U. Committee of directors.--(1) The Board may constitute such number of committees as it may`
  line `deem fit for the purpose of assisting the Board in the efficient discharge of its functions:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Board shall not delegate any of its powers or assign the powers of the Chief Executive,`
  line `to any committee.`
  line
  line `(2) A committee constituted under sub-section (1) may, with the approval of the Board, co-opt such`
  line `number of persons as it deems fit as members of the committee:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Chief Executive appointed under section 378W or a director of the Producer Company`
  line `shall be a member of such committee.`
  line
  line `(3) Every such committee shall function under the general superintendence, direction and control of the`
  line `Board, for such duration, and in such manner as the Board may direct.`
  line
  line `(4) The fee and allowances to be paid to the members of the committee shall be such as may be`
  line `determined by the Board.`
  line
  line `(5) The minutes of each meeting of the committee shall be placed before the Board at its next meeting.`
obj_root_law_sections_378_v:
  sectionId (52445)
  sectionNo 378V
  orderNo 404
  title `Meetings of Board and quorum.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_378_v_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 29 of 2020, s. 52 (w.e.f. 11-2-2021).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=52445&sectionno=378V&orderno=404&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_378_v_content:
  string
  line `^1[378V.Meetings of Board and quorum.--(1) A meeting of the Board shall be held not less than once`
  line `in every three months and at least four such meetings shall be held in every year.`
  line
  line `(2) Notice of every meeting of the Board of Directors shall be given in writing to every director for the`
  line `time being in India, and at his usual address in India to every other director.`
  line
  line `(3) The Chief Executive shall give notice as aforesaid not less than seven days prior to the date of the`
  line `meeting of the Board and if he fails to do so, he shall be liable to a penalty of five thousand rupees:`
  line
  line `Provided that a meeting of the Board may be called at shorter notice and the reasons thereof shall be`
  line `recorded in writing by the Board.`
  line
  line `(4) The quorum for a meeting of the Board shall be one-third of the total strength of directors, subject`
  line `to a minimum of three.`
  line
  line `(5) Save as provided in the articles, directors including the co-opted director, may be paid such fees`
  line `and allowances for attendance at the meetings of the Board, as may be decided by the Members in the`
  line `general meeting.]`
obj_root_law_sections_378_w:
  sectionId (52446)
  sectionNo 378W
  orderNo 405
  title `Chief Executive and his functions.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_378_w_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 29 of 2020, s. 52 (w.e.f. 11-2-2021).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=52446&sectionno=378W&orderno=405&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_378_w_content:
  string
  line `^1[378W. Chief Executive and his functions.-- (1) Every Producer Company shall have a full time Chief`
  line `Executive, by whatever name called, to be appointed by the Board from amongst persons other than`
  line Members.
  line
  line `(2) The Chief Executive shall be ex officio director of the Board and such director shall not retire by`
  line rotation.
  line
  line `(3) Save as otherwise provided in articles, the qualifications, experience and the terms and conditions`
  line `of service of the Chief Executive shall be such as may be determined by the Board.`
  line
  line `(4) The Chief Executive shall be entrusted with substantial powers of management as the Board may`
  line determine.
  line
  line `(5) Without prejudice to the generality of sub-section (4), the Chief Executive may exercise the powers`
  line `and discharge the functions, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) do administrative acts of a routine nature including managing the day-to-day affairs of the`
  line `Producer Company;`
  line
  line `(b) operate bank accounts or authorise any person, subject to the general or special approval of the`
  line `Board in this behalf, to operate the bank account;`
  line
  line `(c) make arrangements for safe custody of cash and other assets of the Producer Company;`
  line
  line `(d) sign such documents as may be authorised by the Board, for and on behalf of the company;`
  line
  line `(e) maintain proper books of account; prepare annual accounts and audit thereof; place the audited`
  line `accounts before the Board and in the annual general meeting of the Members;`
  line
  line `(f) furnish Members with periodic information to apprise them of the operation and functions of`
  line `the Producer Company;`
  line
  line `(g) make appointments to posts in accordance with the powers delegated to him by the Board;`
  line
  line `(h) assist the Board in the formulation of goals, objectives, strategies, plans and policies;`
  line
  line `(i) advise the Board with respect to legal and regulatory matters concerning the proposed and`
  line `ongoing activities and take necessary action in respect thereof;`
  line
  line `(j) exercise the powers as may be necessary in the ordinary course of business;`
  line
  line `(k) discharge such other functions, and exercise such other powers, as may be delegated by the`
  line Board.
  line
  line `(6) The Chief Executive shall manage the affairs of the Producer Company under the general`
  line `superintendence, direction and control of the Board and be accountable for the performance of the Producer`
  line Company.]
obj_root_law_sections_378_x:
  sectionId (52447)
  sectionNo 378X
  orderNo 406
  title `Secretary of Producer Company`
  content obj_root_law_sections_378_x_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 29 of 2020, s. 52 (w.e.f. 11-2-2021).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=52447&sectionno=378X&orderno=406&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_378_x_content:
  string
  line `^1[378X. Secretary of Producer Company.-- (1) Every Producer Company having an average annual`
  line `turnover exceeding five crore rupees or such other amount as may be prescribed in each of three consecutive`
  line `financial years shall have a whole-time secretary.`
  line
  line `(2) No individual shall be appointed as whole-time secretary unless he possesses membership of the`
  line `Institute of Company Secretaries of India constituted under the Company Secretaries Act, 1980 (56 of`
  line `1980).`
  line
  line `(3) If a Producer Company fails to comply with the provisions of sub-section (1), the Company and`
  line `every officer of the Company who is in default, shall be liable to a penalty of one hundred rupees for every`
  line `day during which the default continues subject to a maximum of rupees one lakh:`
  line
  line `Provided that in any proceedings against a person in respect of a default under this sub-section, no`
  line `penalty shall be imposed if it is shown that all reasonable efforts to comply with the provisions of`
  line `sub-section (1) were taken or that the financial position of the Company was such that it was beyond its`
  line `capacity to engage a whole-time secretary.]`
obj_root_law_sections_378_y:
  sectionId (52448)
  sectionNo 378Y
  orderNo 407
  title Quorum
  content obj_root_law_sections_378_y_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 29 of 2020, s. 52 (w.e.f. 11-2-2021).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=52448&sectionno=378Y&orderno=407&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_378_y_content:
  string
  line `^1[378Y. Quorum.-- Unless the articles require a larger number, one-fourth of the total membership shall`
  line `constitute the quorum at a general meeting.]`
obj_root_law_sections_378_z:
  sectionId (52449)
  sectionNo 378Z
  orderNo 408
  title `Voting rights.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_378_z_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 29 of 2020, s. 52 (w.e.f. 11-2-2021).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=52449&sectionno=378Z&orderno=408&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_378_z_content:
  string
  line `^1[378Z. Voting rights.-- Save as otherwise provided in sub-sections (1) and (3) of section 378D, every`
  line `Member shall have one vote and in the case of equality of votes, the Chairman or the person presiding shall`
  line `have a casting vote except in the case of election of the Chairman.]`
obj_root_law_sections_378_za:
  sectionId (52450)
  sectionNo 378ZA
  orderNo 409
  title `Annual general meetings.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_378_za_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 29 of 2020, s. 52 (w.e.f. 11-2-2021).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=52450&sectionno=378ZA&orderno=409&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_378_za_content:
  string
  line `^1[378ZA. Annual general meetings.--(1) Every Producer Company shall in each year, hold, in addition`
  line `to any other meetings, a general meeting, as its annual general meeting and shall specify the meeting as`
  line `such in the notices calling it, and not more than fifteen months shall elapse between the date of one annual`
  line `general meeting of a Producer Company and that of the next:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Registrar may, for any special reason, permit extension of the time for holding any`
  line `annual general meeting (not being the first annual general meeting) by a period not exceeding three months.`
  line
  line `(2) A Producer Company shall hold its first annual general meeting within a period of ninety days from`
  line `the date of its incorporation.`
  line
  line `(3) The Members shall adopt the articles of the Producer Company and appoint directors of its Board`
  line `in the annual general meeting.`
  line
  line `(4) The notice calling the annual general meeting shall be accompanied by the following documents,`
  line `namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the agenda of the annual general meeting;`
  line
  line `(b) the minutes of the previous annual general meeting or the extraordinary general meeting;`
  line
  line `(c) the names of candidates for election, if any, to the office of director including a statement of`
  line `qualifications in respect of each candidate;`
  line
  line `(d) the audited balance-sheet and profit and loss accounts of the Producer Company and its`
  line `subsidiary, if any, together with a report of the Board of Directors of such Company with respect to--`
  line
  line `(i) the state of affairs of the Producer Company;`
  line
  line `(ii) the amount proposed to be carried to reserve;`
  line
  line `(iii) the amount to be paid as limited return on share capital;`
  line
  line `(iv) the amount proposed to be disbursed as patronage bonus;`
  line
  line `(v) the material changes and commitments, if any, affecting the financial position of the`
  line `Producer Company and its subsidiary, which have occurred in between the date of the annual`
  line `accounts of the Producer Company to which the balance-sheet relates and the date of the report of`
  line `the Board;`
  line
  line `(vi) any other matter of importance relating to energy conservation, environmental protection,`
  line `expenditure or earnings in foreign exchanges;`
  line
  line `(vii) any other matter which is required to be, or may be, specified by the Board;`
  line
  line `(e) the text of the draft resolution for appointment of auditors;`
  line
  line `(f) the text of any draft resolution proposing amendment to the memorandum or articles to be`
  line `considered at the general meeting, alongwith the recommendations of the Board.`
  line
  line `(5) The Board of Directors shall, on the requisition made in writing, duly signed and setting out the`
  line `matters for the consideration, made by one-third of the Members entitled to vote in any general meeting,`
  line `proceed to call an extraordinary general meeting in accordance with the relevant provisions contained in`
  line `Chapter VII.`
  line
  line `(6) Every annual general meeting shall be called, for a time during business hours, on a day that is not`
  line `a public holiday and shall be held at the registered office of the Producer Company or at some other place`
  line `within the city, town or village in which the registered office of the Company is situate.`
  line
  line `(7) A general meeting of the Producer Company shall be called by giving not less than fourteen days`
  line `prior notice in writing.`
  line
  line `(8) The notice of the general meeting indicating the date, time and place of the meeting shall be sent to`
  line `every Member and auditor of the Producer Company.`
  line
  line `(9) Unless the articles of the Producer Company provide for a larger number, one-fourth of the total`
  line `number of members of the Producer Company shall be the quorum for its annual general meeting.`
  line
  line `(10) The proceedings of every annual general meeting alongwith the report of the Board of Directors,`
  line `the audited balance-sheet and the profit and loss account shall be filed with the Registrar within sixty days`
  line `of the date on which the annual general meeting is held, with an annual return alongwith the filing fees as`
  line `applicable under the Act.`
  line
  line `(11) In the case where a Producer Company is formed by Producer Institutions, such Institutions shall`
  line `be represented in the general body through the Chairman or the Chief Executive thereof who shall be`
  line `competent to act on its behalf:`
  line
  line `Provided that a Producer Institution shall not be represented if such Institution is in default or failure`
  line `referred to in clauses (d) to (f) of sub-section (1) of section 378Q.]`
obj_root_law_sections_378_zb:
  sectionId (52451)
  sectionNo 378ZB
  orderNo 410
  title `Share capital.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_378_zb_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 29 of 2020, s. 52 (w.e.f. 11-2-2021).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=52451&sectionno=378ZB&orderno=410&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_378_zb_content:
  string
  line `^1[378ZB. Share capital.--(1) The share capital of a Producer Company shall consist of equity shares`
  line only.
  line
  line `(2) The shares held by a Member in a Producer Company, shall as far as may be, be in proportion to`
  line `the patronage of that company.]`
obj_root_law_sections_378_zc:
  sectionId (52452)
  sectionNo 378ZC
  orderNo 411
  title `Special user rights.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_378_zc_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 29 of 2020, s. 52 (w.e.f. 11-2-2021).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=52452&sectionno=378ZC&orderno=411&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_378_zc_content:
  string
  line `^1[378ZC. Special user rights.-- (1) The producers, who are active Members may, if so provided in the`
  line `articles, have special rights and the Producer Company may issue appropriate instruments to them in respect`
  line `of such special rights.`
  line
  line `(2) The instruments of the Producer Company issued under sub-section (1) shall, after obtaining`
  line `approval of the Board in that behalf, be transferable to any other active Member of that Producer Company.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purposes of this section, the expression "special right" means any right relating`
  line `to supply of additional produce by the active Member or any other right relating to his produce which may`
  line `be conferred upon him by the Board.]`
obj_root_law_sections_378_zd:
  sectionId (52453)
  sectionNo 378ZD
  orderNo 412
  title `Transferability of shares and attendant rights.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_378_zd_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 29 of 2020, s. 52 (w.e.f. 11-2-2021).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=52453&sectionno=378ZD&orderno=412&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_378_zd_content:
  string
  line `^1[378ZD.Transferability of shares and attendant rights.--(1) Save as otherwise provided in`
  line `sub-sections (2) to (4), the shares of a Member of a Producer Company shall not be transferable.`
  line
  line `(2) A Member of a Producer Company may, after obtaining the previous approval of the Board, transfer`
  line `the whole or part of his shares alongwith any special rights, to an active Member at par value.`
  line
  line `(3) Every Member shall, within three months of his becoming a Member in the Producer Company,`
  line `nominate, in the manner specified in articles, a person to whom his shares in the Producer Company shall`
  line `vest in the event of his death.`
  line
  line `(4) The nominee shall, on the death of the Member, become entitled to all the rights in the shares of the`
  line `Producer Company and the Board of that Company shall transfer the shares of the deceased Member to his`
  line `nominee:`
  line
  line `Provided that in a case where such nominee is not a producer, the Board shall direct the surrender of`
  line `shares together with special rights, if any, to the Producer Company at par value or such other value as may`
  line `be determined by the Board.`
  line
  line `(5) Where the Board of a Producer Company is satisfied that--`
  line
  line `(a) any Member has ceased to be a primary producer; or`
  line
  line `(b) any Member has failed to retain his qualifications to be a Member as specified in articles,`
  line
  line `the Board shall direct the surrender of shares together with special rights, if any, to the Producer Company`
  line `at par value or such other value as may be determined by the Board:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Board shall not direct such surrender of shares unless the Member has been served`
  line `with a written notice and given an opportunity of being heard.]`
obj_root_law_sections_378_ze:
  sectionId (52454)
  sectionNo 378ZE
  orderNo 413
  title `Books of account`
  content obj_root_law_sections_378_ze_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 29 of 2020, s. 52 (w.e.f. 11-2-2021).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=52454&sectionno=378ZE&orderno=413&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_378_ze_content:
  string
  line `^1[378ZE. Books of account.-- (1) Every Producer Company shall keep at its registered office proper`
  line `books of account with respect to--`
  line
  line `(a) all sums of money received and expended by the Producer Company and the matters in`
  line `respect of which the receipts and expenditure take place;`
  line
  line `(b) all sales and purchase of goods by the Producer Company;`
  line
  line `(c) the instruments of liability executed by or on behalf of the Producer Company;`
  line
  line `(d) the assets and liabilities of the Producer Company;`
  line
  line `(e) in case of a Producer Company engaged in production, processing and manufacturing, the`
  line `particulars relating to utilisation of materials or labour or other items of costs.`
  line
  line `(2) The balance-sheet and profit and loss accounts of the Producer Company shall be prepared, as far`
  line `as may be, in accordance with the provisions contained in section 129.]`
obj_root_law_sections_378_zf:
  sectionId (52455)
  sectionNo 378ZF
  orderNo 414
  title `Internal audit.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_378_zf_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 29 of 2020, s. 52 (w.e.f. 11-2-2021).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=52455&sectionno=378ZF&orderno=414&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_378_zf_content:
  string
  line `^1[378ZF.Internal audit.-- Every Producer Company shall have internal audit of its accounts carried`
  line `out, at such interval and in such manner as may be specified in articles, by a chartered accountant as defined`
  line `in clause (b) of sub-section (1) of section 2 of the Chartered Accountants Act, 1949 (38 of 1949).]`
obj_root_law_sections_378_zg:
  sectionId (52456)
  sectionNo 378ZG
  orderNo 415
  title `Duties of auditor under this Chapter`
  content obj_root_law_sections_378_zg_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 29 of 2020, s. 52 (w.e.f. 11-2-2021).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=52456&sectionno=378ZG&orderno=415&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_378_zg_content:
  string
  line `^1[378ZG. Duties of auditor under this Chapter.--Without prejudice to the provisions contained in`
  line `section 143, the auditor shall report on the following additional matters relating to the Producer Company,`
  line `namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the amount of debts due alongwith particulars of bad debts, if any;`
  line
  line `(b) the verification of cash balance and securities;`
  line
  line `(c) the details of assets and liabilities;`
  line
  line `(d) all transactions which appear to be contrary to the provisions of this Chapter;`
  line
  line `(e) the loans given by the Producer Company to the directors;`
  line
  line `(f) the donations or subscriptions given by the Producer Company;`
  line
  line `(g) any other matter as may be considered necessary by the auditor.]`
obj_root_law_sections_378_zh:
  sectionId (52457)
  sectionNo 378ZH
  orderNo 416
  title `Donation or subscription by Producer Company.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_378_zh_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 29 of 2020, s. 52 (w.e.f. 11-2-2021).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=52457&sectionno=378ZH&orderno=416&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_378_zh_content:
  string
  line `^1[378ZH. Donation or subscription by Producer Company.--A Producer Company may, by special`
  line `resolution, make donation or subscription to any institution or individual for the purposes of--`
  line
  line `(a) promoting the social and economic welfare of Producer Members or producers or general`
  line `public; or`
  line
  line `(b) promoting the mutual assistance principles:`
  line
  line `Provided that the aggregate amount of all such donations and subscriptions in any financial year`
  line `shall not exceed three per cent. of the net profit of the Producer Company in the financial year`
  line `immediately preceding the financial year in which the donation or subscription was made:`
  line
  line `Provided further that no Producer Company shall make directly or indirectly to any political party`
  line `or for any political purpose to any person any contribution or subscription or make available any`
  line `facilities including personnel or material.]`
obj_root_law_sections_378_z_i:
  sectionId (52458)
  sectionNo 378Z-I
  orderNo 417
  title `General and other reserves.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_378_z_i_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 29 of 2020, s. 52 (w.e.f. 11-2-2021).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=52458&sectionno=378Z-I&orderno=417&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_378_z_i_content:
  string
  line `^1[378Z-I. General and other reserves.--(1) Every Producer Company shall maintain a general reserve`
  line `in every financial year, in addition to any reserve maintained by it as may be specified in articles.`
  line
  line `(2) In a case where the Producer Company does not have sufficient funds in any financial year for`
  line `transfer to maintain the reserves as may be specified in articles, the contribution to the reserve shall be`
  line `shared amongst the Members in proportion to their patronage in the business of that Company in that year.]`
obj_root_law_sections_378_zj:
  sectionId (52459)
  sectionNo 378ZJ
  orderNo 418
  title `Issue of bonus shares.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_378_zj_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 29 of 2020, s. 52 (w.e.f. 11-2-2021).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=52459&sectionno=378ZJ&orderno=418&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_378_zj_content:
  string
  line `^1[378ZJ. Issue of bonus Shares.-- Any Producer Company may, upon recommendation of the Board`
  line `and passing of resolution in the general meeting, issue bonus shares by capitalisation of amounts from`
  line `general reserves referred to in section 378Z-I in proportion to the shares held by the Members on the date`
  line `of the issue of such shares.]`
obj_root_law_sections_378_zk:
  sectionId (52460)
  sectionNo 378ZK
  orderNo 419
  title `Loan, etc., to Members.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_378_zk_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 29 of 2020, s. 52 (w.e.f. 11-2-2021).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=52460&sectionno=378ZK&orderno=419&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_378_zk_content:
  string
  line `^1[378ZK. Loan, etc., to Members.-- The Board may, subject to the provisions made in articles, provide`
  line `financial assistance to the Members of the Producer Company by way of--`
  line
  line `(a) credit facility, to any Member, in connection with the business of the Producer Company, for a`
  line `period not exceeding six months;`
  line
  line `(b) loans and advances, against security specified in articles to any Member, repayable within a`
  line `period exceeding three months but not exceeding seven years from the date of disbursement of such`
  line `loan or advances:`
  line
  line `Provided that any loan or advance to any director or his relative shall be granted only after the approval`
  line `by the Members in general meeting.]`
obj_root_law_sections_378_zl:
  sectionId (52461)
  sectionNo 378ZL
  orderNo 420
  title `Investment in other companies, formation of subsidiaries, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_378_zl_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 29 of 2020, s. 52 (w.e.f. 11-2-2021).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=52461&sectionno=378ZL&orderno=420&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_378_zl_content:
  string
  line `^1[378ZL. Investment in other companies, formation of subsidiaries etc.-- (1) The general reserves`
  line `of any Producer Company shall be invested to secure the highest returns available from approved securities,`
  line `fixed deposits, units, bonds issued by the Government or co-operative or scheduled bank or in such other`
  line `mode as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(2) Any Producer Company may, for promotion of its objectives acquire the shares of another Producer`
  line Company.
  line
  line `(3) Any Producer Company may subscribe to the share capital of, or enter into any agreement or other`
  line `arrangement, whether by way of formation of its subsidiary company, joint venture or in any other manner`
  line `with any body corporate, for the purpose of promoting the objects of the Producer Company by special`
  line `resolution in this behalf.`
  line
  line `(4) Any Producer Company, either by itself or together with its subsidiaries, may invest, by way of`
  line `subscription, purchase or otherwise, shares in any other company, other than a Producer Company,`
  line `specified under sub-section (2), or subscription of capital under sub-section (3), for an amount not`
  line `exceeding thirty per cent. of the aggregate of its paid-up capital and free reserves:`
  line
  line `Provided that a Producer Company may, by special resolution passed in its general meeting and with`
  line `prior approval of the Central Government, invest in excess of the limits specified in this section.`
  line
  line `(5) All investments by a Producer Company may be made if such investments are consistent with the`
  line `objects of the Producer Company.`
  line
  line `(6) The Board of a Producer Company may, with the previous approval of Members by a special`
  line `resolution, dispose of any of its investments referred to in sub-sections (3) and (4).`
  line
  line `(7) Every Producer Company shall maintain a register containing particulars of all the investments,`
  line `showing the names of the companies in which shares have been acquired, number and value of shares; the`
  line `date of acquisition; and the manner and price at which any of the shares have been subsequently disposed`
  line of.
  line
  line `(8) The register referred to in sub-section (7) shall be kept at the registered office of the Producer`
  line `Company and the same shall be open to inspection by any Member who may take extracts therefrom.]`
obj_root_law_sections_378_zm:
  sectionId (52462)
  sectionNo 378ZM
  orderNo 421
  title `Penalty for contravention.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_378_zm_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 29 of 2020, s. 52 (w.e.f. 11-2-2021).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=52462&sectionno=378ZM&orderno=421&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_378_zm_content:
  string
  line `^1[378ZM. Penalty for contravention.--(1) If any person, other than a Producer Company registered`
  line `under this Chapter, carries on business under any name which contains the words "Producer Company`
  line `Limited", he shall be punishable with fine which may extend to ten thousand rupees for every day during`
  line `which such name has been used by him.`
  line
  line `(2) If a director or an officer of a Producer Company, who wilfully fails to furnish any information`
  line `relating to the affairs of the Producer Company required by a Member or a person duly authorised in this`
  line `behalf, he shall be liable to imprisonment for a term which may extend to six months and with fine`
  line `equivalent to five per cent. of the turnover of that Company during the preceding financial year.`
  line
  line `(3) If a director or officer of a Producer Company--`
  line
  line `(a) fails to hand over the custody of books of account and other documents or property in his`
  line `custody to the Producer Company of which he is a director or officer; or`
  line
  line `(b) fails to convene annual general meeting or other general meetings,`
  line
  line `he shall be punishable with fine which may extend to one lakh rupees, and in the case of a continuing default`
  line `or failure, with an additional fine which may extend to ten thousand rupees for every day during which such`
  line `default or failure continues.]`
obj_root_law_sections_378_zn:
  sectionId (52463)
  sectionNo 378ZN
  orderNo 422
  title `Amalgamation, merger or division, etc., to form new Producer Companies.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_378_zn_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 29 of 2020, s. 52 (w.e.f. 11-2-2021).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=52463&sectionno=378ZN&orderno=422&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_378_zn_content:
  string
  line `^1[378ZN. Amalgamation merger or division, etc. to form new Producer Companies.--(1) A`
  line `Producer Company may, by a resolution passed at its general meeting,--`
  line
  line `(a) decide to transfer its assets and liabilities, in whole or in part, to any other Producer Company,`
  line `which agrees to such transfer by a resolution passed at its general meeting, for any of the objects`
  line `specified in section 378B;`
  line
  line `(b) divide itself into two or more new Producer Companies.`
  line
  line `(2) Any two or more Producer Companies may, by a resolution passed at any general or special`
  line `meetings of its Members, decide to--`
  line
  line `(a) amalgamate and form a new Producer Company; or`
  line
  line `(b) merge one Producer Company (hereafter in this Chapter referred to as "merging company")`
  line `with another Producer Company (hereafter in this Chapter referred to as "merged company").`
  line
  line `(3) Every resolution of a Producer Company under this section shall be passed at its general meeting`
  line `by a majority of total Members, with right of vote not less than two-thirds of its Members present and voting`
  line `and such resolution shall contain all particulars of the transfer of assets and liabilities, or division,`
  line `amalgamation, or merger, as the case may be.`
  line
  line `(4) Before passing a resolution under this section, the Producer Company shall give notice thereof in`
  line `writing together with a copy of the proposed resolution to all the Members and creditors who may give`
  line `their consent.`
  line
  line `(5) Notwithstanding anything contained in articles or in any contract to the contrary, any Member, or`
  line `any creditor not consenting to the resolution shall, during the period of one month of the date of service of`
  line `the notice on him, have the option,--`
  line
  line `(a) in the case of any such Member, to transfer his shares with the approval of the Board to any`
  line `active Member thereby ceasing to continue as a Member of that Company; or`
  line
  line `(b) in the case of a creditor, to withdraw his deposit or loan or advance, as the case may be.`
  line
  line `(6) Any Member or creditor, who does not exercise his option within the period specified in sub-section`
  line `(5), shall be deemed to have consented to the resolution.`
  line
  line `(7) A resolution passed by a Producer Company under this section shall not take effect until the expiry`
  line `of one month or until the assent thereto of all the Members and creditors has been obtained, whichever is`
  line earlier.
  line
  line `(8) The resolution referred to in this section shall provide for--`
  line
  line `(a) the regulation of conduct of the affairs of the Producer Company in future;`
  line
  line `(b) the purchase of shares or interest of any Members of the Producer Company by other Members`
  line `or by the Producer Company;`
  line
  line `(c) the consequent reduction of its share capital, in case of purchase of shares of one Producer`
  line `Company by another Producer Company;`
  line
  line `(d) termination, setting aside or modification of any agreement, howsoever arrived between the`
  line `company on the one hand and the directors, secretaries and manager on the other hand, apart from such`
  line `terms and conditions as may, in the opinion of the majority of shareholders, be just and equitable in the`
  line `circumstances of the case;`
  line
  line `(e) termination, setting aside or modification of any agreement between the Producer Company and`
  line `any person not referred to in clause (d):`
  line
  line `Provided that no such agreement shall be terminated, set aside or modified except after giving due`
  line `notice to the party concerned:`
  line
  line `Provided further that no such agreement shall be modified except after obtaining the consent of the`
  line `party concerned;`
  line
  line `(f) the setting aside of any transfer, delivery of goods, payment, execution or other act relating to`
  line `property, made or done by or against the Producer Company within three months before the date of`
  line `passing of the resolution, which would if made or done against any individual, be deemed in his`
  line `insolvency to be a fraudulent preference;`
  line
  line `(g) the transfer to the merged company of the whole or any part of the undertaking, property or`
  line `liability of the Producer Company;`
  line
  line `(h) the allotment or appropriation by the merged company of any shares, debentures, policies, or`
  line `other like interests in the merged company;`
  line
  line `(i) the continuation by or against the merged company of any legal proceedings pending by or`
  line `against any Producer Company;`
  line
  line `(j) the dissolution, without winding up, of any Producer Company;`
  line
  line `(k) the provision to be made for the Members or creditors who make dissent;`
  line
  line `(l) the taxes, if any, to be paid by the Producer Company;`
  line
  line `(m) such incidental, consequential and supplemental matters as are necessary to secure that the`
  line `division, amalgamation or merger shall be fully and effectively carried out.`
  line
  line `(9) When a resolution passed by a Producer Company under this section takes effect, the resolution`
  line `shall be a sufficient conveyance to vest the assets and liabilities in the transferee.`
  line
  line `(10) The Producer Company shall make arrangements for meeting in full or otherwise satisfying all`
  line `claims of the Members and the creditors who exercise the option, within the period specified in sub-section`
  line `(4), not to continue as the Member or creditor, as the case may be.`
  line
  line `(11) Where the whole of the assets and liabilities of a Producer Company are transferred to another`
  line `Producer Company in accordance with the provisions of sub-section (9), or where there is merger under`
  line `sub-section (2), the registration of the first mentioned Company or the merging company, as the case may`
  line `be, shall stand cancelled and that Company shall be deemed to have been dissolved and shall cease to exist`
  line `forthwith as a corporate body.`
  line
  line `(12) Where two or more Producer Companies are amalgamated into a new Producer Company in`
  line `accordance with the provisions of sub-section (2) and the Producer Company so formed is duly registered`
  line `by the Registrar, the registration of each of the amalgamating companies shall stand cancelled forthwith on`
  line `such registration and each of the Companies shall thereupon cease to exist as a corporate body.`
  line
  line `(13) Where a Producer Company divides itself into two or more Producer Companies in accordance`
  line `with the provisions of clause (b) of sub-section (1) and the new Producer Companies are registered in`
  line `accordance with the provisions of this Chapter, the registration of the erstwhile Producer Company shall`
  line `stand cancelled forthwith and that Company shall be deemed to have been dissolved and cease to exist as a`
  line `corporate body.`
  line
  line `(14) The amalgamation, merger or division of companies under the foregoing sub-sections shall not in`
  line `any manner whatsoever affect the pre-existing rights or obligations and any legal proceedings that might have been continued or commenced by or against any erstwhile company before the amalgamation, merger`
  line `or division, may be continued or commenced by, or against, the concerned resulting company, or merged`
  line `company, as the case may be.`
  line
  line `(15) The Registrar shall strike off the names of every Producer Company deemed to have been`
  line `dissolved under sub-sections (11) to (14).`
  line
  line `(16) Any member or creditor or employee aggrieved by the transfer of assets, division, amalgamation`
  line `or merger may, within thirty days of the passing of the resolution, prefer an appeal to the Tribunal.`
  line
  line `(17) The Tribunal shall, after giving a reasonable opportunity to the person concerned, pass such orders`
  line `thereon as it may deem fit.`
  line
  line `(18) Where an appeal has been filed under sub-section (16), the transfer of assets, division,`
  line `amalgamation or merger of the Producer Company shall be subject to the decision of the Tribunal.]`
obj_root_law_sections_378_z_o:
  sectionId (52464)
  sectionNo 378Z-O
  orderNo 423
  title Disputes.
  content obj_root_law_sections_378_z_o_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 29 of 2020, s. 52 (w.e.f. 11-2-2021).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=52464&sectionno=378Z-O&orderno=423&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_378_z_o_content:
  string
  line `^1[378Z-O. Disputes.--(1) Where any dispute relating to the formation, management or business of a`
  line `Producer Company arises--`
  line
  line `(a) amongst Members, former Members or persons claiming to be Members or nominees of`
  line `deceased Members; or`
  line
  line `(b) between a Member, former Member or a person claiming to be a Member, or nominee of`
  line `deceased Member and the Producer Company, its Board of Directors, office-bearers, or liquidator, past`
  line `or present; or`
  line
  line `(c) between the Producer Company or its Board, and any director, office-bearer or any former`
  line `director, or the nominee, heir or legal representative of any deceased director of the Producer Company,`
  line
  line `such dispute shall be settled by conciliation or by arbitration as provided under the Arbitration and`
  line `Conciliation Act, 1996 (26 of 1996) as if the parties to the dispute have consented in writing for`
  line `determination of such disputes by conciliation or by arbitration and the provisions of the said Act shall`
  line `apply accordingly.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purposes of this section, a dispute shall include--`
  line
  line `(a) a claim for any debt or other amount due;`
  line
  line `(b) a claim by surety against the principal debtor, where the Producer Company has recovered from`
  line `the surety amount in respect of any debtor or other amount due to it from the principal debtor as a result`
  line `of the default of the principal debtor whether such debt or amount due be admitted or not;`
  line
  line `(c) a claim by Producer Company against a Member for failure to supply produce as required of`
  line him;
  line
  line `(d) a claim by a Member against the Producer Company for not taking goods supplied by him.`
  line
  line `(2) If any question arises whether the dispute relates to formation, management or business of the`
  line `Producer Company, the question shall be referred to the arbitrator, whose decision thereon shall be final.]`
obj_root_law_sections_378_zp:
  sectionId (52465)
  sectionNo 378ZP
  orderNo 424
  title `Strike off name of Producer Company.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_378_zp_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 29 of 2020, s. 52 (w.e.f. 11-2-2021).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=52465&sectionno=378ZP&orderno=424&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_378_zp_content:
  string
  line `^1[378ZP. Strike off name of Producer Company.-- (1) Where a Producer Company fails to commence`
  line `business within one year of its registration or ceases to transact business with the Members or if the`
  line `Registrar is satisfied, after making such inquiry as he thinks fit, that the Producer Company is no longer`
  line `carrying on any of its objects specified in section 378B, he shall make an order striking off the name of the`
  line `Producer Company, which shall thereupon cease to exist forthwith:`
  line
  line `Provided that no such order cancelling the registration as aforesaid shall be passed until a notice to`
  line `show cause has been given by the Registrar to the Producer Company with a copy to all its directors on the`
  line `proposed action and reasonable opportunity to represent its case has been given.`
  line
  line `(2) Where the Registrar has reasonable cause to believe that a Producer Company is not maintaining`
  line `any of the mutual assistance principles specified, he shall strike its name off the register in accordance with`
  line `the provisions contained in section 248.`
  line
  line `(3) Any Member of a Producer Company, who is aggrieved by an order made under sub-section (1),`
  line `may appeal to the Tribunal within sixty days of the order.`
  line
  line `(4) Where an appeal is filed under sub-section (3), the order of striking off the name shall not take effect`
  line `until the appeal is disposed of.]`
obj_root_law_sections_378_zq:
  sectionId (52466)
  sectionNo 378ZQ
  orderNo 425
  title `Provisions of this Chapter to override other laws.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_378_zq_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 29 of 2020, s. 52 (w.e.f. 11-2-2021).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=52466&sectionno=378ZQ&orderno=425&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_378_zq_content:
  string
  line `^1[378ZQ. Provisions of this Chapter to override other laws.-- The provisions of this Chapter shall`
  line `have effect notwithstanding anything inconsistent therewith contained in this Act or any other law for the`
  line `time being in force or any instrument having effect by virtue of any such law; but the provisions of any`
  line `such Act or law or instrument in so far as the same are not varied by, or are inconsistent with, the provisions`
  line `of this Chapter shall apply to the Producer Company.]`
obj_root_law_sections_378_zr:
  sectionId (52467)
  sectionNo 378ZR
  orderNo 426
  title `Application of provisions relating to private companies.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_378_zr_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 29 of 2020, s. 52 (w.e.f. 11-2-2021).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=52467&sectionno=378ZR&orderno=426&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_378_zr_content:
  string
  line `^1[378ZR. Application of provisions relating to private companies.--All the limitations, restrictions`
  line `and provisions of this Act, other than those specified in this Chapter, applicable to a private company, shall,`
  line `as far as may be, apply to a Producer Company, as if it is a private limited company under this Act in so far`
  line `as they are not in conflict with the provisions of this Chapter.]`
obj_root_law_sections_378_zs:
  sectionId (52468)
  sectionNo 378ZS
  orderNo 427
  title `Re-conversion of Producer Company to inter-State co-operative society.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_378_zs_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 29 of 2020, s. 52 (w.e.f. 11-2-2021).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=52468&sectionno=378ZS&orderno=427&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_378_zs_content:
  string
  line `^1[378ZS. Re-conversion of Producer Company to inter-State co-operative society.--(1) Any`
  line `Producer Company, being an erstwhile inter-State co-operative society, formed and registered under this`
  line `Chapter, may make an application--`
  line
  line `(a) after passing a resolution in the general meeting by not less than twothirds of its Members`
  line `present and voting; or`
  line
  line `(b) on request by its creditors representing three-fourths value of its total creditors, to the Tribunal`
  line `for its re-conversion to the inter-State co-operative society.`
  line
  line `(2) The Tribunal shall, on the application made under sub-section (1), direct holding meeting of its`
  line `Members or such creditors, as the case may be, to be conducted in such manner as it may direct.`
  line
  line `(3) If a majority in number representing three-fourths in value of the creditors, or Members, as the case`
  line `may be, present and voting in person at the meeting conducted in pursuance of the directions of the Tribunal`
  line `under sub-section (2), agree for re-conversion, if sanctioned by the Tribunal, be binding on all the Members`
  line `and all the creditors, as the case may be, and also on the company which is being converted:`
  line
  line `Provided that no order sanctioning re-conversion shall be made by the Tribunal unless the Tribunal is`
  line `satisfied that the company or any other person by whom an application has been made under sub-section`
  line `(1) has disclosed to the Tribunal, by affidavit or otherwise, all material facts relating to the company, such`
  line `as the latest financial position of the company, the latest report of the auditor on the accounts of the`
  line `company, the pendency of any investigation proceedings in relation to the company under Chapter XIV,`
  line `and the like.`
  line
  line `(4) An order made by the Tribunal under sub-section (3) shall have no effect until a certified copy of`
  line `the order has been filed with the Registrar.`
  line
  line `(5) A copy of every such order shall be annexed to every copy of the memorandum of the company`
  line `issued after the certified copy of the order has been filed as aforesaid, or in the case of a company not having`
  line `a memorandum, to every copy so issued of the instrument constituting or defining the constitution of the`
  line company.
  line
  line `(6) If default is made in complying with sub-section (4), the company, and every officer of the company`
  line `who is in default, shall be punishable with fine which may extend to one hundred rupees, for each copy in`
  line `respect of which default is made.`
  line
  line `(7) The Tribunal may, at any time after an application has been made to it under this section, stay the`
  line `commencement or continuation of any suit or proceeding against the company on such terms as the Tribunal`
  line `thinks fit, until the application is finally disposed of.`
  line
  line `(8) Every Producer Company, which has been sanctioned re-conversion by the Tribunal, shall make an`
  line `application under the Multi-State Co-operative Societies Act, 2002 (39 of 2002) or any other law for the`
  line `time being in force for its registration as multi-State co-operative society or co-operative society, as the`
  line `case may be, within six months of sanction by the Tribunal and file a report thereof to the Tribunal and the`
  line `Registrar of Companies and to the Registrar of the Co-operative Societies under which it has been registered`
  line `as a multi-State co-operative society or co-operative society, as the case may be.]`
obj_root_law_sections_378_zt:
  sectionId (52469)
  sectionNo 378ZT
  orderNo 428
  title `Power to modify Act in its application to Producer Companies`
  content obj_root_law_sections_378_zt_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 29 of 2020, s. 52 (w.e.f. 11-2-2021).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=52469&sectionno=378ZT&orderno=428&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_378_zt_content:
  string
  line `^1[378ZT. Power to modify Act in its application to Producer Companies.--(1) The Central`
  line `Government may, by notification, direct that any of the provisions of this Act (other than those contained`
  line `in this Chapter) specified in the said notification--`
  line
  line `(a) shall not apply to the Producer Companies or any class or category thereof; or`
  line
  line `(b) shall apply to the Producer Companies or any class or category thereof with such exception or`
  line `adaptation as may be specified in the notification.`
  line
  line `(2) A copy of every notification proposed to be issued under sub-section (1), shall be laid in draft before`
  line `each House of Parliament, while it is in session, for a total period of thirty days which may be comprised`
  line `in one session or in two or more successive sessions, and if, before the expiry of the session immediately`
  line `following the session or the successive sessions aforesaid, both Houses agree in disapproving the issue of`
  line `the notification or both Houses agree in making any modification in the notification, the notification shall`
  line `not be issued or, as the case may be, shall be issued only in such modified form as may be agreed upon by`
  line `both the Houses.]`
obj_root_law_sections_378_zu:
  sectionId (52470)
  sectionNo 378ZU
  orderNo 429
  title `Power to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_378_zu_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 29 of 2020, s. 52 (w.e.f. 11-2-2021).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=52470&sectionno=378ZU&orderno=429&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_378_zu_content:
  string
  line `^1[378ZU. Power to make rules.--The Central Government may make rules for carrying out the purposes`
  line `of this Chapter.]`
obj_root_law_sections_379:
  sectionId (49274)
  sectionNo (379)
  orderNo 430
  title `Application of Act to foreign companies`
  content obj_root_law_sections_379_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_379_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=49274&sectionno=379&orderno=430&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_379_content:
  string
  line `^1[(1) Sections 380 to 386 (both inclusive) and sections`
  line `392 and 393 shall apply to all foreign companies:`
  line
  line `^2* * * * *`
  line
  line `^3[(2)] Where not less than fifty per cent. of the paid-up share capital, whether equity or preference or`
  line `partly equity and partly preference, of a foreign company is held by one or more citizens of India or by one`
  line `or more companies or bodies corporate incorporated in India, or by one or more citizens of India and one`
  line `or more companies or bodies corporate incorporated in India, whether singly or in the aggregate, such`
  line `company shall comply with the provisions of this Chapter and such other provisions of this Act as may be`
  line `prescribed with regard to the business carried on by it in India as if it were a company incorporated in India.`
obj_root_law_sections_379_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 1 of 2018, s. 77 (w.e.f. 9-2-2018).`
  line
  line `2. The Proviso omitted by Act 29 of 2020, s. 53 (w.e.f. 22-1-2021).`
  line
  line `3. Section 379 renumbered as sub-section (2) thereof by s. 77, ibid. (w.e.f. 9-2-2018).`
obj_root_law_sections_380:
  sectionId (49275)
  sectionNo (380)
  orderNo 431
  title `Documents, etc., to be delivered to Registrar by foreign companies.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_380_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_380_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=49275&sectionno=380&orderno=431&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_380_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every foreign`
  line `company shall, within thirty days of the establishment of its place of business in India, deliver to the`
  line `Registrar for registration--`
  line
  line `(a) a certified copy of the charter, statutes or memorandum and articles, of the company or other`
  line `instrument constituting or defining the constitution of the company and, if the instrument is not in the`
  line `English language, a certified translation thereof in the English language;`
  line
  line `(b) the full address of the registered or principal office of the company;`
  line
  line `(c) a list of the directors and secretary of the company containing such particulars as may be`
  line prescribed;
  line
  line `(d) the name and address or the names and addresses of one or more persons resident in India`
  line `authorised to accept on behalf of the company service of process and any notices or other documents`
  line `required to be served on the company;`
  line
  line `(e) the full address of the office of the company in India which is deemed to be its principal place`
  line `of business in India;`
  line
  line `(f) particulars of opening and closing of a place of business in India on earlier occasion or`
  line occasions;
  line
  line `(g) declaration that none of the directors of the company or the authorised representative in India`
  line `has ever been convicted or debarred from formation of companies and management in India or`
  line `abroad; and`
  line
  line `(h) any other information as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(2) Every foreign company existing at the commencement of this Act shall, if it has not delivered to`
  line `the Registrar before such commencement, the documents and particulars specified in sub-section (1) of`
  line `section 592 of the Companies Act, 1956 (1 of 1956), continue to be subject to the obligation to deliver`
  line `those documents and particulars in accordance with that Act.`
  line
  line `(3) Where any alteration is made or occurs in the documents delivered to the Registrar under this`
  line `section, the foreign company shall, within thirty days of such alteration, deliver to the Registrar for`
  line `registration, a return containing the particulars of the alteration in the prescribed form.`
obj_root_law_sections_380_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_381:
  sectionId (49276)
  sectionNo (381)
  orderNo 432
  title `Accounts of foreign company.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_381_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_381_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=49276&sectionno=381&orderno=432&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_381_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every foreign company shall, in every calendar year,--`
  line
  line `(a) make out a balance sheet and profit and loss account in such form, containing such particulars`
  line `and including or having annexed or attached thereto such documents as may be prescribed; and`
  line
  line `(b) deliver a copy of those documents to the Registrar:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Central Government may, by notification, direct that, in the case of any foreign`
  line `company or class of foreign companies, the requirements of clause (a) shall not apply, or shall apply`
  line `subject to such exceptions and modifications as may be specified in that notification.`
  line
  line `(2) If any such document as is mentioned in sub-section (1) is not in the English language, there shall`
  line `be annexed to it a certified translation thereof in the English language.`
  line
  line `(3) Every foreign company shall send to the Registrar along with the documents required to be`
  line `delivered to him under sub-section (1), a copy of a list in the prescribed form of all places of business`
  line `established by the company in India as at the date with reference to which the balance sheet referred to in`
  line `sub-section (1) is made out.`
obj_root_law_sections_381_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_382:
  sectionId (49277)
  sectionNo (382)
  orderNo 433
  title `Display of name, etc., of foreign company`
  content obj_root_law_sections_382_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_382_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=49277&sectionno=382&orderno=433&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_382_content:
  string
  line `Every foreign company shall--`
  line
  line `(a) conspicuously exhibit on the outside of every office or place where it carries on business in`
  line `India, the name of the company and the country in which it is incorporated, in letters easily legible in`
  line `English characters, and also in the characters of the language or one of the languages in general use in`
  line `the locality in which the office or place is situate;`
  line
  line `(b) cause the name of the company and of the country in which the company is incorporated, to`
  line `be stated in legible English characters in all business letters, billheads and letter paper, and in all`
  line `notices, and other official publications of the company; and`
  line
  line `(c) if the liability of the members of the company is limited, cause notice of that fact`
  line
  line `(i) to be stated in every such prospectus issued and in all business letters, bill-heads, letter`
  line `paper, notices, advertisements and other official publications of the company, in legible English`
  line `characters; and`
  line
  line `(ii) to be conspicuously exhibited on the outside of every office or place where it carries on`
  line `business in India, in legible English characters and also in legible characters of the language or`
  line `one of the languages in general use in the locality in which the office or place is situate.`
obj_root_law_sections_382_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_383:
  sectionId (49278)
  sectionNo (383)
  orderNo 434
  title `Service on foreign company.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_383_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_383_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=49278&sectionno=383&orderno=434&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_383_content:
  string
  line `Any process, notice, or other document required to be served`
  line `on a foreign company shall be deemed to be sufficiently served, if addressed to any person whose name`
  line `and address have been delivered to the Registrar under section 380 and left at, or sent by post to, the`
  line `address which has been so delivered to the Registrar or by electronic mode.`
obj_root_law_sections_383_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_384:
  sectionId (49279)
  sectionNo (384)
  orderNo 435
  title `Debentures, annual return, registration of charges, books of account and their inspection.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_384_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 1 of 2018, s. 78 (w.e.f. 9-2-2018).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=49279&sectionno=384&orderno=435&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_384_content:
  string
  line `(1) The provisions of section 71 shall apply mutatis mutandis to a foreign company.`
  line
  line `(2) The provisions of section 92 ^1[and section 135] shall, subject to such exceptions, modifications`
  line `and adaptations as may be made therein by rules made under this Act, apply to a foreign company as they`
  line `apply to a company incorporated in India.`
  line
  line `(3) The provisions of section 128 shall apply to a foreign company to the extent of requiring it to keep`
  line `at its principal place of business in India, the books of account referred to in that section, with respect to`
  line `monies received and spent, sales and purchases made, and assets and liabilities, in the course of or in`
  line `relation to its business in India.`
  line
  line `(4) The provisions of Chapter VI shall apply mutatis mutandis to charges on properties which are`
  line `created or acquired by any foreign company.`
  line
  line `(5) The provisions of Chapter XIV shall apply mutatis mutandis to the Indian business of a foreign`
  line `company as they apply to a company incorporated in India.`
obj_root_law_sections_385:
  sectionId (49280)
  sectionNo (385)
  orderNo 436
  title `Fee for registration of documents.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_385_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_385_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=49280&sectionno=385&orderno=436&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_385_content:
  string
  line `There shall be paid to the Registrar for registering any`
  line `document required by the provisions of this Chapter to be registered by him, such fee, as may be`
  line prescribed.
obj_root_law_sections_385_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_386:
  sectionId (49281)
  sectionNo (386)
  orderNo 437
  title Interpretation
  content obj_root_law_sections_386_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_386_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=49281&sectionno=386&orderno=437&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_386_content:
  string
  line `For the purposes of the foregoing provisions of this Chapter,--`
  line
  line `(a) the expression "certified" means certified in the prescribed manner to be a true copy or a`
  line `correct translation;`
  line
  line `(b) the expression "director", in relation to a foreign company, includes any person in accordance`
  line `with whose directions or instructions the Board of Directors of the company is accustomed to act; and`
  line
  line `(c) the expression "place of business" includes a share transfer or registration office.`
obj_root_law_sections_386_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_387:
  sectionId (49282)
  sectionNo (387)
  orderNo 438
  title `Dating of prospectus and particulars to be contained therein.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_387_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_387_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=49282&sectionno=387&orderno=438&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_387_content:
  string
  line `(1) No person shall issue,`
  line `circulate or distribute in India any prospectus offering to subscribe for securities of a company`
  line `incorporated or to be incorporated outside India, whether the company has or has not established, or when`
  line `formed will or will not establish, a place of business in India, unless the prospectus is dated and signed,`
  line and--
  line
  line `(a) contains particulars with respect to the following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(i) the instrument constituting or defining the constitution of the company;`
  line
  line `(ii) the enactments or provisions by or under which the incorporation of the company was`
  line effected;
  line
  line `(iii) address in India where the said instrument, enactments or provisions, or copies thereof,`
  line `and if the same are not in the English language, a certified translation thereof in the English`
  line `language can be inspected;`
  line
  line `(iv) the date on which and the country in which the company would be or was incorporated;`
  line and
  line
  line `(v) whether the company has established a place of business in India and, if so, the address of`
  line `its principal office in India; and`
  line
  line `(b) states the matters specified under section 26:`
  line
  line `Provided that sub-clauses (i), (ii) and (iii) of clause (a) of this sub-section shall not apply in the case`
  line `of a prospectus issued more than two years after the date at which the company is entitled to commence`
  line business.
  line
  line `(2) Any condition requiring or binding an applicant for securities to waive compliance with any`
  line `requirement imposed by virtue of sub-section (1), or purporting to impute him with notice of any contract,`
  line `documents or matter not specifically referred to in the prospectus, shall be void.`
  line
  line `(3) No person shall issue to any person in India a form of application for securities of such a company`
  line `or intended company as is mentioned in sub-section (1), unless the form is issued with a prospectus which`
  line `complies with the provisions of this Chapter and such issue does not contravene the provisions of section`
  line `388:`
  line
  line `Provided that this sub-section shall not apply if it is shown that the form of application was issued in`
  line `connection with a bona fide invitation to a person to enter into an underwriting agreement with respect to`
  line securities.
  line
  line `(4) This section--`
  line
  line `(a) shall not apply to the issue to existing members or debenture holders of a company of a`
  line `prospectus or form of application relating to securities of the company, whether an applicant for`
  line `securities will or will not have the right to renounce in favour of other persons; and`
  line
  line `(b) except in so far as it requires a prospectus to be dated, to the issue of a prospectus relating to`
  line `securities which are or are to be in all respects uniform with securities previously issued and for the`
  line `time being dealt in or quoted on a recognised stock exchange,`
  line
  line `but, subject as aforesaid, this section shall apply to a prospectus or form of application whether issued on or with reference to the formation of a company or subsequently.`
  line
  line `(5) Nothing in this section shall limit or diminish any liability which any person may incur under any`
  line `law for the time being in force in India or under this Act apart from this section.`
obj_root_law_sections_387_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_388:
  sectionId (49283)
  sectionNo (388)
  orderNo 439
  title `Provisions as to expert‘s consent and allotment.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_388_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_388_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=49283&sectionno=388&orderno=439&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_388_content:
  string
  line `(1) No person shall issue, circulate or`
  line `distribute in India any prospectus offering for subscription in securities of a company incorporated or to`
  line `be incorporated outside India, whether the company has or has not been established, or when formed will`
  line `or will not establish, a place of business in India,--`
  line
  line `(a) if, where the prospectus includes a statement purporting to be made by an expert, he has not`
  line `given, or has before delivery of the prospectus for registration withdrawn, his written consent to the`
  line `issue of the prospectus with the statement included in the form and context in which it is included, or`
  line `there does not appear in the prospectus a statement that he has given and has not withdrawn his`
  line `consent as aforesaid; or`
  line
  line `(b) if the prospectus does not have the effect, where an application is made in pursuance thereof,`
  line `of rendering all persons concerned bound by all the provisions of sections 33 and 40, so far as`
  line applicable.
  line
  line `(2) For the purposes of this section, a statement shall be deemed to be included in a prospectus, if it is`
  line `contained in any report or memorandum appearing on the face thereof or by reference incorporated`
  line `therein or issued therewith.`
obj_root_law_sections_388_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_389:
  sectionId (49284)
  sectionNo (389)
  orderNo 440
  title `Registration of prospectus.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_389_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_389_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=49284&sectionno=389&orderno=440&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_389_content:
  string
  line `No person shall issue, circulate or distribute in India any`
  line `prospectus offering for subscription in securities of a company incorporated or to be incorporated outside`
  line `India, whether the company has or has not established, or when formed will or will not establish, a place`
  line `of business in India, unless before the issue, circulation or distribution of the prospectus in India, a copy`
  line `thereof certified by the chairperson of the company and two other directors of the company as having`
  line `been approved by resolution of the managing body has been delivered for registration to the Registrar and`
  line `the prospectus states on the face of it that a copy has been so delivered, and there is endorsed on or`
  line `attached to the copy, any consent to the issue of the prospectus required by section 388 and such`
  line `documents as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_389_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_390:
  sectionId (49285)
  sectionNo (390)
  orderNo 441
  title `Offer of India Depository Receipts`
  content obj_root_law_sections_390_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_390_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=49285&sectionno=390&orderno=441&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_390_content:
  string
  line `Notwithstanding anything contained in any other law`
  line `for the time being in force, the Central Government may make rules applicable for--`
  line
  line `(a) the offer of Indian Depository Receipts;`
  line
  line `(b) the requirement of disclosures in prospectus or letter of offer issued in connection with Indian`
  line `Depository Receipts;`
  line
  line `(c) the manner in which the Indian Depository Receipts shall be dealt with in a depository mode`
  line `and by custodian and underwriters; and`
  line
  line `(d) the manner of sale, transfer or transmission of Indian Depository Receipts,`
  line
  line `by a company incorporated or to be incorporated outside India, whether the company has or has not`
  line `established, or will or will not establish, any place of business in India.`
obj_root_law_sections_390_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_391:
  sectionId (49286)
  sectionNo (391)
  orderNo 442
  title `Application of sections 34 to 36 and Chapter XX`
  content obj_root_law_sections_391_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 1 of 2018, s. 79, for sub-section (2) (w.e.f. 9-2-2018).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=49286&sectionno=391&orderno=442&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_391_content:
  string
  line `(1) The provisions of sections 34 to 36`
  line `(both inclusive) shall apply to--`
  line
  line `(i) the issue of a prospectus by a company incorporated outside India under section 389 as they`
  line `apply to prospectus issued by an Indian company;`
  line
  line `(ii) the issue of Indian Depository Receipts by a foreign company.`
  line
  line `^1[(2) Subject to the provisions of section 376, the provisions of Chapter XX shall apply mutatis`
  line `mutandis for closure of the place of business of a foreign company in India as if it were a company`
  line `incorporated in India in case such foreign company has raised monies through offer or issue of securities`
  line `under this Chapter which have not been repaid or redeemed.]`
obj_root_law_sections_392:
  sectionId (49287)
  sectionNo (392)
  orderNo 443
  title `Punishment for contravention`
  content `Without prejudice to the provisions of section 391, if a foreign company contravenes the provisions of this Chapter, the foreign company shall be punishable with fine which shall not be less than one lakh rupees but which may extend to three lakh rupees and in the case of a continuing offence, with an additional fine which may extend to fifty thousand rupees for every day after the first during which the contravention continues and every officer of the foreign company who is in default shall be punishable ^1*** with fine which shall not be less than twenty-five thousand rupees but which may extend to ^2[five lakh rupees].`
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_392_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=49287&sectionno=392&orderno=443&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_392_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. The words "with imprisonment for a term which may extend to six months or"omitted by Act 29 of 2020, s. 54 (w.e.f. 21-12-`
  line `2020).`
  line
  line `2.Subs. by s. 54, ibid., for "fifty thousand rupees, or with both" (w.e.f. 21-12-2020).`
obj_root_law_sections_393:
  sectionId (49288)
  sectionNo (393)
  orderNo 444
  title `Company‘s failure to comply with provisions of this Chapter not to affect validity or contracts, etc`
  content obj_root_law_sections_393_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_393_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=49288&sectionno=393&orderno=444&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_393_content:
  string
  line `Any failure by a company to comply with the provisions of this Chapter shall not affect`
  line `the validity of any contract, dealing or transaction entered into by the company or its liability to be sued in`
  line `respect thereof, but the company shall not be entitled to bring any suit, claim any set-off, make any`
  line `counter-claim or institute any legal proceeding in respect of any such contract, dealing or transaction,`
  line `until the company has complied with the provisions of this Act applicable to it.`
obj_root_law_sections_393_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_393_a:
  sectionId (51985)
  sectionNo 393A
  orderNo 445
  title `Exemptions under this Chapter.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_393_a_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_393_a_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=51985&sectionno=393A&orderno=445&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_393_a_content:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_393_a_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_394:
  sectionId (49289)
  sectionNo (394)
  orderNo 446
  title `Annual reports on Government companies.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_394_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_394_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=49289&sectionno=394&orderno=446&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_394_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where the Central Government is a member`
  line `of a Government company, the Central Government shall cause an annual report on the working and`
  line `affairs of that company to be--`
  line
  line `(a) prepared within three months of its annual general meeting before which the comments given`
  line `by the Comptroller and Auditor-General of India and the audit report is placed under the proviso to`
  line `sub-section (6) of section 143; and`
  line
  line `(b) as soon as may be after such preparation, laid before both Houses of Parliament together with`
  line `a copy of the audit report and comments upon or supplement to the audit report, made by the`
  line `Comptroller and Auditor-General of India.`
  line
  line `(2) Where in addition to the Central Government, any State Government is also a member of a`
  line `Government company, that State Government shall cause a copy of the annual report prepared under subsection`
  line
  line `(1) to be laid before the House or both Houses of the State Legislature together with a copy of the`
  line `audit report and the comments upon or supplement to the audit report referred to in sub-section (1).`
obj_root_law_sections_394_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_395:
  sectionId (49290)
  sectionNo (395)
  orderNo 447
  title `Annual reports where one or more State Governments are members of companies.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_395_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_395_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=49290&sectionno=395&orderno=447&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_395_content:
  string
  line `(1)`
  line `Where the Central Government is not a member of a Government company, every State Government`
  line `which is a member of that company, or where only one State Government is a member of the company,`
  line `that State Government shall cause an annual report on the working and affairs of the company to be`
  line
  line `(a) prepared within the time specified in sub-section (1) of section 394; and`
  line
  line `(b) as soon as may be after such preparation, laid before the House or both Houses of the State`
  line `Legislature together with a copy of the audit report and comments upon or supplement to the audit`
  line `report referred to in sub-section (1) of that section.`
  line
  line `(2) The provisions of this section and section 394 shall, so far as may be, apply to a Government`
  line `company in liquidation as they apply to any other Government company.`
obj_root_law_sections_395_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_396:
  sectionId (49291)
  sectionNo (396)
  orderNo 448
  title `Registration offices.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_396_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_396_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=49291&sectionno=396&orderno=448&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_396_content:
  string
  line `(1) For the purposes of exercising such powers and discharging such`
  line `functions as are conferred on the Central Government by or under this Act or under the rules made`
  line `thereunder and for the purposes of registration of companies under this Act, the Central Government`
  line `shall, by notification, establish such number of offices at such places as it thinks fit, specifying their`
  line jurisdiction.
  line
  line `(2) The Central Government may appoint such Registrars, Additional, Joint, Deputy and Assistant`
  line `Registrars as it considers necessary for the registration of companies and discharge of various functions`
  line `under this Act, and the powers and duties that may be exercisable by such officers shall be such as may be`
  line prescribed.
  line
  line `(3) The terms and conditions of service, including the salaries payable to persons appointed under`
  line `sub-section (2), shall be such as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(4) The Central Government may direct a seal or seals to be prepared for the authentication of`
  line `documents required for, or connected with, the registration of companies.`
obj_root_law_sections_396_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_397:
  sectionId (49292)
  sectionNo (397)
  orderNo 449
  title `Admissibility of certain documents as evidence.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_397_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_397_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=49292&sectionno=397&orderno=449&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_397_content:
  string
  line `Notwithstanding anything contained in any`
  line `other law for the time being in force, any document reproducing or derived from returns and documents`
  line `filed by a company with the Registrar on paper or in electronic form or stored on any electronic data`
  line `storage device or computer readable media by the Registrar, and authenticated by the Registrar or any`
  line `other officer empowered by the Central Government in such manner as may be prescribed, shall be`
  line `deemed to be a document for the purposes of this Act and the rules made thereunder and shall be`
  line `admissible in any proceedings thereunder without further proof or production of the original as evidence`
  line `of any contents of the original or of any fact stated therein of which direct evidence is admissible.`
obj_root_law_sections_397_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_398:
  sectionId (49293)
  sectionNo (398)
  orderNo 450
  title `Provisions relating to filing of applications, documents, inspection, etc., in electronic form.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_398_content
  footnotes `1. The word "prospectus" omitted by Act 22 of 2019, s. 38 (w.e.f. 15-8-2019).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=49293&sectionno=398&orderno=450&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_398_content:
  string
  line `(1) Notwithstanding anything to the contrary contained in this Act, and without prejudice to the`
  line `provisions contained in section 6 of the Information Technology Act, 2000 (21 of 2000), the Central`
  line `Government may make rules so as to require from such date as may be prescribed in the rules that--`
  line
  line `(a) such applications, balance sheet, prospectus, return, declaration, memorandum, articles,`
  line `particulars of charges, or any other particulars or document as may be required to be filed or delivered`
  line `under this Act or the rules made thereunder, shall be filed in the electronic form and authenticated in`
  line `such manner as may be prescribed;`
  line
  line `(b) such document, notice, any communication or intimation, as may be required to be served or`
  line `delivered under this Act, in the electronic form and authenticated in such manner as may be`
  line prescribed;
  line
  line `(c) such applications, balance sheet, prospectus, return, register, memorandum, articles,`
  line `particulars of charges, or any other particulars or document and return filed under this Act or rules`
  line `made thereunder shall be maintained by the Registrar in the electronic form and registered or`
  line `authenticated, as the case may be, in such manner as may be prescribed;`
  line
  line `(d) such inspection of the memorandum, articles, register, index, balance sheet, return or any`
  line `other particulars or document maintained in the electronic form, as is otherwise available for`
  line `inspection under this Act or the rules made thereunder, may be made by any person through the`
  line `electronic form in such manner as may be prescribed;`
  line
  line `(e) such fees, charges or other sums payable under this Act or the rules made thereunder shall be`
  line `paid through the electronic form and in such manner as may be prescribed; and`
  line
  line `(f) the Registrar shall register change of registered office, alteration of memorandum or articles,`
  line `^1*** issue certificate of incorporation, register such document, issue such certificate, record the`
  line `notice, receive such communication as may be required to be registered or issued or recorded or`
  line `received, as the case may be, under this Act or the rules made thereunder or perform duties or`
  line `discharge functions or exercise powers under this Act or the rules made thereunder or do any act`
  line `which is by this Act directed to be performed or discharged or exercised or done by the Registrar in`
  line `the electronic form in such manner as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `Explanation. --For the removal of doubts, it is hereby clarified that the rules made under this section`
  line `shall not relate to imposition of fines or other pecuniary penalties or demand or payment of fees or`
  line `contravention of any of the provisions of this Act or punishment therefor.`
  line
  line `(2) The Central Government may, by notification, frame a scheme to carry out the provisions of subsection`
  line `(1) through the electronic form.`
obj_root_law_sections_399:
  sectionId (49294)
  sectionNo (399)
  orderNo 451
  title `Inspection, production and evidence of documents kept by Registrar`
  content obj_root_law_sections_399_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_399_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=49294&sectionno=399&orderno=451&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_399_content:
  string
  line `(1) Save as`
  line `otherwise provided elsewhere in this Act, any person may--`
  line
  line `(a) inspect by electronic means any documents kept by the Registrar in accordance with the rules`
  line `made, being documents filed or registered by him in pursuance of this Act, or making a record of any`
  line `fact required or authorised to be recorded or registered in pursuance of this Act, on payment for each`
  line `inspection of such fees as may be prescribed;`
  line
  line `(b) require a certificate of the incorporation of any company, or a copy or extract of any other`
  line `document or any part of any other document to be certified by the Registrar, on payment in advance`
  line `of such fees as may be prescribed:`
  line
  line `Provided that the rights conferred by this sub-section shall be exercisable--`
  line
  line `(i) in relation to documents delivered to the Registrar with a prospectus in pursuance of`
  line `section 26, only during the fourteen days beginning with the date of publication of the prospectus;`
  line `and at other times, only with the permission of the Central Government; and`
  line
  line `(ii) in relation to documents so delivered in pursuance of clause (b) of subsection (1) of`
  line `section 388, only during the fourteen days beginning with the date of the prospectus; and at other`
  line `times, only with the permission of the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(2) No process for compelling the production of any document kept by the Registrar shall issue from`
  line `any court or the Tribunal except with the leave of that court or the Tribunal and any such process, if`
  line `issued, shall bear thereon a statement that it is issued with the leave of the court or the Tribunal.`
  line
  line `(3) A copy of, or extract from, any document kept and registered at any of the offices for the`
  line `registration of companies under this Act, certified to be a true copy by the Registrar (whose official`
  line `position it shall not be necessary to prove), shall, in all legal proceedings, be admissible in evidence as of`
  line `equal validity with the original document.`
obj_root_law_sections_399_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_400:
  sectionId (49295)
  sectionNo (400)
  orderNo 452
  title `Electronic form to be exclusive, alternative or in addition to physical form.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_400_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_400_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=49295&sectionno=400&orderno=452&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_400_content:
  string
  line `The Central`
  line `Government may also provide in the rules made under section 398 and section 399 that the electronic`
  line `form for the purposes specified in these sections shall be exclusive, or in the alternative or in addition to`
  line `the physical form, therefor.`
obj_root_law_sections_400_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_401:
  sectionId (49296)
  sectionNo (401)
  orderNo 453
  title `Provision of value added services through electronic form`
  content obj_root_law_sections_401_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_401_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=49296&sectionno=401&orderno=453&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_401_content:
  string
  line `The Central Government may`
  line `provide such value added services through the electronic form and levy such fee thereon as may be`
  line prescribed.
obj_root_law_sections_401_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_402:
  sectionId (49297)
  sectionNo (402)
  orderNo 454
  title `Application of provisions of Information Technology Act, 2000.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_402_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_402_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=49297&sectionno=402&orderno=454&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_402_content:
  string
  line `All the provisions of the`
  line `Information Technology Act, 2000 (21 of 2000) relating to the electronic records, including the manner`
  line `and format in which the electronic records shall be filed, in so far as they are not inconsistent with this`
  line `Act, shall apply in relation to the records in electronic form specified under section 398.`
obj_root_law_sections_402_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_403:
  sectionId (49298)
  sectionNo (403)
  orderNo 455
  title `Fee for filing, etc`
  content obj_root_law_sections_403_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_403_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=49298&sectionno=403&orderno=455&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_403_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any document, required to be submitted, filed, registered or recorded,`
  line `or any fact or information required or authorised to be registered under this Act, shall be submitted, filed, registered or recorded within the time specified in the relevant provision on payment of such fee as may be prescribed:`
  line
  line `^1[Provided that where any document, fact or information required to be submitted, filed, registered or recorded, as the case may be, under section 92 or 137 is not submited, filed, registered or recorded, as the case may be, within the period provided in those sections, without prejudice to any other legal action or liability under this Act, it may be submitted, filed, registered or recorded, as the case may be, after expiry of the period so provided in those sections, on payment of such additional fee as may be prescribed,`
  line `which shall not be less than one hundred rupees per day and different amounts may be prescribed for different classes of companies:]`
  line
  line `^2[Provided further that where the document, fact or information, as the case may be, in cases other than referred to in the first proviso, is not submitted, filed, registered or recorded, as the case may be, within the period provided in the relevant section, it may, without prejudice to any other legal action or liability under this Act, be submitted, filed, registered or recorded as the case may be, on payment of such additional fee as may be prescribed and different fees may be prescribed for different classes of companies:`
  line
  line `^3[Provided also that where there is default on two or more occasions in submitting, filing, registering or recording of such document, fact or information, as may be prescribed, it may, without prejudice to any other legal action or liability under this Act, be submitted, filed, registered or recorded, as the case may be, on payment of such higher additional fee, as may be prescribed.]]`
  line
  line `^4[(2) Where a company fails or commits any default to submit, file, register or record any document,`
  line `fact or information under sub-section (1) before the expiry of the period specified in the relevant section,`
  line `the company and the officers of the company who are in default, shall, without prejudice to the liability`
  line `for the payment of fee and additional fee, be liable for the penalty or punishment provided under this Act`
  line `for such failure or default.]`
obj_root_law_sections_403_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 1 of 2018, s. 80, for the first proviso (w.e.f. 7-5-2018).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by, s. 80, ibid, for second and third proviso (w.e.f. 1-7-2022).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 29 of 2020, s. 56, for the third proviso (w.e.f. 1-7-2022).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by Act 1 of 2018, s. 80, for sub-section (2) (w.e.f. 7-5-2018).`
obj_root_law_sections_404:
  sectionId (49299)
  sectionNo (404)
  orderNo 456
  title `Fees, etc., to be credited into public account.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_404_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_404_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=49299&sectionno=404&orderno=456&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_404_content:
  string
  line `All fees, charges and other sums received by`
  line `any Registrar, Additional, Joint, Deputy or Assistant Registrar or any other officer of the Central`
  line `Government in pursuance of any provision of this Act shall be paid into the public account of India in the`
  line `Reserve Bank of India.`
obj_root_law_sections_404_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_405:
  sectionId (49300)
  sectionNo (405)
  orderNo 457
  title `Power of Central Government to direct companies to furnish information or statistics.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_405_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 29 of 2020, s. 57, for sub-section (4) (w.e.f. 21-12-2020).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=49300&sectionno=405&orderno=457&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_405_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may, by order, require companies generally, or any class of companies, or any company, to furnish such information or statistics with regard to their or its constitution or working, and within such time, as may be specified in the order.`
  line
  line `(2) Every order under sub-section (1) shall be published in the Official Gazette and may be addressed to companies generally or to any class of companies, in such manner, as the Central Government may think fit and the date of such publication shall be deemed to be the date on which requirement for information or statistics is made on such companies or class of companies, as the case may be.`
  line
  line `(3) For the purpose of satisfying itself that any information or statistics furnished by a company or companies in pursuance of any order under sub-section (1) is correct and complete, the Central Government may by order require such company or companies to produce such records or documents in its possession or allow inspection thereof by such officer or furnish such further information as that Government may consider necessary.`
  line
  line `^1 [(4) If any company fails to comply with an order made under sub-section (1) or sub-section (3), or furnishes any information or statistics which is incorrect or incomplete in any material respect, the company and every officer of the company who is in default, shall be liable to a penalty of twenty thousand rupees and in case of continuing failure, with a further penalty of one thousand rupees for each day after the first during which such failure continues, subject to a maximum of three lakh rupees.]`
  line
  line `(5) Where a foreign company carries on business in India, all references to a company in this section shall be deemed to include references to the foreign company in relation, and only in relation, to such business.`
obj_root_law_sections_406:
  sectionId (49301)
  sectionNo (406)
  orderNo 458
  title `Provision relating to Nidhis and its application, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_406_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 1 of 2018, s. 81, for section 406 (w.e.f. 15-8-2019).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=49301&sectionno=406&orderno=458&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_406_content:
  string
  line `^1[406. Provision relating to Nidhis and its application, etc.--(1) In this section, "iNidhi" or "Mutual`
  line `Benefit Society" means a company which the Central Government may, by notification in the Official`
  line `Gazette, declare to be a Nidhis or Mutual Benefit Society, as the case may be.`
  line
  line `(2) The Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette, direct that any of the`
  line `provisions of this Act specified in the notification--`
  line
  line `(a) shall not apply to any Nidhis or Mutual Benefit Society; or`
  line
  line `(b) shall apply to any Nidhis or Mutual Benefit Society with such exceptions, modifications and`
  line `adaptations as may be specified in the notification.`
  line
  line `(3) A copy of every notification proposed to be issued under sub-section (2), shall be laid in draft`
  line `before each House of Parliament, while it is in session, for a total period of thirty days, and if, both`
  line `Houses agree in disapproving the issue of notification or both Houses agree in making any modification`
  line `in the notification, the notification shall not be issued or, as the case may be, shall be issued only in such`
  line `modified form as may be agreed upon by both the Houses.`
  line
  line `(4) In reckoning any such period of thirty days as is referred to in sub-section (3), no account shall be`
  line `taken of any period during which the House referred to in sub-section (3) is prorogued or adjourned for`
  line `more than four consecutive days.`
  line
  line `(5) The copies of every notification issued under this section shall, as soon as may be after it has been`
  line `issued, be laid before each House of Parliament.]`
obj_root_law_sections_407:
  sectionId (49302)
  sectionNo (407)
  orderNo 459
  title Definitions
  content obj_root_law_sections_407_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_407_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=49302&sectionno=407&orderno=459&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_407_content:
  string
  line `In this Chapter, unless the context otherwise requires,--`
  line
  line `(a) "Chairperson" means the Chairperson of the Appellate Tribunal;`
  line
  line `(b) "Judicial Member" means a member of the Tribunal or the Appellate Tribunal appointed as`
  line `such and includes the President or the Chairperson, as the case may be;`
  line
  line `(c) "Member" means a member, whether Judicial or Technical of the Tribunal or the Appellate`
  line `Tribunal and includes the President or the Chairperson, as the case may be;`
  line
  line `(d) "President" means the President of the Tribunal;`
  line
  line `(e) "Technical Member" means a member of the Tribunal or the Appellate Tribunal appointed as such.`
obj_root_law_sections_407_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_408:
  sectionId (49303)
  sectionNo (408)
  orderNo 460
  title `Constitution of National Company Law Tribunal.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_408_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_408_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=49303&sectionno=408&orderno=460&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_408_content:
  string
  line `The Central Government shall, by`
  line `notification, constitute, with effect from such date as may be specified therein, a Tribunal to be known as`
  line `the National Company Law Tribunal consisting of a President and such number of Judicial and Technical`
  line `members, as the Central Government may deem necessary, to be appointed by it by notification, to`
  line `exercise and discharge such powers and functions as are, or may be, conferred on it by or under this Act`
  line `or any other law for the time being in force.`
obj_root_law_sections_408_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_409:
  sectionId (49304)
  sectionNo (409)
  orderNo 461
  title `Qualification of President and Members of Tribunal`
  content obj_root_law_sections_409_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_409_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=49304&sectionno=409&orderno=461&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_409_content:
  string
  line `(1) The President shall be a person`
  line `who is or has been a Judge of a High Court for five years.`
  line
  line `(2) A person shall not be qualified for appointment as a Judicial Member unless he--`
  line
  line `(a) is, or has been, a judge of a High Court; or`
  line
  line `(b) is, or has been, a District Judge for at least five years; or`
  line
  line `(c) has, for at least ten years been an advocate of a court.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purposes of clause (c), in computing the period during which a person has`
  line `been an advocate of a court, there shall be included any period during which the person has held`
  line `judicial office or the office of a member of a tribunal or any post, under the Union or a State,`
  line `requiring special knowledge of law after he become an advocate.`
  line
  line `(3) A person shall not be qualified for appointment as a Technical Member unless he--`
  line
  line `(a) has, for at least fifteen years been a member of the Indian Corporate Law Service or Indian`
  line `Legal Service ^1[and has been holding the rank of Secretary or Additional Secretary to the Government`
  line `of India]; or`
  line
  line `(b) is, or has been, in practice as a chartered accountant for at least fifteen years; or`
  line
  line `(c) is, or has been, in practice as a cost accountant for at least fifteen years; or`
  line
  line `(d) is, or has been, in practice as a company secretary for at least fifteen years; or`
  line
  line `^2[(e) is a person of proven ability, integrity and standing having special knowledge and professional experience`
  line `of not less than fifteen years in industrial finance, industrial management, industrial reconstruction, investment`
  line `and accountancy.]`
  line
  line `(f) is, or has been, for at least five years, a presiding officer of a Labour Court, Tribunal or`
  line `National Tribunal constituted under the Industrial Disputes Act, 1947 (14 of 1947).`
obj_root_law_sections_409_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 1 of 2018, s. 82, for "out of which at least three years shall be in the pay scale of Joint Secretary to the`
  line `Government of India or equivalent or above in that service" (w.e.f 9-2-2018).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by s. 82, ibid., for clause (e) (w.e.f. 9-2-2018).`
obj_root_law_sections_410:
  sectionId (49305)
  sectionNo (410)
  orderNo 462
  title `Constitution of Appellate Tribunal.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_410_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_410_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=49305&sectionno=410&orderno=462&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_410_content:
  string
  line `The Central Government shall, by notification, constitute, with effect from such date as may be specified therein, an Appellate Tribunal to be known as the National Company Law Appellate Tribunal consisting of a chairperson and such number of Judicial and Technical Members, ^1***, as the Central Government may deem fit, to be appointed by it by notification, ^2[for hearing appeals against--`
  line
  line `(a) the ^3[orders of the Tribunal or of the National Financial Reporting Authority] under this Act; and`
  line
  line `(b) any direction, decision or order referred to in 4section 53A of the Competition Act, 2002 (12 of 2002) in accordance with the provisions of that Act].`
obj_root_law_sections_410_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. The words "not exceeding eleven" omitted by Act 29 of 2020, s. 58 (w.e.f. 22-1-2021).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 7 of 2017, s. 172, for "for hearing appeals against the orders to the Tribunal" (w.e.f. 26-5-2017).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 1 of 2018, s. 83 for "orders of the Tribunal" (w.e.f. 7-5-2018).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by Act 29 of 2020, s. 58, for "section 53N" (w.e.f. 22-1-2021).`
obj_root_law_sections_411:
  sectionId (49306)
  sectionNo (411)
  orderNo 463
  title `Qualifications of Chairperson and members of Appellate Tribunal.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_411_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by s. 84, ibid., for sub-section (3) (w.e.f. 9-2-2018).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=49306&sectionno=411&orderno=463&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_411_content:
  string
  line `(1) The chairperson`
  line `shall be a person who is or has been a Judge of the Supreme Court or the Chief Justice of a High Court.`
  line
  line `(2) A Judicial Member shall be a person who is or has been a Judge of a High Court or is a Judicial`
  line `Member of the Tribunal for five years.`
  line
  line `^1[(3) A technical member shall be a person of proven ability, integrity and standing having special`
  line `knowledge and professional experience of not less than twenty-five years in industrial finance, industrial`
  line `management, industrial reconstruction, investment and accountancy.]`
obj_root_law_sections_412:
  sectionId (49307)
  sectionNo (412)
  orderNo 464
  title `Selection of Members of Tribunal and Appellate Tribunal.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_412_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by s. 85, ibid., for sub-section (2) (w.e.f. 9-2-2018).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=49307&sectionno=412&orderno=464&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_412_content:
  string
  line `(1) The President of the`
  line `Tribunal and the chairperson and Judicial Members of the Appellate Tribunal, shall be appointed after`
  line `consultation with the Chief Justice of India.`
  line
  line `^1[(2) The Members of the Tribunal and the Technical Members of the Appellate Tribunal shall be`
  line `appointed on the recommendation of a Selection Committee consisting of--`
  line
  line `(a) Chief Justice of India or his nominee--Chairperson;`
  line
  line `(b) a senior Judge of the Supreme Court or Chief Justice of High Court--Member;`
  line
  line `(c) Secretary in the Ministry of Corporate Affairs--Member; and`
  line
  line `(d) Secretary in the Ministry of Law and Justice--Member.`
  line
  line `(2A) Where in a meeting of the Selection Committee, there is equality of votes on any matter, the`
  line `Chairperson shall have a casting vote.]`
  line
  line `(3) The Secretary, Ministry of Corporate Affairs shall be the Convener of the Selection Committee.`
  line
  line `(4) The Selection Committee shall determine its procedure for recommending persons under`
  line `sub-section (2).`
  line
  line `(5) No appointment of the Members of the Tribunal or the Appellate Tribunal shall be invalid merely`
  line `by reason of any vacancy or any defect in the constitution of the Selection Committee.`
obj_root_law_sections_413:
  sectionId (49308)
  sectionNo (413)
  orderNo 465
  title `Term of office of President, Chairperson and other Members`
  content obj_root_law_sections_413_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_413_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=49308&sectionno=413&orderno=465&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_413_content:
  string
  line `(1) The President and every`
  line `other Member of the Tribunal shall hold office as such for a term of five years from the date on which he`
  line `enters upon his office, but shall be eligible for re-appointment for another term of five years.`
  line
  line `(2) A Member of the Tribunal shall hold office as such until he attains,--`
  line
  line `(a) in the case of the President, the age of sixty-seven years;`
  line
  line `(b) in the case of any other Member, the age of sixty-five years:`
  line
  line `Provided that a person who has not completed fifty years of age shall not be eligible for appointment`
  line `as Member:`
  line
  line `Provided further that the Member may retain his lien with his parent cadre or Ministry or Department,`
  line `as the case may be, while holding office as such for a period not exceeding one year.`
  line
  line `(3) The chairperson or a Member of the Appellate Tribunal shall hold office as such for a term of five`
  line `years from the date on which he enters upon his office, but shall be eligible for re-appointment for another`
  line `term of five years.`
  line
  line `(4) A Member of the Appellate Tribunal shall hold office as such until he attains,--`
  line
  line `(a) in the case of the Chairperson, the age of seventy years;`
  line
  line `(b) in the case of any other Member, the age of sixty-seven years:`
  line
  line `Provided that a person who has not completed fifty years of age shall not be eligible for appointment`
  line `as Member:`
  line
  line `Provided further that the Member may retain his lien with his parent cadre or Ministry or Department,`
  line `as the case may be, while holding office as such for a period not exceeding one year.`
obj_root_law_sections_413_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_414:
  sectionId (49309)
  sectionNo (414)
  orderNo 466
  title `Salary, allowances and other terms and conditions of service of Members.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_414_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_414_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=49309&sectionno=414&orderno=466&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_414_content:
  string
  line `The salary,`
  line `allowances and other terms and conditions of service of the Members of the Tribunal and the Appellate`
  line `Tribunal shall be such as may be prescribed:`
  line
  line `Provided that neither the salary and allowances nor the other terms and conditions of service of the`
  line `Members shall be varied to their disadvantage after their appointment.`
obj_root_law_sections_414_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_415:
  sectionId (49310)
  sectionNo (415)
  orderNo 467
  title `Acting President and Chairperson of Tribunal or Appellate Tribunal.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_415_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_415_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=49310&sectionno=415&orderno=467&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_415_content:
  string
  line `(1) In the event of`
  line `the occurrence of any vacancy in the office of the President or the Chairperson by reason of his death,`
  line `resignation or otherwise, the senior-most Member shall act as the President or the Chairperson, as the case`
  line `may be, until the date on which a new President or Chairperson appointed in accordance with the`
  line `provisions of this Act to fill such vacancy enters upon his office.`
  line
  line `(2) When the President or the Chairperson is unable to discharge his functions owing to absence,`
  line `illness or any other cause, the senior-most Member shall discharge the functions of the President or the`
  line `Chairperson, as the case may be, until the date on which the President or the Chairperson resumes his`
  line duties.
obj_root_law_sections_415_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_416:
  sectionId (49311)
  sectionNo (416)
  orderNo 468
  title `Resignation of Members.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_416_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_416_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=49311&sectionno=416&orderno=468&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_416_content:
  string
  line `The President, the Chairperson or any Member may, by notice in`
  line `writing under his hand addressed to the Central Government, resign from his office:`
  line
  line `Provided that the President, the Chairperson, or the Member shall continue to hold office until the`
  line `expiry of three months from the date of receipt of such notice by the Central Government or until a person`
  line `duly appointed as his successor enters upon his office or until the expiry of his term of office, whichever`
  line `is earliest.`
obj_root_law_sections_416_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_417:
  sectionId (49312)
  sectionNo (417)
  orderNo 469
  title `Removal of Members.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_417_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_417_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=49312&sectionno=417&orderno=469&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_417_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may, after consultation with the Chief`
  line `Justice of India, remove from office the President, Chairperson or any Member, who`
  line
  line `(a) has been adjudged an insolvent; or--`
  line
  line `(b) has been convicted of an offence which, in the opinion of the Central Government, involves`
  line `moral turpitude; or`
  line
  line `(c) has become physically or mentally incapable of acting as such President, the Chairperson, or`
  line `Member; or`
  line
  line `(d) has acquired such financial or other interest as is likely to affect prejudicially his functions as`
  line `such President, the Chairperson or Member; or`
  line
  line `(e) has so abused his position as to render his continuance in office prejudicial to the public`
  line `interest:`
  line
  line `Provided that the President, the Chairperson or the Member shall not be removed on any of the`
  line `grounds specified in clauses (b) to (e) without giving him a reasonable opportunity of being heard.`
  line
  line `(2) Without prejudice to the provisions of sub-section (1), the President, the Chairperson or the`
  line `Member shall not be removed from his office except by an order made by the Central Government on the`
  line `ground of proved misbehaviour or incapacity after an inquiry made by a Judge of the Supreme Court`
  line `nominated by the Chief Justice of India on a reference made to him by the Central Government in which`
  line `such President, the Chairperson or Member had been informed of the charges against him and given a`
  line `reasonable opportunity of being heard.`
  line
  line `(3) The Central Government may, with the concurrence of the Chief Justice of India, suspend from`
  line `office, the President, the Chairperson or Member in respect of whom reference has been made to the`
  line `Judge of the Supreme Court under sub-section (2) until the Central Government has passed orders on`
  line `receipt of the report of the Judge of the Supreme Court on such reference.`
  line
  line `(4) The Central Government shall, after consultation with the Supreme Court, make rules to regulate`
  line `the procedure for the inquiry on the ground of proved misbehaviour or incapacity referred to in subsection`
  line `(2).`
obj_root_law_sections_417_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_417_a:
  sectionId (48977)
  sectionNo 417A
  orderNo 470
  title `Qualifications, terms and conditions of service of Chairperson and Member.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_417_a_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_417_a_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=48977&sectionno=417A&orderno=470&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_417_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[417A. Qualifications, terms and conditions of service of Chairperson and Member.-- Notwithstanding`
  line `anything contained in this Act, the qualifications, appointment, term of office, salaries and allowances,`
  line `resignation, removal and other terms and conditions of service of the Chairperson and other Members of`
  line `the Appellate Tribunal appointed after the commencement of ^2[the Tribunals Reforms Act, 2021, shall be governed by the provisions of Chapter II of the said Act]:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Chairperson and Member appointed before the commencement of Part XIV of`
  line `Chapter VI of the Finance Act, 2017, shall continue to be governed by the provisions of this Act and the`
  line `rules made thereunder as if the provisions of section 184 of the Finance Act, 2017 had not come into`
  line force.]
obj_root_law_sections_417_a_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 7 of 2017, s. 172 (w.e.f. 26-5-5017).`
  line
  line `2.Subs. by Act 33 of 2021, s. 28, for “Part XIV of Chapter VI of the Finance Act, 2017 (7 of 2017), shall be governed by the provisions of the section 184 of that Act” (w.e.f. 4-4-2021).`
obj_root_law_sections_418:
  sectionId (49313)
  sectionNo (418)
  orderNo 471
  title `Staff of Tribunal and Appellate Tribunal`
  content obj_root_law_sections_418_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_418_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=49313&sectionno=418&orderno=471&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_418_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government shall, in`
  line `consultation with the Tribunal and the Appellate Tribunal, provide the Tribunal and the Appellate`
  line `Tribunal, as the case may be, with such officers and other employees as may be necessary for the exercise`
  line `of the powers and discharge of the functions of the Tribunal and the Appellate Tribunal.`
  line
  line `(2) The officers and other employees of the Tribunal and the Appellate Tribunal shall discharge their`
  line `functions under the general superintendence and control of the President, or as the case may be, the`
  line `Chairperson, or any other Member to whom powers for exercising such superintendence and control are`
  line `delegated by him.`
  line
  line `(3) The salaries and allowances and other conditions of service of the officers and other employees of`
  line `the Tribunal and the Appellate Tribunal shall be such as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_418_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_418_a:
  sectionId (51986)
  sectionNo 418A
  orderNo 472
  title `Benches of Appellate Tribunal.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_418_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 29 of 2020, s. 59 (w.e.f. 22-1-2021).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=51986&sectionno=418A&orderno=472&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_418_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[418A. Benches of Appellate Tribunal.--(1) The powers of the Appellate Tribunal may be exercised by the Benches thereof to be constituted by the Chairperson:`
  line
  line `Provided that a Bench of the Appellate Tribunal shall have at least one Judicial Member and one Technical Member.`
  line
  line `(2) The Benches of the Appellate Tribunal shall ordinarily sit at New Delhi or such other places as the Central Government may, in consultation with the Chairperson, notify:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Central Government may, by notification, after consultation with the Chairperson, establish such number of Benches of the Appellate Tribunal, as it may consider necessary, to hear appeals against any direction, decision or order referred to in section 53A of the Competition Act, 2002 (12 of 2003) and under section 61 of the Insolvency and Bankruptcy Code, 2016 (31 of 2016).]`
obj_root_law_sections_419:
  sectionId (49314)
  sectionNo (419)
  orderNo 473
  title `Benches of Tribunal.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_419_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 31 of 2016, s. 255 and the Eleventh Schedule, for sub-section (4) (w.e.f. 15-11-2016).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=49314&sectionno=419&orderno=473&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_419_content:
  string
  line `(1) There shall be constituted such number of Benches of the Tribunal,`
  line `as may, by notification, be specified by the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(2) The Principal Bench of the Tribunal shall be at New Delhi which shall be presided over by the`
  line `President of the Tribunal.`
  line
  line `(3) The powers of the Tribunal shall be exercisable by Benches consisting of two Members out of`
  line `whom one shall be a Judicial Member and the other shall be a Technical Member:`
  line
  line `Provided that it shall be competent for the Members of the Tribunal authorised in this behalf to`
  line `function as a Bench consisting of a single Judicial Member and exercise the powers of the Tribunal in`
  line `respect of such class of cases or such matters pertaining to such class of cases, as the President may, by`
  line `general or special order, specify:`
  line
  line `Provided further that if at any stage of the hearing of any such case or matter, it appears to the`
  line `Member that the case or matter is of such a nature that it ought to be heard by a Bench consisting of two`
  line `Members, the case or matter may be transferred by the President, or, as the case may be, referred to him`
  line `for transfer, to such Bench as the President may deem fit.`
  line
  line `^1[(4) The Central Government shall, by notification, establish such number of benches of the`
  line `Tribunal, as it may consider necessary, to exercise the jurisdiction, powers and authority of the`
  line `Adjudicating Authority conferred on such Tribunal by or under Part II of the Insolvency and Bankruptcy`
  line `Code, 2016 (31 of 2016).]`
  line
  line `(5) If the Members of a Bench differ in opinion on any point or points, it shall be decided according`
  line `to the majority, if there is a majority, but if the Members are equally divided, they shall state the point or`
  line `points on which they differ, and the case shall be referred by the President for hearing on such point or`
  line `points by one or more of the other Members of the Tribunal and such point or points shall be decided`
  line `according to the opinion of the majority of Members who have heard the case, including those who first`
  line `heard it.`
obj_root_law_sections_420:
  sectionId (49315)
  sectionNo (420)
  orderNo 474
  title `Orders of Tribunal.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_420_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_420_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=49315&sectionno=420&orderno=474&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_420_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Tribunal may, after giving the parties to any proceeding before`
  line `it, a reasonable opportunity of being heard, pass such orders thereon as it thinks fit.`
  line
  line `(2) The Tribunal may, at any time within two years from the date of the order, with a view to`
  line `rectifying any mistake apparent from the record, amend any order passed by it, and shall make such`
  line `amendment, if the mistake is brought to its notice by the parties:`
  line
  line `Provided that no such amendment shall be made in respect of any order against which an appeal has`
  line `been preferred under this Act.`
  line
  line `(3) The Tribunal shall send a copy of every order passed under this section to all the parties`
  line concerned.
obj_root_law_sections_420_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_421:
  sectionId (49316)
  sectionNo (421)
  orderNo 475
  title `Appeal from orders of Tribunal`
  content obj_root_law_sections_421_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_421_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=49316&sectionno=421&orderno=475&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_421_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any person aggrieved by an order of the Tribunal may`
  line `prefer an appeal to the Appellate Tribunal.`
  line
  line `(2) No appeal shall lie to the Appellate Tribunal from an order made by the Tribunal with the consent`
  line `of parties.`
  line
  line `(3) Every appeal under sub-section (1) shall be filed within a period of forty-five days from the date`
  line `on which a copy of the order of the Tribunal is made available to the person aggrieved and shall be in`
  line `such form, and accompanied by such fees, as may be prescribed:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Appellate Tribunal may entertain an appeal after the expiry of the said period of`
  line `forty-five days from the date aforesaid, but within a further period not exceeding forty-five days, if it is`
  line `satisfied that the appellant was prevented by sufficient cause from filing the appeal within that period.`
  line
  line `(4) On the receipt of an appeal under sub-section (1), the Appellate Tribunal shall, after giving the`
  line `parties to the appeal a reasonable opportunity of being heard, pass such orders thereon as it thinks fit,`
  line `confirming, modifying or setting aside the order appealed against.`
  line
  line `(5) The Appellate Tribunal shall send a copy of every order made by it to the Tribunal and the parties`
  line `to appeal.`
obj_root_law_sections_421_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_422:
  sectionId (49317)
  sectionNo (422)
  orderNo 476
  title `Expeditious disposal by Tribunal and Appellate Tribunal`
  content obj_root_law_sections_422_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_422_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=49317&sectionno=422&orderno=476&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_422_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every application or petition`
  line `presented before the Tribunal and every appeal filed before the Appellate Tribunal shall be dealt with and`
  line `disposed of by it as expeditiously as possible and every endeavour shall be made by the Tribunal or the`
  line `Appellate Tribunal, as the case may be, for the disposal of such application or petition or appeal within`
  line `three months from the date of its presentation before the Tribunal or the filing of the appeal before the`
  line `Appellate Tribunal.`
  line
  line `(2) Where any application or petition or appeal is not disposed of within the period specified in subsection`
  line `(1), the Tribunal or, as the case may be, the Appellate Tribunal, shall record the reasons for not`
  line `disposing of the application or petition or the appeal, as the case may be, within the period so specified;`
  line `and the President or the Chairperson, as the case may be, may, after taking into account the reasons so`
  line `recorded, extend the period referred to in sub-section (1) by such period not exceeding ninety days as he`
  line `may consider necessary.`
obj_root_law_sections_422_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_423:
  sectionId (49318)
  sectionNo (423)
  orderNo 477
  title `Appeal to Supreme Court.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_423_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_423_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=49318&sectionno=423&orderno=477&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_423_content:
  string
  line `Any person aggrieved by any order of the Appellate Tribunal`
  line `may file an appeal to the Supreme Court within sixty days from the date of receipt of the order of the`
  line `Appellate Tribunal to him on any question of law arising out of such order:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Supreme Court may, if it is satisfied that the appellant was prevented by sufficient`
  line `cause from filing the appeal within the said period, allow it to be filed within a further period not`
  line `exceeding sixty days.`
obj_root_law_sections_423_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_424:
  sectionId (49319)
  sectionNo (424)
  orderNo 478
  title `Procedure before Tribunal and Appellate Tribunal.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_424_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 31 of 2016, s. 255 and the Eleventh Schedule (w.e.f. 15-11-2016).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=49319&sectionno=424&orderno=478&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_424_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Tribunal and the Appellate`
  line `Tribunal shall not, while disposing of any proceeding before it or, as the case may be, an appeal before it,`
  line `be bound by the procedure laid down in the Code of Civil Procedure, 1908 (5 of 1908), but shall be`
  line `guided by the principles of natural justice, and, subject to the other provisions of this Act ^1[or of the`
  line `Insolvency and Bankruptcy Code, 2016 (31 of 2016)] and of any rules made hereunder, the Tribunal and`
  line `the Appellate Tribunal shall have power to regulate their own procedure.`
  line
  line `(2) The Tribunal and the Appellate Tribunal shall have, for the purposes of discharging their`
  line `functions under this Act ^1[or under the Insolvency and Bankruptcy Code, 2016 (31 of 2016)], the same`
  line `powers as are vested in a civil court under the Code of Civil Procedure, 1908 (5 of 1908) while trying a`
  line `suit in respect of the following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) summoning and enforcing the attendance of any person and examining him on oath;`
  line
  line `(b) requiring the discovery and production of documents;`
  line
  line `(c) receiving evidence on affidavits;`
  line
  line `(d) subject to the provisions of sections 123 and 124 of the Indian Evidence Act,1872 (1 of 1872),`
  line `requisitioning any public record or document or a copy of such record or document from any office;`
  line
  line `(e) issuing commissions for the examination of witnesses or documents;`
  line
  line `(f) dismissing a representation for default or deciding it ex parte;`
  line
  line `(g) setting aside any order of dismissal of any representation for default or any order passed by it`
  line `ex parte; and`
  line
  line `(h) any other matter which may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(3) Any order made by the Tribunal or the Appellate Tribunal may be enforced by that Tribunal in the`
  line `same manner as if it were a decree made by a court in a suit pending therein, and it shall be lawful for the`
  line `Tribunal or the Appellate Tribunal to send for execution of its orders to the court within the local limits of`
  line `whose jurisdiction,--`
  line
  line `(a) in the case of an order against a company, the registered office of the company is situate; or`
  line
  line `(b) in the case of an order against any other person, the person concerned voluntarily resides or`
  line `carries on business or personally works for gain.`
  line
  line `(4) All proceedings before the Tribunal or the Appellate Tribunal shall be deemed to be judicial`
  line `proceedings within the meaning of sections 193 and 228, and for the purposes of section 196 of the Indian`
  line `Penal Code (45 of 1860), and the Tribunal and the Appellate Tribunal shall be deemed to be civil court`
  line `for the purposes of section 195 and Chapter XXVI of the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974)`
obj_root_law_sections_425:
  sectionId (49320)
  sectionNo (425)
  orderNo 479
  title `Power to punish for contempt.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_425_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_425_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=49320&sectionno=425&orderno=479&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_425_content:
  string
  line `The Tribunal and the Appellate Tribunal shall have the same`
  line `jurisdiction, powers and authority in respect of contempt of themselves as the High Court has and may`
  line `exercise, for this purpose, the powers under the provisions of the Contempt of Courts Act, 1971 (70 of`
  line `1971), which shall have the effect subject to modifications that--`
  line
  line `(a) the reference therein to a High Court shall be construed as including a reference to the`
  line `Tribunal and the Appellate Tribunal; and`
  line
  line `(b) the reference to Advocate-General in section 15 of the said Act shall be construed as a`
  line `reference to such Law Officers as the Central Government may, specify in this behalf.`
obj_root_law_sections_425_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_426:
  sectionId (49321)
  sectionNo (426)
  orderNo 480
  title `Delegation of powers`
  content obj_root_law_sections_426_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_426_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=49321&sectionno=426&orderno=480&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_426_content:
  string
  line `The Tribunal or the Appellate Tribunal may, by general or special`
  line `order, direct, subject to such conditions, if any, as may be specified in the order, any of its officers or`
  line `employees or any other person authorised by it to inquire into any matter connected with any proceeding`
  line `or, as the case may be, appeal before it and to report to it in such manner as may be specified in the order.`
obj_root_law_sections_426_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_427:
  sectionId (49322)
  sectionNo (427)
  orderNo 481
  title `President, Members, officers, etc., to be public servants`
  content obj_root_law_sections_427_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_427_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=49322&sectionno=427&orderno=481&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_427_content:
  string
  line `The President, Members, officers`
  line `and other employees of the Tribunal and the Chairperson, Members, officers and other employees of the`
  line `Appellate Tribunal shall be deemed to be public servants within the meaning of section 21 of the Indian`
  line `Penal Code (45 of 1860).`
obj_root_law_sections_427_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_428:
  sectionId (49323)
  sectionNo (428)
  orderNo 482
  title `Protection of action taken in good faith.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_428_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_428_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=49323&sectionno=428&orderno=482&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_428_content:
  string
  line `No suit, prosecution or other legal proceeding shall`
  line `lie against the Tribunal, the President, Member, officer or other employee, or against the Appellate`
  line `Tribunal, the Chairperson, Member, officer or other employees thereof or liquidator or any other person`
  line `authorised by the Tribunal or the Appellate Tribunal for the discharge of any function under this Act in`
  line `respect of any loss or damage caused or likely to be caused by any act which is in good faith done or`
  line `intended to be done in pursuance of this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_428_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_429:
  sectionId (49324)
  sectionNo (429)
  orderNo 483
  title `Power to seek assistance of Chief Metropolitan Magistrate, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_429_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 31 of 2016, s. 255 and the Eleventh Schedule, for section 429 (w.e.f. 15-11-2016).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=49324&sectionno=429&orderno=483&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_429_content:
  string
  line `^1[(1) The Tribunal may, in`
  line `any proceedings for winding up of a company under this Act or in any proceedings under the Insolvency`
  line `and Bankruptcy Code, 2016 (31 of 2016), in order to take into custody or under its control all property,`
  line `books of account or other documents, request, in writing, the Chief Metropolitan Magistrate, Chief`
  line `Judicial Magistrate or the District Collector within whose jurisdiction any such property, books of`
  line `account or other documents of such company under this Act or of corporate persons under the said Code,`
  line `are situated or found, to take possession thereof, and the Chief Metropolitan Magistrate, Chief Judicial`
  line `Magistrate or the District Collector, as the case may be, shall, on such request being made to him,--`
  line
  line `(a) take possession of such property, books of account or other documents; and`
  line
  line `(b) cause the same to be entrusted to the Tribunal or other persons authorised by it.]`
  line
  line `(2) For the purpose of securing compliance with the provisions of sub-section (1), the Chief`
  line `Metropolitan Magistrate, Chief Judicial Magistrate or the District Collector may take or cause to be taken`
  line `such steps and use or cause to be used such force as may, in his opinion, be necessary.`
  line
  line `(3) No act of the Chief Metropolitan Magistrate, Chief Judicial Magistrate or the District Collector`
  line `done in pursuance of this section shall be called in question in any court or before any authority on any`
  line `ground whatsoever.`
obj_root_law_sections_430:
  sectionId (49325)
  sectionNo (430)
  orderNo 484
  title `Civil court not to have jurisdiction.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_430_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_430_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=49325&sectionno=430&orderno=484&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_430_content:
  string
  line `No civil court shall have jurisdiction to entertain any`
  line `suit or proceeding in respect of any matter which the Tribunal or the Appellate Tribunal is empowered to`
  line `determine by or under this Act or any other law for the time being in force and no injunction shall be`
  line `granted by any court or other authority in respect of any action taken or to be taken in pursuance of any`
  line `power conferred by or under this Act or any other law for the time being in force, by the Tribunal or the`
  line `Appellate Tribunal.`
obj_root_law_sections_430_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_431:
  sectionId (49326)
  sectionNo (431)
  orderNo 485
  title `Vacancy in Tribunal or Appellate Tribunal not to invalidate acts or proceedings.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_431_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_431_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=49326&sectionno=431&orderno=485&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_431_content:
  string
  line `No act`
  line `or proceeding of the Tribunal or the Appellate Tribunal shall be questioned or shall be invalid merely on`
  line `the ground of the existence of any vacancy or defect in the constitution of the Tribunal or the Appellate`
  line `Tribunal, as the case may be.`
obj_root_law_sections_431_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_432:
  sectionId (49327)
  sectionNo (432)
  orderNo 486
  title `Right to legal representation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_432_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_432_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=49327&sectionno=432&orderno=486&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_432_content:
  string
  line `A party to any proceeding or appeal before the Tribunal or the`
  line `Appellate Tribunal, as the case may be, may either appear in person or authorise one or more chartered`
  line `accountants or company secretaries or cost accountants or legal practitioners or any other person to`
  line `present his case before the Tribunal or the Appellate Tribunal, as the case may be`
obj_root_law_sections_432_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_433:
  sectionId (49328)
  sectionNo (433)
  orderNo 487
  title Limitation.
  content obj_root_law_sections_433_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_433_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=49328&sectionno=433&orderno=487&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_433_content:
  string
  line `The provisions of the Limitation Act, 1963 (36 of 1963) shall, as far as may be,`
  line `apply to proceedings or appeals before the Tribunal or the Appellate Tribunal, as the case may be.`
obj_root_law_sections_433_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_434:
  sectionId (49329)
  sectionNo (434)
  orderNo 488
  title `Transfer of certain pending proceedings`
  content obj_root_law_sections_434_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_434_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=49329&sectionno=434&orderno=488&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_434_content:
  string
  line `^1[434. Transfer of certain pending proceedings.--(1) On such date as may be notified by the`
  line `Central Government in this behalf,--`
  line
  line `(a) all matters, proceedings or cases pending before the Board of Company Law Administration`
  line `(herein in this section referred to as the Company Law Board) constituted under sub-section (1) of`
  line `section 10E of the Companies Act, 1956 (1 of 1956), immediately before such date shall stand`
  line `transferred to the Tribunal and the Tribunal shall dispose of such matters, proceedings or cases in`
  line `accordance with the provisions of this Act;`
  line
  line `(b) any person aggrieved by any decision or order of the Company Law Board made before such`
  line `date may file an appeal to the High Court within sixty days from the date of communication of the`
  line `decision or order of the Company Law Board to him on any question of law arising out of such order:`
  line
  line `Provided that the High Court may if it is satisfied that the appellant was prevented by sufficient`
  line `cause from filing an appeal within the said period, allow it to be filed within a further period not`
  line `exceeding sixty days; and`
  line
  line `(c) all proceedings under the Companies Act, 1956 (1 of 1956), including proceedings relating to`
  line `arbitration, compromise, arrangements and reconstruction and winding up of companies, pending`
  line `immediately before such date before any District Court or High Court, shall stand transferred to the`
  line `Tribunal and the Tribunal may proceed to deal with such proceedings from the stage before their`
  line `transfer:`
  line
  line `Provided that only such proceedings relating to the winding up of companies shall be transferred`
  line `to the Tribunal that are at a stage as may be prescribed by the Central Government.`
  line
  line `^2[Provided further that only such proceedings relating to cases other than winding-up, for which`
  line `orders for allowing or otherwise of the proceedings are not reserved by the High Courts shall be`
  line `transferred to the Tribunal`
  line
  line `^3]Provided also that]--`
  line
  line `(i) all proceedings under the Companies Act, 1956 other than the cases relating to winding`
  line `up of companies that are reserved for orders for allowing or otherwise such proceedings; or`
  line
  line `(ii) the proceedings relating to winding up of companies which have not been transferred`
  line `from the High Courts;`
  line
  line `shall be dealt with in accordance with provisions of the Companies Act, 1956 and the Companies`
  line `(Court) Rules, 1959.]`
  line
  line `^4[Provided also that proceedings relating to cases of voluntary winding up of a company where`
  line `notice of the resolution by advertisement has been given under sub-section (1) of section 485 of the`
  line `Companies Act, 1956 but the company has not been dissolved before the 1st April, 2017 shall`
  line `continue to be dealt with in accordance with provisions of the Companies Act, 1956 and the`
  line `Companies (Court) Rules, 1959.]`
  line
  line `(2) The Central Government may make rules consistent with the provisions of this Act to ensure`
  line `timely transfer of all matters, proceedings or cases pending before the Company Law Board or the courts,`
  line `to the Tribunal under this section.]`
obj_root_law_sections_434_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 31 of 2016, s. 255 and the Eleventh Schedule, for section 434 (w.e.f. 15-11-2016).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by Notification No. S.O. 3676(E), dated 7th December 2016 (w.e.f. 15-12-2016).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Notification No. S.O. 2042(E), dated 29th June 2017 for "Provided further that" (w.e.f. 29-6-2017).`
  line
  line `4. Ins., ibid. (w.e.f. 29-6-2017).`
obj_root_law_sections_435:
  sectionId (49330)
  sectionNo (435)
  orderNo 489
  title `Establishment of Special Courts`
  content obj_root_law_sections_435_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_435_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=49330&sectionno=435&orderno=489&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_435_content:
  string
  line `^1[435. Establishment of Special Courts.--(1) The Central Government may, for the purpose of providing speedy trial of ^2[offences under this Act, except under section 452], establish or designate as many Special Courts as may be necessary.`
  line
  line `(2) A Special Court shall consist of--`
  line
  line `(a) a single judge holding office as Session Judge or Additional Session Judge, in case of offences`
  line `punishable under this Act with imprisonment of two years or more; and`
  line
  line `(b) a Metropolitan Magistrate or a Judicial Magistrate of the First Class, in the case of other`
  line `offences, who shall be appointed by the Central Government with the concurrence of the Chief Justice of the High`
  line `Court within whose jurisdiction the judge to be appointed is working.]`
obj_root_law_sections_435_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 1 of 2018, s. 86, for section 435 (w.e.f. 7-5-2018).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 29 of 2020, s. 60, for "offences under this Act, by notification" (w.e.f. 22-1-2021).`
obj_root_law_sections_436:
  sectionId (49331)
  sectionNo (436)
  orderNo 490
  title `Offences triable by Special Courts.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_436_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 21 of 2015, s. 22, for "all offences under this Act" (w.e.f. 29-5-2015).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=49331&sectionno=436&orderno=490&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_436_content:
  string
  line `(1) Notwithstanding anything contained in the Code of`
  line `Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974),--`
  line
  line `(a) ^1[all offences specified under sub-section (1) of section 435] shall be triable only by the`
  line `Special Court established for the area in which the registered office of the company in relation to`
  line `which the offence is committed or where there are more Special Courts than one for such area, by`
  line `such one of them as may be specified in this behalf by the High Court concerned;`
  line
  line `(b) where a person accused of, or suspected of the commission of, an offence under this Act is`
  line `forwarded to a Magistrate under sub-section (2) or sub-section (2A) of section 167 of the Code of`
  line `Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974), such Magistrate may authorise the detention of such person in`
  line `such custody as he thinks fit for a period not exceeding fifteen days in the whole where such`
  line `Magistrate is a Judicial Magistrate and seven days in the whole where such Magistrate is an`
  line `Executive Magistrate:`
  line
  line `Provided that where such Magistrate considers that the detention of such person upon or before`
  line `the expiry of the period of detention is unnecessary, he shall order such person to be forwarded to the`
  line `Special Court having jurisdiction;`
  line
  line `(c) the Special Court may exercise, in relation to the person forwarded to it under clause (b), the`
  line `same power which a Magistrate having jurisdiction to try a case may exercise under section 167 of`
  line `the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974) in relation to an accused person who has been`
  line `forwarded to him under that section; and`
  line
  line `(d) a Special Court may, upon perusal of the police report of the facts constituting an offence`
  line `under this Act or upon a complaint in that behalf, take cognizance of that offence without the accused`
  line `being committed to it for trial.`
  line
  line `(2) When trying an offence under this Act, a Special Court may also try an offence other than an`
  line `offence under this Act with which the accused may, under the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of`
  line `1974) be charged at the same trial.`
  line
  line `(3) Notwithstanding anything contained in the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974), the`
  line `Special Court may, if it thinks fit, try in a summary way any offence under this Act which is punishable`
  line `with imprisonment for a term not exceeding three years:`
  line
  line `Provided that in the case of any conviction in a summary trial, no sentence of imprisonment for a term`
  line `exceeding one year shall be passed:`
  line
  line `Provided further that when at the commencement of, or in the course of, a summary trial, it appears to`
  line `the Special Court that the nature of the case is such that the sentence of imprisonment for a term`
  line `exceeding one year may have to be passed or that it is, for any other reason, undesirable to try the case`
  line `summarily, the Special Court shall, after hearing the parties, record an order to that effect and thereafter`
  line `recall any witnesses who may have been examined and proceed to hear or rehear the case in accordance`
  line `with the procedure for the regular trial.`
obj_root_law_sections_437:
  sectionId (49332)
  sectionNo (437)
  orderNo 491
  title `Appeal and revision.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_437_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_437_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=49332&sectionno=437&orderno=491&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_437_content:
  string
  line `The High Court may exercise, so far as may be applicable, all the`
  line `powers conferred by Chapters XXIX and XXX of the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974) on a`
  line `High Court, as if a Special Court within the local limits of the jurisdiction of the High Court were a Court`
  line `of Session trying cases within the local limits of the jurisdiction of the High Court.`
obj_root_law_sections_437_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_438:
  sectionId (49333)
  sectionNo (438)
  orderNo 492
  title `Application of Code to proceedings before Special Court.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_438_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 1 of 2018, s. 87 for "deemed to be a Court of Session" (w.e.f. 7-5-2018).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=49333&sectionno=438&orderno=492&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_438_content:
  string
  line `Save as otherwise provided in`
  line `this Act, the provisions of the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974) shall apply to the`
  line `proceedings before a Special Court and for the purposes of the said provisions, the Special Court shall be`
  line `^1[deemed to be a Court of Session or the court of Metropolitan Magistrate or a Judicial Magistrate of the`
  line `First Class, as the case may be,] and the person conducting a prosecution before a Special Court shall be`
  line `deemed to be a Public Prosecutor.`
obj_root_law_sections_439:
  sectionId (49334)
  sectionNo (439)
  orderNo 493
  title `Offences to be non-cognizable.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_439_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by s. 88, ibid., (w.e.f. 7-5-2018).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=49334&sectionno=439&orderno=493&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_439_content:
  string
  line `(1) Notwithstanding anything in the Code of Criminal`
  line `Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974), every offence under this Act except the offences referred to in`
  line `sub-section (6) of section 212 shall be deemed to be non-cognizable within the meaning of the said Code.`
  line
  line `(2) No court shall take cognizance of any offence under this Act which is alleged to have been`
  line `committed by any company or any officer thereof, except on the complaint in writing of the Registrar, a`
  line `shareholder ^1[or a member] of the company, or of a person authorised by the Central Government in that`
  line `behalf:`
  line
  line `Provided that the court may take cognizance of offences relating to issue and transfer of securities and`
  line `non-payment of dividend, on a complaint in writing, by a person authorised by the Securities and`
  line `Exchange Board of India:`
  line
  line `Provided further that nothing in this sub-section shall apply to a prosecution by a company of any of`
  line `its officers.`
  line
  line `(3) Notwithstanding anything contained in the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974),where`
  line `the complainant under sub-section (2) is the Registrar or a person authorised by the Central Government,`
  line `the presence of such officer before the Court trying the offences shall not be necessary unless the court`
  line `requires his personal attendance at the trial.`
  line
  line `(4) The provisions of sub-section (2) shall not apply to any action taken by the liquidator of a`
  line `company in respect of any offence alleged to have been committed in respect of any of the matters in`
  line `Chapter XX or in any other provision of this Act relating to winding up of companies.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--The liquidator of a company shall not be deemed to be an officer of the company`
  line `within the meaning of sub-section (2).`
obj_root_law_sections_440:
  sectionId (49335)
  sectionNo (440)
  orderNo 494
  title `Transitional provisions.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_440_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by s. 89, ibid., for "Court of Session" (w.e.f. 7-5-2018).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=49335&sectionno=440&orderno=494&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_440_content:
  string
  line `Any offence committed under this Act, which is triable by a Special`
  line `Court shall, until a Special Court is established, be tried by a ^1[Court of Session or the Court of`
  line `Metropolitan Magistrate or a Judicial Magistrate of the First Class, as the case may be] exercising`
  line `jurisdiction over the area, notwithstanding anything contained in the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973`
  line `(2 of 1974):`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing contained in this section shall affect the powers of the High Court under section`
  line `407 of the Code to transfer any case or class of cases taken cognizance by a ^1[Court of Session or the`
  line `Court of Metropolitan Magistrate or a Judicial Magistrate of the First Class, as the case may be] under`
  line `this section.`
obj_root_law_sections_441:
  sectionId (49336)
  sectionNo (441)
  orderNo 495
  title `Compounding of certain offences.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_441_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_441_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=49336&sectionno=441&orderno=495&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_441_content:
  string
  line `(1) Notwithstanding anything contained in the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974), any offence punishable under this Act (whether committed by a company or any officer thereof) ^1[not being an offence punishable with imprisonment only, or punishable with imprisonment and also with fine], may, either before or after the institution of any prosecution, be compounded by--`
  line
  line `(a) the Tribunal; or`
  line
  line `(b) where the maximum amount of fine which may be imposed for such offence ^2[does not exceed twenty-five lakh rupees], by the Regional Director or any officer authorised by the Central Government, on payment or credit, by the company or, as the case may be, the officer, to the Central Government of such sum as that Tribunal or the Regional Director or any officer authorised by the Central Government, as the case may be, may specify:`
  line
  line `Provided that the sum so specified shall not, in any case, exceed the maximum amount of the fine which may be imposed for the offence so compounded:`
  line
  line `Provided further that in specifying the sum required to be paid or credited for the compounding of an offence under this sub-section, the sum, if any, paid by way of additional fee under sub-section (2) of section 403 shall be taken into account:`
  line
  line `Provided also that any offence covered under this sub-section by any company or its officer shall not be compounded if the investigation against such company has been initiated or is pending under this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) Nothing in sub-section (1) shall apply to an offence committed by a company or its officer within a period of three years from the date on which a similar offence committed by it or him was compounded under this section.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purposes of this section,--`
  line
  line `(a) any second or subsequent offence committed after the expiry of a period of three years from the date on which the offence was previously compounded, shall be deemed to be a first offence;`
  line
  line `(b) "Regional Director" means a person appointed by the Central Government as a Regional Director for the purposes of this Act.`
  line
  line `(3) (a) Every application for the compounding of an offence shall be made to the Registrar who shall forward the same, together with his comments thereon, to the Tribunal or the Regional Director or any officer authorised by the Central Government, as the case may be.`
  line
  line `(b) Where any offence is compounded under this section, whether before or after the institution of any prosecution, an intimation thereof shall be given by the company to the Registrar within seven days from the date on which the offence is so compounded.`
  line
  line `(c) Where any offence is compounded before the institution of any prosecution, no prosecution shall be instituted in relation to such offence, either by the Registrar or by any share holder of the company or by any person authorised by the Central Government against the offender in relation to whom the offence is so compounded.`
  line
  line `(d) Where the compounding of any offence is made after the institution of any prosecution, such compounding shall be brought by the Registrar in writing, to the notice of the court in which the prosecution is pending and on such notice of the compounding of the offence being given, the company or its officer in relation to whom the offence is so compounded shall be discharged.`
  line
  line `(4) The Tribunal or the Regional Director or any officer authorised by the Central Government, as the case may be, while dealing with a proposal for the compounding of an offence for a default in compliance with any provision of this Act which requires a company or its officer to file or register with, or deliver or send to, the Registrar any return, account or other document, may direct, by an order, if it or he thinks fit to do so, any officer or other employee of the company to file or register with, or on payment of the fee, and the additional fee, required to be paid under section 403, such return, account or other document within such time as may be specified in the order.`
  line
  line `^3[(5) If any officer or other employee of the company who fails to comply with any order made by the Tribunal or the Regional Director or any officer authorised by the Central Government under sub-section (4), the maximum amount of fine for the offence proposed to be compounded under this section shall be twice the amount provided in the corresponding section in which punishment for such offence is provided.]`
  line
  line `^4[(6) Notwithstanding anything contained in the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974), any offence which is punishable under this Act with imprisonment only or with imprisonment and also with fine shall not be compoundable.]`
  line
  line `(7) No offence specified in this section shall be compounded except under and in accordance with the provisions of this section.`
obj_root_law_sections_441_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by s. 90, ibid., for "with fine only"(w.e.f. 9-2-2018).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 22 of 2019, s. 39, for "does not exceed five lakh rupees" (w.e.f. 2-11-2018).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 29 of 2020, s. 61, for sub-section (5) (w.e.f. 21-12-2020).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by Act 22 of 2019, s. 39, for sub-section (6) (w.e.f. 2-11-2018).`
obj_root_law_sections_442:
  sectionId (49337)
  sectionNo (442)
  orderNo 496
  title `Mediation and Conciliation Panel.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_442_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_442_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=49337&sectionno=442&orderno=496&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_442_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government shall maintain a panel of`
  line `experts to be called as the Mediation and Conciliation Panel consisting of such number of experts having`
  line `such qualifications as may be prescribed for mediation between the parties during the pendency of any`
  line `proceedings before the Central Government or the Tribunal or the Appellate Tribunal under this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) Any of the parties to the proceedings may, at any time during the proceedings before the Central`
  line `Government or the Tribunal or the Appellate Tribunal, apply to the Central Government or the Tribunal`
  line `or the Appellate Tribunal, as the case may be, in such form along with such fees as may be prescribed, for`
  line `referring the matter pertaining to such proceedings to the Mediation and Conciliation Panel and the`
  line `Central Government or the Tribunal or the Appellate Tribunal, as the case may be, shall appoint one or`
  line `more experts from the panel referred to in sub-section (1).`
  line
  line `(3) The Central Government or the Tribunal or the Appellate Tribunal before which any proceeding is`
  line `pending may, suo motu, refer any matter pertaining to such proceeding to such number of experts from`
  line `the Mediation and Conciliation Panel as the Central Government or the Tribunal or the Appellate`
  line `Tribunal, as the case may be, deems fit.`
  line
  line `(4) The fee and other terms and conditions of experts of the Mediation and Conciliation Panel shall be`
  line `such as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(5) The Mediation and Conciliation Panel shall follow such procedure as may be prescribed and`
  line `dispose of the matter referred to it within a period of three months from the date of such reference and`
  line `forward its recommendations to the Central Government or the Tribunal or the Appellate Tribunal, as the`
  line `case may be.`
  line
  line `(6) Any party aggreived by the recommendation of the Mediation and Conciliation Panel may file`
  line `objections to the Central Government or the Tribunal or the Appellate Tribunal, as the case may be.`
obj_root_law_sections_442_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_443:
  sectionId (49338)
  sectionNo (443)
  orderNo 497
  title `Power of Central Government to appoint company prosecutors`
  content obj_root_law_sections_443_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_443_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=49338&sectionno=443&orderno=497&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_443_content:
  string
  line `Notwithstanding anything`
  line `contained in the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974), the Central Government may appoint`
  line `generally, or for any case, or in any case, or for any specified class of cases in any local area, one or more`
  line `persons, as company prosecutors for the conduct of prosecutions arising out of this Act and the persons so`
  line `appointed as company prosecutors shall have all the powers and privileges conferred by the Code on`
  line `Public Prosecutors appointed under section 24 of the Code.`
obj_root_law_sections_443_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_444:
  sectionId (49339)
  sectionNo (444)
  orderNo 498
  title `Appeal against acquittal.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_444_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_444_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=49339&sectionno=444&orderno=498&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_444_content:
  string
  line `Notwithstanding anything contained in the Code of Criminal`
  line `Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974), the Central Government may, in any case arising under this Act, direct any`
  line `company prosecutor or authorise any other person either by name or by virtue of his office, to present an`
  line `appeal from an order of acquittal passed by any court, other than a High Court, and an appeal presented`
  line `by such prosecutor or other person shall be deemed to have been validly presented to the appellate court.`
obj_root_law_sections_444_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_445:
  sectionId (49340)
  sectionNo (445)
  orderNo 499
  title `Compensation for accusation without reasonable cause.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_445_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_445_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=49340&sectionno=445&orderno=499&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_445_content:
  string
  line `The provisions of section 250 of`
  line `the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974) shall apply mutatis mutandis to compensation for`
  line `accusation without reasonable cause before the Special Court or the Court of Session.`
obj_root_law_sections_445_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_446:
  sectionId (49341)
  sectionNo (446)
  orderNo 500
  title `Application of fines.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_446_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_446_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=49341&sectionno=446&orderno=500&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_446_content:
  string
  line `The court imposing any fine under this Act may direct that the whole or`
  line `any part thereof shall be applied in or towards payment of the costs of the proceedings, or in or towards`
  line `the payment of a reward to the person on whose information the proceedings were instituted.`
obj_root_law_sections_446_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_446_a:
  sectionId (48978)
  sectionNo 446A
  orderNo 501
  title `Factors for determining level of punishment.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_446_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 1 of 2018, s. 91 (w.e.f. 9-2-2018)`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=48978&sectionno=446A&orderno=501&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_446_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[446A. Factors for determining level of punishment-- The court or the Special Court, while deciding`
  line `the amount of fine or imprisonment under this Act, shall have due regard to the following factors, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) size of the company;`
  line
  line `(b) nature of business carried on by the company;`
  line
  line `(c) injury to public interest;`
  line
  line `(d) nature of the default; and`
  line
  line `(e) repetition of the default.]`
obj_root_law_sections_446_b:
  sectionId (48979)
  sectionNo 446B
  orderNo 502
  title `Lesser penalties for One Person Companies or small companies.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_446_b_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 29 of 2020, s. 62, for section 446B (w.e.f. 22-1-2021).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=48979&sectionno=446B&orderno=502&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_446_b_content:
  string
  line `^1[446B. Lesser penalties for certain companies.--Notwithstanding anything contained in this Act, if penalty is payable for non-compliance of any of the provisions of this Act by a One Person Company, small company, start-up company or Producer Company, or by any of its officer in default, or any other person in respect of such company, then such company, its officer in default or any other person, as the case may be, shall be liable to a penalty which shall not be more than one-half of the penalty specified in such provisions subject to a maximum of two lakh rupees in case of a company and one lakh rupees in case of an officer who is in default or any other person, as the case may be.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purposes of this section,--`
  line
  line `(a) "Producer Company" means a company as defined in clause (l) of section 378A;`
  line
  line `(b) "start-up company" means a private company incorporated under this Act or under the Companies Act, 1956 (1 of 1956) and recognised as start-up in accordance with the notification issued by the Central Government in the Department for Promotion of Industry and Internal Trade.]`
obj_root_law_sections_447:
  sectionId (49342)
  sectionNo (447)
  orderNo 503
  title `Punishment for fraud`
  content obj_root_law_sections_447_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_447_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=49342&sectionno=447&orderno=503&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_447_content:
  string
  line `Without prejudice to any liability including repayment of any debt`
  line `under this Actor any other law for the time being in force, any person who is found to be guilty of fraud,`
  line `^1[involving an amount of at least ten lakh rupees or one per cent. of the turnover of the company,`
  line `whichever is lower] shall be punishable with imprisonment for a term which shall not be less than six`
  line `months but which may extend to ten years and shall also be liable to fine which shall not be less than the`
  line `amount involved in the fraud, but which may extend to three times the amount involved in the fraud:`
  line
  line `Provided that where the fraud in question involves public interest, the term of imprisonment shall not`
  line `be less than three years.`
  line
  line `^2[Provided further that where the fraud involves an amount less than ten lakh rupees or one per cent.`
  line `of the turnover of the company, whichever is lower, and does not involve public interest, any person`
  line `guilty of such fraud shall be punishable with imprisonment for a term which may extend to five years or`
  line `with fine which may extend to ^3[fifty lakh rupees] or with both.]`
  line
  line `Explanation.-- For the purposes of this section--`
  line
  line `(i) "fraud", in relation to affairs of a company or any body corporate, includes any act, omission,`
  line `concealment of any fact or abuse of position committed by any person or any other person with the`
  line `connivance in any manner, with intent to deceive, to gain undue advantage from, or to injure the`
  line `interests of, the company or its shareholders or its creditors or any other person, whether or not there`
  line `is any wrongful gain or wrongful loss;`
  line
  line `(ii) "wrongful gain" means the gain by unlawful means of property to which the person gaining is`
  line `not legally entitled;`
  line
  line `(iii) "wrongful loss" means the loss by unlawful means of property to which the person losing is`
  line `legally entitled.`
obj_root_law_sections_447_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 1 of 2018, s. 92 (w.e.f. 9-2-2018).`
  line
  line `2. The proviso ins. by s. 92, ibid. (w.e.f. 9-2-2018).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 22 of 2019, s. 41, for "twenty lakh rupees" (w.e.f. 2-11-2018).`
obj_root_law_sections_448:
  sectionId (49343)
  sectionNo (448)
  orderNo 504
  title `Punishment for false statement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_448_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_448_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=49343&sectionno=448&orderno=504&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_448_content:
  string
  line `Save as otherwise provided in this Act, if in any return,`
  line `report, certificate, financial statement, prospectus, statement or other document required by, or for, the`
  line `purposes of any of the provisions of this Act or the rules made thereunder, any person makes a`
  line statement,--
  line
  line `(a) which is false in any material particulars, knowing it to be false; or`
  line
  line `(b) which omits any material fact, knowing it to be material,`
  line
  line `he shall be liable under section 447.`
obj_root_law_sections_448_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_449:
  sectionId (49344)
  sectionNo (449)
  orderNo 505
  title `Punishment for false evidence.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_449_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_449_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=49344&sectionno=449&orderno=505&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_449_content:
  string
  line `Save as otherwise provided in this Act, if any person`
  line `intentionally gives false evidence--`
  line
  line `(a) upon any examination on oath or solemn affirmation, authorised under this Act; or`
  line
  line `(b) in any affidavit, deposition or solemn affirmation, in or about the winding up of any company`
  line `under this Act, or otherwise in or about any matter arising under this Act,`
  line
  line `he shall be punishable with imprisonment for a term which shall not be less than three years but which`
  line `may extend to seven years and with fine which may extend to ten lakh rupees.`
obj_root_law_sections_449_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_450:
  sectionId (49345)
  sectionNo (450)
  orderNo 506
  title `Punishment where no specific penalty or punishment is provided.`
  content `If a company or any officer of a company or any other person contravenes any of the provisions of this Act or the rules made thereunder, or any condition, limitation or restriction subject to which any approval, sanction, consent, confirmation, recognition, direction or exemption in relation to any matter has been accorded, given or granted, and for which no penalty or punishment is provided elsewhere in this Act, the company and every officer of the company who is in default or such other person shall be ^1 [liable to a penalty of ten thousand rupees, and in case of continuing contravention, with a further penalty of on thousand rupees for each day after the first during which the contravention continue, subject to a maximum of two lakh rupees in case of a company and fifty thousand rupees in case of an officer who is in default or any other person].`
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 29 of 2020, s. 63, for certain words (w.e.f. 21-12-2020).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=49345&sectionno=450&orderno=506&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_451:
  sectionId (49346)
  sectionNo (451)
  orderNo 507
  title `Punishment in case of repeated default`
  content obj_root_law_sections_451_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_451_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=49346&sectionno=451&orderno=507&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_451_content:
  string
  line `If a company or an officer of a company commits`
  line `an offence punishable either with fine or with imprisonment and where the same offence is committed for`
  line `the second or subsequent occasions within a period of three years, then, that company and every officer`
  line `thereof who is in default shall be punishable with twice the amount of fine for such offence in addition to`
  line `any imprisonment provided for that offence.`
obj_root_law_sections_451_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_452:
  sectionId (49347)
  sectionNo (452)
  orderNo 508
  title `Punishment for wrongful withholding of property`
  content obj_root_law_sections_452_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_452_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=49347&sectionno=452&orderno=508&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_452_content:
  string
  line `(1) If any officer or employee of a`
  line company--
  line
  line `(a) wrongfully obtains possession of any property, including cash of the company; or`
  line
  line `(b) having any such property including cash in his possession, wrongfully withholds it or`
  line `knowingly applies it for the purposes other than those expressed or directed in the articles and`
  line `authorised by this Act,`
  line
  line `he shall, on the complaint of the company or of any member or creditor or contributory thereof, be`
  line `punishable with fine which shall not be less than one lakh rupees but which may extend to five lakh`
  line rupees.
  line
  line `(2) The Court trying an offence under sub-section (1) may also order such officer or employee to`
  line `deliver up or refund, within a time to be fixed by it, any such property or cash wrongfully obtained or`
  line `wrongfully withheld or knowingly misapplied, the benefits that have been derived from such property or`
  line `cash or in default, to undergo imprisonment for a term which may extend to two years.`
obj_root_law_sections_452_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_453:
  sectionId (49348)
  sectionNo (453)
  orderNo 509
  title `Punishment for improper use of ―Limited‖ or ―Private Limited‖.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_453_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_453_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=49348&sectionno=453&orderno=509&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_453_content:
  string
  line `If any person or persons`
  line `trade or carry on business under any name or title, of which the word "Limited" or the words "Private`
  line `Limited" or any contraction or imitation thereof is or are the last word or words, that person or each of`
  line `those persons shall, unless duly incorporated with limited liability, or unless duly incorporated as a`
  line `private company with limited liability, as the case may be, punishable with fine which shall not be less`
  line `than five hundred rupees but may extend to two thousand rupees for every day for which that name or`
  line `title has been used.`
obj_root_law_sections_453_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_454:
  sectionId (49349)
  sectionNo (454)
  orderNo 510
  title `Adjudication of penalties.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_454_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_454_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=49349&sectionno=454&orderno=510&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_454_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may, by an order published in the`
  line `Official Gazette, appoint as many officers of the Central Government, not below the rank of Registrar, as`
  line `adjudicating officers for adjudging penalty under the provisions of this Act in the manner as may be`
  line prescribed.
  line
  line `(2) The Central Government shall while appointing adjudicating officers, specify their jurisdiction in`
  line `the order under sub-section (1).`
  line
  line `^1[(3) The adjudicating officer may, by an order--`
  line
  line `(a) impose the penalty on the company, the officer who is in default, or any other person, as the`
  line `case may be, stating therein any non-compliance or default under the relevant provisions of this Act;`
  line and
  line
  line `(b) direct such company, or officer who is in default, or any other person, as the case may be, to`
  line `rectify the default, wherever he considers fit.]`
  line
  line `^2[Provided that in case the default relates to non-compliance of sub-section (4) of section 92 or sub-section (1) or sub-section (2) of section 137 and such default has been rectified either prior to, or within thirty days of, the issue of the notice by the adjudicating officer, no penalty shall be imposed in this regard and all proceedings under this section in respect of such default shall be deemed to be concluded.]`
  line
  line `(4) The adjudicating officer shall, before imposing any penalty, give a reasonable opportunity of`
  line `being heard to ^3[such company, the officer who is in default or any other person].`
  line
  line `(5) Any person aggrieved by an order made by the adjudicating officer under sub-section (3) may`
  line `prefer an appeal to the Regional Director having jurisdiction in the matter.`
  line
  line `(6) Every appeal under sub-section (5) shall be filed within sixty days from the date on which the`
  line `copy of the order made by the adjudicating officer is received by the aggrieved person and shall be in`
  line `such form, manner and be accompanied by such fees as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(7) The Regional Director may, after giving the parties to the appeal an opportunity of being heard,`
  line `pass such order as he thinks fit, confirming, modifying or setting aside the order appealed against.`
  line
  line `(8) (i) Where company ^4[fails to comply with the order made under sub-section (3) or sub-section (7),`
  line `as the case may be,] within a period of ninety days from the date of the receipt of the copy of the order,`
  line `the company shall be punishable with fine which shall not be less than twenty-five thousand rupees but`
  line `which may extend to five lakh rupees`
  line
  line `(ii) ^5[Where an officer of a company or any other person] who is in default ^6[fails to comply with the`
  line `order made under sub-section (3) or sub-section (7), as the may be,] within a period of ninety days from`
  line `the date of the receipt of the copy of the order, such officer shall be punishable with imprisonment which`
  line `may extend to six months or with fine which shall not be less than twenty-five thousand rupees but which`
  line `may extend to one lakh rupees, or with both.`
obj_root_law_sections_454_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 22 of 2019, s. 42, for sub-section (3) (w.e.f. 2-11-2018).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by Act 29 of 2020, s. 65 (w.e.f. 22-1-2021).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 22 of 2019, s. 42, for "such company and the officer who is in default" (w.e.f. 2-11-2018).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by s. 42, ibid., for "does not pay the penalty imposed by the adjudicating officer or the Regional Director" (w.e.f. 2-11-`
  line `2018).`
  line
  line `5. The words "Where an officer of a company or any other person" omitted by s. 42, ibid., (w.e.f. 2-11-2018).`
  line
  line `6. The words "does not pay the penalty" omitted by s. 42, ibid. (w.e.f.. 2-11-2018).`
obj_root_law_sections_454_a:
  sectionId (49493)
  sectionNo 454A
  orderNo 511
  title `Penalty for repeated default.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_454_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by s. 43, ibid. (w.e.f. 2-11-2018).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=49493&sectionno=454A&orderno=511&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_454_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[454A.Penalty for repeated default.-- Where a company or an officer of a company or any other`
  line `person having already been subjected to penalty for default under any provisions of this Act, again`
  line `commits such default within a period of three years from the date of order imposing such penalty passed`
  line `by the adjudicating officer or the Regional Director, as the case may be, it or he shall be liable for the`
  line `second or subsequent defaults for an amount equal to twice the amount of penalty provided for such`
  line `default under the relevant provisions of this Act.]`
obj_root_law_sections_455:
  sectionId (49350)
  sectionNo (455)
  orderNo 512
  title `Dormant company.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_455_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_455_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=49350&sectionno=455&orderno=512&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_455_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where a company is formed and registered under this Act for a future`
  line `project or to hold an asset or intellectual property and has no significant accounting transaction, such a`
  line `company or an inactive company may make an application to the Registrar in such manner as may be`
  line `prescribed for obtaining the status of a dormant company.`
  line
  line `Explanation.-- For the purposes of this section,--`
  line
  line `(i) "inactive company" means a company which has not been carrying on any business or`
  line `operation, or has not made any significant accounting transaction during the last two financial years,`
  line `or has not filed financial statements and annual returns during the last two financial years;`
  line
  line `(ii) "significant accounting transaction" means any transaction other than--`
  line
  line `(a) payment of fees by a company to the Registrar;`
  line
  line `(b) payments made by it to fulfil the requirements of this Act or any other law;`
  line
  line `(c) allotment of shares to fulfil the requirements of this Act; and`
  line
  line `(d) payments for maintenance of its office and records.`
  line
  line `(2) The Registrar on consideration of the application shall allow the status of a dormant company to`
  line `the applicant and issue a certificate in such form as may be prescribed to that effect.`
  line
  line `(3) The Registrar shall maintain a register of dormant companies in such form as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(4) In case of a company which has not filed financial statements or annual returns for two financial`
  line `years consecutively, the Registrar shall issue a notice to that company and enter the name of such`
  line `company in the register maintained for dormant companies.`
  line
  line `(5) A dormant company shall have such minimum number of directors, file such documents and pay`
  line `such annual fee as may be prescribed to the Registrar to retain its dormant status in the register and may`
  line `become an active company on an application made in this behalf accompanied by such documents and fee`
  line `as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(6) The Registrar shall strike off the name of a dormant company from the register of dormant`
  line `companies, which has failed to comply with the requirements of this section.`
obj_root_law_sections_455_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_456:
  sectionId (49351)
  sectionNo (456)
  orderNo 513
  title `Protection of action taken in good faith.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_456_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_456_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=49351&sectionno=456&orderno=513&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_456_content:
  string
  line `No suit, prosecution or other legal proceeding shall`
  line `lie against the Government or any officer of the Government or any other person in respect of anything`
  line `which is in good faith done or intended to be done in pursuance of this Act or of any rules or orders made`
  line `thereunder, or in respect of the publication by or under the authority of the Government or such officer, of`
  line `any report, paper or proceedings.`
obj_root_law_sections_456_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_457:
  sectionId (49352)
  sectionNo (457)
  orderNo 514
  title `Non-disclosure of information in certain cases.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_457_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_457_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=49352&sectionno=457&orderno=514&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_457_content:
  string
  line `Notwithstanding anything contained in any`
  line `other law for the time being in force, the Registrar, any officer of the Government or any other person`
  line `shall not be compelled to disclose to any court, Tribunal or other authority, the source from where he got`
  line `any information which--`
  line
  line `(a) has led the Central Government to order an investigation under section 210; or`
  line
  line `(b) is or has been material or relevant in connection with such investigation.`
obj_root_law_sections_457_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_458:
  sectionId (49353)
  sectionNo (458)
  orderNo 515
  title `Delegation by Central Government of its powers and functions.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_458_content
  footnotes `1. The proviso omitted by Act 1 of 2018, s. 93 (w.e.f. 9-2-2018).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=49353&sectionno=458&orderno=515&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_458_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central`
  line `Government may, by notification, and subject to such conditions, limitations and restrictions as may be`
  line `specified therein, delegate any of its powers or functions under this Act other than the power to make`
  line `rules to such authority or officer as may be specified in the notification:`
  line
  line `^1* * * * *`
  line
  line `(2) A copy of every notification issued under sub-section (1) shall, as soon as may be after it is`
  line `issued, be laid before each House of Parliament.`
obj_root_law_sections_459:
  sectionId (49354)
  sectionNo (459)
  orderNo 516
  title `Power of Central Government of Tribunal to accord approval, etc., subject to conditions and to prescribe fees on applications`
  content obj_root_law_sections_459_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_459_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=49354&sectionno=459&orderno=516&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_459_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where the Central Government or the Tribunal is required`
  line `or authorised by any provision of this Act--`
  line
  line `(a) to accord approval, sanction, consent, confirmation or recognition to, or in relation to, any`
  line `matter; or`
  line
  line `(b) to give any direction in relation to any matter; or`
  line
  line `(c) to grant any exemption in relation to any matter,`
  line
  line `then, the Central Government or the Tribunal may in the absence of anything to the contrary contained in`
  line `that provision or any other provision of this Act, accord, give or grant such approval, sanction, consent,`
  line `confirmation, recognition, direction or exemption, subject to such conditions, limitations or restrictions as`
  line `it may think fit to impose and may, in the case of a contravention of any such condition, limitation or`
  line `restriction, rescind or withdraw such approval, sanction, consent, confirmation, recognition, direction or`
  line exemption.
  line
  line `(2) Save as otherwise provided in this Act, every application which may be, or is required to be, made`
  line `to the Central Government or the Tribunal under any provision of this Act--`
  line
  line `(a) in respect of any approval, sanction, consent, confirmation or recognition to be accorded by`
  line `that Government or the Tribunal to, or in relation to, any matter; or`
  line
  line `(b) in respect of any direction or exemption to be given or granted by that Government or the`
  line `Tribunal in relation to any matter; or`
  line
  line `(c) in respect of any other matter,`
  line
  line `shall be accompanied by such fees as may be prescribed:`
  line
  line `Provided that different fees may be prescribed for applications in respect of different matters or in`
  line `case of applications by different classes of companies.`
obj_root_law_sections_459_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_460:
  sectionId (49355)
  sectionNo (460)
  orderNo 517
  title `Condonation of delay in certain cases`
  content obj_root_law_sections_460_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_460_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=49355&sectionno=460&orderno=517&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_460_content:
  string
  line `Notwithstanding anything contained in this Act,--`
  line
  line `(a) where any application required to be made to the Central Government under any provision of`
  line `this Act in respect of any matter is not made within the time specified therein, that Government may,`
  line `for reasons to be recorded in writing, condone the delay; and`
  line
  line `(b) where any document required to be filed with the Registrar under any provision of this Act is`
  line `not filed within the time specified therein, the Central Government may, for reasons to be recorded in`
  line `writing, condone the delay.`
obj_root_law_sections_460_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_461:
  sectionId (49356)
  sectionNo (461)
  orderNo 518
  title `Annual report by Central Government`
  content obj_root_law_sections_461_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_461_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=49356&sectionno=461&orderno=518&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_461_content:
  string
  line `The Central Government shall cause a general`
  line `annual report on the working and administration of this Act to be prepared and laid before each House of`
  line `Parliament within one year of the close of the year to which the report relates.`
obj_root_law_sections_461_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_462:
  sectionId (49357)
  sectionNo (462)
  orderNo 519
  title `Power to exempt class or classes of companies from provisions of this Act.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_462_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 21 of 2015, s. 23, for sub-section (2) (w.e.f. 29-5-2015).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=49357&sectionno=462&orderno=519&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_462_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central`
  line `Government may in the public interest, by notification direct that any of the provisions of this Act,`
  line
  line `(a) shall not apply to such class or classes of companies; or`
  line
  line `(b) shall apply to the class or classes of companies with such exceptions, modifications and`
  line `adaptations as may be specified in the notification.`
  line
  line `^1[(2) A copy of every notification proposed to be issued under sub-section (1), shall be laid in draft`
  line `before each House of Parliament, while it is in session, for a total period of thirty days, and if, both`
  line `Houses agree in disapproving the issue of notification or both Houses agree in making any modification`
  line `in the notification, the notification shall not be issued or, as the case may be, shall be issued only in such`
  line `modified form as may be agreed upon by both the Houses.`
  line
  line `(3) In reckoning any such period of thirty days as is referred to in sub-section (2), no account shall be`
  line `taken of any period during which the House referred to in sub-section (2) is prorogued or adjourned for`
  line `more than four consecutive days.`
  line
  line `(4) The copies of every notification issued under this section shall, as soon as may be after it has been`
  line `issued, be laid before each House of Parliament.]`
obj_root_law_sections_463:
  sectionId (49358)
  sectionNo (463)
  orderNo 520
  title `Power of court to grant relief in certain cases.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_463_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_463_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=49358&sectionno=463&orderno=520&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_463_content:
  string
  line `(1) If in any proceeding for negligence,`
  line `default, breach of duty, misfeasance or breach of trust against an officer of a company, it appears to the`
  line `court hearing the case that he is or may be liable in respect of the negligence, default, breach of duty,`
  line `misfeasance or breach of trust, but that he has acted honestly and reasonably, and that having regard to all`
  line `the circumstances of the case, including those connected with his appointment, he ought fairly to be`
  line `excused, the court may relieve him, either wholly or partly, from his liability on such term, as it may think`
  line `fit:`
  line
  line `Provided that in a criminal proceeding under this sub-section, the court shall have no power to grant`
  line `relief from any civil liability which may attach to an officer in respect of such negligence, default, breach`
  line `of duty, misfeasance or breach of trust.`
  line
  line `(2) Where any such officer has reason to apprehend that any proceeding will or might be brought`
  line `against him in respect of any negligence, default, breach of duty, misfeasance or breach of trust, he may`
  line `apply to the High Court for relief and the High Court on such application shall have the same power to`
  line `relieve him as it would have had if it had been a court before which a proceedings against that officer for`
  line `negligence, default, breach of duty, misfeasance or breach of trust had been brought under sub-section`
  line `(1).`
  line
  line `(3) No court shall grant any relief to any officer under sub-section (1) or sub-section (2) unless it has,`
  line `by notice served in the manner specified by it, required the Registrar and such other person, if any, as it`
  line `thinks necessary, to show cause why such relief should not be granted.`
obj_root_law_sections_463_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_464:
  sectionId (49359)
  sectionNo (464)
  orderNo 521
  title `Prohibition of association or partnership of persons exceeding certain number.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_464_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_464_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=49359&sectionno=464&orderno=521&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_464_content:
  string
  line `(1) No`
  line `association or partnership consisting of more than such number of persons as may be prescribed shall be`
  line `formed for the purpose of carrying on any business that has for its object the acquisition of gain by the`
  line `association or partnership or by the individual members thereof, unless it is registered as a company under`
  line `this Act or is formed under any other law for the time being in force:`
  line
  line `Provided that the number of persons which may be prescribed under this sub-section shall not exceed`
  line `one hundred.`
  line
  line `(2) Nothing in sub-section (1) shall apply to--`
  line
  line `(a) a Hindu undivided family carrying on any business; or`
  line
  line `(b) an association or partnership, if it is formed by professionals who are governed by special`
  line Acts.
  line
  line `(3) Every member of an association or partnership carrying on business in contravention of subsection`
  line `(1) shall be punishable with fine which may extend to one lakh rupees and shall also be personally`
  line `liable for all liabilities incurred in such business.`
obj_root_law_sections_464_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_465:
  sectionId (49360)
  sectionNo (465)
  orderNo 522
  title `Repeal of certain enactments and savings.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_465_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_465_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=49360&sectionno=465&orderno=522&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_465_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Companies Act, 1956 (1 of 1956) and`
  line `the Registration of Companies (Sikkim) Act, 1961 (Sikkim Act 8 of 1961) (hereafter in this section`
  line `referred to as the repealed enactments) shall stand repealed:`
  line
  line `Provided that the provisions of Part IX A of the Companies Act, 1956 (1 of 1956) shall be applicable`
  line `mutatis mutandis to a Producer Company in a manner as if the Companies Act, 1956 has not been`
  line `repealed until a special Act is enacted for Producer Companies:`
  line
  line `Provided further that until a date is notified by the Central Government under subsection (1) of`
  line `Section 434 for transfer of all matters, proceedings or cases to the Tribunal, the provisions of the`
  line `Companies Act, 1956 (1 of 1956) in regard to the jurisdiction, powers, authority and functions of the`
  line `Board of Company Law Administration and court shall continue to apply as if the Companies Act, 1956`
  line `has not been repealed:`
  line
  line `Provided also that provisions of the Companies Act, 1956 (1 of 1956) referred in the notification`
  line `issued under section 67 of the Limited Liability Partnership Act, 2008 (6 of 2009) shall, until the relevant`
  line `notification under such section applying relevant corresponding provisions of this Act to limited liability`
  line `partnerships is issued, continue to apply as if the Companies Act, 1956 has not been repealed.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding the repeal under sub-section (1) of the repealed enactments,--`
  line
  line `(a) anything done or any action taken or purported to have been done or taken, including any rule,`
  line `notification, inspection, order or notice made or issued or any appointment or declaration made or any`
  line `operation undertaken or any direction given or any proceeding taken or any penalty, punishment,`
  line `forfeiture or fine imposed under the repealed enactments shall, insofar as it is not inconsistent with`
  line `the provisions of this Act, be deemed to have been done or taken under the corresponding provisions`
  line `of this Act;`
  line
  line `(b) subject to the provisions of clause (a), any order, rule, notification, regulation, appointment,`
  line `conveyance, mortgage, deed, document or agreement made, fee directed, resolution passed, direction`
  line `given, proceeding taken, instrument executed or issued, or thing done under or in pursuance of any`
  line `repealed enactment shall, if in force at the commencement of this Act, continue to be in force, and`
  line `shall have effect as if made, directed, passed, given, taken, executed, issued or done under or in`
  line `pursuance of this Act;`
  line
  line `(c) any principle or rule of law, or established jurisdiction, form or course of pleading, practice or`
  line `procedure or existing usage, custom, privilege, restriction or exemption shall not be affected,`
  line `notwithstanding that the same respectively may have been in any manner affirmed or recognised or`
  line `derived by, in, or from, the repealed enactments;`
  line
  line `(d) any person appointed to any office under or by virtue of any repealed enactment shall be`
  line `deemed to have been appointed to that office under or by virtue of this Act;`
  line
  line `(e) any jurisdiction, custom, liability, right, title, privilege, restriction, exemption, usage, practice,`
  line `procedure or other matter or thing not in existence or in force shall not be revised or restored;`
  line
  line `(f) the offices existing on the commencement of this Act for the registration of companies shall`
  line `continue as if they have been established under the provisions of this Act;`
  line
  line `(g) the incorporation of companies registered under the repealed enactments shall continue to be`
  line `valid and the provisions of this Act shall apply to such companies as if they were registered under this`
  line Act;
  line
  line `(h) all registers and all funds constituted and established under the repealed enactments shall be`
  line `deemed to be registers and funds constituted or established under the corresponding provisions of this`
  line Act;
  line
  line `(i) any prosecution instituted under the repealed enactments and pending immediately before the`
  line `commencement of this Act before any Court shall, subject to the provisions of this Act, continue to be`
  line `heard and disposed of by the said Court;`
  line
  line `(j) any inspection, investigation or inquiry ordered to be done under the Companies Act, 1956 (1`
  line `of 1956) shall continue to be proceeded with as if such inspection, investigation or inquiry has been`
  line `ordered under the corresponding provisions of this Act; and`
  line
  line `(k) any matter filed with the Registrar, Regional Director or the Central Government under the`
  line `Companies Act, 1956 (1 of 1956) before the commencement of this Act and not fully addressed at`
  line `that time shall be concluded by the Registrar, Regional Director or the Central Government, as the`
  line `case may be, in terms of that Act, despite its repeal.`
  line
  line `(3) The mention of particular matters in sub-section (2) shall not be held to prejudice the general`
  line `application of section 6 of the General Clauses Act, 1897 (10 of 1897) with regard to the effect of repeal`
  line `of the repealed enactments as if the Registration of Companies (Sikkim) Act, 1961 (Sikkim Act 8 of`
  line `1961) were also a Central Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_465_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_466:
  sectionId (49361)
  sectionNo (466)
  orderNo 523
  title `Dissolution of Company Law Board and consequential provisions.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_466_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_466_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=49361&sectionno=466&orderno=523&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_466_content:
  string
  line `(1) Notwithstanding`
  line `anything contained in section 465, the Board of Company Law Administration constituted under the`
  line `Companies Act, 1956 (1 of 1956) (hereafter in this section referred to as the Company Law Board) shall`
  line `stand dissolved on the constitution of the Tribunal and the Appellate Tribunal:`
  line
  line `Provided that until the Tribunal and the Appellate Tribunal is constituted, the Chairman, ViceChairman`
  line `and Members of the Company Law Board immediately before the constitution of the Tribunal`
  line `and the Appellate Tribunal, who fulfil the qualifications and requirements provided under this Act`
  line `regarding appointment as President or Chairperson or Member of the Tribunal or the Appellate Tribunal,`
  line `shall function as President, Chairperson or Member of the Tribunal or the Appellate Tribunal:`
  line
  line `Provided further that every officer or other employee, who had been appointed on deputation basis to`
  line `the Company Law Board, shall, on such dissolution,--`
  line
  line `(i) become officer or employee of the Tribunal or the Appellate Tribunal, if he fulfils the`
  line `qualifications and requirements under this Act; and`
  line
  line `(ii) stand reverted to his parent cadre, Ministry or Department, in any other case:`
  line
  line `Provided also that every officer and the other employee of the Company Law Board, employed on`
  line `regular basis by that Board, shall become, on and from such dissolution the officer and other employee,`
  line `respectively, of the Tribunal or the Appellate Tribunal with the same rights and privileges as to pension,`
  line `gratuity and other like benefits as would have been admissible to him if he had continued to serve that`
  line `Board and shall continue to do so unless and until his employment in the Tribunal or the Appellate`
  line `Tribunal is duly terminated or until his remuneration, terms and conditions of employment are duly`
  line `altered by the Tribunal or the Appellate Tribunal, as the case may be:`
  line
  line `Provided also that notwithstanding anything contained in the Industrial Disputes Act, 1947 (14 of`
  line `1947) or in any other law for the time being in force, any officer or other employee who becomes an`
  line `officer or other employee of the Tribunal or the Appellate Tribunal under the preceding proviso shall not`
  line `be entitled to any compensation under this Act or under any other law for the time being in force and no`
  line `such claim shall be entertained by any court, tribunal or other authority:`
  line
  line `Provided also that where the Company Law Board has established a provident fund, superannuation`
  line `fund, welfare fund or other fund for the benefit of the officers and other employees employed in that`
  line `Board, the monies relatable to the officers and other employees who have become officers or employees`
  line `of the Tribunal or the Appellate Tribunal shall, out of the monies standing to the credit of such provident`
  line `fund, superannuation fund, welfare fund or other fund, stand transferred to, and vest in, the Tribunal or`
  line `the Appellate Tribunal, as the case may be, and such monies which stand so transferred shall be dealt with`
  line `by the Tribunal or the Appellate Tribunal in such manner as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(2) The persons holding the offices of Chairman, Vice-Chairman and Members, and officers and`
  line `other employees of the Company Law Board immediately before the constitution of the Tribunal and the`
  line `Appellate Tribunal who are not covered under proviso to sub-section (1) shall vacate their respective`
  line `offices on such constitution and no such Chairman, Vice-Chairman and Members and officers or other`
  line `employees shall be entitled to claim any compensation for the premature termination of the term of his`
  line `office or of any contract of service, if any.`
obj_root_law_sections_466_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_467:
  sectionId (49362)
  sectionNo (467)
  orderNo 524
  title `Power of Central Government to amend Schedules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_467_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_467_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=49362&sectionno=467&orderno=524&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_467_content:
  string
  line `(1) Subject to the provisions of this`
  line `section, the Central Government may, by notification, alter any of the regulations, rules, Tables, forms`
  line `and other provisions contained in any of the Schedules to this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) Any alteration notified under sub-section (1) shall have effect as if enacted in this Act and shall`
  line `come into force on the date of the notification, unless the notification otherwise directs:`
  line
  line `Provided that no such alteration in Table F of Schedule I shall apply to any company registered before`
  line `the date of such alteration.`
  line
  line `(3) Every alteration made by the Central Government under sub-section (1) shall be laid as soon as`
  line `may be after it is made before each House of Parliament while it is in session for a total period of thirty`
  line `days which may be comprised in one session or in two or more successive sessions, and if, before the`
  line `expiry of the session immediately following the session or the successive sessions aforesaid, both Houses`
  line `agree in making any modification in the alteration, or both Houses agree that the alteration should not be`
  line `made, the alteration shall thereafter have effect only in such modified form or be of no effect, as the case`
  line `may be; so, however, that any such modification or annulment shall be without prejudice to the validity of`
  line `anything previously done in pursuance of that alteration.`
obj_root_law_sections_467_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_468:
  sectionId (49363)
  sectionNo (468)
  orderNo 525
  title `Power of Central Government to make rules relating to winding up.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_468_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 31 of 2016, s. 255 and the Eleventh Schedule, for sub-section (2) (w.e.f. 15-11-2016).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=49363&sectionno=468&orderno=525&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_468_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central`
  line `Government shall, make rules consistent with the Code of Civil Procedure, 1908 (5 of 1908) providing`
  line `for all matters relating to the winding up of companies, which by this Act, are to be prescribed, and may`
  line `make rules providing for all such matters, as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `^1[(2) In particular, and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, such rules may`
  line `provide for all or any of the following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(i) as to the mode of proceedings to be held for winding up of a company by the Tribunal under`
  line `this Act;`
  line
  line `(ii) for the holding of meetings of creditors and members in connection with proceedings under`
  line `section 230;`
  line
  line `(iii) for giving effect to the provisions of this Act as to the reduction of the capital;`
  line
  line `(iv) generally for all applications to be made to the Tribunal under the provisions of this Act;`
  line
  line `(v) the holding and conducting of meetings to ascertain the wishes of creditors and contributories;`
  line
  line `(vi) the settling of lists of contributories and the rectifying of the register of members where`
  line `required, and collecting and applying the assets;`
  line
  line `(vii) the payment, delivery, conveyance, surrender or transfer of money, property, books or papers`
  line `to the liquidator;`
  line
  line `(viii) the making of calls; and`
  line
  line `(ix) the fixing of a time within which debts and claims shall be proved.]`
  line
  line `(3) All rules made by the Supreme Court on the matters referred to in this section as it stood`
  line `immediately before the commencement of this Act and in force at such commencement, shall continue to`
  line `be in force, till such time the rules are made by the Central Government and any reference to the High`
  line `Court in relation to winding up of a company in such rules shall be construed as a reference to the`
  line Tribunal.
obj_root_law_sections_469:
  sectionId (49364)
  sectionNo (469)
  orderNo 526
  title `Power of Central Government to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_469_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_469_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=49364&sectionno=469&orderno=526&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_469_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may, by`
  line `notification, make rules for carrying out the provisions of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) Without prejudice to the generality of the provisions of sub-section (1), the Central Government`
  line `may make rules for all or any of the matters which by this Act are required to be, or may be, prescribed or`
  line `in respect of which provision is to be or may be made by rules.`
  line
  line `(3) Any rule made under sub-section (1) may provide that a contravention thereof shall be punishable`
  line `with fine which may extend to five thousand rupees and where the contravention is a continuing one, with`
  line `a further fine which may extend to five hundred rupees for every day after the first during which such`
  line `contravention continues.`
  line
  line `(4) Every rule made under this section and every regulation made by Securities and Exchange Board`
  line `under this Act, shall be laid, as soon as may be after it is made, before each House of Parliament, while it`
  line `is in session, for a total period of thirty days which may be comprised in one session or in two or more`
  line `successive sessions, and if, before the expiry of the session immediately following the session or the`
  line `successive sessions aforesaid, both Houses agree in making any modification in the rule or regulation or`
  line `both Houses agree that the rule or regulation should not be made, the rule or regulation shall thereafter`
  line `have effect only in such modified form or be of no effect, as the case may be; so, however, that any such`
  line `modification or annulment shall be without prejudice to the validity of anything previously done under`
  line `that rule or regulation.`
obj_root_law_sections_469_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_470:
  sectionId (49365)
  sectionNo (470)
  orderNo 527
  title `Power to remove difficulties.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_470_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_470_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856&sectionId=49365&sectionno=470&orderno=527&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00008_201318_1517807327856
obj_root_law_sections_470_content:
  string
  line `(1) If any difficulty arises in giving effect to the provisions of`
  line `this Act, the Central Government may, by order published in the Official Gazette, make such provisions,`
  line `not inconsistent with the provisions of this Act, as appear to it to be necessary or expedient for removing`
  line `the difficulty:`
  line
  line `Provided that no such order shall be made after the expiry of a period of five years from the date of`
  line `commencement of section 1 of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) Every order made under this section shall, as soon as may be after it is made, be laid before each`
  line `House of Parliament.`
obj_root_law_sections_470_footnotes:
  string
  line
